window.ICML_PAPERS["68692"] = [{"id":"63376","en":"From Prompts to Responses: Dual-Sided Data Leakage and Defense in Split Large Language Models","ko":"프롬프트에서 응답까지: 분할 대규모 언어 모델에서 양방향 데이터 유출과 방어","authors":"Zixuan GU, Xiaojun Ye, Yang Liu","pos":"#2013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XgCyH9OZ5J","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly deployed in privacy-sensitive domains, where users must balance the risk of data exposure through external APIs against the high computational cost of local deployment. Split learning has therefore emerged as a promising paradigm for LLM fine-tuning and inference under limited local resources. However, it introduces new privacy risks. Prior work primarily studies leakage of private input prompts, typically via inversion attacks on intermediate representations, while the potential for sensitive information leakage through generative response outputs remains largely unexplored. In this work, we unveil novel vulnerabilities of Split-LLM by presenting<strong>P</strong>atched Model <strong>I</strong>nversion with <strong>D</strong>ual-Sided <strong>I</strong>nitialization(<strong>PIDI</strong>), a two-stage attack that simultaneously targets both private input prompts and output responses in Split-LLM settings. It combines dual-sided initialization with a patched inversion strategy to tackle long sequences, substantially outperforming prior inversion methods. To counter threats from both sides, we further propose the <strong>A</strong>dapter-based <strong>D</strong>ualGuard with <strong>M</strong>utual <strong>I</strong>nformation Defense(<strong>ADMI</strong>), which integrates an adapter-based local warmup strategy and mutual information regularization to provide a strong privacy guarantee with minimal impact on task performance. Extensive experiments across diverse tasks and models demonstrate that ADMI effectively defends against PIDI and other state-of-the-art inversion attacks. Our code is publicly available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DDRA/.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)는 점점 privacy-sensitive domain에 배치되고 있으며, 이때 사용자는 외부 API를 통한 데이터 노출 위험과 로컬 배포의 높은 연산 비용 사이에서 균형을 맞춰야 한다. 따라서 Split learning은 제한된 로컬 자원 하에서 LLM fine-tuning과 inference를 위한 유망한 패러다임으로 부상했다. 그러나 이는 새로운 privacy risk도 도입한다. 기존 연구는 주로 private input prompt의 leakage를 다루었고, 보통 intermediate representation에 대한 inversion attack을 통해 이를 분석했다. 반면 generative response output을 통한 sensitive information leakage 가능성은 대부분 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 Split-LLM의 새로운 취약점을 밝히기 위해, Split-LLM 설정에서 private input prompt와 output response를 동시에 대상으로 하는 two-stage attack인<strong>P</strong>atched Model <strong>I</strong>nversion with <strong>D</strong>ual-Sided <strong>I</strong>nitialization(<strong>PIDI</strong>)를 제시한다. 이 방법은 dual-sided initialization과 patched inversion strategy를 결합하여 긴 sequence를 다루며, 기존 inversion method를 크게 능가한다. 양쪽 위협에 모두 대응하기 위해, 우리는 또한 adapter-based local warmup strategy와 mutual information regularization을 통합하여 task performance에 미치는 영향은 최소화하면서 강력한 privacy guarantee를 제공하는 <strong>A</strong>dapter-based <strong>D</strong>ualGuard with <strong>M</strong>utual <strong>I</strong>nformation Defense(<strong>ADMI</strong>)를 제안한다. 다양한 task와 model에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 ADMI가 PIDI 및 다른 state-of-the-art inversion attack에 효과적으로 방어함을 보여준다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DDRA/ 에 공개되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"60591","en":"Step-Size Stability in Stochastic Optimization: A Theoretical Perspective","ko":"확률적 최적화에서 스텝 크기 안정성: 이론적 관점","authors":"Fabian Schaipp, Robert Gower, Adrien Taylor","pos":"#3600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yhvzMLgpdV","abs":"<p>We present a theoretical analysis of stochastic optimization methods in terms of their sensitivity with respect to the step size.     We identify a key quantity that, for each method, describes how the performance degrades as the step size becomes too large.     For convex problems, we show that this quantity directly impacts the suboptimality bound of the method.     Most importantly, our analysis provides direct <em>theoretical</em> evidence that adaptive step size methods, such as SPS or NGN, are more robust than SGD.     This allows us to quantify the advantage of these adaptive methods beyond empirical evaluation.     Finally, we show through experiments that our theoretical bound qualitatively mirrors the actual performance as a function of the step size, even for nonconvex problems.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 stochastic optimization method를 step size에 대한 민감도 측면에서 이론적으로 분석한다. 우리는 각 방법에 대해 step size가 너무 커질 때 성능이 어떻게 저하되는지를 설명하는 핵심 quantity를 식별한다. convex problem의 경우, 이 quantity가 해당 방법의 suboptimality bound에 직접적인 영향을 미침을 보인다. 가장 중요하게는, 우리의 분석이 SPS나 NGN과 같은 adaptive step size method가 SGD보다 더 robust하다는 직접적인 <em>이론적</em> 증거를 제공한다. 이를 통해 우리는 경험적 평가를 넘어 이러한 adaptive method의 이점을 정량화할 수 있다. 마지막으로, 실험을 통해 우리의 이론적 bound가 비convex problem에서도 step size의 함수로서 실제 성능을 정성적으로 잘 반영함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66637","en":"TokenRatio: Principled Token-Level Preference Optimization via Ratio Matching","ko":"TokenRatio: 비율 매칭을 통한 원칙적 토큰 수준 선호 최적화","authors":"Truong Nguyen, Tien-Phat Nguyen, Linh Van, Duy Nguyen, Khoa Doan, Trung Le","pos":"#4601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1twve5mNUU","abs":"<p>Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) is a widely used RL-free method for aligning language models from pairwise preferences, but it models preferences over full sequences even though generation is driven by per-token decisions. Existing token-level extensions typically decompose a sequence-level Bradley–Terry objective across timesteps, leaving per-prefix (state-wise) optimality implicit. We study how to recover <strong>token-level</strong> preference optimality using only standard sequence-level pairwise comparisons. We introduce <strong>Token-level Bregman Preference Optimization (TBPO)</strong>, which posits a token-level Bradley--Terry preference model over next-token actions conditioned on the prefix, and derive a Bregman-divergence density-ratio matching objective that generalizes the logistic/DPO loss while preserving the optimal policy induced by the token-level model and maintaining DPO-like simplicity. We introduce two instantiations: TBPO-Q, which explicitly learns a lightweight state baseline, and TBPO-A, which removes the baseline through advantage normalization. Across instruction following, helpfulness/harmlessness, and summarization, TBPO improves alignment quality and training stability and increases output diversity relative to strong sequence-level and token-level baselines.</p>"},{"id":"62501","en":"Generalization of Gibbs and Langevin Monte Carlo Algorithms in the Interpolation Regime","ko":"보간 영역에서의 Gibbs 및 Langevin Monte Carlo 알고리즘 일반화","authors":"Andreas Maurer, Erfan Mirzaei, Massimiliano Pontil","pos":"#4604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g2emeL0i3t","abs":"<p>This paper provides data-dependent bounds on the expected error of the Gibbs algorithm in the overparameterized interpolation regime, where low training errors are also obtained for impossible data, such as random labels in classification. The results show that generalization in the low-temperature regime is already signaled by small training errors in the more classical high temperature regime. The bounds are stable under approximation with Langevin Monte Carlo algorithms. The analysis motivates the design of an algorithm to compute bounds, which on the MNIST and CIFAR-10 datasets yield nontrivial, close predictions on the test error for true labeled data, while maintaining a correct upper bound on the test error for random labels.</p>","absKo":"<p>본 논문은 overparameterized interpolation regime에서 Gibbs algorithm의 expected error에 대한 data-dependent bound를 제시한다. 이 regime에서는 classification에서의 random label처럼 불가능한 data에 대해서도 낮은 training error가 얻어진다. 결과는 low-temperature regime의 generalization이 더 고전적인 high-temperature regime에서 이미 작은 training error로 신호된다는 점을 보여준다. 이러한 bound는 Langevin Monte Carlo algorithm으로 근사할 때도 안정적이다. 분석은 bound를 계산하는 algorithm 설계를 동기로 삼으며, MNIST와 CIFAR-10 dataset에서 true labeled data에 대한 test error를 비자명하고 근접하게 예측하는 동시에 random label에 대해서는 test error의 올바른 upper bound를 유지한다.</p>"},{"id":"65244","en":"Investigating Component Contributions in Multi-Agent ML Systems","ko":"멀티 에이전트 ML 시스템에서 구성 요소 기여도 조사","authors":"Junsung Kim, Ilia Mireskandari, Seungwan Son, Yifan Zhou, Khizer Shahid, Dylan Dai","pos":"#117","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FOfvTwBGUX","abs":"<p>Autonomous agents for machine learning engineering have advanced rapidly, yet comparing their effectiveness remains difficult. Existing systems combine different techniques---multi-agent decomposition, iterative refinement, memory management, and planning---in varying configurations, making it unclear which components actually drive performance. Complicating evaluation, existing benchmarks rely on historical competitions whose data likely contaminates LLM training corpora and whose static baselines reflect outdated human performance. To address this, we conduct over 4,000 controlled experiments systematically ablating architectural components, alongside K-live, a new benchmark of 25 active competitions that provides a contamination-free, dynamic evaluation environment. Our findings challenge common design assumptions: iterative feedback contributes more than architectural complexity, and multi-agent coordination can hurt as often as it helps. These results provide concrete guidance for practitioners building ML engineering agents.</p>","absKo":"<p>machine learning engineering을 위한 autonomous agent는 빠르게 발전해 왔지만, 그 효과를 비교하는 일은 여전히 어렵다. 기존 시스템은 multi-agent decomposition, iterative refinement, memory management, planning을 서로 다른 구성으로 결합하고 있어, 실제로 어떤 component가 성능을 견인하는지 불분명하다. 평가를 더 복잡하게 만드는 것은, 기존 benchmark가 LLM training corpus를 오염시켰을 가능성이 높은 과거 competition에 의존하며, 정적인 baseline은 이미 시대에 뒤처진 human performance를 반영한다는 점이다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 architectural component를 체계적으로 ablation한 4,000회 이상의 controlled experiment를 수행했고, 동시에 25개 active competition으로 구성된 새로운 benchmark인 K-live를 제안하여 contamination-free한 dynamic evaluation environment를 제공한다. 우리의 결과는 흔한 설계 가정에 도전한다. iterative feedback은 architectural complexity보다 더 큰 기여를 하며, multi-agent coordination은 도움을 주는 만큼 해가 되기도 한다. 이러한 결과는 ML engineering agent를 만드는 실무자에게 구체적인 지침을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"64183","en":"BuildArena: A Physics‑Aligned Interactive Benchmark of LLMs for Engineering Construction","ko":"BuildArena: 공학 건설을 위한 물리 정렬 인터랙티브 LLM 벤치마크","authors":"Tian Xia, Tianrun Gao, Wenhao Deng, Long Wei, Xiaowei Qian, Chenglei Yu, Tailin Wu","pos":"#118","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QAQKmIp3SZ","abs":"<p>Engineering construction automation aims to transform natural language specifications into physically viable structures, requiring complex integrated reasoning under strict physical constraints. While modern LLMs possess broad knowledge and strong reasoning capabilities that make them promising candidates for this domain, their construction competencies remain largely unevaluated. To address this gap, we introduce BuildArena, the first physics-aligned interactive benchmark designed for language-driven engineering construction. It takes a first step towards engineering automation using LLMs. Technically, it contributes to the community in two aspects: (1) an extendable task design strategy spanning static and dynamic mechanics across multiple difficulty tiers; (2) a 3D Spatial Geometric Computation Library for supporting construction based on language instructions. On nine frontier LLMs, BuildArena comprehensively evaluates their capabilities for language-driven and physics-grounded construction automation.</p>","absKo":"<p>공학 건설 자동화는 자연어 사양을 물리적으로 실현 가능한 구조물로 변환하는 것을 목표로 하며, 엄격한 물리 제약 하에서 복잡한 통합 추론을 요구한다. 현대 LLM은 폭넓은 지식과 강력한 추론 능력을 갖추고 있어 이 분야의 유망한 후보이지만, 건설 역량은 아직 대체로 평가되지 않았다. 이 공백을 메우기 위해, 우리는 언어 기반 공학 건설을 위해 물리적으로 정합된 상호작용형 benchmark인 BuildArena를 최초로 제안한다. 이는 LLM을 활용한 engineering automation의 첫걸음을 내딛는다. 기술적으로는 두 가지 측면에서 기여한다: (1) 여러 난이도 층위에 걸쳐 static 및 dynamic mechanics를 포괄하는 확장 가능한 task design strategy; (2) 언어 지시를 기반으로 한 건설을 지원하는 3D Spatial Geometric Computation Library. 9개의 frontier LLM을 대상으로 한 BuildArena는 언어 기반 및 물리 기반의 건설 자동화 역량을 종합적으로 평가한다.</p>"},{"id":"66328","en":"Omni-Perception Policy Optimization for Multimodal Emotion Reasoning","ko":"멀티모달 감정 추론을 위한 전지각 정책 최적화","authors":"Zhiyuan Han, Beier Zhu, Wenwen Tong, Pengyang Shao, Peipei Song, Xinyi Wang, Jiangnan Chen, Lewei Lu, Xun Yang","pos":"#1807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4dwe2wlxx5","abs":"<p>Recent Omni-MLLMs are driving a paradigm shift in multimodal emotion recognition from label-only prediction toward <em>Multimodal Emotion Reasoning</em> (MER), where models output both emotions and textual explanations grounded in visual, acoustic, and linguistic signals. However, we show that current emotion-oriented Omni-MLLMs still lack <em>reliable omni-modal perception</em>: they (i) underutilize multimodal cues in their reasoning trajectories and (ii) exhibit unfaithful behavior, often hallucinating modality-specific statements from other modalities. Building on these insights, we propose <strong>OPPO</strong> (<strong>O</strong>mni-<strong>P</strong>erception <strong>P</strong>olicy <strong>O</strong>ptimization), a reinforcement learning framework that explicitly optimizes multimodal perception. First, an Omni-Perception Reward decomposes ground-truth reasoning into fine-grained visual, acoustic, and emotion cues and rewards trajectories that semantically recover these cues. Second, an Omni-Perception Loss compares the policy under full and unimodally masked inputs, applying a KL penalty only to modality-specific evidence tokens to suppress cross-modal hallucination. We further introduce <em>MEP-Bench</em>, a diagnostic benchmark that quantifies <em>utilization</em> and <em>faithfulness</em>. Experiments show that OPPO achieves state-of-the-art performance on MER-UniBench and substantially improves utilization and faithfulness scores on MEP-Bench, highlighting the importance of sufficient and faithful omni perception for multimodal emotion reasoning. The code is provided in the Supplementary Materials.</p>"},{"id":"62124","en":"Grounding LLMs in Scientific Discovery via Embodied Actions","ko":"체화된 행동을 통한 과학적 발견에서의 LLM Grounding","authors":"Bo Zhang, Jinfeng Zhou, Yuxuan Chen, Jianing Yin, Minlie Huang, Hongning Wang","pos":"#1912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jeP0AARoA2","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have shown significant potential in scientific discovery but struggle to bridge the gap between theoretical reasoning and verifiable physical simulation. Existing solutions operate in a passive \"execute-then-response\" loop and thus lack runtime perception, obscuring agents to transient anomalies (e.g., numerical instability or diverging oscillations). To address this limitation, we propose EmbodiedAct, a framework that transforms established scientific software into active embodied agents by grounding LLMs in embodied actions with a tight perception-execution loop. We instantiate EmbodiedAct within MATLAB and evaluate it on complex engineering design and scientific modeling tasks. Extensive experiments show that EmbodiedAct significantly outperforms existing baselines, achieving SOTA performance by ensuring satisfactory reliability and stability in long-horizon simulations and enhanced accuracy in scientific modeling.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models(LLMs)은 과학적 발견에서 큰 잠재력을 보여 왔지만, 이론적 추론과 검증 가능한 물리 시뮬레이션 사이의 간극을 메우는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 기존 솔루션은 수동적인 \"execute-then-response\" 루프에서 동작하므로 runtime perception이 부족하고, 그 결과 에이전트가 일시적 이상 현상(예: numerical instability 또는 diverging oscillation)을 포착하지 못한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 EmbodiedAct를 제안한다. 이는 LLM을 embodied action에 grounding하고 촘촘한 perception-execution loop를 결합함으로써 기존의 과학 소프트웨어를 능동적인 embodied agent로 변환하는 프레임워크이다. 우리는 EmbodiedAct를 MATLAB 안에 구현하고, 복잡한 engineering design 및 scientific modeling task에서 이를 평가한다. 광범위한 실험 결과, EmbodiedAct가 장기 horizon 시뮬레이션에서 만족스러운 reliability와 stability를 보장하고 과학적 modeling에서 향상된 정확도를 달성함으로써 기존 baseline을 크게 능가하며 SOTA 성능을 달성함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65078","en":"Gecko: A Simulation Environment with Stateful Feedback for Refining Agent Tool Calls","ko":"Gecko: 에이전트 도구 호출을 정교화하기 위한 상태 기반 피드백 시뮬레이션 환경","authors":"Zeyu Zhang, Guohao Li, Zhenchang Xing, Alexandros Apostolopoulos, Yu Lin Lee, Liang Zheng","pos":"#2014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Gz0RAgBfid","abs":"The ability to use tools is fundamental for large language model (LLM) agents. Given a task, existing systems use LLMs to plan and generate tool calls, which are executed by real-world tools to complete the task. However, tool calls are prone to errors because they are derived merely from LLM intrinsic capabilities. What is more, while it is useful to let LLMs iteratively refine the tool-call sequence using execution results from real tools, this process can be expensive and lead to unsafe results. To improve LLM tool calls and address issues caused by using real tools for refinement, we introduce Gecko, a comprehensive environment that simulates tool responses using a combination of rules and LLMs. Specifically, Gecko checks the validity of tool calls including input arguments and tool names, synthesizes reasonable responses that adhere to the output schema, and assesses whether all task objectives have been achieved. These three types of feedback provided by Gecko allow LLMs to refine their tool calls, forming a simple yet effective test-time scaling method named GATS. On BFCLv3 and $\\tau^2$-bench, GATS consistently improves the tool calling performance of various LLMs including GPT-4o, GPT-5, and Gemini-3.0-pro. We further discuss working mechanisms of our method and share future possibilities.","absKo":"tool을 사용하는 능력은 large language model(LLM) agent의 근간이다. 주어진 task에 대해, 기존 시스템은 LLM을 사용해 계획을 세우고 tool call을 생성하며, 이 호출은 실제 tool에 의해 실행되어 task를 완료한다. 그러나 tool call은 LLM의 intrinsic capability에만 기반해 도출되기 때문에 오류가 발생하기 쉽다. 더 나아가, 실제 tool의 execution result를 사용해 LLM이 tool-call sequence를 반복적으로 정제하도록 하는 것은 유용하지만, 이 과정은 비용이 크고 unsafe result를 초래할 수 있다. LLM의 tool call을 개선하고, 정제를 위해 실제 tool을 사용하는 데서 발생하는 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 규칙과 LLM을 결합해 tool response를 시뮬레이션하는 포괄적인 환경인 Gecko를 도입한다. 구체적으로, Gecko는 input argument와 tool name을 포함한 tool call의 유효성을 검사하고, output schema를 따르는 합리적인 response를 합성하며, 모든 task objective가 달성되었는지 평가한다. Gecko가 제공하는 이 세 가지 종류의 feedback은 LLM이 tool call을 정제하도록 하며, GATS라는 단순하지만 효과적인 test-time scaling method를 형성한다. BFCLv3와 $\\tau^2$-bench에서 GATS는 GPT-4o, GPT-5, Gemini-3.0-pro를 포함한 다양한 LLM의 tool calling 성능을 일관되게 향상시킨다. 우리는 또한 방법의 작동 메커니즘을 추가로 논의하고 향후 가능성을 공유한다."},{"id":"64377","en":"$\\tau^2$-Bench: Evaluating Conversational Agents in a Dual-Control Environment","ko":"$\\tau^2$-Bench: 이중 제어 환경에서 대화형 에이전트 평가","authors":"Victor Barres, Honghua Dong, Soham Ray, Xujie Si, Karthik Narasimhan","pos":"#2207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OC2z7iSQKa","abs":"Existing benchmarks for conversational AI agents simulate *single-control* environments, where only the AI agent can use tools to interact with the world, while the user remains a passive information provider. This differs from real-world scenarios like technical support, where users need to actively participate in modifying the state of the (shared) world. In order to address this gap, we introduce $\\tau^2$-bench, with four key contributions:   1. A novel **Telecom dual-control domain** modeled as a Dec-POMDP, where both agent and user make use of tools to act in a shared, dynamic environment that tests both agent coordination and communication, 2. A **compositional task generator** that programmatically creates diverse, verifiable tasks from atomic components, ensuring domain coverage and controlled complexity, 3. A **reliable user simulator** tightly coupled with the environment, whose behavior is constrained by tools and observable states, improving simulation fidelity, 4. **fine-grained analysis of agent performance** through multiple ablations including separating errors arising from reasoning vs communication/coordination.  In particular, our experiments show significant performance drops when agents shift from no-user to dual-control, highlighting the challenges of guiding users. Overall, $\\tau^2$-bench provides a controlled testbed for agents that must both reason effectively and guide user actions.","absKo":"대화형 AI agent를 위한 기존 benchmark는 *single-control* 환경을 시뮬레이션하는데, 여기서는 AI agent만이 도구를 사용해 세계와 상호작용할 수 있고 사용자는 수동적인 정보 제공자에 머문다. 이는 사용자가 (공유된) 세계의 상태를 적극적으로 수정하는 데 참여해야 하는 기술 지원과 같은 실제 상황과 다르다. 이 격차를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 $\\tau^2$-bench를 제안하며, 다음 네 가지 핵심 기여를 포함한다. 1. agent와 user가 모두 도구를 사용해 공유된 동적 환경에서 행동하는 **Telecom dual-control domain**을 Dec-POMDP로 모델링한 새로운 설정으로, agent의 조정(coordination)과 communication을 모두 시험한다. 2. 원자적 구성요소로부터 다양한 검증 가능한 task를 프로그램적으로 생성하는 **compositional task generator**로, 도메인 커버리지와 제어된 복잡도를 보장한다. 3. 도구와 관측 가능한 상태에 의해 행동이 제약되는, 환경과 긴밀히 결합된 **reliable user simulator**로, 시뮬레이션 충실도를 향상시킨다. 4. 추론 대 communication/coordination에서 비롯되는 오류를 분리하는 등 여러 ablation을 포함한 **fine-grained analysis of agent performance**이다. 특히, 실험 결과는 agent가 no-user 설정에서 dual-control로 전환할 때 성능이 크게 하락함을 보여주며, 사용자를 안내하는 어려움을 부각한다. 전반적으로, $\\tau^2$-bench는 효과적으로 추론하면서 동시에 user의 행동을 안내해야 하는 agent를 위한 통제된 testbed를 제공한다."},{"id":"67072","en":"Position: Quantum Program Generation Must Prioritize Validity Over Probabilistic Scaling","ko":"Position: Quantum Program 생성은 확률적 확장보다 유효성을 우선해야 한다","authors":"Junhao Song, Yu Zhou, William J. Knottenbelt, Yudong Cao","pos":"#2312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oX1vWuQ13y","abs":"<p>The scaling hypothesis assumes that increasing model parameters yields emergent reasoning capabilities. This position paper argues that applying this probabilistic paradigm to generic quantum circuit synthesis is a category error. Unlike natural languages, quantum circuits require strict adherence to mathematical constraints, such as unitarity. Training on unverified code constitutes data poisoning. Models learn syntax but fail to capture the physical semantics of Hilbert space. Since the valid subset of circuit designs decays exponentially with the number of qubits, post-hoc filtering is mathematically intractable. We propose a pivot from human-centric copilots to verifier-centric agents. We integrate hierarchical constraints, topological masks, and symbolic proxies directly into generation. Our analysis suggests that scale alone cannot bridge the validity gap. Verification-aware architectures offer a viable path for modular quantum program generation. The community must stop simulating the physicist and instead satisfy the physical rules.</p>"},{"id":"62576","en":"Order Matters: Unveiling the Hidden Impact of Macro Placement Sequences via Proxy-Guided LLM Evolution","ko":"순서가 중요하다: Proxy-Guided LLM Evolution으로 Macro Placement Sequence의 숨은 영향 분석","authors":"Shibing Mo, Jing Liu, Jianchu Xu, Ruilin Wu","pos":"#2613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fPjkFDW9j7","abs":"<p>Macro placement is a fundamental step in modern VLSI physical design, determining the solution quality of high-dimensional combinatorial optimization problems. Despite recent advancements in machine learning for spatial coordinate determination, the temporal dimension of placement sequencing remains largely governed by static heuristics. In this work, we demonstrate that the placement sequence is not merely a preprocessing step but a decisive factor in optimization, where suboptimal early decisions trigger irreversible domino effects that constrain the solution space. To harness this unexplored dimension, we propose \\textbf{OrderPlace}, a novel framework that automates the discovery of macro placement strategies via proxy-guided Large Language Model (LLM) evolution. Unlike existing methods that rely on manual rules like area or connectivity, OrderPlace leverages LLMs to evolve generalizable, code-level ordering strategies—ranging from static metrics to dynamic, physics-inspired mechanisms. To mitigate the prohibitive cost of evaluating sequences, we introduce a lightweight proxy evaluation mechanism that efficiently filters candidates using a deterministic greedy probe. Experimental results on the standard ISPD 2005 benchmarks demonstrate that OrderPlace discovers novel ordering strategies. Compared with WireMask-EA and the state-of-the-art method EGPlace, OrderPlace reduces wirelength by 34.04% and 14.08%, respectively.</p>","absKo":"<p>Macro placement은 현대 VLSI physical design에서의 근본적인 단계로, 고차원 조합 최적화 문제의 해 품질을 결정한다. 최근 spatial coordinate 결정을 위한 machine learning의 발전에도 불구하고, placement sequencing의 시간적 차원은 여전히 정적인 heuristic에 크게 의존하고 있다. 본 연구에서는 placement sequence가 단순한 preprocessing step이 아니라 최적화에서 결정적인 요인임을 보인다. 즉, 초기의 suboptimal decision은 되돌릴 수 없는 domino effect를 유발하여 solution space를 제약한다. 이 미지의 차원을 활용하기 위해, 우리는 proxy-guided Large Language Model (LLM) evolution을 통해 macro placement strategy의 발견을 자동화하는 새로운 framework인 \\textbf{OrderPlace}를 제안한다. area나 connectivity와 같은 manual rule에 의존하는 기존 방법과 달리, OrderPlace는 LLM을 활용해 static metric부터 dynamic하고 physics-inspired한 mechanism에 이르기까지 일반화 가능한 code-level ordering strategy를 진화시킨다. sequence 평가에 드는 높은 비용을 완화하기 위해, 우리는 deterministic greedy probe를 사용하여 candidate를 효율적으로 걸러내는 lightweight proxy evaluation mechanism을 도입한다. 표준 ISPD 2005 benchmark에서의 실험 결과, OrderPlace가 새로운 ordering strategy를 발견함을 보여준다. WireMask-EA 및 state-of-the-art 방법 EGPlace와 비교했을 때, OrderPlace는 wirelength를 각각 34.04%와 14.08% 줄인다.</p>"},{"id":"62069","en":"CMI-RewardBench: Evaluating Music Reward Models with Compositional Multimodal Instruction","ko":"CMI-RewardBench: Compositional Multimodal Instruction 기반 음악 Reward Model 평가","authors":"Yinghao Ma, Haiwen Xia, Hewei Gao, Weixiong Chen, Ye Yuxin, Yuchen Yang, Sungkyun Chang, Mingshuo Ding, Yizhi Li, Ruibin Yuan, Simon Dixon, Emmanouil Benetos","pos":"#2702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=k9DhP16RZt","abs":"<p>While music generation models have evolved to handle complex multimodal inputs mixing text, lyrics, and reference audio, evaluation mechanisms have lagged behind, remaining fragmented and narrowly focused. In this paper, we bridge this critical gap by establishing a comprehensive ecosystem for Compositional Music Instruction (CMI) reward modeling, where the generated music may be conditioned on text descriptions, lyrics, and/or audio prompts. We first introduce CMIPref-Pseudo, a large-scale preference dataset comprising 110k pseudo-labeled samples, and CMI-Pref, a high-quality, human-annotated corpus tailored for fine-grained alignment tasks. To unify the evaluation landscape, we propose CMIRewardBench, a unified benchmark that evaluates music reward models on heterogeneous samples across musicality, text–music alignment, and compositional instruction alignment. Leveraging these resources, we develop CMI reward models (CMI-RMs), a parameter-efficient reward model family capable of processing heterogeneous inputs. We evaluate their correlation with human judgments scores on Music Arena and CMI-Pref test set, as well as preference agreement on Music Arena and CMI-Pref. Additional analyses examine performance variation across factors such as annotators, annotation timing and confidence, music generation models, and audio length. Experiments demonstrate that CMI-RM not only correlates strongly with human judgments, but also enables effective inference-time scaling via topk filtering. Our work provides the necessary data, benchmarks, and models to advance aligned music generation.</p>","absKo":"<p>음악 생성 모델은 text, lyrics, reference audio를 혼합한 복잡한 multimodal input을 다룰 수 있을 정도로 발전했지만, 평가 메커니즘은 이에 뒤처져 파편화되고 지나치게 좁은 범위에 머물러 있다. 본 논문에서는 generated music이 text description, lyrics, 및/또는 audio prompt를 조건으로 할 수 있는 Compositional Music Instruction (CMI) reward modeling을 위한 포괄적인 ecosystem을 구축함으로써 이 중요한 간극을 메운다. 먼저, 11만 개의 pseudo-labeled sample로 이루어진 대규모 preference dataset인 CMIPref-Pseudo와, 세밀한 alignment task에 맞춘 고품질 human-annotated corpus인 CMI-Pref를 소개한다. 평가 환경을 통합하기 위해, musicality, text–music alignment, compositional instruction alignment 전반의 heterogeneous sample에서 music reward model을 평가하는 통합 benchmark인 CMIRewardBench를 제안한다. 이러한 자원을 활용하여, heterogeneous input을 처리할 수 있는 parameter-efficient reward model family인 CMI reward model(CMI-RM)을 개발한다. 우리는 Music Arena와 CMI-Pref test set에서 human judgment score와의 상관관계를 평가하고, Music Arena와 CMI-Pref에서의 preference agreement도 함께 평가한다. 추가 분석에서는 annotator, annotation timing과 confidence, music generation model, audio length와 같은 요인에 따른 성능 변동을 검토한다. 실험 결과, CMI-RM은 human judgment와 강하게 상관될 뿐만 아니라 topk filtering을 통한 inference-time scaling도 효과적으로 가능하게 함을 보여준다. 우리의 연구는 aligned music generation을 발전시키는 데 필요한 data, benchmark, model을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60747","en":"Co-RedTeam: Orchestrated Security Discovery and Exploitation with LLM Agents","ko":"Co-RedTeam: LLM Agent를 활용한 조율된 보안 발견 및 Exploitation","authors":"Pengfei He, Ash Fox, Lesly Miculicich, Stefan Friedli, Daniel Fabian, Burak Gokturk, Jiliang Tang, Chen-Yu Lee, Tomas Pfister, Long T. Le","pos":"#2908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wz57SLSTk3","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) have shown promise in assisting cybersecurity tasks, yet existing approaches struggle with automatic vulnerability discovery and exploitation due to limited interaction, weak execution grounding, and a lack of experience reuse. We propose Co-RedTeam, a security-aware multi-agent framework designed to mirror real-world red-teaming workflows by integrating security-domain knowledge, code-aware analysis, execution-grounded iterative reasoning, and long-term memory. Co-RedTeam decomposes vulnerability analysis into coordinated discovery and exploitation stages, enabling agents to plan, execute, validate, and refine actions based on real execution feedback while learning from prior trajectories. Extensive evaluations on challenging security benchmarks demonstrate that Co-RedTeam consistently outperforms strong baselines across diverse backbone models, achieving over 60\\% success rate in vulnerability exploitation and over 10\\% absolute improvement in vulnerability detection. Ablation and iteration studies further confirm the critical role of execution feedback, structured interaction, and memory for building robust and generalizable cybersecurity agents.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM)은 cybersecurity 작업을 보조하는 데 유망함을 보여 왔지만, 기존 접근법은 제한된 상호작용, 약한 execution grounding, 그리고 경험 재사용의 부재로 인해 자동 취약점 발견과 exploit에 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 보안 도메인 지식, code-aware analysis, execution-grounded iterative reasoning, 그리고 long-term memory를 통합하여 실제 red-teaming workflow를 모사하도록 설계된 security-aware multi-agent framework인 Co-RedTeam을 제안한다. Co-RedTeam은 취약점 분석을 coordinated discovery와 exploitation 단계로 분해하여, agent가 이전 trajectory로부터 학습하면서 실제 execution feedback에 기반해 행동을 계획, 실행, 검증, 개선할 수 있게 한다. 어려운 security benchmark에 대한 광범위한 평가는, Co-RedTeam이 다양한 backbone model 전반에서 강력한 baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, vulnerability exploitation에서 60\\% 이상의 성공률과 vulnerability detection에서 10\\% 이상의 절대적 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. Ablation 및 iteration 연구는 또한 robust하고 generalizable한 cybersecurity agent를 구축하는 데 있어 execution feedback, structured interaction, 그리고 memory의 핵심적 역할을 추가로 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"66275","en":"AdvEvo-MARL: Shaping Internalized Safety through Adversarial Co-Evolution in Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning","ko":"AdvEvo-MARL: 다중 에이전트 강화 학습에서 적대적 공진화를 통한 내재화된 안전성 형성","authors":"Zhenyu Pan, Yiting Zhang, Zhuo Liu, Yolo Tang, Zeliang Zhang, Haozheng Luo, Chenwei Xu, Yuwei Han, Jianshu Zhang, Dennis Wu, Hong-Yu Chen, Haoran Lu, Haoyang Fang, Manling Li, Chenliang Xu, Philip Yu, Han Liu","pos":"#3001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5D3ZblXmW2","abs":"<p>LLM-based multi-agent systems excel at planning, tool use, and role coordination, but their openness and interaction complexity also expose them to jailbreak and adversarial collaboration. Existing defenses fall into two lines: (i) self-verification that asks each agent to pre-filter unsafe instructions before execution, and (ii) external guard modules that police behaviors. The former often underperforms because a standalone agent lacks sufficient capacity to detect cross-agent unsafe chains and delegation-induced risks; the latter increases system overhead and creates a single-point-of-failure—once compromised, system-wide safety collapses, and adding more guards worsens cost and complexity. To solve these challenges, we propose AdvEvo-MARL, a co-evolutionary multi-agent reinforcement learning framework that internalizes safety into task agents. Rather than relying on external guards, AdvEvo-MARL jointly optimizes attackers (which synthesize evolving jailbreak prompts) and defenders (task agents trained to both accomplish their duties and resist attacks) in adversarial learning environments. To stabilize learning and foster cooperation, we introduce a public baseline for advantage estimation: agents within the same functional group share a group-level mean-return baseline, enabling lower-variance updates and stronger intra-group coordination. Across representative attack scenarios, AdvEvo-MARL consistently keeps attack-success rate (ASR) below 20\\%, whereas baselines reach up to 38.33\\%, while preserving or even improving task accuracy (up to +3.67\\%). These results show that safety and utility can be jointly improved without relying on extra guard agents or added system overhead.</p>"},{"id":"64663","en":"Opt-Verifier: Unleashing the Power of LLMs for Optimization Modeling via Dual-Side Verification","ko":"Opt-Verifier: Dual-Side Verification을 통한 최적화 모델링을 위한 LLM의 잠재력 실현","authors":"Haoyang Liu, Jie Wang, Boxuan Niu, Xiongwei Han, Yian Xu, Mingxuan Ye, Zijie Geng, Fangzhou Zhu, Tao Zhong, Mingxuan Yuan, Jianye Hao","pos":"#3509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=L7NsVVUm9H","abs":"<p>Building mathematical optimization models is critical in operations research (OR), while it requires substantial human expertise. Recent advancements have utilized large language models (LLMs) to automate this modeling process. However, existing works often struggle to verify the correctness of the generated optimization models, without checking the rationality of the constraints and variables or the validity of solutions to the generated models. This hampers the subsequent verification and correction steps, and thus it severely hurts the modeling accuracy. To address this challenge, we propose a novel LLM-based framework with Dual-side Verification (OptiVer) from both structure and solution perspectives, thereby improving the modeling accuracy. The structure-side verification ensures that the modeling structure of the generated optimization models aligns with the original problem description, accurately capturing the problem's constraints and requirements. Meanwhile, the solution-side verification interprets and evaluates the validity of the solutions, confirming that the optimization models are logically and mathematically sound. Extensive experiments on several popular benchmarks demonstrate that our approach significantly outperforms the state-of-the-art, achieving over 20\\% improvement in accuracy.</p>","absKo":"<p>수학적 optimization model을 구성하는 일은 operations research (OR)에서 매우 중요하지만, 상당한 인간 전문성이 요구된다. 최근의 발전은 이 modeling process를 자동화하기 위해 large language models (LLMs)를 활용해 왔다. 그러나 기존 연구는 생성된 optimization model의 정확성을 검증하는 데 종종 어려움을 겪으며, constraint와 variable의 합리성이나 생성된 model에 대한 solution의 타당성을 점검하지 않는다. 이는 이후의 검증 및 수정 단계를 저해하고, 결과적으로 modeling accuracy를 심각하게 떨어뜨린다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 구조와 solution 관점 모두에서 Dual-side Verification을 수행하는 새로운 LLM-based framework인 OptiVer를 제안하여 modeling accuracy를 향상시킨다. structure-side verification은 생성된 optimization model의 modeling structure가 원래 문제 설명과 일치하는지 확인하고, 문제의 constraint와 requirement를 정확히 포착한다. 한편 solution-side verification은 solution의 타당성을 해석하고 평가하여 optimization model이 논리적이고 수학적으로 타당함을 검증한다. 여러 널리 사용되는 benchmark에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근이 state-of-the-art를 크게 능가하며, accuracy를 20\\% 이상 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66433","en":"On Effectiveness and Efficiency of Agentic Tool-calling and RL Training","ko":"에이전트형 도구 호출과 RL 훈련의 효과성 및 효율성에 관하여","authors":"Tong Liu, Cheng Qian, Matej Cief, Yuan He, Daniele Dan, Nikolaos Aletras, Gabriella Kazai","pos":"#3602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3oMO1ZQNwT","abs":"<p>Tool-calling is a central component of modern large language model (LLM) agents, equipping them with skills beyond their parametric knowledge. This paper studies tool-calling along two complementary axes: \\textbf{effectiveness}, i.e., how this capability is \\textit{measured}, and \\textbf{efficiency}, i.e., how it is \\textit{learned}. On effectiveness, we systematically analyze tool-calling evaluation pipelines and show that results can be highly sensitive to seemingly minor, often undocumented implementation choices including the random seed, system prompt, multi-turn template construction, and how prior interaction/reasoning history is carried forward.  These choices can lead to substantial differences in reported performance, especially in multi-turn settings where without rigorous standardization, leaderboard rankings are unreliable.  On efficiency, we examine standard reinforcement learning (RL) for tool-calling and identify two sources of computational waste: (i) during rollouts, many prompts produce no learning signal, and (ii) during policy updates, optimization incurs high computational cost. Guided by these findings, we introduce two techniques that accelerate RL-based tool-calling training, achieving substantial wall-clock speedup without degrading performance.</p>"},{"id":"67215","en":"Position: AGI Requires a Coordination Layer on Top of Pattern Repositories","ko":"Position: AGI에는 패턴 저장소 위에 조정 계층이 필요하다","authors":"Edward Chang","pos":"#4400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=B12xAFr2Cq","abs":"<p>This <strong>position paper</strong> argues that influential critiques dismissing Large Language Models (LLMs) as a dead end for AGI misidentify the bottleneck: they confuse the ocean with the net. Pattern repositories are the necessary System-1 substrate; the missing component is a System-2 coordination layer that selects, constrains, and binds these patterns. We formalize this layer via an anchoring theory that models reasoning as a phase transition governed by effective support (rho<em>d), representational mismatch (d</em>r), and an adaptive anchoring budget (gamma log k). We translate theory into architecture with a multi-agent coordination stack. Moving beyond the hype of unstructured swarms, this layer provides a principled integration of diversity and control via baiting (PID-modulated debate), filtering (trace-output verification), and persistence (transactional memory). Empirical validation on causal judgment and the sycophancy-paranoia trade-off demonstrates that static prompting fails where adaptive control succeeds, confirming that failures attributed to substrate limitations are often resolved by regulated coordination. By reframing common objections as testable coordination failures, we argue that the path to AGI runs through LLMs, not around them.</p>"},{"id":"61689","en":"CodeTaste: Can LLMs Generate Human-Level Code Refactorings?","ko":"CodeTaste: LLM은 인간 수준의 코드 Refactoring을 생성할 수 있는가?","authors":"Alex Thillen, Niels Mündler, Veselin Raychev, Martin Vechev","pos":"#4410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nj1oXU2tln","abs":"<p>Large language model (LLM)-based coding agents can generate working code, but their solutions often introduce complexity, duplication, and architectural debt. Human developers address such issues through refactoring: behavior-preserving program transformations that improve structure and maintainability. In this paper, we investigate if LLM agents (i) can execute refactorings reliably and (ii) identify refactorings that human developers chose in real codebases. We present CodeTaste, a benchmark of refactoring tasks mined from large-scale multi-file changes in open-source repositories. To score solutions, we combine repository test suites with custom static checks that verify removal of undesired code patterns and introduction of desired patterns using dataflow reasoning.  Our experimental results indicate a clear gap across frontier models: agents perform well when refactorings are specified in detail, but often fail to discover the human refactoring choices when only presented with a focus area for improvement. A propose-then-implement decomposition improves alignment, and selecting the best-aligned proposal before implementation yields further gains. CodeTaste provides an evaluation target and a potential preference signal for aligning coding agents with human refactoring decisions in realistic codebases.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model (LLM) 기반 coding agent는 동작하는 코드를 생성할 수 있지만, 그 해결책은 종종 복잡성, 중복, 그리고 architectural debt를 초래한다. 인간 개발자는 refactoring, 즉 구조와 유지보수성을 개선하면서 behavior를 보존하는 program transformation을 통해 이러한 문제를 해결한다. 본 논문에서는 LLM agent가 (i) refactoring을 안정적으로 수행할 수 있는지, 그리고 (ii) 인간 개발자가 실제 codebase에서 선택한 refactoring을 식별할 수 있는지를 조사한다. 우리는 오픈소스 repository의 대규모 multi-file change에서 추출한 refactoring task들의 benchmark인 CodeTaste를 제시한다. 해법 채점에는 repository test suite와 custom static check를 결합하여, dataflow reasoning을 사용해 바람직하지 않은 code pattern의 제거와 바람직한 pattern의 도입을 검증한다. 우리의 실험 결과는 frontier model 전반에 걸쳐 뚜렷한 격차가 있음을 보여준다. 즉, refactoring이 상세히 명시되면 agent는 잘 수행하지만, 개선할 focus area만 제시되었을 때는 인간의 refactoring 선택을 발견하는 데 자주 실패한다. propose-then-implement 분해는 alignment를 개선하며, 구현 전에 가장 잘 정렬된 proposal을 선택하면 추가적인 성능 향상이 나타난다. CodeTaste는 실제 codebase에서 coding agent를 인간의 refactoring 결정과 정렬시키기 위한 평가 대상이자 잠재적인 preference signal을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66427","en":"SL-VC: A Benchmark and Automated Framework for Separation Logic Verification Condition Proving","ko":"SL-VC: Separation Logic 검증 조건 증명을 위한 벤치마크 및 자동화 프레임워크","authors":"Hanyang Wang, Xiwei Wu, Qinxiang Cao","pos":"#801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3rvOJyHibr","abs":"<p>Formal verification of system software with complex heap manipulations remains challenging. Standard automated solvers frequently fail to discharge separation logic verification conditions even when correct specifications like loop invariants are provided, forcing verification engineers to manually construct proofs. While large language models (LLMs) have shown promise in proof synthesis, specialized approaches for separation logic remain unexplored. To bridge this gap, we introduce SL-VC (Separation Logic Verification Conditions), a benchmark of 208 verification conditions derived from real-world C programs, including data structures and algorithms, the LiteOS kernel's linked list library, and the mini-gmp library. Our evaluation reveals that general-purpose LLMs and existing LLM-based Rocq provers struggle to effectively discharge these verification conditions. To address this challenge, we propose SPLIT (Split spatial and pure Proving with LLM-frIendly Tactics), a novel framework that enables predictable proof state transitions through an LLM-friendly tactic library, combined with a two-stage workflow that separates spatial and pure reasoning to align with separation logic semantics. Experimental results on SL-VC demonstrate that SPLIT consistently outperforms existing approaches, showing that LLM-assisted proof synthesis is a promising solution for separation logic verification of real-world system software.</p>"},{"id":"63870","en":"SonicMaster: Towards Controllable All-in-One Music Restoration and Mastering","ko":"SonicMaster: 제어 가능한 올인원 음악 복원 및 마스터링을 향하여","authors":"Jan Melechovsky, Ambuj Mehrish, Abhinaba Roy, Dorien Herremans","pos":"#802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=T0HjpdCPxU","abs":"<p>Music recordings often suffer from audio quality issues such as excessive reverberation, distortion, clipping, tonal imbalances, and a narrowed stereo image, especially when created in non-professional settings without specialized equipment or expertise. These problems are typically corrected using separate specialized tools and manual adjustments. In this paper, we introduce SonicMaster, the first unified generative model for music restoration and mastering that addresses a broad spectrum of audio artifacts with text-based control. SonicMaster is conditioned on natural language instructions to apply targeted enhancements, or can operate in an automatic mode for general restoration. To train this model, we construct the SonicMaster dataset, a large dataset of paired degraded and high-quality tracks by simulating common degradation types with nineteen degradation functions belonging to five enhancements groups: equalization, dynamics, reverb, amplitude, and stereo. Our approach leverages a flow-matching generative training paradigm to learn an audio transformation that maps degraded inputs to their cleaned, mastered versions guided by text prompts. Objective audio quality metrics demonstrate that SonicMaster significantly improves sound quality across all artifact categories. Furthermore, subjective listening tests confirm that listeners prefer SonicMaster’s enhanced outputs over other baselines. Demo samples are available through https://msonic793.github.io/SonicMaster/</p>","absKo":"<p>음악 녹음은 특히 전문 장비나 숙련된 지식 없이 제작된 경우, 과도한 reverberation, distortion, clipping, tonal imbalance, 좁아진 stereo image와 같은 audio quality 문제를 자주 겪는다. 이러한 문제는 보통 별도의 전문 도구와 수동 조정을 통해 수정한다. 본 논문에서는 text-based control을 통해 폭넓은 audio artifact를 다루는, 음악 restoration과 mastering을 위한 최초의 통합 generative model인 SonicMaster를 소개한다. SonicMaster는 자연어 지시를 조건으로 하여 표적화된 개선을 적용하거나, 일반적인 restoration을 위한 automatic mode로 동작할 수 있다. 이 model을 학습시키기 위해, 우리는 equalization, dynamics, reverb, amplitude, stereo의 다섯 enhancement group에 속하는 열아홉 개의 degradation function을 사용해 일반적인 열화 유형을 모사함으로써, degraded track와 high-quality track이 짝지어진 대규모 SonicMaster dataset을 구축했다. 우리의 접근법은 flow-matching generative training paradigm을 활용하여, text prompt의 guidance를 받아 degraded input을 정제되고 mastering된 버전으로 변환하는 audio transformation을 학습한다. 객관적 audio quality metric은 SonicMaster가 모든 artifact 범주에서 sound quality를 유의미하게 향상시킴을 보여 준다. 또한 주관적 listening test는 청취자들이 다른 baseline보다 SonicMaster의 향상된 출력물을 선호함을 확인한다. demo sample은 https://msonic793.github.io/SonicMaster/ 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"63779","en":"Improving ML attacks on LWE with data repetition and stepwise regression","ko":"데이터 반복과 단계적 회귀를 활용한 LWE에 대한 ML 공격 개선","authors":"Alberto Alfarano, Eshika Saxena, Emily Wenger, Francois Charton, Kristin Lauter","pos":"#905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Tq5dFAGeBL","abs":"ML attacks on Learning with Errors (LWE) with binary or small secrets only succeed on LWE settings with very simple secrets. For example, they can recover secrets with up to three non-zero bits when models are trained on not-reduced LWE data, and three non-zero bits in the ''cruel region'' [9] when BKZ pre-processing is applied. We show that larger training sets and the use of repeated examples in the training data allow the recovery of denser secrets. We empirically observe a power-law relationship between model based attempts to recover the secrets, dataset size and repeated examples. We introduce a stepwise regression technique to recover the ``cool bits'' of the secret. Overall, these techniques allow for the recovery of denser binary secrets: up to Hamming weight $70$ (and $8$ cruel bits) for dimension $256$ $\\log_2 q=20$ and $75$ (and $7$ cruel bits) for dimension $512$ $\\log_2 q=41$ (vs $33$ and $63$ Hamming weight and $3$ cruel bits in previous works). We also demonstrate our methods' effectiveness on denser ternary secrets, showing a substantial improvement over prior work.","absKo":"이진 또는 작은 secret을 사용하는 Learning with Errors(LWE)에 대한 ML attack은 매우 단순한 secret을 가진 LWE setting에서만 성공한다. 예를 들어, 모델이 비축소(reduced되지 않은) LWE data로 학습될 때 최대 세 개의 non-zero bit를 가진 secret을 복원할 수 있으며, BKZ pre-processing이 적용된 경우에는 \"cruel region\" [9]에서 세 개의 non-zero bit를 복원할 수 있다. 우리는 더 큰 training set과 training data 내 반복 예제의 사용이 더 밀집된 secret의 복원을 가능하게 함을 보인다. 우리는 모델 기반 secret 복원 시도, dataset 크기, 반복 예제 사이에 power-law 관계가 있음을 실증적으로 관찰한다. 우리는 secret의 ``cool bits''를 복원하기 위한 stepwise regression 기법을 도입한다. 전반적으로 이러한 기법들은 더 밀집된 binary secret의 복원을 가능하게 한다. 즉, dimension $256$ $\\log_2 q=20$에서 Hamming weight 최대 $70$(그리고 $8$ cruel bits), dimension $512$ $\\log_2 q=41$에서 $75$(그리고 $7$ cruel bits)까지 복원할 수 있다(이는 이전 연구의 $33$ 및 $63$ Hamming weight와 $3$ cruel bits보다 향상된 결과이다). 또한 우리는 더 밀집된 ternary secret에 대해서도 우리의 방법이 효과적임을 보이며, 선행 연구에 비해 상당한 향상을 보여준다."},{"id":"60686","en":"FullStack-Agent: Enhancing Agentic Full-Stack Web Coding via Development-Oriented Testing and Repository Back-Translation","ko":"FullStack-Agent: 개발 지향 Testing과 Repository Back-Translation을 통한 Agentic Full-Stack Web Coding 향상","authors":"Zimu Lu, Houxing Ren, Yunqiao Yang, Ke Wang, Zhuofan Zong, Mingjie Zhan, Hongsheng Li","pos":"#908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xblX2nQrj7","abs":"<p>Assisting non-expert users to develop complex interactive websites has become a popular task for LLM-powered code agents. However, existing code agents tend to only generate frontend web pages, masking the lack of real full-stack data processing and storage with fancy visual effects. Notably, constructing production-level full-stack web applications is far more challenging than only generating frontend web pages, demanding careful control of data flow, comprehensive understanding of constantly updating packages and dependencies, and accurate localization of obscure bugs in the codebase. To address these difficulties, we introduce FullStack-Agent, a unified agent system for full-stack agentic coding that consists of three parts: (1) FullStack-Dev, a multi-agent framework with strong planning, code editing, codebase navigation, and bug localization abilities. (2) FullStack-Learn, an innovative data-scaling and self-improving method that back-translates crawled and synthesized website repositories to improve the backbone LLM of FullStack-Dev. (3) FullStack-Bench, a comprehensive benchmark that systematically tests the frontend, backend and database functionalities of the generated website. Our FullStack-Dev outperforms the previous state-of-the-art method by 8.7\\%, 38.2\\%, and 15.9\\% on the frontend, backend, and database test cases respectively. Additionally, FullStack-Learn raises the performance of a 30B model by 9.7\\%, 9.5\\%, and 2.8\\% on the three sets of test cases through self-improvement, demonstrating the effectiveness of our approach.</p>","absKo":"<p>복잡한 interactive website를 개발하도록 non-expert user를 돕는 일은 LLM 기반 code agent에서 인기 있는 task가 되었다. 그러나 기존 code agent는 보통 frontend web page만 생성하며, 화려한 visual effect로 실제 full-stack data processing과 storage의 부재를 가린다. 특히 production-level full-stack web application을 구축하는 일은 frontend web page만 생성하는 것보다 훨씬 더 어렵고, data flow에 대한 세심한 제어, 지속적으로 업데이트되는 package와 dependency에 대한 포괄적 이해, 그리고 codebase 내 모호한 bug의 정확한 위치 파악을 요구한다. 이러한 어려움을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 세 부분으로 구성된 full-stack agentic coding을 위한 통합 agent system인 FullStack-Agent를 제안한다: (1) 강력한 planning, code editing, codebase navigation, bug localization 능력을 갖춘 multi-agent framework인 FullStack-Dev. (2) 크롤링 및 합성된 website repository를 back-translation하여 FullStack-Dev의 backbone LLM을 향상시키는 혁신적인 data-scaling 및 self-improving 방법인 FullStack-Learn. (3) 생성된 website의 frontend, backend, database 기능을 체계적으로 테스트하는 포괄적 benchmark인 FullStack-Bench. 우리의 FullStack-Dev는 frontend, backend, database test case에서 각각 8.7\\%, 38.2\\%, 15.9\\%로 이전 state-of-the-art method를 능가한다. 또한 FullStack-Learn은 self-improvement를 통해 30B model의 성능을 세 종류의 test case에서 각각 9.7\\%, 9.5\\%, 2.8\\% 향상시켜, 우리의 접근의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62139","en":"AnalogVerifier: A Neuro-Symbolic Framework for Analog Circuit Verification","ko":"AnalogVerifier: 아날로그 회로 검증을 위한 Neuro-Symbolic 프레임워크","authors":"Yanfang Liu, Mingjun Wang, Peng XU, Rongliang Fu, Bei Yu, Tsung-Yi Ho","pos":"#913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jTiplBUfn9","abs":"<p>Analog circuits constitute the indispensable interface between physical reality and digital computation, underpinning safety-critical systems from autonomous driving to medical implants. Consequently, verification correctness is paramount; yet, it remains the critical bottleneck in hardware design, consuming over 50\\% of engineering cycles due to a heavy reliance on the manual interpretation of unstructured, heterogeneous specifications. While Large Language Models (LLMs) offer automation potential, their probabilistic, autoregressive nature is structurally misaligned with the strict determinism required for analog verification tasks. Specifically, generic LLMs struggle to resolve semantic dispersion, latent causal dependencies, and numerical precision. To bridge this gap, we introduce AnalogVerifier, a neuro-symbolic framework that automates end-to-end testbench generation by decoupling semantic translation from logical enforcement. We propose a four-stage architecture: (1) Context-Aware Task Serialization transforms complex specifications into atomic tasks via an agentic workflow; (2) Graph-Symbolic Scheduling satisfies analog design constraints through Port Dependency Graphs (PDG) for correct-by-construction sequencing; (3) Numerical-Symbolic Grounding mitigates numerical hallucination by delegating threshold derivation to a deterministic symbolic oracle; (4) Closed-Loop Repair enables correctness and completeness of the generated testbenches by simulation feedback. Evaluation on five industrial analog circuits demonstrates that AnalogVerifier achieves 82.3\\%--100\\% functional pass rate, establishing a new paradigm for reliable, automated analog verification. The code and data are publicly available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ICML26--AnalogVerifier-72EE/}.</p>","absKo":"<p>아날로그 회로는 물리적 현실과 디지털 계산 사이의 필수적인 인터페이스를 구성하며, autonomous driving에서 medical implant에 이르기까지 safety-critical system의 기반을 이룬다. 따라서 verification의 정확성은 무엇보다 중요하지만, 비정형적이고 이질적인 specification을 사람이 직접 해석하는 데 크게 의존하기 때문에 하드웨어 설계에서 가장 중요한 병목으로 남아 있으며, engineering cycle의 50\\% 이상을 소모한다. Large Language Model(LLM)이 자동화 잠재력을 제공하긴 하지만, 그 확률적이고 autoregressive한 특성은 아날로그 verification task에 요구되는 엄격한 결정성과 구조적으로 맞지 않는다. 특히 일반적인 LLM은 semantic dispersion, latent causal dependency, 그리고 수치 정밀도를 제대로 처리하지 못한다. 이 격차를 메우기 위해 우리는 semantic translation과 logical enforcement를 분리하여 end-to-end testbench 생성을 자동화하는 neuro-symbolic framework인 AnalogVerifier를 도입한다. 우리는 네 단계 아키텍처를 제안한다: (1) Context-Aware Task Serialization은 agentic workflow를 통해 복잡한 specification을 원자적 task로 변환한다; (2) Graph-Symbolic Scheduling은 Port Dependency Graph(PDG)를 사용해 아날로그 설계 제약을 만족시키며 correct-by-construction 순서를 보장한다; (3) Numerical-Symbolic Grounding은 threshold derivation을 결정론적 symbolic oracle에 위임함으로써 수치 hallucination을 완화한다; (4) Closed-Loop Repair는 simulation feedback을 통해 생성된 testbench의 정확성과 완전성을 보장한다. 다섯 개의 산업용 아날로그 회로에 대한 평가에서 AnalogVerifier는 82.3\\%--100\\%의 functional pass rate를 달성하여, 신뢰할 수 있는 자동 아날로그 verification을 위한 새로운 패러다임을 확립했다. 코드와 데이터는 \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ICML26--AnalogVerifier-72EE/}에서 공개되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"61847","en":"AOEB: Benchmarking Agent-Oriented Multimodal Embeddings","ko":"AOEB: Agent-Oriented Multimodal Embedding 벤치마킹","authors":"Xin Zhang, Jiaxin Xu, mengjia zhou, Xinping Zhao, Yinghui Li, di yin, Xing Sun, Meishan Zhang, Baotian Hu, Wenjie Li, Min zhang","pos":"#1012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mNOx4mKh3F","abs":"<p>LLM agents powered by retrieval and RAG are increasingly prevalent across research and applications. Embedding models play a critical role in these systems, particularly in embedding-based retrieval. However, current benchmarks for embeddings, such as MTEB, remain focused on general-purpose scenarios, which fail to align well with the diverse and evolving needs of agentic applications. To close this gap, we introduce Agent-Oriented Embedding Benchmark (AOEB), a comprehensive evaluation suite dedicated to agent-centric retrieval for embedding models. AOEB is characterized by two key features: (1) Multi-Task, covering five essential capabilities for retrieval in LLM agents, including code, tool, reasoning, and memory retrieval; and (2) Multi-Modal, providing evaluation with both textual and visual data for each task category. We evaluate representative embedding models on AOEB and observe that they exhibit distinct strengths across different agent-oriented retrieval tasks. By curating AOEB, we aim to promote a move toward more practically oriented directions within the embedding community and foster further progress.</p>","absKo":"<p>retrieval과 RAG로 구동되는 LLM agent는 연구와 응용 전반에서 점점 더 보편화되고 있다. embedding model은 이러한 시스템, 특히 embedding-based retrieval에서 중요한 역할을 한다. 그러나 MTEB와 같은 현재의 embedding benchmark는 여전히 범용 시나리오에 초점을 맞추고 있어, agentic application의 다양하고 진화하는 요구와 잘 맞지 않는다. 이 격차를 메우기 위해 우리는 embedding model의 agent-centric retrieval에 특화된 포괄적 평가 세트인 Agent-Oriented Embedding Benchmark (AOEB)를 소개한다. AOEB는 두 가지 핵심 특징을 가진다. (1) Multi-Task: code, tool, reasoning, memory retrieval을 포함하여 LLM agent의 retrieval에 필수적인 다섯 가지 능력을 포괄하고, (2) Multi-Modal: 각 task 범주에 대해 textual data와 visual data 모두를 이용한 평가를 제공한다. 우리는 대표적인 embedding model을 AOEB에서 평가하고, 서로 다른 agent-oriented retrieval task 전반에서 각기 다른 강점을 보임을 관찰한다. AOEB를 구축함으로써 우리는 embedding community가 더 실용 지향적인 방향으로 나아가고 더 큰 발전을 이루도록 촉진하고자 한다.</p>"},{"id":"65247","en":"EXVERUS: Verus Proof Repair via Counterexample Reasoning","ko":"EXVERUS: 반례 추론을 통한 Verus 증명 수리","authors":"Jun Yang, Yuechun Sun, Yi Wu, Rodrigo Caridad, Yongwei Yuan, Jianan Yao, Shan Lu, Kexin Pei","pos":"#2004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FNDkXA0OUJ","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have shown promising results in automating formal verification. However, existing approaches treat proof generation as a static, end-to-end prediction over source code, relying on limited verifier feedback and lacking access to concrete program behaviors. We present EXVERUS, a counterexample-guided framework that enables LLMs to reason about proofs using behavioral feedback via counterexamples. When a proof fails, EXVERUS automatically generates and validates counterexamples, and then guides the LLM to generalize them into inductive invariants to block these failures. Our evaluation shows that EXVERUS significantly improves proof accuracy, robustness, and token efficiency over the state-of-the-art prompting-based Verus proof generator.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)는 formal verification 자동화에서 유망한 결과를 보여 왔다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 proof generation을 source code에 대한 정적 end-to-end prediction으로 취급하며, 제한적인 verifier feedback에 의존하고 구체적인 program behavior에 대한 접근이 부족하다. 우리는 counterexample을 통해 behavioral feedback을 사용하여 LLM이 proof에 대해 추론할 수 있게 하는 counterexample-guided framework인 EXVERUS를 제시한다. proof가 실패하면 EXVERUS는 counterexample을 자동으로 생성하고 검증한 뒤, LLM이 이를 generalize하여 이러한 실패를 차단하는 inductive invariant로 확장하도록 유도한다. 우리의 평가 결과, EXVERUS는 state-of-the-art prompting-based Verus proof generator에 비해 proof accuracy, robustness, token efficiency를 크게 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"65992","en":"Escaping Whack-a-Mole: Code Documentation Optimization via Dependency-Guided Bi-level Search","ko":"두더지 잡기에서 벗어나기: 의존성 유도 이단계 탐색을 통한 코드 문서화 최적화","authors":"Yutong Cheng, Haifeng Chen, Wenchao Yu, Xujiang Zhao, Peng Gao, Wei Cheng","pos":"#2006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=88NO4CL9EQ","abs":"<p>As large language models increasingly serve as autonomous coding agents, code documentation must be optimized for agent comprehension rather than human readability. We frame agent-oriented documentation generation as a black-box optimization problem over the documentation space, where quality is measured solely by downstream code correctness. A central challenge for conventional LLM refinement methods is <em>output coupling</em>—program entities are interdependent, and refining the documentation of one entity can invalidate its callers, resulting in a persistent <em>whack-a-mole</em> phenomenon during inference-time scaling. We propose DocSearch, a dependency-guided bi-level search framework that systematically exploits test-time feedback. The outer level conducts a priority search over the program-entity dependency DAG, enforcing a callee-before-caller refinement order to prevent downstream interference. The inner level performs a beam search over documentation refinements, using diversified error message sampling from self-generated unit tests to better exploit diagnostic signals and escape local optima. We provide theoretical guarantees of monotonic progress, showing that our worthy condition prevents regression while enabling efficient exploration. On DevEval+, DocSearch achieves a 90.7% solve rate with GPT-4o, outperforming the strongest baseline by 32.6%. Cross-language experiments further demonstrate that optimized documentation transfers effectively to different target programming languages.</p>"},{"id":"64101","en":"Autoregressive, Yet Revisable: In Decoding Revision for Secure Code Generation","ko":"자기회귀적이면서 수정 가능한: 안전한 코드 생성을 위한 디코딩 내 수정","authors":"Chengran Yang, zichao wei, Heminghao Deng, Jinfeng Jiang, Zhensu Sun, Ting Zhang, Tianyi Wu, Ming Wen, David Lo","pos":"#2911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QrOWZ2GkI0","abs":"<p>Large Language Model (LLM) based code generation is predominantly formulated as a strictly monotonic process, appending tokens linearly to an immutable prefix. This formulation contrasts to the cognitive process of programming, which is inherently interleaved with forward generation and on-the-fly revision. While prior works attempt to introduce revision via post-hoc agents or external static tools, they either suffer from high latency or fail to leverage the model's intrinsic semantic reasoning. In this paper, we propose Stream of Revision, a paradigm shift that elevates code generation from a monotonic stream to a dynamic, self-correcting trajectory by leveraging model's intrinsic capabilities. We introduce specific action tokens that enable the model to seamlessly backtrack and edit its own history within a single forward pass. By internalizing the revision loop, our framework Stream of Revision allows the model to activate its latent capabilities just-in-time without external dependencies. Empirical results on secure code generation show that Stream of Revision significantly reduces vulnerabilities with minimal inference overhead. We release our code and dataset at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Stream-of-Revision-CB74/}, and models will be released upon publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model (LLM) 기반 code generation은 대체로 엄격한 단조 과정으로 정식화되어, 변하지 않는 prefix에 token을 선형적으로 추가한다. 이 정식화는 본질적으로 forward generation과 즉석 수정을 교차시키는 programming의 인지 과정과 대조된다. 선행 연구들은 post-hoc agent나 외부 static tool을 통해 revision을 도입하려고 시도했지만, 이들은 높은 latency를 겪거나 모델의 고유한 semantic reasoning을 활용하지 못한다. 본 논문에서는 모델의 고유한 능력을 활용하여 code generation을 단조적 stream에서 동적이고 자기 수정적인 trajectory로 끌어올리는 패러다임 전환, Stream of Revision을 제안한다. 우리는 모델이 단일 forward pass 안에서 자신의 history를 매끄럽게 backtrack하고 편집할 수 있게 하는 특정 action token을 도입한다. revision loop를 내부화함으로써, 우리의 프레임워크인 Stream of Revision은 외부 의존성 없이 모델이 잠재 능력을 just-in-time으로 활성화하도록 한다. 안전한 code generation에 대한 실증 결과는 Stream of Revision이 최소한의 inference overhead로 취약성을 크게 줄임을 보여준다. 우리의 code와 dataset은 \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Stream-of-Revision-CB74/}에서 공개하며, model은 출판 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64289","en":"LOVE: Benchmarking and Evaluating Text-to-Video Generation and Video-to-Text Interpretation","ko":"LOVE: Text-to-Video 생성 및 Video-to-Text 해석의 벤치마킹 및 평가","authors":"Jiarui Wang, Huiyu Duan, Ziheng Jia, Zicheng Zhang, Yu Zhao, Juntong Wang, Guangtao Zhai, Xiongkuo Min","pos":"#3507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P6fWeIVbwb","abs":"<p>Recent advancements in large multimodal models (LMMs) have driven substantial progress in both text-to-video (T2V) generation and video-to-text (V2T) interpretation tasks.  However, current AI-generated videos (AIGVs) still exhibit limitations in terms of perceptual quality and text-video alignment.  To this end, we present <strong>AIGVE-60K</strong>, a comprehensive dataset and benchmark for AI-Generated Video Evaluation, which features <strong>(i)</strong> comprehensive tasks, encompassing 3,050 extensive prompts across 20 fine-grained task dimensions, <strong>(ii)</strong> the largest human annotations, including 120K mean-opinion scores (MOSs) and 60K question-answering (QA) pairs annotated on 58,500 videos generated from 30 T2V models, and <strong>(iii)</strong> bidirectional benchmarking and evaluating for both T2V generation and V2T interpretation capabilities. Based on AIGVE-60K, we propose <strong>LOVE</strong>, a LMM-based metric for AIGV Evaluation from multiple dimensions including perceptual preference, text-video correspondence, and task-specific accuracy. Building upon LOVE, we further introduce <strong>LOVE-Reward</strong> to optimize T2V models through reinforcement learning, effectively enhancing both the perceptual quality and text-video correspondence of generated videos.  Comprehensive experiments demonstrate that LOVE achieves state-of-the-art performance and generalizes effectively to various AIGV benchmarks. LOVE-Reward significantly improves video generation quality. These findings highlight the significance of the AIGVE-60K dataset and the effectiveness of our proposed methods. The database and codes will be available upon publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 large multimodal models (LMMs)의 발전은 text-to-video (T2V) 생성과 video-to-text (V2T) 해석 과제 모두에서 상당한 진전을 이끌어 왔습니다. 그러나 현재 AI-generated videos (AIGVs)는 여전히 지각적 품질과 text-video alignment 측면에서 한계를 보입니다. 이를 위해 우리는 AI-Generated Video Evaluation을 위한 포괄적인 dataset이자 benchmark인 <strong>AIGVE-60K</strong>를 제안합니다. 이 데이터셋은 <strong>(i)</strong> 20개의 세분화된 task 차원에 걸친 3,050개의 방대한 prompt를 포함하는 포괄적인 tasks, <strong>(ii)</strong> 30개의 T2V 모델로 생성된 58,500개의 video에 대해 주석된 120K mean-opinion scores (MOSs)와 60K question-answering (QA) pairs를 포함하는 최대 규모의 human annotations, 그리고 <strong>(iii)</strong> T2V 생성 능력과 V2T 해석 능력 모두에 대한 양방향 benchmarking 및 평가를 특징으로 합니다. AIGVE-60K를 기반으로, 우리는 지각적 선호도, text-video 대응성, task-specific accuracy를 포함한 여러 차원에서 AIGV를 평가하는 LMM 기반 metric인 <strong>LOVE</strong>를 제안합니다. 또한 LOVE를 바탕으로 reinforcement learning을 통해 T2V 모델을 최적화하는 <strong>LOVE-Reward</strong>를 추가로 도입하여, 생성된 video의 지각적 품질과 text-video 대응성을 효과적으로 향상시킵니다. 종합적인 실험은 LOVE가 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하고 다양한 AIGV benchmark로 효과적으로 일반화됨을 보여줍니다. LOVE-Reward는 video 생성 품질을 유의미하게 향상시킵니다. 이러한 결과는 AIGVE-60K 데이터셋의 중요성과 제안한 방법들의 효과를 강조합니다. 데이터베이스와 코드는 논문 출판 시 공개될 예정입니다.</p>"},{"id":"66447","en":"LocalV: Exploiting Information Locality for IP-level Verilog Generation","ko":"LocalV: IP 수준 Verilog 생성을 위한 정보 국소성 활용","authors":"Hanqi Lyu, Di Huang, Yaoyu Zhu, Kangcheng Liu, Bohan Dou, Chongxiao Li, Pengwei Jin, Shuyao Cheng, Rui Zhang, Zidong Du, Qi Guo, Xing Hu, Yunji Chen","pos":"#3601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3ebavardTL","abs":"<p>The generation of Register-Transfer Level (RTL) code is a crucial yet labor-intensive step in digital hardware design, traditionally requiring engineers to manually translate complex specifications into thousands of lines of synthesizable Hardware Description Language (HDL) code. While Large Language Models (LLMs) have shown promise in automating this process, existing approaches—including fine-tuned domain-specific models and advanced agent-based systems—struggle to scale to industrial IP-level design tasks. We identify three key challenges: (1) handling long, highly detailed documents, where critical interface constraints become buried in unrelated submodule descriptions; (2) generating long RTL code, where both syntactic and semantic correctness degrade sharply with increasing output length;  and (3) navigating the complex debugging cycles required for functional verification through simulation and waveform analysis. To overcome these challenges, we propose \\textit{LocalV}, a multi-agent framework that leverages \\textit{information locality} in modular hardware design. LocalV decomposes the long-document to long-code generation problem into a set of short-document, short-code tasks, enabling scalable generation and debugging.  Specifically, LocalV integrates hierarchical document partitioning, task planning, localized code generation, interface-consistent merging, and AST-guided locality-aware debugging.  Experiments on \\textsc{RealBench}, an IP-level Verilog generation benchmark, demonstrate that LocalV substantially outperforms state-of-the-art (SOTA) LLMs and agents, achieving a pass rate of 45.0\\% compared to 21.6\\%.</p>"},{"id":"66682","en":"$G^2$-Reader: Dual Evolving Graphs for Multimodal Document QA","ko":"$G^2$-Reader: 멀티모달 문서 QA를 위한 Dual Evolving Graph","authors":"Yaxin Du, Junru Song, Yifan Zhou, Cheng Wang, Jiahao Gu, Zimeng Chen, Menglan Chen, Wen Yao, Yang Yang, Ying Wen, Siheng Chen","pos":"#3705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1NACQKPp1n","abs":"Retrieval-augmented generation is a practical paradigm for question answering over long documents, but it remains brittle for multimodal reading where text, tables, and figures are interleaved across many pages. First, flat chunking breaks document-native structure and cross-modal alignment, yielding semantic fragments that are hard to interpret in isolation. Second, even iterative retrieval can fail in long contexts by looping on partial evidence or drifting into irrelevant sections as noise accumulates, since each step is guided only by the current snippet without a persistent global search state. We introduce $G^2$-Reader, a dual-graph system, to address both issues. It evolves a Content Graph to preserve document-native structure and cross-modal semantics, and maintains a Planning Graph, an agentic directed acyclic graph of sub-questions, to track intermediate findings and guide stepwise navigation for evidence completion. On VisDoMBench across five multimodal domains, $G^2$-Reader with Qwen3-VL-32B-Instruct reaches 66.21\\% average accuracy, outperforming strong baselines and a standalone GPT-5 (53.08\\%). Code is available: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/D2-Reader-8526."},{"id":"62318","en":"On Path to Multimodal Historical Reasoning: HistBench and HistAgent","ko":"멀티모달 역사 추론으로 가는 길: HistBench와 HistAgent","authors":"Jiahao Qiu, Fulian Xiao, Yimin Wang, Yuchen Mao, Yijia Chen, Xinzhe Juan, Siran Wang, Xuan Qi, Tongcheng Zhang, Zixin Yao, Jiacheng Guo, Yifu Lu, Charles Argon, Jundi Cui, Daixin Chen, Junran Zhou, Shuyao Zhou, Zhanpeng Zhou, Ling Yang, Shilong Liu, Hongru WANG, Kaixuan Huang, xun jiang, Xi Gao, Mengdi Wang","pos":"#403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hh1FITGR8C","abs":"<p>Recent advances in large language models (LLMs) have led to remarkable progress across various domains, yet their capabilities in the humanities, particularly history, remain underexplored. Historical reasoning poses unique challenges for LLMs, involving multimodal source interpretation, temporal inference, and cross-linguistic analysis. Existing general-purpose agents perform well on many current benchmarks but lack the domain expertise needed to address complex historical questions. To address this gap, we introduce HistBench, a new benchmark of 414 high-quality and carefully-reviewed questions stratified by difficulty and designed to evaluate LLM's capacity for historical reasoning. The tasks span a wide range of historical problems—from factual retrieval based on primary sources to interpretive analysis of manuscripts and images, to interdisciplinary challenges involving archaeology, linguistics, or cultural history. Furthermore, the benchmark dataset spans 29 ancient and modern languages and covers a wide range of historical periods and world regions. Finding the poor performance of LLMs and other agents on HistBench, we further present HistAgent, a history-specific agent equipped with carefully designed tools for OCR, translation, archival search, and image understanding in History. On HistBench, HistAgent based on GPT-4o achieves an accuracy of 27.54% pass@1 and 36.47% pass@2, significantly outperforming LLMs with online search and generalist agents, including GPT-4o (18.60%), DeepSeek-R1(14.49%), Grok 3(17.63%) and Open Deep Research by smolagents(20.29% pass@1 and 25.12% pass@2). These results highlight the limitations of existing LLMs and generalist agents and demonstrate the advantages of HistAgent for historical reasoning. Notably, HistAgent also achieves 60.00% pass@1 accuracy on the GAIA benchmark, showing that domain-specific customization doesn't hinder HistAgent's competitive performance on real-world general tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 language model (LLM)의 최근 발전은 다양한 영역에서 놀라운 진전을 이끌었지만, 인문학, 특히 역사 분야에서의 역량은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 역사적 추론은 multimodal source interpretation, temporal inference, cross-linguistic analysis를 포함하는 LLM에게 고유한 도전을 제시한다. 기존의 general-purpose agent는 많은 최신 benchmark에서 좋은 성능을 보이지만, 복잡한 역사 질문을 다루는 데 필요한 domain expertise는 부족하다. 이 격차를 해소하기 위해, 우리는 LLM의 역사적 추론 능력을 평가하도록 설계된 difficulty별로 stratify된 414개의 고품질·정밀 검토 질문으로 이루어진 새로운 benchmark인 HistBench를 소개한다. 이 task는 primary source를 바탕으로 한 factual retrieval부터 manuscript와 이미지에 대한 interpretive analysis, archaeology, linguistics, cultural history를 포함한 interdisciplinary challenge까지 폭넓은 역사 문제를 포괄한다. 더 나아가, 이 benchmark dataset은 29개의 고대 및 현대 언어를 아우르며 광범위한 역사적 시기와 세계 지역을 포함한다. HistBench에서 LLM과 다른 agent의 낮은 성능을 확인한 후, 우리는 History 분야에서 OCR, translation, archival search, image understanding을 위해 세심하게 설계된 도구를 갖춘 history-specific agent인 HistAgent를 추가로 제시한다. HistBench에서 GPT-4o 기반 HistAgent는 27.54% pass@1과 36.47% pass@2의 정확도를 달성하여, online search를 사용하는 LLM과 generalist agent, including GPT-4o(18.60%), DeepSeek-R1(14.49%), Grok 3(17.63%), smolagents의 Open Deep Research(20.29% pass@1 및 25.12% pass@2)를 크게 능가한다. 이러한 결과는 기존 LLM과 generalist agent의 한계를 드러내는 동시에, 역사적 추론에 있어 HistAgent의 장점을 보여준다. 주목할 점은 HistAgent가 GAIA benchmark에서도 60.00% pass@1 정확도를 달성하여, domain-specific customization이 실제 세계의 일반 task에서 HistAgent의 경쟁력 있는 성능을 저해하지 않음을 보여준다는 것이다.</p>"},{"id":"66769","en":"SciNet: Evaluating AI Agents in Relation-Aware Scientific Literature Retrieval","ko":"SciNet: 관계 인지 과학 문헌 검색에서 AI 에이전트 평가","authors":"Chenyang Shao, Fengli Xu, Yong Li","pos":"#4405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0S2WJSFkp0","abs":"<p>AI agents have seen widespread adoption in information retrieval for scientific research, giving rise to tools such as <em>Deep Research</em>. However, existing retrieval agents mainly rely on keyword- or embedding-based methods. While effective at capturing content-level similarities, they struggle to understand complex relational networks among scientific papers, such as identifying corroborating or conflicting studies and tracing technological lineages. This fundamental limitation often results in fragmented knowledge structures, misinterpreted research sentiment, and ineffective modeling of collective scientific progress. To address this limitation, we introduce <strong>SciNet</strong>, the first <strong>Sci</strong>entific <strong>Net</strong>work relation-aware dataset for information retrieval agents. Built on a meta-database of 269 million papers across 7 disciplines and containing 8,940 carefully designed tasks, SciNet systematically captures three levels of relational understanding: ego-centric retrieval of papers with novel knowledge structures, pairwise identification of scholarly relationships, and path-wise reconstruction of scientific evolution. Extensive evaluation of three categories of retrieval agents shows that their accuracy on relation-aware tasks often falls below 20%, highlighting a fundamental shortcoming of current retrieval paradigms. Importantly, in a downstream literature review application, agents empowered with SciNet achieve a 25.3% improvement in review quality, highlighting the critical value of relation-aware retrieval for deepening scientific insights. We publicly release SciNet at <a href=\"https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SciNet/\">https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SciNet/</a> to support future research.</p>"},{"id":"62856","en":"AppWorld-UL: Benchmarking Diverse Agent-User Interactions for Tool-Use","ko":"AppWorld-UL: Tool-Use를 위한 다양한 Agent-User 상호작용 벤치마킹","authors":"Junzhi Chen, Harsh Trivedi, Jane Pan, Michael Zhang, Tejas Srinivasan, Niranjan Balasubramanian, Ashish Sabharwal","pos":"#4407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cUXV9vtDXd","abs":"<p>Tool-use agents that address day-to-day digital tasks such as ordering groceries must not only operate applications, but also interact with the user, e.g., to ask clarification questions, prompt for confirmation, and inform the user when the instruction is infeasible. However, current benchmarks for evaluating agent-user interactions do not capture the diversity of such interactions. Further, they operate in small environments with few, often non-state-changing, APIs. To address this gap, we introduce AppWorld-UL, a ``user-in-the-loop'' benchmark of 306 challenging tasks requiring diverse agent-user interactions. Building upon the AppWorld framework with 9 popular simulated apps like Amazon and Spotify, we systematically modify original tasks to introduce ambiguities and constraints that necessitate various types of agent-user interaction. User behavior is simulated by an LLM prompted to respond with carefully designed knowledge boundaries, offering more reliable simulation than the unconstrained or overly rigid alternatives used in prior work. Our evaluation reveals that a state-of-the-art LLM, GPT-5, achieves only 38.2\\% success on AppWorld-UL and that correct user-interaction is crucial for success. This demonstrates the benchmark's difficulty and its potential to advance research on user-in-the-loop tool-use agents.</p>","absKo":"<p>식료품 주문과 같은 일상적인 디지털 작업을 처리하는 tool-use agent는 애플리케이션을 조작할 뿐 아니라, clarification question을 묻고, 확인을 요청하고, 지시를 수행할 수 없을 때 사용자에게 알려주는 등 사용자와도 상호작용해야 한다. 그러나 agent-user interaction을 평가하기 위한 현재 benchmark는 이러한 상호작용의 다양성을 포착하지 못한다. 또한 규모가 작고, 상태를 거의 변화시키지 않는 API만 포함하는 환경에서 동작한다. 이 간극을 해소하기 위해 우리는 다양한 agent-user interaction을 요구하는 306개의 어려운 task로 구성된 ``user-in-the-loop'' benchmark인 AppWorld-UL을 소개한다. Amazon과 Spotify 같은 9개의 인기 시뮬레이션 앱을 포함하는 AppWorld framework 위에 구축하여, 원래 task를 체계적으로 수정해 다양한 유형의 agent-user interaction이 필요하도록 모호성과 제약을 도입했다. 사용자 행동은 carefully designed knowledge boundary를 반영하도록 prompt된 LLM으로 시뮬레이션되며, 이는 기존 연구에서 사용된 무제약 또는 지나치게 경직된 대안보다 더 신뢰할 수 있는 시뮬레이션을 제공한다. 우리의 평가에 따르면 최첨단 LLM인 GPT-5도 AppWorld-UL에서 성공률이 38.2\\%에 그쳤으며, 올바른 사용자 상호작용이 성공에 결정적이다. 이는 이 benchmark의 난이도와 user-in-the-loop tool-use agent 연구를 발전시킬 잠재력을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65101","en":"PPT-Eval: A Benchmark for Computer-Use Agents on PowerPoint Tasks","ko":"PPT-Eval: PowerPoint 작업에서 Computer-Use 에이전트를 위한 벤치마크","authors":"Apurva Gandhi, Vishwas Suryanarayanan, Firoz Shaik, Raja Anwar, Shubhang Desai, Thong Nguyen, Muhammad Raza, Vishal Chowdhary, Graham Neubig","pos":"#4413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GmeK95WQQ4","abs":"Creating and editing slides is a rich, multimodal activity that is ubiquitous in professional and educational settings, making it an ideal testbed for real-world computer-use agents. Microsoft PowerPoint is among the most widely adopted and feature-rich environments for presentation creation. We introduce PPT-Eval, a benchmark of 120 diverse PowerPoint tasks across 12 files that cover both content creation and presentation editing scenarios, organized by difficulty. A central challenge in this domain is evaluation: tasks are complex, multimodal, and often admit many valid solutions. Moreover, today’s agents frequently make only partial progress, which binary success metrics fail to capture. To address this, we design a robust evaluation framework to help create task-specific rubrics for PowerPoint tasks, taking inspiration from and building on past works for rubric-based evaluation. These rubrics award partial credit for intermediate steps, penalize unnecessary changes and poor aesthetics, and provide natural language feedback. This nuanced approach proves highly effective, achieving a Kendall's $\\tau_b$ correlation of 0.77 with human judgments.  We find that existing frontier agents still struggle with solving PowerPoint tasks, with strong models like Claude-4.5-Opus achieving only a 43\\% success rate and an average partial score of 59\\%.","absKo":"슬라이드를 만들고 편집하는 일은 풍부한 multimodal 활동으로, 전문 및 교육 환경 전반에 널리 존재하므로, 실제 computer-use agent를 시험하기에 이상적인 testbed이다. Microsoft PowerPoint는 프레젠테이션 제작을 위한 가장 널리 채택되고 기능이 풍부한 환경 중 하나이다. 우리는 12개 파일에 걸친 120개의 다양한 PowerPoint task로 구성된 benchmark인 PPT-Eval을 소개하며, 이는 difficulty에 따라 정리된 content creation과 presentation editing 시나리오를 모두 포괄한다. 이 영역에서 핵심적인 과제는 evaluation이다. task가 복잡하고 multimodal하며, 종종 유효한 해법이 매우 많기 때문이다. 더구나 오늘날의 agent는 부분적인 진전만 이루는 경우가 많아, binary success metric으로는 이를 포착할 수 없다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 rubric-based evaluation에 관한 기존 연구에서 영감을 받아 이를 확장한, PowerPoint task에 맞춤형 rubric을 만드는 강건한 evaluation framework를 설계한다. 이러한 rubric은 중간 단계에 대해 partial credit을 부여하고, 불필요한 변경과 낮은 미적 품질을 감점하며, 자연어 피드백을 제공한다. 이 정교한 접근은 매우 효과적이어서 human judgment와의 Kendall's $\\tau_b$ 상관계수 0.77을 달성한다. 우리는 기존 frontier agent들이 여전히 PowerPoint task 해결에 어려움을 겪는다는 사실을 발견했으며, Claude-4.5-Opus 같은 강력한 모델도 43\\%의 성공률과 평균 59\\%의 partial score에 그쳤다."},{"id":"66568","en":"MathlibLemma: Folklore Lemma Generation and Benchmark for Formal Mathematics","ko":"MathlibLemma: 형식 수학을 위한 정설 보조정리 생성 및 벤치마크","authors":"Xinyu Liu, Zixuan Xie, Amir Moeini, Claire Chen, Shuze Liu, Yu Meng, Aidong Zhang, Shangtong Zhang","pos":"#900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2WfRsrQxpC","abs":"<p>While the ecosystem of Lean and Mathlib has enjoyed celebrated success in formal mathematical reasoning with the help of large language models (LLMs), the absence of many folklore lemmas in Mathlib remains a persistent barrier that limits Lean's usability as an everyday tool for mathematicians like \\LaTeX{} or Maple. To address this, we introduce \\textsc{MathlibLemma}, the first LLM-based multi-agent system to automate the discovery and formalization of mathematical folklore lemmas. This framework constitutes our primary contribution, proactively mining the missing connective tissue of mathematics. Its efficacy is demonstrated by the production of a verified library of folklore lemmas, a subset of which has already been formally merged into the latest build of Mathlib, thereby validating  the system's real-world utility and alignment with expert standards. Leveraging this pipeline, we further construct the \\textsc{MathlibLemma} benchmark, a suite of approximately 4,000 type-checked Lean statements spanning a broad range of mathematical domains. By transforming the role of LLMs from passive consumers to active contributors, this work establishes a constructive methodology for the self-evolution of formal mathematical libraries.</p>"},{"id":"64492","en":"MOOSE-Star: Unlocking Tractable Training for Scientific Discovery by Breaking the Complexity Barrier","ko":"MOOSE-Star: 복잡도 장벽 돌파를 통한 과학적 발견을 위한 다루기 쉬운 학습 실현","authors":"Zonglin Yang, Lidong Bing","pos":"#901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=N1N4H50yS2","abs":"While large language models (LLMs) show promise in scientific discovery, existing research focuses on inference or feedback-driven training, leaving the direct modeling of the generative reasoning process, $P(\\text{hypothesis}|\\text{background})$ ($P(h|b)$), unexplored. We demonstrate that directly training $P(h|b)$ is mathematically intractable due to the combinatorial complexity ($O(N^k)$) inherent in retrieving and composing inspirations from a vast knowledge base. To break this barrier, we introduce MOOSE-Star, a unified framework enabling tractable training and scalable inference. In the best case, MOOSE-Star reduces complexity from exponential to logarithmic ($O(\\log N)$) by (1) training on decomposed subtasks derived from the probabilistic equation of discovery, (2) employing motivation-guided hierarchical search to enable logarithmic retrieval and prune irrelevant subspaces, and (3) utilizing bounded composition for robustness against retrieval noise. To facilitate this, we release TOMATO-Star, a benchmark of 120,000 decomposed papers (38,400 GPU hours) for training. Furthermore, we show that while brute-force sampling hits a ``complexity wall,'' MOOSE-Star exhibits continuous test-time scaling.","absKo":"Large language models(LLMs)가 과학적 발견에서 유망함을 보이지만, 기존 연구는 inference 또는 feedback-driven training에 초점을 맞춰 왔으며, 생성적 추론 과정인 $P(\\text{hypothesis}|\\text{background})$ ($P(h|b)$)를 직접 모델링하는 문제는 아직 탐구되지 않았습니다. 우리는 방대한 knowledge base에서 영감을 검색하고 조합하는 데 내재된 조합적 복잡도($O(N^k)$) 때문에 $P(h|b)$를 직접 학습하는 것은 수학적으로 다루기 어렵다는 점을 보입니다. 이 장벽을 극복하기 위해, 우리는 tractable training과 scalable inference를 가능하게 하는 통합 프레임워크인 MOOSE-Star를 제안합니다. 최선의 경우, MOOSE-Star는 (1) discovery의 probabilistic equation에서 도출된 decomposed subtask로 학습하고, (2) motivation-guided hierarchical search를 사용해 logarithmic retrieval을 가능하게 하며 irrelevant subspace를 가지치기하고, (3) retrieval noise에 대한 robustness를 위해 bounded composition을 활용함으로써 복잡도를 exponential에서 logarithmic($O(\\log N)$)으로 줄입니다. 이를 지원하기 위해, 우리는 학습용으로 120,000개의 decomposed paper(38,400 GPU hours)로 구성된 benchmark인 TOMATO-Star를 공개합니다. 더 나아가, brute-force sampling이 ``complexity wall''에 부딪히는 반면, MOOSE-Star는 연속적인 test-time scaling을 보인다는 점을 보여줍니다."},{"id":"64521","en":"MEnvAgent: Scalable Polyglot Environment Construction for Verifiable Software Engineering","ko":"MEnvAgent: 검증 가능한 소프트웨어 공학을 위한 확장 가능한 다중 언어 환경 구축","authors":"Chuanzhe Guo, Jingjing Wu, Sijun He, Yang Chen, Zhaoqi Kuang, Shilong Fan, Bingjin Chen, Siqi Bao, Jing Liu, Hua Wu, Qingfu Zhu, Wanxiang Che, Haifeng Wang","pos":"#902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Mkal0hTCnh","abs":"<p>The evolution of Large Language Model (LLM) agents for software engineering (SWE) is constrained by the scarcity of verifiable datasets, a bottleneck stemming from the complexity of constructing executable environments across diverse languages. To address this, we introduce <strong>MEnvAgent</strong>, a <strong>M</strong>ulti-language framework for automated <strong>Env</strong>ironment construction that facilitates scalable generation of verifiable task instances. MEnvAgent employs a multi-agent Planning-Execution-Verification architecture to autonomously resolve construction failures and integrates a novel Environment Reuse Mechanism that reduces computational overhead by incrementally patching historical environments. Evaluations on MEnvBench, a new benchmark comprising 1,000 tasks across 10 languages, demonstrate that MEnvAgent outperforms baselines, improving Fail-to-Pass (F2P) rates by <strong>8.6%</strong> while reducing time costs by <strong>43%</strong>. Additionally, we demonstrate the utility of MEnvAgent by constructing MEnvData-SWE, the largest open-source polyglot dataset of realistic verifiable Docker environments to date, alongside solution trajectories that enable consistent performance gains on SWE tasks across a wide range of models.</p>","absKo":"<p>소프트웨어 공학(SWE)을 위한 Large Language Model(LLM) agent의 발전은 검증 가능한 데이터셋의 부족이라는 제약을 받으며, 이는 다양한 언어에 걸쳐 실행 가능한 환경을 구축하는 복잡성에서 비롯된 병목이다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 <strong>MEnvAgent</strong>를 소개한다. <strong>M</strong>ulti-language framework for automated <strong>Env</strong>ironment construction으로서, 검증 가능한 task instance의 확장 가능한 생성을 가능하게 한다. MEnvAgent는 다중 agent Planning-Execution-Verification 아키텍처를 사용하여 구축 실패를 자율적으로 해결하고, 기존 환경을 점진적으로 patch함으로써 계산 오버헤드를 줄이는 새로운 Environment Reuse Mechanism을 통합한다. 10개 언어에 걸친 1,000개 task로 구성된 새로운 benchmark인 MEnvBench에서의 평가 결과, MEnvAgent는 baseline을 능가하여 Fail-to-Pass (F2P) rate를 <strong>8.6%</strong> 향상시키는 동시에 시간 비용을 <strong>43%</strong> 절감함을 보였다. 또한 우리는 현실적인 검증 가능한 Docker 환경으로 이루어진 현재까지 가장 큰 open-source polyglot dataset인 MEnvData-SWE를 구축하여 MEnvAgent의 유용성을 입증했으며, 다양한 model 전반에서 SWE task의 일관된 성능 향상을 가능하게 하는 solution trajectory도 함께 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63884","en":"JADE: Expert-Grounded Dynamic Evaluation for Open-Ended Professional Tasks","ko":"JADE: 개방형 전문 업무를 위한 전문가 기반 동적 평가","authors":"Lanbo Lin, Jiayao Liu, Tianyuan Yang, Li Cai, Yuanwu Xu, Lei Wei, TT, Guannan Zhang","pos":"#903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SoilRyCv1i","abs":"<p>Evaluating agentic AI on open-ended professional tasks faces a fundamental dilemma between rigor and flexibility. Static rubrics provide rigorous, reproducible assessment but fail to accommodate diverse valid response strategies, while LLM-as-a-judge approaches adapt to individual responses yet suffer from instability and bias. Human experts address this dilemma by combining domain-grounded principles with dynamic, claim-level assessment. Inspired by this process, we propose JADE, a two-layer evaluation framework. Layer 1 encodes expert knowledge as a predefined set of evaluation skills, providing stable evaluation criteria. Layer 2 performs report-specific, claim-level evaluation to flexibly assess diverse reasoning strategies, with evidence-dependency gating to invalidate conclusions built on refuted claims. Experiments on BizBench show that JADE improves evaluation stability and reveals critical agent failure modes missed by holistic LLM-based evaluators. We further demonstrate strong alignment with expert-authored rubrics and effective transfer to a medical-domain benchmark, validating JADE across professional domains.</p>","absKo":"<p>개방형 professional task에서 agentic AI를 평가하는 일은 rigor와 flexibility 사이의 근본적인 딜레마에 직면한다. static rubric은 엄밀하고 재현 가능한 평가를 제공하지만 다양한 정당한 응답 전략을 수용하지 못하고, LLM-as-a-judge 접근법은 개별 응답에 적응할 수 있지만 불안정성과 bias에 시달린다. human expert는 domain-grounded principle과 dynamic claim-level assessment를 결합함으로써 이 딜레마를 해결한다. 이러한 과정에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 두 층으로 구성된 평가 framework인 JADE를 제안한다. Layer 1은 expert knowledge를 사전에 정의된 evaluation skill 집합으로 인코딩하여 안정적인 평가 기준을 제공한다. Layer 2는 report-specific한 claim-level evaluation을 수행하여 다양한 reasoning strategy를 유연하게 평가하며, evidence-dependency gating을 통해 반박된 claim 위에 구축된 결론을 무효화한다. BizBench에서의 실험은 JADE가 평가 안정성을 향상시키고, 전체적인 LLM 기반 evaluator가 놓치는 핵심 agent failure mode를 드러냄을 보여준다. 또한 우리는 expert가 작성한 rubric과의 강한 정렬 및 medical-domain benchmark로의 효과적인 transfer를 입증하여, JADE가 다양한 professional domain 전반에서 유효함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64106","en":"InteractScience: Programmatic and Visually-Grounded Evaluation of Interactive Scientific Demonstration Code Generation","ko":"InteractScience: 인터랙티브 과학 시연 코드 생성의 프로그래밍적·시각적 기반 평가","authors":"Qiaosheng Chen, Yang Liu, Lei Li, Kai Chen, Qipeng Guo, Gong Cheng, fei yuan","pos":"#904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QooehkRtN5","abs":"<p>While Large Language Models (LLMs) hold promise for automating science and education, generating interactive scientific demonstrations demands a complex synthesis of deep domain knowledge and precise reactive coding. Current benchmarks fail to capture this synergy, largely bifurcating into static code generation or text-only reasoning. To address this, we introduce \\textsc{InteractScience}, the first benchmark dedicated to evaluating the holistic creation of interactive scientific applications. We propose a novel hybrid framework that integrates programmatic functional testing for logic verification with visually-grounded qualitative assessment for rendering fidelity. Our evaluation of 30 leading models across five disciplines reveals critical gaps in grounding scientific reasoning within interactive interfaces. By standardizing this combined capability, \\textsc{InteractScience} establishes a crucial foundation for reliable AI-driven tools in science and education.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model (LLM)은 과학과 교육의 자동화에 유망하지만, 상호작용적인 scientific demonstration을 생성하려면 깊은 domain knowledge와 정밀한 reactive coding의 복잡한 합성이 필요하다. 현재의 benchmark는 이러한 시너지를 포착하지 못하며, 대체로 static code generation 또는 text-only reasoning으로 양분되어 있다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 상호작용적 scientific application의 총체적 생성을 평가하는 데 전념한 최초의 benchmark인 \\textsc{InteractScience}를 소개한다. 우리는 logic verification을 위한 programmatic functional testing과 rendering fidelity를 위한 visual-grounded qualitative assessment를 통합하는 새로운 hybrid framework를 제안한다. 다섯 개 학문 분야에 걸쳐 30개의 선도 모델을 평가한 결과, 상호작용형 인터페이스 안에서 scientific reasoning을 정합시키는 데 중요한 격차가 드러났다. 이 결합된 능력을 표준화함으로써, \\textsc{InteractScience}는 과학과 교육에서 신뢰할 수 있는 AI 기반 도구를 위한 중요한 기반을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"64860","en":"Grounded in Reality: Learning and Deploying Proactive LLM from Offline Logs","ko":"현실에 기반하여: Offline Log로부터 능동적 LLM 학습 및 배포","authors":"Fei Wei, Daoyuan Chen, Ce Wang, Yilun Huang, Yushuo Chen, Xuchen Pan, Yaliang Li, Bolin Ding","pos":"#907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=J4k8q8nku1","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are strong passive responders, but learning to proactively elicit information—asking the right questions and stopping at the right time—remains difficult. Existing approaches, such as optimizing turn-level attributes or relying on user simulators to generate training trajectories, often struggle with a persistent reality gap.  We propose \\texttt{Learn-to-Ask}, a simulator-free framework that learns proactive questioning policies directly from offline expert conversations. Our key insight is to leverage the \\textbf{observed future} of each expert trajectory to derive dense, turn-level rewards that reflect expert long-horizon strategy, reducing policy learning to a sequence of supervised learning tasks that jointly enable LLMs to know \\textbf{what to ask} and \\textbf{when to stop}. To ensure the LLM-generated contents, such as reward fidelity and sampling quality, align with expectations, we further introduce an automated pipeline that calibrates the prompts with minimal human supervision.  Across multiple datasets and model scales, \\texttt{Learn-to-Ask} consistently improves proactive information-seeking behavior. We also report a large-scale real-world deployment where the trained agent surpasses an internal expert baseline under professional audit, which demonstrates the effectiveness of our framework and our rewards as a reality-validated proxy metric for LLM proactivity.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)은 강력한 passive responder이지만, 정보를 선제적으로 이끌어내는 능력, 즉 적절한 질문을 하고 적절한 시점에 멈추는 것을 학습하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. turn-level attribute를 최적화하거나 user simulator에 의존해 training trajectory를 생성하는 기존 접근법은 흔히 지속적인 reality gap에 직면한다. 우리는 offline expert conversation에서 직접 proactive questioning policy를 학습하는 simulator-free framework인 \\texttt{Learn-to-Ask}를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 각 expert trajectory의 \\textbf{observed future}를 활용해 expert의 long-horizon strategy를 반영하는 dense한 turn-level reward를 도출하고, 이를 통해 policy learning을 \\textbf{무엇을 물을지}와 \\textbf{언제 멈출지}를 LLM이 함께 익히도록 하는 일련의 supervised learning task로 환원하는 것이다. reward fidelity와 sampling quality와 같은 LLM-generated content가 기대에 부합하도록, 우리는 최소한의 human supervision으로 prompt를 보정하는 automated pipeline도 추가로 도입한다. 여러 dataset과 model scale 전반에서 \\texttt{Learn-to-Ask}는 proactive information-seeking behavior를 일관되게 개선한다. 또한 우리는 실제 대규모 배포 사례를 보고하며, 학습된 agent가 professional audit에서 내부 expert baseline을 능가함을 보여준다. 이는 본 framework의 효과성과, LLM proactivity의 reality-validated proxy metric으로서의 reward의 유용성을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61864","en":"Editable Proof Sketch for Automated Theorem Proving","ko":"자동 정리 증명을 위한 편집 가능한 Proof Sketch","authors":"Zikai Xiao, Hanzheng Wang, Meng-Hao Guo, Shi-min Hu, Shing-Tung Yau","pos":"#909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mI3K0e1KsN","abs":"<p>As large language models (LLMs) improve in mathematical reasoning and formal understanding, a promising approach for automated theorem proving (ATP) is to enable LLMs construct proof sketches, which plan a high-level proof strategy and decompose complex theorems into independently provable subgoals. However, most existing proof sketches are immutable. As a result, any revision typically requires rebuilding the entire sketch, which discards already proved subgoals and  bring additional cost. In this paper, we address this limitation by introducing EditableSketch, an editable proof-sketch structure that supports in-place edits for error correction and further subgoal decomposition while preserving previously proved subgoals. Building on EditableSketch, we introduce SketchRefine, a proof-generation framework for ATP by iteratively refining proof sketches through localized, incremental edits. Experiments show that our method not only reduces the cost of the proof process, but also achieves superior performance. For example, our method realizes 76.0% pass rate on FormalMath-Lite (+14.1\\% vs. DeepSeek-Prover-V2-671B). Meanwhile, compared with Hilbert, our method significantly reduces token overhead while achieving comparable performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model (LLM)이 수학적 추론과 formal understanding에서 향상됨에 따라, automated theorem proving (ATP)을 위한 유망한 접근법은 LLM이 proof sketch를 구성하도록 하는 것이다. 이는 고수준의 proof strategy를 계획하고 복잡한 theorem을 독립적으로 증명 가능한 subgoal로 분해한다. 그러나 기존의 대부분의 proof sketch는 불변적이다. 그 결과, 어떤 수정이든 일반적으로 전체 sketch를 다시 작성해야 하며, 이미 증명된 subgoal은 버려지고 추가 비용이 발생한다. 본 논문에서는 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 오류 수정과 추가 subgoal 분해를 위해 in-place edit를 지원하면서도 이전에 증명된 subgoal은 보존하는 editable proof-sketch 구조인 EditableSketch를 도입한다. EditableSketch를 바탕으로, 우리는 localized하고 incremental한 edit를 통해 proof sketch를 반복적으로 정제하는 ATP용 proof-generation framework인 SketchRefine을 제안한다. 실험 결과, 우리의 방법은 proof process의 비용을 줄일 뿐만 아니라 우수한 성능도 달성한다. 예를 들어, 우리의 방법은 FormalMath-Lite에서 76.0% pass rate를 달성했으며(+14.1\\% vs. DeepSeek-Prover-V2-671B), 동시에 Hilbert와 비교했을 때 token overhead를 크게 줄이면서도 비슷한 성능을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"65622","en":"CVE-Factory: Scaling Expert-Level Agentic Tasks for Code Security Vulnerability","ko":"CVE-Factory: 코드 보안 취약점을 위한 전문가 수준 에이전트 작업 확장","authors":"Xianzhen Luo, Jingyuan Zhang, Shiqi Zhou, JinYang Huang, Chuan Xiao, Qingfu Zhu, Zhiyuan Ma, YUE XING, Yang Yue, WencongZeng, Wanxiang Che","pos":"#910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BkMSFFtm5M","abs":"<p>Evaluating and improving the security capabilities of code agents requires high-quality, executable vulnerability tasks. However, existing works rely on costly, unscalable manual reproduction and suffer from outdated data distributions. To address these, we present CVE-Factory, the first multi-agent framework to achieve expert-level quality in automatically transforming sparse CVE metadata into fully executable agentic tasks. Cross-validation against human expert reproductions shows that CVE-Factory achieves 95\\% solution correctness and 96\\% environment fidelity, confirming its expert-level quality. It is also evaluated on the latest realistic vulnerabilities and achieves a 66.2\\% verified success. This automation enables two downstream contributions. First, we construct LiveCVEBench, a continuously updated benchmark of 190 tasks spanning 14 languages and 153 repositories that captures emerging threats including AI-tooling vulnerabilities. Second, we synthesize over 1,000 executable training environments, the first large-scale scaling of agentic tasks in code security.  Fine-tuned Qwen3-32B improves from 5.3\\% to 35.8\\% on LiveCVEBench, surpassing Claude 4.5 Sonnet, with gains generalizing to Terminal Bench (12.5\\% to 31.3\\%). We open-source all code, data, and models.</p>"},{"id":"62968","en":"CRAMER: Control via Request-Aware Masking for Editing Recommenders","ko":"CRAMER: 추천 시스템 편집을 위한 Request-Aware Masking 기반 제어","authors":"Zhiyuan Su, Naihe Feng, Zhen (Luther) Qin, Ga Wu","pos":"#911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bNL5b87dVr","abs":"<p>Sequential recommendation models, while powerful, have limited flexibility in responding to immediate user requests, making it difficult to adapt their recommendations to the user's timely interests. Unfortunately, existing user request adaptation methods often incur high computational overhead due to either 1) retraining the entire backbone network or 2) leveraging the inference ability of large language models (a.k.a. prompt engineering), limiting their applicability in large-scale recommendation services. This paper presents <strong>C</strong>ontrol via <strong>R</strong>equest-<strong>A</strong>ware <strong>M</strong>asking for <strong>E</strong>diting <strong>R</strong>ecommenders (<strong>CRAMER</strong>), a framework that takes users' natural-language requests to immediately change sequential recommendation models' behavior. Specifically, inspired by the model control theory, CRAMER treats user requests as control signals to modulate frozen backbone parameters through masking, achieving instant adaptation to diverse requests while avoiding costly retraining. Experiments on multiple large-scale benchmark datasets show that CRAMER outperforms four state-of-the-art request-aware baselines across multiple recommendation metrics while achieving minimal overhead. Moreover, the proposed framework exhibits enhanced controllability and cross-domain adaptability, establishing a new paradigm for request-aware sequential recommendation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Sequential recommendation 모델은 강력하지만, 즉각적인 사용자 요청에 대응하는 유연성이 제한되어 있어 사용자의 시의적절한 관심사에 맞게 추천을 조정하기 어렵다. 안타깝게도 기존의 user request adaptation 방법은 1) 전체 backbone network를 재학습하거나 2) large language model의 inference 능력, 즉 prompt engineering, 을 활용해야 하므로 계산 오버헤드가 크며, 그 결과 대규모 recommendation 서비스에 적용하기 어렵다. 이 논문은 사용자의 자연어 요청을 받아 sequential recommendation 모델의 동작을 즉시 변경하는 <strong>C</strong>ontrol via <strong>R</strong>equest-<strong>A</strong>ware <strong>M</strong>asking for <strong>E</strong>diting <strong>R</strong>ecommenders (<strong>CRAMER</strong>)를 제안한다. 구체적으로, model control theory에서 영감을 받아 CRAMER는 사용자 요청을 control signal로 간주하고 masking을 통해 고정된 backbone parameter를 조절함으로써, 비용이 큰 재학습을 피하면서 다양한 요청에 즉시 적응한다. 여러 대규모 benchmark dataset에 대한 실험 결과, CRAMER는 최소한의 오버헤드만으로 여러 recommendation metric에서 최첨단 request-aware baseline 4개를 능가한다. 또한 제안한 framework는 향상된 controllability와 cross-domain adaptability를 보여 주어, request-aware sequential recommendation을 위한 새로운 패러다임을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"63632","en":"CALM Before the STORM: Unlocking Native Reasoning for Optimization Modeling","ko":"CALM이 STORM 전에: 최적화 모델링을 위한 native reasoning 활성화","authors":"Zhengyang Tang, Zihan Ye, Chenyu Huang, Xuhan Huang, Chengpeng Li, Sihang Li, Guanhua CHEN, Ming Yan, Zizhuo Wang, Hongyuan Zha, Dayiheng Liu, Benyou Wang","pos":"#912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VFZWSzWgtS","abs":"<p>Large Reasoning Models (LRMs) have demonstrated strong capabilities in complex multi-step reasoning, opening new opportunities for automating optimization modeling. However, existing domain adaptation methods, originally designed for earlier instruction-tuned models, often fail to exploit the advanced reasoning patterns of modern LRMs --- In particular, we show that direct fine-tuning on traditional <em>non-reflective</em> datasets leads to limited gains. To fully leverage LRMs' inherent reasoning abilities, we propose <strong>CALM</strong> (<em>Corrective Adaptation with Lightweight Modification</em>), a framework that progressively refines LRMs within their native reasoning modes for optimization modeling tasks. In CALM, an expert intervener identifies reasoning flaws and provides concise corrective hints, which the LRM incorporates to produce improved reasoning trajectories. These interventions modify fewer than 2.6\\% of generated tokens, but generate high-quality data for soft adaptation through supervised fine-tuning. The adapted model is then further improved through reinforcement learning. Building on CALM, we develop <strong>STORM</strong> (<em>Smart Thinking Optimization Reasoning Model</em>), a 4B-parameter LRM that achieves a new state-of-the-art average accuracy of 68.9\\% across five popular optimization modeling benchmarks, matching the performance of a 671B LRM. These results demonstrate that dynamic, hint-based data synthesis both preserves and amplifies the native reasoning patterns of modern LRMs, offering a more effective and scalable path towards expert-level performance on challenging optimization modeling tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Reasoning Models (LRMs)는 복잡한 다단계 reasoning에서 강한 능력을 보여 주며, optimization modeling의 자동화를 위한 새로운 기회를 열었다. 그러나 초기 instruction-tuned model을 위해 설계된 기존의 domain adaptation method는 현대 LRMs의 고급 reasoning pattern을 충분히 활용하지 못하는 경우가 많다. 특히, 전통적인 <em>non-reflective</em> dataset으로 직접 fine-tuning하면 향상 폭이 제한적임을 보인다. LRMs가 본래 지닌 reasoning 능력을 최대한 활용하기 위해, 우리는 optimization modeling task에서 네이티브 reasoning mode 내에서 LRMs를 점진적으로 정제하는 프레임워크인 <strong>CALM</strong> (<em>Corrective Adaptation with Lightweight Modification</em>)을 제안한다. CALM에서 expert intervener는 reasoning의 결함을 식별하고 간결한 corrective hint를 제공하며, LRM은 이를 반영해 더 나은 reasoning trajectory를 생성한다. 이러한 개입은 생성 토큰의 2.6\\% 미만만을 수정하지만, supervised fine-tuning을 통한 soft adaptation을 위해 고품질 데이터를 만들어 낸다. 이후 적응된 모델은 reinforcement learning을 통해 추가로 개선된다. CALM을 기반으로, 우리는 4B parameter를 가진 LRM인 <strong>STORM</strong> (<em>Smart Thinking Optimization Reasoning Model</em>)을 개발했으며, 이는 5개의 인기 있는 optimization modeling benchmark에서 68.9\\%의 새로운 최고 평균 정확도를 달성하여 671B LRM의 성능과 맞먹는다. 이 결과는 동적이고 hint 기반의 data synthesis가 현대 LRMs의 네이티브 reasoning pattern을 보존하는 동시에 증폭시켜, 까다로운 optimization modeling task에서 expert 수준의 성능으로 가는 더 효과적이고 확장 가능한 경로를 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66362","en":"AgentSelect: Benchmark for Narrative Query-to-Agent Recommendation","ko":"AgentSelect: 서술형 쿼리-에이전트 추천 벤치마크","authors":"Yunxiao Shi, Wujiang Xu, Tingwei Chen, Haoning Shang, Ling Yang, Yunfeng Wan, Zhuo Cao, Xing Zi, Dimitris Metaxas, Min Xu","pos":"#914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4M5Kj2UqaM","abs":"<p>LLM agents are rapidly becoming the practical interface for task automation, yet the ecosystem lacks a principled way to \\emph{choose} among an exploding space of deployable configurations. Existing LLM leaderboards and tool/agent benchmarks evaluate components in isolation and remain fragmented across tasks, metrics, and candidate pools, leaving a critical research gap: there is little \\emph{query-conditioned} supervision for learning to recommend end-to-end agent configurations that couple a backbone model with a toolkit. We address this gap with \\methodname, a benchmark that reframes agent selection as narrative query-to-agent recommendation over capability profiles   and systematically converts heterogeneous evaluation artifacts into unified, positive-only interaction data. \\methodname comprises 111,179 queries, 107,721 deployable agents, and 251,103 interaction records aggregated from 40+ sources, spanning LLM-only, toolkit-only, and compositional agents. Our analyses reveal a regime shift from dense head reuse to long-tail, near one-off supervision, where popularity-based CF/GNN methods become fragile and content-aware capability matching is essential. We further show that Part~III synthesized compositional interactions are learnable, induce capability-sensitive behavior under controlled counterfactual edits, and improve coverage over realistic   compositions; models trained on \\methodname also transfer to a public agent marketplace (MuleRun), yielding consistent gains on an unseen catalog. Overall, \\methodname provides the first unified data and evaluation infrastructure for agent recommendation, which establishes a reproducible foundation to study and accelerate the emerging agent ecosystem. \\footnote{\\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/AgentMatch-F950}}</p>"},{"id":"64068","en":"RefChess: Monte-Carlo Move Selection for Zero-Shot Referring Image Segmentation","ko":"RefChess: 제로샷 참조 이미지 분할을 위한 몬테카를로 수 선택","authors":"Shiyan Tong, Jinxia Zhang, Zhiyuan Wang, Hao Tian, YingYing Wang, Kanjian Zhang, Haikun Wei","pos":"#1001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RESRoG7nvd","abs":"<p>Recent advances in zero-shot referring image segmentation (RIS), driven by foundation models such as SAM and CLIP, have improved cross-modal alignment between visual regions and natural language expressions. Nevertheless, selecting the correct segmentation proposal remains challenging, as existing methods typically rely on independent proposal scoring and lack contextual reasoning among visually similar candidates. To address this limitation, we propose RefChess, a training-free framework that reformulates proposal selection as a decision-making problem under contextual perturbations rather than a single-step ranking task. RefChess models each proposal as a candidate chess move and applies Monte-Carlo Tree Search to evaluate its robustness by simulating interactions with competing regions, guided by a stability-aware reward that integrates language decomposition, vision–language similarity, object-centric cues, and spatial guidance signals. Experimental results on standard RIS benchmarks indicate that this decision-centric formulation leads to consistent improvements in robustness and referring segmentation performance. Code is available at \\url{anonymous URL}.</p>","absKo":"<p>SAM과 CLIP 같은 foundation model에 의해 주도된 최근 zero-shot referring image segmentation(RIS)의 발전은 시각적 영역과 자연어 표현 사이의 cross-modal alignment를 향상시켰다. 그럼에도 불구하고 올바른 segmentation proposal을 선택하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 기존 방법은 일반적으로 독립적인 proposal scoring에 의존하며, 시각적으로 유사한 후보들 사이의 contextual reasoning이 부족하기 때문이다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 RefChess를 제안한다. RefChess는 proposal 선택을 단일 단계의 ranking task가 아니라 contextual perturbation 하에서의 의사결정 문제로 재정식화하는 training-free framework이다. RefChess는 각 proposal을 후보 체스 수로 모델링하고, language decomposition, vision–language similarity, object-centric cue, spatial guidance signal을 통합하는 stability-aware reward를 이용해 경쟁 region과의 상호작용을 시뮬레이션함으로써 그 강건성을 평가하기 위해 Monte-Carlo Tree Search를 적용한다. 표준 RIS benchmark 실험 결과, 이러한 decision-centric formulation이 강건성과 referring segmentation 성능 모두에서 일관된 향상을 이끈다는 것을 보여준다. 코드는 \\url{anonymous URL}에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"68784","en":"Repositioning the Subject within Image","ko":"이미지 내 대상 재배치","authors":"Yikai Wang, Chenjie Cao, Ke Fan, Qiaole Dong, Yifan Li, Xiangyang Xue, Yanwei Fu","pos":"#1002","abs":"<p>Current image manipulation primarily centers on static manipulation, such as replacing specific regions within an image or altering its overall style. In this paper, we introduce an innovative dynamic manipulation task, subject repositioning. This task involves relocating a user-specified subject to a desired position while preserving the image's fidelity. Our research reveals that the fundamental sub-tasks of subject repositioning, which include filling the void left by the repositioned subject, reconstructing obscured portions of the subject and blending the subject to be consistent with surrounding areas, can be effectively reformulated as a unified, prompt-guided inpainting task. Consequently, we can employ a single diffusion generative model to address these sub-tasks using various task prompts learned through our proposed task inversion technique. Additionally, we integrate pre-processing and post-processing techniques to further enhance the quality of subject repositioning. These elements together form our SEgment-gEnerate-and-bLEnd (SEELE) framework. To assess SEELE's effectiveness in subject repositioning, we assemble a real-world subject repositioning dataset called ReS. Results of SEELE on ReS demonstrate its efficacy. Code and ReS dataset are available at https://yikai-wang.github.io/seele/.</p>"},{"id":"62181","en":"SphericalDreamer: Generating Navigable Immersive 3D Worlds with Panorama Fusion","ko":"SphericalDreamer: 파노라마 융합으로 탐색 가능한 몰입형 3D 월드 생성","authors":"Antoine Schnepf, Karim Kassab, Flavian Vasile, Andrew Comport","pos":"#1006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iyeNyj06Nt","abs":"The generation of immersive and navigable 3D environments is increasingly prevalent with the growing adoption of virtual reality and 3D content. However, recent methods face a fundamental limitation: they cannot produce 3D worlds that simultaneously (i) are navigable over long-range spatial extents and (ii) cover the complete omnidirectional field of view ($360^\\circ$ horizontally and $180^\\circ$ vertically). To address this challenge, we introduce SphericalDreamer, a method for generating fully immersive and long-range 3D environments from textual prompts. Our approach is built on the generation of multiple panoramic images, which are subsequently lifted into 3D and fused together while maintaining visual and geometric consistency. SphericalDreamer produces highly detailed, fully immersive 3D environments, while substantially improving scale and navigability compared to prior approaches.","absKo":"몰입형이고 탐색 가능한 3D environment의 생성은 virtual reality와 3D content의 채택이 증가함에 따라 점점 더 보편화되고 있다. 그러나 최근 방법들은 본질적인 한계에 직면한다. 즉, (i) 장거리 공간 범위에서 탐색 가능하면서도 (ii) 완전한 omnidirectional field of view(가로 360° 및 세로 180°)를 모두 포괄하는 3D world를 생성하지 못한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 text prompt로부터 완전 몰입형이며 장거리 3D environment를 생성하는 방법인 SphericalDreamer를 소개한다. 우리의 접근법은 여러 panoramic image를 생성한 뒤, 이를 3D로 lift하고 visual 및 geometric consistency를 유지한 채 하나로 융합하는 방식에 기반한다. SphericalDreamer는 매우 세밀하고 완전 몰입적인 3D environment를 생성하며, 이전 접근법에 비해 scale과 navigability를 크게 향상시킨다."},{"id":"64354","en":"Spiral RoPE: Rotate Your Rotary Positional Embeddings in the 2D Plane","ko":"Spiral RoPE: 2D 평면에서 회전 위치 임베딩 회전시키기","authors":"Haoyu Liu, Sucheng Ren, Tingyu Zhu, Peng Wang, Cihang Xie, Alan Yuille, Zeyu Zheng, Feng Wang","pos":"#1007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ORwyqAzROx","abs":"<p>Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE) is the de facto positional encoding in large language models due to its ability to encode relative positions and support length extrapolation. When adapted to vision transformers, the standard axial formulation decomposes two-dimensional spatial positions into horizontal and vertical components, implicitly restricting positional encoding to axis-aligned directions. We identify this directional constraint as a fundamental limitation of the standard axial 2D RoPE, which hinders the modeling of oblique spatial relationships that naturally exist in natural images. To overcome this limitation, we propose Spiral RoPE, a simple yet effective extension that enables multi-directional positional encoding by partitioning embedding channels into multiple groups associated with uniformly distributed directions. Each group is rotated according to the projection of the patch position onto its corresponding direction, allowing spatial relationships to be encoded beyond the horizontal and vertical axes. Across a wide range of vision tasks including classification, segmentation, and generation, Spiral RoPE consistently improves performance. Qualitative analyzes of attention maps further show that Spiral RoPE exhibits more concentrated activations on semantically relevant objects and better respects local object boundaries, highlighting the importance of multi-directional positional encoding in vision transformers.</p>","absKo":"<p>Rotary Position Embedding(RoPE)은 상대적 위치를 인코딩하고 길이 외삽(length extrapolation)을 지원할 수 있다는 점에서 large language model의 사실상 표준 positional encoding입니다. 이를 vision transformer에 적용할 때, standard axial formulation은 2차원 공간 위치를 수평 및 수직 성분으로 분해하여 positional encoding을 축 정렬 방향(axis-aligned directions)으로 암묵적으로 제한합니다. 우리는 이러한 방향성 제약을 standard axial 2D RoPE의 근본적인 한계로 식별하며, 이는 자연 이미지에 본질적으로 존재하는 사선 방향 공간 관계를 모델링하는 것을 방해합니다. 이 한계를 극복하기 위해 우리는 embedding channel을 균일하게 분포된 여러 방향과 연관된 여러 그룹으로 분할하여 다방향 positional encoding을 가능하게 하는 간단하면서도 효과적인 확장인 Spiral RoPE를 제안합니다. 각 그룹은 패치 위치의 해당 방향으로의 projection에 따라 회전하며, 이를 통해 수평 및 수직 축을 넘어선 공간 관계를 인코딩할 수 있습니다. classification, segmentation, generation을 포함한 다양한 vision task 전반에서 Spiral RoPE는 일관되게 성능을 향상시킵니다. attention map에 대한 정성적 분석은 Spiral RoPE가 의미적으로 관련 있는 객체에서 더 집중된 activation을 보이고 local object boundary를 더 잘 따름을 추가로 보여주며, vision transformer에서 multi-directional positional encoding의 중요성을 부각합니다.</p>"},{"id":"65184","en":"VIP: Visual-guided Prompt Evolution for Efficient Dense Vision-Language Inference","ko":"VIP: 효율적 밀집 Vision-Language 추론을 위한 시각 기반 프롬프트 진화","authors":"Hao Zhu, Shuo Jin, Wenbin Liao, Jiayu Xiao, Yan Zhu, Siyue Yu, Feng Dai","pos":"#1009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=G1BYq33C3G","abs":"<p>Pursuing training-free open-vocabulary semantic segmentation in an efficient and generalizable manner remains challenging due to the deep-seated spatial bias in CLIP. To overcome the limitations of existing solutions, this work moves beyond the CLIP-based paradigm and harnesses the recent spatially-aware dino.txt framework to facilitate more efficient and high-quality dense prediction. While dino.txt exhibits robust spatial awareness, we find that the semantic ambiguity of text queries gives rise to severe mismatch within its dense cross-modal interactions. To address this, we introduce VIsual-guided Prompt evolution (VIP) to rectify the semantic expressiveness of text queries in dino.txt, unleashing its potential for fine-grained object perception. Towards this end, VIP integrates alias expansion with a visual-guided distillation mechanism to mine valuable semantic cues, which are robustly aggregated in a saliency-aware manner to yield a high-fidelity prediction. Extensive evaluations demonstrate that VIP: I) surpasses the top-leading methods by 1.4%~8.4\\% average mIoU, II) generalizes well to diverse challenging domains, and III) requires marginal inference time and memory overhead. Our code will be released to foster future research.</p>","absKo":"<p>CLIP에 깊이 뿌리내린 spatial bias 때문에 training-free open-vocabulary semantic segmentation을 효율적이고 일반화 가능하게 수행하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 기존 해법의 한계를 극복하기 위해, 이 연구는 CLIP 기반 패러다임을 넘어 최근의 spatially-aware dino.txt framework를 활용하여 더 효율적이고 고품질의 dense prediction을 가능하게 한다. dino.txt는 강한 spatial awareness를 보이지만, text query의 semantic ambiguity가 dense cross-modal interaction 내부에서 심각한 mismatch를 유발한다는 사실을 확인했다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 dino.txt에서 text query의 semantic expressiveness를 교정하고 fine-grained object perception의 잠재력을 끌어내기 위한 VIsual-guided Prompt evolution (VIP)을 도입한다. 이를 위해 VIP는 alias expansion과 visual-guided distillation mechanism을 통합하여 유용한 semantic cue를 발굴하며, 이를 saliency-aware 방식으로 견고하게 집계해 고충실도 prediction을 생성한다. 광범위한 평가 결과, VIP는 I) top-leading method보다 평균 mIoU 기준 1.4%~8.4\\% 향상, II) 다양한 challenging domain에 대해 우수한 generalization, III) 최소한의 inference time과 memory overhead만을 요구함을 보인다. 향후 연구를 촉진하기 위해 코드를 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65595","en":"VividCam: Learning Unconventional Camera Motions from Virtual Synthetic Videos","ko":"VividCam: 가상 합성 영상으로부터 비관습적 카메라 움직임 학습하기","authors":"Qiucheng Wu, Handong Zhao, Zhixin Shu, Jing Shi, Yang Zhang, Shiyu Chang","pos":"#1010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=C0WnTbVSEs","abs":"<p>Although recent text-to-video generative models are getting more capable of following external camera controls, imposed by either text descriptions or camera trajectories, they still struggle to generalize to unconventional camera motions, which is crucial in creating truly original and artistic videos. The challenge lies in the difficulty of finding sufficient training videos with the intended uncommon camera motions. To address this challenge, we propose VividCam, a training paradigm that enables diffusion models to learn complex camera motions from synthetic videos, releasing the reliance on collecting realistic training videos. VividCam incorporates multiple disentanglement strategies that isolates camera motion learning from synthetic appearance artifacts, ensuring more robust motion representation and mitigating domain shift. We demonstrate that our design synthesizes a wide range of precisely controlled and complex camera motions using surprisingly simple synthetic data. Notably, this synthetic data often consists of basic geometries within a low-poly 3D scene and can be efficiently rendered by engines like Unity. Our video results can be found in https://anonymoususers196.github.io/VividCamDemo/ .</p>"},{"id":"63486","en":"WeatherSyn: An Instruction Tuning MLLM For Weather Forecasting Report Generation","ko":"WeatherSyn: 기상 예보 보고서 생성을 위한 명령 튜닝 MLLM","authors":"Zinan Zheng, Yang Liu, Nuo Chen, Juepeng Zheng, Hong Cheng, Jia Li","pos":"#1011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WlScVvMwpB","abs":"<p>Accurate weather forecast reporting enables individuals and communities to better plan daily activities, agricultural operations, and transportation. However, the current reporting process primarily relies on manual analysis of multi-source data, which often leads to information overload and reduced efficiency. With the rapid advancement of multimodal large language models (MLLMs), leveraging data-driven models to analyze and generate reports in the weather forecasting domain remains largely underexplored. In this work, we propose the Weather Forecasting Report (WFR) task and construct the first instruction-tuning dataset for this task, named WSInstruct, which covers 31 cities in America and 8 weather aspects. Based on this corpus, we develop the first model, WeatherSyn, specialized in generating weather forecast reports. Evaluation across multiple metrics on our dataset shows that WeatherSyn consistently outperforms leading closed-source MLLMs, particularly on structurally complex weather aspects. We further analyze its performance across diverse geographic regions and weather aspects. WeatherSyn demonstrates strong transferability across different regions, highlighting its zero-shot generalization capability. WeatherSyn offers valuable insight for developing MLLMs specialized in weather report generation.</p>","absKo":"<p>정확한 weather forecast report는 개인과 지역사회가 일상 활동, 농업 운영, 교통을 더 잘 계획할 수 있게 해준다. 그러나 현재의 보고 과정은 주로 multi-source data에 대한 수작업 분석에 의존하며, 이는 종종 정보 과부하와 효율 저하로 이어진다. multimodal large language model(MLLM)의 빠른 발전에도 불구하고, weather forecasting 도메인에서 데이터 기반 모델을 활용해 보고서를 분석하고 생성하는 연구는 여전히 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 Weather Forecasting Report(WFR) task를 제안하고, 미국 31개 도시와 8개 weather aspect를 포괄하는 이 task를 위한 최초의 instruction-tuning dataset인 WSInstruct를 구축한다. 이 말뭉치를 기반으로, 우리는 weather forecast report 생성에 특화된 최초의 모델 WeatherSyn을 개발한다. 우리 dataset에서 여러 metric으로 평가한 결과, WeatherSyn은 특히 구조적으로 복잡한 weather aspect에서 선도적인 closed-source MLLM을 일관되게 능가한다. 또한 서로 다른 지리적 지역과 weather aspect 전반에서의 성능을 추가로 분석한다. WeatherSyn은 지역 간 강한 transferability를 보이며, zero-shot generalization capability를 강조한다. WeatherSyn은 weather report generation에 특화된 MLLM 개발을 위한 유용한 통찰을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63024","en":"PixCLIP: Towards Fine-grained Vision-Language Understanding via Any-granularity Pixel-Text Alignment","ko":"PixCLIP: 임의 해상도 Pixel-Text Alignment을 통한 정밀 Vision-Language 이해","authors":"YiCheng Xiao, Yu Chen, Hao-Xuan Ma, Jiale Hong, Caorui Li, Lingxiang Wu, Haiyun Guo, Jinqiao Wang","pos":"#1100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ao1SgPdAQm","abs":"<p>While CLIP has achieved strong performance across vision–language tasks, fine-grained image–text alignment remains challenging. Recent efforts improve textual granularity by leveraging long, detailed descriptions and replacing CLIP’s text encoder with LLM, but often overlook the visual-side bottleneck: achieving finer alignment requires region- and pixel-level visual grounding, not just finer text. To address this issue, we propose PixCLIP, a framework that jointly enhances both sides by accommodating visual prompt regions and long-form text within a unified training objective. Firstly, to support training at this granularity, we develop an automated annotation pipeline that produces long-form descriptions with pixel-level localization, and use it to construct LongGRIT, a high-quality dataset with nearly 1.5M samples. Furthermore, we introduce a three-branch pixel–text alignment framework that aligns image regions with corresponding textual descriptions across multiple granularities. Experiments show that PixCLIP achieves state-of-the-art performance on pixel- and region-level alignment tasks while preserving strong results on standard global image–text retrieval benchmarks, even with arbitrarily shaped region prompts and long compositional texts.</p>","absKo":"<p>CLIP이 vision-language task 전반에서 강한 성능을 보였지만, 세밀한 image-text alignment는 여전히 어렵다. 최근 연구들은 긴 상세 설명을 활용하고 CLIP의 text encoder를 LLM으로 대체함으로써 텍스트의 granularity를 높였지만, 시각 측면의 병목, 즉 더 정밀한 alignment를 위해서는 더 세밀한 텍스트만이 아니라 region-level 및 pixel-level visual grounding이 필요하다는 점을 종종 간과한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 PixCLIP을 제안한다. PixCLIP은 단일한 training objective 안에서 visual prompt region과 long-form text를 함께 수용함으로써 양쪽을 모두 향상시키는 framework다. 먼저, 이러한 granularity 수준의 학습을 지원하기 위해 우리는 pixel-level localization이 포함된 long-form description을 생성하는 자동 annotation pipeline을 개발했고, 이를 사용해 약 150만 개 샘플로 이루어진 고품질 데이터셋 LongGRIT을 구축했다. 또한 여러 granularity에 걸쳐 image region을 대응하는 텍스트 설명과 정렬하는 three-branch pixel-text alignment framework를 도입한다. 실험 결과, PixCLIP은 임의의 형태를 가진 region prompt와 긴 compositional text가 주어져도, 표준 global image-text retrieval benchmark에서 강한 결과를 유지하면서 pixel-level 및 region-level alignment task에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"62090","en":"OpenGPT-4o-Image: A Comprehensive Dataset for Advanced Image Generation and Editing","ko":"OpenGPT-4o-Image: 고급 이미지 생성과 편집을 위한 종합 데이터셋","authors":"zhihong Chen, Xuehai Bai, Yang Shi, Chaoyou Fu, Huanyu Zhang, Haotian Wang, Xiaoyan Sun, Zhang Zhang, Liang Wang, Yuanxing Zhang, Pengfei Wan, Yi-Fan Zhang","pos":"#1101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=juGAf5Y7V2","abs":"<p>The performance of unified multimodal models for image generation and editing is fundamentally constrained by the quality and comprehensiveness of their training data. While existing datasets have covered basic tasks like style transfer and simple object manipulation, they often lack the systematic structure and challenging scenarios required for real-world applications. To address this bottleneck, we introduce \\textbf{OpenGPT-4o-Image}, a large-scale dataset constructed using a novel methodology that combines hierarchical task taxonomy with automated data generation. Our taxonomy not only includes fundamental capabilities such as {text rendering} and {style control} but also introduces highly practical yet challenging categories like \\textbf{scientific imagery} for physics/chemistry illustrations and \\textbf{complex instruction editing} requiring simultaneous execution of multiple operations. Through an automated pipeline leveraging structured resource pools and GPT-4o, we generate 80k high-quality instruction-image pairs with controlled diversity, covering 11 major domains and 51 subtasks. Extensive experiments show that fine-tuning leading models on our dataset achieves significant performance gains across multiple benchmarks, with improvements of up to 18% on editing tasks (UniWorld-V1 on ImgEdit-Bench) and 13% on generation tasks (Harmon on GenEval). Our work demonstrates that systematic data construction is key to advancing multimodal AI capabilities.</p>","absKo":"<p>이미지 생성과 편집을 위한 unified multimodal model의 성능은 근본적으로 학습 데이터의 품질과 포괄성에 의해 제약된다. 기존 dataset은 style transfer나 단순 object manipulation 같은 기본 task를 다루어 왔지만, 실제 응용에 필요한 체계적인 구조와 도전적인 scenario는 종종 부족하다. 이러한 병목을 해결하기 위해 우리는 hierarchical task taxonomy와 automated data generation을 결합한 새로운 methodology로 구축한 대규모 dataset인 \\textbf{OpenGPT-4o-Image}를 제안한다. 우리의 taxonomy는 {text rendering}과 {style control} 같은 기본 capability뿐 아니라, 물리/화학 illustration을 위한 \\textbf{scientific imagery}와 여러 operation의 동시 실행이 필요한 \\textbf{complex instruction editing} 같은 매우 실용적이면서도 도전적인 category도 포함한다. structured resource pool과 GPT-4o를 활용하는 automated pipeline을 통해 우리는 제어된 다양성을 갖춘 8만 개의 고품질 instruction-image pair를 생성했으며, 11개 주요 domain과 51개 subtask를 포괄한다. 광범위한 실험 결과, 우리 dataset으로 leading model을 fine-tuning하면 여러 benchmark에서 유의미한 성능 향상을 달성하며, editing task에서는 최대 18%(ImgEdit-Bench에서 UniWorld-V1), generation task에서는 13%(GenEval에서 Harmon)까지 향상된다. 우리의 연구는 체계적인 data construction이 multimodal AI capability를 발전시키는 핵심임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63895","en":"ObjEmbed: Towards Universal Multimodal Object Embeddings","ko":"ObjEmbed: 범용 멀티모달 객체 embedding을 향하여","authors":"Shenghao Fu, Yukun Su, Fengyun Rao, Jing LYU, Xiaohua Xie, Wei-Shi Zheng","pos":"#1103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Sjbl4SueQS","abs":"<p>Aligning objects with corresponding textual descriptions is a fundamental challenge and a realistic requirement in vision-language understanding. While recent multimodal embedding models excel at global image-text alignment, they often struggle with fine-grained alignment between image regions and specific phrases. In this work, we present ObjEmbed, a novel MLLM embedding model that decomposes the input image into multiple regional embeddings, each corresponding to an individual object, along with global embeddings. It supports a wide range of visual understanding tasks like visual grounding, local image retrieval, and global image retrieval. ObjEmbed enjoys three key properties: (1) Object-Oriented Representation: It captures both semantic and spatial aspects of objects by generating two complementary embeddings for each region: an object embedding for semantic matching and an IoU embedding that predicts localization quality. The final object matching score combines semantic similarity with the predicted IoU, enabling more accurate retrieval. (2) Versatility: It seamlessly handles both region-level and image-level tasks. (3) Efficient Encoding: All objects in an image, along with the full image, are encoded in a single forward pass for high efficiency. Superior performance on 18 diverse benchmarks demonstrates its strong semantic discrimination. We will release the code, models, and data for future research.</p>","absKo":"<p>객체를 대응하는 텍스트 설명과 정렬하는 것은 vision-language understanding의 근본적인 과제이며, 현실적인 요구사항이기도 하다. 최근의 multimodal embedding model은 전역적인 image-text alignment에서는 뛰어나지만, 이미지 영역과 특정 구문 사이의 세밀한 정렬에서는 종종 어려움을 겪는다. 본 연구에서 우리는 입력 이미지를 여러 regional embedding으로 분해하고, 각 embedding이 개별 객체에 대응하도록 하면서 global embedding도 함께 제공하는 새로운 MLLM embedding model인 ObjEmbed를 제시한다. 이 모델은 visual grounding, local image retrieval, global image retrieval과 같은 다양한 visual understanding task를 지원한다. ObjEmbed는 세 가지 핵심 특성을 갖는다. (1) Object-Oriented Representation: 각 region에 대해 semantic matching을 위한 object embedding과 localization quality를 예측하는 IoU embedding이라는 두 가지 상보적 embedding을 생성함으로써 객체의 의미적, 공간적 측면을 모두 포착한다. 최종 object matching score는 semantic similarity와 예측된 IoU를 결합하여 더 정확한 retrieval을 가능하게 한다. (2) Versatility: region 수준과 image 수준 task를 모두 매끄럽게 처리한다. (3) Efficient Encoding: 한 번의 forward pass로 이미지 내 모든 객체와 전체 이미지를 함께 인코딩하여 높은 효율성을 제공한다. 18개의 다양한 benchmark에서 우수한 성능을 보여주며, 강력한 semantic discrimination을 입증한다. 우리는 향후 연구를 위해 코드, 모델, 데이터 를 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65288","en":"Neutral-Reference Prompting for Vision–Language Models","ko":"Vision–Language Model을 위한 중립 참조 프롬프팅","authors":"Senmao Tian, Xiang Wei, Shunli Zhang","pos":"#1104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=F5XJeuhwU7","abs":"<p>Efficient transfer learning of vision–language models (VLMs) commonly suffers from a Base–New Trade-off (BNT): improving performance on unseen (new) classes often degrades accuracy on known (base) classes. Addressing how to boost recognition of unseen classes without sacrificing known-class performance remains a central challenge. Existing work often simplistically attributes the BNT to overfitting on known classes. We observe an interesting phenomenon: VLMs frequently exhibit asymmetric confusion on certain downstream data, i.e., samples of class A are systematically mispredicted as class B, while the reverse confusion (B → A) rarely occurs. For known classes, this kind of bias can be mitigated by tuning using a cross-entropy loss, but for unseen classes, such pretraining-induced bias persists and harms generalization. Motivated by this, we propose NeRP, a plug-and-play prompting correction strategy that improves discrimination on unseen classes without modifying model parameters. NeRP leverages neutral text prompts and reference images to measure class-wise prior preferences along the pre-trained inter-class geometry, and combines them with the sample likelihood to obtain the model’s surrogate score. If, for a given sample, the prior strongly favors the current prediction while the observed evidence is clearly insufficient, we perform a local flip between easily confusable class pairs, thereby correcting prior-dominated mispredictions. Extensive experiments across multiple backbones and 15 few-shot and cross-domain benchmarks show that NeRP substantially improves accuracy on unseen classes while preserving known-class prediction performance.</p>"},{"id":"61153","en":"MLLM-4D: Towards Visual-based Spatial-Temporal Intelligence","ko":"MLLM-4D: 시각 기반 Spatio-Temporal Intelligence를 향하여","authors":"Xingyilang Yin, Chengzhengxu Li, Jiahao Chang, Chi-Man Pun, Xiaodong Cun","pos":"#1106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tBYIaHHTqq","abs":"<p>Humans are born with vision-based 4D spatial-temporal intelligence, which enables us to perceive and reason about the evolution of 3D space over time from purely visual inputs. Despite its importance, this capability remains a significant bottleneck for current multimodal large language models (MLLMs). To tackle this challenge, we introduce MLLM-4D, a comprehensive framework designed to bridge the gaps in training data curation and model post-training for spatiotemporal understanding and reasoning. On the data front, we develop a cost-efficient data curation pipeline that repurposes existing stereo video datasets into high-quality 4D spatiotemporal instructional data. This results in the MLLM4D-2M and MLLM4D-R1-30k datasets for Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) and Reinforcement Fine-Tuning (RFT), alongside MLLM4D-Bench for comprehensive evaluation. Regarding model training, our post-training strategy establishes a foundational 4D understanding via SFT and further catalyzes 4D reasoning capabilities by employing Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) with specialized Spatiotemporal Chain of Thought (ST-CoT) prompting and Spatiotemporal reward functions without involving the modification of architecture. Extensive experiments demonstrate that MLLM-4D achieves state-of-the-art spatial-temporal understanding and reasoning capabilities from purely 2D RGB inputs. Our project will be made publicly available.</p>","absKo":"인간은 vision-based 4D spatial-temporal intelligence를 타고나며, 이를 통해 순수한 visual input만으로 시간에 따른 3D space의 진화를 지각하고 추론할 수 있다. 이러한 중요성에도 불구하고, 이 능력은 현재 multimodal large language model(MLLM)의 주요 병목으로 남아 있다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 spatiotemporal understanding과 reasoning을 위한 training data curation과 model post-training의 격차를 메우도록 설계된 포괄적 framework인 MLLM-4D를 제안한다. 데이터 측면에서, 우리는 기존 stereo video dataset을 고품질 4D spatiotemporal instructional data로 재가공하는 비용 효율적인 data curation pipeline을 개발한다. 그 결과 Supervised Fine-Tuning(SFT)과 Reinforcement Fine-Tuning(RFT)을 위한 MLLM4D-2M 및 MLLM4D-R1-30k dataset과, 포괄적 평가를 위한 MLLM4D-Bench를 구축한다. 모델 학습 측면에서, 우리의 post-training 전략은 SFT를 통해 기본적인 4D 이해를 확립하고, architecture 수정 없이 specialized Spatiotemporal Chain of Thought(ST-CoT) prompting과 Spatiotemporal reward function을 사용한 Group Relative Policy Optimization(GRPO)을 통해 4D reasoning capability를 추가로 촉진한다. 광범위한 실험은 MLLM-4D가 순수한 2D RGB input으로부터 state-of-the-art spatial-temporal understanding과 reasoning capability를 달성함을 보여준다. 우리의 project는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65792","en":"GemDepth: Geometry-Embedded Features for 3D-Consistent Video Depth","ko":"GemDepth: 3D 일관성 영상 깊이를 위한 기하학 임베딩 특징","authors":"Yuecheng Liu, Junda Cheng, Longliang Liu, Wenjing Liao, Hanrui Cheng, Yuzhou Wang, Xin Yang","pos":"#1108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A5KwfEqWSu","abs":"<p>Video depth estimation extends monocular prediction into the temporal domain to ensure coherence. However, existing methods often suffer from spatial blurring in fine-detail regions and temporal inconsistencies. We argue that current approaches, which primarily rely on temporal smoothing via Transformers, struggle to maintain strict 3D geometric consistency—particularly under rotations or drastic view changes. To address this, we propose GemDepth, a framework built on the insight that an explicit awareness of camera motion and global 3D structure is a prerequisite for 3D consistency. Distinctively, GemDepth introduces a Geometry-Embedding Module (GEM) that predicts inter-frame camera poses to generate implicit geometric embeddings. This injection of motion priors equips the network with intrinsic 3D perception and alignment capabilities. Guided by these geometric cues, our Alternating Spatio-Temporal Transformer (ASTT) captures latent point-level correspondences to simultaneously enhance spatial precision for sharp details and enforce rigorous temporal consistency. Furthermore, GemDepth employs a data-efficient training strategy, effectively bridging the gap between high efficiency and robust geometric consistency. As shown in Fig.2, comprehensive evaluations demonstrate that GemDepth achieves state-of-the-art performance across multiple datasets, particularly in complex dynamic scenarios.</p>"},{"id":"61808","en":"G$^2$TAM: Geometry Grounded Track Anything Model","ko":"G$^2$TAM: 기하 기반 Track Anything Model","authors":"Chenming Zhu, Peizhou Cao, Jingli Lin, Wenbo Hu, Yunlong Ran, Tai Wang, Jiangmiao Pang, Xihui Liu","pos":"#1109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mkguKl16Ou","abs":"Human spatial understanding arises from jointly perceiving geometry and semantics, enabling consistent object identification and localization across viewpoints and time. Current video segmentation models depend on explicit object appearance memory banks for instance tracking, yet they remain vulnerable to large viewpoint changes and long-term occlusions. Leveraging the spatial consistency afforded by modern feed-forward 3D reconstruction models, we propose the Geometry Grounded Tracking Anything Model (G$^2$TAM), a unified framework for promptable instance tracking in 3D using only unordered RGB images or videos. G$^2$TAM employs spatially aligned geometric representations as implicit memory, ensuring stable instance identity and localization across frames and views. At its core is a cross-modal spatial encoder that integrates visual and textual prompts into a shared geometric space, enabling end-to-end spatial reconstruction and instance-consistent mask prediction. To support training and evaluation, we construct InsTrack, a large-scale dataset with a dedicated validation split for benchmarking. Extensive experiments show that G$^2$TAM delivers strong cross-view consistency, promptable instance spatial tracking, video object segmentation, and spatial reconstruction, establishing a foundation for interactive, geometry-grounded spatial reasoning.","absKo":"인간의 공간 이해는 기하와 의미를 함께 지각함으로써 형성되며, 이를 통해 시점과 시간을 가로질러 일관된 객체 식별과 localization이 가능해진다. 현재의 video segmentation 모델은 instance tracking을 위해 명시적인 object appearance memory bank에 의존하지만, 큰 시점 변화와 장기 occlusion에는 여전히 취약하다. 현대의 feed-forward 3D reconstruction 모델이 제공하는 공간적 일관성을 활용하여, 우리는 Geometry Grounded Tracking Anything Model (G$^2$TAM)을 제안한다. 이는 순서가 없는 RGB image 또는 video만 사용하여 3D에서 promptable instance tracking을 수행하는 통합 프레임워크이다. G$^2$TAM은 공간적으로 정렬된 geometric representation을 암묵적 memory로 사용하여, frame과 view 전반에 걸쳐 안정적인 instance identity와 localization을 보장한다. 그 핵심에는 시각 및 텍스트 prompt를 공유 geometric space에 통합하는 cross-modal spatial encoder가 있으며, 이를 통해 end-to-end spatial reconstruction과 instance-consistent mask prediction을 가능하게 한다. 학습과 평가를 지원하기 위해, 우리는 benchmark용 전용 validation split을 갖춘 대규모 dataset인 InsTrack을 구축한다. 광범위한 실험은 G$^2$TAM이 강한 cross-view consistency, promptable instance spatial tracking, video object segmentation, 그리고 spatial reconstruction을 제공함을 보여 주며, interactive하고 geometry-grounded한 spatial reasoning의 토대를 확립한다."},{"id":"64625","en":"FastSESR: Fast Scene-level Explicit Surface Reconstruction","ko":"FastSESR: 빠른 Scene-level 명시적 표면 재구성","authors":"Jueqi Liu, Xuechao Zou, Congyan Lang","pos":"#1110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LZXjgxypYT","abs":"Explicit surface reconstruction aims to recover high-fidelity meshes directly from point clouds. While existing methods achieve strong performance on scene-level data, they often rely on test-time optimization, resulting in a prohibitive runtime of several minutes. To address this bottleneck, we propose FastSESR, a two-stage framework for efficient scene-level explicit surface reconstruction. In the first stage, a lightweight triangular candidate network (TCN) captures local connections via an edge-factorized parameterization, enabling effective extraction of surface triangles from uniformly sampled points. In the second stage, an offset optimization network amortizes offset refinement into a small, fixed number of learnable update steps guided by TCN, producing geometries that are more suitable for triangulation. Experiments on multiple scene-level datasets show that FastSESR accelerates surface reconstruction by at least $20 \\times$ over prior methods while maintaining competitive reconstruction quality. Moreover, evaluations on shape-level benchmarks indicate good generalization performance. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FastSR-84C1.","absKo":"Explicit surface reconstruction은 point cloud로부터 고충실도의 mesh를 직접 복원하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존 방법들은 scene-level data에서 강한 성능을 보이지만, test-time optimization에 의존하는 경우가 많아 수분에 이르는 과도한 runtime이 발생한다. 이러한 병목을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 효율적인 scene-level explicit surface reconstruction을 위한 two-stage framework인 FastSESR를 제안한다. 첫 번째 stage에서는 lightweight triangular candidate network (TCN)이 edge-factorized parameterization을 통해 local connection을 포착하여, 균일하게 샘플링된 point로부터 surface triangle을 효과적으로 추출할 수 있게 한다. 두 번째 stage에서는 offset optimization network가 TCN의 지도를 받아 offset refinement를 소수의 고정된 learnable update step으로 amortize하여, triangulation에 더 적합한 geometry를 생성한다. 여러 scene-level dataset에서의 실험은 FastSESR가 이전 방법들보다 최소 $20 \\times$ 빠르게 surface reconstruction을 수행하면서도 경쟁력 있는 reconstruction quality를 유지함을 보여준다. 또한 shape-level benchmark에서의 평가는 우수한 generalization performance를 나타낸다. 우리의 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FastSR-84C1 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"61236","en":"ExpAlign: Expectation-Guided Vision–Language Alignment for Open-Vocabulary Grounding","ko":"ExpAlign: Open-Vocabulary Grounding을 위한 Expectation-Guided Vision-Language Alignment","authors":"Junyi Hu, Tian Bai, Fengyi Wu, Wenyan Li, Zhenming Peng, Yi ZHANG","pos":"#1111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sNUjy8nZhD","abs":"Open-vocabulary grounding requires accurate vision-language alignment under weak supervision, yet existing methods either rely on global sentence embeddings that lack fine-grained expressiveness or introduce token-level alignment with explicit supervision or heavy cross-attention designs. We propose \\textbf{ExpAlign}, a theoretically grounded vision-language alignment framework built on a principled multiple instance learning formulation. ExpAlign introduces an Expectation Alignment Head that performs attention-based soft MIL pooling over token-region similarities, enabling implicit token and instance selection without additional annotations. To further stabilize alignment learning, we develop an energy-based multi-scale consistency regularization scheme, including a Top-K multi-positive contrastive objective and a Geometry-Aware Consistency Objective derived from a Lagrangian-constrained free-energy minimization. Extensive experiments show that ExpAlign consistently improves open-vocabulary detection and zero-shot instance segmentation, particularly on long-tail categories. Most notably, it achieves 36.2 AP$_r$ on the LVIS minival split, outperforming other state-of-the-art methods at comparable model scale, while remaining lightweight and inference-efficient.","absKo":"Open-vocabulary grounding은 약한 supervision 하에서 정확한 vision-language alignment를 요구하지만, 기존 방법은 미세한 표현력이 부족한 global sentence embedding에 의존하거나, explicit supervision 또는 heavy cross-attention 설계를 동반한 token-level alignment를 도입합니다. 우리는 원리적으로 정립된 multiple instance learning formulation 위에 구축한 이론적으로 타당한 vision-language alignment 프레임워크인 \\textbf{ExpAlign}을 제안합니다. ExpAlign은 attention-based soft MIL pooling을 token-region similarity에 대해 수행하는 Expectation Alignment Head를 도입하여, 추가 주석 없이도 implicit token 및 instance selection을 가능하게 합니다. alignment learning을 더욱 안정화하기 위해, 우리는 Top-K multi-positive contrastive objective와 Lagrangian-constrained free-energy minimization에서 유도된 Geometry-Aware Consistency Objective를 포함하는 energy-based multi-scale consistency regularization scheme을 개발합니다. 대규모 실험 결과, ExpAlign은 특히 long-tail category에서 open-vocabulary detection과 zero-shot instance segmentation을 일관되게 향상시킵니다. 가장 주목할 만하게는, 유사한 model scale에서 다른 state-of-the-art 방법들을 능가하면서도 lightweight하고 inference-efficient한 상태로 LVIS minival split에서 36.2 AP$_r$를 달성합니다."},{"id":"61092","en":"AmbiRefer3D: 3D Visual Grounding with Referential Ambiguity","ko":"AmbiRefer3D: 지시적 모호성을 고려한 3D Visual Grounding","authors":"Rongjiang Zhu, Wei Kang, Zeqi Liu, Chen junyu, Shuo Yang, Xinxiao Wu","pos":"#1209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tkOMvqB6E9","abs":"<p>Traditional 3D visual grounding  typically assumes that natural language expressions unambiguously refer to target objects in a 3D scene. However, in practical applications, human instructions are often ambiguous or insufficient, which may lead existing models to associate the query with multiple possible objects, resulting in incorrect results. In this paper,  we propose a new task, 3D visual grounding with referential ambiguity, which allows for referential ambiguity in language descriptions,  making it more broadly applicable to real-world scenarios. To tackle this task, we propose an interactive grounding framework that performs multi-round question-answer interactions, in which the model actively generates clarifying questions and receives human-provided answers to acquire additional object attributes, spatial relationships, and other contextual information, thereby resolving referential ambiguity and achieving accurate grounding. To support the learning of interactive grounding,  we construct a large-scale dataset named AmbiRefer3D, which contains 47,085 samples with 141,255 annotations of question-answer dialogues that capture interactive disambiguation processes, covering 7,316 indoor 3D scenes. Furthermore, we establish multi-round evaluation metrics to measure both disambiguation efficiency and grounding accuracy.</p>","absKo":"<p>전통적인 3D visual grounding은 보통 자연어 표현이 3D scene의 target object를 모호함 없이 지칭한다고 가정한다. 그러나 실제 응용에서는 인간의 지시가 종종 모호하거나 불충분하며, 이로 인해 기존 model이 query를 여러 가능한 object와 연관시켜 잘못된 결과를 낳을 수 있다. 본 논문에서는 language description에서 referential ambiguity를 허용하여 실제 세계 시나리오에 더 널리 적용 가능한 새로운 task인 3D visual grounding with referential ambiguity를 제안한다. 이 task를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 multi-round question-answer interaction을 수행하는 interactive grounding framework를 제안한다. 여기서 model은 적극적으로 clarifying question을 생성하고 인간이 제공한 answer를 받아 추가적인 object attribute, spatial relationship, 그리고 기타 contextual information을 획득함으로써 referential ambiguity를 해소하고 정확한 grounding을 달성한다. interactive grounding 학습을 지원하기 위해, 우리는 7,316개의 indoor 3D scene을 포괄하는 141,255개의 question-answer dialogue annotation이 포함된 AmbiRefer3D라는 대규모 dataset을 구축하였다. 더 나아가, disambiguation efficiency와 grounding accuracy를 모두 측정하는 multi-round evaluation metric도 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"66324","en":"Beyond Single-View Indexing: Structure-Aware Multi-View Retrieval for Knowledge-Based VQA","ko":"단일 뷰 인덱싱을 넘어서: 지식 기반 VQA를 위한 구조 인지 다중 뷰 검색","authors":"Hao Wang, Xujia Li, Lei Chen","pos":"#1210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4gfPd3ukxU","abs":"<p>Knowledge-Based Visual Question Answering (KB-VQA) relies on retrieval from large-scale knowledge bases, yet this stage is often treated simplistically. Existing methods typically adopt single-view indexing or naive multi-view fusion, leading to systematic coverage gaps. In this work, we demonstrate that different views exhibit strong complementarity in retrieval. Motivated by this observation, we propose SCAR, a Structure-aware Cross-View Retrieval framework that exploits cross-view structural complementarity at inference time without additional training. SCAR enhances retrieval via structure-aware similarity propagation within each view and explicit cross-view redundancy regulation. Experiments on multiple KB-VQA benchmarks demonstrate that SCAR substantially improves retrieval recall, approaches retrieval coverage upper bounds, and consistently boosts end-to-end KB-VQA performance with negligible inference overhead.</p>"},{"id":"60729","en":"CLIP Tricks You: Training-free Token Pruning for Efficient Pixel Grounding in Large Vision-Language Models","ko":"CLIP Tricks You: Large Vision-Language Model의 효율적 Pixel Grounding을 위한 Training-Free Token Pruning","authors":"Sangin Lee, Yukyung Choi","pos":"#1211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x88YyM4ano","abs":"In large vision-language models (LVLMs), visual tokens typically constitute the majority of input tokens, leading to substantial computational overhead. To address this, recent studies have explored pruning redundant or less informative visual tokens for image understanding tasks. However, these methods struggle with pixel grounding tasks, where token importance is highly contingent on the input text. Through an in-depth analysis of CLIP, we observe that visual tokens located within referent regions often exhibit low similarity to the textual representation. Motivated by this insight, we introduce LiteLVLM, a training-free, text-guided token pruning strategy for efficient pixel grounding inference. By reversing the ranking of CLIP's visual-text similarity, LiteLVLM effectively retains visual tokens covering the referent regions, while recovering context tokens to enable clear foreground-background separation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that LiteLVLM significantly outperforms existing methods by over 5\\% across diverse token budgets. Without any training or fine-tuning, LiteLVLM maintains 90\\% of the original performance with a 22\\% speedup and a 2.3$\\times$ memory reduction. The code will be publicly released after publication.","absKo":"대규모 vision-language model(LVLM)에서 visual token은 보통 입력 token의 대부분을 차지하여 상당한 계산 오버헤드를 초래한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 최근 연구들은 image understanding task에서 중복되거나 정보량이 낮은 visual token을 pruning하는 방법을 탐구해 왔다. 그러나 이러한 방법은 token 중요도가 입력 text에 크게 좌우되는 pixel grounding task에서는 성능이 떨어진다. CLIP에 대한 심층 분석을 통해, referent region 내에 위치한 visual token이 종종 textual representation과의 similarity가 낮게 나타난다는 점을 관찰했다. 이러한 통찰에 기반하여 우리는 효율적인 pixel grounding inference를 위한 training-free text-guided token pruning strategy인 LiteLVLM을 제안한다. CLIP의 visual-text similarity 순위를 뒤집음으로써, LiteLVLM은 referent region을 덮는 visual token을 효과적으로 유지하는 동시에 context token을 복원하여 foreground-background를 명확히 분리할 수 있게 한다. 광범위한 실험은 LiteLVLM이 다양한 token budget 전반에서 기존 방법보다 5% 이상 크게 우수함을 보여준다. 추가적인 학습이나 fine-tuning 없이도 LiteLVLM은 원래 성능의 90%를 유지하면서 22%의 속도 향상과 2.3$\\times$의 메모리 절감을 달성한다. 코드는 출판 후 공개될 예정이다."},{"id":"62389","en":"MoDA: Modulation Adapter for Fine-Grained Visual Understanding in Instructional MLLMs","ko":"MoDA: Instructional MLLM의 정밀 시각 이해를 위한 Modulation Adapter","authors":"Wayner Barrios, Andrés Villa, Juan Leon Alcazar, SouYoung Jin, Bernard Ghanem","pos":"#1805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=h4RYP8bojp","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) have achieved remarkable success in instruction-following tasks by integrating pretrained visual encoders with large language models (LLMs). However, existing approaches often struggle with fine-grained visual grounding due to semantic entanglement in visual patch representations, where individual patches blend multiple distinct visual elements, making it difficult for models to focus on instruction-relevant details. To address this challenge, we propose MoDA (Modulation Adapter), a lightweight module that enhances visual grounding through instruction-guided channel-wise modulation. Unlike token-level methods such as Q-Former that perform additive feature selection, MoDA operates at the channel level through multiplicative modulation on already-aligned features, enabling fine-grained control over which embedding dimensions are relevant for each instruction. MoDA applies cross-attention between language instructions and pre-aligned visual features, generating dynamic modulation masks without architectural modifications or additional supervision. We evaluate MoDA on recent baselines including LLaVA-MoRE (2025) across 12 diverse benchmarks spanning visual question answering, vision-centric reasoning, and hallucination detection, including recent 2024 benchmarks (MMVP, CV-Bench, MMStar, RealWorldQA). MoDA achieves substantial improvements of +12.0 points on MMVP and +4.8 points on ScienceQA, outperforming baselines on all 12 benchmarks with minimal overhead (&lt;1 FLOPs).</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs)는 pretrained visual encoder와 large language model (LLM)을 통합함으로써 instruction-following task에서 놀라운 성과를 달성했다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 종종 visual patch representation의 semantic entanglement 때문에 fine-grained visual grounding에서 어려움을 겪는다. 개별 patch가 여러 개의 서로 다른 visual element를 섞어 담고 있어, model이 instruction과 관련된 세부 사항에 집중하기 어렵기 때문이다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 instruction-guided channel-wise modulation을 통해 visual grounding을 향상시키는 경량 모듈 MoDA (Modulation Adapter)를 제안한다. Q-Former와 같은 token-level method가 additive feature selection을 수행하는 것과 달리, MoDA는 이미 정렬된 feature에 multiplicative modulation을 적용하는 channel level에서 동작하여, 각 instruction에 대해 어떤 embedding dimension이 관련 있는지 세밀하게 제어할 수 있게 한다. MoDA는 language instruction과 pre-aligned visual feature 사이에 cross-attention을 적용하여, architecture 수정이나 추가 supervision 없이 dynamic modulation mask를 생성한다. 우리는 최근의 baseline인 LLaVA-MoRE (2025)를 포함해, visual question answering, vision-centric reasoning, hallucination detection을 아우르는 12개의 다양한 benchmark에서 MoDA를 평가했으며, 최근 2024 benchmark인 MMVP, CV-Bench, MMStar, RealWorldQA도 포함하였다. MoDA는 MMVP에서 +12.0 point, ScienceQA에서 +4.8 point의 substantial improvement를 달성했으며, 모든 12개 benchmark에서 minimal overhead(&lt;1 FLOPs)로 baseline을 능가했다.</p>"},{"id":"62211","en":"Does Reasoning Improve Seeing? Understanding When Vision-Language Models Benefit from Thinking","ko":"추론이 Seeing을 개선할까? Vision-Language Models가 Thinking에서 이득을 보는 경우 이해","authors":"Jing Bi, Luchuan Song, Dingxin Zhang, Pinxin Liu, Guangyu Sun, Lianggong Wen, Weidong Cai, Chen Chen, Chenliang Xu","pos":"#2002","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ieUs1hK3HG","abs":"<p>Vision–language models (VLMs) now support both direct Instruct and explicit-reasoning Thinking modes, but practitioners lack principled ways to decide when reasoning helps or how much computation to allocate at test time. We investigate whether VLMs encode meta-cognitive signals for adaptive inference. We derive oracle labels for two properties: (1) reasoning helpfulness—whether explicit reasoning improves accuracy, and (2) optimal generation length—the minimal token budget for correctness. Probing final-layer representations in InternVL and Qwen3-VL models, we find Thinking models encode these signals more linearly than Instruct models, suggesting reasoning-oriented training enhances meta-cognitive structure. Head-wise attribution reveals two circuits: length-control heads in lower layers, and reasoning/difficulty heads in higher layers. Causal interventions confirm these roles: scaling length heads controls output length with little accuracy loss, while scaling reasoning heads enables a perception–reasoning trade-off, improving accuracy by up to 5.3\\%. These effects generalize across benchmarks. Our results show reasoning-tuned VLMs develop localized, manipulable circuits for meta-cognitive control, enabling test-time steering of computation and reasoning without retraining.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-language model(VLM)은 이제 직접적인 Instruct 모드와 명시적 추론을 수행하는 Thinking 모드를 모두 지원하지만, 실제 사용자들은 언제 reasoning이 도움이 되는지, 혹은 test time에 얼마나 많은 computation을 할당해야 하는지에 대해 원칙적인 판단 기준이 부족하다. 우리는 VLM이 적응적 추론을 위한 meta-cognitive signal을 인코딩하는지 조사한다. 우리는 두 가지 속성에 대한 oracle label을 도출한다. (1) reasoning helpfulness - 명시적 reasoning이 정확도를 향상시키는지 여부, (2) optimal generation length - 정답을 위해 필요한 최소 token budget. InternVL과 Qwen3-VL model의 final-layer representation을 probing한 결과, Thinking model이 Instruct model보다 이러한 신호를 더 선형적으로 인코딩하며, 이는 reasoning 지향 학습이 meta-cognitive structure를 강화함을 시사한다. head-wise attribution은 두 가지 circuit을 드러낸다. 낮은 layer의 length-control head와 높은 layer의 reasoning/difficulty head이다. causal intervention은 이러한 역할을 확인해 준다. length head를 조정하면 정확도 손실이 거의 없이 출력 길이를 제어할 수 있고, reasoning head를 조정하면 perception-reasoning trade-off를 가능하게 하여 정확도를 최대 5.3\\%까지 향상시킨다. 이러한 효과는 여러 benchmark 전반에서 일반화된다. 우리의 결과는 reasoning-tuned VLM이 meta-cognitive control을 위한 국소적이고 조작 가능한 circuit을 발달시킨다는 점을 보여주며, 재학습 없이 test-time에서 computation과 reasoning을 조정할 수 있게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"63195","en":"BabyVision: Visual Reasoning Beyond Language","ko":"BabyVision: 언어를 넘어선 시각적 추론","authors":"Liang Chen, Weichu Xie, Liang Yiyan, Hongfeng He, Haozhe Zhao, Zhibo Yang, Zhiqi Huang, Haoning Wu, Haoyu Lu, Y.Charles, Yiping Bao, YuanTao Fan, Guopeng Li, Haiyang Shen, Xuanzhong Chen, Wendong Xu, Shuzheng Si, Zefan Cai, Wenhao Chai, Ziqi Huang, Maofan Lin, Tianyu Liu, Baobao Chang, Ming Wu, Xiaobo Hu, Kaiyuan Chen, Yixin Ren, Yang Liu, Yuan Gong, Kuan Li","pos":"#2113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZD3BniFPto","abs":"<p>While humans develop core visual skills long before acquiring language, contemporary Multimodal LLMs (MLLMs) still rely heavily on linguistic priors to compensate for their fragile visual understanding. We uncovered a crucial fact: state-of-the-art MLLMs consistently fail on basic visual tasks that humans, even 3-year-olds, can solve effortlessly. To systematically investigate this gap, we introduce BabyVision, a benchmark designed to assess core visual abilities independent of linguistic knowledge for MLLMs. BabyVision spans a wide range of tasks, with 388 items divided into 22 subclasses across four key categories. Empirical results and human evaluation reveal that leading MLLMs perform significantly below human baselines. Gemini3-Pro-Preview scores 49.7, lagging behind 6-year-old humans and falling well behind the average adult score of 94.1. These results show despite excelling in knowledge-heavy evaluations, current MLLMs still lack fundamental visual primitives. Progress in BabyVision represents a step toward human-level visual perception and reasoning capabilities. We also explore solving visual reasoning with generation models by proposing Babyvision-Gen and automatic evaluation toolkit. Our code and benchmark data are released at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/BabyVision-E88F/ for reproduction.</p>","absKo":"<p>인간은 언어를 획득하기 훨씬 전부터 핵심 시각 능력을 발달시키지만, 현대의 Multimodal LLM(MLLM)은 여전히 취약한 시각 이해를 보완하기 위해 언어적 prior에 크게 의존한다. 우리는 중요한 사실 하나를 발견했다. 최신 MLLM은 인간, 심지어 3세 아동도 쉽게 해결할 수 있는 기본적인 시각 과제에서 일관되게 실패한다. 이 격차를 체계적으로 조사하기 위해, 우리는 MLLM의 언어 지식과 무관한 핵심 시각 능력을 평가하도록 설계된 benchmark인 BabyVision을 제안한다. BabyVision은 4개 핵심 범주 아래 22개 subclass로 나뉜 388개 항목을 포함하는 넓은 task 범위를 포괄한다. 실증 결과와 인간 평가는 선도적인 MLLM의 성능이 인간 baseline에 비해 현저히 낮음을 보여준다. Gemini3-Pro-Preview는 49.7점을 기록했으며, 6세 인간보다 뒤처지고 평균 성인 점수 94.1에 한참 못 미친다. 이러한 결과는 지식 중심 평가에서는 뛰어나더라도, 현재 MLLM이 여전히 근본적인 시각 primitive를 갖추지 못했음을 보여준다. BabyVision에서의 진전은 인간 수준의 시각 인지와 추론 능력을 향한 한 걸음이다. 우리는 또한 Babyvision-Gen과 자동 평가 툴킷을 제안하여 generation model로 시각 추론을 해결하는 가능성도 탐구한다. 우리의 code와 benchmark data는 재현을 위해 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/BabyVision-E88F/ 에 공개되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"63027","en":"TopAdapter: Topology-Aware Prompt Tuning for Efficient Point Cloud Understanding","ko":"TopAdapter: 효율적인 점군 이해를 위한 위상 인지 프롬프트 튜닝","authors":"Changshuo Wang, Shuting He, Xiang Fang, Weijun Li, Yixian Shen, Mingkun Xu, Zhongtian Sun, Prayag Tiwari","pos":"#412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aml4ddsbKL","abs":"<p>Point cloud data, with its inherent geometric and topological structures, plays a critical role in 3D vision tasks. However, existing parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) methods predominantly focus on input token prompting, overlooking the intrinsic geometric information. To address this limitation, we propose TopAdapter, a novel PEFT framework that enhances geometric perception by injecting local topological information into pre-trained 3D vision models. TopAdapter leverages 0D, 1D, and 2D simplices from algebraic topology as fundamental building blocks, introducing two core modules: the Topology Injection module (ToInjection) and the Topology Transfer module (ToTransfer). ToInjection constructs multi-scale topological features using a simplex generator and dynamically fuses them with semantic features via a geometric controller, thereby enhancing geometric adaptability. ToTransfer propagates these topological primitives across Transformer layers, ensuring efficient transmission of geometric information. Extensive experiments demonstrate that TopAdapter outperforms existing PEFT methods, achieving performance comparable to full fine-tuning across various benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>고유한 기하학적 및 위상적 구조를 지닌 point cloud data는 3D vision task에서 중요한 역할을 한다. 그러나 기존의 parameter-efficient fine-tuning(PEFT) 방법은 주로 input token prompting에 집중하여 내재된 기하학 정보를 간과한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 사전 학습된 3D vision model에 local topological information을 주입하여 기하 인식을 향상시키는 새로운 PEFT framework인 TopAdapter를 제안한다. TopAdapter는 algebraic topology의 0D, 1D, 2D simplex를 기본 구성 요소로 활용하며, 두 개의 핵심 모듈인 Topology Injection module(ToInjection)과 Topology Transfer module(ToTransfer)을 도입한다. ToInjection은 simplex generator를 사용해 multi-scale topological feature를 구성하고, geometric controller를 통해 이를 semantic feature와 동적으로 융합함으로써 기하학적 적응성을 높인다. ToTransfer는 이러한 topological primitive를 Transformer layer 전반으로 전파하여 기하 정보의 효율적인 전달을 보장한다. 광범위한 실험은 TopAdapter가 기존 PEFT 방법들을 능가하며, 다양한 benchmark에서 full fine-tuning에 필적하는 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61723","en":"Task-Aware Mechanism: Hybrid MoE Vision Tower Towards Holistic Video Understanding","ko":"Task-Aware Mechanism: 전체론적 비디오 이해를 위한 Hybrid MoE Vision Tower","authors":"Qishen Yin, Tanghui Jia, Peng Jin, Hao Li, Juntong Wu, Guanlin Lu, Li Yuan","pos":"#1008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nVBt6ifvl0","abs":"<p>Does \\emph{Comprehending the main idea of a 2-hour movie} and \\emph{Counting the birds appearing in a 15-second clip} really warrant the same video processing pipeline? We present Task-Aware Mechanism (TAM), a hybrid-gated Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) vision tower that adapts frame count and resolution to the user query and video length. TAM introduces a compact 0.1B text-only \\emph{Inductor} trained on our TA-116K dataset to infer task types, enabling task-aware visual budgeting and routing: a soft-gated MoE vision encoder for stability, and hard-gated resolution-specific projectors/pipelines for efficient specialization. Built on Qwen2-7B, TallVA-8B-A7B achieves state-of-the-art performance among models with comparable LLMs across diverse video benchmarks and remains competitive against stronger-LLM baselines, showing that task-aware visual budgeting makes video understanding more holistic. The code is included in the supplementary material.</p>","absKo":"<p>\\emph{2시간짜리 영화의 핵심 줄거리를 이해하는 것}과 \\emph{15초 클립에 등장하는 새의 수를 세는 것}이 정말 같은 video processing pipeline을 써야 할까요? 우리는 Task-Aware Mechanism (TAM)을 제안합니다. TAM은 사용자 query와 video length에 맞춰 frame 수와 resolution을 조정하는 hybrid-gated Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) vision tower입니다. TAM은 task type을 추론하도록 TA-116K dataset으로 학습한 compact한 0.1B text-only \\emph{Inductor}를 도입하여 task-aware visual budgeting과 routing을 가능하게 합니다. 즉, 안정성을 위한 soft-gated MoE vision encoder와, 효율적인 specialization을 위한 hard-gated resolution-specific projector/pipeline을 함께 사용합니다. Qwen2-7B 위에 구축된 TallVA-8B-A7B는 다양한 video benchmark 전반에서 유사한 LLM을 사용하는 모델들 가운데 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하며, 더 강한 LLM을 쓰는 baseline과도 경쟁력을 유지합니다. 이는 task-aware visual budgeting이 video understanding을 더 holistic하게 만든다는 점을 보여줍니다. 코드는 supplementary material에 포함되어 있습니다.</p>"},{"id":"62792","en":"Proteo-R1: Thinking Foundation Models for De Novo Protein Binder Design","ko":"Proteo-R1: De Novo 단백질 Binder 설계를 위한 Thinking Foundation Models","authors":"Fang Wu, Li Erran Li, Weihao Xuan, Heli Qi, Zeqi Zhou, Hanqun CAO, Heng-Jui Chang, Haokai Zhao, Jian Ma, Zijian Ma, Yu-Chi Cheng, Robert Tang, Zehong Wang, Kuan Pang, Hanchen Wang, Kejun Ying, Pan Lu, Chiho Im, Seungju Han, Peng Xia, Yinxi Li, Guanlue Li, Tinson Xu, Deyao Zhu, Pheng Ann Heng, Naoto Yokoya, Masashi Sugiyama, Jure Leskovec, Yejin Choi","pos":"#2505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dDowWwInhz","abs":"<p>Recent advances in generative diffusion and flow-matching models have revolutionized molecular design, enabling the creation of novel proteins, small molecules, and RNA sequences with unprecedented fidelity. Yet, these models remain intuitive rather than intelligent—they generate without reasoning. \\textbf{ThinkProteo} reimagines generative science by introducing reasoning-guided diffusion models that think step-by-step, akin to how a scientist hypothesizes, tests, and refines molecular ideas. By embedding chain-of-thought (CoT) reasoning into the continuous generative trajectory, ThinkProteo transforms diffusion into a process of thought: each denoising step becomes an interpretable act of molecular reasoning guided by structural, energetic, and functional objectives. This framework bridges symbolic reasoning and physical generation, yielding models that not only design molecules but also explain why they work. We envision ThinkProteo as a foundation for cognitive generative chemistry—uniting the creativity of diffusion models with the deliberation of human reasoning to accelerate the discovery of safe and effective therapeutics.</p>","absKo":"<p>생성 diffusion 및 flow-matching model의 최근 발전은 molecular design을 혁신하여, 전례 없는 충실도로 새로운 protein, small molecule, RNA sequence를 생성할 수 있게 했다. 그러나 이러한 모델은 여전히 지능적이라기보다 직관적이다. 즉, 추론하지 않고 생성한다. \\textbf{ThinkProteo}는 과학자가 molecular idea를 가설화하고, 검증하고, 정제하듯이 step-by-step으로 생각하는 reasoning-guided diffusion model을 도입함으로써 생성 과학을 새롭게 구상한다. chain-of-thought(CoT) reasoning을 연속적인 생성 trajectory에 내장함으로써, ThinkProteo는 diffusion을 사고의 과정으로 전환한다: 각 denoising step은 구조적, 에너지적, 기능적 목표에 의해 안내되는 해석 가능한 molecular reasoning 행위가 된다. 이 framework는 symbolic reasoning과 물리적 생성을 연결하여, 분자를 설계할 뿐 아니라 왜 그것이 작동하는지도 설명하는 모델을 산출한다. 우리는 ThinkProteo를 cognitive generative chemistry의 기반으로 구상한다. 즉, diffusion model의 창의성과 인간 추론의 숙고를 결합하여 안전하고 효과적인 therapeutic 발견을 가속화하려는 것이다.</p>"},{"id":"66474","en":"Rethinking Federated Prompt Learning for Medical Images: From Textual Tuning to Visual Manifold Anchoring","ko":"의료 영상을 위한 Federated 프롬프트 학습 재고: 텍스트 튜닝에서 시각 다양체 앵커링으로","authors":"Yipan Wei, Wenke Huang, Yapeng Li, He Li, Qixin Zhang, Mang Ye, Bo Du","pos":"#600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3LymHCdeRd","abs":"<p>Federated Prompt Learning (FPL) adapts Vision-Language Models to privacy-sensitive medical imaging, typically via a textual tuning paradigm that assumes the frozen visual encoder provides a discriminative feature geometry. We argue this assumption breaks down in medical settings, leading to two geometric pathologies: (1) Intra-client: Medical Manifold Collapse, where high morphological similarity reduces the effective rank of visual features; and (2) Inter-client: Medical Topological Misalignment, where heterogeneous acquisition protocols induce inconsistent geometry across clients. To address these, we propose FedMAP, which shifts the paradigm to Visual Manifold Anchoring. FedMAP utilizes an LLM-derived codebook as a client-invariant synchronization signal to restructure the visual space, via Manifold Semantic Anchoring (MSA) and Topology Structural Alignment (TSA) to enforce consistent inter-class relations. Experiments on FedISIC, FedCamelyon17, and a private ultrasound dataset show that FedMAP consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods, especially in high-noise regimes where manifold collapse is most severe.</p>"},{"id":"63717","en":"SP-Mind: An Autonomous Reasoning Agent for Spatial Proteomics Analysis","ko":"SP-Mind: Spatial Proteomics 분석을 위한 자율 추론 에이전트","authors":"YuCheng Yuan, Ji Yuanfeng, Zhongxiao Li, Ruijiang Li","pos":"#601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UJcB3XrffF","abs":"<p>Spatial proteomics enables single-cell-resolution characterization of protein expression within tissue architecture, playing a critical role in understanding tumor microenvironments and guiding precision medicine. However, current analysis workflows remain fragmented, requiring expert manual orchestration of heterogeneous tools and limiting research scalability and reproducibility. We present <strong>SP-Mind</strong>, the first autonomous AI agent designed to unify the spatial proteomics analysis pipeline, from raw multiplexed tissue imaging to downstream phenotype discovery. Equipped with expert-curated biological analysis skills and specialized computational tools, SP-Mind converts natural-language queries into end-to-end analytical workflows without task-specific fine-tuning. To rigorously evaluate its capabilities, we introduce <strong>SP-Bench</strong>, a comprehensive benchmark spanning diverse tissue types and imaging technologies (fluorescence-based and mass spectrometry imaging), comprising 102 tasks across 18 distinct categories. Through extensive evaluation on SP-Bench and established downstream tasks, SP-Mind achieves <strong>state-of-the-art</strong> performance compared to existing open-source biomedical agent baselines. Code and benchmark will be publicly available upon acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spatial proteomics는 조직 구조 내에서 단일 세포 해상도로 protein expression을 특성화할 수 있게 하며, tumor microenvironment를 이해하고 precision medicine을 안내하는 데 중요한 역할을 한다. 그러나 현재의 분석 워크플로는 여전히 파편화되어 있어, 이질적인 도구들을 전문가가 수동으로 조율해야 하며, 이는 연구의 확장성과 재현성을 제한한다. 우리는 raw multiplexed tissue imaging에서 downstream phenotype discovery에 이르기까지 spatial proteomics 분석 파이프라인을 통합하도록 설계된 첫 번째 자율 AI agent인 <strong>SP-Mind</strong>를 제시한다. 전문가가 선별한 생물학적 분석 기술과 특화된 계산 도구를 갖춘 SP-Mind는 task-specific fine-tuning 없이 자연어 질의를 end-to-end 분석 워크플로로 변환한다. 그 성능을 엄격하게 평가하기 위해, 우리는 다양한 tissue type과 imaging technology(fluorescence-based 및 mass spectrometry imaging)를 포괄하고 18개의 서로 다른 범주에 걸친 102개 task로 구성된 포괄적 benchmark인 <strong>SP-Bench</strong>를 도입한다. SP-Bench와 기존 downstream task 전반에 대한 광범위한 평가에서, SP-Mind는 기존 open-source biomedical agent baseline과 비교해 <strong>state-of-the-art</strong> 성능을 달성한다. 코드는 채택 시 benchmark와 함께 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"60577","en":"Steering Large Language Models through the DMTA Cycle: Structure-Based Drug Design via Knowledge-Driven Bi-Level Thompson Sampling","ko":"DMTA 사이클을 통한 대규모 언어 모델 조향: 지식 주도 이중 수준 Thompson Sampling 기반 구조 기반 신약 설계","authors":"Xuanning Hu, Hao Tuo, Jinglong Ji, Anchen Li, Qianli Xing, Bo Yang","pos":"#602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yqF2ubqiCn","abs":"<p>Structure-based drug design (SBDD) can be effectively realized through an iterative refinement via the Design-Make-Test-Analyze (DMTA) cycle, which is a common workflow used by human experts. However, most LLMs function as one-shot generators that lack feedback mechanisms, leaving the DMTA loop disconnected. In this work, we propose K-BTS, a Knowledge-Driven Bi-level Thompson Sampling framework that formalizes iterative SBDD as a Dynamic Hierarchical Multi-Armed Bandit problem. K-BTS closes the DMTA loop by decoupling decisions into two levels: an upper-level policy that prioritizes high-potential molecular lineages and a lower-level mechanism that retrieves explicit chemical rules to guide LLM generation. By integrating a dual-level Bayesian update, the framework transforms sparse docking scores into reusable experience. On the CrossDocked2020 benchmark, K-BTS achieves a state-of-the-art Top-1 average docking score. The results from diverse dimensions show that K-BTS ensures search determinism through a smooth, monotonic convergence that synchronizes structural drift with affinity improvement.</p>","absKo":"<p>structure-based drug design(SBDD)은 인간 전문가가 사용하는 일반적인 workflow인 Design-Make-Test-Analyze(DMTA) cycle을 통한 반복적 refinement로 효과적으로 구현될 수 있다. 그러나 대부분의 LLM은 feedback mechanism이 없는 one-shot generator로 작동하여 DMTA loop가 단절된 상태로 남는다. 본 연구에서는 iterative SBDD를 Dynamic Hierarchical Multi-Armed Bandit problem으로 정식화하는 Knowledge-Driven Bi-level Thompson Sampling framework인 K-BTS를 제안한다. K-BTS는 의사결정을 두 수준으로 분리하여 DMTA loop를 닫는다. 상위 수준 policy는 잠재력이 높은 molecular lineage를 우선시하고, 하위 수준 메커니즘은 LLM generation을 유도하기 위해 명시적인 chemical rule을 검색한다. 이중 수준 Bayesian update를 통합함으로써, 이 framework는 sparse docking score를 재사용 가능한 경험으로 전환한다. CrossDocked2020 benchmark에서 K-BTS는 state-of-the-art Top-1 average docking score를 달성한다. 다양한 차원에서의 결과는 K-BTS가 structural drift와 affinity improvement를 동기화하는 부드럽고 monotonic한 convergence를 통해 search determinism을 보장함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63759","en":"SynerMedGen: Synergizing Medical Multimodal Understanding with Generation via Task Alignment","ko":"SynerMedGen: 과제 정렬을 통한 의료 멀티모달 이해와 생성을 시너지화","authors":"Weiren Zhao, DONG Yi, Cheng Chen","pos":"#603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Tyv61ZKb9s","abs":"<p>Unifying multimodal understanding and generation is a compelling frontier that is beginning to emerge in the medical field. However, the limited existing unified medical models typically treat understanding and generation as disjoint objectives, lacking a meaningful functional synergy. In this work, we identify and address a critical question in unified medical modeling: what form of “understanding” truly benefits generation. We present SynerMedGen, a unified framework built on the proposed principle of generation-aligned understanding, which synergizes understanding objectives with generation tasks via task alignment. SynerMedGen introduces three generation-aligned understanding tasks and a two-stage training strategy that transfers generation-beneficial representations learned during understanding training to medical image synthesis. Remarkably, even with understanding training alone, our SynerMedGen achieves strong zero-shot performance across 22 medical image synthesis tasks and demonstrates robust generalization to unseen datasets. When combined with generation training, SynerMedGen consistently outperforms state-of-the-art specialized medical image synthesis models as well as recent unified medical models. We also release a large-scale dataset named SynerMed consisting of 1M paired synthesis samples and 2M generation-derived understanding instances to support further research on understanding-generation synergy.</p>","absKo":"<p>multimodal understanding과 generation을 통합하는 것은 의료 분야에서 이제 막 부상하기 시작한 매력적인 frontier이다. 그러나 기존의 제한적인 unified medical model은 보통 understanding과 generation을 분리된 objective로 취급하여, 의미 있는 functional synergy가 부족하다. 이 연구에서는 unified medical modeling에서 핵심적인 질문, 즉 어떤 형태의 “understanding”이 실제로 generation에 도움이 되는가를 식별하고 해결한다. 우리는 generation-aligned understanding이라는 제안된 원리에 기반한 unified framework인 SynerMedGen을 제시하며, task alignment를 통해 understanding objective와 generation task를 상호보완적으로 결합한다. SynerMedGen은 generation-aligned understanding task 세 가지와, understanding training 동안 학습된 generation에 유익한 representation을 medical image synthesis로 전달하는 two-stage training strategy를 도입한다. 놀랍게도, understanding training만으로도 SynerMedGen은 22개의 medical image synthesis task 전반에서 강력한 zero-shot performance를 달성하고, 보지 못한 dataset에 대해서도 견고한 generalization을 보인다. generation training과 결합하면, SynerMedGen은 최신 specialized medical image synthesis model과 최근 unified medical model을 일관되게 능가한다. 또한 further research를 지원하기 위해, 1M개의 paired synthesis sample과 2M개의 generation-derived understanding instance로 구성된 SynerMed이라는 대규모 dataset도 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"64049","en":"TD3B: Transition-Directed Discrete Diffusion for Allosteric Binder Generation","ko":"TD3B: 알로스테릭 결합체 생성을 위한 전이 지향 이산 Diffusion","authors":"Hanqun CAO, Aastha Pal, Sophia Tang, Yinuo Zhang, Jingjie Zhang, Pheng Ann Heng, Pranam Chatterjee, PhD","pos":"#604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RNuC8Nj6rD","abs":"<p>Protein function is often controlled by ligands that bias the direction of state transitions, such as agonists and antagonists, rather than stabilizing a single conformation. This is especially important for clinically relevant G protein-coupled receptors (GPCRs), where therapeutic efficacy depends on functional directionality. Structure-based design methods optimize binding to static conformations and cannot represent non-reversible, directional effects or systematically distinguish agonist from antagonist behavior. To address this gap, we introduce <strong>T</strong>ransition-<strong>D</strong>irected <strong>D</strong>iscrete <strong>D</strong>iffusion for allosteric <strong>B</strong>inder design (<strong>TD3B</strong>), a sequence-based generative framework that designs binders with specified agonist or antagonist behavior via a directional transition control objective. TD3B combines a target-aware Direction Oracle, a soft binding-affinity gate, and amortized fine-tuning of a pre-trained discrete diffusion model, enabling targeted agonist and antagonist generation decoupled from binding affinity and unattainable by equilibrium-based or inference-only guidance baselines.</p>","absKo":"Protein function은 종종 단일 conformation을 안정화하기보다 agonist와 antagonist처럼 state transition의 방향을 편향시키는 ligand에 의해 제어된다. 이는 기능적 방향성이 치료 효과를 좌우하는 임상적으로 중요한 G protein-coupled receptor (GPCR)에서 특히 중요하다. Structure-based design method는 정적인 conformation에 대한 binding 최적화에만 초점을 맞추며, 비가역적이고 방향적인 효과를 표현할 수 없고 agonist와 antagonist 행동을 체계적으로 구분할 수도 없다. 이러한 공백을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 allosteric binder design을 위한 <strong>T</strong>ransition-<strong>D</strong>irected <strong>D</strong>iscrete <strong>D</strong>iffusion(<strong>TD3B</strong>)을 도입한다. TD3B는 방향성 transition control objective를 통해 지정된 agonist 또는 antagonist 행동을 갖는 binder를 설계하는 sequence-based generative framework이다. TD3B는 target-aware Direction Oracle, soft binding-affinity gate, 그리고 pre-trained discrete diffusion model의 amortized fine-tuning을 결합하여, binding affinity와 분리된 채 targeted agonist 및 antagonist generation을 가능하게 하며, equilibrium-based 또는 inference-only guidance baseline으로는 달성할 수 없다.</p>"},{"id":"62640","en":"Token-Sparse Medical Multimodal Reasoning via Dual-Stream Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Dual-Stream Reinforcement Learning 기반 Token-Sparse Medical Multimodal Reasoning","authors":"Kaitao Chen, Weiqian Zhao, Jiamin Wu, Qihao Zheng, Shangquan Sun, Chunfeng Song, Xiaosong Wang, Mu Zhou, Mianxin Liu","pos":"#605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=elrnTLDiT3","abs":"<p>Vision-language models (VLMs) combining reinforcement learning (RL) ignite remarkable progress in multimodal reasoning, yet still struggle with medical images, which typically exhibit extremely sparse visual evidence to inform clinical decision-making. We recognize that pruning visual tokens outside the grounding region greatly enhances medical reasoning. However, a united RL framework for active visual token pruning (VTP) and medical multimodal reasoning remains unestablished. Here, we propose a dual-stream RL framework, ViToS, to fulfill token pruning and question answering. ViToS trains one policy model with two task branches, where one focuses on grounding while the other conducts token-sparse reasoning after VTP. Furthermore, we solve the coupled policy learning problem by introducing the cross-feedback sequential optimization, avoiding gradient conflict and facilitating convergence of the shared policy model. Evaluated on seven medical benchmarks, our method reduces visual tokens to 77\\% of the original sequence length while achieving a 108.27\\% relative performance on Lingshu-7B and 104.16\\% relative performance on HuatuoGPT-Vision-7B. Overall, ViToS delivers superior performance and inference speedup, establishing an efficient paradigm for medical multimodal reasoning.</p>","absKo":"<p>reinforcement learning (RL)과 결합된 vision-language model (VLM)은 multimodal reasoning에서 놀라운 진전을 이끌었지만, 임상 의사결정에 필요한 시각적 근거가 극도로 희소하게 나타나는 medical image에서는 여전히 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 grounding region 밖의 visual token을 pruning하면 medical reasoning이 크게 향상된다는 점을 확인했다. 그러나 active visual token pruning (VTP)과 medical multimodal reasoning을 위한 통합된 RL framework는 아직 확립되지 않았다. 여기서 우리는 token pruning과 question answering을 수행하기 위한 dual-stream RL framework인 ViToS를 제안한다. ViToS는 하나의 policy model을 두 개의 task branch로 학습하는데, 한 branch는 grounding에 집중하고 다른 branch는 VTP 이후 token-sparse reasoning을 수행한다. 더 나아가, 우리는 cross-feedback sequential optimization을 도입해 결합된 policy learning 문제를 해결함으로써 gradient conflict를 피하고 shared policy model의 수렴을 촉진한다. 7개의 medical benchmark에서 평가한 결과, 우리의 방법은 visual token을 원래 sequence length의 77\\%로 줄이면서도 Lingshu-7B에서 108.27\\%의 relative performance, HuatuoGPT-Vision-7B에서 104.16\\%의 relative performance를 달성했다. 전반적으로 ViToS는 우수한 성능과 inference speedup을 제공하며, medical multimodal reasoning을 위한 효율적인 paradigm을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"66764","en":"Towards Docking-oriented De Novo Ligand Design via Gradient Inversion","ko":"Gradient Inversion을 통한 Docking 지향 De Novo Ligand 설계를 향하여","authors":"Zekai Chen, Xunkai Li, Sirui Zhang, Henan Sun, Jia Li, Qiangqiang Dai, Hongchao Qin, Zhenjun Li, Bing Zhou, Rong-Hua Li, Guoren Wang","pos":"#606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0VEeF91Fm6","abs":"<p>De novo ligand design is a fundamental task that seeks to generate protein or molecule candidates that can effectively dock with protein receptors and achieve strong binding affinity entirely from scratch.      It holds paramount significance for a wide spectrum of biomedical applications.     However, most existing studies are constrained by the \\textbf{Pseudo De Novo}, \\textbf{Limited Docking Modeling}, and \\textbf{Inflexible Ligand Type}.     To address these issues, we propose MagicDock, a forward-looking framework grounded in the progressive pipeline and differentiable surface modeling.     (1) We adopt a well-designed gradient inversion framework.     To begin with, general docking knowledge of receptors and ligands is incorporated into the backbone model.     Subsequently, the docking knowledge is instantiated as reverse gradient flows by binding prediction, which iteratively guide the de novo generation of ligands.     (2) We emphasize differentiable surface modeling in the \\textit{generation process}, leveraging learnable 3D point-cloud representations to precisely capture docking details, thereby ensuring that the generated ligands preserve docking validity through interpretable spatial fingerprints.     (3) We introduce customized designs for different ligand types and integrate them into a unified gradient inversion framework with flexible triggers, thereby ensuring broad applicability.     Moreover, we provide sufficient theoretical guarantees for MagicDock.     Extensive experiments across 9 scenarios demonstrate that MagicDock achieves average improvements of 7.0\\% and 7.4\\% over SOTA baselines specialized for protein or molecule ligand design, respectively.</p>"},{"id":"66054","en":"UniMedVL: Unifying Medical Multimodal Understanding and Generation through Observation-Knowledge-Analysis","ko":"UniMedVL: 관찰-지식-분석을 통한 의료 멀티모달 이해와 생성의 통합","authors":"Junzhi Ning, Wei Li, Cheng Tang, Jiashi Lin, Chenglong Ma, Chaoyang Zhang, Jiyao Liu, Ying Chen, Shujian Gao, Lihao Liu, Yuandong Pu, Huihui Xu, Chenhui Gou, Ziyan Huang, Yi Xin, Qi Qin, Zhongying Deng, Diping Song, Bin Fu, Guang Yang, Ji Yuanfeng, Tianbin Li, Yanzhou Su, Jin Ye, SHIXIANG TANG, Ming Hu, Junjun He","pos":"#607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7UR3rNXMz9","abs":"<p>Medical diagnosis demands models that can process multimodal medical inputs, such as medical images and patient histories, and generate diverse outputs including textual reports and visual content, such as annotations or segmentation masks. Despite this need, existing medical AI models disrupt this unified process: image understanding models interpret images without producing visual outputs, while image generation models produce visual outputs but cannot provide textual explanations. Therefore, we propose a multi-level framework called Observation-Knowledge-Analysis (OKA) to unify the distinct processes. Specifically, at the observation level, we construct UniMed-5M, a dataset comprising over 5.6M samples that reformat diverse unimodal data into multimodal pairs. At the knowledge level, we propose Progressive Curriculum Learning, where models simultaneously learn medical multimodal understanding and generation knowledge from UniMed-5M.At the analysis level, we introduce UniMedVL, the first medical unified multimodal model that unifies image understanding and generation within a single architecture without manually reloading model checkpoints. UniMedVL achieves superior performance on 5 medical image understanding benchmarks, while matching specialized models in generation quality across 8 medical imaging modalities. Crucially, our unified architecture enables bidirectional knowledge sharing, improving performance on both image understanding and generation tasks. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Uni-MedVL-65F2/README.md.</p>"},{"id":"66367","en":"VecMol: Vector-Field Representations for 3D Molecule Generation","ko":"VecMol: 3D 분자 생성을 위한 벡터장 표현","authors":"Yuchen Hua, Xingang Peng, Jianzhu Ma, Muhan Zhang","pos":"#608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4K87H0eSqu","abs":"<p>Generative modeling of three-dimensional (3D) molecules is a fundamental yet challenging problem in drug discovery and materials science. Existing approaches typically represent molecules as 3D graphs and co-generate discrete atom types with continuous atomic coordinates, leading to intrinsic learning difficulties such as heterogeneous modality entanglement and geometry–chemistry coherence constraints. We propose VecMol, a novel representation that models 3D molecules as continuous vector fields over Euclidean space, where vectors point toward nearby atoms and implicitly encode molecular structure. The vector field is parameterized by a neural field and generated using a latent diffusion model, avoiding explicit graph generation and decoupling structure learning from discrete atom instantiation. Experiments on the QM9 and GEOM-Drugs benchmarks demonstrate that VecMol achieves competitive generation quality, suggesting vector-field-based representations as a promising new direction for 3D molecular generation.</p>"},{"id":"66077","en":"iLoRA: Bayesian Low-Rank Adaptation with Latent Interaction Graphs for Microbiome Diagnosis","ko":"iLoRA: 미생물군 진단을 위한 잠재 상호작용 그래프 기반 Bayesian 저계급 적응","authors":"Yang Song, Yixuan Zhang, Lingfa Meng, Tongyuan Hu, Haizhou Shi, Hao Wang, Samir Bhatt, Hengguan Huang","pos":"#609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7FF8g7hCre","abs":"<p>Reliable microbiome-based diagnosis is critical for precision medicine at scale in inflammatory diseases, yet current post-training pipelines in LLMs often overlook the interaction structure that governs microbial ecosystems. In inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), disease signals arise not only from species-level abundance shifts but also from latent microbe–microbe cross-talk. We propose iLoRA, a parameter-efficient Bayesian LoRA framework that infers latent interaction graphs from microbiome inputs and integrates them into adaptation, enabling joint clinical prediction and interaction discovery. Unlike correlation-based post hoc analysis, iLoRA models microbial interactions as latent variables learned end-to-end, yielding uncertainty-aware estimates of cross-talk. We evaluate iLoRA on (i) interactive question answering with human-annotated interaction graphs to quantify structural recovery and (ii) gut microbiome cohorts for IBD diagnosis. Across both domains, iLoRA consistently improves accuracy over strong LoRA baselines while producing interpretable interaction graphs consistent with annotated relations and conventional microbiome association networks.</p>"},{"id":"62160","en":"scChord: A Probabilistic Manifold Rectification Framework for RNA-to-Protein Translation","ko":"scChord: RNA-to-Protein 번역을 위한 Probabilistic Manifold Rectification Framework","authors":"Jiawei Zhang, Kangjun Jin, Shuai Xiao, Jiachen Yang","pos":"#610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jCKbsTW9m8","abs":"<p>Measuring single-cell protein abundance is essential for resolving biological mechanisms and disease progression with high resolution. However, due to the high costs and antibody throughput limitations of current proteomics, inferring protein levels from readily available RNA data has become a critical computational necessity. Existing regression and generative methods face a fundamental geometric bottleneck: enforcing deterministic constraints on noisy, heteroscedastic data collapses intrinsic uncertainty into a rough latent manifold, which destabilizes the learning process. To overcome this, we present scChord, a noise-decoupled conditional flow matching framework built on Probabilistic Manifold Rectification. Our approach utilizes a probabilistic decoder to disentangle technical noise and over-dispersion from the raw counts, absorbing them into distributional parameters. This allows the rectified latent manifold to focus more on biological signals, serving as a robust geometric regularizer for learning efficient transport trajectories. Extensive experiments on multiple multi-omics benchmarks demonstrate that scChord not only achieves state-of-the-art inference accuracy but also faithfully reconstructs high-fidelity biological heterogeneity and complex protein distributions.</p>","absKo":"<p>단일 세포 수준의 단백질 abundance를 측정하는 것은 높은 해상도로 생물학적 메커니즘과 질병 진행을 규명하는 데 필수적이다. 그러나 현재 proteomics의 높은 비용과 antibody 처리량 한계로 인해, 쉽게 확보할 수 있는 RNA 데이터로부터 protein level을 추정하는 일은 핵심적인 계산적 필요가 되었다. 기존의 regression 및 generative method는 근본적인 geometric bottleneck에 직면해 있다. 즉, noisy하고 heteroscedastic한 데이터에 deterministic constraint를 강제하면 내재적 불확실성이 거친 latent manifold로 수렴해 learning process가 불안정해진다. 이를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 Probabilistic Manifold Rectification 위에 구축된 noise-decoupled conditional flow matching framework인 scChord를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 probabilistic decoder를 활용해 raw counts로부터 technical noise와 over-dispersion을 분리하고, 이를 distributional parameter에 흡수한다. 이를 통해 rectified latent manifold는 biological signal에 더 집중할 수 있으며, 효율적인 transport trajectory 학습을 위한 견고한 geometric regularizer로 작동한다. 여러 multi-omics benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 scChord가 state-of-the-art inference accuracy를 달성할 뿐 아니라, 고충실도의 biological heterogeneity와 복잡한 protein distribution도 충실하게 재구성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62951","en":"ProtDBench: A Unified Benchmark of Protein Binder Design and Evaluation","ko":"ProtDBench: Protein Binder 설계 및 평가 통합 벤치마크","authors":"Cong Liu, Milong Ren, Jiaqi Guan, Chengyue Gong, Jinyuan Sun, Xinshi Chen, Wenzhi Xiao","pos":"#700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bWLfplRNzt","abs":"Recent advances in $\\textit{de novo}$ protein binder design have enabled increasing experimental validation, yet reported $\\textit{in silico}$ metrics remain difficult to interpret or compare across studies due to non-standardized evaluation protocols. We introduce $\\textbf{ProtDBench}$, a standardized and throughput-aware evaluation framework for protein binder design. ProtDBench defines unified benchmark tasks, evaluation protocols, and success criteria, enabling systematic analysis of how evaluation design influences observed performance. Using a large wet-lab annotated dataset, we analyze commonly used structure prediction models as evaluation verifiers, revealing substantial verifier-dependent bias and limited agreement under identical filtering protocols. We then benchmark representative open-source generative binder design methods across ten diverse protein targets under a fixed evaluation protocol. Beyond per-sequence success rates, ProtDBench incorporates throughput-aware metrics based on a fixed 24-hour budget, as well as cluster-level success criteria to account for structural diversity. Together, these results expose systematic differences induced by filtering rules, success definitions, and throughput-aware evaluation between computational efficiency, success rate, and structural diversity. Overall, ProtDBench provides a fair and reproducible evaluation pipeline that supports systematic and controlled comparison of protein binder design methods under realistic evaluation settings.","absKo":"$\\textit{de novo}$ protein binder design의 최근 발전은 점점 더 많은 실험적 검증을 가능하게 했지만, 보고된 $\\textit{in silico}$ 지표는 비표준화된 평가 프로토콜 때문에 연구 간 해석이나 비교가 어렵다. 우리는 protein binder design을 위한 표준화되고 throughput-aware한 평가 프레임워크인 $\\textbf{ProtDBench}$를 소개한다. ProtDBench는 통합 benchmark task, 평가 프로토콜, 성공 기준을 정의하여, 평가 설계가 관측 성능에 어떤 영향을 미치는지 체계적으로 분석할 수 있게 한다. 대규모 wet-lab 주석 데이터셋을 사용해, 일반적으로 쓰이는 structure prediction model을 evaluation verifier로 분석한 결과, 동일한 filtering protocol에서도 verifier에 따른 편향과 제한된 합의가 상당함을 확인했다. 이어서 고정된 평가 프로토콜 아래, 열 가지 다양한 protein target에 대해 대표적인 open-source generative binder design 방법들을 benchmark했다. 시퀀스별 성공률을 넘어서, ProtDBench는 고정된 24시간 예산을 기반으로 한 throughput-aware metric과 structural diversity를 반영하는 cluster-level 성공 기준을 포함한다. 이 모든 결과는 filtering rule, 성공 정의, throughput-aware evaluation이 computational efficiency, 성공률, structural diversity 사이에 체계적인 차이를 유도함을 드러낸다. 전반적으로 ProtDBench는 현실적인 평가 설정에서 protein binder design 방법을 공정하고 재현 가능하게 비교할 수 있는 평가 파이프라인을 제공한다."},{"id":"66234","en":"ProMiSE: Protein Multi-state Structure Evaluation Benchmark in Biological Contexts","ko":"ProMiSE: 생물학적 맥락에서의 단백질 다중 상태 구조 평가 벤치마크","authors":"Bonjae Ku, Seeun Kim, Yubeen Kim, Hahnbeom Park, Chaok Seok","pos":"#701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5ZN3tiSetW","abs":"<p>Proteins are inherently dynamic, with biological functions often emerging from transitions between multiple conformational states. While recent breakthroughs have largely addressed the static structure prediction problem, a systematic benchmark is absent to demonstrate how well current models capture functionally relevant dynamics. We introduce ProMiSE, the first benchmark that provides both a dataset and evaluation scheme, based on native biological assemblies and integrating major conformational change mechanisms—intrinsic, ligand-induced, and protein-induced—within a single curated dataset. We conducted a comprehensive evaluation of state-of-the-art structure prediction models, including AlphaFold3 and recent generative approaches. Our findings reveal that current models exhibit a limited ability to sample intrinsic dynamics and are often insensitive to biological context in induced scenarios. We further investigate whether these multi-state prediction biases are associated with multiple sequence alignment (MSA) signals or training data distributions, while analyzing internal model representations throughout the model to identify where these biases arise. Ultimately, ProMiSE benchmarks limitations in conformational diversity and biological relevance, enabling improved multi-state and dynamics-aware modeling.</p>"},{"id":"61797","en":"Preference-based Antibody Expression Ranking: Scaling with Large-scale Weak Supervision","ko":"Preference 기반 Antibody Expression Ranking: 대규모 Weak Supervision으로 확장","authors":"Josh Sun, Morteza Babaie, Wenyang hou, Mark Crowley, David Young","pos":"#702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mrZiCCb3zv","abs":"<p>Antibody expression ranking is a critical task in antibody design, yet its modeling is severely hindered by the scarcity of labeled experimental data. To address this, we propose a unified preference-based learning framework that integrates scarce quantitative expression data with large-scale weak positive supervision from immunization data. We adapt Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) to protein language models by introducing a union-masked log-likelihood approximation and IMGT-based alignment, enabling efficient training on variable-length sequences. Evaluating on a diverse internal dataset of 1254 labeled sequences and 4 million unlabeled camelid-derived antibodies, we show that our method consistently outperforms baselines on most metrics. Our results demonstrate that preference learning can effectively learn from weak supervision, providing a scalable solution for antibody expressibility optimization in data-constrained settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>antibody expression ranking은 antibody design에서 중요한 task이지만, labeled experimental data가 부족해 modeling이 심각하게 제한된다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 희소한 quantitative expression data와 immunization data로부터 얻은 대규모 weak positive supervision을 통합하는 unified preference-based learning framework를 제안한다. 우리는 union-masked log-likelihood approximation과 IMGT-based alignment를 도입해 Direct Preference Optimization (DPO)을 protein language model에 적용함으로써, variable-length sequence에 대해 효율적인 training을 가능하게 한다. 1254개의 labeled sequence와 400만 개의 unlabeled camelid-derived antibody로 구성된 다양한 내부 dataset에서 평가한 결과, 우리의 방법은 대부분의 metric에서 baseline을 일관되게 능가한다. 우리의 결과는 preference learning이 weak supervision으로부터 효과적으로 학습할 수 있음을 보여주며, data가 제한된 setting에서 antibody expressibility optimization을 위한 확장 가능한 solution을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"65054","en":"PepCompass: Navigating Peptide Embedding Spaces Using Riemannian Geometry","ko":"PepCompass: Riemannian Geometry를 활용한 Peptide Embedding 공간 탐색","authors":"Marcin Możejko, Adam Bielecki, Jurand Prądzyński, Marcin Traskowski, Antoni Janowski, Hyun-Su Lee, Marcelo Torres, Michal Kmicikiewicz, Paulina Szymczak, Karol Jurasz, Michał Kucharczyk, Cesar de la Fuente-Nunez, Ewa Szczurek","pos":"#704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HENUU9VR8F","abs":"Antimicrobial peptide discovery is challenged by the astronomical size of peptide space and the relative scarcity   of active peptides. While generative models provide latent maps of this space, they typically ignore decoder-induced geometry and rely on flat Euclidean metrics, making exploration distorted and inefficient. Existing manifold-based approaches  assume fixed intrinsic dimensionality, which fails for real peptide data. We introduce **PepCompass**, a geometry-aware framework  based on a **Union of $\\kappa$-Stable Riemannian Manifolds** that captures local decoder geometry while maintaining computational stability. PepCompass performs global interpolation via **Potential-minimizing Geodesic Search (PoGS)** to bias discovery toward promising seeds and enables local exploration through **Second-Order Riemannian Brownian Efficient Sampling** and **Mutation Enumeration in Tangent Space**, which together form **Local Enumeration Bayesian Optimization (LE-BO)**. PepCompass achieves a 100% *in-vitro* validation rate:  PoGS identifies four novel seeds and LE-BO optimizes them into 25 highly active, broad-spectrum peptides, demonstrating that geometry-informed exploration is a powerful paradigm for antimicrobial peptide design.","absKo":"항균 펩타이드 발견은 펩타이드 공간의 천문학적 규모와 활성 펩타이드의 상대적 희소성 때문에 어려움을 겪는다. Generative model은 이 공간의 latent map을 제공하지만, 대개 decoder가 유도하는 geometry를 무시하고 평평한 Euclidean metric에 의존하므로 탐색이 왜곡되고 비효율적이다. 기존 manifold-based 접근은 고정된 intrinsic dimensionality를 가정하는데, 이는 실제 peptide data에는 맞지 않는다. 우리는 국소 decoder geometry를 포착하면서 계산적 안정성은 유지하는 **Union of $\\kappa$-Stable Riemannian Manifolds**에 기반한 geometry-aware framework인 **PepCompass**를 제안한다. PepCompass는 **Potential-minimizing Geodesic Search(PoGS)**를 통해 전역 interpolation을 수행하여 유망한 seed 쪽으로 discovery를 편향시키고, **Second-Order Riemannian Brownian Efficient Sampling**과 **Mutation Enumeration in Tangent Space**를 통해 국소 탐색을 가능하게 하며, 이 둘은 함께 **Local Enumeration Bayesian Optimization(LE-BO)**를 이룬다. PepCompass는 100% *in-vitro* validation rate를 달성했다. PoGS는 네 개의 새로운 seed를 찾아냈고, LE-BO는 이를 25개의 고활성 광범위 항균 펩타이드로 최적화했으며, 이는 geometry-informed exploration이 항균 펩타이드 설계에 강력한 패러다임임을 보여준다."},{"id":"63207","en":"PDFBench: A Benchmark for De Novo Protein Design from Function","ko":"PDFBench: 기능으로부터의 De Novo 단백질 설계를 위한 벤치마크","authors":"Jiahao Kuang, Nuowei Liu, Changzhi Sun, Jie Wang, Tao Ji, Yuanbin Wu","pos":"#705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z6dCaMpiqV","abs":"<p>Function-guided protein design is a crucial task with significant applications in drug discovery and enzyme engineering. However, the field lacks a unified and comprehensive evaluation framework. Current models are assessed using inconsistent and limited subsets of metrics, which prevents fair comparison and a clear understanding of the relationships between different evaluation criteria. To address this gap, we introduce <strong>PDFBench</strong>, the first comprehensive benchmark for function-guided de novo protein design. Our benchmark systematically evaluates eight state-of-the-art models on 16 metrics across two key settings: description-guided design, for which we repurpose the Mol-Instructions dataset, originally lacking quantitative benchmarking, and keyword-guided design, for which we introduce a new test set, SwissTest, created with a strict datetime cutoff to ensure data integrity. By benchmarking across a wide array of metrics and analyzing their correlations, <strong>PDFBench</strong> enables more reliable model comparisons and provides key insights to guide future research.</p>","absKo":"<p>Function-guided protein design은 drug discovery와 enzyme engineering에서 중요한 응용을 갖는 핵심 task이다. 그러나 이 분야에는 통합적이고 포괄적인 평가 프레임워크가 부족하다. 현재 모델들은 일관성이 없고 제한적인 metric subset으로 평가되어, 공정한 비교와 서로 다른 평가 기준 간 관계에 대한 명확한 이해를 어렵게 한다. 이러한 간극을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 function-guided de novo protein design을 위한 최초의 포괄적 benchmark인 <strong>PDFBench</strong>를 소개한다. 우리의 benchmark는 두 가지 핵심 setting에서 16개 metric을 통해 8개의 state-of-the-art model을 체계적으로 평가한다: description-guided design은 원래 정량적 benchmark가 없던 Mol-Instructions dataset을 재구성하여 사용하고, keyword-guided design은 data integrity를 보장하기 위해 엄격한 datetime cutoff로 새롭게 구축한 test set인 SwissTest를 도입한다. 다양한 metric 전반에서 benchmark를 수행하고 그 상관관계를 분석함으로써, <strong>PDFBench</strong>는 더 신뢰할 수 있는 model 비교를 가능하게 하고 향후 연구를 이끌 핵심 통찰을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63768","en":"PDAgent: An LLM-Driven Autonomous Agent Framework Towards *In Silico* Protein Design via Directed Mutation","ko":"PDAgent: Directed Mutation을 통한 *in silico* Protein Design을 위한 LLM 구동 자율 에이전트 프레임워크","authors":"Song Ouyang, Zhijie Dong, Yong Luo, Kehua Su, Huangxuan Zhao, Miaojing Shi, Bo Du","pos":"#706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TwTvDVj6cH","abs":"<p>Computational protein design holds immense promise across diverse domains, but existing approaches face significant challenges: traditional physics-based methods require substantial domain expertise, while emerging deep learning methods often rely on restricted functional ontologies, struggle to bridge the semantic gap between text and protein sequences, or lack closed-loop optimization mechanisms. In this paper, we present PDAgent, an LLM-driven autonomous agent framework that enables <em>in silico</em> protein design through template-based directed mutation. Our framework accepts natural language specifications of desired protein properties and employs a ReAct-style reasoning loop comprising five phases: THINK, PLAN, ACT, OBSERVE, and REFLECT. PDAgent integrates template retrieval, conservation-aware mutation strategies, and domain-specific computational tools for property optimization across eight biophysical dimensions. Experiments on 100 diverse protein design tasks demonstrate that PDAgent achieves a 91.34% average constraint satisfaction rate with high structural quality (mean pLDDT 87.69), substantially outperforming both direct LLM generation and specialized deep learning methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>Computational protein design은 다양한 분야에서 큰 가능성을 지니지만, 기존 접근법은 심각한 제약에 직면한다. 전통적인 physics-based method는 상당한 domain expertise를 요구하는 반면, 새롭게 등장하는 deep learning method는 제한된 functional ontology에 의존하거나, text와 protein sequence 사이의 semantic gap을 메우는 데 어려움을 겪거나, closed-loop optimization mechanism이 부족한 경우가 많다. 본 논문에서는 template-based directed mutation을 통해 <em>in silico</em> protein design을 가능하게 하는 LLM-driven autonomous agent framework인 PDAgent를 제시한다. 우리의 framework는 원하는 protein property에 대한 natural language specification을 받아들이며, THINK, PLAN, ACT, OBSERVE, REFLECT의 다섯 단계로 구성된 ReAct-style reasoning loop를 사용한다. PDAgent는 eight biophysical dimension 전반에서 property optimization을 위해 template retrieval, conservation-aware mutation strategy, domain-specific computational tool을 통합한다. 100개의 다양한 protein design task에 대한 실험은 PDAgent가 높은 구조 품질(mean pLDDT 87.69)과 함께 91.34%의 평균 constraint satisfaction rate를 달성하며, direct LLM generation과 specialized deep learning method를 크게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63147","en":"MutAtlas: A PDB-Wide Energy-Guided Atlas of Protein Mutation Effects","ko":"MutAtlas: 단백질 돌연변이 효과에 대한 PDB 전반의 에너지 유도 아틀라스","authors":"Ruihan Guo, Chaoran Cheng, Zhanghan Ni, Neil He, Bangji Yang, Ge Liu","pos":"#707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZcVSBTJj2m","abs":"<p>Predicting protein mutation effects is fundamental to protein engineering and disease variant interpretation, yet experimental mutation data remain accurate but extremely sparse. Large-scale computational augmentation offers scalability, but introduces heterogeneous and poorly calibrated supervision signals arising from distinct modeling paradigms. We construct a PDB-wide, structure-aligned mutation augmentation dataset that exhaustively enumerates single-site substitutions and aligns mutation signals from physics-based energy models, protein language models, and structure-conditioned inverse folding models. Large-scale analysis under a unified mutation preference representation reveals substantial differences in preference structure, confidence, and cross-model agreement, indicating that disagreement is pervasive and reflects conflicting inductive biases rather than random noise. Motivated by these observations, we propose an unsupervised multi-source mutation preference distillation framework that learns from relative mutation preferences while explicitly modeling cross-source disagreement. Without using any experimental mutation labels during training, our approach achieves consistent improvements on the ProteinGym benchmark over zero-shot baselines and naive multi-source fusion strategies. We release the dataset and evaluation pipeline to support reproducible studies of protein mutation effects.</p>","absKo":"<p>protein mutation effect 예측은 protein engineering과 disease variant interpretation에 필수적이지만, 실험적 mutation data는 정확하지만 극도로 희소하다. 대규모 computational augmentation은 확장성을 제공하지만, 서로 다른 modeling paradigm에서 비롯된 이질적이고 보정이 잘 되지 않은 supervision signal을 도입한다. 우리는 physics-based energy model, protein language model, structure-conditioned inverse folding model의 mutation signal을 exhaustive하게 열거하고 정렬하는, PDB 전역 구조 정렬 mutation augmentation dataset을 구성한다. 통합된 mutation preference representation 아래에서 수행한 대규모 분석은 preference structure, confidence, cross-model agreement에 상당한 차이가 있음을 보여 주며, disagreement가 광범위하게 존재하고 이는 무작위 잡음이 아니라 상충하는 inductive bias를 반영함을 시사한다. 이러한 관찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 source 간 disagreement를 명시적으로 모델링하면서 상대적 mutation preference로부터 학습하는 unsupervised multi-source mutation preference distillation framework를 제안한다. 학습 동안 어떠한 실험적 mutation label도 사용하지 않고도, 우리의 방법은 ProteinGym benchmark에서 zero-shot baseline과 naive multi-source fusion strategy를 일관되게 능가한다. 우리는 재현 가능한 protein mutation effect 연구를 지원하기 위해 dataset과 evaluation pipeline을 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"66574","en":"MolAlign3D: Enhancing Fixed-Dimensional E(3)-Equivariant Latent Space for High-Fidelity 3D Molecular Reconstruction and Editing","ko":"MolAlign3D: 고충실도 3D 분자 재구성 및 편집을 위한 고정 차원 E(3)-등변 잠재 공간 향상","authors":"Zitao Chen, Jiatong Ji, Yinjun Jia, Wei-Ying Ma, Yanyan Lan","pos":"#708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2USw3I5GiJ","abs":"<p>Recent advances in 3D molecular modeling have achieved high-fidelity structural synthesis, yet these models often lack an explicit and manipulable representation space. To address this, MolFLAE introduced a fixed-dimensional, E(3)-equivariant latent space, providing a novel framework for molecular editing independent of atom counts. However, because its latent space was primarily optimized for geometric reconstruction, it remains semantically shallow and inadequate for comprehensive representation learning. In this work, we propose <strong>MolAlign3D</strong>, which evolves this architecture into a unified semantic-generative engine. By anchoring MolFLAE’s manipulable latents with embeddings from a pre-trained molecular encoder, we yield a manifold that is both semantically dense and geometrically precise. Experiments show that MolAlign3D achieves high-fidelity molecular reconstruction and attains comparable performance on molecular property prediction benchmarks. Notably, the integration of rich semantic priors significantly enhances zero-shot molecular manipulation, including atom-number editing and latent-space interpolation, outperforming prior fixed-dimensional equivariant latent baseline.</p>"},{"id":"63940","en":"MoLF: Mixture-of-Latent-Flow for Pan-Cancer Spatial Gene Expression Prediction from Histology","ko":"MoLF: 조직학에서 전암 spatial gene expression 예측을 위한 Mixture-of-Latent-Flow","authors":"Susu Hu, Stefanie Speidel","pos":"#709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SNRYGh6n69","abs":"<p>Inferring spatial transcriptomics (ST) from histology enables scalable histogenomic profiling, yet current methods are largely restricted to single-tissue models. This fragmentation fails to leverage biological principles shared across cancer types and hinders application to data-scarce scenarios. While pan-cancer training offers a solution, the resulting heterogeneity challenges monolithic architectures. To bridge this gap, we introduce <strong>MoLF</strong> (<em>Mixture-of-Latent-Flow</em>), a generative model for pan-cancer histogenomic prediction. MoLF leverages a conditional Flow Matching objective to map noise to the gene latent manifold, parameterized by a Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) velocity field. By dynamically routing inputs to specialized sub-networks, this architecture effectively decouples the optimization of diverse tissue patterns. Our experiments demonstrate that MoLF establishes a new state-of-the-art, consistently outperforming both specialized and foundation model baselines on pan-cancer benchmarks. Furthermore, MoLF exhibits zero-shot generalization to cross-species data, suggesting it captures fundamental, conserved histo-molecular mechanisms.</p>","absKo":"<p>조직학(histology)에서 spatial transcriptomics(ST)를 추론하는 것은 확장 가능한 histogenomic profiling을 가능하게 하지만, 현재 방법들은 대체로 단일 조직(single-tissue) 모델에 국한되어 있다. 이러한 분절화는 암 유형 전반에 공유되는 생물학적 원리를 활용하지 못하며, 데이터가 부족한 시나리오에의 적용도 방해한다. pan-cancer 학습이 해결책이 될 수 있지만, 그 결과로 생기는 이질성은 단일체(monolithic) 아키텍처에 도전이 된다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 pan-cancer histogenomic prediction을 위한 생성 모델 <strong>MoLF</strong>(<em>Mixture-of-Latent-Flow</em>)를 제안한다. MoLF는 conditional Flow Matching objective를 활용하여 잡음을 gene latent manifold로 매핑하고, Mixture-of-Experts(MoE) velocity field로 매개변수화된다. 입력을 전문화된 sub-network로 동적으로 라우팅함으로써, 이 아키텍처는 다양한 조직 패턴의 최적화를 효과적으로 분리한다. 우리의 실험은 MoLF가 새로운 state-of-the-art를 수립하며, pan-cancer benchmark에서 특화 모델과 foundation model baseline 모두를 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다. 더 나아가 MoLF는 cross-species 데이터에 대한 zero-shot generalization을 보이며, 이는 기본적이고 보존된 histo-molecular mechanism을 포착함을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"63842","en":"Mitigating Surgical Data Imbalance with Dual-Prediction Video Diffusion Model","ko":"dual-prediction 비디오 diffusion model로 수술 데이터 불균형 완화","authors":"Danush Kumar Venkatesh, Adam Schmidt, Muhammad Abdullah Jamal, Omid Mohareri","pos":"#710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TFCjR5gSuX","abs":"Surgical video datasets are essential for scene understanding, enabling procedural modeling and intra-operative support. However, these datasets are often heavily imbalanced, with rare actions and tools under-represented, which limits the robustness of downstream models. We address this challenge with *SurgiFlowVid*, a sparse and controllable video diffusion framework for generating surgical videos of under-represented classes. Our approach introduces a dual-prediction diffusion module that jointly denoises RGB frames and optical flow, providing temporal inductive biases to improve motion modeling from limited samples. In addition, a sparse visual encoder conditions the generation process on lightweight signals (e.g., sparse segmentation masks or RGB frames), enabling controllability without dense annotations. We validate our approach on three surgical datasets across tasks including action recognition, tool presence detection, and laparoscope motion prediction. Synthetic data generated by our method yields consistent gains of $10$–$20$% over competitive baselines, establishing *SurgiFlowVid* as a promising strategy to mitigate data imbalance and advance surgical video understanding methods.","absKo":"수술 영상 데이터셋은 scene understanding과 procedural modeling, 그리고 intra-operative support를 가능하게 하는 데 필수적이다. 그러나 이러한 데이터셋은 희귀한 action과 tool이 과소대표되는 심한 불균형을 보이는 경우가 많아 downstream model의 robustness를 제한한다. 우리는 이러한 문제를, 과소대표된 class의 surgical video를 생성하기 위한 sparse하고 controllable한 video diffusion framework인 *SurgiFlowVid*로 해결한다. 우리의 접근법은 RGB frame과 optical flow를 공동으로 denoise하는 dual-prediction diffusion module을 도입하여, 제한된 샘플로부터 motion modeling을 개선하는 temporal inductive bias를 제공한다. 또한 sparse visual encoder는 sparse segmentation mask나 RGB frame과 같은 lightweight signal에 기반해 생성 과정을 조건화하여, dense annotation 없이도 controllability를 가능하게 한다. 우리는 action recognition, tool presence detection, laparoscope motion prediction을 포함한 task에서 세 개의 surgical dataset으로 이 접근법을 검증한다. 우리의 방법으로 생성된 synthetic data는 경쟁력 있는 baseline보다 일관되게 $10$–$20$%의 성능 향상을 제공하며, *SurgiFlowVid*를 data imbalance를 완화하고 surgical video understanding 방법을 발전시키는 유망한 전략으로 자리매김시킨다."},{"id":"63100","en":"MedSIGHT: Towards Grounded Visual Comprehension in Medical Large Vision-Language Models","ko":"MedSIGHT: 의료 대규모 Vision-Language 모델에서 근거 기반 시각 이해를 향하여","authors":"Aofei Chang, Le Huang, Alex Boyd, parminder bhatia, Taha Kass-Hout, Fenglong Ma, Cao Xiao","pos":"#711","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=a7mORMEWYX","abs":"<p>Medical large vision-language models (Med-LVLMs) have recently achieved remarkable progress in vision–language comprehension and medical image segmentation. However, existing models still struggle to unify these two capabilities, which is essential for achieving clinically reasoning that connects visual findings with semantic interpretation. We present MedSIGHT, a unified framework that equips Med-LVLMs with structured, pixel-level understanding for grounded visual comprehension. MedSIGHT introduces a novel Region Perceiver module that produces region-centric tokens, encoding spatial information directly into representation space of the language model. We further propose a medical region codebook into the LLM vocabulary, allowing the model to generate discrete region codes as symbolic representations of anatomical and pathological regions. These codes are decoded through the Region Perceiver to reconstruct segmentation mask, achieving end-to-end spatial grounding. Lastly, MedSIGHT combines Region Perceiver, Codebook and LLM using our proposed progressive training strategy to gradually aligns these modules stably. Trained on only 72K multimodal instruction pairs, MedSIGHT achieves state-of-the-art performance across diverse imaging modalities on both medical comprehension and segmentation tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Medical large vision-language models (Med-LVLMs)은 최근 vision-language comprehension과 medical image segmentation에서 놀라운 발전을 이뤘다. 그러나 기존 모델은 여전히 이 두 능력을 통합하는 데 어려움을 겪으며, 이는 visual findings를 semantic interpretation과 연결하는 clinically reasoning에 필수적이다. 우리는 grounded visual comprehension을 위한 structured, pixel-level understanding을 Med-LVLMs에 부여하는 unified framework인 MedSIGHT를 제시한다. MedSIGHT는 region-centric token을 생성하는 새로운 Region Perceiver module을 도입하여, spatial information을 language model의 representation space에 직접 인코딩한다. 또한 우리는 medical region codebook을 LLM vocabulary에 추가하여, 모델이 해부학적 및 병리학적 region의 symbolic representation으로 discrete region code를 생성할 수 있게 한다. 이 code는 Region Perceiver를 통해 디코딩되어 segmentation mask를 재구성하며, end-to-end spatial grounding을 달성한다. 마지막으로, MedSIGHT는 우리가 제안한 progressive training strategy를 사용해 Region Perceiver, Codebook, LLM을 결합하여 이들 모듈을 점진적으로 안정적으로 정렬한다. 단 72K개의 multimodal instruction pair로 학습된 MedSIGHT는 의료 comprehension과 segmentation task 모두에서 다양한 imaging modality에 걸쳐 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"66170","en":"Learning Adaptive Topology with FiLM-Guided Distillation for Tertiary Structure-Based RNA Design","ko":"3차 구조 기반 RNA 설계를 위한 FiLM 유도 증류 기반 적응형 위상 학습","authors":"Zixun Zhang, Yuncheng Jiang, Yuzhe Zhou, Jiayou Zheng, Shuguang Cui, Zhen Li","pos":"#712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=68GUslfGLY","abs":"<p>Tertiary structure-based RNA design aims to generate RNA sequences that can fold into desired 3D structures, but remains a challenging problem due to the scarcity of annotated data, structural noise, and the intrinsic complexity of RNA topology. Existing structure-to-sequence frameworks largely rely on static k-nearest neighbor graphs and rigid message passing schemes, which fail to capture the flexible and heterogeneous nature of RNA geometry. To address these issues, we propose a unified framework, ATL-FGD, that integrates Adaptive Topology Learning (ATL) and FiLM-Guided Distillation (FGD) for robust RNA design. ATL introduces a differentiable edge gating mechanism to jointly learn topology and representation, enabling the model to construct data-driven, layer-adaptive graphs that better reflect structural dynamics and biochemical consistency. On top of this, FGD bridges structural and sequence representations via feature-wise linear modulation, softly transferring the semantic knowledge from RNA foundation models without relying on them during inference. Extensive experiments on tertiary structure-based RNA design benchmarks demonstrate that our approach achieves significant improvements in both sequence recovery and structural fidelity.</p>"},{"id":"64639","en":"InfoGlobe: Local-and-Global Information-Preserving Statistical Manifold Learning for Single-Cell Transcriptomics","ko":"InfoGlobe: 단일 세포 Transcriptomics를 위한 Local-and-Global 정보 보존 통계적 Manifold 학습","authors":"Cheng Wang, Jinpu Cai, Chongxiao Mao, Yuxuan Wang, Xinzhu Jiang, Yunhao Qiao, Luqi Yang, Luting Zhou, Qiuyu Lian, Hongyi Xin","pos":"#713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LMrsqvShfy","abs":"<p>Geometry-preserving dimension reduction is critical for single-cell transcriptomics, where low-dimensional distances should reflect biological divergence between cell types along the transcriptomic manifold. Due to inadequate metrics, the global structure is not sufficiently preserved in the low-dimensional manifold in standard dimension reduction regimes. We model RNA counts as Multinomial samples, leveraging their hierarchical closure property: gene-level counts refine functional gene-group counts via nested Multinomial distributions. Extending Chentsov's Theorem, we show that the Fisher-Rao metric on coarse (gene-group) and fine (gene) statistical manifolds is isometric. Following this isometry property, we propose InfoGlobe, an information-preserving statistical manifold learning framework that projects cells from high-dimensional hyperspheres (full transcriptome) to low-dimensional hyperspheres (functional groups) while preserving information geometry. Embeddings on the low-dimensional sphere explicitly represent Multinomial distributions by functional gene groups. Benchmarks demonstrate superior preservation of local-and-global cell-type geodesic distances, automatic and robust gene-group discovery, nuanced cell subtype resolution without manual feature engineering and natural batch effect mitigation without explicit alignments.</p>","absKo":"<p>기하 구조를 보존하는 dimension reduction은 single-cell transcriptomics에서 매우 중요하다. 여기서 low-dimensional distance는 transcriptomic manifold를 따라 cell type 간 생물학적 발산을 반영해야 한다. 부적절한 metric 때문에 표준 dimension reduction regime에서는 global structure가 low-dimensional manifold에서 충분히 보존되지 않는다. 우리는 RNA count를 Multinomial sample로 모델링하며, 그 계층적 closure property를 활용한다: gene-level count는 nested Multinomial distribution을 통해 functional gene-group count로 정련된다. Chentsov's Theorem을 확장하여, coarse(gene-group) 및 fine(gene) statistical manifold 위의 Fisher-Rao metric이 isometric함을 보인다. 이러한 isometry property를 따라, 우리는 정보 보존 statistical manifold learning framework인 InfoGlobe를 제안한다. 이 방법은 information geometry를 보존하면서 cell을 고차원 hypersphere(full transcriptome)에서 저차원 hypersphere(functional group)로 투영한다. 저차원 sphere 위의 embedding은 functional gene group을 통해 Multinomial distribution을 명시적으로 표현한다. 벤치마크 결과는 local 및 global cell-type geodesic distance의 우수한 보존, 자동적이고 견고한 gene-group discovery, 수작업 feature engineering 없는 세분화된 cell subtype resolution, 그리고 explicit alignment 없이 자연스러운 batch effect 완화를 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60987","en":"Influence-Guided Symbolic Regression: Scientific Discovery via LLM-Driven Equation Search with Granular Feedback","ko":"Influence-Guided Symbolic Regression: 세분화된 Feedback을 갖춘 LLM 기반 Equation Search를 통한 과학적 발견","authors":"Evgeny S. Saveliev, Samuel Holt, Nabeel Seedat, David Bentley, Jim Weatherall, Mihaela van der Schaar","pos":"#714","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ujiUua1gGV","abs":"Large Language Models (LLMs) offer a promising avenue for scientific discovery, yet their application to symbolic regression is often constrained by inefficient search strategies and coarse feedback signals. Current methods typically guide LLMs using scalar metrics (e.g., global Mean Squared Error), which fail to identify which specific components of a proposed equation are driving performance or causing error. We introduce \\textit{Influence-Guided Symbolic Regression} (IGSR), a method that frames equation discovery as an iterative two-step process combining diverse term generation with rigorous selection: an LLM generates candidate basis functions $\\psi_j(\\mathbf{x})$ for a linear model, which are then evaluated using granular influence scores $\\Delta_j$. These scores quantify each term's marginal contribution to generalization accuracy, enabling an influence-guided pruning process that systematically refines the model structure. Integrating this mechanism into a Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) enables navigating the combinatorial search space while balancing exploration of novel functional forms with exploitation of high-influence components. We demonstrate IGSR's effectiveness across a diverse suite of benchmarks, including LLM-SRBench, pharmacological PKPD models, an epidemiological simulation, and real-world genomic data. Notably, we validate the framework's capacity for genuine discovery in a case study using a high-dimensional biological dataset, in which IGSR identified a novel relationship between DNA methylation and RNA Polymerase II pausing; a hypothesis that was subsequently supported via wet-lab experimentation.","absKo":"Large Language Models (LLMs)는 과학적 발견을 위한 유망한 경로를 제공하지만, symbolic regression에의 적용은 비효율적인 탐색 전략과 거친 feedback signal로 인해 종종 제약을 받는다. 현재의 방법들은 대개 scalar metric(예: global Mean Squared Error)을 사용해 LLM을 유도하는데, 이는 제안된 방정식의 어떤 특정 구성요소가 성능을 끌어올리거나 오차를 유발하는지 식별하지 못한다. 우리는 \\textit{Influence-Guided Symbolic Regression} (IGSR)을 제안하는데, 이는 방정식 발견을 다양한 term 생성과 엄격한 선택을 결합한 반복적 2단계 과정으로 정식화한다. 즉, LLM이 선형 모델을 위한 후보 basis function $\\psi_j(\\mathbf{x})$를 생성하고, 이후 이를 세분화된 influence score $\\Delta_j$로 평가한다. 이 score는 각 term이 generalization accuracy에 기여하는 주변 기여도를 정량화하며, 이를 통해 모델 구조를 체계적으로 정제하는 influence-guided pruning 과정을 가능하게 한다. 이 메커니즘을 Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS)에 통합함으로써, 새로운 함수 형태의 탐색(exploration)과 높은 influence를 가진 구성요소의 활용(exploitation)을 균형 있게 조정하면서 조합적 탐색 공간을 탐색할 수 있다. 우리는 LLM-SRBench, pharmacological PKPD model, epidemiological simulation, 실제 genomic data를 포함한 다양한 benchmark 전반에서 IGSR의 효과를 입증한다. 특히 고차원 biological dataset을 사용한 case study에서는 이 프레임워크가 진정한 발견 능력을 갖고 있음을 검증했으며, IGSR은 DNA methylation과 RNA Polymerase II pausing 사이의 새로운 관계를 발견했고, 이후 wet-lab experiment를 통해 이 가설이 지지되었다."},{"id":"61622","en":"Asymmetric Contrastive Objectives for Efficient Phenotypic Screening","ko":"효율적인 표현형 스크리닝을 위한 비대칭 Contrastive Objective","authors":"Luke Nightingale, Joseph Tuersley, Scott Warchal, Andrea Cairoli, Jacob Howes, Cameron Shand, Andrew Powell, Darren Green, Amy Strange, Michael Howell","pos":"#804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oQSqJfJUvJ","abs":"<p>Phenotypic screening experiments produce many microscope images of cells under diverse perturbations, with biologically significant responses often subtle or difficult to identify visually. A central challenge is to extract image representations that distinguish activity from controls and group phenotypically similar perturbations. In this work we propose new adaptations of contrastive loss functions that incorporate experimental metadata as learned class vectors, and a geometrically inspired variant, called SPC, where class vectors are confined to the unit sphere and updated only by attractive terms (allowing more overlap of phenotypically similar classes). The approach is tested on two popular benchmarking datasets, BBBC021 and RxRx3-core; and we also evaluate performance on uncurated screens of HaCaT cells to gauge effectiveness in a realistic use-case scenario. We find we outperform prior methods across the three datasets and on a wide array of metrics measuring phenotype grouping, biological recall, drug-target interaction and mechanism-of-action inference. We also show we maintain this improved performance compared to models over 10x larger in parameter count, and that SPC can be used as an effective fine-tuning technique. The method is easy to implement and is well suited to settings with limited data or compute resources.</p>","absKo":"<p>Phenotypic screening 실험은 다양한 perturbation 하에서 세포의 많은 microscope 이미지를 생성하며, 생물학적으로 중요한 반응은 종종 미묘하거나 시각적으로 식별하기 어렵다. 핵심 과제는 control과 activity를 구분하고 phenotypically 유사한 perturbation을 그룹화하는 image representation을 추출하는 것이다. 본 연구에서는 실험 metadata를 학습된 class vector로 통합하는 contrastive loss function의 새로운 변형과, class vector를 unit sphere에 가두고 attractive term으로만 갱신하는 기하학적 영감의 변형인 SPC를 제안한다(이를 통해 phenotypically 유사한 class 간 더 많은 overlap을 허용한다). 이 접근법은 두 개의 널리 쓰이는 benchmarking dataset인 BBBC021과 RxRx3-core에서 평가되며, 실제 사용 사례에 대한 효과를 가늠하기 위해 HaCaT 세포의 uncurated screen에서도 성능을 평가한다. 우리는 세 데이터셋 전반과 phenotype grouping, biological recall, drug-target interaction, mechanism-of-action 추론을 측정하는 다양한 metric에서 기존 방법들을 능가함을 확인했다. 또한 parameter 수가 10배 이상 큰 모델과 비교해도 이러한 향상된 성능을 유지하며, SPC가 효과적인 fine-tuning 기법으로 사용될 수 있음을 보인다. 이 방법은 구현이 쉽고 데이터나 compute resource가 제한된 환경에 특히 적합하다.</p>"},{"id":"61574","en":"Beyond Independent Genes: Learning Module-Inductive Representations for Gene Perturbation Prediction","ko":"독립 유전자를 넘어: Gene Perturbation Prediction을 위한 Module-Inductive Representation 학습","authors":"Jiafa Ruan, Zongxin Yang, Ruijie Quan, Liyang Xu, Yi Yang","pos":"#805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=onuLk72nRw","abs":"<p>Predicting transcriptional responses to genetic perturbations is a central problem in functional genomics.  In practice, perturbation responses are rarely gene-independent but instead manifest as coordinated, program-level transcriptional changes among functionally related genes.  However, most existing methods do not explicitly model such coordination, due to gene-wise modeling paradigms and reliance on static biological priors that cannot capture dynamic program reorganization. To address these limitations, we propose scBIG, a module-inductive perturbation prediction framework that explicitly models coordinated gene programs. scBIG induces coherent gene programs from data via Gene-Relation Clustering, captures inter-program interactions through a Gene-Cluster-Aware Encoder, and preserves modular coordination using structure-aware alignment objectives. These structured representations are then modeled using conditional flow matching to enable flexible and generalizable perturbation prediction. Extensive experiments on multiple single-cell perturbation benchmarks show that scBIG consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods, particularly on unseen and combinatorial perturbation settings, achieving an average improvement of 6.7% over the strongest baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>유전적 perturbation에 대한 transcriptional response를 예측하는 것은 functional genomics의 핵심 문제이다. 실제로 perturbation response는 gene-independent한 경우가 드물고, 대신 기능적으로 관련된 gene들 사이에서 program 수준의 조정된 transcriptional 변화로 나타난다. 그러나 기존 방법의 대부분은 gene-wise modeling paradigm과 동적인 program 재구성을 포착할 수 없는 정적인 biological prior에 의존하기 때문에 이러한 조정을 명시적으로 모델링하지 않는다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 조정된 gene program을 명시적으로 모델링하는 module-inductive perturbation prediction framework인 scBIG를 제안한다. scBIG는 Gene-Relation Clustering을 통해 데이터로부터 일관된 gene program을 유도하고, Gene-Cluster-Aware Encoder를 통해 program 간 상호작용을 포착하며, structure-aware alignment objective를 사용해 modular coordination을 보존한다. 이어서 이러한 구조화된 표현을 conditional flow matching으로 모델링하여 유연하고 일반화 가능한 perturbation prediction을 가능하게 한다. 여러 single-cell perturbation benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험에서 scBIG는 특히 unseen 및 combinatorial perturbation 설정에서 일관되게 state-of-the-art 방법들을 능가했으며, 가장 강력한 baseline 대비 평균 6.7%의 성능 향상을 달성했다.</p>"},{"id":"65752","en":"Bridging Dynamics and Data: A Unified Diffusion Framework for Mechanistically-Informed Epidemic Forecasting","ko":"동역학과 데이터의 연결: 기계론적 정보 기반 감염병 예측을 위한 통합 Diffusion 프레임워크","authors":"Guanghui Min, Tianhao Huang, Ke Wan, Qi Wang, Chen Chen","pos":"#806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AY7L7acRtD","abs":"<p>Reliable epidemic forecasting is critical for public health decision-making yet remains challenging due to data sparsity and the non-stationary nature of disease dynamics. While recent hybrid models attempt to integrate mechanistic principles with data-driven approaches, they often relegate mechanistic priors to merely auxiliary features or regularization terms. This design not only obscures the interpretability of the mechanistic contribution but also fails to inherit the capability of physical models to generalize under non-stationary dynamics, as the core architecture remains predominantly data-driven. To address these limitations, we propose EpiDiff, a unified framework that synergizes epidemiological domain knowledge with the generative power of diffusion models. Unlike methods that rigidly fuse features, EpiDiff employs a novel uncertainty-aware steering mechanism during inference. Specifically, we quantify the posterior uncertainty of mechanistic estimations and use it to dynamically modulate the diffusion process. Extensive experiments on real-world datasets demonstrate that EpiDiff consistently outperforms state-of-the-art baselines in accuracy and robustness, particularly under non-stationary distributions, while offering transparent insights into model reliance by explicitly visualizing when the forecast is governed by mechanistic laws versus data-driven patterns. Our code and datasets are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/epidiff-4782.</p>"},{"id":"63547","en":"CellBRIDGE: Learning Cellular Trajectories via Interaction-Aware Alignment","ko":"CellBRIDGE: 상호작용 인지 정렬을 통한 세포 궤적 학습","authors":"Silas Ruhrberg Estevez, Nicolas Huynh, Tennison Liu, Roderik Kortlever, Gerard Evan, David Bentley, Mihaela van der Schaar","pos":"#807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=W9EgZALquo","abs":"Inferring dynamics from population snapshots is a fundamental challenge in machine learning and biology. In scRNA-sequencing (scRNA-seq), destructive measurements preclude direct tracking of individual cells across time, making trajectory inference underdetermined. Optimal Transport (OT) provides a principled framework for snapshot alignment, but a long-standing modeling question is which cost functions yield biologically meaningful couplings. Standard OT approaches rely on gene-expression distances, implicitly treating cells as independent points and neglecting structured cell-cell communication mediated by ligand--receptor signaling. We introduce $\\texttt{CellBRIDGE}$ ($\\textit{Cell-Based Regularized Interaction-Driven Gene Expression}$), which augments feature-based OT with a directed, typed interaction cost derived from ligand-receptor activity. By explicitly modeling cell--cell communication, $\\texttt{CellBRIDGE}$ improves cross-snapshot couplings and downstream trajectory estimates across synthetic and real scRNA-seq datasets relative to feature-only baselines. Notably, $\\texttt{CellBRIDGE}$ enables mechanistically interpretable in silico perturbations: on lung cancer data, silencing specific ligand-receptor pairs induces trajectory shifts that recapitulate expected effects of targeted pathway inhibition.","absKo":"Population snapshot으로부터 dynamics를 추론하는 것은 machine learning과 biology에서 근본적인 과제이다. scRNA-sequencing(scRNA-seq)에서는 파괴적 측정 때문에 시간에 따른 개별 세포를 직접 추적할 수 없으므로, trajectory inference는 underdetermined가 된다. Optimal Transport(OT)는 snapshot 정렬을 위한 원칙적인 framework를 제공하지만, 어떤 cost function이 biologically meaningful coupling을 이끌어내는지는 오랫동안 남아 있던 modeling 질문이다. 표준 OT 접근법은 gene-expression distance에 의존하며, 이는 세포를 독립적인 점으로 암묵적으로 취급하고 ligand--receptor signaling이 매개하는 구조화된 cell-cell communication을 무시한다. 우리는 feature-based OT에 ligand-receptor activity로부터 도출된 directed, typed interaction cost를 더한 $\\texttt{CellBRIDGE}$ ($\\textit{Cell-Based Regularized Interaction-Driven Gene Expression}$)를 제안한다. cell--cell communication을 명시적으로 모델링함으로써, $\\texttt{CellBRIDGE}$는 synthetic 및 real scRNA-seq dataset 전반에서 feature-only baseline에 비해 cross-snapshot coupling과 downstream trajectory estimate를 개선한다. 특히 $\\texttt{CellBRIDGE}$는 mechanistically interpretable한 in silico perturbation을 가능하게 한다. lung cancer 데이터에서는 특정 ligand-receptor pair를 silencing하면 표적 pathway inhibition의 예상 효과를 재현하는 trajectory shift가 유도된다."},{"id":"65443","en":"Conditionally Site-Independent Neural Evolution of Antibody Sequences","ko":"항체 서열의 조건부 위치 독립적 신경 진화","authors":"Stephen Lu, Aakarsh Vermani, Kohei Sanno, Jiarui Lu, Frederick Matsen, Milind Jagota, Yun Song","pos":"#808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DcyK4f7ZyU","abs":"<p>Common deep learning approaches for antibody engineering focus on modeling the marginal distribution of sequences. By treating sequences as independent samples, however, these methods overlook affinity maturation as a rich and largely untapped source of information about the evolutionary process by which antibodies explore the underlying fitness landscape. In contrast, classical phylogenetic models explicitly represent evolutionary dynamics but lack the expressivity to capture complex epistatic interactions. We bridge this gap with <strong>CoSiNE</strong>, a continuous-time Markov chain  parameterized by a deep neural network. Mathematically, we prove that CoSiNE provides a first-order approximation to the intractable sequential point mutation process, capturing epistatic effects with an error bound that is quadratic in branch length. Empirically, CoSiNE outperforms state-of-the-art language models in zero-shot variant effect prediction by explicitly disentangling selection from context-dependent somatic hypermutation. Finally, we introduce <em>Guided Gillespie</em>, a classifier-guided sampling scheme that steers CoSiNE at inference time, enabling efficient optimization of antibody binding affinity toward specific antigens.</p>"},{"id":"61882","en":"DeCoDe: Decoupling Binding Position and Molecular Conformation in 3D Ligand Diffusion for Structure-Based Drug Design","ko":"DeCoDe: Structure-Based Drug Design을 위한 3D Ligand Diffusion에서 Binding Position과 Molecular Conformation 분리","authors":"Julong Yang, Wen Huang, Junhui Chen, Jian Peng","pos":"#810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lywUbYpYfG","abs":"<p>Recent advances in diffusion models show promise for Structure-Based Drug Design (SBDD), which aims to generate 3D ligand molecules that bind tightly to specific protein targets.  This involves jointly optimizing the ligand's 3D conformation and its binding position within the protein pocket.  However, existing diffusion-based SBDD methods diffuse conformation and binding position simultaneously within a high-dimensional joint space, leading to inefficient exploration and suboptimal generation quality in both aspects. To address this, we propose <strong>DeCoDe</strong>, a novel diffusion framework that <strong>decouples</strong> the diffusion processes of the binding position and molecular conformation.  Our key insight is to prioritize the perturbation of the ligand's internal conformation in the early stages of the forward (noising) process, while accelerating the perturbation of its global binding position later. This design guides the reverse (denoising) process to <em>first coarsely position</em> the ligand within the pocket before \\textit{refining its detailed structure}, mimicking a more efficient, step-wise generation strategy. Extensive experiments on the CrossDocked2020 benchmark show that DeCoDe achieves significantly higher structural fidelity (with an average improvement of 18%), while maintaining competitive binding affinity and overall molecular properties compared to state-of-the-art baselines. Code will be released after acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>diffusion model의 최근 발전은 특정 protein target에 강하게 결합하는 3D ligand molecule을 생성하는 것을 목표로 하는 Structure-Based Drug Design(SBDD)에 유망성을 보여주고 있다. 이는 ligand의 3D conformation과 protein pocket 내 binding position을 함께 최적화하는 것을 포함한다. 그러나 기존 diffusion 기반 SBDD 방법은 conformation과 binding position을 고차원 joint space에서 동시에 diffuse하므로, 양쪽 모두에서 비효율적인 탐색과 낮은 생성 품질을 초래한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 binding position과 molecular conformation의 diffusion process를 분리하는 새로운 diffusion framework인 <strong>DeCoDe</strong>를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 forward(noising) process의 초기 단계에서는 ligand의 내부 conformation perturbation을 우선하고, 이후에는 전역적 binding position의 perturbation을 가속하는 것이다. 이 설계는 reverse(denoising) process가 먼저 ligand를 pocket 내에 대략적으로 배치한 뒤 \\textit{세부 구조를 정교화}하도록 유도하여, 더 효율적인 단계적 생성 전략을 모사한다. CrossDocked2020 benchmark에서의 광범위한 실험은 DeCoDe가 최첨단 baseline과 비교해 경쟁적인 binding affinity와 전체 molecular property를 유지하면서도 구조적 fidelity를 크게 향상시킴을 보여준다(평균 18% 향상). 코드는 채택 후 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61142","en":"Discrete Diffusion with Physical Mass Constraints for \\emph{De Novo} Peptide Sequencing","ko":"De Novo Peptide Sequencing을 위한 물리적 질량 제약 Discrete Diffusion","authors":"Zeyu An, Wanyu LIN","pos":"#811","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tIG4D44jn9","abs":"{\\em De novo} peptide sequencing is a pivotal technique that directly reconstructs amino acid sequences from tandem mass spectrometry (MS/MS) data; it enables the identification of novel proteins and variants absent from reference databases. Previous methods are typically based on autoregressive (AR) decoding or one-shot generation. The AR-based methods conflict with the bidirectional and globally constrained nature of MS/MS evidence and inevitably accumulate errors, while one-shot generation does not explicitly enforce physical constraints, failing to produce chemically valid and reliable peptides in a single pass. Accurate sequencing necessitates reasoning over the entire peptide simultaneously, enabling iterative self-correction under global constraints.  To this end, we introduce $\\textbf{PhysNovo}$, a novel paradigm that harnesses discrete diffusion to enable simultaneous global reasoning and iterative refinement. Specifically, PhysNovo reformulates sequencing as a $\\textbf{phys}$ically mass-constrained reasoning process by embedding a knapsack-based feasibility kernel to enforce exact precursor mass consistency. By conditioning the diffusion process on global spectral context, PhysNovo supports abductive reasoning where bidirectional evidence is exploited to iteratively resolve local inconsistencies and ensure physically valid predictions. PhysNovo achieves state-of-the-art performance, exceeding baselines by over 2\\% in precision, with larger gains on out-of-distribution data.","absKo":"{\\em De novo} peptide sequencing은 tandem mass spectrometry (MS/MS) 데이터로부터 amino acid sequence를 직접 복원하는 핵심 기술로, reference database에 없는 novel protein과 variant를 식별할 수 있게 합니다. 기존 방법은 보통 autoregressive (AR) decoding 또는 one-shot generation에 기반합니다. AR 기반 방법은 MS/MS evidence의 bidirectional하고 globally constrained된 특성과 충돌하며 오류를 불가피하게 누적시키는 반면, one-shot generation은 물리적 제약을 명시적으로 강제하지 않아 화학적으로 유효하고 신뢰할 수 있는 peptide를 한 번의 pass에서 생성하지 못합니다. 정확한 sequencing은 peptide 전체를 동시에 추론하여 global constraint 하에서 iterative self-correction을 수행할 것을 요구합니다. 이를 위해 우리는 discrete diffusion을 활용해 simultaneous global reasoning과 iterative refinement를 가능하게 하는 새로운 패러다임 $\\textbf{PhysNovo}$를 도입합니다. 구체적으로, PhysNovo는 knapsack-based feasibility kernel을 내장하여 정확한 precursor mass consistency를 강제함으로써 sequencing을 $\\textbf{phys}$ically mass-constrained reasoning process로 재정식화합니다. global spectral context에 조건화된 diffusion process를 통해 PhysNovo는 bidirectional evidence를 활용해 local inconsistency를 반복적으로 해결하고 물리적으로 유효한 예측을 보장하는 abductive reasoning을 지원합니다. PhysNovo는 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하며, precision에서 baseline을 2\\% 이상 능가하고, out-of-distribution data에서는 더 큰 향상을 보입니다."},{"id":"61366","en":"EpiCoCo: De Novo Epitope Generation via MHC-Context Co-Modeling and Contrastive Affinity Guidance","ko":"EpiCoCo: MHC-Context Co-Modeling과 Contrastive Affinity Guidance를 통한 De Novo Epitope Generation","authors":"Haoyang Luan, Gufeng Yu, Letian Chen, Zhenran Xiao, Yueshan Huang, Junkun Guo, Yang Yang","pos":"#812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qwtCnzt5B8","abs":"<p>The <em>de novo</em> generation of high-affinity epitopes tailored to specific major histocompatibility complex (MHC) proteins is a pivotal challenge in computational immunotherapy. However, current methods struggle to effectively integrate the MHC context into the generation process, and often fail to guarantee high binding affinity due to the neglect of discriminative signals from non-binders. To bridge these gaps, we present <strong>EpiCoCo</strong>, a probabilistic framework for <strong>Epi</strong>tope generation via MHC-context <strong>Co</strong>-modeling and <strong>Co</strong>ntrastive affinity learning. EpiCoCo treats the pMHC complex as a dynamic, co-adaptive system by operating on the joint E(3) graph. In addition, we introduce Contrastive Affinity Guidance (CAG), an inference mechanism that leverages the gradient difference between learned high- and low-affinity distributions. CAG actively drives the generation trajectory towards high-affinity manifolds while utilizing repulsive signals to filter out candidates with poor binding potential. Extensive evaluations demonstrate that EpiCoCo achieves a mean binding free energy of -45.20 REU, a 23% improvement over the state-of-the-art, while maintaining high structural plausibility. The results validate that context co-modeling and negative-informed guidance are essential for generating valid, high-potency immunotherapeutics.</p>","absKo":"<p><em>de novo</em>로 특정 major histocompatibility complex(MHC) protein에 맞춘 고친화도 epitope를 생성하는 것은 computational immunotherapy의 핵심 과제이다. 그러나 현재의 방법은 MHC context를 생성 과정에 효과적으로 통합하는 데 어려움을 겪고, non-binder에서 오는 판별 신호를 간과함으로써 높은 binding affinity를 보장하지 못하는 경우가 많다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 MHC-context <strong>Co</strong>-modeling과 <strong>Co</strong>ntrastive affinity learning을 통한 <strong>Epi</strong>tope generation을 위한 확률적 프레임워크인 <strong>EpiCoCo</strong>를 제안한다. EpiCoCo는 pMHC complex를 joint E(3) graph 위에서 동작하는 동적이고 상호 적응적인 시스템으로 간주한다. 또한 우리는 학습된 high-affinity 분포와 low-affinity 분포의 gradient 차이를 활용하는 inference mechanism인 Contrastive Affinity Guidance(CAG)를 도입한다. CAG는 repulsive signal을 사용해 결합 가능성이 낮은 후보를 걸러내면서, 생성 궤적을 고친화도 manifold 쪽으로 적극적으로 유도한다. 광범위한 평가 결과, EpiCoCo는 평균 binding free energy -45.20 REU를 달성하여 state-of-the-art 대비 23% 향상된 성능을 보이는 동시에 높은 structural plausibility를 유지함을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 context co-modeling과 negative-informed guidance가 유효하고 강력한 immunotherapeutic 생성에 필수적임을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65413","en":"Geometric Pocket-Centric Protein Encoding for Polypharmacology-Guided Multi-Target Drug Design","ko":"다중 표적 약물 설계를 위한 기하학적 포켓 중심 단백질 인코딩","authors":"Haoran liu, Xiaoli Lin, Jing Hu, Yu Zou, Xiaolong Zhang","pos":"#813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DuaA7vJGF6","abs":"<p>Polypharmacology provides a powerful strategy for treating complex diseases, but identifying molecules that simultaneously satisfy coupled constraints across multiple biological targets remains difficult. Existing methods typically model protein pockets in isolation and struggle to jointly account for multiple heterogeneous binding sites when designing a single shared ligand. To address these limitations, we propose a pocket-structure-centric generative framework for polypharmacology. This framework introduces a novel protein topological representation that selectively masks ligand-irrelevant residues while explicitly modeling backbone folding geometry and inter-residue spatial proximity within binding pockets. In addition, structural representations are jointly fused with amino acid and nucleotide sequences to capture their complementary information across targets. Experiments on COVID-19, schizophrenia, and tumor targets show that this framework generates valid candidates with significantly improved binding affinities compared to state-of-the-art methods.</p>"},{"id":"64611","en":"DC-W2S: Dual-Consensus Weak-to-Strong Training for Reliable Process Reward Modeling in Biological Reasoning","ko":"DC-W2S: 생물학적 추론에서 신뢰할 수 있는 Process Reward Modeling을 위한 Dual-Consensus Weak-to-Strong 학습","authors":"Chi-Min Chan, Ehsan Hajiramezanali, Xiner Li, Edward De Brouwer, Carl Edwards, Wei Xue, Sirui Han, Yike Guo, Gabriele Scalia","pos":"#809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Lh3Hico2Pe","abs":"<p>In scientific reasoning tasks, the veracity of the reasoning process is as critical as the final outcome. While Process Reward Models (PRMs) offer a solution to the coarse-grained supervision problems inherent in Outcome Reward Models (ORMs), their deployment is hindered by the prohibitive cost of obtaining expert-verified step-wise labels. This paper addresses the challenge of training reliable PRMs using abundant but noisy \"weak\" supervision. We argue that existing Weak-to-Strong Generalization (W2SG) theories lack prescriptive guidelines for selecting high-quality training signals from noisy data. To bridge this gap, we introduce the Dual-Consensus Weak-to-Strong (DC-W2S) framework. By intersecting Self-Consensus (SC) metrics among weak supervisors with Neighborhood-Consensus (NC) metrics in the embedding space, we stratify supervision signals into distinct reliability regimes. We then employ a curriculum of instance-level balanced sampling and label-level reliability-aware masking to guide the training process. We demonstrate that DC-W2S enables the training of robust PRMs for complex reasoning without exhaustive expert annotation, proving that strategic data curation is more effective than indiscriminate training on large-scale noisy datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>과학적 추론 과제에서는 추론 과정의 진실성 또한 최종 결과만큼 중요하다. Process Reward Models (PRMs)는 Outcome Reward Models (ORMs)에 내재된 거친 supervision 문제에 대한 해결책을 제공하지만, 전문가가 검증한 step-wise label을 획득하는 데 드는 과도한 비용 때문에 배포가 어렵다. 본 논문은 풍부하지만 잡음이 많은 \"weak\" supervision을 사용해 신뢰할 수 있는 PRM을 학습하는 문제를 다룬다. 우리는 기존 Weak-to-Strong Generalization (W2SG) 이론이 noisy data에서 고품질 training signal을 선택하기 위한 처방적 지침을 충분히 제공하지 못한다고 주장한다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 Dual-Consensus Weak-to-Strong (DC-W2S) 프레임워크를 제안한다. 약한 supervisor 간의 Self-Consensus (SC) metric과 embedding space에서의 Neighborhood-Consensus (NC) metric을 교차함으로써, 우리는 supervision signal을 서로 다른 신뢰도 regime으로 계층화한다. 그런 다음 instance-level balanced sampling과 label-level reliability-aware masking으로 구성된 curriculum을 사용하여 학습 과정을 유도한다. 우리는 DC-W2S가 광범위한 전문가 annotation 없이도 복잡한 추론을 위한 강건한 PRM 학습을 가능하게 하며, 대규모 noisy dataset에 무차별적으로 학습하는 것보다 전략적 데이터 선별이 더 효과적임을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65243","en":"Guideline-Grounded Evidence Accumulation for High-Stakes Agent Verification","ko":"고위험 에이전트 검증을 위한 지침 기반 증거 축적","authors":"Yichi Zhang, Nabeel Seedat, Yinpeng Dong, Peng Cui, Jun Zhu, Mihaela van der Schaar","pos":"#814","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FP23eFYhAy","abs":"<p>As LLM-powered agents have been used for high-stakes decision-making, such as clinical diagnosis, it becomes critical to develop reliable verification of their decisions to facilitate trustworthy deployment. Yet, existing verifiers usually underperform owing to a lack of domain knowledge and limited calibration. To address this, we establish <strong>GLEAN</strong>, an agent verification framework with <strong>G</strong>uide<strong>L</strong>ine-grounded <strong>E</strong>vidence <strong>A</strong>ccumulatio<strong>N</strong> that compiles expert-curated protocols into trajectory-informed, well-calibrated correctness signals. GLEAN evaluates the step-wise alignment with domain guidelines and aggregates multi-guideline ratings into surrogate features, which are accumulated along the trajectory and calibrated into correctness probabilities using Bayesian logistic regression. Moreover, the estimated uncertainty triggers active verification, which selectively collects additional evidence for uncertain cases via expanding guideline coverage and performing differential checks. We empirically validate GLEAN with agentic clinical diagnosis across three diseases from the MIMIC-IV dataset, surpassing the best baseline by 12\\% in AUROC and 50\\% in Brier score reduction, which confirms the effectiveness in both discrimination and calibration. In addition, the expert study with clinicians recognizes GLEAN's utility in practice.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM-powered agent가 clinical diagnosis와 같은 high-stakes decision-making에 사용되면서, 신뢰할 수 있는 배치를 위해 이들의 결정을 안정적으로 검증하는 일이 매우 중요해졌다. 그러나 기존 verifier는 대체로 domain knowledge 부족과 제한된 calibration 때문에 성능이 낮다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 <strong>GLEAN</strong>을 제안한다. 이는 <strong>G</strong>uide<strong>L</strong>ine-grounded <strong>E</strong>vidence <strong>A</strong>ccumulatio<strong>N</strong>를 갖춘 agent verification framework로, expert-curated protocol을 trajectory-informed하고 well-calibrated한 correctness signal로 컴파일한다. GLEAN은 step-wise로 domain guideline과의 alignment를 평가하고, multi-guideline rating을 surrogate feature로 집계한 뒤, 이를 trajectory를 따라 누적하여 Bayesian logistic regression을 통해 correctness probability로 calibration한다. 또한 추정된 uncertainty는 active verification을 유도하여, guideline coverage를 확장하고 differential check를 수행함으로써 불확실한 사례에 대해 추가 evidence를 선택적으로 수집한다. 우리는 MIMIC-IV dataset의 세 가지 질병에 대한 agentic clinical diagnosis로 GLEAN을 실증적으로 검증했으며, AUROC에서 최고의 baseline을 12\\% 상회하고 Brier score reduction에서 50\\% 개선을 보여, discrimination과 calibration 모두에서의 효과를 확인했다. 더 나아가 clinician과의 expert study에서도 GLEAN의 실용성이 인정되었다.</p>"},{"id":"65875","en":"Training-Free Multimodal Large Language Model Orchestration","ko":"학습 불필요 멀티모달 대형 언어 모델 오케스트레이션","authors":"Tianyu Xie, Yuexiao Ma, Yuhang Wu, Wang Chen, Jiayi Ji, Tat-Seng Chua, Xiawu Zheng, Rongrong Ji","pos":"#1613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9DKnuvRbSM","abs":"<p>Building interactive omni-modal assistants often relies on end-to-end multimodal alignment to fuse heterogeneous modalities, which incurs substantial data and compute costs and limits extensibility. We present Training-Free Large Language Model Orchestration (LLM Orchestration), a training-free orchestration framework that integrates off-the-shelf modality experts into a unified multimodal input--output system without additional gradient-based training for integration. LLM Orchestration comprises three components: (1) an LLM controller that infers user intent and emits explicit control tokens for expert selection and sequencing, enabling protocol-constrained and auditable routing; (2) a text-centric cross-modal memory that compresses multimodal evidence into structured records for lightweight retrieval and reuse, reducing redundant expert invocations across turns; and (3) a unified interaction layer that executes routing and memory decisions to support consistent modality transitions, full-duplex streaming, and interruption-aware dialogue. Across diverse multimodal benchmarks, LLM Orchestration achieves strong performance under standard evaluation constraints while maintaining low orchestration overhead and modular upgradeability, providing a practical alternative to costly joint training for omni-modal systems.</p>"},{"id":"66164","en":"OMAC: A Holistic Optimization Framework for LLM-Based Multi-Agent Collaboration","ko":"OMAC: LLM 기반 다중 에이전트 협업을 위한 총체적 최적화 프레임워크","authors":"Shijun Li, Hilaf Hasson, Joydeep Ghosh","pos":"#1806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6C4YQcq8YX","abs":"<p>Agents powered by advanced large language models (LLMs) have demonstrated impressive capabilities across diverse complex applications. Recently, Multi-Agent Systems (MAS), wherein multiple agents collaborate and communicate with each other, have exhibited enhanced capabilities in complex tasks, such as high-quality code generation and arithmetic reasoning. However, the development of such systems often relies on handcrafted methods, and the literature on systematic design and optimization of LLM-based MAS remains limited.  In this work, we introduce OMAC, a general framework designed for holistic optimization of LLM-based MAS. Specifically, we identify five key optimization dimensions for MAS, encompassing both agent functionality and collaboration structure. Building upon these dimensions, we first propose a general algorithm, utilizing two actors termed the Semantic Initializer and the Contrastive Comparator, to optimize any single dimension. Then, we present an algorithm for joint optimization across multiple dimensions. Extensive experiments demonstrate the superior performance of OMAC on diverse tasks against recent approaches. Codes are available at: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/OMAC-Sub-3FF8.</p>"},{"id":"63188","en":"Context-Driven Incremental Compression for Multi-Turn Dialogue Generation","ko":"다중 턴 대화 생성을 위한 문맥 기반 증분 압축","authors":"Yeongseo Jung, Jaehyeok Kim, Eunseo Jung, Jiachuan Wang, Yongqi Zhang, Ka Chun Cheung, Simon See, Lei Chen","pos":"#2105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZGeVMaiIlb","abs":"<p>Modern conversational agents condition on an ever-growing dialogue history at each turn, incurring redundant attention and encoding costs that grow with conversation length. Naive truncation or summarization degrades fidelity, while existing context compressors lack cross-turn memory sharing or revision, causing information loss and compounding errors in long dialogues. We revisit the context compression under conversational dynamics and empirically present its fragility. To improve both efficiency and robustness, we introduce Context-Driven Incremental Compression (C-DIC), which treats a conversation as interleaved contextual threads and stores revisable per-thread compression states in a single, compact dialogue memory. At each turn, a lightweight retrieve → revise → write-back loop shares information across turns and updates stale memories, stabilizing long-horizon behavior. In addition, we adapt truncated backpropagation-through-time (TBPTT) to our multi-turn setting, learning cross-turn dependencies without full-history backpropagation. Extensive experiments on long-form dialogue benchmarks demonstrate superior performance and efficiency of C-DIC; notably, C-DIC maintains near-constant inference time and stable perplexity even over hundreds of dialogue turns, supporting a scalable path to high-quality dialogue modeling.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대의 conversational agent는 각 turn마다 점점 길어지는 dialogue history에 조건화되며, 이로 인해 대화 길이에 따라 redundant attention과 encoding 비용이 증가한다. 단순한 truncation이나 summarization은 fidelity를 떨어뜨리고, 기존 context compressor는 turn 간 memory sharing이나 revision이 부족하여 정보 손실과 장기 대화에서의 오류 누적을 초래한다. 우리는 conversational dynamics 하에서의 context compression을 재검토하고, 그 취약성을 실증적으로 보인다. 효율성과 robustness를 모두 개선하기 위해, 우리는 대화를 interleaved contextual thread로 간주하고 각 thread별로 수정 가능한 compression state를 하나의 compact dialogue memory에 저장하는 Context-Driven Incremental Compression (C-DIC)를 제안한다. 각 turn마다 lightweight retrieve → revise → write-back loop가 turn 간 정보를 공유하고 오래된 memory를 갱신하여 장기적 행동을 안정화한다. 또한, 우리는 truncated backpropagation-through-time (TBPTT)을 다중 turn 설정에 맞게 적응시켜, 전체 history에 대한 backpropagation 없이 cross-turn dependency를 학습한다. 장문 대화 benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 C-DIC의 우수한 성능과 효율성을 보여준다. 특히 C-DIC는 수백 개의 dialogue turn에 걸쳐서도 거의 일정한 inference time과 안정적인 perplexity를 유지하여, 고품질 dialogue modeling을 위한 확장 가능한 경로를 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"63959","en":"STAR-VAE: Structured Topology-Aware Regularization for Audio Reconstruction and Generation","ko":"STAR-VAE: 오디오 복원과 생성을 위한 구조적 위상 인식 정규화","authors":"Huadai Liu, Wen Wang, Kaicheng Luo, Qian Chen, Xiangang Li, Wei Xue","pos":"#2304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SDWG5xr20c","abs":"<p>Continuous Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) serve as the fundamental continuous tokenizer for modern neural audio generation systems, enabling high-fidelity reconstruction while providing a compact, smooth latent space for downstream generative priors. However, continuous VAEs face a fundamental conflict when balancing \\textit{compression rate}, \\textit{reconstruction fidelity}, and \\textit{latent space topology}—a challenge we formalize as the \\textbf{Rate-Distortion-Regularity Trilemma}. This trilemma stems from a critical \\textit{topological mismatch}: the prevailing isotropic Gaussian prior in standard VAEs imposes a \\textit{flat} latent geometry that fails to accommodate audio's \\textit{hierarchical} nature, where low-frequency components are structured and compressible while high-frequency components are stochastic and incompressible, leading to \\textit{disordered information packing} where crucial semantic features are randomly interleaved with high-entropy noise. To resolve this challenge, we propose \\textbf{Structured Topology-Aware Regularization (STAR)}, a general training strategy that reshapes latent space geometry by imposing a growth-based constraint field, routing structural and textural information into channel subspaces with matching capacities. STAR is applicable to any VAE architecture and effectively resolves the trilemma, as demonstrated in CNN-based VAEs. To fully exploit STAR's potential, we present \\textbf{STAR-VAE}, combining STAR with a hybrid CNN-Mamba architecture that synergizes local feature extraction with linear-complexity global context modeling, achieving state-of-the-art performance. We further propose \\textbf{STAR-Gen}, an LLM-based Flow Matching framework that leverages STAR-VAE's structured latent space for high-fidelity generation without suffering from vector quantization artifacts. Empirical results demonstrate that STAR-VAE successfully resolves the trilemma, achieving state-of-the-art reconstruction fidelity and enhanced semantic information preservation across diverse audio domains. The structured latent space improves both traditional diffusion models and our \\textbf{STAR-Gen} paradigm, achieving state-of-the-art performance in text-to-audio generation. The project page is available at~\\url{https://STAR-VAE.github.io}.</p>","absKo":"<p>Continuous Variational Autoencoders (VAEs)는 현대 neural audio generation systems의 기본적인 continuous tokenizer로서, downstream generative prior를 위한 compact하고 smooth한 latent space를 제공하면서도 high-fidelity reconstruction을 가능하게 한다. 그러나 continuous VAE는 \\textit{compression rate}, \\textit{reconstruction fidelity}, \\textit{latent space topology} 사이의 균형을 맞추는 데 근본적인 충돌을 겪으며, 이를 우리는 \\textbf{Rate-Distortion-Regularity Trilemma}로 정식화한다. 이 trilemma는 핵심적인 \\textit{topological mismatch}에서 비롯된다. standard VAE에서 널리 쓰이는 isotropic Gaussian prior는 \\textit{flat}한 latent geometry를 강제하는데, 이는 audio의 \\textit{hierarchical}한 성질을 수용하지 못한다. 즉, low-frequency component는 구조화되고 압축 가능하지만 high-frequency component는 stochastic하고 압축 불가능하기 때문에, 중요한 semantic feature가 높은 entropy의 noise와 무작위로 뒤섞이는 \\textit{disordered information packing}이 발생한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 \\textbf{Structured Topology-Aware Regularization (STAR)}를 제안한다. STAR는 growth-based constraint field를 부과하여 latent space geometry를 재구성하고, structural information과 textural information을 각각 그에 맞는 capacity를 가진 channel subspace로 라우팅하는 범용 training strategy이다. STAR는 어떤 VAE architecture에도 적용 가능하며, CNN-based VAE에서 보이듯이 이 trilemma를 효과적으로 해소한다. STAR의 잠재력을 충분히 활용하기 위해 우리는 \\textbf{STAR-VAE}를 제시한다. 이는 local feature extraction과 linear-complexity global context modeling을 시너지 있게 결합하는 hybrid CNN-Mamba architecture와 STAR를 통합한 것으로, state-of-the-art performance를 달성한다. 더 나아가 우리는 \\textbf{STAR-Gen}을 제안한다. 이는 STAR-VAE의 structured latent space를 활용하여 vector quantization artifact 없이 high-fidelity generation을 수행하는 LLM-based Flow Matching framework이다. 실험 결과는 STAR-VAE가 trilemma를 성공적으로 해소하며, 다양한 audio domain에서 state-of-the-art reconstruction fidelity와 향상된 semantic information preservation을 달성함을 보여준다. 구조화된 latent space는 전통적인 diffusion model과 우리의 \\textbf{STAR-Gen} paradigm 모두를 개선하여, text-to-audio generation에서 state-of-the-art performance를 달성한다. 프로젝트 페이지는~\\url{https://STAR-VAE.github.io}에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"61537","en":"HieraMAS: Optimizing Intra-Node LLM Mixtures and Inter-Node Topology for Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"HieraMAS: Multi-Agent Systems를 위한 Intra-Node LLM Mixtures와 Inter-Node Topology 최적화","authors":"Tianjun Yao, Zhaoyi Li, Zhiqiang Shen","pos":"#2606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=p7p5foAXaB","abs":"<p>Multi-agent systems (MAS) built on large language models (LLMs) have demonstrated remarkable performance across diverse tasks. Existing approaches optimize communication topology, role assignment, or LLM routing in isolation, while treating each agent as a monolithic unit—failing to exploit internal LLM mixtures that can enhance individual role capabilities. We propose <strong><code>HieraMAS</code></strong>, a hierarchical agent collaboration framework with intra-node LLM mixtures and inter-node communication topology. HieraAgent introduces <em>supernodes</em>, where each functional role comprises multiple heterogeneous LLMs in a propose-synthesis structure. The optimization of <strong><code>HieraMAS</code></strong> poses unique credit assignment challenges, as final task performance heavily depends on LLM capabilities, potentially causing erroneous reinforcement of suboptimal configurations. We address this via a two-stage algorithm: (1) multi-level reward attribution providing fine-grained feedback at both node and system levels; and (2) graph classification treating topology selection as a holistic task rather than per-edge optimization. Experiments on reasoning and coding benchmarks demonstrate that <strong><code>HieraMAS</code></strong> significantly outperforms existing methods while achieving better cost-performance trade-offs.</p>","absKo":"<p>large language model(LLM) 기반 multi-agent system(MAS)은 다양한 task에서 놀라운 성능을 보여 왔다. 기존 접근은 communication topology, role assignment, 또는 LLM routing을 각각 독립적으로 최적화하는 반면, 각 agent를 하나의 monolithic unit으로 취급하여 개별 role 능력을 향상시킬 수 있는 내부 LLM mixture를 활용하지 못한다. 우리는 intra-node LLM mixture와 inter-node communication topology를 갖는 hierarchical agent collaboration framework인 <strong><code>HieraMAS</code></strong>를 제안한다. HieraAgent는 각 functional role이 propose-synthesis 구조의 여러 heterogeneous LLM으로 구성되는 supernode를 도입한다. <strong><code>HieraMAS</code></strong>의 최적화는 최종 task 성능이 LLM 능력에 크게 의존하기 때문에 독특한 credit assignment 문제를 유발하며, 그 결과 suboptimal configuration에 잘못된 reinforcement가 일어날 수 있다. 우리는 이를 두 단계 알고리즘으로 해결한다: (1) node 수준과 system 수준 모두에서 세밀한 feedback을 제공하는 multi-level reward attribution, 그리고 (2) topology selection을 edge별 최적화가 아니라 전체적 task로 취급하는 graph classification. reasoning과 coding benchmark에서의 실험은 <strong><code>HieraMAS</code></strong>가 기존 방법을 크게 능가하면서도 더 나은 cost-performance trade-off를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62215","en":"Scaling Transformers for End-to-End Discrete Audio Tokenization","ko":"End-to-End 이산 오디오 토큰화를 위한 Transformers 스케일링","authors":"Yitian Gong, Kuangwei Chen, Zhaoye Fei, Xiaogui Yang, Ke Chen, Yang Wang, Kexin Huang, Mingshu Chen, Ruixiao Li, Qinyuan Cheng, Shimin Li, Xipeng Qiu","pos":"#302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=icMRkTnuU7","abs":"Discrete audio tokenizers are fundamental to empowering large language models with native audio processing and generation capabilities. Despite recent progress, existing approaches often rely on pretrained encoders, semantic distillation, or heterogeneous CNN-based architectures. These designs introduce fixed inductive biases that limit reconstruction fidelity and hinder effective scaling. In this paper, we argue that discrete audio tokenization should be learned fully end-to-end using a homogeneous and scalable architecture.  Based on this perspective, we propose $\\textbf{TAC}$, a Transformer-based audio tokenizer that jointly optimizes the encoder, quantizer, and decoder from scratch for high-fidelity reconstruction of general audio. We show that a simple, fully end-to-end learned tokenizer built from homogeneous, causal Transformer blocks scales gracefully and supports high-fidelity reconstruction across diverse audio domains. Across speech, sound, and music, the proposed tokenizer consistently outperforms prior codecs over a wide range of bitrates, while exhibiting predictable improvements with increased scale. Notably, leveraging TAC’s discrete tokens, we develop the first purely autoregressive TTS model that surpasses prior non-autoregressive and cascaded systems. Furthermore, TAC enables competitive ASR performance without auxiliary encoders. Our findings position TAC as a unified, scalable interface for the next generation of native audio foundation models.","absKo":"이산 오디오 토크나이저는 대규모 언어 모델이 기본적인 오디오 처리 및 생성 기능을 갖추도록 하는 데 핵심적이다. 최근 진전에도 불구하고, 기존 접근법은 사전학습된 encoder, semantic distillation, 또는 heterogeneous CNN 기반 아키텍처에 의존하는 경우가 많다. 이러한 설계는 고정된 inductive bias를 도입하여 reconstruction fidelity를 제한하고 효과적인 scaling을 저해한다. 본 논문에서는 이산 오디오 tokenization은 homogeneous하고 scalable한 아키텍처를 사용해 완전히 end-to-end 방식으로 학습되어야 한다고 주장한다. 이 관점에 기반하여, 우리는 일반 오디오의 고충실도 reconstruction을 위해 encoder, quantizer, decoder를 처음부터 공동 최적화하는 Transformer 기반 오디오 tokenizer인 $\\textbf{TAC}$을 제안한다. 우리는 homogeneous한 causal Transformer block으로 구성된 단순하고 완전한 end-to-end 학습 tokenizer가 우아하게 scale되며 다양한 오디오 도메인에서 고충실도 reconstruction을 지원함을 보인다. 음성, sound, music 전반에서, 제안한 tokenizer는 폭넓은 bitrate 범위에서 기존 codec을 일관되게 능가하며, 규모가 커질수록 예측 가능한 향상을 보인다. 특히 TAC의 discrete token을 활용해, 우리는 기존 non-autoregressive 및 cascaded system을 능가하는 최초의 순수 autoregressive TTS 모델을 개발한다. 또한 TAC는 auxiliary encoder 없이도 경쟁력 있는 ASR 성능을 가능하게 한다. 우리의 결과는 TAC를 차세대 native audio foundation model을 위한 통합적이고 scalable한 interface로 자리매김한다."},{"id":"63007","en":"Beyond Confidence: Adaptive and Coherent Decoding for Diffusion Language Models","ko":"Confidence를 넘어: Diffusion Language Models를 위한 적응형·일관성 있는 디코딩","authors":"Kecheng Chen, Ziru Liu, Xijia Tao, Hui Liu, Xinyu Fu, Suiyun Zhang, Dandan Tu, Lingpeng Kong, Rui Liu, Haoliang Li","pos":"#313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=b0O96emqNj","abs":"<p>Diffusion Language Models (DLMs) have recently achieved significant success due to their any-order generation capabilities. However, existing inference methods typically rely on local, immediate-step metrics—such as confidence or entropy—which inherently lack a more reliable perspective, leading to sub-optimal generation quality. To address this, we propose <strong>C</strong>oherent <strong>C</strong>ontextual <strong>D</strong>ecoding (<strong>CCD</strong>), a novel inference framework built upon two core innovations. First, CCD bypasses the potential bias of the single context to leverage historical contexts for approximating the marginal distribution of token prediction, leading to better sequence coherence and the early rejection of sub-optimal paths. More importantly, we demonstrate that this mechanism is theoretically equivalent to modeling the consistency of historical steps via the conditional mutual information between contexts and token predictions. Finally, CCD achieves significantly milder performance degradation under highly parallel decoding scenarios compared to baselines. Empirically, our method achieves a simultaneous enhancement in both inference speed and performance across diverse benchmarks on Dream and LLaDA.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion Language Models(DLMs)는 최근 any-order generation capability 덕분에 큰 성공을 거두었다. 그러나 기존 inference method는 일반적으로 confidence나 entropy와 같은 local한 immediate-step metric에 의존하는데, 이는 본질적으로 더 신뢰할 만한 관점을 제공하지 못해 sub-optimal generation quality로 이어진다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 <strong>C</strong>oherent <strong>C</strong>ontextual <strong>D</strong>ecoding(<strong>CCD</strong>)을 제안한다. 이는 두 가지 핵심 혁신 위에 구축된 새로운 inference framework이다. 첫째, CCD는 단일 context가 가질 수 있는 잠재적 bias를 우회하여 historical context를 활용해 token prediction의 marginal distribution을 근사하며, 이를 통해 sequence coherence를 향상시키고 sub-optimal path를 조기에 배제한다. 더 중요하게는, 이 메커니즘이 context와 token prediction 사이의 conditional mutual information을 통해 historical step의 consistency를 모델링하는 것과 이론적으로 동등함을 보인다. 마지막으로, CCD는 highly parallel decoding scenario에서 baseline에 비해 performance degradation이 훨씬 완만하다. 실험적으로, 우리의 방법은 Dream과 LLaDA 전반의 다양한 benchmark에서 inference speed와 performance를 동시에 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"65794","en":"Does Reinforcement Fine-Tuning Improve Generalization of LLM Agents?  An Empirical Study","ko":"강화 파인튜닝이 LLM 에이전트의 일반화를 향상시키는가? 실증 연구","authors":"Zhiheng Xi, Xin Guo, Jiaqi Liu, Jiazheng Zhang, Yutao Fan, Zhihao Zhang, Shichun Liu, Mingxu Chai, Xiaowei Shi, Yitao Zhai, Xunliang Cai, Tao Gui, Qi Zhang, Xuanjing Huang","pos":"#3609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A4wPhPe6nW","abs":"<p>Reinforcement fine-tuning (RFT) has shown promise for training LLM agents to perform multi-turn decision-making based on environment feedback. However, most existing evaluations remain largely in-domain—training and testing are conducted in the same environment or even on the same tasks.  In real-worlddeployment, agents may operate in unseen environments with different background knowledge, observation spaces, and action interfaces. To characterize the generalization profile of RFT under such shifts, we conduct a systematic study along three axes: (1) within-environment generalization across task difficulty, (2) cross-environment transfer to unseen environments, and (3) sequential multi-environment training to quantify transfer and forgetting. Our results show that RFT generalizes well across task difficulty within an environment, but exhibits unstable transfer to unseen environments, which correlates with shifts in both semantic priors and observation/action interfaces. In contrast, sequential training yields promising downstream gains with minimal upstream forgetting, and mixture training across environments improves the overall balance. We further provide detailed analyses and deeper insights, and hope our work helps the community develop and deploy generalizable LLM agents.</p>"},{"id":"66590","en":"$\\tau$-Voice: Benchmarking Full-Duplex Voice Agents on Real-World Domains","ko":"$\\tau$-Voice: 실세계 도메인에서 Full-Duplex 음성 에이전트 벤치마킹","authors":"Soham Ray, Keshav Dhandhania, Victor Barres, Karthik Narasimhan","pos":"#4600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2Oj6fg0m1j","abs":"Full-duplex voice agents—systems that listen and speak simultaneously—are rapidly moving from research to production. However, existing evaluations address conversational dynamics and task completion in isolation. We introduce $\\tau$-voice, a benchmark for evaluating voice agents on grounded tasks with real-world complexity: agents must navigate complex multi-turn conversations, adhere to domain policies, and interact with the environment. The framework extends $\\tau^2$-bench into a novel voice agent benchmark combining verifiable completion of complex grounded tasks, full-duplex interaction, and realistic audio—enabling direct comparison between voice and text performance. A controllable and realistic voice user simulator provides diverse accents, realistic audio environments, and rich turn-taking dynamics; by decoupling simulation from wall-clock time, the user simulator can use the most capable LLM without real-time constraints. We evaluate task completion (pass@1) and voice interaction quality across 278 tasks: while GPT-5 (reasoning) achieves 80\\%, voice agents reach only 29--42\\% under clean conditions and 19--30\\% under realistic conditions with noise and diverse accents—a 50--61pp gap; qualitative analysis confirms 75--90\\% of failures stem from agent behavior, suggesting that observed failures primarily reflect agent behavior under our evaluation setup. $\\tau$-voice provides a reproducible testbed for measuring progress toward voice agents that are natural, conversational, and reliable."},{"id":"63282","en":"Toward Robust Multilingual Adaptation of LLMs for Low-Resource Languages","ko":"저자원 언어를 위한 LLM의 견고한 다국어 적응을 향하여","authors":"Haolin Li, Haipeng Zhang, Mang Li, Yaohua Wang, Lijie Wen, Yu Zhang, Biqing Huang","pos":"#501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YPq13MlFgO","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) continue to struggle with low-resource languages, primarily due to limited training data, translation noise, and unstable cross-lingual alignment. To address these challenges, we propose LiRA (Linguistic Robust Anchoring for LLMs)—a plug-and-play framework that requires only lightweight fine-tuning on top of existing pretrained backbones. LiRA jointly optimizes representation stability and cross-lingual semantic consistency by combining two key components: Arca (Anchored Representation Composition Architecture), which aligns low-resource inputs to a shared English semantic space through anchor-based alignment and collaborative encoding; and LaSR (Language-coupled Semantic Reasoner), a lightweight, language-aware head that enforces consistency regularization for unified cross-lingual understanding, retrieval, and reasoning. We theoretically show that under controlled anchoring error and translation-induced bias, LiRA guarantees bounded representation deviation and stable downstream performance under local Lipschitz continuity. To facilitate research, we release a new multilingual product retrieval dataset covering five Southeast Asian and two South Asian languages. Extensive experiments across diverse low-resource benchmarks demonstrate consistent improvements in retrieval, ranking, question answering, and reasoning tasks. Code will be publicly available on GitHub, and the dataset will be hosted on Hugging Face.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)는 제한된 학습 데이터, 번역 노이즈, 불안정한 cross-lingual alignment 때문에 여전히 저자원 언어에서 어려움을 겪는다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 기존 pretrained backbone 위에 가벼운 fine-tuning만 필요로 하는 plug-and-play framework인 LiRA (Linguistic Robust Anchoring for LLMs)를 제안한다. LiRA는 두 가지 핵심 구성요소를 결합하여 representation stability와 cross-lingual semantic consistency를 공동으로 최적화한다. 하나는 anchor-based alignment와 collaborative encoding을 통해 저자원 입력을 공유 English semantic space에 정렬하는 Arca (Anchored Representation Composition Architecture)이고, 다른 하나는 통합된 cross-lingual understanding, retrieval, reasoning을 위해 consistency regularization을 강제하는 lightweight, language-aware head인 LaSR (Language-coupled Semantic Reasoner)이다. 우리는 제어된 anchoring error와 translation-induced bias 하에서 LiRA가 bounded representation deviation과 local Lipschitz continuity 하의 안정적인 downstream 성능을 보장함을 이론적으로 보인다. 연구를 촉진하기 위해, 우리는 Southeast Asian 언어 5개와 South Asian 언어 2개를 포함하는 새로운 multilingual product retrieval dataset을 공개한다. 다양한 low-resource benchmark 전반의 광범위한 실험은 retrieval, ranking, question answering, reasoning task에서 일관된 성능 향상을 보여준다. 코드는 GitHub에 공개될 예정이며, dataset은 Hugging Face에 호스팅될 것이다.</p>"},{"id":"62733","en":"Self-Guidance: Enhancing Neural Codecs via Decoder Manifold Alignment","ko":"Self-Guidance: Decoder Manifold Alignment로 Neural Codec 강화","authors":"Xiang Li, Yixuan Zhou, Xie, Zhiyong Wu, Hui Wang","pos":"#502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=druaDr7zNI","abs":"<p>Neural speech codecs based on Vector-Quantized VAEs (VQ-VAEs) are core audio tokenizers for speech LLMs, yet their reconstruction fidelity is bottlenecked by quantization error. Instead of modifying the quantizer or increasing model capacity—common approaches that complicate downstream language modeling—we introduce self-guidance, a simple yet general training principle that enhances the decoder's robustness to quantization error. Our core idea is to align the decoder's internal feature manifolds when processing both the quantized tokens and their original continuous embeddings, using a lightweight feature-mapping loss. This requires minimal training overhead and no inference-time changes. Applied to XCodec2, self-guidance improves all reconstruction metrics, achieving state-of-the-art low-bitrate performance. It generalizes across codebook sizes, quantizer types, and network architectures, demonstrating value as a universal codec enhancer. Notably, it enables a 4× codebook reduction without fidelity loss, which downstream TTS experiments show significantly improves LLM-based synthesis by simplifying the token modeling space. Self-guidance thus establishes an efficient, broadly applicable method for high-fidelity neural audio coding.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vector-Quantized VAE (VQ-VAE) 기반의 neural speech codec은 speech LLM의 핵심 audio tokenizer이지만, reconstruction fidelity가 quantization error에 의해 병목된다. quantizer를 수정하거나 model capacity를 늘리는 대신, downstream language modeling을 복잡하게 만드는 일반적 접근법과 달리, 우리는 decoder가 quantization error에 대해 더 robust해지도록 하는 간단하면서도 일반적인 training principle인 self-guidance를 도입한다. 핵심 아이디어는, quantized token과 원래의 continuous embedding을 모두 처리할 때 decoder의 내부 feature manifold를 lightweight feature-mapping loss를 사용해 정렬하는 것이다. 이는 최소한의 training overhead만 필요하며 inference-time 변경도 없다. XCodec2에 적용했을 때 self-guidance는 모든 reconstruction metric을 개선하며 state-of-the-art low-bitrate 성능을 달성한다. 이 방법은 codebook size, quantizer type, network architecture 전반에 걸쳐 일반화되며, universal codec enhancer로서의 가치를 입증한다. 특히 fidelity 손실 없이 codebook을 4배 축소할 수 있게 하며, downstream TTS 실험은 token modeling space가 단순화되어 LLM 기반 synthesis가 크게 향상됨을 보여준다. 따라서 self-guidance는 고충실도 neural audio coding을 위한 효율적이고 폭넓게 적용 가능한 방법을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"64195","en":"SAM Audio: Segment Anything in Audio","ko":"SAM Audio: 오디오에서의 Segment Anything","authors":"Bowen Shi, Andros Tjandra, John Hoffman, Helin Wang, YI-CHIAO WU, Luya Gao, Julius Richter, Matthew Le, Apoorv Vyas, Sanyuan Chen, Christoph Feichtenhofer, Piotr Dollár, Wei-Ning Hsu, Ann Lee","pos":"#503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Q4Cca8N7na","abs":"<p>General audio source separation is a key capability for multimodal AI systems that can perceive and reason about sound. Despite substantial progress in recent years, existing separation models are either domain-specific, designed for fixed categories such as speech or music, or limited in controllability, supporting only a single prompting modality such as text. In this work, we present SAM AUDIO, a foundation model for general audio separation that unifies text, visual, and temporal span prompting within a single framework. Built on a diffusion transformer architecture, SAM AUDIO is trained with flow matching on large-scale audio data spanning speech, music, and general sounds, and can flexibly separate target sources described by language, visual masks, or temporal spans. The model achieves state-of-the-art performance across a diverse suite of benchmarks, including general sound, speech, music, and musical instrument separation in both in-the-wild and professionally produced audios, substantially outperforming prior general-purpose and specialized systems. Furthermore, we introduce a new real-world separation benchmark with human-labeled multimodal prompts and a reference-free evaluation model that correlates strongly with human judgment.</p>","absKo":"<p>일반 audio source separation은 소리를 인지하고 추론할 수 있는 multimodal AI system의 핵심 역량이다. 최근 몇 년간 상당한 진전이 있었지만, 기존 separation model은 speech나 music처럼 고정된 범주를 대상으로 설계된 domain-specific 모델이거나, text와 같은 하나의 prompting modality만 지원하는 식으로 controllability가 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 text, visual, temporal span prompting을 하나의 framework로 통합하는 general audio separation용 foundation model인 SAM AUDIO를 제시한다. diffusion transformer architecture 위에 구축된 SAM AUDIO는 speech, music, general sound 전반의 대규모 audio data로 flow matching을 사용해 학습되며, language, visual mask, temporal span으로 기술된 target source를 유연하게 분리할 수 있다. 이 모델은 wild 환경과 professionally produced audio 모두에서 general sound, speech, music, musical instrument separation을 포함한 다양한 benchmark 전반에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하며, 기존의 범용 및 특화 시스템을 크게 능가한다. 더 나아가, 우리는 human-labeled multimodal prompt를 포함하는 새로운 real-world separation benchmark와 human judgment와 강하게 상관되는 reference-free evaluation model도 제안한다.</p>"},{"id":"64119","en":"S3Audio: Towards Streaming Synchronized Spatial Audio Generation via Autoregressive Diffusion Transformer","ko":"S3Audio: 자기회귀 Diffusion Transformer를 통한 스트리밍 동기화 공간 오디오 생성","authors":"Ke Lei, Yu Zhang, Changhao Pan, Xueyi Pu, Wenxiang Guo, Ruiqi Li, Zhou Zhao","pos":"#504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QlKWT5s4Wy","abs":"<p>Real-time and accurate spatial audio generation is pivotal for delivering an immersive experience.  However, existing spatial audio synthesis technologies are often encumbered by a tradeoff between generation quality and high inference latency, as well as difficulty in capturing precise spatial information from multimodal inputs.  To address these challenges, we propose S3Audio, a unified streaming framework for high-fidelity spatial audio generation from panoramic videos and text prompts. S3Audio mainly makes the following contributions: 1) We introduce a causal autoregressive diffusion transformer architecture that enables streaming high-quality spatial audio generation. 2) We design a Spatial Video–Audio Contrastive (SVAC) learning strategy to align the video encoder with the acoustic domain, and further employ a multi-objective online direct preference optimization~(ODPO) scheme, resulting in strong spatial perception and robust multimodal spatial audio synthesis. 3) To alleviate the current scarcity of spatial audio datasets, we also develop an automated annotation pipeline for generating detailed spatial captions.  Experimental results demonstrate that S3Audio achieves superior performance in both video-to-spatial and text-to-spatial audio generation tasks. Demos can be found at: \\url{https://s3audio.github.io}</p>","absKo":"<p>실시간이고 정확한 spatial audio 생성은 몰입형 경험을 제공하는 데 핵심적이다. 그러나 기존의 spatial audio 합성 기술은 종종 생성 품질과 높은 inference latency 사이의 trade-off, 그리고 multimodal input에서 정밀한 spatial information을 포착하는 어려움에 의해 제약을 받는다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 panoramic video와 text prompt로부터 고충실도 spatial audio를 생성하는 unified streaming framework인 S3Audio를 제안한다. S3Audio의 주요 기여는 다음과 같다. 1) streaming 고품질 spatial audio 생성을 가능하게 하는 causal autoregressive diffusion transformer architecture를 도입한다. 2) video encoder를 acoustic domain과 정렬하기 위해 Spatial Video–Audio Contrastive(SVAC) learning strategy를 설계하고, 더 나아가 multi-objective online direct preference optimization(ODPO) scheme을 적용하여 강한 spatial perception과 견고한 multimodal spatial audio 합성을 달성한다. 3) 현재의 spatial audio dataset 부족을 완화하기 위해, 세부적인 spatial caption을 생성하는 자동 주석 파이프라인도 개발한다. 실험 결과는 S3Audio가 video-to-spatial 및 text-to-spatial audio 생성 작업 모두에서 우수한 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 데모는 다음에서 확인할 수 있다: \\url{https://s3audio.github.io}</p>"},{"id":"62650","en":"PosterAgent: Agentic Poster Generation via Stage-Aware Reinforcement Learning","ko":"PosterAgent: Stage-Aware Reinforcement Learning 기반 Agentic Poster 생성","authors":"Zhuocheng Yu, Feng Zhang, Sujian Li, Kai Jia","pos":"#505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ehKGFkxIo7","abs":"<p>Poster generation is a complex task demanding a harmonious integration of visual aesthetics and information hierarchy. While recent text-to-image models have advanced visual synthesis, they remain non-editable and struggle with precise text rendering. Conversely, existing layout-generation methods offer structure but typically rely on static, one-shot predictions, lacking the mechanism for self-correction essential to professional design. Inspired by the iterative workflow of human designers, we introduce PosterAgent, a novel framework that reformulates poster creation as an agentic workflow involving initial drafting followed by iterative refinement. To effectively train this multi-turn capability, we propose Stage-Aware Reinforcement Learning (SARL), which decouples the optimization into draft-specific and refinement-specific phases, ensuring precise credit assignment for both initial drafting and incremental refinement actions.  Extensive experiments demonstrate that PosterAgent significantly outperforms strong baselines, validating the potential of agentic systems in graphic design.</p>","absKo":"<p>Poster generation은 시각적 미학과 정보 계층 구조의 조화로운 통합을 요구하는 복잡한 작업이다. 최근 text-to-image model은 시각 합성 능력을 발전시켰지만, 편집이 불가능하고 정확한 text rendering에 어려움을 겪는다. 반대로 기존 layout-generation 방법은 구조를 제공하지만 대개 정적인 one-shot prediction에 의존하여, 전문적인 디자인에 필수적인 자기 수정 메커니즘이 부족하다. 인간 디자이너의 반복적 workflow에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 poster 제작을 초기 draft 이후 반복적 refinement를 수행하는 agentic workflow로 재정식화하는 새로운 프레임워크 PosterAgent를 제안한다. 이러한 multi-turn capability를 효과적으로 학습하기 위해, 우리는 최적화를 draft-specific 단계와 refinement-specific 단계로 분리하여 초기 drafting과 점진적 refinement 행동 모두에 대해 정밀한 credit assignment를 보장하는 Stage-Aware Reinforcement Learning (SARL)을 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 PosterAgent가 강력한 baseline을 크게 능가함을 보여 주며, 그래픽 디자인에서 agentic system의 가능성을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61119","en":"PhaseCoder: Microphone Geometry-Agnostic Spatial Audio Understanding for Multimodal LLMs","ko":"PhaseCoder: Multimodal LLM을 위한 마이크 배열 무관 Spatial Audio Understanding","authors":"Artem Dementyev, Wazeer Zulfikar, Sinan Hersek, Pascal Getreuer, Anurag Kumar, Vivek Kumar","pos":"#507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tU3raVqvYe","abs":"<p>Current multimodal LLMs process audio as a mono stream, ignoring the rich spatial information essential for embodied AI. Existing spatial audio models, conversely, are constrained to fixed microphone geometries, preventing deployment across diverse devices. We present PhaseCoder, a transformer-only spatial audio encoder that is agnostic to microphone geometry. PhaseCoder takes raw multichannel audio and microphone coordinates as inputs to perform localization and produces robust spatial embeddings. We integrate PhaseCoder with the Gemma 3n LLM by finetuning it to reason over ``spatial audio tokens''. We show our encoder achieves state-of-the-art results on microphone-invariant localization benchmarks and, for the first time, enables an LLM to perform complex spatial reasoning and targeted transcription tasks from an arbitrary microphone array.</p>","absKo":"<p>현재의 multimodal LLM은 audio를 mono stream으로 처리하여, embodied AI에 필수적인 풍부한 spatial information을 무시한다. 반면 기존 spatial audio model은 고정된 microphone geometry에 제약되어 있어 다양한 device에 배포하기 어렵다. 우리는 microphone geometry에 구애받지 않는 transformer-only spatial audio encoder인 PhaseCoder를 제안한다. PhaseCoder는 raw multichannel audio와 microphone coordinate를 입력으로 받아 localization을 수행하고, 견고한 spatial embedding을 생성한다. 우리는 PhaseCoder를 Gemma 3n LLM과 결합하여, 이를 ``spatial audio token'' 위에서 추론하도록 finetuning한다. 우리의 encoder가 microphone-invariant localization benchmark에서 state-of-the-art 결과를 달성하며, 처음으로 LLM이 임의의 microphone array로부터 복잡한 spatial reasoning과 targeted transcription task를 수행할 수 있게 됨을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66271","en":"Neural-Inspired Modeling of Auditory Selection and Compensation for Audio-Visual Speech Separation","ko":"오디오-비주얼 음성 분리를 위한 청각 선택과 보상의 신경 영감 모델링","authors":"Xinmeng Xu, Haoran Xie, Xiaohui Tao, Lin Li, S. Joe Qin","pos":"#508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5EXWftfZlE","abs":"<p>Current audio-visual speech separation (AVSS) models typically rely on implicit multimodal fusion, but the absence of explicit modality alignment and reliability modeling often causes semantic misalignment and contaminates speech representations. The brain addresses this with a hierarchy: top-down auditory selection uses visual priors to maintain target-consistent acoustics, while bottom-up cross-modal compensation integrates temporally aligned articulatory cues to reconstruct and stabilize speech. Guided by this principle, we present Neuro-SCNet, an AVSS architecture that makes selection and compensation explicit and reliability-aware. The Auditory Selection Mechanism applies top-down, visually guided gain along the audio pathway to isolate target time-frequency units and suppress distractors. The module preserves the auditory trace with an identity bypass and adds controlled visual refinements via a residual path. A synchrony-driven gate reduces the influence of low-confidence visual cues. Additionally, a lightweight pre-alignment for visual feature pre-processing estimates and corrects small temporal offsets, and a compact magnitude-phase encoder is used to preserve fine acoustic detail to stabilize reconstruction. Evaluations on LRS2, LRS3, and VoxCeleb2 show state-of-the-art separation with improved efficiency, supporting the value of explicit selection and reliability-aware compensation.</p>"},{"id":"61578","en":"NaviAgent: Graph‑Driven Bilevel Planning for Scalable Tool Orchestration","ko":"NaviAgent: 확장 가능한 Tool Orchestration을 위한 Graph-Driven Bilevel Planning","authors":"Yan Jiang, HAO ZHOU, Lizhong Gu, Tianlong Li, Ruinan Jin, Wanqi Zhou, Ai Han","pos":"#509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=omRyEle4jZ","abs":"Large Language Models (LLMs) increasingly act as function call agents that invoke external tools to tackle tasks beyond their static knowledge. However, they typically invoke tools one at a time without a global view of task structure. As tools often depend on one another, this leads to error accumulation and poor scalability, particularly when scaling to hundreds or thousands of tools. To address these limitations, we propose NaviAgent, an explicit bilevel architecture that decouples task planning from tool execution through graph‑based modeling of tool relations. At the planning level, the LLM‑based agent decides whether to respond directly, clarify intent, or retrieve and execute a toolchain independent of inter‑tool complexity. At the execution level, a Tool World Navigation Model (TWNM) encodes structural and behavioral relations among tools, steering the agent to compose scalable and robust invocation sequences. Incorporating feedback from real tool interactions, NaviAgent achieves closed‑loop alignment between planning and execution, enabling adaptive navigation in large‑scale tool ecosystems. Evaluations on API-Bank and ToolBench show consistent improvements in task success rate (TSR), with TWNM boosting performance on complex tasks by up to 17 points. Further tests on 50 real APIs across 7 domains confirm a average 10\\% improvement in TSR over $\\alpha$‑UMI with fewer steps and lower latency, demonstrating robust generalization under real world dynamics.","absKo":"LLM(Large Language Model)은 점점 더 static knowledge를 넘어서는 과제를 수행하기 위해 external tool을 호출하는 function call agent로 활용되고 있다. 그러나 이들은 대개 task 구조에 대한 전역적 관점 없이 한 번에 하나의 tool만 호출한다. Tool들은 종종 서로 의존하므로, 이는 error accumulation과 poor scalability로 이어지며, 특히 수백 개 또는 수천 개의 tool로 확장할 때 더욱 심각해진다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 graph-based modeling of tool relations을 통해 task planning과 tool execution을 분리하는 explicit bilevel architecture인 NaviAgent를 제안한다. planning level에서 LLM-based agent는 inter-tool complexity와 무관하게 직접 응답할지, 의도를 명확히 할지, 또는 toolchain을 검색하고 실행할지를 결정한다. execution level에서 Tool World Navigation Model(TWNM)은 tool 간 구조적 및 행동적 관계를 인코딩하여 agent가 확장 가능하고 강건한 invocation sequence를 구성하도록 유도한다. 실제 tool interaction으로부터의 feedback을 통합함으로써, NaviAgent는 planning과 execution 사이의 closed-loop alignment를 달성하여 대규모 tool ecosystem에서 adaptive navigation을 가능하게 한다. API-Bank와 ToolBench 평가에서는 task success rate(TSR)가 일관되게 향상되었으며, TWNM은 복잡한 과제에서 최대 17 point까지 성능을 끌어올렸다. 또한 7개 도메인의 50개 real API에 대한 추가 실험은 더 적은 step과 더 낮은 latency로 $\\alpha$‑UMI 대비 TSR이 평균 10\\% 향상됨을 확인했으며, 실제 세계의 동적 환경에서의 강건한 일반화를 입증했다.</p>"},{"id":"66187","en":"How Far Can LLM Agents Reason with Tables? Benchmarking Multi-Turn Agentic Table Question Answering in the Wild","ko":"LLM 에이전트는 표로 얼마나 추론할 수 있는가? 실세계 다중 턴 에이전트형 표 질의응답 벤치마킹","authors":"Jingwang Huang, Jie Zhang, Haoyang Zeng, Changzai Pan, Xianjie Wu, Guanting Dong, Jiaheng Liu, Wei Zhang, Mingyu Zheng, Chunxiao Liu, Kaiwen Wei, Jiang Zhong, Jian Yang","pos":"#510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5yZAgkjGQ0","abs":"<p>Recent advances in large language models (LLMs) have substantially expanded the scope of Table Question Answering (TableQA). However, existing benchmarks primarily treat TableQA as a passive, single-turn natural language understanding task, lacking the capacity to evaluate autonomous reasoning and tool-call trajectories in realistic, multi-turn scenarios. To bridge this gap, we introduce TableAgent-Bench, a large-scale bilingual benchmark that reformulates TableQA as proactive, agentic interactions over structurally complex, multi-table environments. With a topology-aware construction strategy, TableAgent-Bench captures dynamic intent evolution through 1,310 multi-turn dialogues grounded in 2,275 industrial tables. Furthermore, we propose the Table-centric Agent Evaluation Framework (TAEF) to assess agent interactions with complex table structures. Specifically, TAEF integrates a specialized agent toolset and 4 metric categories to systematically diagnose intermediate failure modes, assessing performance across table localization, tool-invocation rationality, and trajectory-level pass rate. Extensive experiments with 25 state-of-the-art LLM agents reveal a substantial capability gap, with even the strongest model Gemini-3-Pro-Preview achieving only 53.4% information coverage. We expect TableAgent-Bench to serve as a rigorous testbed for developing and evaluating agents capable of robust table-centric reasoning.</p>"},{"id":"63269","en":"Graph-R1: Towards Agentic GraphRAG Framework via End-to-end Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Graph-R1: 종단간 강화학습을 통한 에이전트형 GraphRAG 프레임워크를 향하여","authors":"Haoran Luo, Haihong E, Guanting Chen, Qika Lin, Yikai Guo, Fangzhi Xu, Zemin Kuang, Meina Song, Xiaobao Wu, Yifan Zhu, Anh Tuan Luu","pos":"#512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YXnFGsSkCC","abs":"<p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) mitigates hallucination in LLMs by incorporating external knowledge, but relies on chunk-based retrieval that lacks structural semantics. GraphRAG methods improve RAG by modeling knowledge as entity-relation graphs, but still face challenges in high construction cost, fixed one-time retrieval, and reliance on long-context reasoning and prompt design. To address these challenges, we propose Graph-R1, an agentic GraphRAG framework via end-to-end reinforcement learning (RL). It introduces lightweight knowledge hypergraph construction, models retrieval as a multi-turn agent-environment interaction, and optimizes the agent process via an end-to-end reward mechanism. Experiments on standard RAG datasets show that Graph-R1 outperforms traditional GraphRAG and RL-enhanced RAG methods in reasoning accuracy, retrieval efficiency, and generation quality. Our code is available.</p>","absKo":"<p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)은 외부 지식을 통합함으로써 LLM의 hallucination을 완화하지만, 구조적 의미를 갖지 못하는 chunk-based retrieval에 의존한다. GraphRAG 방법은 지식을 entity-relation graph로 모델링하여 RAG를 개선하지만, 여전히 높은 construction cost, 고정된 일회성 retrieval, 그리고 long-context reasoning 및 prompt design에 대한 의존이라는 문제에 직면한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 end-to-end reinforcement learning (RL)을 통한 agentic GraphRAG framework인 Graph-R1을 제안한다. 이 방법은 경량 knowledge hypergraph construction을 도입하고, retrieval을 multi-turn agent-environment interaction으로 모델링하며, end-to-end reward mechanism을 통해 agent process를 최적화한다. 표준 RAG dataset에서 수행한 실험은 Graph-R1이 reasoning accuracy, retrieval efficiency, generation quality 측면에서 기존 GraphRAG 및 RL-enhanced RAG 방법들을 능가함을 보여준다. 코드는 공개되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"66431","en":"Dual-View Predictive Diffusion: Lightweight Speech Enhancement via Spectrogram-Image Synergy","ko":"Dual-View 예측 Diffusion: 스펙트로그램-이미지 시너지를 통한 경량 음성 향상","authors":"Ke Xue, Rongfei Fan, Kai Li, Shanping Yu, Puning Zhao, Jianping An","pos":"#513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3qX5RS8kpJ","abs":"<p>Diffusion models have recently set new benchmarks in Speech Enhancement (SE). However, most existing score-based models treat speech spectrograms merely as generic 2D images, applying uniform processing that ignores the intrinsic structural sparsity of audio, which results in inefficient spectral representation and prohibitive computational complexity. To bridge this gap, we propose <strong>DVPD</strong>, an extremely lightweight <strong>D</strong>ual-<strong>V</strong>iew <strong>P</strong>redictive <strong>D</strong>iffusion model, which uniquely exploits the dual nature of spectrograms as both visual textures and physical frequency-domain representations across both training and inference stages. Specifically, during training, we optimize spectral utilization via the Frequency-Adaptive Non-uniform Compression (FANC) encoder, which preserves critical low-frequency harmonics while pruning high-frequency redundancies. Simultaneously, we introduce a Lightweight Image-based Spectro-Awareness (LISA) module to capture features from a visual perspective with minimal overhead. During inference, we propose a Training-free Lossless Boost (TLB) strategy that leverages the same dual-view priors to refine generation quality without any additional fine-tuning. Extensive experiments across various benchmarks demonstrate that DVPD achieves state-of-the-art performance while requiring only <strong>35</strong> of the parameters and <strong>40%</strong> of the inference MACs compared to SOTA lightweight model, PGUSE. These results highlight DVPD's superior ability to balance high-fidelity speech quality with extreme architectural efficiency. Code and audio samples are available at the anonymous website: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/dvpd_demo-E630</p>"},{"id":"60804","en":"CoCoEmo: Composable and Controllable Human-Like Emotional TTS via Activation Steering","ko":"CoCoEmo: Activation Steering을 통한 조합 가능하고 제어 가능한 인간형 감정 TTS","authors":"Siyi Wang, Shihong Tan, Siyi Liu, Hong Jia, Gongping Huang, James Bailey, Ting Dang","pos":"#611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wW2LIHSCfw","abs":"<p>Emotional expression in human speech is nuanced and compositional, often involving multiple, sometimes conflicting, affective cues that may diverge from linguistic content. In contrast, most expressive text-to-speech (TTS) systems enforce a single utterance-level emotion, collapsing affective diversity and suppressing mixed or text–emotion–misaligned expression. While activation steering via latent direction vectors offers a promising solution, it remains unclear whether emotion representations are linearly steerable in TTS, where steering should be applied within hybrid TTS architectures, and how such complex emotion behaviors should be evaluated. This paper presents the first systematic analysis of activation steering for emotional control in hybrid TTS models, introducing a quantitative, controllable steering framework, and multi-rater evaluation protocols that enable composable mixed-emotion synthesis and reliable text–emotion mismatch synthesis. Our results demonstrate, for the first time, that emotional prosody and expressive variability are primarily synthesized by the TTS language module instead of the flow-matching module, and also provide a lightweight steering approach for generating natural, human-like emotional speech.</p>","absKo":"<p>human speech의 감정 표현은 미묘하고 조합적이며, 언어적 내용과 어긋날 수도 있는 여러 감정 단서가 때로는 서로 충돌하기도 한다. 반면 대부분의 expressive text-to-speech (TTS) 시스템은 단일 utterance-level emotion을 강제해 감정의 다양성을 축소하고, 혼합된 표현이나 text–emotion–misaligned expression을 억제한다. latent direction vector를 이용한 activation steering은 유망한 해법이지만, TTS에서 감정 표현이 선형적으로 steer 가능한지, steering을 hybrid TTS architecture의 어느 지점에 적용해야 하는지, 그리고 이러한 복잡한 감정 행동을 어떻게 평가해야 하는지는 여전히 불분명하다. 이 논문은 hybrid TTS 모델에서 감정 제어를 위한 activation steering의 첫 체계적 분석을 제시하며, 정량적이고 제어 가능한 steering framework와 multi-rater evaluation protocol을 도입해 composable mixed-emotion synthesis와 신뢰할 수 있는 text–emotion mismatch synthesis를 가능하게 한다. 우리의 결과는 처음으로 emotional prosody와 expressive variability가 flow-matching module이 아니라 TTS language module에서 주로 합성된다는 점을 보여주며, 자연스럽고 human-like한 emotional speech 생성을 위한 경량 steering 접근법도 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61304","en":"ConsMSA: Semantic Distribution Consistency Learning for Multimodal Sentiment Analysis","ko":"ConsMSA: Multimodal Sentiment Analysis를 위한 의미 분포 일관성 학습","authors":"Pan Wang, Lipeng Ke, Huajun Ying, Pritish Mohapatra, Rohan Sarkar, Suresh Lakhani, sankar venkataraman, Jingtong Hu","pos":"#612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rWTqAgyZcd","abs":"Multimodal sentiment analysis (MSA) aims to predict human sentiments by integrating signals from different modalities such as text, video, and audio. However, raw multimodal sequences often suffer from semantic inconsistencies--exhibiting redundancy or conflicts within and across modalities--which hinders robust understanding and increases computational cost. To this end, we introduce ConsMSA, which explicitly formalizes semantic distribution consistency across both \\textit{intra}- and \\textit{inter}-modality, providing a principled mechanism for robust and efficient multimodal sentiment prediction. Specifically, ConsMSA projects multimodal token features into a shared sentiment space to compute an Intra- and Inter-modality Consistency Score ($I^2CS$). By coupling this score with predictive relevance, we formulate principled importance signals that are utilized: (i) as a consistency regularizer to align latent distributions during training, (ii) to derive semantic-aware weights for adaptive multimodal token reweighting, and (iii) as a principled criterion to prune redundant or conflicting tokens. Extensive experiments on CMU-MOSI and CMU-MOSEI demonstrate that ConsMSA achieves state-of-the-art performance while remaining robust under aggressive token compression--retaining only 10\\% of tokens yields comparable accuracy.  These results establish semantic distribution consistency as a principled foundation for synergizing predictive robustness with computational efficiency.","absKo":"Multimodal sentiment analysis (MSA)는 text, video, audio와 같은 서로 다른 modality의 신호를 통합하여 인간의 감성을 예측하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 raw multimodal sequence는 종종 semantic inconsistency를 겪는데, 이는 modality 내부 및 modality 간에서 redundancy나 conflict로 나타나며, 견고한 이해를 저해하고 계산 비용을 증가시킨다. 이를 위해 우리는 ConsMSA를 제안한다. ConsMSA는 \\\\textit{intra}-modality와 \\\\textit{inter}-modality 전반에서 semantic distribution consistency를 명시적으로 정식화하여, robust하고 효율적인 multimodal sentiment prediction을 위한 원리 기반 메커니즘을 제공한다. 구체적으로, ConsMSA는 multimodal token feature를 shared sentiment space로 투영하여 Intra- and Inter-modality Consistency Score ($I^2CS$)를 계산한다. 이 점수를 predictive relevance와 결합하여, 우리는 다음에 활용되는 원리적 importance signal을 구성한다: (i) 학습 중 latent distribution을 정렬하기 위한 consistency regularizer로서, (ii) adaptive multimodal token reweighting을 위한 semantic-aware weight를 도출하기 위해, 그리고 (iii) redundant하거나 conflicting token을 prune하기 위한 원리적 기준으로서. CMU-MOSI와 CMU-MOSEI에서의 광범위한 실험은 ConsMSA가 aggressive token compression 하에서도 견고함을 유지하면서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. token의 10%만 유지해도 비교 가능한 정확도를 얻는다. 이러한 결과는 semantic distribution consistency가 predictive robustness와 computational efficiency를 시너지 있게 결합하는 원리적 기반임을 입증한다."},{"id":"60946","en":"Do Audio LLMs Listen or Read? Analyzing and Mitigating Paralinguistic Failures with VoxParadox","ko":"Audio LLM은 듣는가, 읽는가? VoxParadox로 Paralinguistic Failure 분석 및 완화","authors":"Jiacheng Pang, Ashutosh Chaubey, Mohammad Soleymani","pos":"#613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v7rYbRR9Zw","abs":"<p>Audio large language models (Audio LLMs) demonstrate strong performance on speech understanding tasks, yet their ability to understand paralinguistic information remains limited. To systematically quantify this issue, we introduce VoxParadox, an adversarial benchmark with 2,000 verified examples, spanning 10 paralinguistic tasks, created with controlled speech synthesis to intentionally mismatch transcript claims and speaking style, enabling direct measurement of speech paralinguistic understanding. Evaluation of a diverse set of Audio LLMs reveals consistently low accuracy on acoustic ground truth and a strong tendency to follow language-implied (incorrect) answers. To understand the cause of this gap, we perform layer wise probing and find that (i) paralinguistic cues can degrade in deeper encoder layers and at the encoder–LLM interface, and (ii) even when such cues are available in audio tokens, the language model frequently ignores them. To address these problems, we propose Prompt-Conditioned Layer Mixer (PCLM), which adaptively combines information from multiple audio layers based on the input prompt, and pair it with Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) to explicitly prefer acoustically supported options over language-implied alternatives. These methods substantially improve Audio LLM paralinguistic understanding, improving Audio Flamingo 3 from 17.40% to 65.20% on VoxParadox, and from 37.74% to 54.78% on MMSU paralinguistic subset.</p>","absKo":"<p>Audio large language models (Audio LLMs)은 speech understanding task에서 강력한 성능을 보이지만, paralinguistic information을 이해하는 능력은 여전히 제한적이다. 이 문제를 체계적으로 정량화하기 위해 우리는 VoxParadox를 소개한다. 이는 2,000개의 검증된 example로 구성된 adversarial benchmark로, transcript의 주장과 speaking style이 의도적으로 불일치하도록 통제된 speech synthesis를 사용하여 만들어졌으며, speech paralinguistic understanding을 직접 측정할 수 있게 한다. 다양한 Audio LLMs를 평가한 결과, acoustic ground truth에 대한 정확도는 일관되게 낮았고 language-implied (잘못된) answer를 따르려는 경향이 강하게 나타났다. 이러한 격차의 원인을 이해하기 위해 우리는 layer-wise probing을 수행했고, (i) paralinguistic cue가 더 깊은 encoder layer와 encoder-LLM interface에서 약화될 수 있으며, (ii) 그런 cue가 audio token에 존재하더라도 language model이 이를 자주 무시한다는 사실을 발견했다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Prompt-Conditioned Layer Mixer (PCLM)를 제안한다. 이는 입력 prompt에 따라 여러 audio layer의 정보를 적응적으로 결합하며, Direct Preference Optimization (DPO)과 함께 사용해 언어적으로 암시된 대안보다 음향적으로 뒷받침되는 선택지를 명시적으로 선호하도록 한다. 이러한 방법은 Audio LLM의 paralinguistic 이해를 크게 향상시켜, Audio Flamingo 3의 성능을 VoxParadox에서 17.40%에서 65.20%로, MMSU paralinguistic subset에서는 37.74%에서 54.78%로 끌어올린다.</p>"},{"id":"63817","en":"Plan Then Action: High-Level Planning Guidance Reinforcement Learning  for LLM Reasoning","ko":"Plan Then Action: LLM 추론을 위한 고수준 계획 유도 강화학습","authors":"Zhihao Dou, Qinjian Zhao, Zhongwei Wan, Zhang Dinggen, Weida Wang, Benteng Chen, Towsif Raiyan, Qingtao Pan, Yang Ouyang, Chaoda Song, Zhiqiang Gao, shufei zhang, Sumon Biswas","pos":"#1812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TTuzGDlGNA","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) demonstrate strong reasoning abilities via Chain-of-Thought (CoT), but their token-level generation encourages local decisions and lacks global planning, often leading to redundant or inaccurate reasoning. Existing methods, such as tree-based search and reinforcement learning (RL), attempt to address this issue but incur high computational costs and still struggle to produce reliable reasoning trajectories. To address these challenges, we propose Plan-Then-Action Enhanced Reasoning with Group Relative Policy Optimization (PTA-GRPO), a two-stage framework designed to jointly improve high-level planning and fine-grained CoT reasoning.  Specifically, in the first stage, a given LLM is responsible for summarizing CoT reasoning into compact high-level guidance, which is then leveraged for supervised fine-tuning. Then, we introduce a guidance-aware reinforcement learning method that jointly optimizes the final output and the quality of guidance, enhancing reasoning effectiveness. We evaluate PTA-GRPO on ten reasoning benchmarks across mathematics and natural sciences, using five diverse base models spanning multiple data modalities. The results show that PTA-GRPO consistently delivers stable and significant improvements across models and tasks, demonstrating strong effectiveness and generalization.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model(LLM)은 Chain-of-Thought(CoT)를 통해 강력한 reasoning 능력을 보이지만, token-level generation은 local decision을 유도하고 global planning이 부족하여 종종 중복되거나 부정확한 reasoning으로 이어진다. tree-based search와 reinforcement learning(RL) 같은 기존 방법은 이 문제를 해결하려 시도하지만, 계산 비용이 높고 여전히 신뢰할 수 있는 reasoning trajectory를 생성하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 이러한 도전에 대응하기 위해 우리는 Plan-Then-Action Enhanced Reasoning with Group Relative Policy Optimization(PTA-GRPO)을 제안한다. 이는 high-level planning과 fine-grained CoT reasoning을 함께 향상시키도록 설계된 two-stage framework이다. 구체적으로 첫 번째 단계에서 주어진 LLM은 CoT reasoning을 간결한 high-level guidance로 요약하는 역할을 맡으며, 이후 이를 supervised fine-tuning에 활용한다. 그런 다음 final output과 guidance의 품질을 공동 최적화하는 guidance-aware reinforcement learning 방법을 도입하여 reasoning effectiveness를 향상시킨다. 우리는 수학과 자연과학 전반의 10개 reasoning benchmark에서, 여러 data modality를 포괄하는 5개의 다양한 base model을 사용하여 PTA-GRPO를 평가한다. 결과는 PTA-GRPO가 모델과 task 전반에서 일관되게 안정적이고 유의미한 개선을 제공하며, 강한 효과와 generalization을 보여줌을 나타낸다.</p>"},{"id":"60559","en":"Self-Soupervision: Cooking Model Soups without Labels","ko":"Self-Soupervision: 라벨 없이 모델 수프 만들기","authors":"Anthony Fuller, James Green, Evan Shelhamer","pos":"#1502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=z0UM7y0L4r","abs":"<p>Model soups are strange and strangely effective combinations of parameters. They take a model (the stock), fine-tune it into multiple models (the ingredients), and then mix their parameters back into one model (the soup) to improve predictions. While all known soups require supervised learning, and optimize the same loss on labeled data, our recipes for Self-Soupervision generalize soups to self-supervised learning (SSL). Our Self-Souping lets us flavor ingredients on new data sources, e.g. from unlabeled data from a task for transfer or from a shift for robustness. We show that Self-Souping on corrupted test data, then fine-tuning back on uncorrupted train data, boosts robustness by +3.5% (ImageNet-C) and +7% (LAION-C). Self-Soupervision also unlocks countless SSL algorithms to cook the diverse ingredients needed for more robust soups. We show for the first time that ingredients can differ in their SSL hyperparameters---and more surprisingly, in their SSL algorithms. We cook soups of MAE, MoCoV3, and MMCR ingredients that are more accurate than any one single SSL ingredient.</p>","absKo":"<p>Model soup은 parameter의 기묘하면서도 놀라울 정도로 효과적인 조합이다. 하나의 model(stock)을 가져와 여러 모델(ingredients)로 fine-tune한 뒤, 그들의 parameter를 다시 하나의 모델(soup)로 섞어 예측 성능을 개선한다. 알려진 모든 soup이 supervised learning을 사용하고 labeled data에 대해 같은 loss를 최적화하는 반면, 우리의 Self-Soupervision 레시피는 soup을 self-supervised learning(SSL)으로 일반화한다. 우리의 Self-Souping은 transfer를 위한 task의 unlabeled data나 robustness를 위한 shift와 같은 새로운 data source에서 ingredient를 flavoring할 수 있게 해준다. 우리는 corrupted test data에서 Self-Souping을 수행한 뒤 uncorrupted train data로 다시 fine-tuning하면 robustness가 ImageNet-C에서 +3.5%, LAION-C에서 +7% 향상된다는 것을 보였다. Self-Soupervision은 또한 더 robust한 soup에 필요한 다양한 ingredient를 만들기 위해 수많은 SSL algorithm을 활용할 수 있게 한다. 우리는 처음으로 ingredient가 SSL hyperparameter뿐 아니라, 더욱 놀랍게도 SSL algorithm에서도 서로 다를 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 MAE, MoCoV3, MMCR ingredient로 soup을 만들었고, 이 soup은 어떤 단일 SSL ingredient보다 더 높은 정확도를 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"60765","en":"Learning to Theorize the World from Observation","ko":"관찰로부터 세계를 이론화하는 법 학습","authors":"Doojin Baek, Gyubin Lee, Junyeob Baek, Hosung Lee, Sungjin Ahn","pos":"#1506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wsA8LgHU5U","abs":"<p>What does it mean to understand the world? Is it simply to predict future video frames? Developmental cognitive science suggests that understanding the world is fundamentally the process of constructing internal theories of how it works rather than mere prediction, even before language is acquired. However, in machine learning, it remains unclear how to endow AI systems with such theory-building capability from raw, non-textual observation alone. In this paper, we introduce Learning-to-Theorize (L2T), a learning paradigm in which an AI system acquires the ability to construct theories represented as executable programs directly from observation alone. To instantiate this paradigm, we propose the Neural Language-of-Thought Programmer, a neural model that induces and executes latent programs as explanations rather than task-specific predictors or policies. In experiments, we show that this formulation enables explanation-driven generalization, allowing observations to be understood in terms of the programs that generate them.</p>","absKo":"<p>세계를 이해한다는 것은 무엇을 의미하는가? 그것은 단지 미래의 video frame을 예측하는 것과 같은 것인가? 발달 인지과학은 세계 이해가 단순한 예측이 아니라, 언어를 습득하기 전부터 세계가 어떻게 작동하는지에 대한 internal theory를 구성하는 과정이라고 시사한다. 그러나 machine learning에서는 원시적이고 비텍스트적인 관찰만으로 AI system에 이러한 theory-building capability를 어떻게 부여할 수 있는지 아직 분명하지 않다. 본 논문에서는 Learning-to-Theorize (L2T)를 소개하는데, 이는 AI system이 관찰만으로 executable program 형태로 표현되는 theory를 구성하는 능력을 획득하는 learning paradigm이다. 이 paradigm을 구현하기 위해, 우리는 task-specific predictor나 policy가 아니라 설명으로서 latent program을 유도하고 실행하는 Neural Language-of-Thought Programmer를 제안한다. 실험을 통해, 이 formulation이 explanation-driven generalization을 가능하게 하여, 관찰을 그것을 생성하는 program의 관점에서 이해할 수 있음을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"60873","en":"MCP-Persona: Benchmarking LLM Agents on Personalized MCP Tools and Tasks","ko":"MCP-Persona: 개인화된 MCP Tool 및 Task에서 LLM Agent Benchmarking","authors":"Wenhao Wang, Peizhi Niu, Gongyi Zou, Xiyuan Yang, Jingxing Wang, Haoting Shi, Yaxin Du, Jingyi Chai, Xianghe Pang, shuo tang, Yanfeng Wang, Siheng Chen","pos":"#1800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vmT3p2w83l","abs":"<p>a transformative standard for connecting large language models (LLMs) with external data sources and tools, and has been rapidly adopted across personal applications and development platforms. However, existing benchmarks predominantly focus on generic information-seeking tools and fail to capture the practical challenges posed by personal social applications, where tools interact with individual accounts or local databases. To bridge this critical gap, we introduce MCP-Persona, the first benchmark specifically designed for evaluating agent performance on real-world, personalized MCP tools. MCP-Persona encompasses a diverse set of widely-used applications, ranging from social media platforms like Reddit and Xiaohongshu (Rednote) to enterprise collaboration suites such as Lark (Feishu) and Slack. Our extensive experiments on various state-of-the-art (SOTA) agents demonstrate their significant struggles with personalized tool use, thereby highlighting the benchmark's crucial role in identifying and addressing these limitations. MCP-Persona is publicly available at \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MCP-Persona-F85D}{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MCP-Persona-F85D}</p>","absKo":"<p>external data source와 tool을 large language model (LLM)과 연결하는 transformative standard로 자리 잡았으며, 개인용 애플리케이션과 개발 플랫폼 전반에 빠르게 채택되고 있다. 그러나 기존 benchmark는 주로 일반적인 정보 탐색 tool에 초점을 맞추고 있어, tool이 개별 계정이나 로컬 database와 상호작용하는 개인용 social application이 제기하는 실질적 어려움을 포착하지 못한다. 이러한 중요한 공백을 메우기 위해, 우리는 실제 personalized MCP tool에서의 agent 성능을 평가하도록 특별히 설계된 첫 benchmark인 MCP-Persona를 소개한다. MCP-Persona는 Reddit와 Xiaohongshu (Rednote) 같은 social media platform부터 Lark (Feishu)와 Slack 같은 enterprise collaboration suite에 이르기까지 널리 사용되는 다양한 application을 포괄한다. 다양한 state-of-the-art (SOTA) agent에 대한 광범위한 실험은 personalized tool use에서 이들이 크게 어려움을 겪는다는 점을 보여주며, 이를 통해 이 benchmark가 이러한 한계를 식별하고 해결하는 데 중요한 역할을 함을 부각한다. MCP-Persona는 \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MCP-Persona-F85D}{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MCP-Persona-F85D}에서 공개적으로 이용 가능하다</p>"},{"id":"64278","en":"Optimal Splitting of Language Models from Mixtures to Specialized Domains","ko":"혼합 모델에서 전문 도메인으로의 언어 모델 최적 분할","authors":"Skyler Seto, Pierre Ablin, Anastasiia Filippova, Jiayuan Ye, Louis Béthune, Angelos Katharopoulos, David Grangier","pos":"#1809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PCJE2swkGn","abs":"Language models achieve impressive performance on a variety of knowledge, language, and reasoning tasks due to the scale and diversity of pretraining data available.  The standard training recipe is a two-stage paradigm: pretraining first on the full corpus of data followed by specialization on a much smaller subset of high quality, specialized data from the full corpus. In the multi-domain setting, this involves continued pretraining of multiple models on each specialized domain, referred to as split model training.  We propose a method for pretraining multiple models independently over a general pretraining corpus, and determining the optimal compute allocation between pretraining and continued pretraining using scaling laws. Our approach accurately predicts the loss of a model of size $N$ with $D$ pretraining and $D'$ specialization tokens, and extrapolates to larger model sizes and number of tokens.  Applied to language model training, our approach improves performance consistently across common sense knowledge and reasoning benchmarks across different model sizes and compute budgets.","absKo":"언어 모델은 사전 학습 데이터의 규모와 다양성 덕분에 다양한 지식, 언어, 추론 task에서 인상적인 성능을 달성한다. 표준 학습 절차는 두 단계 paradigm이다. 먼저 전체 corpus로 pretraining을 수행한 뒤, 전체 corpus에서 추출한 훨씬 더 작은 고품질의 specialized data subset으로 specialization을 진행한다. multi-domain setting에서는 각 specialized domain에서 여러 모델을 계속 pretraining하는데, 이를 split model training이라고 부른다. 우리는 일반 pretraining corpus 위에서 여러 모델을 독립적으로 pretraining하고, scaling law를 사용해 pretraining과 continued pretraining 사이의 최적 compute allocation을 결정하는 방법을 제안한다. 우리의 접근은 크기 $N$의 모델이 $D$개의 pretraining token과 $D'$개의 specialization token을 가질 때의 loss를 정확하게 예측하며, 더 큰 model size와 token 수로 외삽한다. language model training에 적용했을 때, 우리의 접근은 서로 다른 model size와 compute budget 전반에서 common sense, knowledge, reasoning benchmark 모두에서 일관되게 성능을 향상시킨다."},{"id":"61985","en":"FAFO: Lossy KV Cache Compression for Lossless Inference Acceleration via Draftless Fumble Decoding","ko":"FAFO: draftless fumble decoding을 통한 손실 없는 추론 가속을 위한 손실 허용 KV cache compression","authors":"Hoang Anh Duy Le, Shaochen (Henry) Zhong, Yifan Lu, Yingtong Dou, Jiayi Yuan, Yu-Neng Chuang, Xiran Fan, Guanchu Wang, Yuzhong Chen, Xia Hu","pos":"#2010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kz7n1D8Y1o","abs":"<p>Lossy KV cache compression is a well-explored subfield of machine learning efficiency, with improved latency being one of its major gains. However, lossy compression techniques can fumble from time to time, exhibiting various — and often catastrophic — failure patterns that are not only difficult to resolve but sometimes even hard to identify in the first place, making the direct deployment of models with compressed KV cache a risky endeavor. In this work, we explore a way to preserve lossless generation quality while still benefiting from the acceleration provided by attending only to a compressed KV cache. Specifically, we draw inspiration from the n-gram candidate pool decoding paradigm pioneered by Lookahead Decoding — a largely overlooked and underdeveloped way to achieve efficient yet lossless decoding — where we purposely allow the model to Fumble Around with compressed KV cache to generate multiple lossy ''n-gram guesses'' with just one forward pass, while Find Out via lossless verification in the same forward pass in truly parallel fashion. From a conceptual standpoint, our proposed framework is compatible with all typical static or dynamic KV cache compression methods from the token dropping realm, thus opening up a new avenue for the stagnant n-gram decoding paradigm. Practically, we show that — with careful system support — this framework presents many useful traits that similar draftless baselines (e.g., Self-Speculative Decoding) simply cannot achieve, such as requiring only one set of KV cache and being far less sensitive to model, task, and input-length scenarios. Our comprehensive empirical results show FAFO provides 1.20-2.71x latency speedup over the original model, while consistently outperforming other lossless + draftless solutions by a large margin.</p>","absKo":"<p>Lossy KV cache compression은 machine learning efficiency의 잘 연구된 하위 분야로, latency 향상은 그 주요 이점 중 하나이다. 그러나 lossy compression 기법은 때때로 제대로 동작하지 못해, 다양한 - 그리고 종종 치명적인 - 실패 패턴을 보이는데, 이는 해결하기도 어렵고 처음부터 식별하기도 어려운 경우가 많아 compressed KV cache를 가진 모델을 직접 배포하는 것을 위험한 시도로 만든다. 본 연구에서는 compressed KV cache에만 attention하더라도 제공되는 acceleration의 이점을 누리면서도 lossless generation quality를 보존하는 방법을 탐구한다. 구체적으로는, Lookahead Decoding이 개척한 n-gram candidate pool decoding 패러다임에서 영감을 얻는다. 이는 효율적이면서도 lossless한 decoding을 달성하는, 대체로 간과되고 충분히 발전되지 않은 방식이다. 여기서 우리는 의도적으로 model이 compressed KV cache와 함께 Fumble Around하도록 하여, 하나의 forward pass만으로 여러 개의 lossy ''n-gram guesses''를 생성하게 하고, 같은 forward pass 안에서 lossless verification을 통해 Find Out을 진정한 병렬 방식으로 수행한다. 개념적으로 제안한 프레임워크는 token dropping 계열의 일반적인 static 또는 dynamic KV cache compression 방법들과 모두 호환되므로, 정체된 n-gram decoding 패러다임에 새로운 가능성을 연다. 실용적으로는, careful system support와 함께 이 프레임워크가 Self-Speculative Decoding과 같은 유사한 draftless baseline들이 단순히 달성할 수 없는 여러 유용한 특성을 제공함을 보인다. 예를 들어 KV cache를 한 세트만 필요로 하고, model, task, input-length 시나리오에 훨씬 덜 민감하다. 우리의 포괄적인 실험 결과는 FAFO가 원래 모델 대비 1.20-2.71x의 latency speedup을 제공하며, 다른 lossless + draftless 솔루션들을 일관되게 큰 폭으로 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64267","en":"DIVER: Diving Deeper into Distilled Data via Expressive Semantic Recovery","ko":"DIVER: 표현적 시맨틱 복원을 통한 증류 데이터 심층 탐구","authors":"Qianxin Xia, Zhiyong Shu, Wenbo Jiang, Jiawei Du, Jielei Wang, Guoming Lu","pos":"#2404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PL8qP67p6E","abs":"Dataset distillation aims to synthesize a compact proxy dataset that is unreadable or non-raw from the original dataset for privacy protection and highly efficient learning. However, previous approaches typically adopt a single-stage distillation paradigm, which suffers from learning specific patterns that overfit on a prior architecture, consequently suppressing the expression of semantics and leading to performance degradation across heterogeneous architectures. To address this issue, we propose a novel dual-stage distillation framework called ${\\textbf{DIVER}}$, which leverages the pre-trained diffusion model to dive deeper into $\\textbf{DI}$stilled data $\\textbf{V}$ia $\\textbf{E}$xpressive semantic $\\textbf{R}$ecovery,  a process of semantic inheritance, guidance, and fusion. Semantic inheritance distills high-level semantic knowledge of abstract distilled images into the latent space to filter out architecture-specific ``noise\" and retain the intrinsic semantics. Furthermore, semantic guidance improves the preservation of the original semantics by directing the reverse procedure. Ultimately, \\textcolor{red}{semantic fusion is designed to provide semantic guidance only during the concrete phase of the reverse process, preventing semantic ambiguity and artifacts while maintaining the guidance information.} Extensive experiments validate the effectiveness and efficiency of our method in improving classical distillation techniques and significantly improving cross-architecture generalization, requiring processing time comparable to raw DiT on ImageNet (256$\\times$256) with only 4 GB of GPU memory usage.","absKo":"Dataset distillation은 원본 dataset으로부터 개인정보 보호와 매우 효율적인 learning을 위해 읽을 수 없거나 raw가 아닌 compact proxy dataset을 합성하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 대개 단일 단계 distillation paradigm을 채택하는데, 이는 prior architecture에 과적합되는 특정 pattern을 학습하여 semantics의 표현을 억제하고, 결과적으로 heterogeneous architecture 전반에서 성능 저하를 초래한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 ${\\textbf{DIVER}}라는 새로운 dual-stage distillation framework를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크는 pre-trained diffusion model을 활용해, $\\textbf{DI}$stilled data를 $\\textbf{V}$ia $\\textbf{E}$xpressive semantic $\\textbf{R}$ecovery 방식으로 더 깊게 파고들며, semantic inheritance, guidance, fusion 과정으로 구성된다. Semantic inheritance는 abstract distilled image의 고수준 semantic knowledge를 latent space로 distill하여 architecture-specific ``noise\"를 걸러내고 본질적 semantics를 보존한다. 또한 semantic guidance는 reverse procedure를 유도함으로써 원래 semantics의 보존을 향상시킨다. 최종적으로 \\textcolor{red}{semantic fusion은 reverse process의 concrete phase 동안에만 semantic guidance를 제공하도록 설계되어, guidance 정보를 유지하면서 semantic ambiguity와 artifact를 방지한다.} 광범위한 실험은 우리의 방법이 기존 distillation 기법을 개선하고 cross-architecture generalization을 크게 향상시키는 데 효과적이고 효율적임을 검증한다. 이 방법은 ImageNet (256$\\\\times$256)에서 raw DiT와 비슷한 처리 시간만 필요하면서 GPU 메모리 사용량은 4 GB에 불과하다.</p>"},{"id":"60631","en":"Modular Pretraining Enables Access Control","ko":"모듈식 사전학습을 통한 접근 제어","authors":"Ethan Roland, Murat Cubuktepe, Erick Martinez, Stijn Servaes, Keenan Pepper, Michael Vaiana, Diogo de Lucena, Judd Rosenblatt, Addie Foote, Cem Anil, Alex Cloud","pos":"#2508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yIubI9l3IT","abs":"<p>AI developers face a dual-use dilemma. The same capability that helps one user cure a disease can help another synthesize one. This dilemma could be resolved by access control, granting different users access to different AI capabilities. A gold standard for access control would be to serve models with different capabilities to different users. However, training and deploying multiple models is prohibitively expensive. We address this challenge by developing gradient-routed mixture-of-experts (GR-MoE), a pretraining method that selectively updates experts to induce specialization. Ablating an expert at inference time removes its capability, approximating a model trained on filtered data. We evaluate GR-MoE on synthetic stories and realistic dual-use data spanning biology, cybersecurity, nuclear physics, and code. On realistic data, GR-MoE preserves performance on retained capabilities while achieving 30% compute efficiency on forget capabilities. GR-MoE limits recovery more effectively than post-hoc unlearning and preserves capabilities better than LoRA. GR-MoE's advantages improve when scaled from 48M to 2B parameters, approaching multiple data filtered models in a single training run.</p>","absKo":"<p>AI 개발자는 dual-use 딜레마에 직면한다. 한 사용자가 질병을 치료하도록 돕는 동일한 capability가 다른 사용자가 그것을 합성하도록 도울 수도 있다. 이 딜레마는 다른 사용자에게 서로 다른 AI capability를 부여하는 access control로 해결할 수 있다. access control의 gold standard는 서로 다른 capability를 가진 모델을 서로 다른 사용자에게 제공하는 것이다. 그러나 여러 모델을 학습하고 배포하는 것은 지나치게 비용이 많이 든다. 우리는 specialization을 유도하기 위해 expert를 선택적으로 업데이트하는 pretraining method인 gradient-routed mixture-of-experts (GR-MoE)를 개발함으로써 이 문제를 해결한다. inference time에 expert를 제거(ablation)하면 그 capability가 사라지며, 이는 filtered data로 학습된 모델을 근사한다. 우리는 생물학, cybersecurity, nuclear physics, code에 걸친 synthetic story와 현실적인 dual-use data에서 GR-MoE를 평가한다. 현실적인 데이터에서 GR-MoE는 보존된 capability에 대한 성능을 유지하면서 forget capability에 대해 30%의 compute efficiency를 달성한다. GR-MoE는 post-hoc unlearning보다 recovery를 더 효과적으로 제한하고, LoRA보다 capability를 더 잘 보존한다. GR-MoE의 장점은 48M에서 2B parameter로 확장될 때 향상되며, 단일 training run에서 여러 data filtered model에 근접한다.</p>"},{"id":"61530","en":"Shortcut-Resistant CAM Distillation for Long-Tailed Recognition","ko":"Long-Tailed Recognition을 위한 Shortcut-Resistant CAM Distillation","authors":"Wenhai Wan, Teng Zhang, Shao-Yuan Li, Xinrui Wang, Qiang-Sheng Hua, Songcan Chen","pos":"#2510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pDrQ4YeSIr","abs":"<p>Real-world datasets often follow a long-tailed distribution, making generalization to tail classes difficult. We revisit this problem through the lens of shortcut learning, where models prefer the easiest predictive cues (e.g., background or textures) over object-centric semantics, especially under scarce and biased supervision. We find that this tendency is amplified for tail classes: limited examples often share similar contexts, making non-semantic signals highly correlated and thus tempting shortcuts, whereas head classes with diverse appearances and environments encourage more stable object-focused representations. Motivated by this observation, we propose Shortcut-Resistant CAM Distillation (SRCD), a plug-and-play framework that transfers object-focused explanations from head to tail classes. SRCD operates in the Class Activation Map (CAM) space, where a CAM provides a class-specific spatial evidence map for a prediction. SRCD aggregates CAMs from a small set of head-class candidates into a shortcut-resistant teacher using an energy-model weighting based on coherence (Laplacian smoothness) and concentration (Hoyer sparsity), and distills it to the tail-class CAM. We provide a theoretical analysis that quantifies shortcut reliance as shortcut-region evidence mass in CAM space and shows that SRCD suppresses tail shortcuts. Extensive experiments on long-tailed benchmarks consistently improve strong baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>실세계 데이터셋은 종종 long-tailed distribution을 따르므로 tail class로의 generalization이 어렵다. 우리는 이 문제를 shortcut learning의 관점에서 다시 살펴본다. 여기서 모델은 특히 희소하고 편향된 supervision 하에서 객체 중심 semantics보다 가장 쉬운 예측 단서(예: background나 texture)를 선호한다. 우리는 이러한 경향이 tail class에서 더욱 강해짐을 발견했다. 제한된 예시는 종종 유사한 context를 공유하기 때문에 비의미적 신호가 매우 강하게 상관되어 shortcut을 유혹하는 반면, 다양한 외형과 환경을 가진 head class는 더 안정적인 객체 중심 representation을 촉진한다. 이러한 관찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 head class에서 tail class로 객체 중심 explanation을 전달하는 plug-and-play framework인 Shortcut-Resistant CAM Distillation (SRCD)을 제안한다. SRCD는 Class Activation Map (CAM) space에서 작동하며, CAM은 prediction에 대한 class-specific spatial evidence map을 제공한다. SRCD는 coherence (Laplacian smoothness)와 concentration (Hoyer sparsity)에 기반한 energy-model weighting을 사용해 소수의 head-class candidate로부터 CAM을 집계하여 shortcut-resistant teacher를 구성하고, 이를 tail-class CAM으로 distill한다. 우리는 CAM space에서 shortcut-region evidence mass로 shortcut 의존성을 정량화하는 이론적 분석을 제시하고, SRCD가 tail shortcut을 억제함을 보인다. long-tailed benchmark에서의 광범위한 실험은 강력한 baseline을 일관되게 개선한다.</p>"},{"id":"66147","en":"PsumQuant: In-line Post-training Partial Sum Quantizer for Energy Efficient NPU Inference","ko":"PsumQuant: 에너지 효율적 NPU 추론을 위한 인라인 사후 훈련 부분합 양자화기","authors":"Sangwoo Hwang, Yeeun Hong, Jaeha Kung","pos":"#2511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6Qbb6IcCVy","abs":"The rapid growth of deep neural networks (DNNs) has intensified the demand for efficient hardware acceleration under quantization.  While prior research has successfully reduced weight and activation precision, partial sums generated during accumulation often retain high precision, resulting in significant energy overhead. In this work, we analyze psum distributions in tiled architectures and reveal that within-tile outliers are input-dependent. We propose PsumQuant, a post-training, input-aware quantization that predicts psum scales on-the-fly. By leveraging the crest factor of input activations, our learnable scale predictor effectively bounds the psum bit-width while handling the extreme outliers in DNNs. Experimental results on a $128 \\times 128$ systolic array demonstrate that PsumQuant compresses psum precision down to 8-bit within only a 1\\% accuracy drop on ResNet-18 and a marginal 0.04 perplexity increase on Llama-3.1.  Furthermore, bit-width reduction with PsumQuant results in a 45\\% reduction in total energy with minimal accuracy loss, demonstrating that PsumQuant provides a highly efficient solution for actual NPU architectures."},{"id":"66083","en":"Dissecting Quantization Error: A Concentration-Alignment Perspective","ko":"양자화 오류 해부: 집중-정렬 관점","authors":"Marco Federici, Boris van Breugel, Paul Whatmough, Markus Nagel","pos":"#2602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7BoFyTPqMr","abs":"<p>Quantization can drastically increase the efficiency of large language and vision models, but typically incurs an accuracy drop. Recently, function-preserving transforms (e.g. rotations, Hadamard transform, channel-wise scaling) have been successfully applied to reduce post-training quantization error, yet a principled explanation remains elusive.   We analyze linear-layer quantization via the signal-to-quantization-noise ratio (SQNR), showing that for uniform integer quantization at a fixed bit width, SQNR decomposes into (i) the concentration of weights and activations (capturing spread and outliers), and (ii) the alignment of their dominant variation directions. This provides an actionable insight: enhancing alignment between weight and activation variation directions can reduce quantization error, complementing concentration-focused approaches. Motivated by this, we introduce Concentration–Alignment Transforms (CAT), a lightweight linear transformation that uses a covariance estimate from a small calibration set to jointly improve concentration and alignment, approximately maximizing SQNR. Experiments across several LLMs show that CAT consistently matches or outperforms prior transform-based quantization methods at 4-bit precision.</p>"},{"id":"61506","en":"Forgetting Whenever You Want: A Decentralized Continual Learning Framework with On-Demand Unlearning","ko":"원할 때마다 잊기: On-Demand Unlearning을 갖춘 Decentralized Continual Learning 프레임워크","authors":"Xiao Zhang, Zengzhe Chen, Mingyi Li, Jing Qiao, Fuzhen Zhuang, YUAN YUAN, Dongxiao Yu","pos":"#2605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pSOiiUSOzp","abs":"<p>Decentralized class continual learning refers to a paradigm where distributed clients continuously acquire new classes while retaining previously learned information without relying on a central server. With increasing emphasis on privacy preservation, there is a growing need for on-demand unlearning, introducing two key challenges: Historical Class Unlearning and Network-Wide Knowledge Entanglement. In this work, we propose a decentralized continual learning framework with on-demand unlearning (DCU), which is the first attempt at achieving class continual learning and arbitrary-time class unlearning in a distributed setting. Specifically, our proposed DCU comprises three main stages: prototypes extraction, prototype-guided continual learning, and unlearning with disposable prototypes. Firstly, the prototypes extraction mechanism is designed to capture the class-specific concepts as lightweight, disposable embeddings. Then, the synthetic data guided by these prototypes can be combined with real data to achieve incremental learning through distillation. Besides, synthetic samples with noisy label are used to guide the adjustment of the model's decision boundary, effectively erasing the influence of the target class while preserving other classes' knowledge. Extensive experiments conducted on two datasets demonstrate the effectiveness of our DCU in dynamic learning and target class unlearning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Decentralized class continual learning은 중앙 서버에 의존하지 않으면서 분산된 client가 이전에 학습한 정보를 유지한 채 새로운 class를 지속적으로 획득하는 패러다임을 의미한다. privacy preservation에 대한 강조가 커짐에 따라, on-demand unlearning의 필요성이 증가하고 있으며, 이는 Historical Class Unlearning과 Network-Wide Knowledge Entanglement라는 두 가지 핵심 과제를 제기한다. 본 연구에서는 분산 환경에서 class continual learning과 arbitrary-time class unlearning을 달성하려는 최초의 시도인 on-demand unlearning을 위한 decentralized continual learning framework(DCU)를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 제안하는 DCU는 prototype extraction, prototype-guided continual learning, disposable prototype을 이용한 unlearning의 세 가지 주요 단계로 구성된다. 먼저 prototype extraction mechanism은 class-specific concept를 경량의 disposable embedding으로 포착하도록 설계된다. 이어서 이러한 prototype이 유도하는 synthetic data는 real data와 결합되어 distillation을 통한 incremental learning을 달성할 수 있다. 또한 noisy label을 가진 synthetic sample은 모델의 decision boundary 조정을 유도하는 데 사용되어, 다른 class의 지식을 보존하면서 목표 class의 영향을 효과적으로 지운다. 두 데이터셋에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 dynamic learning과 target class unlearning에서 DCU의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62765","en":"LATMiX: Learnable Affine Transformations for Microscaling Quantization of LLMs","ko":"LATMiX: LLM Microscaling 양자화를 위한 학습 가능한 Affine 변환","authors":"Ofir Gordon, Lior Dikstein, Arnon Netzer, Idan Achituve, Hai Victor Habi","pos":"#2609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dayZnm0dgh","abs":"<p>Post-training quantization (PTQ) is a widely used approach for reducing the memory and compute costs of large language models (LLMs). Recent studies have shown that applying invertible transformations to activations can significantly improve quantization robustness by reducing activation outliers; however, existing approaches are largely restricted to rotation or Hadamard-based transformations. Moreover, most studies focused primarily on traditional quantization schemes, whereas modern hardware increasingly supports the microscaling (MX) data format. Attempts to combine both showed severe performance degradation, leading prior work to introduce assumptions on the transformations. In this work, we take a complementary perspective. First, we provide a theoretical analysis of transformations under MX quantization by deriving a bound on the quantization error. Our analysis emphasizes the importance of accounting for both the activation distribution and the underlying quantization structure. Building on this analysis, we propose LATMiX, a method that generalizes outlier reduction to learnable invertible affine transformations optimized using standard deep learning tools.  Experiments show consistent improvements in average accuracy for MX low-bit quantization over strong baselines on a wide range of zero-shot benchmarks, across multiple model sizes.</p>","absKo":"<p>Post-training quantization(PTQ)은 large language models(LLMs)의 메모리와 연산 비용을 줄이기 위해 널리 사용되는 접근법이다. 최근 연구들은 activation에 invertible transformation을 적용하면 activation outlier를 줄여 quantization robustness를 크게 향상시킬 수 있음을 보였지만, 기존 접근법은 대부분 rotation 또는 Hadamard 기반 transformation에 제한되어 있다. 또한 대부분의 연구는 전통적인 quantization scheme에 주로 초점을 맞추었으며, 현대 하드웨어는 점점 microscaling(MX) data format을 지원하고 있다. 두 방식을 결합하려는 시도는 심각한 성능 저하를 보였고, 이에 따라 선행 연구는 transformation에 대한 가정을 도입했다. 본 연구에서는 상보적 관점에서 접근한다. 먼저, quantization error에 대한 bound를 유도하여 MX quantization 하의 transformation을 이론적으로 분석한다. 우리의 분석은 activation distribution과 underlying quantization structure를 모두 고려하는 것의 중요성을 강조한다. 이 분석을 바탕으로, 우리는 standard deep learning tool로 최적화되는 learnable invertible affine transformation을 통해 outlier reduction을 일반화하는 방법인 LATMiX를 제안한다. 실험 결과, 여러 model size에 걸쳐 다양한 zero-shot benchmark에서, 강력한 baseline 대비 MX low-bit quantization의 평균 정확도를 일관되게 향상시킴을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"62459","en":"On the Expressive Power of Permutation-Equivariant Weight-Space Networks","ko":"Permutation-Equivariant Weight-Space Network의 표현력 분석","authors":"Adir Dayan, Yam Eitan, Haggai Maron","pos":"#2612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gQXkbQSZWS","abs":"<p>Weight-space learning studies neural architectures that operate directly on the parameters of other neural networks. Motivated by the growing availability of pretrained models, recent work has demonstrated the effectiveness of weight-space networks across a wide range of tasks. SOTA weight-space networks rely on permutation-equivariant designs to improve generalization. However, this may negatively affect expressive power, warranting theoretical investigation. Importantly, unlike other structured domains, weight-space learning targets maps operating on both weight and function spaces, making expressivity analysis particularly subtle. While a few prior works provide partial expressivity results, a comprehensive characterization is still missing. In this work, we address this gap by developing a systematic theory for expressivity of weight-space networks. We first prove that all prominent permutation-equivariant networks are equivalent in expressive power. We then establish universality in both weight- and function-space settings under mild, natural assumptions on the input weights, and characterize the edge-case regimes where universality no longer holds. Together, these results provide a strong and unified foundation for the expressivity of weight-space networks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Weight-space learning은 다른 neural network의 parameter 위에서 직접 작동하는 neural architecture를 연구한다. pretrained model의 가용성이 증가함에 따라, 최근 연구는 다양한 task에서 weight-space network의 효과를 입증해 왔다. SOTA weight-space network는 generalization을 향상시키기 위해 permutation-equivariant design에 의존한다. 그러나 이는 expressive power를 저해할 수 있어 이론적 검토가 필요하다. 특히 다른 structured domain과 달리, weight-space learning은 weight space와 function space 양쪽에서 작동하는 map을 대상으로 하므로 expressivity 분석이 특히 미묘하다. 기존의 몇몇 연구가 부분적인 expressivity 결과를 제공했지만, 포괄적인 characterization은 여전히 부족하다. 본 연구에서는 weight-space network의 expressivity에 대한 체계적 이론을 구축함으로써 이 공백을 메운다. 우리는 먼저 주요 permutation-equivariant network들이 모두 표현력 측면에서 동등하다는 것을 증명한다. 이어서 입력 weight에 대한 완만하고 자연스러운 가정 하에서 weight space와 function space 설정 모두에서 universality를 확립하고, universality가 더 이상 성립하지 않는 경계 사례 regime을 특징지어 설명한다. 이 결과들은 weight-space network의 expressivity에 대해 강력하고 통합된 기반을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"65955","en":"RTInfer: Exploiting Concurrency for Multiple Real-Time DNN Inference on Edge GPUs","ko":"RTInfer: 엣지 GPU에서 다중 실시간 DNN 추론을 위한 동시성 활용","authors":"Renjie Li, Tong Sun, Yi Gao, Wei Dong","pos":"#2709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8XC5ebkGII","abs":"<p>While edge GPUs are increasingly used for latency-critical DNN tasks, limited resources often fail to meet strict real-time (RT) requirements under concurrent workloads.  Existing preemption and early-exit mechanisms often underutilize GPU resources through single-task queuing and sacrifice excessive accuracy during task bursts. To address this, we propose RTInfer, a novel system that enables concurrent RT task execution while balancing throughput and accuracy. RTInfer integrates an accuracy-calibrated lightweight variant co-optimization to generate efficient models, a memory-layout-aware scheduler to mitigate fragmentation during preemption, and an on-demand loading strategy to minimize host-to-GPU latency. Extensive evaluations demonstrate that RTInfer outperforms state-of-the-art methods by up to 98.2\\% in deadline miss rate (DMR) and 58.0\\% in accuracy.</p>"},{"id":"62036","en":"Beyond Majority Voting: Self-Reflective Test-Time Reinforcement Learning for LLM Reasoning","ko":"다수결을 넘어: LLM 추론을 위한 자기반영 Test-Time Reinforcement Learning","authors":"Sitong Wu, Haoru Tan, Xichen Zhang, Bin Xia, Shaofeng Zhang, XIAOJUAN QI, Bei Yu, Jiaya Jia","pos":"#301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kSuRY5sCuR","abs":"The core challenge of Test-Time Reinforcement Learning (TTRL) lies in estimating rewards without access to ground-truth supervision. Existing TTRL methods predominantly rely on majority voting to generate pseudo-labels, under the assumption that the most frequent answer among sampled trajectories is correct. However, we observe that this assumption frequently breaks down in complex reasoning tasks, where correct solutions often constitute a logical minority. As a result, rare yet correct trajectories are systematically undervalued by majority-voting-based approaches.  To address this limitation, we propose Self-Reflective Test-Time Reinforcement Learning (SR-TTRL), a novel framework that leverages self-reflective verification to produce high-fidelity pseudo-labels. Specifically, given multiple sampled trajectories for a problem, SR-TTRL first groups trajectories according to their final answers and selects one representative from each group to form a candidate pool. Each candidate trajectory is then summarized to preserve its core reasoning steps while reducing verbosity. Finally, the model performs self-reflection over the candidate pool, critically evaluating and selecting the most plausible trajectory as the pseudo-label.  Empirically, SR-TTRL achieves substantially higher pseudo-label fidelity and sample efficiency than prior majority-voting-based TTRL methods. Extensive experiments across diverse benchmarks and model families demonstrate that SR-TTRL consistently outperforms majority-voting baselines and significantly improves generalization to novel problems. For example, SR-TTRL improves the Pass@1 accuracy of Qwen3-8B on AIME24 from $29.1$ to $55.8$ (a gain of $+26.7$), exceeding standard TTRL by an additional $+9.1$.","absKo":"Test-Time Reinforcement Learning (TTRL)의 핵심 과제는 ground-truth supervision 없이 reward를 추정하는 데 있다. 기존 TTRL 방법은 대부분 majority voting에 의존해 pseudo-label을 생성하며, 샘플링된 trajectory들 중 가장 빈번한 답이 정답이라는 가정을 둔다. 그러나 우리는 복잡한 reasoning task에서는 이 가정이 자주 무너진다는 점을 관찰했다. 이러한 상황에서 정답 해가 논리적 minority를 이루는 경우가 많다. 그 결과, majority-voting-based approach는 드물지만 정답인 trajectory를 체계적으로 저평가한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 self-reflective verification을 활용하여 high-fidelity pseudo-label을 생성하는 새로운 framework인 Self-Reflective Test-Time Reinforcement Learning (SR-TTRL)을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 하나의 문제에 대해 여러 sampled trajectory가 주어지면 SR-TTRL은 먼저 최종 답변에 따라 trajectory를 그룹화하고, 각 그룹에서 하나의 대표를 선택해 candidate pool을 구성한다. 그런 다음 각 candidate trajectory를 요약하여 장황함은 줄이면서 핵심 reasoning step은 보존한다. 마지막으로 model이 candidate pool에 대해 self-reflection을 수행하여, 비판적으로 평가한 뒤 가장 plausible한 trajectory를 pseudo-label로 선택한다. 실험적으로 SR-TTRL은 기존 majority-voting-based TTRL 방법보다 pseudo-label fidelity와 sample efficiency가 크게 높다. 다양한 benchmark와 model family에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 SR-TTRL이 일관되게 majority-voting baseline을 능가하고, 새로운 문제로의 generalization을 유의미하게 향상시킴을 보여준다. 예를 들어 SR-TTRL은 AIME24에서 Qwen3-8B의 Pass@1 정확도를 $29.1$에서 $55.8$로 높였으며($+26.7$), 이는 standard TTRL보다 추가로 $+9.1$ 향상된 수치다."},{"id":"62807","en":"A Formal Comparison Between Chain of Thought and Latent Thought","ko":"Chain of Thought와 Latent Thought의 정식 비교","authors":"Kevin Xu, Issei Sato","pos":"#310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=d6BqyajwMj","abs":"<p>Chain of thought (CoT) elicits reasoning in large language models by explicitly generating intermediate tokens. In contrast, latent thought reasoning operates directly in the continuous latent space, enabling computation beyond discrete linguistic representations. While both approaches exploit iterative computation, their comparative capabilities remain underexplored. In this work, we present a formal analysis showing that latent thought admits efficient parallel computation, in contrast to the inherently sequential nature of CoT. Conversely, CoT enables approximate counting through stochastic decoding. These separations suggest the tasks for which depth-driven recursion is more suitable, thereby offering practical guidance for choosing between reasoning paradigms.</p>","absKo":"<p>Chain of thought (CoT)는 중간 token을 명시적으로 생성함으로써 large language models의 reasoning을 이끈다. 이에 비해 latent thought reasoning은 연속적인 latent space에서 직접 작동하여, discrete linguistic representation을 넘어선 computation을 가능하게 한다. 두 접근 모두 iterative computation을 활용하지만, 이들의 비교 가능성은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 latent thought가 본질적으로 sequential한 CoT와 대조적으로 efficient parallel computation을 허용함을 보이는 formal analysis를 제시한다. 반대로 CoT는 stochastic decoding을 통해 approximate counting을 가능하게 한다. 이러한 분리는 depth-driven recursion이 더 적합한 task를 시사하며, reasoning paradigm 사이를 선택할 때 실질적인 지침을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66384","en":"Mitigating Reward Hacking in LLM-based Recommendation: A Preference Optimization Approach","ko":"LLM 기반 추천에서 Reward Hacking 완화: 선호 최적화 접근법","authors":"Heyu Chen, Junkang Wu, Guoqing Hu, Kexin Huang, Xiang Wang, Jiancan Wu","pos":"#3603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4BGl1dY83o","abs":"Post-training adaptation has become the central paradigm for leveraging large language models (LLMs) in recommendation.  While recent preference optimization methods, such as Direct Preference Optimization (DPO), enhance pairwise preference discrimination, they remain vulnerable to \\emph{reward hacking}: models exploit imperfections in reward signals, leading to inflated training metrics without genuine recommendation gains. We analyze this issue from a gradient perspective and formalize the concept of the  \\emph{$\\varepsilon$-insensitive region} region, where pairwise updates exert little influence on the ordering between positives and unsampled negatives. Under the Bradley–Terry model, we further show that these regions can occupy a substantial fraction of the preference space, inevitably leading to misaligned rankings. To address this issue, we propose Simulated Preference Optimization for Reward-hacking mitigation using Pseudo-negatives (SIRIUS).  Our framework introduces pseudo-negative samples to enrich contrastive signals and reduce the prevalence of $\\varepsilon$-insensitive regions. Extensive experiments on three public benchmarks show that \\our{} consistently improves ranking quality and effectively mitigates reward hacking, providing both theoretical and practical insights for advancing LLM-based recommendation.  Our code is available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/C557-id}"},{"id":"65696","en":"Memory Caching: RNNs with Growing Memory","ko":"Memory Caching: 메모리가 증가하는 RNN","authors":"Ali Behrouz, Zeman Li, Yuan Deng, Peilin Zhong, Meisam Razaviyayn, Vahab Mirrokni","pos":"#3611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=B5SkWFRE8U","abs":"Transformers have been established as the de-facto backbones for most recent advances in sequence modeling, mainly due to their growing memory capacity that scales with the context length. While plausible for retrieval tasks, it causes quadratic complexity and so has motivated recent studies to explore viable subquadratic recurrent alternatives. Despite showing promising preliminary results in diverse tasks, such recurrent architectures underperform Transformers in recall-intensive tasks, {often attributed to their fixed-size memory. In this paper, we introduce Memory Caching (MC), a simple yet effective technique that enhances recurrent models by caching checkpoints of their memory states (a.k.a. hidden states). Memory Caching allows the effective memory capacity of RNNs to grow with sequence length, offering a flexible trade-off that interpolates between the fixed memory ( $O(L)$ complexity) of RNNs and the growing memory (  $O(L^2)$ complexity) of Transformers. We propose four variants of MC, including gated aggregation and sparse selective mechanisms, and discuss their implications on both linear and deep memory modules.} Our experimental results on language modeling, and long-context understanding tasks show that MC enhances the performance of recurrent models, supporting its effectiveness. In in-context recall tasks, our results indicate that while Transformers still achieve the best performance, our MC variants show competitive performance, close the gap with Transformers, and performs better than state-of-the-art recurrent models."},{"id":"62013","en":"PLoRA: Efficient Concurrent LoRA Training for Large Language Models","ko":"PLoRA: 대규모 LLM을 위한 효율적 동시 LoRA 학습","authors":"Minghao Yan, Zhuang Wang, Zhen Jia, Shivaram Venkataraman, Yida Wang","pos":"#3700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=khYw62jVZ2","abs":"<p>Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) has gained popularity as a fine-tuning approach for Large Language Models (LLMs) due to its low resource requirements and good performance. While numerous studies have investigated improving LoRA serving efficiency by serving multiple LoRAs concurrently, existing methods assume that a wide range of LoRA adapters are available for serving. In our work, we conduct extensive empirical studies to show that current LoRA training paradigms do not efficiently utilize hardware resources and incur high overhead to obtain a performant LoRA adapter. Leveraging these insights, we propose PLoRA, which automatically orchestrates concurrent LoRA fine-tuning jobs under given hardware and model constraints and develops performant kernels to improve training efficiency. Across a range of LLMs and LoRA configurations, PLoRA improves training throughput by up to 12.8x and reduces the overall fine-tuning makespan by up to 7.52x compared to existing approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA)는 낮은 자원 요구량과 우수한 성능 덕분에 Large Language Models (LLMs)의 fine-tuning 기법으로 큰 인기를 얻고 있다. 여러 연구가 여러 LoRA를 동시에 서빙하는 방식으로 LoRA 서빙 효율을 높이는 방법을 탐구해 왔지만, 기존 방법은 서빙에 사용할 수 있는 다양한 LoRA adapter가 존재한다고 가정한다. 본 연구에서는 현재의 LoRA 학습 패러다임이 hardware 자원을 효율적으로 활용하지 못하며, 성능이 좋은 LoRA adapter를 얻는 데 높은 오버헤드를 유발함을 보여주는 광범위한 실증 연구를 수행한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 주어진 hardware 및 model 제약 하에서 동시 LoRA fine-tuning job을 자동으로 조율하고 training efficiency를 향상시키는 고성능 kernel을 개발하는 PLoRA를 제안한다. 다양한 LLM과 LoRA 설정 전반에서 PLoRA는 기존 접근법과 비교해 training throughput을 최대 12.8배 향상시키고 전체 fine-tuning makespan을 최대 7.52배 단축한다.</p>"},{"id":"64467","en":"Can Muon Fine-tune Adam-Pretrained Models?","ko":"Muon은 Adam으로 사전학습된 모델을 미세조정할 수 있는가?","authors":"Xingyu Qu, Peigeng Huang, Samuel Horváth","pos":"#3701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NKKwTEYdAm","abs":"<p>Muon has emerged as an efficient alternative to Adam for pretraining, yet remains underused for fine-tuning. A key obstacle is that most open models are pretrained with Adam, and naively switching to Muon for fine-tuning leads to degraded performance due to an optimizer mismatch. We study this mismatch through controlled experiments and relate it to the distinct implicit biases of Adam and Muon. We provide evidence that fine-tuning with a mismatched optimizer disrupts pretrained knowledge, and show that constraining updates with Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) mitigates this issue. Across language and vision tasks, LoRA with Muon matches or outperforms LoRA with Adam when fine-tuning Adam-pretrained models. Furthermore, in settings with pronounced mismatch, this benefit diminishes when LoRA updates approach full fine-tuning. These results shed light on how optimizer mismatch affects fine-tuning and how it can be mitigated. Our code is available <a href=\"https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Muon-FT-4358\">here</a>.</p>","absKo":"<p>Muon은 pretraining에서 Adam의 효율적인 대안으로 부상했지만, fine-tuning에는 아직 널리 사용되지 않고 있다. 핵심 장애물은 대부분의 open model이 Adam으로 pretrain되었고, fine-tuning에서 Muon으로 단순히 전환하면 optimizer mismatch 때문에 성능이 저하된다는 점이다. 우리는 통제된 실험을 통해 이 mismatch를 연구하고, 이를 Adam과 Muon의 서로 다른 implicit bias와 연결한다. 우리는 mismatched optimizer로 fine-tuning하면 pretrained knowledge가 교란된다는 증거를 제시하며, Low-Rank Adaptation(LoRA)으로 update를 제약하면 이 문제를 완화할 수 있음을 보인다. language 및 vision task 전반에서, Adam으로 pretrain된 model을 fine-tuning할 때 Muon과 함께한 LoRA는 Adam과 함께한 LoRA와 같거나 더 나은 성능을 보인다. 더 나아가 mismatch가 두드러지는 setting에서는 LoRA update가 full fine-tuning에 가까워질수록 이 이점이 줄어든다. 이 결과는 optimizer mismatch가 fine-tuning에 어떤 영향을 미치며 어떻게 완화될 수 있는지에 대한 통찰을 제공한다. 우리의 code는 <a href=\"https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Muon-FT-4358\">여기</a>에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"68791","en":"LumiNet: Perception-Driven Knowledge Distillation via Statistical Logit Calibration","ko":"LumiNet: 통계적 Logit Calibration을 통한 인식 주도 Knowledge Distillation","authors":"Md. Ismail Hossain, M M Lutfe Elahi, Sameera Ramasinghe, Ali Cheraghian, Fuad Rahman, Nabeel Mohammed, Shafin Rahman","pos":"#3808","abs":"<p>In the knowledge distillation literature, feature-based methods have dominated due to their ability to effectively tap into extensive teacher models. In contrast, logit-based approaches, which aim to distill <code>dark knowledge' from teachers, typically exhibit inferior performance compared to feature-based methods. To bridge this gap, we present LumiNet, a novel knowledge distillation algorithm designed to enhance logit-based distillation. We introduce the concept of</code>perception', aiming to calibrate logits based on the model's representation capability. This concept addresses overconfidence issues in the logit-based distillation method while also introducing a novel method to distill knowledge from the teacher. It reconstructs the logits of a sample/instances by considering relationships with other samples in the batch. LumiNet excels on benchmarks like CIFAR-100, ImageNet, and MSCOCO, outperforming the leading feature-based methods, e.g., compared to KD with ResNet18 and MobileNetV2 on ImageNet, it shows improvements of 1.5\\% and 2.05\\%, respectively.</p>"},{"id":"61710","en":"Language as a Wave Phenomenon: Semantic Phase Locking and Interference in Neural Networks","ko":"파동 현상으로서의 언어: 신경망의 의미론적 위상 고정과 간섭","authors":"Alper YILDIRIM, İbrahim Yücedağ","pos":"#4001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nZy6lUWvhI","abs":"<p>In standard Transformer architectures, semantic importance is often conflated with activation magnitude, obscuring the geometric structure of latent representations. To disentangle these factors, we introduce PRISM, a complex-valued architecture designed to isolate the computational role of phase. By enforcing a strict unit-norm constraint (|z| = 1) and replacing attention with gated harmonic convolutions, the model is compelled to utilize subtractive interference in the frequency domain to suppress noise, rather than relying on magnitude-based gating. We utilize this constrained regime to demonstrate that a hybrid architecture—fusing phase-based routing with standard attention—achieves superior parameter efficiency and representation quality compared to unconstrained baselines. Mechanistically, we identify geometric phase clustering, where tokens naturally self-organize to resolve semantic ambiguities. This establishes an O(N log N) reasoning framework based on spectral interference, providing an algorithmic existence proof that subtractive logic is a logical primitive for deep reasoning.</p>","absKo":"표준 Transformer architecture에서는 semantic importance가 종종 activation magnitude와 혼동되어 latent representation의 기하학적 구조가 가려진다. 이러한 요인을 분리하기 위해, 우리는 phase의 계산적 역할을 분리하도록 설계된 complex-valued architecture인 PRISM을 도입한다. 엄격한 unit-norm 제약(|z| = 1)을 강제하고 attention을 gated harmonic convolution으로 대체함으로써, 모델은 magnitude-based gating에 의존하는 대신 frequency domain에서 subtractive interference를 활용해 noise를 억제하도록 유도된다. 우리는 이 제약된 regime를 활용하여 phase-based routing과 standard attention을 결합한 hybrid architecture가 비제약 baseline보다 우수한 parameter efficiency와 representation quality를 달성함을 보인다. 기작적으로는 token이 의미적 모호성을 해소하기 위해 자연스럽게 자기 조직화하는 geometric phase clustering을 식별한다. 이는 spectral interference에 기반한 O(N log N) reasoning framework를 확립하며, subtractive logic이 deep reasoning의 논리적 primitive라는 algorithmic existence proof를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63497","en":"FlashOptim: Memory Efficient Optimizers for Large-Scale Training","ko":"FlashOptim: 대규모 학습을 위한 메모리 효율적 옵티마이저","authors":"Jose Javier Gonzalez Ortiz, Abhay Gupta, Christopher Rinard, Davis Blalock","pos":"#410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Wfe1iJocjF","abs":"<p>Standard mixed-precision training of neural networks requires many bytes of accelerator memory for each model parameter. These bytes reflect not just the parameter itself, but also its gradient and one or more optimizer state variables. With each of these values typically requiring 4 bytes, training even a 7 billion parameter model can be impractical for researchers with less than 100GB of accelerator memory.  We introduce FlashOptim, a suite of optimizations that reduces per-parameter memory by over 50% while preserving model quality and API compatibility. Our approach introduces two key techniques. First, we improve master weight splitting by finding and exploiting a tight bound on its quantization error. Second, we design companding functions that greatly reduce the error in 8-bit optimizer state quantization. Together with 16-bit gradients, these techniques reduce AdamW memory from 16 bytes to 7 bytes per parameter, or 5 bytes with gradient release. They also cut model checkpoint sizes by more than half.  Experiments with FlashOptim applied to SGD, AdamW, and Lion show no measurable quality degradation on any task from a collection of standard vision and language benchmarks, including Llama-3.1-8B finetuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>신경망의 표준 mixed-precision training은 각 model parameter마다 accelerator memory의 많은 바이트를 필요로 한다. 이 바이트들은 parameter 자체뿐 아니라 gradient와 하나 이상의 optimizer state variable을 반영한다. 각 값이 일반적으로 4바이트를 요구하기 때문에, 7 billion parameter model조차 100GB 미만의 accelerator memory를 가진 연구자에게는 실용적이지 않을 수 있다. 우리는 model quality와 API compatibility를 유지하면서 parameter당 memory를 50% 이상 줄이는 최적화 모음인 FlashOptim을 소개한다. 우리의 접근은 두 가지 핵심 기법을 도입한다. 첫째, master weight splitting을 quantization error에 대한 타이트한 bound를 찾아 활용함으로써 개선한다. 둘째, 8-bit optimizer state quantization의 error를 크게 줄이는 companding function을 설계한다. 16-bit gradient와 결합하면, 이러한 기법은 AdamW memory를 parameter당 16바이트에서 7바이트로, 또는 gradient release 시 5바이트로 줄인다. 또한 model checkpoint size도 절반 이상 감소시킨다. SGD, AdamW, Lion에 FlashOptim을 적용한 실험은 Llama-3.1-8B finetuning을 포함한 표준 vision 및 language benchmark 모음의 어떤 task에서도 측정 가능한 quality degradation이 없음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63014","en":"Towards On-Policy SFT: Distribution Discriminant Theory and its Applications in LLM Training","ko":"On-Policy SFT를 향하여: Distribution Discriminant Theory와 LLM 훈련의 응용","authors":"Miaosen Zhang, Yishan Liu, Shuxia Lin, Qi Dai, Chong Luo, Baining Guo, Weihao Jiang, Peng Hou, Anxiang Zeng, Xu Yang, Xin Geng","pos":"#413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=auOFVW0iSO","abs":"<p>Supervised fine-tuning (SFT) is computationally efficient but often yields inferior generalization compared to reinforcement learning (RL). This gap is primarily driven by RL’s use of on-policy data. We propose a framework to bridge this chasm by enabling On-Policy SFT. We first present <em><strong>Distribution Discriminant Theory (DDT)</strong></em>, which explains and quantifies the alignment between data and the model-induced distribution. Leveraging DDT, we introduce two complementary techniques: (i) <em><strong>In-Distribution Finetuning (IDFT)</strong></em>, a loss-level method to enhance generalization ability of SFT, and (ii) <em><strong>Hinted Decoding</strong></em>, a data-level technique that can re-align the training corpus to the model’s distribution.  Extensive experiments demonstrate that our framework achieves generalization performance on par with prominent offline RL algorithms, including DPO and SimPO, while maintaining the efficiency of an SFT pipeline. The proposed framework thus offers a practical alternative in domains where RL is infeasible. We will open-source the code and data on GitHub.</p>","absKo":"<p>Supervised fine-tuning (SFT)은 계산 효율적이지만, reinforcement learning (RL)과 비교하면 일반화 성능이 종종 더 떨어진다. 이러한 격차는 주로 RL이 on-policy 데이터를 사용하기 때문에 발생한다. 우리는 On-Policy SFT를 가능하게 함으로써 이 간극을 메우는 프레임워크를 제안한다. 먼저, 데이터와 model-induced distribution 간의 정렬을 설명하고 정량화하는 <em><strong>Distribution Discriminant Theory (DDT)</strong></em>를 제시한다. DDT를 활용하여, 우리는 서로 보완적인 두 기법을 도입한다: (i) SFT의 일반화 능력을 향상시키는 loss-level 방법인 <em><strong>In-Distribution Finetuning (IDFT)</strong></em>, 그리고 (ii) training corpus를 model의 distribution에 다시 정렬시킬 수 있는 data-level 기법인 <em><strong>Hinted Decoding</strong></em>이다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 프레임워크가 DPO와 SimPO를 포함한 대표적인 offline RL 알고리즘에 필적하는 generalization 성능을 달성하면서도 SFT pipeline의 효율성은 유지함을 보여준다. 따라서 제안하는 프레임워크는 RL이 불가능한 영역에서 실용적인 대안을 제공한다. 코드는 GitHub에, 데이터는 GitHub에 오픈소스로 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61034","en":"Convolutional Learnable-Group Weightless Neural Network","ko":"컨볼루션 학습형 그룹 Weightless 신경망","authors":"Qinhong Ma, Yulin Chen, Zhiwei Fan, Suzhen Wu, Bo Mao","pos":"#4201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uMUGXv4881","abs":"<p>Weightless Neural Networks (WNNs) based on interconnected Lookup Tables (LUTs) have attracted attention for inference in extremely compact models, but achieving competitive accuracy under such tight resource budgets remains challenging. To address these issues, we introduce the Convolutional Learnable-Group Weightless Neural Network (CLGN). CLGN constructs convolutional layers using LUTs and incorporates a learnable GroupSum connection, thereby enhancing the accuracy of WNNs while maintaining low implementation resource consumption. Moreover, we propose a hierarchical training strategy to improve the training efficiency. We evaluate CLGN in two edge computing scenarios: (1) FPGA, where we evaluate accuracy, latency, throughput, power consumption, LUTs usage, and parameter size; and (2) Microprocessor, where we evaluate latency and memory usage. Compared with the state-of-the-art solutions, the proposed CLGN achieves superior accuracy while maintaining lower implementation resource consumption.</p>","absKo":"<p>상호 연결된 Lookup Table (LUT) 기반의 Weightless Neural Networks (WNNs)는 매우 컴팩트한 모델에서의 inference를 위해 주목받아 왔지만, 이러한 극도로 제한된 자원 예산 하에서 경쟁력 있는 정확도를 달성하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Convolutional Learnable-Group Weightless Neural Network (CLGN)를 제안한다. CLGN은 LUT를 사용해 convolutional layer를 구성하고 learnable GroupSum connection을 통합함으로써, 낮은 구현 자원 소비를 유지하면서 WNN의 정확도를 향상시킨다. 더 나아가, 학습 효율을 개선하기 위한 hierarchical training strategy를 제안한다. 우리는 CLGN을 두 가지 edge computing 시나리오에서 평가한다: (1) FPGA에서는 정확도, 지연시간, throughput, 전력 소비, LUT 사용량, parameter size를 평가하고, (2) Microprocessor에서는 지연시간과 메모리 사용량을 평가한다. state-of-the-art solution과 비교했을 때, 제안한 CLGN은 더 낮은 구현 자원 소비를 유지하면서도 더 우수한 정확도를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"66276","en":"Grokking Finite-Dimensional Algebra","ko":"유한 차원 대수의 Grokking","authors":"Pascal Jr Tikeng Notsawo, Guillaume Dumas, Guillaume Rabusseau","pos":"#4611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5Cvh976L09","abs":"<p>This paper investigates the grokking phenomenon, which refers to the sudden transition from a long memorization to generalization observed during neural networks training, in the context of learning multiplication in finite-dimensional algebras (FDA).  While prior work on grokking has focused mainly on group operations, we extend the analysis to more general algebraic structures, including non-associative, non-commutative, and non-unital algebras. We show that learning group operations is a special case of learning FDA, and that learning multiplication in FDA amounts to learning a bilinear product specified by the algebra’s structure tensor. For algebras over the reals, we connect the learning problem to matrix factorization with an implicit low-rank bias, and for algebras over finite fields, we show that grokking emerges naturally as models must learn discrete representations of algebraic elements. This leads us to experimentally investigate the following core questions: (i) how do algebraic properties such as commutativity, associativity, and unitality influence both the emergence and timing of grokking, (ii) how structural properties of the structure tensor of the FDA, such as sparsity and rank, influence generalization, and (iii) to what extent generalization correlates with the model learning latent embeddings aligned with the algebra’s representation. Our work provides a unified framework for grokking across algebraic structures and new insights into how mathematical structure governs neural network generalization dynamics.</p>"},{"id":"65584","en":"Patterning: The Dual of Interpretability","ko":"Patterning: 해석 가능성의 쌍대","authors":"George Wang, Daniel Murfet","pos":"#4617","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CC4KunEY5I","abs":"<p>Mechanistic interpretability aims to understand how neural networks generalize beyond their training data by reverse-engineering their internal structures. We introduce patterning as the dual problem: given a desired form of generalization, determine what training data produces it. Our approach is based on susceptibilities, which measure how posterior expectation values of observables respond to infinitesimal shifts in the data distribution. Inverting this linear response relationship yields the data intervention that steers the model toward a target internal configuration. We demonstrate patterning in a small language model, showing that re-weighting training data along principal susceptibility directions can accelerate or delay the formation of structure, such as the induction circuit. In a synthetic parentheses balancing task where multiple algorithms achieve perfect training accuracy, we show that patterning can select which algorithm the model learns by targeting the local learning coefficient of each solution. These results establish that the same mathematical framework used to read internal structure can be inverted to write it.</p>"},{"id":"60610","en":"Spatially-Adaptive Gradient Re-parameterization for 3D Large Kernel Optimization","ko":"3D 대형 커널 최적화를 위한 공간 적응형 그래디언트 재매개변수화","authors":"Ho Hin Lee, Quan Liu, Shunxing Bao, Yuankai Huo, Bennett Landman","pos":"#1005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yUvMzLLyfE","abs":"<p>Large kernel convolutions offer a scalable alternative to vision transformers for high-resolution 3D volumetric analysis, yet naïvely increasing kernel size often leads to optimization instability. Motivated by the spatial bias inherent in effective receptive fields (ERFs), we theoretically demonstrate that structurally re-parameterized blocks induce spatially varying learning rates that are crucial for convergence. Leveraging this insight, we introduce Rep3D, a framework that employs a lightweight modulation network to generate receptive-biased scaling masks, adaptively re-weighting kernel updates within a plain encoder architecture. This approach unifies spatial inductive bias with optimization-aware learning, avoiding the complexity of multi-branch designs while ensuring robust local-to-global convergence. Extensive evaluations on five 3D segmentation benchmarks demonstrate that Rep3D consistently outperforms state-of-the-art transformer and fixed-prior baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large kernel convolution은 high-resolution 3D volumetric analysis를 위한 vision transformer의 확장 가능한 대안이지만, kernel size를 무작정 키우면 최적화 불안정성이 자주 발생한다. effective receptive field(ERF)에 내재된 spatial bias에 착안하여, 우리는 구조적으로 re-parameterized block이 수렴에 핵심적인 공간별로 달라지는 learning rate를 유도함을 이론적으로 보인다. 이러한 통찰을 활용해, 우리는 가벼운 modulation network를 사용하여 receptive-biased scaling mask를 생성하고 plain encoder architecture 내에서 kernel update를 적응적으로 재가중하는 Rep3D를 제안한다. 이 접근은 spatial inductive bias와 optimization-aware learning을 통합하며, 다중 branch 설계의 복잡성을 피하는 동시에 강건한 local-to-global 수렴을 보장한다. 다섯 개의 3D segmentation benchmark에 대한 광범위한 평가는 Rep3D가 state-of-the-art transformer 및 fixed-prior baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65485","en":"Mixture of Distributions Matters: Dynamic Sparse Attention for Efficient Video Diffusion Transformers","ko":"분포 혼합이 중요하다: 효율적 Video Diffusion Transformer를 위한 동적 Sparse Attention","authors":"Yuxi Liu, Yipeng Hu, Zekun Zhang, Kunze Jiang, Kun Yuan","pos":"#1105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=D8ETPuIu7Q","abs":"<p>While Diffusion Transformers (DiTs) have achieved notable progress in video generation, this long-sequence generation task remains constrained by the quadratic complexity inherent to self-attention mechanisms, creating significant barriers to practical deployment. Although sparse attention methods attempt to address this challenge, existing approaches either rely on oversimplified static patterns or require computationally expensive sampling operations to achieve dynamic sparsity, resulting in inaccurate pattern predictions and degraded generation quality. To overcome these limitations, we propose a \\underline{\\textbf{M}}ixture-\\underline{\\textbf{O}}f-\\underline{\\textbf{D}}istribution \\textbf{DiT} (\\textbf{MOD-DiT}), a novel sampling-free dynamic attention framework that accurately models evolving attention patterns through a two-stage process. First, MOD-DiT leverages prior information from early denoising steps and adopts a {distributed mixing approach} to model an efficient linear approximation model, which is then used to predict mask patterns for a specific denoising interval. Second, an online block masking strategy dynamically applies these predicted masks while maintaining historical sparsity information, eliminating the need for repetitive sampling operations. Extensive evaluations demonstrate consistent acceleration and quality improvements across multiple benchmarks and model architectures, validating MOD-DiT's effectiveness for efficient, high-quality video generation while overcoming the computational limitations of traditional sparse attention approaches.</p>"},{"id":"62285","en":"Diffeomorphism-Equivariant Neural Networks","ko":"미분동형사상 등변 신경망","authors":"Josephine Elisabeth Oettinger, Zakhar Shumaylov, Johannes Bostelmann, Jan Lellmann, Carola-Bibiane Schönlieb","pos":"#1112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hyK30n4mra","abs":"<p>Incorporating group symmetries via equivariance into neural networks has emerged as a robust approach for overcoming the efficiency and data demands of modern deep learning. While most existing approaches, such as group convolutions and averaging-based methods, focus on compact, finite, or low-dimensional groups with linear actions, this work explores how equivariance can be extended to infinite-dimensional groups. We propose a strategy designed to induce diffeomorphism equivariance in pre-trained neural networks via energy-based canonicalisation. Formulating equivariance as an optimisation problem allows us to access the rich toolbox of already established differentiable image registration methods. Empirical results on segmentation and classification tasks confirm that our approach achieves approximate equivariance and generalises to unseen transformations without relying on extensive data augmentation or retraining.</p>","absKo":"<p>군 대칭을 equivariance로 신경망에 통합하는 것은 현대 딥러닝의 효율성과 데이터 요구량 문제를 극복하기 위한 강력한 접근법으로 부상했습니다. group convolution과 averaging 기반 방법 등 대부분의 기존 접근법은 linear action을 갖는 compact, finite, 또는 low-dimensional group에 초점을 맞추는 반면, 본 연구는 equivariance를 infinite-dimensional group으로 어떻게 확장할 수 있는지를 탐구합니다. 우리는 energy-based canonicalisation을 통해 pre-trained neural network에 diffeomorphism equivariance를 유도하기 위한 전략을 제안합니다. equivariance를 최적화 문제로 정식화하면, 이미 확립된 다양한 differentiable image registration 방법을 활용할 수 있습니다. segmentation 및 classification 과제에서의 실험 결과는, 우리의 접근법이 근사적 equivariance를 달성하고 광범위한 data augmentation이나 retraining에 의존하지 않으면서 보지 못한 transformation에도 일반화됨을 확인합니다.</p>"},{"id":"63425","en":"Euler–Poincaré Neural Dynamics: A Geometric-Mechanics Framework for Scientific Simulation","ko":"Euler-Poincaré 신경 동역학: 과학적 시뮬레이션을 위한 기하-역학 프레임워크","authors":"Jiwoong Kim, Jongwon Lee, Sungwoo Park","pos":"#1205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XInXredBC1","abs":"<p>We introduce Euler–Poincaré Neural Dynamics (EPND), a geometric-mechanics–driven framework that redefines how Koopman-type neural models learn dynamical systems. Unlike conventional operator-learning methods that rely on function-space linearization, EPND places geometric mechanics at the core of its architecture the mathematical engine governing evolution through Lie-group flows. This foundation enables a principled treatment of curvature, symmetry, and conservation, that ensures both interpretability and physical consistency. Building on this foundation, we develop the Euler–Poincaré Parallel Scan, a parallel algorithm that leverages the associative algebra of Lie-group compositions to overcome the inefficiencies of sequential computation. By unifying geometric structure with scalable computation, EPND achieves high accuracy, strong stability, and significant parallel acceleration in modeling long-horizon dynamics of versatile scientific simulation.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 Euler–Poincaré Neural Dynamics(EPND)를 소개한다. 이는 Koopman-type neural model이 dynamical system을 학습하는 방식을 재정의하는 geometric-mechanics 기반 프레임워크다. 함수 공간 선형화에 의존하는 전통적인 operator-learning 방법과 달리, EPND는 Lie-group flow를 통한 진화를 지배하는 수학적 엔진인 geometric mechanics를 아키텍처의 핵심에 둔다. 이러한 기반은 curvature, symmetry, conservation을 원칙적으로 다루게 하며, 해석 가능성과 물리적 일관성을 모두 보장한다. 이 토대 위에서 우리는 Lie-group composition의 associative algebra를 활용해 순차 계산의 비효율을 극복하는 병렬 알고리즘인 Euler–Poincaré Parallel Scan을 개발한다. geometric structure와 확장 가능한 계산을 통합함으로써, EPND는 다양한 scientific simulation의 장기 horizon dynamics를 모델링하는 데서 높은 정확도, 강한 안정성, 그리고 큰 병렬 가속을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"61791","en":"On the origin of neural scaling laws:  from random graphs to natural language","ko":"Neural Scaling Law의 기원: Random Graph에서 Natural Language까지","authors":"Maissam Barkeshli, Alberto Alfarano, Andrey Gromov","pos":"#1309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mu17VSX8q9","abs":"<p>Scaling laws have played a major role in modern AI, providing predictive power over how model performance will improve with increasing resources. This has spurred intense interest in their origin, with a common suggestion being that they arise from power laws already present in the data. Here we study scaling laws for transformers trained to predict random walks on graphs with tunable complexity. We show that this simplified setting already yields scaling laws even in the absence of power laws in the data correlations. We further consider dialing down the complexity of language by training on sequences sampled from increasingly simplified generative language models, from 4,2,1-layer transformer language models down to language bigrams, revealing a monotonic evolution of the scaling exponents. Our results also include scaling laws obtained from training on random walks on random graphs drawn from Erdös-Renyi and scale-free Barabási-Albert ensembles. Finally, we revisit scaling laws for language modeling, demonstrating that several essential results can be reproduced using 2 layer transformers with context length of 100, demonstrate an alternative method for obtaining compute optimal curves, and provide preliminary evidence that maximal update parameterization may be more parameter efficient than standard parameterization.</p>","absKo":"<p>Scaling law는 modern AI에서 중요한 역할을 해왔으며, resource가 증가함에 따라 model performance가 어떻게 향상될지에 대한 예측력을 제공한다. 이에 따라 그 기원에 대한 강한 관심이 촉발되었고, 흔한 설명으로는 data에 이미 존재하는 power law에서 비롯된다는 주장이 있다. 여기서는 조절 가능한 complexity를 가진 graph 위의 random walk를 예측하도록 학습된 transformer의 scaling law를 연구한다. 우리는 이 단순화된 setting에서도 data correlation에 power law가 존재하지 않더라도 scaling law가 이미 나타남을 보인다. 또한 4, 2, 1-layer transformer language model부터 language bigram에 이르기까지 점점 더 단순화된 generative language model에서 샘플링한 sequence로 학습하여 language의 complexity를 낮추는 경우를 살펴보고, scaling exponent가 단조롭게 변화하는 양상을 확인한다. 우리의 결과에는 Erdös-Renyi 및 scale-free Barabási-Albert ensemble에서 뽑은 random graph 위의 random walk로 학습해 얻은 scaling law도 포함된다. 마지막으로 language modeling에 대한 scaling law를 다시 살펴보며, context length 100의 2-layer transformer만으로도 몇 가지 핵심 결과를 재현할 수 있음을 보이고, compute-optimal curve를 얻는 대안적 방법을 제시하며, maximal update parameterization이 standard parameterization보다 parameter 효율성이 더 높을 수 있다는 예비 증거를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60797","en":"What If We Allocate Test-Time Compute Adaptively?","ko":"Test-Time Compute를 Adaptive하게 할당하면 어떨까?","authors":"Ahsan Bilal, Muhammad Ahmed Mohsin, Muhammad Umer, Ali Subhan, Hassan Rizwan, Ayesha Mohsin, Dean Hougen","pos":"#1512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wblvinAlrW","abs":"<p>Test-time compute scaling allocates inference computation uniformly, uses fixed sampling strategies, and applies verification only for reranking. In contrast, we propose a verifier-guided adaptive framework treating reasoning as iterative trajectory generation and selection. For each problem, the agent runs multiple inference iterations. In each iteration, it optionally produces a high-level plan, selects a set of reasoning tools and a compute strategy together with an exploration parameter, and then generates a candidate reasoning trajectory. A process reward model (PRM) serves as a unified control signal: within each iteration, step-level PRM scores are aggregated to guide pruning and expansion during generation, and across iterations, aggregated trajectory rewards are used to select the final response. Across datasets, our dynamic, PRM-guided approach consistently outperforms direct test-time scaling, yielding large gains on MATH-500 and several-fold improvements on harder benchmarks such as AIME24 and AMO-Bench. We characterize efficiency using theoretical FLOPs and a compute intensity metric penalizing wasted generation and tool overhead, demonstrating that verification-guided allocation concentrates computation on high-utility reasoning paths.</p>","absKo":"<p>test-time compute scaling은 inference computation을 균일하게 배분하고, 고정된 sampling 전략을 사용하며, verification을 reranking에만 적용한다. 이와 달리, 우리는 추론을 반복적인 trajectory 생성과 선택으로 보는 verifier-guided adaptive framework를 제안한다. 각 문제마다 agent는 여러 번의 inference iteration을 수행한다. 각 iteration에서 agent는 선택적으로 high-level plan을 생성하고, 탐색 매개변수와 함께 reasoning tool 집합 및 compute strategy를 선택한 뒤, candidate reasoning trajectory를 생성한다. process reward model(PRM)은 통합된 control signal로 작동한다. 각 iteration 내부에서는 step-level PRM score를 집계하여 생성 중 pruning과 expansion을 유도하고, iteration 간에는 집계된 trajectory reward를 사용하여 최종 response를 선택한다. 여러 데이터셋 전반에서 우리의 dynamic, PRM-guided 접근법은 direct test-time scaling을 일관되게 능가하며, MATH-500에서 큰 향상을, AIME24와 AMO-Bench 같은 더 어려운 benchmark에서는 수배의 개선을 달성한다. 우리는 theoretical FLOPs와, 낭비되는 생성과 tool overhead를 패널티로 반영하는 compute intensity metric을 사용해 효율성을 정량화하며, verification-guided allocation이 computation을 높은 유틸리티를 지닌 reasoning path에 집중시킴을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"61136","en":"ST-Veto: Spatio-Temporal Token Veto for Diffusion MLLMs via Taylor Prediction and Visual Grounding","ko":"ST-Veto: Taylor Prediction과 Visual Grounding을 통한 Diffusion MLLM의 Spatio-Temporal Token Veto","authors":"Keuntae Kim, Beomseok Lee, Hyunwoo Kim, Yong Suk Choi","pos":"#1700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tMt8mhUQ2P","abs":"<p>Vision Language Models (VLMs) achieve strong reasoning with Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting but incur high sequential-generation cost, error accumulation, and limited self-correction. Diffusion Multimodal Large Language Models (dMLLMs) unmask tokens in an order-agnostic process, improving efficiency and enabling self-correction, yet their reasoning and how to enhance it remain underexplored. We propose a training-free method, Spatio-Temporal token Veto (ST-Veto), leveraging the ability to observe all tokens at each diffusion step. ST-Veto vetoes temporally unstable tokens via second-order Taylor prediction of confidence dynamics and filters weakly grounded tokens using image attention mass, swapping them with safer candidates. Across multiple dMLLMs and multimodal reasoning benchmarks, ST-Veto consistently outperforms standard decoding policies and prior VLM reasoning methods, improving accuracy by up to 9\\% with no additional training or generation cost. Analyses show that ST-Veto steers generation toward higher-confidence, better-grounded paths, and we will release our code upon publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision Language Model (VLM)은 Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting으로 강한 reasoning을 달성하지만, 높은 sequential-generation cost, error accumulation, 제한된 self-correction을 수반한다. Diffusion Multimodal Large Language Model (dMLLM)은 order-agnostic process로 token을 unmasking하여 효율성을 높이고 self-correction을 가능하게 하지만, 그 reasoning과 이를 향상시키는 방법은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 우리는 diffusion step마다 모든 token을 관찰할 수 있는 능력을 활용하는 training-free method인 Spatio-Temporal token Veto (ST-Veto)를 제안한다. ST-Veto는 confidence dynamics의 second-order Taylor prediction을 통해 시간적으로 불안정한 token을 veto하고, image attention mass를 사용해 약하게 grounded된 token을 필터링한 뒤, 더 안전한 후보로 교체한다. 여러 dMLLM과 multimodal reasoning benchmark 전반에서 ST-Veto는 standard decoding policy와 기존 VLM reasoning method를 일관되게 능가하며, 추가 training이나 generation cost 없이 정확도를 최대 9\\%까지 향상시킨다. 분석 결과 ST-Veto가 generation을 더 높은 confidence와 더 잘 grounded된 경로로 유도함을 보였으며, 논문 게재 시 코드를 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61964","en":"RLSF-V: Mitigating Hallucinations in MLLMs via Fuzzy Semantic Self-Feedback","ko":"RLSF-V: fuzzy semantic self-feedback을 통한 MLLM hallucination 완화","authors":"Changhao He, ShuhaoYan, Shuxian Li, Xi Peng, Peng Hu","pos":"#1705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lCTZsWotjL","abs":"Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) extend large language models (LLMs) with visual perception for open-world understanding, but exacerbate LLMs' hallucinations, in which generated text contradicts visual evidence or common sense. To mitigate hallucinations, a dominant strategy is Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) using hallucination-labeled responses. Existing pipelines, however, face two key limitations: they either (i) rely on human inspection or proprietary models to correct hallucinated outputs, producing off-policy preference data that violate the basic assumptions of DPO, or (ii) depend on stronger peer models to evaluate responses, leading to an unfavorable trade-off between performance and scalability. Departing from these paradigms, we propose an on-policy \\emph{self-feedback} framework that constructs preference data for hallucination mitigation without any external supervision (\\textit{e.g.}, large models or humans). Specifically, we present a novel \\emph{local fuzzy semantic} evaluation paradigm that derives a hallucination-sensitive confidence signal directly from the model's own logits, which is then used to automatically rank diverse generated responses to build high-quality preference pairs for fine-tuning. Trained on a 10k-scale self-generated preference dataset, our self-feedback pipeline achieves over a 50\\% relative reduction in \\textit{HalRate}$\\downarrow$ on AMBER compared to the GPT-4V feedback baselines. Models, code, and datasets will be released upon acceptance.","absKo":"<p>Multimodal large language model(MLLM)은 open-world understanding을 위해 large language model(LLM)에 visual perception을 확장하지만, 생성된 텍스트가 visual evidence나 common sense와 모순되는 hallucination 문제를 더욱 악화시킨다. hallucination을 완화하기 위한 지배적인 전략은 hallucination label이 붙은 response를 사용한 Direct Preference Optimization(DPO)이다. 그러나 기존 pipeline은 두 가지 핵심 한계에 직면한다. (i) human inspection이나 proprietary model에 의존해 hallucinated output을 수정함으로써 DPO의 기본 가정을 위반하는 off-policy preference data를 생성하거나, (ii) 더 강한 peer model에 의존해 response를 평가하여 성능과 확장성 사이에서 바람직하지 않은 trade-off를 초래한다. 이러한 패러다임에서 벗어나, 우리는 external supervision(예: 대형 모델이나 사람) 없이 hallucination mitigation을 위한 preference data를 구성하는 on-policy \\emph{self-feedback} framework를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 모델 자신의 logits에서 직접 hallucination에 민감한 confidence signal을 도출하는 새로운 \\emph{local fuzzy semantic} 평가 패러다임을 제시하고, 이를 이용해 다양하게 생성된 response를 자동으로 순위화하여 fine-tuning용 고품질 preference pair를 구축한다. 10k 규모의 self-generated preference dataset으로 학습한 결과, 우리의 self-feedback pipeline은 GPT-4V feedback baseline과 비교해 AMBER에서 \\textit{HalRate}$\\downarrow$를 50\\% 이상 상대적으로 감소시킨다. 모델, code, dataset은 승인 시 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61503","en":"Lavida-R1: Advancing Reasoning for Unified Multimodal Diffusion Language Models","ko":"Lavida-R1: Unified Multimodal Diffusion Language Models의 추론 고도화","authors":"Shufan Li, Yuchen Zhu, Jiuxiang Gu, Kangning Liu, Zhe Lin, Yongxin Chen, Molei Tao, Aditya Grover, Jason Kuen","pos":"#200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pVcEcaHHD2","abs":"<p>Diffusion language models (dLLMs) recently emerged as a promising alternative to auto-regressive LLMs. The latest works further extended it to multimodal understanding and generation tasks. In this work, we propose LaViDa-R1, a multimodal, general-purpose reasoning dLLM. Unlike existing works that build reasoning dLLMs through task-specific reinforcement learning, LaViDa-R1 incorporates diverse multimodal understanding and generation tasks in a unified manner. In particular, LaViDa-R1 is built with a novel unified post-training framework that seamlessly integrates supervised finetuning (SFT) and multi-task reinforcement learning (RL). It employs several novel training techniques, including answer-forcing, tree search, and complementary likelihood estimation, to enhance effectiveness and scalability. Extensive experiments demonstrate LaViDa-R1's strong performance on a wide range of multimodal tasks, including visual math reasoning, reason-intensive grounding, and image editing.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion language model(dLLM)은 최근 auto-regressive LLM에 대한 유망한 대안으로 부상했다. 최신 연구들은 이를 multimodal understanding 및 generation task로 더욱 확장했다. 본 연구에서는 multimodal, general-purpose reasoning dLLM인 LaViDa-R1을 제안한다. task-specific reinforcement learning을 통해 reasoning dLLM을 구축하는 기존 연구와 달리, LaViDa-R1은 다양한 multimodal understanding 및 generation task를 통합된 방식으로 포함한다. 특히 LaViDa-R1은 supervised finetuning(SFT)과 multi-task reinforcement learning(RL)을 매끄럽게 통합하는 새로운 unified post-training framework로 구축된다. 또한 answer-forcing, tree search, complementary likelihood estimation을 포함한 여러 새로운 training technique을 사용하여 효과성과 확장성을 향상시킨다. 광범위한 실험은 LaViDa-R1이 visual math reasoning, reason-intensive grounding, image editing을 포함한 다양한 multimodal task에서 강력한 성능을 보임을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63256","en":"Dual Latent Memory for Visual Multi-agent System","ko":"시각적 다중 에이전트 시스템을 위한 이중 잠재 메모리","authors":"Xinlei Yu, Chengming Xu, Zhangquan Chen, Bo Yin, Cheng Yang, Yongbo He, Yihao Hu, Jiangning Zhang, Cheng Tan, Xiaobin Hu, Shuicheng YAN","pos":"#2003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Yhc2PvgFyh","abs":"While Visual Multi-Agent Systems (VMAS) promise to enhance comprehensive abilities through inter-agent collaboration, empirical evidence reveals a counter-intuitive \"scaling wall\": increasing agent turns often degrades performance while exponentially inflating token costs. We attribute this failure to the information bottleneck inherent in text-centric communication, where converting perceptual and thinking trajectories into discrete natural language inevitably induces semantic loss. To this end, we propose L$^{2}$-VMAS, a novel model-agnostic framework that enables inter-agent collaboration with dual latent memories. Based on such a design, we decouple the perception and thinking while dynamically synthesizing dual latent memories. Additionally, we introduce an entropy-driven proactive triggering that replaces passive information transmission with efficient, on-demand memory access. Extensive experiments among backbones, sizes, and multi-agent structures demonstrate that our method effectively breaks the \"scaling wall\" with superb scalability, improving average accuracy by 2.7-5.4% while reducing total token usage by 21.3-44.8%. The codes will be publicly released.","absKo":"Visual Multi-Agent System(VMAS)은 agent 간 협력을 통해 포괄적인 능력을 향상시킬 것으로 기대되지만, 실증적 증거는 직관에 반하는 \"scaling wall\"을 드러낸다. agent turn을 늘리면 성능이 오히려 저하되는 경우가 많고 token cost는 기하급수적으로 증가한다. 우리는 이러한 실패의 원인을 text-centric communication에 내재한 information bottleneck으로 본다. 지각 및 사고 trajectory를 이산적인 natural language로 변환하는 과정에서 필연적으로 semantic loss가 발생하기 때문이다. 이를 위해 우리는 dual latent memory를 통해 agent 간 협력을 가능하게 하는 새로운 model-agnostic framework인 L$^{2}$-VMAS를 제안한다. 이러한 설계를 바탕으로 우리는 perception과 thinking을 분리하면서 dual latent memory를 동적으로 합성한다. 추가로, 수동적인 information transmission을 효율적인 on-demand memory access로 대체하는 entropy-driven proactive triggering을 도입한다. backbone, size, multi-agent structure 전반에 대한 광범위한 실험은 우리의 방법이 평균 정확도를 2.7-5.4% 향상시키면서 total token usage를 21.3-44.8% 줄여, 뛰어난 scalability로 \"scaling wall\"을 효과적으로 돌파함을 보여준다. 코드는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64161","en":"DOUBT: Decoupled Object-level Understanding and Bridging via vMF-based Trustworthiness for Hallucination Detection in MLLMs","ko":"DOUBT: MLLM의 환각 탐지를 위한 vMF 기반 신뢰성을 통한 분리된 객체 수준 이해 및 연결","authors":"Kaiqi Chen, Yang Qin, Changhao He, Xi Peng, Peng Hu","pos":"#2100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QMf9CBpEIf","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) frequently produce hallucinations (i.e., assertions that contradict the image or facts), undermining reliability in high-risk applications. Existing detection approaches typically feed images and texts jointly and estimate hallucination scores by measuring the consistency of model outputs. However, because the visual module often lags behind the language module in understanding and reasoning, MLLMs can repeatedly produce similar yet incorrect answers, yielding deceptively high measured trustworthiness and therefore missed detections. To address this, we propose a simple yet effective model-agnostic method, dubbed Decoupled Object-level Understanding and Bridging via vMF-based Trustworthiness (DOUBT). DOUBT i) elicits richer object-aware responses by decoupling object recognition from relational reasoning via a two-step prompting scheme (Object-level Understanding and Bridging, OUB), and ii) measures reliability with a von Mises–Fisher (vMF)-based trustworthiness metric that is more stable than semantic-entropy metrics under small-sample regimes. Specifically, OUB first prompts the model to list recognized objects, and then conditions chain-of-thought reasoning on those objects to produce object-bridged responses. For trustworthiness estimation, we replace conventional measures with the proposed vMF-based metric, which is robust even under low-sample settings and exhibits smoother behavior than prior techniques. Extensive experiments and ablation studies across multiple benchmarks demonstrate that DOUBT consistently outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, offering a robust and generalizable solution for hallucination detection in MLLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs)는 종종 hallucination, 즉 이미지나 사실과 모순되는 진술을 생성하여 고위험 응용에서 신뢰성을 저해한다. 기존 탐지 방법들은 일반적으로 image와 text를 함께 입력하고 model output의 일관성을 측정하여 hallucination score를 추정한다. 그러나 visual module이 언어 module보다 이해와 추론에서 뒤처지는 경우가 많기 때문에, MLLMs는 유사하지만 여전히 잘못된 답을 반복적으로 생성할 수 있고, 그 결과 겉보기에는 trustworthiness가 높게 측정되어 탐지가 누락될 수 있다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Decoupled Object-level Understanding and Bridging via vMF-based Trustworthiness (DOUBT)라고 부르는 단순하지만 효과적인 model-agnostic 방법을 제안한다. DOUBT는 i) 두 단계 prompting scheme(Object-level Understanding and Bridging, OUB)을 통해 object recognition과 relational reasoning을 분리함으로써 더 풍부한 object-aware response를 이끌어내고, ii) small-sample regime에서 semantic-entropy metric보다 더 안정적인 von Mises–Fisher (vMF)-based trustworthiness metric으로 신뢰성을 측정한다. 구체적으로 OUB는 먼저 모델에게 인식한 object를 나열하도록 유도한 다음, 그 object들을 조건으로 chain-of-thought reasoning을 수행하여 object-bridged response를 생성한다. trustworthiness 추정을 위해 우리는 기존 측도를 제안하는 vMF-based metric으로 대체하며, 이 metric은 low-sample setting에서도 견고하고 이전 기법보다 더 매끄러운 동작을 보인다. 여러 benchmark에 걸친 광범위한 실험과 ablation study는 DOUBT가 state-of-the-art baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, MLLM의 hallucination detection을 위한 견고하고 일반화 가능한 해법을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60892","en":"Probing the Inductive Bias of Neural Networks through Learning Random Cellular Automata","ko":"무작위 Cellular Automata 학습을 통한 Neural Network의 Inductive Bias 탐색","authors":"Jan Disselhoff, Michael Wand","pos":"#2512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vZklm1hnbW","abs":"<p>Why do neural networks generalize well on natural data? Natural data originates from processes subject to specific physical constraints, such as temporal and spatial invariance, that make it easier to learn. We investigate the sufficiency of these properties using 2D cellular automata as a controlled testbed: systems that are perfectly local, symmetric, and deterministic. We find that these conditions alone are \\textit{not sufficient} to predict the k-step evolution of a cellular automaton. We then examine smoothness (average sensitivity) as an additional criterion and find it predictive but still incomplete. Finally, we introduce a circuit complexity perspective, hypothesizing that natural functions are computable by small circuits. Junta coefficients, measuring the concentration of Fourier weight by interaction degree, provide a tighter predictor of learnability and a correspondence to combinatorial complexity. Across architectures (CNNs, transformers, MLPs), learnable functions are predominantly those with spectral weight concentrated at low degrees and therefore low complexity. These results would be consistent with the hypothesis that natural data is learnable because natural dynamics filters out complex, high-degree interactions.</p>","absKo":"<p>왜 neural network는 자연 데이터에서 잘 generalize하는가? 자연 데이터는 temporal invariance와 spatial invariance 같은 특정 물리적 제약을 받는 process에서 비롯되며, 이는 학습을 더 쉽게 만든다. 우리는 2D cellular automata를 통제된 testbed로 사용하여 이러한 성질의 충분성을 조사한다. 이는 완전히 local하고, symmetric하며, deterministic한 system이다. 우리는 이러한 조건만으로는 cellular automaton의 k-step evolution을 예측하기에 <i>충분하지 않음</i>을 발견한다. 이어서 추가 기준으로 smoothness(average sensitivity)를 살펴본 결과, 이는 예측 가능성을 갖지만 여전히 불완전했다. 마지막으로, 우리는 natural function은 작은 circuit으로 계산 가능하다는 가설을 세우는 circuit complexity 관점을 도입한다. interaction degree에 따라 Fourier weight가 얼마나 집중되는지를 측정하는 junta coefficient는 learnability의 더 강한 predictor이자 combinatorial complexity와의 대응 관계를 제공한다. 다양한 architecture(CNN, transformer, MLP) 전반에서, 학습 가능한 함수는 주로 spectral weight가 낮은 degree에 집중되어 있고 따라서 complexity가 낮은 함수들이다. 이러한 결과는 natural dynamics가 복잡하고 high-degree interaction을 걸러내기 때문에 natural data가 학습 가능하다는 가설과 일치한다고 볼 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"63581","en":"Decoupled Training with Local Reinforcement Fine-Tuning in Federated Learning","ko":"연합학습에서의 로컬 강화 미세조정을 이용한 분리형 학습","authors":"Yuting Ma, Lechao Cheng, Xiaohua Xu","pos":"#2600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VoqRpteakw","abs":"<p>Federated Learning (FL) with pre-trained Vision-Language Models (VLMs) has emerged as a promising paradigm for various downstream tasks. By leveraging its strong representations, recent studies improve task adaptation under insufficient local data while preserving generalization. However, these methods emphasize fully local optimization with simple parameter aggregation, which can amplify inter-client optimization inconsistency and intra-client over-specialization under heterogeneous and full-data FL settings, making it difficult to balance global task adaptation and generalization. To address these challenges, we propose FedDTL, a novel federated VLM framework that decouples the image encoder and text encoder across clients and the server. Through decoupled encoder training with server-client modality alignment, FedDTL promotes coherent global semantic update and reduces inter-client optimization inconsistency, improving global task adaptation. To further mitigate intra-client over-specialization, we introduce a two-stage local fine-tuning, where a supervised fine-tuning stage enables rapid and reliable warm-start, followed by a reinforcement learning stage that enhances generalization. Extensive experiments on multiple benchmarks, including label skew and feature shift, demonstrate that FedDTL achieves an effective balance between global task adaptation and generalization under various FL data distributions in both few-shot and full-data regimes.</p>","absKo":"<p>사전 학습된 Vision-Language Models(VLMs)을 활용한 Federated Learning(FL)은 다양한 downstream task를 위한 유망한 패러다임으로 떠오르고 있다. 강력한 representation을 활용함으로써, 최근 연구들은 일반화를 유지하면서도 local data가 부족한 상황에서 task adaptation을 향상시킨다. 그러나 이러한 방법들은 단순한 parameter aggregation에 기반한 완전한 local optimization에 초점을 맞추고 있어, heterogeneous하고 full-data인 FL setting에서 client 간 optimization 불일치와 client 내부 over-specialization을 증폭시킬 수 있으며, 이로 인해 global task adaptation과 generalization의 균형을 맞추기 어렵다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 image encoder와 text encoder를 client와 server 사이에서 decouple하는 새로운 federated VLM framework인 FedDTL을 제안한다. server-client modality alignment를 통한 decoupled encoder training을 통해, FedDTL은 일관된 global semantic update를 촉진하고 client 간 optimization 불일치를 줄여 global task adaptation을 향상시킨다. 또한 client 내부 over-specialization을 더 완화하기 위해, 우리는 두 단계의 local fine-tuning을 도입한다. 여기서 supervised fine-tuning stage는 빠르고 안정적인 warm-start를 가능하게 하고, 이어지는 reinforcement learning stage는 generalization을 강화한다. label skew와 feature shift를 포함한 여러 benchmark에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은, FedDTL이 few-shot과 full-data regime 모두에서 다양한 FL data distribution 하에 global task adaptation과 generalization 사이의 효과적인 균형을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62008","en":"Equivariant Covariance Tensors: Guaranteed SPD Uncertainty for Tensor-Valued Geometric Learning","ko":"Equivariant covariance tensor: tensor-valued geometric learning을 위한 SPD uncertainty 보장","authors":"Ruihan Liu, Yu Ji, Jianbo Yu, Shifu Yan, Qingchao Jiang","pos":"#2603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=klDHS09WNY","abs":"Tensor-valued prediction is fundamental to geometric deep learning, yet uncertainty quantification (UQ) for such outputs remains an open challenge. While E(3)-equivariant neural networks excel at point estimates, they lack rigorous confidence measures. We introduce a general framework for E(3)-equivariant UQ, modeling the full predictive distribution where both mean and covariance preserve rotational symmetry. Our approach decomposes the covariance into irreducible representations $\\mathrm{Sym}^2(\\rho_c) \\cong 2\\times(l=0) \\oplus 2\\times(l=2) \\oplus 1\\times(l=4)$. By mapping from the flat Lie algebra $\\mathfrak{sym}(6)$ to the curved SPD manifold via matrix exponentiation, we strictly ensure positive-definite covariances while maintaining exact equivariance. Furthermore, we formulate a Log-Euclidean Equivariant Scoring Objective (LE-ESO)---a robust surrogate loss based on the Multivariate Laplace distribution---providing mathematical robustness to heavy-tailed errors and guaranteed stability. Extensive validation on ModelNet40 (inertia tensors) and large-scale materials science benchmarks (dielectric tensors) demonstrates that our method achieves competitive performance and provides physically consistent, symmetry-preserving uncertainty estimates with reliable OOD detection capabilities.","absKo":"Tensor-valued prediction은 geometric deep learning의 핵심이지만, 이러한 출력에 대한 uncertainty quantification(UQ)은 여전히 해결되지 않은 과제이다. E(3)-equivariant neural network는 point estimate에서는 뛰어나지만, 엄밀한 confidence measure는 제공하지 못한다. 우리는 mean과 covariance가 모두 rotational symmetry를 보존하는 full predictive distribution을 모델링하는, E(3)-equivariant UQ를 위한 일반적 프레임워크를 제안한다. 우리의 접근은 covariance를 irreducible representation으로 분해한다: $\\mathrm{Sym}^2(\\rho_c) \\cong 2\\times(l=0) \\oplus 2\\times(l=2) \\oplus 1\\times(l=4)$. 평탄한 Lie algebra $\\mathfrak{sym}(6)$에서 matrix exponentiation을 통해 curved SPD manifold로 사상함으로써, 정확한 equivariance를 유지하면서 positive-definite covariance를 엄격히 보장한다. 더 나아가, 우리는 Multivariate Laplace distribution을 기반으로 한 robust surrogate loss인 Log-Euclidean Equivariant Scoring Objective(LE-ESO)를 정식화하여, heavy-tailed error에 대한 수학적 강건성과 보장된 안정성을 제공한다. ModelNet40(inertia tensor)와 대규모 materials science benchmark(dielectric tensor)에 대한 광범위한 검증은 우리의 방법이 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성하며, 물리적으로 일관되고 symmetry를 보존하는 uncertainty estimate와 신뢰할 수 있는 OOD detection 능력을 제공함을 보여준다."},{"id":"63822","en":"Flowers: A Warp Drive for Neural PDE Solvers","ko":"Flowers: 신경 PDE solver를 위한 warp drive","authors":"Till Muser, Alexandra Spitzer, Matti Lassas, Maarten de Hoop, Ivan Dokmanic","pos":"#2604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TPpUKH8fuQ","abs":"<p>We introduce Flower, a neural architecture for learning PDE solution operators built entirely from multihead warps. Aside from pointwise channel mixing and a multiscale scaffold, Flowers use no Fourier multipliers, no dot-product attention, and no convolutional mixing. Each head predicts a displacement field and warps the mixed input features. Motivated by physics and computational efficiency, displacements are predicted pointwise, without any spatial aggregation, and nonlocality enters <em>only</em> through sparse sampling at source coordinates, <em>one</em> per head. Stacking warps in multiscale residual blocks yields Flowers, which implement adaptive, global interactions at linear cost. We theoretically motivate this design through three complementary lenses: flow maps for conservation laws, waves in inhomogeneous media, and a kinetic-theoretic continuum limit. Flowers achieve excellent performance on a broad suite of 2D and 3D time-dependent PDE benchmarks, particularly flows and waves. A compact 17M-parameter model consistently outperforms Fourier, convolution, and attention-based baselines of similar size, while a 150M-parameter variant improves over recent transformer-based foundation models with much more parameters, data, and training compute.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 multihead warp만으로 구성된 PDE solution operator 학습을 위한 neural architecture인 Flower를 소개한다. pointwise channel mixing과 multiscale scaffold를 제외하면, Flower는 Fourier multiplier, dot-product attention, convolutional mixing을 전혀 사용하지 않는다. 각 head는 displacement field를 예측하고 mixed input feature를 warp한다. 물리와 계산 효율성에 대한 동기에 따라, displacement는 공간적 aggregation 없이 pointwise로 예측되며, nonlocality는 각 head마다 <em>하나</em>의 source coordinate에서 sparse sampling을 통해서만 도입된다. multiscale residual block에 warp를 적층하면, 선형 비용으로 adaptive하고 global한 상호작용을 구현하는 Flower가 만들어진다. 우리는 conservation law를 위한 flow map, 비균질 매질에서의 wave, kinetic theory적 continuum limit이라는 세 가지 상보적 관점으로 이 설계를 이론적으로 정당화한다. Flower는 2D 및 3D time-dependent PDE benchmark의 광범위한 집합, 특히 flow와 wave에서 뛰어난 성능을 달성한다. 17M parameter의 compact model은 유사한 크기의 Fourier, convolution, attention 기반 baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, 150M parameter variant는 훨씬 더 많은 parameter, data, training compute를 사용한 최근 transformer 기반 foundation model보다도 더 나은 성능을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64093","en":"Improving Visual Token Reduction via Rectifying Distortions for Efficient Multimodal LLM Inference","ko":"효율적 멀티모달 LLM 추론을 위한 왜곡 보정을 통한 시각 토큰 감축 개선","authors":"Hyeonwoo Cho, Donghyeon Baek, Yewon Kim, Bumsub Ham","pos":"#2607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QxU5sv16tg","abs":"<p>Recent advancements in Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) have achieved remarkable success in vision-language tasks, yet the quadratic computational complexity arising from the vast number of visual tokens creates significant memory and latency bottlenecks. While visual token reduction (VTR) strategies have been explored to mitigate this burden, existing methods overlook the positional and attentional consistency between the full and reduced sequences, resulting in a distorted representation. To this end, we propose a novel VTR framework that rectifies the positional and attentional distortions while maintaining efficiency. Specifically, we present a simple yet effective calibration method that recovers lost visual attention by modulating attention weights based on relative distances. We also introduce a distinctive anchor selection for token merging to mitigate information loss during feature averaging. Experimental results on multiple benchmarks demonstrate that our method consistently improves the accuracy of various reduction methods, achieving state-of-the-art performance while maintaining computational efficiency. We will make our code publicly available online.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models(MLLMs)의 최근 발전은 vision-language task에서 놀라운 성공을 거두었지만, 방대한 수의 visual token에서 비롯되는 quadratic computational complexity는 심각한 memory 및 latency bottleneck을 만든다. 이러한 부담을 완화하기 위해 visual token reduction(VTR) 전략이 연구되어 왔지만, 기존 방법은 full sequence와 reduced sequence 사이의 positional 및 attentional consistency를 간과하여 왜곡된 representation을 초래한다. 이를 위해 우리는 효율성을 유지하면서 positional 및 attentional distortion을 바로잡는 새로운 VTR framework를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 상대적 거리에 기반해 attention weight를 조절함으로써 손실된 visual attention을 복원하는 간단하지만 효과적인 calibration method를 제시한다. 또한 feature averaging 동안의 information loss를 완화하기 위해 token merging에서 distinct anchor selection을 도입한다. 여러 benchmark에서의 실험 결과는 우리의 방법이 다양한 reduction method의 정확도를 일관되게 향상시키며, computational efficiency를 유지하면서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 우리는 코드를 온라인에 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"66244","en":"Large Language Model Teaches Visual Students: Cross-Modality Transfer of Fine-Grained Conceptual Knowledge","ko":"대규모 언어 모델이 시각 학생을 가르치다: 세밀한 개념 지식의 교차 모달리티 전이","authors":"Thomas Shih-Chao Liang, Zhuoran Yu, Yong Jae Lee","pos":"#2610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5UbOL26kGP","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) possess broad conceptual knowledge acquired through large-scale text pretraining, yet their potential to supervise models in other modalities remains underexplored. In this work, we propose \\LaViD—Language-to-Visual Knowledge Distillation—a simple and effective framework for transferring high-level semantic knowledge from a language-only teacher to a vision-only student model. Instead of relying on paired multimodal data, LaViD elicits conceptual signals from an LLM by prompting it to generate multiple-choice questions (MCQs) that probe semantic distinctions between visual classes. Each class is mapped to a soft label distribution over these MCQs, forming a rich conceptual signature that guides the student through an auxiliary distillation loss. Notably, despite using a language-only teacher without access to image data, LaViD consistently outperforms recent methods like MaKD that distill from vision-language models across multiple fine-grained benchmarks. It also achieves competitive or superior performance compared to state-of-the-art visual distillation methods such as DKD and MLKD, with further gains when combined with logit standardization. On the Waterbirds dataset, LaViD substantially improves worst-group accuracy, demonstrating enhanced robustness to spurious correlations with distillation.</p>"},{"id":"63921","en":"Model Fusion via Retrofitting","ko":"Retrofitting을 통한 model fusion","authors":"Phoomraphee Luenam, Andreas Spanopoulos, Amit Sant, Sotiris Anagnostidis, Thomas Hofmann, Sidak Pal Singh","pos":"#2611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SXOqLX0T6X","abs":"<p>Model fusion aims to combine the knowledge of multiple models by creating one representative model that captures the strengths of all of its parents. However, this process is non-trivial due to differences in internal representations, which can stem from permutation invariance, random initialization, or differently distributed training data. We present a novel, neuron-centric family of model fusion algorithms designed to integrate multiple trained neural networks into a single network effectively regardless of training data distribution. Our algorithms group intermediate neurons of parent models to create target representations that the fused model approximates with its corresponding sub-network. Unlike prior approaches, our approach incorporates neuron attribution scores into the fusion process. Furthermore, our algorithms can generalize to arbitrary layer types. Experimental results on various benchmark datasets demonstrate that our algorithms consistently outperform previous fusion techniques, particularly in zero-shot and non-IID fusion scenarios. We make our code publicly available.</p>","absKo":"<p>Model fusion은 여러 model의 지식을 결합하여, 모든 parent의 강점을 담아내는 하나의 대표 model을 만드는 것을 목표로 합니다. 그러나 permutation invariance, random initialization, 서로 다르게 분포된 training data 등으로 인해 internal representation이 달라질 수 있으므로 이 과정은 비자명합니다. 우리는 training data distribution과 무관하게 여러 학습된 neural network를 하나의 network로 효과적으로 통합하도록 설계된, neuron-centric한 새로운 model fusion algorithm family를 제시합니다. 우리의 algorithm은 parent model의 intermediate neuron을 그룹화하여, fused model이 해당 sub-network로 근사하는 target representation을 만듭니다. 기존 접근과 달리, 우리의 방법은 fusion 과정에 neuron attribution score를 포함합니다. 또한 우리의 algorithm은 임의의 layer type으로 일반화될 수 있습니다. 다양한 benchmark dataset에 대한 실험 결과는 우리의 algorithm이 특히 zero-shot 및 non-IID fusion 시나리오에서 이전 fusion technique보다 일관되게 우수함을 보여줍니다. 우리는 코드를 공개적으로 제공합니다.</p>"},{"id":"64816","en":"Platonic Transformers: A Solid Choice For Equivariance","ko":"Platonic Transformer: 등변성을 위한 확실한 선택","authors":"Mohammad Mohaiminul Islam, Rishabh Anand, David Wessels, Friso de Kruiff, Thijs Kuipers, ZHITAO YING, Clara Sánchez, Sharvaree Vadgama, Georg Bökman, Olga Zaghen","pos":"#2614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JTu5Mawn86","abs":"<p>While widespread, Transformers lack inductive biases for geometric symmetries common in science and computer vision. Existing equivariant methods often sacrifice the efficiency and flexibility that make Transformers so effective through complex, computationally intensive designs. We introduce the Platonic Transformer to resolve this trade-off. By defining attention relative to reference frames from the Platonic solid symmetry groups, our method induces a principled weight-sharing scheme. This enables combined equivariance to continuous translations and Platonic symmetries, while preserving the exact architecture and computational cost of a standard Transformer. Furthermore, we show that this attention is formally equivalent to a dynamic group convolution, which reveals that the model learns adaptive geometric filters and enables a <em>highly scalable, linear-time convolutional variant</em>. Across diverse benchmarks in computer vision (CIFAR-10), 3D point clouds (ScanObjectNN), and molecular dynamics, property prediction and generation (OMol25, ProteinMD, QM9), the Platonic Transformer achieves competitive performance by leveraging these geometric constraints at no additional cost.</p>","absKo":"<p>Transformer는 널리 사용되지만, 과학 및 computer vision에서 흔한 geometric symmetry에 대한 inductive bias가 부족하다. 기존의 equivariant method는 종종 복잡하고 계산 집약적인 설계를 통해 Transformer를 효과적으로 만드는 효율성과 유연성을 희생한다. 우리는 이러한 trade-off를 해결하기 위해 Platonic Transformer를 제안한다. Platonic solid symmetry group에서 얻은 reference frame에 대해 attention을 정의함으로써, 우리의 방법은 원칙적인 weight-sharing scheme을 유도한다. 이를 통해 continuous translation과 Platonic symmetry에 대한 combined equivariance를 달성하면서도, standard Transformer의 정확한 architecture와 계산 비용은 그대로 유지한다. 더 나아가, 우리는 이 attention이 dynamic group convolution과 formal하게 동치임을 보이며, 이는 model이 adaptive geometric filter를 학습한다는 점을 드러내고 <em>highly scalable, linear-time convolutional variant</em>를 가능하게 한다. Computer vision(CIFAR-10), 3D point cloud(ScanObjectNN), 그리고 molecular dynamics, property prediction 및 generation(OMol25, ProteinMD, QM9)에 걸친 다양한 benchmark에서, Platonic Transformer는 추가 비용 없이 이러한 geometric constraint를 활용하여 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60910","en":"AnyMod-LLVE: Low-Light Video Enhancement with Modality-Agnostic Inference","ko":"AnyMod-LLVE: Modality-Agnostic Inference를 통한 저조도 비디오 향상","authors":"Hangfeng Liang, Yutao Hu, Yanhan Hu, Xiaohan Wu, WENQI SHAO, Ying Fu","pos":"#2703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vNKtSK8q8D","abs":"<p>Low-light video enhancement (LLVE) remains a challenging task due to severe information degradation under low-illumination conditions. Recent multimodal approaches have significantly improved enhancement performance by incorporating auxiliary modalities, such as event streams and infrared images. However, these methods typically assume the availability of these modalities at inference, which is often not feasible in real-world scenarios. To solve this problem, in this work, we propose AMNet, a unified multimodal framework for LLVE, to support flexible modality-agnostic inference, where auxiliary modalities may be unavailable. To address the issue of modality absence, we introduce a Spatial-Spectral Dual-Gated Translator that learns the correspondence between auxiliary modalities and RGB inputs, producing implicit auxiliary representations to support the robust enhancement. Additionally, to fully facilitate the learning of cross-modal correspondence, we conduct large-scale multimodal pretraining based on the RGB-only dataset with synthetic auxiliary modalities. Extensive experiments demonstrate that AMNet could handle arbitrary inference-time modality combinations and exhibits superior performance for LLVE under modality absence conditions.</p>","absKo":"<p>저조도 비디오 향상(LLVE)은 낮은 조명 조건에서 심각한 정보 손실이 발생하기 때문에 여전히 어려운 과제다. 최근 multimodal 접근법은 event stream과 infrared image 같은 보조 모달리티를 통합함으로써 향상 성능을 크게 높였다. 그러나 이러한 방법들은 일반적으로 추론 시점에서 해당 모달리티를 사용할 수 있다고 가정하며, 이는 실제 환경에서 자주 불가능하다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 본 연구에서는 보조 모달리티가 없을 수 있는 유연한 modality-agnostic inference를 지원하는 LLVE용 통합 multimodal framework인 AMNet을 제안한다. 모달리티 부재 문제를 다루기 위해, 우리는 보조 모달리티와 RGB 입력 간의 대응관계를 학습하여 강건한 향상을 지원하는 implicit auxiliary representation을 생성하는 Spatial-Spectral Dual-Gated Translator를 도입한다. 또한 cross-modal correspondence 학습을 충분히 촉진하기 위해, synthetic auxiliary modality를 사용한 RGB-only 데이터셋 기반의 대규모 multimodal pretraining을 수행한다. 광범위한 실험은 AMNet이 추론 시점의 임의 모달리티 조합을 처리할 수 있으며, 모달리티가 결여된 조건에서 LLVE에 대해 우수한 성능을 보임을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"63566","en":"QPKO: Differentiable QP-Embedded Deep Koopman Framework for Modeling Nonlinear Systems","ko":"QPKO: 비선형 시스템 모델링을 위한 미분 가능한 QP 내장 Deep Koopman 프레임워크","authors":"Runze Tian, Peng Kou","pos":"#2710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VwVBmkAoc9","abs":"<p>Deep learning has been widely regarded as a powerful tool for Koopman operator theory-based modeling, as it provides a promising architecture for data-driven learning of observable functions. To fully leverage this advantage, a well-designed training paradigm is required. However, the existing training paradigms typically either incur high optimization complexity or hinder effective end-to-end training, limiting modeling accuracy and training efficiency. To address this issue, we propose a differentiable quadratic programming (QP)-embedded deep Koopman framework (QPKO). In QPKO, a QP problem, which comprises a one-step accuracy-oriented objective function and a set of multi-step accuracy-oriented constraints, is formulated to introduce a mapping from observable functions to the global linear model. By doing so, the global linear model no longer needs to be treated as an independent trainable component, thereby effectively reducing optimization complexity. This QP-based mapping is implemented as a differentiable and computationally efficient module by leveraging OptNet (a differentiable QP layer), enabling effective end-to-end training. Experiments on four nonlinear dynamical systems show that QPKO achieves satisfactory improvements in modeling accuracy, training efficiency, and control performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Deep learning은 observable function의 data-driven learning을 위한 유망한 architecture를 제공하므로, Koopman operator theory 기반 modeling을 위한 강력한 도구로 널리 여겨져 왔다. 이 이점을 충분히 활용하려면 잘 설계된 training paradigm이 필요하다. 그러나 기존 training paradigm은 대체로 높은 optimization complexity를 유발하거나 효과적인 end-to-end training을 저해하여, modeling 정확도와 training 효율을 제한한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 differentiable quadratic programming(QP)-embedded deep Koopman framework(QPKO)를 제안한다. QPKO에서는 one-step accuracy 지향 objective function과 multi-step accuracy 지향 constraint 집합으로 구성된 QP problem을 정식화하여, observable function에서 global linear model로의 mapping을 도입한다. 이를 통해 global linear model을 더 이상 독립적인 trainable component로 다룰 필요가 없어져 optimization complexity가 효과적으로 줄어든다. 이 QP 기반 mapping은 OptNet(differentiable QP layer)을 활용하여 differentiable하고 계산 효율적인 module로 구현되며, 이를 통해 효과적인 end-to-end training이 가능해진다. 네 가지 nonlinear dynamical system에 대한 실험에서 QPKO는 modeling accuracy, training efficiency, control performance 모두에서 만족스러운 향상을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"61915","en":"Equilibrium Reasoners: Learning Attractors Enables Scalable Reasoning","ko":"Equilibrium Reasoners: attractor 학습을 통한 확장형 추론","authors":"Benhao Huang, Zhengyang Geng, Zico Kolter","pos":"#2712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lh95PnOlpM","abs":"Reasoning is central to building intelligent systems that can solve unseen problems beyond training. Yet we still lack a principled understanding of what internal mechanism enables neural networks to generalize reasoning beyond memorized patterns. We hypothesize that generalizable reasoning emerges through learning task-conditioned attractors. Concretely, the model learns a latent dynamical system whose fixed points correspond to valid solutions. We term models that reason by converging to such task-conditioned fixed points *Equilibrium Reasoners (EqR)*.  This attractor view elucidates when and how to scale test-time compute. Empirically, improvements from scaling test-time compute are tightly coupled with convergence to attractors. By shaping a more favorable attractor landscape and leveraging stochasticity, EqR improves convergence and scales reliably at test time. Our models scale along two axes: *depth* by running more solver steps, and *width* by aggregating stochastic trajectories from multiple random initializations. As we scale test-time compute by $8192\\times$, with max effective layers surpassing 300,000 layers when unrolled, reasoning accuracy rises from 8\\% to over 99\\% on Sudoku-Extreme. We hope our attractor perspective sheds light on scalable reasoning through test-time computation.","absKo":"Reasoning은 학습 중 보지 못한 문제를 해결할 수 있는 intelligent system을 구축하는 데 핵심적이다. 그러나 neural network가 암기된 pattern을 넘어 reasoning을 일반화하게 만드는 내부 메커니즘이 무엇인지에 대해서는 여전히 원리적인 이해가 부족하다. 우리는 일반화 가능한 reasoning이 task-conditioned attractor를 학습함으로써 출현한다고 가정한다. 구체적으로, 모델은 fixed point가 유효한 해에 대응하는 latent dynamical system을 학습한다. 우리는 이러한 task-conditioned fixed point로 수렴함으로써 reasoning하는 model을 *Equilibrium Reasoners (EqR)*라고 부른다. 이 attractor 관점은 test-time compute를 언제, 어떻게 확장할지에 대한 통찰을 제공한다. 경험적으로, test-time compute를 확장했을 때의 향상은 attractor로의 수렴과 밀접하게 연결되어 있다. 더 유리한 attractor landscape를 형성하고 stochasticity를 활용함으로써, EqR은 수렴을 개선하고 test time에서 안정적으로 scale된다. 우리의 모델은 두 축으로 확장된다. 더 많은 solver step을 실행하는 *depth*와, 여러 random initialization에서 나온 stochastic trajectory를 집계하는 *width*이다. test-time compute를 $8192\\times$까지 확장하고, unroll했을 때 최대 effective layer 수가 300,000 layers를 넘어서자, Sudoku-Extreme에서 reasoning 정확도는 8\\%에서 99\\% 이상으로 상승했다. 우리는 이 attractor 관점이 test-time computation을 통한 scalable reasoning에 빛을 비추길 바란다."},{"id":"62736","en":"CauchyNet: Compact and Data-Efficient Learning using Holomorphic Activation Functions","ko":"CauchyNet: Holomorphic Activation Functions 기반의 경량·데이터 효율적 학습","authors":"Hong-Kun Zhang, Xin Li, Sikun Yang, Zhihong Xia","pos":"#2814","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dpniDbdApf","abs":"<p>A novel neural network inspired by Cauchy's integral formula, is proposed for function approximation tasks that include time series forecasting, missing data imputation, etc. Hence, the novel neural network is named CauchyNet. By embedding real-valued data into the complex plane, CauchyNet efficiently captures complex temporal dependencies, surpassing traditional real-valued models in both predictive performance and computational efficiency. Grounded in Cauchy's integral formula and supported by the universal approximation theorem, CauchyNet offers strong theoretical guarantees for function approximation. The architecture incorporates complex-valued activation functions, enabling robust learning from incomplete data while maintaining a compact parameter footprint and reducing computational overhead. Through extensive experiments in diverse domains, including transportation, energy consumption, and epidemiological data, CauchyNet consistently outperforms state-of-the-art models in predictive accuracy, often achieving a lower mean absolute error with fewer parameters. These findings highlight CauchyNet’s potential as an effective and efficient tool for data-driven predictive modeling, particularly in resource-constrained and data-scarce environments. The code used to reproduce the results will be released upon the publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>시간 series forecasting, missing data imputation 등을 포함하는 function approximation task를 위해 Cauchy의 integral formula에서 영감을 받은 새로운 neural network를 제안한다. 따라서 이 새로운 neural network는 CauchyNet이라 명명된다. 실수값 데이터를 complex plane에 embedding함으로써 CauchyNet은 complex temporal dependency를 효율적으로 포착하여, predictive performance와 computational efficiency 모두에서 전통적인 real-valued model을 능가한다. Cauchy의 integral formula에 기반하고 universal approximation theorem에 의해 뒷받침되는 CauchyNet은 function approximation에 대해 강력한 theoretical guarantee를 제공한다. 이 architecture는 complex-valued activation function을 포함하여, compact한 parameter footprint를 유지하면서 incomplete data로부터 robust하게 학습할 수 있게 하고 computational overhead를 줄인다. transportation, energy consumption, epidemiological data를 포함한 다양한 domain에서의 광범위한 실험을 통해, CauchyNet은 예측 정확도에서 state-of-the-art model을 일관되게 능가하며, 더 적은 parameter로 더 낮은 mean absolute error를 달성하는 경우가 많음을 확인했다. 이러한 결과는 CauchyNet이 특히 자원이 제한되고 데이터가 부족한 환경에서 데이터 기반 예측 모델링을 위한 효과적이고 효율적인 도구가 될 잠재력을 보여준다. 결과 재현에 사용된 코드는 논문 출판 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"66039","en":"Calibrated Multimodal Representation Learning with Missing Modalities","ko":"결측 모달리티가 있는 보정된 멀티모달 표현 학습","authors":"Xiaohao Liu, Xiaobo Xia, Jiaheng Wei, Shuo Yang, Xiu Su, See-Kiong Ng, Tat-Seng Chua","pos":"#3608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7fI30TOBtA","abs":"<p>Multimodal representation learning harmonizes distinct modalities by aligning them into a unified latent space. Recent research generalizes traditional cross-modal alignment to produce enhanced multimodal synergy but requires all modalities to be present for a common instance, making it challenging to utilize prevalent datasets with missing modalities. We provide theoretical insights into this issue from an anchor shift perspective. Observed modalities are aligned with a local anchor that deviates from the optimal one when all modalities are present, resulting in an inevitable shift. To address this, we propose CalMRL for multimodal representation learning to calibrate incomplete alignments caused by missing modalities. Specifically, CalMRL leverages the priors and the inherent connections among modalities to model the imputation for the missing ones at the representation level. To resolve the optimization dilemma, we employ a bi-step learning method with the closed-form solution of the posterior distribution of shared latents. We validate its mitigation of anchor shift and convergence with theoretical guidance. By equipping the calibrated alignment with the existing advanced method, we offer new flexibility to absorb data with missing modalities, which is originally unattainable. Extensive experiments and comprehensive analyses demonstrate the superiority of CalMRL. Our code, model checkpoints, and evaluation raw data will be publicly available.</p>"},{"id":"66614","en":"Text Before Vision: Staged Knowledge Injection Matters for Agentic RLVR in Ultra-High-Resolution Remote Sensing Understanding","ko":"시각보다 텍스트 먼저: 초고해상도 원격 탐사 이해에서 에이전트형 RLVR을 위한 단계적 지식 주입의 중요성","authors":"Fengxiang Wang, Mingshuo Chen, Yueying Li, Yang Yajie, Yuhao Zhou, Di Wang, Yi-Fan Zhang, Haoyu Wang, Haiyan Zhao, Hongda Sun, Long Lan, Jun Song, Yulin Wang, Jing Zhang, Wenlong Zhang, Bo Du","pos":"#3704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=29m0TW0Xb3","abs":"<p>Multimodal reasoning for ultra-high-resolution (UHR) remote sensing (RS) is usually bottlenecked by visual evidence acquisition: the model necessities localizing tiny task-relevant regions in massive pixel spaces.  While Agentic Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) using zoom-in tools offers a path forward, we find that standard reinforcement learning struggles to navigate these vast visual spaces without structured domain priors. In this paper, we investigate the interplay between post-training paradigms: comparing Cold-start Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT), RLVR, and Agentic RLVR on the UHR RS benchmark. Our controlled studies yield a counter-intuitive finding: high-quality Earth-science text-only QA is a primary driver of UHR visual reasoning gains. Despite lacking images, domain-specific text injects the concepts, mechanistic explanations, and decision rules necessary to guide visual evidence retrieval. Based on this, we propose a staged knowledge injection recipe: (1) cold-starting with scalable, knowledge-graph-verified Earth-science text QA to instill reasoning structures; and (2) \"pre-warming'' on the same hard UHR image–text examples during SFT to stabilize and amplify subsequent tool-based RL. This approach achieves a 60.04\\% Pass@1 on XLRS-Bench, significantly outperforming larger general-purpose models (e.g., GPT-5.2, Gemini 3.0 Pro, Intern-S1) and establishing a new state-of-the-art. We provide both the automated data pipeline and the rigorous ablation studies that validate this \"Text-Before-Vision'' paradigm. Datasets and code will be released.</p>"},{"id":"62665","en":"GFedCL: Graph-Based Federated Continual Learning with Spatial and Temporal Awareness","ko":"공간 및 시간 인식을 갖춘 Graph-Based 연합 Continual Learning","authors":"Qingyang Yu, Yang Hua, Qizhen Zhang, Hao Wang","pos":"#3805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=eYgiPtpWOh","abs":"<p>Recent years have witnessed a surge of interest in federated learning. In particular, federated continual learning (FCL) emerged as an effective approach that enables clients with evolving, non-storable data to engage in collective learning. Among FCL approaches, replay-based methods excel by mitigating data storage constraints through synthetic data generation. However, existing replay-based methods overlook spatial and temporal information inherent in FCL settings, leading to suboptimal model performance. For instance, spatial variation in COVID-19 prevalence across hospitals in different states (e.g., Delta surging in Florida vs. Omicron in New York) and the temporal evolution of regional outbreaks are critical information for accurately distinguishing between COVID variants. This paper presents GFedCL to address this limitation. GFedCL is a new FCL approach that (1) constructs spatial- and temporal-aware relational graphs with attention mechanisms, and (2) uses the graphs, combined with generative adversarial learning, to generate high-quality synthetic data. GFedCL can generate synthetic data that matches the expectation of real data distribution while preserving privacy with theoretical guarantees. GFedCL consistently outperforms state-of-the-art FCL methods, gaining 27.95% improvement on TinyImageNet.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 몇 년간 federated learning에 대한 관심이 급증했습니다. 특히 federated continual learning(FCL)은 진화하고 저장할 수 없는 데이터를 가진 client들이 collective learning에 참여할 수 있게 해주는 효과적인 접근법으로 부상했습니다. FCL 접근법 중 replay-based method는 synthetic data generation을 통해 데이터 저장 제약을 완화함으로써 뛰어난 성능을 보입니다. 그러나 기존 replay-based method는 FCL 환경에 내재된 spatial 및 temporal information을 간과하여 model performance가 최적에 미치지 못합니다. 예를 들어, 서로 다른 주에 있는 병원 간 COVID-19 유병률의 spatial variation(예: Florida의 Delta 급증 vs. New York의 Omicron)과 지역 outbreak의 temporal evolution은 COVID variant를 정확히 구분하는 데 핵심적인 정보입니다. 본 논문은 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 GFedCL을 제안합니다. GFedCL은 (1) attention mechanism을 사용해 spatial- 및 temporal-aware relational graph를 구성하고, (2) 해당 graph를 generative adversarial learning과 결합하여 고품질 synthetic data를 생성하는 새로운 FCL 접근법입니다. GFedCL은 theoretical guarantee와 함께 privacy를 보존하면서 real data distribution의 expectation에 부합하는 synthetic data를 생성할 수 있습니다. GFedCL은 state-of-the-art FCL 방법을 일관되게 능가하며, TinyImageNet에서 27.95%의 향상을 달성합니다.</p>"},{"id":"61784","en":"Hierarchical Retrieval at Scale: Bridging Transparency and Efficiency","ko":"대규모 계층적 Retrieval: 투명성과 효율성의 연결","authors":"Shubham Gupta, Zichao Li, Tianyi Chen, Cem Subakan, Siva Reddy, Perouz Taslakian, Valentina Zantedeschi","pos":"#4101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mydeyPBS0K","abs":"<p>Information retrieval is a core component of many intelligent systems as it enables conditioning of outputs on new and large-scale datasets. While effective, the standard practice of encoding data into high-dimensional representations for similarity search entails large memory and compute footprints, and also makes it hard to inspect the inner workings of the system. Hierarchical retrieval methods offer an interpretable alternative by organizing data at multiple granular levels, yet do not match the efficiency and performance of flat retrieval approaches. In this paper, we propose Retreever, a tree-based method that makes hierarchical retrieval viable at scale by directly optimizing its structure for retrieval performance while naturally providing transparency through meaningful semantic groupings. Our method offers the flexibility to balance cost and utility by indexing data using representations from any tree level. We show that Retreever delivers strong coarse (intermediate levels) and fine representations (terminal level), while achieving the highest retrieval accuracy at the lowest latency among hierarchical methods. These results demonstrate that this family of techniques is viable in practical applications.</p>","absKo":"<p>정보 검색은 새로운 대규모 데이터셋과의 conditioning을 가능하게 하므로, 많은 지능형 시스템의 핵심 구성 요소이다. 효과적이긴 하지만, 데이터를 similarity search를 위한 고차원 representation으로 인코딩하는 표준 관행은 큰 memory와 compute footprint를 수반하며, 시스템 내부 동작을 निरी하기 어렵게 만든다. Hierarchical retrieval method는 데이터를 여러 세분화 수준에서 조직함으로써 해석 가능한 대안을 제공하지만, flat retrieval approach의 효율성과 성능에는 미치지 못한다. 이 논문에서는 Retreever를 제안한다. 이는 retrieval 성능을 위해 구조를 직접 최적화하면서, 의미 있는 semantic grouping을 통해 자연스럽게 투명성을 제공함으로써 hierarchical retrieval을 대규모로 실용화하는 tree-based method이다. 우리의 방법은 어떤 tree level의 representation이든 사용해 데이터를 indexing함으로써 비용과 유용성의 균형을 맞출 수 있는 유연성을 제공한다. Retreever는 강력한 coarse representation(중간 level)과 fine representation(terminal level)을 제공하면서도, hierarchical method 중 가장 낮은 latency에서 가장 높은 retrieval accuracy를 달성함을 보인다. 이러한 결과는 이 계열의 기법이 실제 응용에서 충분히 활용 가능함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63786","en":"A Consensus Anchor-guided Hypergraph Framework For Incomplete Multi-view Clustering","ko":"불완전한 멀티뷰 클러스터링을 위한 합의 앵커 유도 하이퍼그래프 프레임워크","authors":"Yipin Hu, Yanxi Liu, Fangxi Liu, Yanwei Yu, Lei Meng, Jie Wen, Guoqing Chao","pos":"#4401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Tm0ZpeNHfB","abs":"<p>Handling large-scale incomplete multi-view data poses a significant challenge in unsupervised representation learning. While anchor-based strategies have alleviated computational burdens, they typically rely on shallow bipartite graphs restricted to pairwise relations, failing to capture complex high-order correlations among samples. Furthermore, existing methods often treat observed and missing instances indiscriminately, ignoring the distributional shifts that lead to systematic bias in consensus anchor learning. To address these limitations, we propose a novel framework tailored for scalability and robustness, termed Hypergraph-Augmented Incomplete Multi-View Clustering (HA-IMVC). Unlike traditional approaches, HA-IMVC constructs a consensus anchor-guided hypergraph that explicitly models group-wise interactions, thereby preserving structural integrity even under high missing rates. Crucially, we incorporate a dual-adaptive reweighting mechanism that calibrates importance at both the view and sample levels. This strategy adaptively penalizes severely incomplete samples to mitigate bias while harmonizing inconsistent views. Extensive experiments on diverse benchmarks demonstrate that HA-IMVC achieves superior clustering accuracy and maintains high efficiency, even in scenarios characterized by severe data incompleteness.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 incomplete multi-view data를 처리하는 것은 unsupervised representation learning에서 큰 도전 과제이다. anchor-based 전략은 계산 부담을 완화해 왔지만, 일반적으로 pairwise relation에 국한된 shallow bipartite graph에 의존하여 샘플 간 복잡한 고차 상관관계를 포착하지 못한다. 또한 기존 방법은 관측된 인스턴스와 결측 인스턴스를 종종 구분 없이 다루어, consensus anchor learning에서 체계적 편향을 초래하는 distribution shift를 무시한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 확장성과 강건성을 위해 설계된 새로운 프레임워크인 Hypergraph-Augmented Incomplete Multi-View Clustering (HA-IMVC)를 제안한다. 전통적 접근과 달리, HA-IMVC는 group-wise interaction을 명시적으로 모델링하는 consensus anchor-guided hypergraph를 구성하여, 높은 결측률에서도 구조적 무결성을 보존한다. 특히, 우리는 view 수준과 sample 수준 모두에서 중요도를 보정하는 dual-adaptive reweighting mechanism을 도입한다. 이 전략은 심하게 불완전한 sample에 적응적으로 페널티를 부여하여 bias를 완화하는 동시에, 서로 일치하지 않는 view를 조화시킨다. 다양한 benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 HA-IMVC가 심각한 데이터 불완전성이 존재하는 상황에서도 우수한 clustering accuracy를 달성하고 높은 효율성을 유지함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"66693","en":"OMP: One-step Meanflow Policy with Directional Alignment","ko":"OMP: 방향 정렬을 갖춘 One-step Meanflow Policy","authors":"Han Fang, Yize Huang, Yuheng Zhao, Paul Weng, Xiao Li, Yutong Ban","pos":"#500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1IQTouHYl2","abs":"<p>Robot manipulation has increasingly adopted data-driven generative policy frameworks, yet the field faces a persistent trade-off: diffusion models suffer from high inference latency, while flow-based methods often require complex architectural constraints. Although in image generation domain, the MeanFlow paradigm offers a path to single-step inference, its direct application to robotics is impeded by critical theoretical pathologies, specifically spectral bias and gradient starvation in low-velocity regimes. To overcome these limitations, we propose the One-step MeanFlow Policy (OMP), a novel framework designed for high-fidelity, real-time manipulation. We introduce a lightweight directional alignment mechanism to explicitly synchronize predicted velocities with true mean velocities. Furthermore, we implement a Differential Derivation Equation (DDE) to approximate the Jacobian-Vector Product (JVP) operator, which decouples forward and backward passes to significantly reduce memory complexity. Extensive experiments on the Adroit and Meta-World benchmarks demonstrate that OMP outperforms state-of-the-art methods in success rate and trajectory accuracy, particularly in high-precision tasks, while retaining the efficiency of single-step generation.</p>"},{"id":"61341","en":"Quant VideoGen: Auto-Regressive Long Video Generation via 2-Bit KV-Cache Quantization","ko":"Quant VideoGen: 2-Bit KV-Cache 양자화를 통한 Auto-Regressive 장편 비디오 생성","authors":"Haocheng Xi, Shuo Yang, Yilong Zhao, Muyang Li, Han Cai, Xingyang Li, Yujun Lin, Zhuoyang Zhang, Jintao Zhang, Xiuyu Li, Zhiying Xu, Jun Wu, Chenfeng Xu, Ion Stoica, Song Han, Kurt Keutzer","pos":"#4603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=r9UJgVH1Fx","abs":"<p>Despite rapid progress in auto-regressive video diffusion, we identify an emerging system–algorithm bottleneck that limits both deployability and generation quality: KV-cache memory. In auto-regressive video generation models, the KV-cache grows with generation history and quickly dominates GPU memory (often ≥30 GB), preventing deployment on widely available hardware. More critically, memory-bounded KV budgets constrain the effective working memory, directly degrading long-horizon consistency in identity, layout, and motion. To address this challenge, we present Quant VideoGen (QVG), a training-free KV-cache quantization framework for auto-regressive video diffusion models. QVG exploits video’s inherent spatiotemporal redundancy via Semantic-Aware Smoothing, producing low-magnitude, quantization-friendly residuals. Building on this, QVG introduces Progressive Residual Quantization, a coarse-to-fine multi-stage scheme that further reduces quantization error while enabling a smooth quality–memory trade-off. Across LongCat-Video, HY-WorldPlay, and Self-Forcing, QVG establishes a new Pareto frontier between quality and memory efficiency, reducing KV memory by up to 7.0× with less than 4% end-to-end latency overhead, while delivering significantly better generation quality than existing baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>auto-regressive video diffusion의 급속한 발전에도 불구하고, 우리는 배포 가능성과 생성 품질을 동시에 제한하는 새로운 시스템-알고리즘 병목, 즉 KV-cache 메모리를 식별한다. auto-regressive video generation 모델에서 KV-cache는 생성 이력과 함께 계속 증가하며 빠르게 GPU 메모리를 지배한다(종종 ≥30 GB), 이로 인해 널리 उपलब्ध한 하드웨어에 배포하는 것이 불가능해진다. 더 중요하게는, 메모리 제약이 있는 KV budget은 유효한 작업 기억 용량을 제한하여 identity, layout, motion의 장기 일관성을 직접적으로 저해한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 auto-regressive video diffusion 모델을 위한 training-free KV-cache quantization 프레임워크인 Quant VideoGen (QVG)를 제안한다. QVG는 Semantic-Aware Smoothing을 통해 비디오 고유의 spatiotemporal redundancy를 활용하여, 양자화에 유리한 낮은 크기의 residual을 생성한다. 이를 바탕으로 QVG는 Progressive Residual Quantization을 도입하는데, 이는 거친 단계에서 미세한 단계로 진행되는 다단계 스킴으로 양자화 오차를 추가로 줄이는 동시에 매끄러운 quality-메모리 trade-off를 가능하게 한다. LongCat-Video, HY-WorldPlay, Self-Forcing 전반에서 QVG는 quality와 memory efficiency 사이의 새로운 Pareto frontier를 확립하며, 4% 미만의 end-to-end latency overhead로 KV 메모리를 최대 7.0× 줄이면서 기존 baseline보다 현저히 더 나은 생성 품질을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63472","en":"Timestep Rescheduling in Diffusion Inversion","ko":"Diffusion 역변환에서의 Timestep 재스케줄링","authors":"Shangquan Sun, Ting Gong, Liu, Jiamin Wu, Runkai Zhao, Mianxin Liu, Wenqi Ren, Xiaochun Cao","pos":"#2300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WsZwXIx5r8","abs":"<p>Diffusion inversion, which maps images back to the Gaussian latent space of a diffusion model, is a critical task for image reconstruction and editing.  While DDIM enables fast deterministic inversion, it inherently introduces deviations that accumulate into noticeable inversion errors.  Existing methods often address this by solving a fixed-point problem but largely overlook how the selection of the diffusion timestep in the noise scheduler influences inversion fidelity. In this work, we reveal that the deviation scale in diffusion inversion is strongly dependent on the timestep size, and exhibits a parabolic trend, with larger errors concentrated at both small and large timesteps.  Based on this finding, we propose a simple yet effective nonuniform timestep scheduler that integrates a global rescaling with a local dynamic programming based rescheduling, enabling a strategic allocation of computational effort that minimizes the overall inversion error and preserves higher inversion accuracy. Our method serves as an off-the-shelf enhancement for existing inversion techniques and requires no extra parameters or computational overhead. Through extensive experiments, we verify that integrating our scheduler consistently boosts the performance of existing inversion methods, achieving superior results in image reconstruction and editing.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion inversion은 이미지를 diffusion model의 Gaussian latent space로 되돌리는 과정으로, image reconstruction과 editing에서 핵심적인 task이다. DDIM은 빠르고 결정적인 inversion을 가능하게 하지만, 본질적으로 편차를 유발하며 이 편차는 누적되어 눈에 띄는 inversion error로 이어진다. 기존 방법들은 종종 이를 fixed-point problem을 풀어서 해결하지만, noise scheduler에서 diffusion timestep을 어떻게 선택하느냐가 inversion fidelity에 미치는 영향은 대체로 간과해왔다. 본 연구에서는 diffusion inversion에서의 deviation scale이 timestep 크기에 강하게 의존하며, 작은 timestep과 큰 timestep 양쪽에서 더 큰 error가 집중되는 포물선형 경향을 보인다는 점을 밝힌다. 이 발견을 바탕으로, 우리는 전역 rescaling과 local dynamic programming 기반 rescheduling을 통합한 간단하지만 효과적인 nonuniform timestep scheduler를 제안한다. 이를 통해 전체 inversion error를 최소화하고 더 높은 inversion accuracy를 유지하도록 계산 노력을 전략적으로 배분할 수 있다. 우리의 방법은 기존 inversion technique에 바로 적용 가능한 off-the-shelf enhancement로서, 추가 파라미터나 계산 오버헤드를 요구하지 않는다. 광범위한 실험을 통해 우리의 scheduler를 통합하면 기존 inversion method의 성능이 일관되게 향상되며, image reconstruction과 editing에서 우수한 결과를 달성함을 검증했다.</p>"},{"id":"66281","en":"Solving Inverse Problems with Flow-based Models via Model Predictive Control","ko":"Model Predictive Control을 통한 Flow 기반 모델로 역문제 풀기","authors":"George Webber, Alexander Denker, Riccardo Barbano, Andrew Reader","pos":"#1004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=57lp1pmJVo","abs":"<p>Flow-based generative models provide strong unconditional priors for inverse problems, but guiding their dynamics for conditional generation remains challenging. Recent work casts training-free conditional generation in flow models as an optimal control problem; however, solving the resulting trajectory optimisation is computationally and memory intensive, requiring differentiation through the flow dynamics or adjoint solves. We propose MPC-Flow, a model predictive control framework that formulates inverse problem solving with flow-based generative models as a sequence of control sub-problems, enabling practical optimal control-based guidance at inference time. We provide theoretical guarantees linking MPC-Flow to the underlying optimal control objective and show how different algorithmic choices yield a spectrum of guidance algorithms, including regimes that avoid backpropagation through the generative model trajectory. We evaluate MPC-Flow on benchmark image restoration tasks, spanning linear and non-linear settings such as in-painting, deblurring, and super-resolution, and demonstrate strong performance and scalability to massive state-of-the-art architectures via training-free guidance of FLUX.2 (32B) in a quantised setting on consumer hardware.</p>"},{"id":"64483","en":"Periodic Bayesian Flow Networks with Additive Accuracy","ko":"가법적 정확도를 갖는 주기적 베이지안 흐름 네트워크","authors":"Peijia Lin, Zihan Zhang, zhangrui zhao, Shaohao Rui, Junyi An, Yun-Fei Shi, Fenglei Cao, Weijie Ma, Yutong Lu","pos":"#1207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=N7hieduZYV","abs":"<p>Generating periodic data---such as fractional atomic coordinates in crystal structures and phase patterns in compressive light-field (CLF) displays---is challenging because wrap-around boundaries complicate probabilistic modeling and learning. While Bayesian Flow Networks (BFNs) offer a powerful generative framework with strictly additive accuracy in Euclidean space, existing periodic adaptations typically sacrifice additivity and become sensitive to schedule heuristics. We introduce \\emph{PeriodicBFN}, which embeds each periodic scalar into a two-dimensional unit-circle representation and performs Gaussian Bayesian updates in the resulting Cartesian space, thereby restoring strictly additive accuracy. To address invariance in periodic generative modeling, we further derive a Rao--Blackwellized objective that analytically marginalizes global periodic translations, producing a translation-invariant target with reduced gradient variance. Experiments on crystal structure prediction and multi-layer phase synthesis for CLF displays demonstrate improved training stability and strong performance. To our knowledge, this is the first work to extend periodic-data generative modeling to phase synthesis for modern glasses-free 3D display systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>crystal structure의 fractional atomic coordinate와 compressive light-field (CLF) display의 phase pattern과 같은 periodic data를 생성하는 일은 wrap-around boundary가 probabilistic modeling과 learning을 복잡하게 만들기 때문에 어렵다. Bayesian Flow Networks (BFNs)는 Euclidean space에서 엄밀히 additive한 accuracy를 갖는 강력한 generative framework를 제공하지만, 기존의 periodic adaptation은 대개 additivity를 희생하고 schedule heuristic에 민감해진다. 우리는 각 periodic scalar를 2차원 unit-circle representation에 embedding하고, 그 결과로 얻어진 Cartesian space에서 Gaussian Bayesian update를 수행함으로써 엄밀히 additive한 accuracy를 복원하는 \\emph{PeriodicBFN}을 제안한다. periodic generative modeling에서의 invariance를 다루기 위해, 우리는 전역 periodic translation을 해석적으로 marginalize하는 Rao--Blackwellized objective를 추가로 유도하여, gradient variance를 줄인 translation-invariant target을 만든다. crystal structure prediction과 CLF display를 위한 multi-layer phase synthesis에 대한 실험은 향상된 training stability와 강한 성능을 보여준다. 우리가 아는 한, 이것은 periodic-data generative modeling을 현대 glass-free 3D display system의 phase synthesis로 확장한 최초의 작업이다.</p>"},{"id":"63429","en":"Variational Flow Maps: Make Some Noise for One-Step Conditional Generation","ko":"Variational Flow Maps: 원스텝 조건부 생성을 위한 노이즈 만들기","authors":"Abbas Mammadov, So Takao, Bohan Chen, Ricardo Baptista, Morteza Mardani, Yee-Whye Teh, Julius Berner","pos":"#2202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XHI7FCd1w1","abs":"<p>Flow maps enable high-quality image generation in a single forward pass. However, unlike iterative diffusion models, their lack of an explicit sampling trajectory impedes incorporating external constraints for conditional generation and solving inverse problems. We put forth <em>Variational Flow Maps</em>, a framework for conditional sampling that shifts the perspective of conditioning from \"guiding a sampling path\", to that of \"learning the proper initial noise\". Specifically, given an observation, we seek to learn a <em>noise adapter model</em> that outputs a noise distribution, so that after mapping to the data space via flow map, the samples respect the observation and data prior. To this end, we develop a principled variational objective that jointly trains the noise adapter and the flow map, improving noise-data alignment, such that sampling from complex data posterior is achieved with a simple adapter. Experiments on various inverse problems show that VFMs produce well-calibrated conditional samples in a single (or few) steps. For ImageNet, VFM attains competitive fidelity  while accelerating the sampling by orders of magnitude compared to alternative iterative diffusion/flow models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Flow map은 단일 forward pass에서 고품질 이미지 생성을 가능하게 한다. 그러나 iterative diffusion model과 달리, 명시적인 sampling trajectory가 없기 때문에 conditional generation에 외부 제약을 통합하거나 inverse problem을 해결하는 것이 어렵다. 우리는 <em>Variational Flow Maps</em>를 제안한다. 이는 conditioning의 관점을 \"sampling path를 안내하는 것\"에서 \"적절한 초기 noise를 학습하는 것\"으로 전환하는 conditional sampling framework이다. 구체적으로, 관측값이 주어졌을 때 우리는 flow map을 통해 data space로 매핑된 이후 샘플이 관측값과 data prior를 모두 만족하도록 noise distribution을 출력하는 <em>noise adapter model</em>을 학습하고자 한다. 이를 위해, noise adapter와 flow map을 공동으로 학습하는 원리적인 variational objective를 개발하여 noise-data alignment를 향상시키며, 그 결과 복잡한 data posterior로부터의 샘플링을 간단한 adapter만으로 달성한다. 다양한 inverse problem에 대한 실험은 VFM이 단일(또는 소수) step에서 잘 보정된 conditional sample을 생성함을 보여준다. ImageNet에서는 VFM이 경쟁력 있는 fidelity를 달성하면서도 대안적인 iterative diffusion/flow model에 비해 샘플링 속도를 수십 배 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"66609","en":"Stable Velocity: A Variance Perspective on Flow Matching","ko":"Stable Velocity: Flow Matching에 대한 분산 관점","authors":"Donglin Yang, Yongxing Zhang, Xin Yu, Liang Hou, Xin Tao, Pengfei Wan, XIAOJUAN QI, Renjie Liao","pos":"#2301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2C6ENeBAZB","abs":"While flow matching is elegant, its reliance on single-sample conditional velocities leads to high-variance training targets that destabilize optimization and slow convergence. By explicitly characterizing this variance, we identify 1) a *high-variance regime* near the prior, where optimization is challenging, and 2) a *low-variance regime* near the data distribution, where conditional and marginal velocities nearly coincide. Leveraging this insight, we propose **Stable Velocity**, a unified framework that improves both training and sampling. For training, we introduce Stable Velocity Matching (StableVM), an unbiased variance-reduction objective, along with Variance-Aware Representation Alignment (VA-REPA), which adaptively strengthen auxiliary supervision in the *low-variance regime*. For inference, we show that dynamics in the *low-variance regime* admit closed-form simplifications, enabling Stable Velocity Sampling (StableVS), a finetuning-free acceleration. Extensive experiments on ImageNet $256\\times256$ and large pretrained text-to-image and text-to-video models, including SD3.5, Flux, Qwen-Image, and Wan2.2, demonstrate consistent improvements in training efficiency and more than $2\\times$ faster sampling within the *low-variance regime* without degrading sample quality."},{"id":"65935","en":"SlerpFlow: Spherical Trajectory Correction for Rectified Flow Inversion","ko":"SlerpFlow: Rectified Flow Inversion을 위한 구면 궤적 보정","authors":"Wenbin Duan, Yan Shu, Zhuoyuan Fu, Fangmin Zhao, Yan Li, Yaru Zhao, Binyang Li","pos":"#2303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8kBvoukwPs","abs":"<p>Rectified-flow-based diffusion transformers, particularly FLUX, have demonstrated outstanding performance in high-quality image generation. However, achieving fast and accurate inversion—transforming images back to latent noise for faithful reconstruction and editing—remains a challenging bottleneck due to the discretization errors of linear solvers. This paper introduces \\textbf{SlerpFlow}, a straightforward yet highly effective zero-shot approach that unlocks the full potential of FLUX for high-fidelity inversion and editing. Unlike existing approaches (e.g., RF-Solver) that rely on complex numerical approximations such as  high-order Taylor expansions to correct trajectory errors, we present a geometric view based on the Manifold Hypothesis: the empirically observed trajectory curvature is not a numerical artifact, but rather serves as a necessary ``centripetal force\" that constrains the flow to remain on the data manifold. Guided by this insight, SlerpFlow integrates Spherical Linear Interpolation (Slerp) to rectify flow velocity directions on the hypersphere, strictly adhering to the intrinsic curvature of the latent space. Crucially, by caching the corrected velocity for subsequent steps, SlerpFlow achieves high-precision inversion while maintaining the computational efficiency of a first-order Euler solver. Extensive experiments on FLUX-based reconstruction and editing tasks demonstrate that our method delivers superior structural consistency and lower reconstruction errors compared to state-of-the-art baselines without requiring additional training.</p>"},{"id":"65248","en":"SE(n)-Invariant Flow Matching: A General Framework with Application to Object Reassembly","ko":"SE(n)-불변 Flow Matching: 객체 재조립 응용을 포함한 일반 프레임워크","authors":"Gaël Heck, Sylvie Le Hégarat-Mascle, Nicolas Lermé","pos":"#2305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FN7KIzIQiA","abs":"Reassembling $N$ fragments in $n$-dimensional space is a shape reconstruction task that is invariant to global rigid motions.  Training directly on $\\mathcal{M}=\\mathrm{SE}(n)^N$ can be ill-posed: standard losses penalize solutions that differ only by a global transform.  Existing methods often address this with ad-hoc anchoring which breaks permutation invariance across fragments and can introduce biases that must be mitigated with extensive and costly data augmentation. We propose a geometric framework that enforces invariance by construction. First, a **Global Gauge Fixing** (GGF) strategy deterministically aligns configurations using an intrinsic generalized-inertia rule.  Second, we introduce a **quotient-invariant Flow Matching objective** that operates via orthogonal projection onto the horizontal tangent bundle. This construction factors out global pose at each timestep, enabling the model to learn only shape-changing dynamics on the quotient space $\\mathcal{M}/\\mathrm{SE}(n)$.  Our unified $\\mathrm{SE}(n)$-invariant framework admits efficient closed-form 2D/3D instantiations and improves accuracy on polygonal jigsaw puzzles and 3D fracture reassembly benchmarks.","absKo":"N개의 fragment를 n차원 공간에서 재조립하는 문제는 global rigid motion에 불변인 shape reconstruction task이다. $\\mathcal{M}=\\mathrm{SE}(n)^N$에서 직접 학습하는 것은 잘 정의되지 않을 수 있는데, standard loss는 global transform만 다를 뿐인 해를 불필요하게 벌주기 때문이다. 기존 방법은 종종 이를 ad-hoc anchoring으로 해결하지만, 이는 fragment 간 permutation invariance를 깨뜨리고 광범위하고 비용이 큰 data augmentation으로만 완화할 수 있는 bias를 도입할 수 있다. 우리는 구성 자체로 invariance를 보장하는 geometric framework를 제안한다. 첫째, **Global Gauge Fixing** (GGF) 전략은 intrinsic generalized-inertia rule을 사용해 configuration을 결정적으로 정렬한다. 둘째, 우리는 orthogonal projection을 통해 horizontal tangent bundle 위에서 작동하는 **quotient-invariant Flow Matching objective**를 도입한다. 이 구성은 각 timestep에서 global pose를 소거하여, model이 quotient space $\\mathcal{M}/\\mathrm{SE}(n)$에서 shape-changing dynamics만 학습하도록 한다. 우리의 통합된 $\\mathrm{SE}(n)$-invariant framework는 효율적인 closed-form 2D/3D instantiation을 허용하며, polygonal jigsaw puzzle과 3D fracture reassembly benchmark에서 정확도를 향상시킨다."},{"id":"65239","en":"SE(3)-Equivariant Flow Matching with Gaussian Process Priors for Geometric Trajectory Prediction","ko":"기하학적 궤적 예측을 위한 Gaussian Process 사전정보 기반 SE(3)-Equivariant Flow Matching","authors":"Xuyang Wang, Xinzhe Zhou, Xiaoming Duan, Jianping He","pos":"#2306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FR0ZFbkGnX","abs":"<p>The trajectory prediction of N-body systems is of great significance and remains challenging with broad applications across various fields such as physics, chemistry and biology.  Recent advances in generative models including flow matching and diffusion models have emerged as effective solutions to this problem, owing to their capacity to model the stochasticity and underlying distributions of complex system trajectories.  However, existing approaches typically adopt trivial prior distributions that neglect the temporal correlations and spatial symmetries of N-body trajectories, which not only complicates the generation process but also limits model performance. To address these limitations, we propose GP-EquiFlow, an SE(3)-equivariant flow matching model incorporating vector-valued Gaussian processes.  Based on observed trajectories, we employ vector-valued Gaussian processes to construct SE(3)-equivariant prior distributions, which exhibit enhanced consistency with the target data distribution in both spatial and temporal dynamics.  Extensive experiments on N-body simulations and molecular dynamics demonstrate that the proposed GP-EquiFlow delivers more accurate predictions while requiring fewer sampling steps, underscoring the effectiveness of integrating Gaussian process-based SE(3)-equivariant prior distributions in geometric trajectory prediction.</p>","absKo":"<p>N-body system의 trajectory prediction은 매우 중요하며, physics, chemistry, biology 등 다양한 분야에서 넓은 응용을 가진 채 여전히 어려운 문제로 남아 있다. 최근 flow matching과 diffusion model을 포함한 generative model은 복잡한 system trajectory의 stochasticity와 underlying distribution을 모델링할 수 있는 능력 덕분에 이 문제에 대한 효과적인 해법으로 부상했다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 일반적으로 N-body trajectory의 temporal correlation과 spatial symmetry를 무시하는 단순한 prior distribution을 채택하며, 이는 생성 과정을 복잡하게 만들 뿐 아니라 모델 성능도 제한한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 vector-valued Gaussian process를 통합한 SE(3)-equivariant flow matching model인 GP-EquiFlow를 제안한다. 관측된 trajectory를 바탕으로, 우리는 vector-valued Gaussian process를 사용해 SE(3)-equivariant prior distribution을 구성하며, 이는 spatial 및 temporal dynamics 모두에서 target data distribution과의 일관성을 높인다. N-body simulation과 molecular dynamics에 대한 광범위한 실험은 제안한 GP-EquiFlow가 더 적은 sampling step으로도 더 정확한 예측을 제공함을 보여주며, geometric trajectory prediction에서 Gaussian process 기반 SE(3)-equivariant prior distribution을 통합하는 효과를 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"65439","en":"Riemannian MeanFlow for One-Step Generation on Manifolds","ko":"다양체에서 One-Step 생성을 위한 Riemannian MeanFlow","authors":"Zichen Zhong, Haoliang Sun, Yukun Zhao, Yongshun Gong, Yilong Yin","pos":"#2307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DeOm4Axr9W","abs":"<p>Flow Matching enables simulation-free training of generative models on Riemannian manifolds, yet sampling typically still relies on numerically integrating a probability-flow ODE. We propose Riemannian MeanFlow (RMF), extending MeanFlow to manifold-valued generation where velocities lie in location-dependent tangent spaces. RMF defines an average-velocity field via parallel transport and derives a Riemannian MeanFlow identity that links average and instantaneous velocities for intrinsic supervision. We make this identity practical in a log-map tangent representation, avoiding trajectory simulation and heavy geometric computations. For stable optimization, we decompose the RMF objective into two terms and apply conflict-aware multi-task learning to mitigate gradient interference. RMF also supports conditional generation via classifier-free guidance. Experiments on spheres, tori, and SO(3) demonstrate competitive one-step sampling with improved quality–efficiency trade-offs and substantially reduced sampling cost.</p>"},{"id":"61661","en":"Random Process Flow Matching: Generative Implicit Representations of Multivariate Random Fields","ko":"Random Process Flow Matching: 다변량 Random Field의 생성적 Implicit Representation","authors":"Julien Lalanne, David Picard, Lionel Boillot, Lina-María GUAYACÁN-CARRILLO, Leon Barens, Jean-Michel Pereira","pos":"#2309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nzYTAVwZeJ","abs":"<p>Generative modeling provides a powerful framework for learning data distributions. These models initially relied on probabilistic methods such as Gaussian Processes (GP) for uncertainty-aware predictions and shifted towards larger trainable models to learn more complex distributions. In this work, we introduce <em>Random Process (RP) Flow</em>, a Flow Matching-based framework that represents the vector field as a neural implicit function. Unlike modern generative methods, our setting involves a single observed field, from which only sparse measurements are available. RP Flow uses Random Fourier Features to learn an implicit signal representation that can be queried at any arbitrary location from a limited set of observations, while encoding uncertainty through ensemble sampling. We propose constructing a Bayesian posterior by GP regression in the source space to generate high-quality samples. Our empirical results demonstrate that this framework generates realistic samples along with calibrated uncertainty estimates, even under challenging conditions such as high frequency, high sparsity, or high dimensionality. These findings position RP Flow as a milestone towards generative models for reconstruction tasks where data is scarce and uncertainty must remain traceable.</p>","absKo":"<p>Generative modeling은 데이터 분포를 학습하기 위한 강력한 프레임워크를 제공합니다. 이러한 모델은 초기에는 불확실성 인지 예측을 위해 Gaussian Processes (GP)와 같은 확률적 방법에 의존했으며, 더 복잡한 분포를 학습하기 위해 점차 더 큰 trainable 모델로 이동했습니다. 본 연구에서는 벡터 필드를 neural implicit function으로 표현하는 Flow Matching 기반 프레임워크인 <em>Random Process (RP) Flow</em>를 소개합니다. 현대의 생성 방법과 달리, 우리의 설정은 단일 관측된 field를 다루며, 여기서 얻을 수 있는 것은 sparse measurements뿐입니다. RP Flow는 Random Fourier Features를 사용하여 제한된 관측 집합으로부터 임의의 위치에서 질의 가능한 implicit signal representation을 학습하는 동시에, ensemble sampling을 통해 불확실성을 인코딩합니다. 우리는 source space에서 GP regression으로 Bayesian posterior를 구성하여 고품질 샘플을 생성하는 방법을 제안합니다. 우리의 실험 결과는 이 프레임워크가 high frequency, high sparsity, high dimensionality와 같은 어려운 조건에서도 잘 보정된 불확실성 추정과 함께 현실적인 샘플을 생성함을 보여줍니다. 이러한 결과는 RP Flow를 데이터가 희소하고 불확실성을 추적 가능하게 유지해야 하는 reconstruction task를 위한 generative model로 나아가는 이정표로 자리매김합니다.</p>"},{"id":"62800","en":"Contrastive Flow Map Matching","ko":"대조적 Flow Map Matching","authors":"Junyu Zhang, Daochang Liu, Younghyun Kim, Jong Hwan Ko, Shichao Zhang, Chang Xu, Eunbyung Park","pos":"#2403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=d9AhmsW5JA","abs":"<p>Flow map matching (FMM) enables one- and few-step sampling for diffusion-style generation, yet its performance is often hindered by the mismatch between ground-truth training transitions and model-induced flow maps. We propose \\textbf{Contrastive Flow Map Matching (CFMM)}, a principled framework that explicitly aligns FMM training with practical sampling. Our approach is grounded in a theoretical upper bound on the reverse KL divergence, which decomposes the distributional gap into a marginal mismatch over intermediate states and a conditional mismatch in endpoint reconstruction. This analysis motivates two complementary objectives: average-velocity regression for marginal alignment and a sampling-aligned InfoNCE contrastive loss for conditional refinement. CFMM is a training-only plug-in for pre-trained FMMs, incurs no inference-time overhead, and supports training FMMs from scratch. Experiments on CIFAR-10, ImageNet, and LSUN across multiple FMM baselines demonstrate consistent improvements in fidelity and perceptual quality with only modest additional training cost.</p>","absKo":"<p>Flow map matching (FMM)은 diffusion-style generation에서 one-step 및 few-step sampling을 가능하게 하지만, ground-truth training transition과 model-induced flow map 사이의 mismatch 때문에 성능이 종종 저하됩니다. 우리는 FMM training을 실제 sampling과 명시적으로 정렬하는 원리적인 framework인 \\textbf{Contrastive Flow Map Matching (CFMM)}을 제안합니다. 우리의 접근은 reverse KL divergence에 대한 이론적 upper bound에 기반하며, 이는 distributional gap을 intermediate state에 대한 marginal mismatch와 endpoint reconstruction의 conditional mismatch로 분해합니다. 이 분석은 두 개의 상보적 목표를 이끕니다: marginal alignment를 위한 average-velocity regression과 conditional refinement를 위한 sampling-aligned InfoNCE contrastive loss입니다. CFMM은 pre-trained FMM에 대한 training-only plug-in이며 inference-time overhead가 없고, scratch부터 FMM을 학습하는 것도 지원합니다. CIFAR-10, ImageNet, LSUN에서 여러 FMM baseline에 걸친 실험은 적당한 추가 training cost만으로 fidelity와 perceptual quality를 일관되게 개선함을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"62479","en":"How to guide your flow: Steering flow maps for rapid test-time alignment","ko":"flow를 안내하라: 빠른 test-time alignment를 위한 steering flow maps","authors":"Jerry Huang, Justin Lin, Sheel Shah, Kartik Nair, Nicholas Boffi","pos":"#2408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gEogY6cPrL","abs":"<p>In generative modeling, we often wish to produce samples that satisfy a user-specified reward such as measurement consistency, aesthetic quality, or alignment with human intent, a problem known as inference-time guidance. While flow-based models enable high-quality generation, existing guidance methods either require expensive multi-particle, many-step schemes to sample from a reward-tilted distribution or rely on heuristic approximations. To design efficient algorithms, we instead reformulate guidance as a deterministic optimal control problem, rather than the stochastic control problem from which the reward tilt emerges. We find that the flow map arises naturally in the optimal solution, and that many existing flow-based guidance methods are best understood as coarse approximations that replace it with a single Euler step. Rather than relying on these approximations, we propose Flow Map Trajectory Guidance (FMTG): a principled framework that uses the flow map to both integrate and guide, enabling training-free alignment in just a few network evaluations. We demonstrate FMTG at text-to-image scale using a FLUX.1-distilled flow map, showing that it achieves comparable performance to baselines across inverse problems and image editing tasks with up to 10 times fewer function evaluations.</p>","absKo":"<p>generative modeling에서는 measurement consistency, aesthetic quality, human intent alignment와 같이 사용자가 지정한 reward를 만족하는 샘플을 생성하고자 하는 경우가 많으며, 이 문제는 inference-time guidance로 알려져 있다. flow-based model은 고품질 생성을 가능하게 하지만, 기존 guidance 방법은 reward-tilted distribution에서 샘플링하기 위해 비용이 큰 multi-particle, many-step scheme을 요구하거나 heuristic approximation에 의존한다. 효율적인 알고리즘을 설계하기 위해, 우리는 guidance를 reward tilt가 유도되는 stochastic control problem이 아니라 deterministic optimal control problem으로 재정식화한다. 우리는 optimal solution에서 flow map이 자연스럽게 등장함을 발견했으며, 기존의 많은 flow-based guidance method는 이를 single Euler step으로 대체하는 거친 approximation으로 이해하는 것이 가장 적절함을 보인다. 이러한 approximation에 의존하는 대신, 우리는 Flow Map Trajectory Guidance (FMTG)를 제안한다. 이는 flow map을 이용해 적분과 guidance를 모두 수행하는 principled framework로, 단 몇 번의 network evaluation만으로 training-free alignment를 가능하게 한다. 우리는 FLUX.1-distilled flow map을 사용하여 text-to-image scale에서 FMTG를 시연하며, 최대 10배 적은 function evaluation으로도 inverse problem과 image editing task 전반에서 baseline과 비슷한 성능을 달성함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64603","en":"Multi-marginal temporal Schrödinger Bridge Matching from unpaired data","ko":"짝지어지지 않은 데이터로부터의 Multi-marginal 시간적 Schrödinger Bridge Matching","authors":"Thomas Gravier, Thomas Boyer, Auguste Genovesio","pos":"#2410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LnDNFS8Lea","abs":"<p>Many natural dynamic processes –such as in vivo cellular differentiation or disease progression– can only be observed through the lens of static sample snapshots. While challenging, reconstructing their temporal evolution to decipher underlying dynamic properties is of major interest to scientific research. Existing approaches enable data transport along a temporal axis but are poorly scalable in high dimension and require restrictive assumptions to be met. To address these issues, we propose Multi-Marginal temporal Schrödinger Bridge Matching (MMtSBM) from unpaired data, extending the theoretical guarantees and empirical efficiency of Diffusion Schrödinger Bridge Matching (Shi et al., 2023) by deriving the Iterative Markovian Fitting algorithm to multiple marginals in a novel factorized fashion. Experiments show that MMtSBM retains theoretical properties on toy examples, achieves state-of-the-art performance on real-world datasets such as transcriptomic trajectory inference in 100 dimensions, and, for the first time, recovers couplings and dynamics in very high-dimensional image settings. Our work establishes multi-marginal Schrödinger bridges as a practical and principled approach for recovering hidden dynamics from static data.</p>","absKo":"<p>생체 내 세포 분화나 질병 진행과 같은 많은 자연적 동적 과정은 정적 샘플 스냅샷의 관점에서만 관찰할 수 있다. 이는 어렵지만, 기저의 동적 특성을 해독하기 위해 이들의 시간적 진화를 재구성하는 일은 과학 연구에서 매우 중요하다. 기존 접근법은 시간축을 따라 데이터를 이동시키는 것을 가능하게 하지만, 고차원에서는 확장성이 낮고 충족해야 할 제약 가정이 지나치게 엄격하다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 비짝지어진 데이터에서 Multi-Marginal temporal Schrödinger Bridge Matching (MMtSBM)을 제안한다. 이는 새로운 factorized 방식으로 multiple marginals에 대한 Iterative Markovian Fitting 알고리즘을 도출함으로써 Diffusion Schrödinger Bridge Matching (Shi et al., 2023)의 이론적 보장과 실증적 효율성을 확장한다. 실험 결과, MMtSBM은 toy example에서 이론적 성질을 유지하고, 100차원 transcriptomic trajectory inference와 같은 실제 데이터셋에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하며, 처음으로 매우 고차원 이미지 설정에서 coupling과 dynamics를 복원한다. 우리의 연구는 정적 데이터로부터 숨겨진 동역학을 복원하기 위한 실용적이고 원리적인 접근법으로서 multi-marginal Schrödinger bridge를 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"65827","en":"Analytic Bijections for Smooth and Interpretable Normalizing Flows","ko":"매끄럽고 해석 가능한 Normalizing Flow를 위한 해석적 전단사 함수","authors":"Mathis Gerdes, Miranda C. N. Cheng","pos":"#2500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9kkrASoSbp","abs":"A key challenge in normalizing flows is finding expressive invertible scalar bijections. Existing approaches face trade-offs: affine transformations are smooth and analytically invertible but lack expressivity; monotonic splines offer local control but are only piecewise smooth and act on bounded domains; residual flows achieve smoothness but need numerical inversion. We introduce three families of *analytic bijections* that are globally smooth ($C^\\infty$), defined on all of $\\mathbb{R}$, and analytically invertible in closed form, combining the favorable properties of prior approaches. Beyond serving as drop-in replacements in coupling flows, where they match or exceed spline performance, we develop *radial flows*: a novel architecture using direct parametrization that transforms the radial coordinate while preserving angular direction. Radial flows exhibit exceptional training stability, produce geometrically interpretable transformations, and on targets with radial structure can achieve comparable quality to coupling flows with $1000\\times$ fewer parameters. We provide comprehensive evaluation on 1D and 2D benchmarks, and demonstrate applicability to higher-dimensional physics problems through experiments on $\\phi^4$ lattice field theory, where our bijections outperform affine baselines and enable problem-specific designs that address mode collapse."},{"id":"66487","en":"Adversarial Flow Models","ko":"적대적 Flow 모델","authors":"Shanchuan Lin, Ceyuan Yang, Zhijie Lin, Hao Chen, Haoqi Fan","pos":"#2501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3GPPUHlJU9","abs":"<p>We present adversarial flow models, a class of generative models that belongs to both adversarial and flow families of models. Our method supports native one-step or multi-step generation and is trained using the adversarial objective. Unlike traditional GANs, where the generator learns an arbitrary transport plan between the noise and the data distributions, our generator learns a deterministic noise-to-data mapping, which is the same optimal transport as in flow-matching models. This significantly stabilizes adversarial training. Also, unlike consistency-based methods, our model directly learns one-step or few-step generation without having to learn the intermediate timesteps of the probability flow for propagation. This saves model capacity, reduces training iterations, and avoids error accumulation. Under the same 1NFE setting on ImageNet-256px, our B/2 model approaches the performance of consistency-based XL/2 models, while our XL/2 model creates a new best FID of 2.38. We additionally show the possibility of end-to-end training of 56-layer and 112-layer models through depth repetition without any intermediate supervision, and achieve FIDs of 2.08 and 1.94 using a single forward pass, surpassing their 28-layer 2NFE and 4NFE counterparts.</p>"},{"id":"61240","en":"A Unifying View of Variational Generative Wasserstein Flows","ko":"Variational Generative Wasserstein Flow의 통합적 관점","authors":"Paul Caucheteux, Clément Bonet, Anna Korba","pos":"#2502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sJ7ngz2eQx","abs":"<p>Many modern generative models can be viewed as minimizing divergences between probability distributions, yet they rely on different algorithmic and geometric principles. Wasserstein gradient flows provide a continuous-time formulation for optimizing over distributions, and can be approximated through their implicit discretization via the Jordan–Kinderlehrer–Otto (JKO) scheme.  In this work, we present a unified theoretical framework for generative modeling based on Wasserstein gradient flows, which we refer to as Generative Wasserstein Flows. We show that a broad class of existing methods can be derived as instances of parametric JKO schemes for f-divergences objectives, and we establish equivalences between several recently proposed algorithms. We extend this framework beyond f-divergences to integral probability metrics, deriving new JKO-based generative algorithms for objectives such as Maximum Mean Discrepancy. We also clarify their connections with GANs. Finally, we analyze parametric Wasserstein flows, where the evolution is restricted to distributions generated by parameterized maps. We characterize the resulting dynamics as projected or preconditioned Wasserstein gradient flows, highlighting the role of the Wasserstein geometry in shaping the learning dynamics of generative models.</p>","absKo":"<p>많은 현대 generative model은 probability distribution 사이의 divergence를 최소화하는 것으로 볼 수 있지만, 서로 다른 algorithmic 및 geometric principle에 의존합니다. Wasserstein gradient flow는 distribution 위에서의 최적화를 위한 continuous-time formulation을 제공하며, Jordan–Kinderlehrer–Otto(JKO) scheme을 통한 implicit discretization으로 근사할 수 있습니다. 이 연구에서 우리는 Wasserstein gradient flow에 기반한 generative modeling을 위한 통합 이론 프레임워크를 제시하며, 이를 Generative Wasserstein Flows라고 부릅니다. 우리는 기존 방법들의 폭넓은 클래스가 f-divergence objective에 대한 parametric JKO scheme의 인스턴스로 유도될 수 있음을 보이고, 최근 제안된 여러 알고리즘 사이의 등가성을 확립합니다. 또한 이 프레임워크를 f-divergence를 넘어 integral probability metric으로 확장하여, Maximum Mean Discrepancy와 같은 objective를 위한 새로운 JKO 기반 generative algorithm을 도출합니다. 아울러 이들 방법과 GANs의 연결도 명확히 합니다. 마지막으로, evolution이 parameterized map에 의해 생성되는 distribution으로 제한되는 parametric Wasserstein flow를 분석합니다. 우리는 그 결과 dynamics를 projected 또는 preconditioned Wasserstein gradient flow로 특징지으며, Wasserstein geometry가 generative model의 learning dynamics를 형성하는 역할을 강조합니다.</p>"},{"id":"62780","en":"Tilt Matching for Scalable Sampling and Fine-Tuning","ko":"확장형 샘플링 및 Fine-Tuning을 위한 Tilt Matching","authors":"Peter Potaptchik, Lee Kit, Michael Albergo","pos":"#308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dQA4Gjt4KU","abs":"<p>We propose a simple, scalable algorithm based on stochastic interpolants for sampling from unnormalized densities and for fine-tuning generative models. The approach, Tilt Matching, arises from a dynamical equation relating the flow matching velocity to one targeting the same distribution tilted by a reward, implicitly solving a stochastic optimal control problem. The resulting velocity inherits the regularity of stochastic interpolant transports while minimizing an objective with strictly lower variance than flow matching itself. The update to the velocity field can be interpreted as the sum of all joint cumulants between the interpolant velocity and the reward, and to first order is their covariance. The method requires neither reward gradients nor backpropagation through trajectories of the flow or diffusion. We empirically demonstrate that the approach is efficient and highly scalable, providing state-of-the-art results on sampling under Lennard-Jones systems and competitive performance for fine-tuning Stable Diffusion, without requiring reward multipliers. The framework also applies directly to tilting few-step flow map models.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 unnormalized density에서 sampling하고 generative model을 fine-tuning하기 위한 stochastic interpolant 기반의 단순하고 확장 가능한 algorithm을 제안한다. Tilt Matching이라는 이 접근은 flow matching velocity를 reward로 같은 분포를 tilt한 대상을 향하는 velocity와 연결하는 dynamical equation에서 유래하며, 이를 통해 stochastic optimal control problem을 암묵적으로 푼다. 그 결과로 얻어지는 velocity는 stochastic interpolant transport의 regularity를 계승하면서, flow matching 자체보다 strictly lower variance를 갖는 objective를 최소화한다. velocity field에 대한 업데이트는 interpolant velocity와 reward 사이의 모든 joint cumulant의 합으로 해석될 수 있으며, 1차 근사에서는 그 covariance에 해당한다. 이 방법은 reward gradient도 필요 없고, flow나 diffusion trajectory를 통한 backpropagation도 필요하지 않다. 우리는 이 접근이 효율적이고 매우 확장 가능함을 실험적으로 보이며, reward multiplier 없이 Lennard-Jones system에서의 sampling에 대해 state-of-the-art 결과를, Stable Diffusion fine-tuning에서는 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 이 framework는 few-step flow map model의 tilting에도 직접 적용된다.</p>"},{"id":"66213","en":"Test-Time Guidance for Flow-Based Generative Models via Parallel Tempering on Source Distributions","ko":"소스 분포에 대한 Parallel Tempering을 통한 Flow 기반 생성 모델의 테스트 시점 가이드","authors":"Shih-Hsin Wang, Joel Keller, Taos Transue, Drake Brown, Thomas Strohmer, Bao Wang","pos":"#3604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5jGcYMUZx1","abs":"<p>Generative models that transport a simple source distribution to a complex data distribution—such as diffusion and flow-based models—are central to high‑fidelity data generation. Test-time guidance can further steer pretrained models toward user-specified high-reward regions without costly retraining. However, existing guidance methods face critical limitations: they struggle with non-differentiable rewards, fail to navigate complex landscapes, and often lack theoretical guarantees on generation performance. We propose {\\it Source Parallel Tempering (SPT)}, a gradient‑free test‑time guidance framework that operates entirely in source space, leveraging its simpler geometry to avoid the complexities of the data manifold. SPT couples a local exploration kernel with parallel tempering, enabling efficient barrier crossing and robust discovery of high‑reward modes. Theoretically, we provide a new error bound linking training-time approximation error to test-time guidance performance. Empirically, SPT significantly improves over state-of-the-art methods on benchmark tasks in conditional image synthesis, protein structure generation, and dynamical system trajectory sampling.</p>"},{"id":"63343","en":"Exploring More to Solve More: Boosting Diversity in Text Diffusion Models via Entropy-Based Guidance","ko":"더 탐색하여 더 풀기: 엔트로피 기반 유도를 통한 텍스트 Diffusion 모델의 다양성 향상","authors":"Jingwei Zhang, Haoyu LEI, Zijin Feng, Jiacheng Sun, Farzan Farnia","pos":"#2009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XtODOFDNwa","abs":"<p>Although diffusion models have revolutionized continuous domains like image synthesis through high quality generations and controllable guidance mechanisms, bringing this controllability to the discrete, sequential nature of text remains an open challenge. Meanwhile, current sampling strategies and guidance methods adjust token likelihoods without capturing the broader semantic landscape, leading to a suboptimal balance between fidelity and diversity. In this work, we introduce a novel training-free Semantic-Aware Kernel Entropy (SAKE) guidance method. Our method computes the order-2 Rényi entropy over a kernel Gram matrix that captures both cross-token semantic interactions and relative token positions. By linearizing this objective in the embedding space, we derive a tractable guidance signal that dynamically adjusts the sampling distribution—flattening it to encourage exploration during redundancy and sharpening it for fidelity when diverse. Empirical experiments demonstrate that our approach achieves a superior Pareto frontier between fidelity and diversity, and improves multi-sample performance on reasoning-intensive tasks, such as code and mathematics generation, compared to temperature scaling and discrete guidance baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>diffusion model이 고품질 생성과 controllable guidance mechanism을 통해 image synthesis 같은 continuous domain을 혁신했지만, 이러한 controllability를 discrete하고 sequential한 text에 가져오는 일은 여전히 열린 문제다. 한편 현재의 sampling 전략과 guidance 방법은 더 넓은 semantic landscape를 포착하지 못한 채 token likelihood만 조정하므로, fidelity와 diversity 사이의 균형이 최적이 되지 못한다. 본 연구에서는 새로운 training-free Semantic-Aware Kernel Entropy(SAKE) guidance method를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 token 간 semantic interaction과 상대적 token position을 모두 포착하는 kernel Gram matrix 위에서 order-2 Rényi entropy를 계산한다. 이 목적함수를 embedding space에서 linearize함으로써, sampling distribution을 동적으로 조정하는 tractable한 guidance signal을 도출한다. 이는 redundancy가 있을 때는 분포를 평탄하게 하여 exploration을 장려하고, 다양성이 필요할 때는 fidelity를 위해 분포를 날카롭게 만든다. 실험 결과 우리의 접근법은 fidelity와 diversity 사이에서 더 우수한 Pareto frontier를 달성하며, temperature scaling과 discrete guidance baseline에 비해 code 및 mathematics generation 같은 reasoning-intensive task에서 multi-sample performance를 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"63909","en":"CG-MLLM: Captioning and Generating 3D content via Multi-modal Large Language Models","ko":"CG-MLLM: multimodal large language model을 통한 3D 콘텐츠 캡션 및 생성","authors":"Junming Huang, Chi Wang, Letian Li, Guangkai Xu, Donglin Huang, Hao Chen, Qiang Dai, Weiwei Xu","pos":"#2112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Sd1014TyrA","abs":"<p>Large Language Models(LLMs) have revolutionized text generation and multimodal perception, but their capabilities in 3D content generation remain underexplored. Existing methods compromise by producing either low-resolution meshes or coarse structural proxies, failing to capture fine-grained geometry natively. In this paper, we propose CG-MLLM, a novel Multi-modal Large Language Model (MLLM) capable of 3D captioning and high-resolution 3D generation in a single framework.   Leveraging the Mixture-of-Transformer architecture, CG-MLLM decouples disparate modeling needs, where the Token-level Autoregressive (TokenAR) Transformer handles token-level content, and the Block-level Autoregressive (BlockAR) Transformer handles block-level content. By integrating a pre-trained vision-language backbone with a specialized 3D VAE latent space, CG-MLLM facilitates long-context interactions between standard tokens and spatial blocks within a single integrated architecture.    Experimental results show that CG-MLLM significantly outperforms existing MLLMs in generating high-fidelity 3D objects, effectively bringing high-resolution 3D content creation into the mainstream LLM paradigm.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models(LLMs)는 text generation과 multimodal perception을 혁신했지만, 3D content generation에서의 역량은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았습니다. 기존 방법들은 저해상도 mesh 또는 거친 구조적 proxy를 생성하는 데 그쳐, 정교한 기하 정보를 본질적으로 포착하지 못합니다. 본 논문에서는 CG-MLLM을 제안합니다. CG-MLLM은 3D captioning과 고해상도 3D 생성을 하나의 framework에서 모두 수행할 수 있는 새로운 Multi-modal Large Language Model(MLLM)입니다. Mixture-of-Transformer architecture를 활용하여, CG-MLLM은 서로 다른 modeling 요구를 분리합니다. Token-level Autoregressive(TokenAR) Transformer는 token-level content를 처리하고, Block-level Autoregressive(BlockAR) Transformer는 block-level content를 처리합니다. 사전 학습된 vision-language backbone과 특화된 3D VAE latent space를 통합함으로써, CG-MLLM은 표준 token과 spatial block 사이의 long-context interaction을 하나의 통합된 architecture 안에서 가능하게 합니다. 실험 결과, CG-MLLM은 고충실도 3D object 생성에서 기존 MLLM을 크게 능가하며, 고해상도 3D content creation을 주류 LLM paradigm으로 효과적으로 끌어옵니다.</p>"},{"id":"64100","en":"VAnim: Rendering-Aware Sparse State Modeling for Structure-Preserving Vector Animation","ko":"VAnim: 구조 보존 벡터 애니메이션을 위한 렌더링 인식 희소 상태 모델링","authors":"Guotao Liang, Zhangcheng Wang, Chuang Wang, Juncheng Hu, Haitao Zhou, Junhua Liu, Jing Zhang, Dong Xu, Qian Yu","pos":"#2200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Qs63Njpn1R","abs":"<p>Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) animation generation is pivotal for professional design due to their structural editability and resolution independence. However, this task remains challenging as it requires bridging discrete code representations with continuous visual dynamics. Existing optimization-based methods often destroy topological consistency, while general-purpose LLMs rely on rigid CSS/SMIL transformations, failing to model geometry-level non-rigid deformations. To address these limitations, we present VAnim, the first LLM-based framework for open-domain text-to-SVG animation. We reconceptualize animation not as sequence generation, but as Sparse State Updates (SSU) on a persistent SVG DOM tree. This paradigm compresses sequence length by over 9.8x while mathematically guaranteeing topological isomorphism and identity persistence. To enable precise control, we propose an Identification-First Motion Planning mechanism that grounds textual instructions in explicit visual entities. Furthermore, to overcome the non-differentiable nature of SVG rendering, we employ Rendering-Aware Reinforcement Learning via Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO). By leveraging a hybrid reward from a state-of-the-art video perception encoder, we align discrete code updates with high-fidelity visual feedback. We also introduce SVGAnim-134k, the first benchmark for vector animation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that VAnim significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines in semantic alignment and structural validity, demonstrating a robust capacity for synthesizing high-fidelity non-rigid deformations without requiring explicit temporal consistency constraints.</p>","absKo":"<p>Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) animation generation은 구조적 편집 가능성과 해상도 독립성 때문에 전문 디자인에서 핵심적이다. 그러나 이 과제는 discrete code representation과 연속적인 visual dynamics를 연결해야 하므로 여전히 어렵다. 기존의 optimization-based 방법은 종종 topology consistency를 훼손하는 반면, 범용 LLM은 경직된 CSS/SMIL transformation에 의존하여 geometry-level non-rigid deformation을 모델링하지 못한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 open-domain text-to-SVG animation을 위한 최초의 LLM 기반 프레임워크인 VAnim을 제시한다. 우리는 animation을 sequence generation이 아니라 persistent SVG DOM tree 위의 Sparse State Updates (SSU)로 재개념화한다. 이 패러다임은 sequence length를 9.8배 이상 압축하는 동시에, topological isomorphism과 identity persistence를 수학적으로 보장한다. 정밀한 제어를 가능하게 하기 위해, 우리는 텍스트 지시를 명시적 visual entity에 정합하는 Identification-First Motion Planning 메커니즘을 제안한다. 또한 SVG rendering의 미분 불가능성을 극복하기 위해, Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO)을 통한 Rendering-Aware Reinforcement Learning을 사용한다. 최첨단 video perception encoder로부터 얻은 hybrid reward를 활용하여, 우리는 discrete code update를 고충실도 visual feedback과 정렬한다. 우리는 또한 vector animation을 위한 최초의 benchmark인 SVGAnim-134k를 소개한다. 광범위한 실험은 VAnim이 semantic alignment와 structural validity에서 최신 baselines를 크게 능가하며, 명시적 temporal consistency constraint 없이도 고충실도 non-rigid deformation을 합성하는 강력한 능력을 보임을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66161","en":"Variable-Length Tokenization via Learnable Global Merging for Diffusion Transformers","ko":"Diffusion Transformer를 위한 학습 가능한 전역 병합을 통한 가변 길이 토큰화","authors":"Dong Hoon Lee, Seunghoon Hong","pos":"#2201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6ER1mP51np","abs":"Latent Diffusion Models (LDMs) have become dominant in visual synthesis, but their quality–compute trade-off is largely constrained by the tokenizer’s fixed compression ratio. Variable-length tokenizers (VLTs) promise adaptive compression by varying token counts, allowing diffusion models to flexibly balance quality and compute. However, conventional VLTs modulate length by truncating ordered token sequences, which changes token semantics across lengths and breaks representational alignment. This leads to significant cross-length variation in the latent distribution that hinders a single variable-length diffusion model from operating effectively.  To address this, we propose a novel variable-length tokenizer that modulates length by merging tokens. We show that encouraging similar tokens to merge enables direct cross-length representation alignment when the diffusion transformer operates according to the merging pattern. Since conventional merging methods are data-dependent, making the merging pattern inaccessible during generation, we introduce learnable global merging, which is data-independent, to ensure compatibility with diffusion transformers. On ImageNet 256$\\times$256 generation, our merging-based variable-length tokenizer integrated with a diffusion transformer achieves a superior gFID–compute trade-off compared to prior VLT methods."},{"id":"62444","en":"Sparse Autoencoders are Topic Models","ko":"희소 Autoencoder는 Topic Model이다","authors":"Leander Girrbach, Zeynep Akata","pos":"#2302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gXXrubolmR","abs":"<p>Sparse autoencoders (SAEs) are used to analyze embeddings, but their role and practical value are debated. We propose a new perspective on SAEs by demonstrating that they can be naturally understood as topic models. We extend Latent Dirichlet Allocation to embedding spaces and derive the SAE objective as a maximum a posteriori estimator under this model. This view implies SAE features are thematic components rather than steerable directions. Based on this, we introduce SAE-TM, a topic modeling framework that: (1) trains an SAE to learn reusable topic atoms, (2) interprets them as word distributions on downstream data, and (3) merges them into any number of topics without retraining. SAE-TM yields more coherent topics than strong baselines on text and image datasets while maintaining diversity. Finally, we analyze thematic structure in image datasets and trace topic changes over time in Japanese woodblock prints. Our work positions SAEs as effective tools for large-scale thematic analysis across modalities. Code and data will be released upon publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>Sparse autoencoders (SAEs)는 embedding을 분석하는 데 사용되지만, 그 역할과 실용적 가치는 논쟁의 대상이다. 우리는 SAEs가 자연스럽게 topic model로 이해될 수 있음을 보여주며 SAEs에 대한 새로운 관점을 제안한다. 우리는 Latent Dirichlet Allocation을 embedding space로 확장하고, 이 모델 아래에서 SAE objective가 maximum a posteriori estimator로 유도됨을 보인다. 이 관점은 SAE feature가 steerable direction이 아니라 thematic component임을 시사한다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 SAE-TM을 제안한다. 이는 (1) 재사용 가능한 topic atom을 학습하기 위해 SAE를 학습하고, (2) downstream data에서 이를 word distribution으로 해석하며, (3) 재학습 없이 원하는 수의 topic으로 병합하는 topic modeling framework이다. SAE-TM은 text 및 image dataset에서 강력한 baseline보다 더 coherent한 topic을 생성하면서도 diversity를 유지한다. 마지막으로, 우리는 image dataset의 thematic structure를 분석하고 일본 목판화에서 시간에 따른 topic 변화를 추적한다. 우리의 연구는 SAEs를 modality 전반에 걸친 대규모 thematic analysis를 위한 효과적인 도구로 자리매김한다. 코드와 데이터는 출판 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64790","en":"ReTabSyn: Realistic Tabular Data Synthesis via Reinforcement Learning","ko":"ReTabSyn: Reinforcement Learning을 통한 현실적 Tabular 데이터 합성","authors":"Xiaofeng Lin, Seungbae Kim, Zhuoya Li, Zachary DeSoto, Charles Fleming, Guang Cheng","pos":"#2308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JmfyJj8aBf","abs":"Deep generative models can help with data scarcity and privacy by producing synthetic training data, but they struggle in low-data, imbalanced tabular settings to fully learn the complex data distribution.  We argue that striving for the full joint distribution could be overkill; for greater data efficiency, models should prioritize learning the conditional distribution $P(y\\mid \\bm{X})$, as suggested by recent theoretical analysis. Therefore, we overcome this limitation with \\textbf{ReTabSyn}, a \\textbf{Re}inforced \\textbf{Tab}ular \\textbf{Syn}thesis pipeline that provides direct feedback on feature correlation preservation during synthesizer training.  This objective encourages the generator to prioritize the most useful predictive signals when training data is limited, thereby strengthening downstream model utility.  We empirically fine-tune a language model-based generator using this approach, and across benchmarks with small sample sizes, class imbalance, and distribution shift, ReTabSyn consistently outperforms state-of-the-art baselines.  Moreover, our approach can be readily extended to control various aspects of synthetic tabular data, such as applying expert-specified constraints on generated observations.","absKo":"딥 생성 모델은 synthetic training data를 생성함으로써 데이터 부족과 프라이버시 문제를 완화할 수 있지만, low-data의 imbalanced tabular setting에서는 복잡한 데이터 분포를 충분히 학습하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 전체 joint distribution을 완전히 학습하려는 시도는 과도할 수 있으며, 더 큰 data efficiency를 위해서는 최근 이론 분석이 시사하듯 모델이 conditional distribution $P(y\\mid \\bm{X})$ 학습을 우선해야 한다고 주장한다. 따라서 우리는 synthesizer training 동안 feature correlation 보존에 대한 직접적인 피드백을 제공하는 \\textbf{ReTabSyn}, 즉 \\textbf{Re}inforced \\textbf{Tab}ular \\textbf{Syn}thesis pipeline으로 이 한계를 극복한다. 이 목표는 제한된 training data 환경에서 generator가 가장 유용한 predictive signal을 우선하도록 유도하여 downstream model utility를 강화한다. 우리는 이 접근을 사용해 language model 기반 generator를 실증적으로 fine-tune했고, 소표본, class imbalance, distribution shift를 포함한 여러 benchmark에서 ReTabSyn이 state-of-the-art baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보였다. 더 나아가 우리의 접근은 생성된 관측치에 대해 전문가가 지정한 constraint를 적용하는 것처럼 synthetic tabular data의 다양한 측면을 제어하도록 손쉽게 확장될 수 있다."},{"id":"65043","en":"Quantum latent distributions in deep generative models","ko":"심층 Generative Model에서의 양자 잠재 분포","authors":"Omar Bacarreza, Thorin Farnsworth, Alexander Makarovskiy, Hugo Wallner, Tessa Hicks, Santiago Sempere-Llagostera, John Price, Robert Francis-Jones, William Clements","pos":"#2310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HNiFn4aRD5","abs":"<p>Many successful families of generative models leverage a low-dimensional latent distribution that is mapped to a data distribution. Though simple latent distributions are often used, the choice of distribution has a strong impact on model performance. Recent experiments have suggested that the probability distributions produced by quantum processors, which are typically highly correlated and classically intractable, can lead to improved performance on some datasets. However, when and why latent distributions produced by quantum processors can improve performance, and whether these improvements are connected to quantum properties of these distributions, are open questions that we investigate in this work. We show in theory that, under certain conditions, these \"quantum latent distributions\" enable generative models to produce data distributions that classical latent distributions cannot efficiently produce. We provide intuition as to the underlying mechanisms that could explain a performance advantage on real datasets. Based on this, we perform extensive benchmarking on a synthetic quantum dataset and the QM9 molecular dataset, using both simulated and real photonic quantum processors. We find that the statistics arising from quantum interference lead to improved generative performance compared to classical baselines, suggesting that quantum processors can play a role in expanding the capabilities of deep generative models.</p>","absKo":"<p>많은 성공적인 generative model family는 데이터 분포로 매핑되는 저차원 latent distribution을 활용한다. 단순한 latent distribution이 자주 사용되지만, 어떤 분포를 선택하느냐는 모델 성능에 큰 영향을 미친다. 최근 실험에서는 일반적으로 강한 상관성을 갖고 고전적으로 처리하기 어려운 quantum processor가 생성한 probability distribution이 일부 dataset에서 성능 향상으로 이어질 수 있음을 시사했다. 그러나 quantum processor가 생성한 latent distribution이 언제, 왜 성능을 향상시키는지, 그리고 이러한 향상이 이들 분포의 quantum property와 연결되는지는 여전히 열린 질문이며, 본 연구에서는 이를 조사한다. 우리는 특정 조건하에서 이러한 \"quantum latent distribution\"이 classical latent distribution으로는 효율적으로 생성할 수 없는 data distribution을 generative model이 생성하도록 해준다는 이론적 결과를 보인다. 또한 실제 데이터셋에서 나타날 수 있는 성능 우위의 근본 메커니즘에 대한 직관을 제시한다. 이를 바탕으로, simulated 및 real photonic quantum processor를 모두 사용하여 synthetic quantum dataset과 QM9 molecular dataset에서 광범위한 benchmark를 수행한다. 우리는 quantum interference에서 비롯된 statistics가 classical baseline에 비해 더 나은 generative performance로 이어짐을 확인했으며, 이는 quantum processor가 deep generative model의 능력을 확장하는 데 역할을 할 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"60497","en":"Q-Tab: Quantized Tabular Data Generator","ko":"Q-Tab: 양자화된 테이블 데이터 생성기","authors":"Julian Wustl, Philipp Haid, Yarema Okhrin, Claudius Schnörr","pos":"#2311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ziw0N3L4KD","abs":"<p>Codebook-based generators built on masked language model (MLM) transformers have become highly effective in text and vision, yet remain underused for tabular data. This is because codebooks typically act as information bottlenecks, whereas tabular generation requires them to generalize. We address this gap with Q-Tab, a codebook-based tabular generator based on lookup-free quantization (LFQ) with residual corruption. The resulting corruption kernel induces a moving Nadaraya–Watson–style kernel regression over a large discrete code space, which turns codebook learning into a moving-target problem. We derive necessary conditions for the learnability of such moving codebooks and show how the residual LFQ construction aligns with these conditions. Q-Tab achieves state-of-the-art downstream predictive utility and missing-value imputation, while matching the distributional fidelity of diffusion-based generators, notably without any post-hoc temperature tuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>masked language model (MLM) transformers 위에 구축된 codebook 기반 생성기는 text와 vision에서 매우 효과적이지만, tabular data에서는 여전히 충분히 활용되지 못하고 있다. 이는 codebook이 보통 information bottleneck으로 작동하는 반면, tabular generation에서는 오히려 일반화가 요구되기 때문이다. 우리는 residual corruption을 결합한 lookup-free quantization (LFQ) 기반 codebook-based tabular generator인 Q-Tab으로 이 간극을 해소한다. 그 결과 생성되는 corruption kernel은 큰 discrete code space 위에서 moving Nadaraya–Watson 스타일의 kernel regression을 유도하며, codebook learning을 moving-target 문제로 바꾼다. 우리는 이러한 moving codebook의 학습 가능성에 대한 필요한 조건을 유도하고, residual LFQ 구성이 이 조건들과 어떻게 정렬되는지 보인다. Q-Tab은 downstream predictive utility와 missing-value imputation에서 state-of-the-art를 달성하며, diffusion-based generator의 distributional fidelity와도 맞먹는 성능을 보이면서, 특히 post-hoc temperature tuning 없이 이를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60979","en":"Concept-Guided Tokenization: Closing the Gap Between Reconstruction and Generation","ko":"Concept-Guided Tokenization: Reconstruction과 Generation 사이의 격차 줄이기","authors":"Yunqiao Yang, Haokun Lin, Guanzhong Wu, Ying Wei","pos":"#2401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=utRSxIkoSJ","abs":"<p>Recent advances in image generation have been largely driven by image tokenization, which compresses raw pixels into compact latent representations. While existing tokenizers excel at preserving low-level visual details through reconstruction-based training, they often lack explicit semantic guidance, which limits their ability to capture semantically structured representations and thus hinders their performance on downstream tasks like image generation. To overcome this limitation, we propose a novel tokenization framework that incorporates high-level semantics through two key innovations: (1) a text-integrated encoder that jointly processes images and textual descriptions to produce semantically enriched latent representations, and (2) a concept-guided training objective that leverages sparse autoencoders to decompose pre-trained vision-language model features to a semantic concept space, employing sparse and disentangled concept indices for guidance. Our approach achieves strong alignment with semantic concepts, maintaining high reconstruction fidelity with an rFID of 1.39 on ImageNet, while achieving a gFID of 2.65 on the class-conditional image generation task and 10.73 on the text-to-image generation task. By infusing high-level semantic structures into low-level visual fidelity, our method bridges the reconstruction-generation divide and drives generative modeling as a powerful foundation.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 image generation의 발전은 주로 image tokenization에 의해 이끌려 왔으며, 이는 raw pixel을 compact한 latent representation으로 압축한다. 기존 tokenizer는 reconstruction-based training을 통해 저수준 visual detail을 보존하는 데는 뛰어나지만, 명시적인 semantic guidance가 부족한 경우가 많아 의미적으로 구조화된 representation을 포착하는 능력이 제한되고, 그 결과 image generation과 같은 downstream task에서 성능이 저하된다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해 우리는 두 가지 핵심 혁신을 통해 high-level semantics를 통합하는 새로운 tokenization framework를 제안한다: (1) image와 textual description을 공동으로 처리하여 semantic이 풍부한 latent representation을 생성하는 text-integrated encoder, 그리고 (2) sparse autoencoder를 활용해 pre-trained vision-language model feature를 semantic concept space로 분해하고, guidance를 위해 sparse하며 disentangled된 concept index를 사용하는 concept-guided training objective이다. 우리의 접근법은 semantic concept과의 강한 alignment를 달성하면서도 ImageNet에서 rFID 1.39의 높은 reconstruction fidelity를 유지하고, class-conditional image generation task에서 gFID 2.65, text-to-image generation task에서 10.73을 달성한다. 저수준 visual fidelity에 high-level semantic structure를 주입함으로써, 우리의 방법은 reconstruction-generation 간의 간극을 메우고 generative modeling을 강력한 foundation으로 이끈다.</p>"},{"id":"62789","en":"DetailMaster: Can Your Text-to-Image Model Handle Long Prompts?","ko":"DetailMaster: Text-to-Image 모델이 긴 프롬프트를 처리할 수 있을까?","authors":"Qirui Jiao, Daoyuan Chen, Yilun Huang, Xika Lin, Ying Shen, Yaliang Li","pos":"#2405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dHH6UrXIQ5","abs":"<p>While recent Text-to-Image (T2I) models show impressive capabilities in synthesizing images from brief descriptions, they struggle with the long, detailed prompts required for professional applications. We present DetailMaster, a comprehensive benchmark for evaluating T2I capabilities on long prompts with complex compositional requirements, accompanied by an automated data construction pipeline and an evaluation workflow. Comprising expert-validated prompts averaging 284.89 tokens, our benchmark introduces four critical evaluation dimensions: Character Attributes, Structured Character Locations, Multi-Dimensional Scene Attributes, and Spatial/Interactive Relationships. Evaluations on various general-purpose and long-prompt-optimized models reveal critical performance limitations, showing that weak encoders struggle to preserve syntactic dependencies within prompts and diffusion models suffer from attribute leakage under detail-intensive conditions. Through a controlled ablation study under varying constraints, we further show that high-fidelity generation requires a synergistic combination of expanded prompt limits and long-prompt training. We open-source our dataset and code to foster progress in long-prompt-driven T2I generation.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 Text-to-Image(T2I) 모델은 짧은 설명으로부터 이미지를 합성하는 데 인상적인 성능을 보이지만, 전문적 응용에서 요구되는 길고 상세한 prompt를 다루는 데에는 여전히 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 복잡한 구성 요건을 갖는 긴 prompt에 대한 T2I 성능을 평가하기 위한 포괄적 benchmark인 DetailMaster를 제시하며, 자동 data construction pipeline과 evaluation workflow를 함께 제공한다. 전문가 검증을 거친 평균 284.89 token 길이의 prompt로 구성된 이 benchmark는 네 가지 핵심 평가 차원을 도입한다: Character Attributes, Structured Character Locations, Multi-Dimensional Scene Attributes, 그리고 Spatial/Interactive Relationships. 다양한 범용 모델과 long-prompt 최적화 모델에 대한 평가는 중요한 성능 한계를 드러내며, 약한 encoder는 prompt 내부의 syntactic dependency를 유지하는 데 어려움을 겪고 diffusion model은 세부 정보가 많은 조건에서 attribute leakage를 겪는다는 점을 보여준다. 다양한 제약 조건하에서 수행한 통제된 ablation study를 통해, 고충실도 생성에는 확장된 prompt 길이와 long-prompt training의 시너지 결합이 필요함을 추가로 보인다. 우리는 long-prompt 기반 T2I 생성의 발전을 촉진하기 위해 데이터셋과 코드를 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"66707","en":"Feature-aware (Hyper)graph Generation via Next-Scale Prediction","ko":"Next-Scale Prediction을 통한 특성 인지 (하이퍼)그래프 생성","authors":"Dorian Gailhard, Enzo Tartaglione, Lirida Naviner, Jhony H. Giraldo","pos":"#2406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=19ksKPfJcT","abs":"<p>Graph generative models perform well on small structured data but struggle to scale to large, complex structures. Hierarchical approaches improve scalability but often ignore node and edge features, which are critical in real-world applications, particularly for hypergraphs that model higher-order relationships. In this paper, we propose FAHNES (feature-aware (hyper)graph generation via next-scale prediction), a hierarchical framework that jointly generates topology and features for graphs and hypergraphs. FAHNES builds multi-scale representations through node coarsening and localized expansion, guided by a novel hierarchical scale encoding that controls granularity and ensures cross-scale consistency. Experiments on synthetic, 3D mesh, and graph point cloud datasets demonstrate state-of-the-art performance in joint structure and feature generation.</p>"},{"id":"65222","en":"Forget-It-All: Multi-Concept Machine Unlearning via Concept-Aware Neuron Masking","ko":"Forget-It-All: 개념 인지 뉴런 마스킹을 통한 다중 개념 Machine Unlearning","authors":"Kaiyuan Deng, Bo Hui, Gen Li, Jie Ji, Minghai Qin, Geng Yuan, Xiaolong Ma","pos":"#2407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FfrpNZofIk","abs":"<p>The widespread adoption of text-to-image (T2I) diffusion models has raised concerns about their potential to generate copyrighted, inappropriate, or sensitive imagery learned from massive training corpora. As a practical solution, machine unlearning aims to selectively erase unwanted concepts from a pre-trained model without retraining from scratch. While most existing methods are effective for single-concept unlearning, they often struggle in real-world scenarios that require removing multiple concepts, since extending them to this setting is both non-trivial and problematic, causing significant challenges in unlearning effectiveness, generation quality, and sensitivity to hyperparameters and datasets. In this paper, we take a unique perspective on multi-concept unlearning by leveraging model sparsity and propose the Forget It All (FIA) framework. FIA first introduces Contrastive Concept Saliency to quantify each weight connection’s contribution to a target concept. It then identifies Concept-Sensitive Neurons by combining temporal and spatial information, ensuring that only neurons consistently responsive to the target concept are selected. Finally, FIA constructs masks from the identified neurons and fuses them into a unified multi-concept mask, where Concept-Agnostic Neurons that broadly support general content generation are preserved while concept-specific neurons are pruned to remove the targets. FIA is training-free and requires only minimal hyperparameter tuning for new tasks, thereby promoting a plug-and-play paradigm. Extensive experiments across three distinct unlearning tasks demonstrate that FIA achieves more reliable multi-concept unlearning, improving forgetting effectiveness while maintaining semantic fidelity and image quality.</p>","absKo":"<p>text-to-image (T2I) diffusion model의 광범위한 채택은, 대규모 training corpus에서 학습된 저작권 침해 가능 이미지, 부적절한 이미지, 또는 민감한 이미지를 생성할 수 있다는 우려를 낳고 있다. 실용적인 해결책으로, machine unlearning은 처음부터 다시 학습하지 않고 pre-trained model에서 원치 않는 concept을 선택적으로 지우는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존 방법의 대부분은 single-concept unlearning에는 효과적이지만, 여러 concept을 제거해야 하는 실제 시나리오에서는 이를 일반화하기가 비자명하고 문제도 많아, unlearning effectiveness, generation quality, hyperparameter 및 dataset 민감도 측면에서 상당한 도전이 발생한다. 이 논문에서는 model sparsity를 활용해 multi-concept unlearning을 바라보는 독특한 관점을 제시하고, Forget It All (FIA) framework를 제안한다. FIA는 먼저 Contrastive Concept Saliency를 도입하여 각 weight connection이 target concept에 기여하는 정도를 정량화한다. سپس temporal 정보와 spatial 정보를 결합해 Concept-Sensitive Neuron을 식별함으로써, target concept에 일관되게 반응하는 neuron만 선택되도록 한다. 마지막으로 FIA는 식별된 neuron들로부터 mask를 구성하고 이를 통합된 multi-concept mask로 결합하는데, 여기서 일반적인 content generation을 폭넓게 지원하는 Concept-Agnostic Neuron은 보존되고, target을 제거하기 위해 concept-specific neuron은 pruning된다. FIA는 training-free이며 새로운 task에 대해 최소한의 hyperparameter tuning만 필요하므로 plug-and-play paradigm을 촉진한다. 세 가지 서로 다른 unlearning task에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 FIA가 더 신뢰할 수 있는 multi-concept unlearning을 달성하며, semantic fidelity와 image quality를 유지하면서 forgetting effectiveness를 향상시킨다는 점을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61067","en":"LineageFlow: Flow Matching for High-Fidelity Family-Aware Protein Sequence Generation","ko":"LineageFlow: 고충실도 Family-Aware 단백질 서열 생성을 위한 Flow Matching","authors":"Langzhang Liang, Ming Yang, Yi Feng, Junfan Li, Shirui Pan, Xu Yinghui, Tianlei Ying, YIZHEN ZHENG, Zenglin Xu","pos":"#2409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=u0LjAArXHi","abs":"<p>Protein sequence generation for engineering requires samples that are biophysically plausible and, when targeting a family/domain, remain recognizable members while exploring within-family diversity. Current discrete generative models typically start from uniform or masked-token noise, which discards strong position-specific constraints induced by evolution and forces the model to reconstruct conserved residues from scratch, leading to weak family control and low foldability. We propose \\emph{LineageFlow}, a simplex-valued flow-matching model that initializes generation from lineage priors derived from ancestral sequence reconstruction, turning generation into structured mutation from an evolved scaffold. Across diverse protein families, LineageFlow achieves family validity close to held-out natural sequences and improves predicted structural confidence over uniform-/mask-initialized baselines while maintaining substantial within-family novelty and diversity, even surpassing a large pretrained baseline trained on substantially more data. Finally, we introduce \\emph{rerouting}, a single intermediate-time mutate--select--amplify intervention that enables objective-guided sampling without per-step predictor guidance and yields further gains in plausibility, including a zero-shot enzyme generation case study.</p>","absKo":"<p>공학을 위한 protein sequence generation은 생물물리적으로 타당한 샘플이 필요하며, family/domain을 대상으로 할 때는 family member로 인식 가능하면서도 family 내부 다양성을 탐색해야 한다. 현재의 discrete generative model은 대개 uniform 또는 masked-token noise에서 시작하는데, 이는 evolution이 부여한 강한 position-specific constraint를 버리고 conserved residue를 처음부터 다시 복원하도록 강제하므로, family control이 약하고 foldability도 낮아진다. 우리는 \\\\emph{LineageFlow}를 제안한다. 이는 ancestral sequence reconstruction에서 도출한 lineage prior로 generation을 초기화하는 simplex-valued flow-matching model로, generation을 진화된 scaffold 위에서의 구조화된 mutation으로 전환한다. 다양한 protein family 전반에서 LineageFlow는 hold-out된 자연 서열에 가까운 family validity를 달성하고, uniform-/mask-initialized baseline보다 예측 구조 신뢰도를 향상시키면서도 family 내부 novelty와 diversity를 충분히 유지하며, 훨씬 더 많은 데이터로 학습된 대규모 pretrained baseline까지 능가한다. 마지막으로, 우리는 \\\\emph{rerouting}을 도입한다. 이는 단일 중간 시점의 mutate--select--amplify 개입으로, 단계별 predictor guidance 없이 objective-guided sampling을 가능하게 하고, zero-shot enzyme generation 사례를 포함해 plausibility를 추가로 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"62529","en":"Overclocking Electrostatic Generative Models","ko":"정전기 생성 모델의 오버클로킹","authors":"Daniil Shlenskii, Aleksandr Korotin","pos":"#2411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=flo449mncA","abs":"Electrostatic generative models such as PFGM++ have recently emerged as a powerful framework, achieving state-of-the-art performance in image synthesis. PFGM++ operates in an extended data space with auxiliary dimensionality $D$, recovering the diffusion model framework as $D\\to\\infty$, while yielding superior empirical results for finite $D$. Like diffusion models, PFGM++ relies on expensive ODE simulations to generate samples, making it computationally costly. To address this, we propose Inverse Poisson Flow Matching (IPFM), a novel distillation framework that accelerates electrostatic generative models across all values of $D$. Our IPFM reformulates distillation as an inverse problem: learning a generator whose induced electrostatic field matches that of the teacher. We derive a tractable training objective for this problem and show that, as $D \\to \\infty$, our IPFM closely recovers Score Identity Distillation (SiD), a recent method for distilling diffusion models. Empirically, our IPFM produces distilled generators that achieve near-teacher or even superior sample quality using only a few function evaluations. Moreover, we observe that distillation converges faster for finite $D$ than in the $D \\to \\infty$ (diffusion) limit, which is consistent with prior findings that finite-$D$ PFGM++ models exhibit more favorable optimization and sampling properties.","absKo":"PFGM++와 같은 electrostatic generative model은 최근 image synthesis에서 state-of-the-art performance를 달성하며 강력한 framework로 떠올랐다. PFGM++는 보조 차원 $D$를 갖는 확장된 data space에서 동작하며, $D\\to\\infty$일 때 diffusion model framework를 복원하는 한편 유한한 $D$에서는 더 우수한 empirical result를 낸다. diffusion model과 마찬가지로 PFGM++는 sample 생성에 비용이 큰 ODE simulation에 의존하므로 계산 비용이 높다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 모든 $D$ 값에서 electrostatic generative model을 가속하는 새로운 distillation framework인 Inverse Poisson Flow Matching(IPFM)을 제안한다. 우리의 IPFM은 distillation을 inverse problem으로 재정식화한다. 즉, teacher가 유도하는 electrostatic field와 일치하는 generator를 학습하는 것이다. 우리는 이 문제에 대한 tractable training objective를 유도하고, $D \\to \\infty$일 때 우리의 IPFM이 diffusion model distillation을 위한 최근 방법인 Score Identity Distillation(SiD)을 거의 그대로 복원함을 보인다. 실험적으로, 우리의 IPFM은 소수의 function evaluation만으로도 teacher와 비슷하거나 더 나은 sample quality를 달성하는 distilled generator를 생성한다. 또한 유한한 $D$에서 distillation이 $D \\to \\infty$(diffusion) limit보다 더 빠르게 수렴함을 관찰했는데, 이는 유한한 $D$의 PFGM++ model이 더 유리한 optimization 및 sampling property를 보인다는 기존 결과와 일치한다.</p>"},{"id":"65093","en":"(1D) Ordered Tokens Enable Efficient Test-Time Search","ko":"(1D) 순서화된 토큰이 효율적인 Test-Time 탐색을 가능하게 한다","authors":"Zhitong Gao, Parham Rezaei, Ali Cy, Mingqiao Ye, Nataša Jovanović, Jesse Allardice, Afshin Dehghan, Roman Bachmann, Oğuzhan Fatih Kar, Amir Zamir","pos":"#2504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Gr3wxsTqLw","abs":"<p>Tokenization is a key component of autoregressive generative models, converting raw data into more manageable units for modeling. Commonly, tokens describe local information, such as regions of pixels in images or word pieces in text, and autoregressive generation commonly predicts these tokens in a fixed order. A worthwhile question is whether token structures affect the ability to steer the generation through test-time search, where multiple candidate generations are explored and evaluated by a verifier. Using image generation as our testbed, we hypothesize that recent 1D ordered tokenizers with coarse-to-fine structure can be more amenable to search than classical 2D grid structures. This is rooted in the fact that the intermediate states in coarse-to-fine sequences carry semantic meaning that verifiers can reliably evaluate, enabling effective steering during generation.   We find that autoregressive models trained on coarse-to-fine ordered tokens exhibit improved test-time scaling behavior compared to grid-based counterparts. Moreover, we demonstrate that, thanks to the ordered structure, pure test-time search over token sequences (i.e., without training an autoregressive model) can perform training-free text-to-image generation when guided by an image-text verifier. Beyond this, we also systematically study how classical search algorithms (best-of-N, beam search, lookahead search) interact with different token structures, as well as the role of different verifiers and autoregressive priors in guiding the generation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Tokenization은 autoregressive generative model의 핵심 구성 요소로, 원시 데이터를 모델링하기 더 다루기 쉬운 단위로 변환한다. 일반적으로 token은 이미지의 픽셀 영역이나 텍스트의 word piece처럼 국소 정보를 나타내며, autoregressive generation은 보통 이 token들을 고정된 순서로 예측한다. 여기서 중요한 질문은 token structure가 test-time search를 통해 generation을 제어하는 능력에 영향을 주는가 하는 점이다. 이때 여러 후보 generation을 탐색하고 verifier로 평가한다. 이미지 생성을 testbed로 사용하여, 우리는 최근의 1D ordered tokenizer가 coarse-to-fine structure를 가지므로 classical 2D grid structure보다 search에 더 적합할 수 있다고 가정한다. 이는 coarse-to-fine sequence의 중간 상태가 semantic meaning을 담고 있어 verifier가 이를 신뢰성 있게 평가할 수 있기 때문이며, 이를 통해 generation 중 효과적인 steering이 가능해진다. 우리는 coarse-to-fine ordered token으로 학습된 autoregressive model이 grid-based counterpart보다 test-time scaling behavior가 향상됨을 확인한다. 또한 ordered structure 덕분에, token sequence에 대한 순수한 test-time search만으로도(즉, autoregressive model을 학습하지 않고도) image-text verifier의 guidance를 받아 training-free text-to-image generation이 가능함을 보인다. 이 외에도 우리는 classical search algorithm(best-of-N, beam search, lookahead search)이 서로 다른 token structure와 어떻게 상호작용하는지, 그리고 generation을 유도하는 데 있어 서로 다른 verifier와 autoregressive prior의 역할을 체계적으로 연구한다.</p>"},{"id":"65390","en":"Infinite-Precision Autoregressive Modeling for Vector Graphics and Layouts","ko":"벡터 그래픽 및 레이아웃을 위한 무한 정밀도 자기회귀 모델링","authors":"Yeonsang Shin, Insoo Kim, Bongkeun Kim, Keonwoo Bae, Bohyung Han","pos":"#2608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=E8m9sL7N0d","abs":"<p>Transformer-based autoregressive models excel in data generation but are inherently constrained by their reliance on discretized tokens, which limits their ability to represent continuous values with high precision. We analyze the scalability limitations of existing discretization-based approaches for generating hybrid discrete-continuous sequences, particularly in high-precision domains such as logos, layouts, and semiconductor circuit designs, where precision loss potentially leads to visual artifacts, aesthetic degradation, and even functional failure. To address the challenge, we propose a novel unified framework that jointly models discrete and continuous values for variable-length sequences. Our approach employs a hybrid approach that combines categorical prediction for discrete values with diffusion-based modeling for continuous values, incorporating two key technical components: an end-of-sequence (EOS) logit adjustment mechanism that uses an MLP to dynamically adjust EOS token logits based on sequence context, and a length regularization term integrated into the loss function. Additionally, we present ContLayNet, a large-scale benchmark comprising 334K high-precision semiconductor layout samples with specialized evaluation metrics that capture functional correctness, where precision errors significantly impact performance. Experiments on semiconductor layouts (ContLayNet), graphic layouts, and SVGs demonstrate that our approach achieves higher-fidelity hybrid vector representations than discretization-based and fixed-schema baselines, while scaling to high-precision generation across multiple domains.</p>"},{"id":"62597","en":"MUSE: Resolving Manifold Misalignment in Visual Tokenization via Topological Orthogonality","ko":"MUSE: Topological Orthogonality로 Visual Tokenization의 manifold misalignment 완화","authors":"Panqi Yang, Haodong Jing, Jiahao Chao, Tingyan Xiang, Li Lin, Yao Hu, Yang Luo, Yongqiang Ma","pos":"#306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fCjkHj6Z4V","abs":"<p>Unified visual tokenization faces a fundamental trade-off: optimizing for high-fidelity pixel reconstruction (spatial equivariance) inherently conflicts with semantic abstraction (conceptual invariance). We identify the root cause as Manifold Misalignment, where naive joint optimization leads to conflicting gradients that force a zero-sum game between these two objectives. In this paper, we propose MUSE, a framework that resolves this deadlock via Topological Orthogonality. Recognizing Structure as the orthogonal bridge, MUSE physically decouples the optimization subspaces within Transformers. We route structural gradients to refine attention topology and semantic gradients to update feature values, transforming destructive interference into Mutual Reinforcement. Extensive experiments demonstrate that MUSE breaks the trade-off, matching state-of-the-art generation (gFID 3.08) while notably outperforming its own teacher InternViT-300M in linear probing (85.2% vs. 82.5%), proving that structurally aligned reconstruction actively refines semantic perception.</p>","absKo":"<p>Unified visual tokenization은 근본적인 trade-off에 직면한다. 고충실도 pixel reconstruction(spatial equivariance)을 최적화하는 것은 semantic abstraction(conceptual invariance)과 본질적으로 충돌한다. 우리는 그 근본 원인을 Manifold Misalignment로 식별하는데, 단순한 joint optimization은 두 목표 사이에 zero-sum game을 강제하는 상충 gradient를 유발한다. 본 논문에서는 Topological Orthogonality를 통해 이 교착 상태를 해소하는 framework인 MUSE를 제안한다. Structure를 orthogonal bridge로 인식하여, MUSE는 Transformer 내부의 optimization subspace를 물리적으로 분리한다. 우리는 structural gradient를 attention topology 정제에, semantic gradient를 feature value 업데이트에 각각 라우팅하여 파괴적 간섭을 Mutual Reinforcement으로 전환한다. 광범위한 실험은 MUSE가 이 trade-off를 깨뜨려, state-of-the-art generation(gFID 3.08)을 유지하면서도 linear probing에서 자체 teacher인 InternViT-300M을 현저히 능가함(85.2% vs. 82.5%)을 보여준다. 이는 구조적으로 정렬된 reconstruction이 semantic perception을 능동적으로 정제함을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64942","en":"Scalable Single-Cell Gene Expression Generation with Latent Diffusion Models","ko":"Latent Diffusion Model을 활용한 확장 가능한 단일 세포 유전자 발현 생성","authors":"Giovanni Palla, Sudarshan Babu, Payam Dibaeinia, James Pearce, Donghui Li, Aly Khan, Theofanis Karaletsos, Jakub Tomczak","pos":"#3512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IRwg87oeJo","abs":"<p>Computational modeling of single-cell gene expression is crucial for understanding cellular processes, but generating realistic expression profiles remains a major challenge. This difficulty arises from the count nature of gene expression data and complex latent dependencies among genes. Existing generative models often impose artificial gene orderings or rely on shallow neural network architectures. We introduce a scalable latent diffusion model for single-cell gene expression data, which we refer to as scLDM, that respects the fundamental exchangeability property of the data. Our VAE uses fixed-size latent variables leveraging a unified Multi-head Cross-Attention Block (MCAB) architecture, which serves dual roles: permutation-invariant pooling in the encoder and permutation-equivariant unpooling in the decoder. We enhance this framework by replacing the Gaussian prior with a latent diffusion model using Diffusion Transformers and linear interpolants, enabling high-quality generation with multi-conditional classifier-free guidance. We show its superior performance in a variety of experiments for both observational and perturbational single-cell data, as well as downstream tasks like cell-level classification.</p>","absKo":"<p>single-cell gene expression의 computational modeling은 cellular process를 이해하는 데 핵심적이지만, realistic한 expression profile을 생성하는 것은 여전히 큰 과제이다. 이러한 어려움은 gene expression data의 count 성질과 gene 간 복잡한 latent dependency에서 비롯된다. 기존 generative model은 종종 인위적인 gene ordering을 부여하거나 얕은 neural network architecture에 의존한다. 우리는 data의 근본적인 exchangeability property를 보존하는, single-cell gene expression data를 위한 scalable latent diffusion model인 scLDM을 제안한다. 우리의 VAE는 통합된 Multi-head Cross-Attention Block(MCAB) architecture를 활용하는 고정 크기 latent variable을 사용하며, 이는 encoder에서 permutation-invariant pooling과 decoder에서 permutation-equivariant unpooling이라는 이중 역할을 수행한다. 우리는 Gaussian prior를 Diffusion Transformer와 linear interpolant를 사용하는 latent diffusion model로 대체하여 이 프레임워크를 강화하며, multi-conditional classifier-free guidance를 통한 고품질 생성을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 observational 및 perturbational single-cell data 모두에 대한 다양한 실험과 cell-level classification 같은 downstream task에서 그 우수한 성능을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63829","en":"OmniDenseCap: Scripting Multi-Scene Videos with Time-Aware and Structural Audio-Visual Captions","ko":"OmniDenseCap: 시간 인지 및 구조적 audio-visual caption으로 멀티 장면 비디오 스크립팅","authors":"Linli Yao, Yuancheng Wei, Yaojie Zhang, Lei Li, Xinlong Chen, Feifan Song, Ziyue Wang, Kun Ouyang, Yuanxin Liu, Lingpeng Kong, Qi Liu, Pengfei Wan, Kun Gai, Yuanxing Zhang, Xu SUN","pos":"#1102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TL787dxmIM","abs":"<p>This paper proposes Omni Dense Captioning, a novel task designed to generate continuous, fine-grained, and structured audio-visual narratives with explicit timestamps. To ensure dense semantic coverage, we introduce a six-dimensional structural schema to create \"script-like\" captions, enabling readers to vividly imagine the video content scene-by-scene, akin to a cinematographic screenplay. To facilitate research, we construct OmniDCBench, a high-quality human-annotated benchmark, and propose SodaM, a unified metric that evaluates time-aware detailed descriptions while mitigating scene boundary ambiguity. Furthermore, we construct a training dataset OmniDenseCap-40K and present Omni-Captioner-7B, a strong baseline trained via SFT and GRPO with task-specific rewards. Extensive experiments demonstrate that Omni-Captioner-7B achieves state-of-the-art performance, surpassing Gemini-2.5-Pro, while its generated dense descriptions significantly boost downstream capabilities in audio-visual reasoning (DailyOmni and WorldSense) and temporal grounding (Charades-STA). All datasets, models, and code will be made publicly available.</p>","absKo":"<p>이 논문은 explicit timestamp를 갖춘 연속적이고 세밀하며 구조화된 audio-visual narrative를 생성하는 새로운 task인 Omni Dense Captioning을 제안한다. dense semantic coverage를 보장하기 위해, 우리는 \"script-like\" caption을 생성할 수 있는 6차원 structural schema를 도입하여 독자가 영상 내용을 장면별로 생생하게 상상할 수 있도록 한다. 연구를 촉진하기 위해, 우리는 고품질 human-annotated benchmark인 OmniDCBench를 구축하고, scene boundary ambiguity를 완화하면서 time-aware detailed description을 평가하는 통합 metric인 SodaM을 제안한다. 더 나아가, training dataset인 OmniDenseCap-40K를 구축하고, task-specific reward를 사용한 SFT와 GRPO로 학습된 강력한 baseline인 Omni-Captioner-7B를 제시한다. 광범위한 실험은 Omni-Captioner-7B가 Gemini-2.5-Pro를 능가하며 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보이고, 이 모델이 생성한 dense description이 audio-visual reasoning (DailyOmni, WorldSense)과 temporal grounding (Charades-STA)에서 downstream capability를 크게 향상시킴을 보여준다. 모든 dataset, model, code는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64205","en":"When RAG Hurts: Diagnosing and Mitigating Attention Distraction in Retrieval-Augmented LVLMs","ko":"RAG가 해로울 때: 검색 증강 LVLM에서 어텐션 산만 진단 및 완화","authors":"Beidi Zhao, wenlong deng, Xinting Liao, Yushu Li, Nazim Shaikh, Yao Nie, Xiaoxiao Li","pos":"#1509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PzXOrmsRZn","abs":"<p>While Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is one of the dominant paradigms for enhancing Large Vision-Language Models (LVLMs) on knowledge-based VQA tasks, recent work attributes RAG failures to insufficient attention towards the retrieved context, proposing to reduce the attention allocated to image tokens. In this work, we identify a distinct failure mode that previous study overlooked: Attention Distraction (AD). When the retrieved context is sufficient (highly relevant or including the correct answer), the retrieved text suppresses the visual attention globally, and the attention on image tokens shifts away from question-relevant regions. This leads to failures on questions the model could originally answer correctly without the retrieved text. To mitigate this issue, we propose MAD-RAG, a training-free intervention that decouples visual grounding from context integration through a dual-question formulation, combined with attention mixing to preserve image-conditioned evidence. Extensive experiments on OK-VQA, E-VQA, and InfoSeek demonstrate that MAD-RAG consistently outperforms existing baselines across different model families, yielding absolute gains of up to 4.76%, 9.20%, and 6.18% over the vanilla RAG baseline. Notably, MAD-RAG rectifies up to 74.68% of failure cases with negligible computational overhead.</p>","absKo":"<p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)은 knowledge-based VQA task에서 Large Vision-Language Models (LVLMs)을 향상시키는 지배적인 paradigm 중 하나이지만, 최근 연구는 RAG 실패를 검색된 context에 대한 attention 부족으로 돌리며 image token에 할당되는 attention을 줄일 것을 제안한다. 이 연구에서 우리는 이전 연구가 간과한 별개의 실패 양상인 Attention Distraction (AD)을 식별한다. 검색된 context가 충분할 때(매우 관련성이 높거나 정답을 포함할 때), 검색된 text는 전역적으로 visual attention을 억제하고 image token에 대한 attention이 질문과 관련된 region에서 벗어나게 만든다. 이는 검색된 text가 없으면 원래 올바르게 답할 수 있었던 질문에서 실패로 이어진다. 이 문제를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 dual-question formulation을 통해 visual grounding과 context integration을 분리하고 attention mixing을 결합하여 image-conditioned evidence를 보존하는 training-free intervention인 MAD-RAG를 제안한다. OK-VQA, E-VQA, InfoSeek에 대한 광범위한 실험은 MAD-RAG가 서로 다른 model family 전반에서 기존 baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, vanilla RAG baseline 대비 최대 4.76%, 9.20%, 6.18%의 절대 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. 특히 MAD-RAG는 거의 무시할 만한 계산 오버헤드로 실패 사례의 최대 74.68%를 수정한다.</p>"},{"id":"60743","en":"What Makes Effective Supervision in Latent Chain-of-Thought: An Information-Theoretic Analysis","ko":"Latent Chain-of-Thought에서 효과적인 Supervision은 무엇인가: 정보이론적 분석","authors":"Xinghao Chen, Chak Tou Leong, Wenjin Guo, Jian Wang, Wenjie Li, Xiaoyu Shen","pos":"#1511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x21YkF1UfR","abs":"<p>Latent Chain-of-Thought (CoT) aims to internalize reasoning into continuous hidden states, promising to transcend the computational bottlenecks of explicit tokens. However, the precise mechanisms ensuring its validity remain opaque. To bridge this gap, we establish an Information-Theoretic Framework that dissects supervision into Trajectory Control and State Alignment. Our analysis identifies structural scaffolding as the fundamental prerequisite for valid latent dynamics, and demonstrate that Outcome Supervision falters due to optimization barriers, while Process Supervision succeeds by minimizing conditional entropy, thereby enforcing trajectory predictability. And we expose a divergence in alignment strategies: rigid Geometric Compression acts as a destructive prior that collapses the reasoning manifold, whereas Generative Reconstruction serves as a flexible semantic tether, optimizing for reconstructibility to preserve the intrinsic dimensionality of the latent space. To quantify these dynamics, we introduce the Unified Latent-MI Probe (ULP), which unveils a strict Information-Performance Binding: reasoning accuracy is deeply correlated with the mutual information retained in the latent chain.Ultimately, we advocate for a paradigm shift from geometric imitation to mutual information maximization to counter the information decay inherent in autoregressive generation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Latent Chain-of-Thought (CoT)는 명시적 토큰의 계산 병목을 넘어 continuous hidden state 안에 reasoning을 내재화하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 이를 보장하는 정확한 메커니즘은 여전히 불투명하다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 supervision을 Trajectory Control과 State Alignment로 분해하는 Information-Theoretic Framework를 확립한다. 우리의 분석은 valid latent dynamics를 위한 근본적 전제조건으로 structural scaffolding을 식별하며, Outcome Supervision은 optimization barrier 때문에 실패하는 반면 Process Supervision은 conditional entropy를 최소화함으로써 trajectory predictability를 강제하여 성공함을 보인다. 또한 alignment 전략의 차이를 드러낸다: 경직된 Geometric Compression은 reasoning manifold를 붕괴시키는 destructive prior로 작동하는 반면, Generative Reconstruction은 reconstructibility를 최적화하여 latent space의 intrinsic dimensionality를 보존하는 유연한 semantic tether로 기능한다. 이러한 dynamics를 정량화하기 위해, 우리는 Unified Latent-MI Probe (ULP)를 도입하며, 이는 엄격한 Information-Performance Binding을 드러낸다. 즉, reasoning accuracy는 latent chain에 유지된 mutual information과 깊게 상관된다. 궁극적으로 우리는 autoregressive generation에 내재된 information decay에 대응하기 위해, 기하학적 모방에서 mutual information 최대화로의 paradigm shift를 제안한다.</p>"},{"id":"62346","en":"Scene Graph Thinking: Reinforcing Structured Visual Reasoning for Multimodal Large Language Models","ko":"Scene Graph Thinking: 멀티모달 Large Language Models의 구조화된 시각 추론 강화","authors":"Zhiwei Yang, Yuanchen Wu, Nan Zhang, Yucong Meng, Ke Yan, Shouhong Ding","pos":"#1600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hRSLIreHlx","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) have demonstrated strong perception and reasoning capabilities. However, most existing models focus on isolated objects and neglect structured relationships for efficient target navigation, limiting their performance on visually intensive tasks. To address this challenge, we introduce Scene Graph Thinking (SaGe), a novel paradigm that enables fine-grained and structured visual reasoning through explicit scene-graph representations. Specifically, we first introduce an automated data engine that converts flat image–text corpora into structured scene graphs, where hierarchical entities constitute the nodes and diverse visual relations define the edges. Building upon this, we construct 120K high-quality training data by sampling reasoning traces from scene graphs. Then two-stage graph-aligned post-training paradigms are introduced, where supervised fine-tuning internalizes MLLMs with structured reasoning, and subsequent reinforcement fine-tuning proposes node-as-proxy graph rewards to consolidate efficient graph exploration. With curated data and graph-aligned training, our approach achieves significant improvements across eight multimodal benchmarks, demonstrating strong effectiveness on fine-grained perception and reasoning tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models(MLLMs)은 강력한 perception과 reasoning 능력을 입증해 왔다. 그러나 대부분의 기존 모델은 고립된 객체에 초점을 맞추고, 효율적인 target navigation에 필요한 구조화된 관계를 간과하여 시각적으로 집약적인 과제에서 성능이 제한된다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 명시적인 scene-graph representation을 통해 세밀하고 구조화된 visual reasoning을 가능하게 하는 새로운 패러다임인 Scene Graph Thinking(SaGe)을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 먼저 평면적인 image-text 코퍼스를 구조화된 scene graph로 변환하는 자동화된 data engine을 도입하는데, 여기서 계층적 entity는 node를 이루고 다양한 visual relation이 edge를 정의한다. 이를 바탕으로, scene graph에서 reasoning trace를 샘플링하여 120K개의 고품질 training data를 구성한다. 이어서 두 단계의 graph-aligned post-training 패러다임을 도입하는데, supervised fine-tuning은 MLLM에 structured reasoning을 내재화하고, 이후의 reinforcement fine-tuning은 node-as-proxy graph reward를 제안하여 효율적인 graph exploration을 공고히 한다. 정제된 데이터와 graph-aligned training을 통해, 우리의 접근법은 8개의 multimodal benchmark 전반에서 유의미한 개선을 달성하며, 세밀한 perception 및 reasoning task에서 강한 효과를 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65080","en":"Schema-Guided World Modeling for Understanding Hierarchical Visual Dynamics","ko":"계층적 시각 동역학 이해를 위한 스키마 기반 World Modeling","authors":"Silin Gao, Hao Zhao, Zeming Chen, Sepideh Mamooler, Antara R Bhattacharya, Qiyu Wu, Hiromi Wakaki, Yuki Mitsufuji, Li Mi, Syrielle Montariol, Antoine Bosselut","pos":"#1601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Gy0C1ykv2o","abs":"<p>Multimodal LLMs lack a systematic understanding of visual dynamics in complex human world activities, which requires the model to predict or simulate multiple levels of dynamic constituents, such as the general progression of actions and the associated changes of low-level details in the world. To address this challenge, we propose a dynamic visual schema-guided world model, DynaVieW, optimized for visual dynamic prediction and simulation. DynaVieW achieves an in-depth understanding of visual dynamics by learning interleaved state-transition sequences, where states cover broad visual scenes from video keyframes, and transitions capture comprehensive dynamic constituents within a hierarchical schema. DynaVieW jointly models transition prediction and state simulation under a mixture-of-experts architecture, with a cross-expert selective attention and a schema token re-weighted loss, to ensure effective and robust learning. DynaVieW's superior visual dynamic understanding boosts its downstream performances on both visual narrative creation and world simulation, showing improved consistency and controllability of visual generation and better instruction-following ability.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal LLM은 복잡한 human world activity에서 visual dynamics에 대한 체계적인 이해가 부족하다. 이는 모델이 행동의 일반적인 진행과 세계의 저수준 세부사항 변화와 같은 동적인 구성 요소의 여러 수준을 예측하거나 시뮬레이션해야 하기 때문이다. 이 과제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 visual dynamic prediction과 simulation에 최적화된 dynamic visual schema-guided world model인 DynaVieW를 제안한다. DynaVieW는 state-transition sequence를 interleaved하게 학습함으로써 visual dynamics를 심층적으로 이해한다. 여기서 state는 video keyframe에서 포괄적인 visual scene을 포괄하고, transition은 hierarchical schema 내에서 포괄적인 dynamic constituent를 포착한다. DynaVieW는 cross-expert selective attention과 schema token re-weighted loss를 갖는 mixture-of-experts architecture 아래에서 transition prediction과 state simulation을 공동으로 모델링하여, 효과적이고 견고한 학습을 보장한다. DynaVieW의 우수한 visual dynamic 이해 능력은 downstream 성능을 visual narrative creation과 world simulation 모두에서 향상시키며, visual generation의 consistency와 controllability를 개선하고 instruction-following ability를 높인다.</p>"},{"id":"61633","en":"Semantic Impact–Driven Visual Scheduling in Vision-Language Models","ko":"Vision-Language Model에서 의미적 영향 기반 시각 스케줄링","authors":"Xuan Wang, Liu Yilin, Fangxiang Feng, Caixia Yuan, Huixing Jiang, Xiaojie Wang","pos":"#1602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oFZT8HCxmW","abs":"<p>Vision-Language Models (VLMs) suffer from high inference latency due to long visual sequences. To enable efficient, on-demand utilization of visual information, we argue that visual necessity should be assessed by its semantic impact on the output distribution, rather than inferred from intermediate interaction signals such as attention weights. We propose a training-free framework based on token embedding subspace decomposition, which we term a prediction-conditioned Semantic Lens. Specifically, at fixed decoding intervals, we perform QR decomposition on the Top-K candidate token embeddings to construct an orthogonal semantic basis. We then introduce Semantic IImpact–Driven Visual Scheduling (SIVS), which measures how visual inputs impact model predictions by projecting visual-induced hidden-state variations onto this semantic lens. SIVS provides a geometrically grounded, impact-driven criterion for dynamic visual KV scheduling. Empirical results demonstrate that SIVS achieves ~87% visual KV compression while maintaining over 99% of model performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-Language Model(VLM)은 긴 visual sequence로 인해 inference latency가 높다. 시각 정보를 효율적으로, 필요할 때만 활용하기 위해서는 visual necessity를 attention weight 같은 중간 interaction signal에서 추론하기보다 output distribution에 대한 semantic impact로 평가해야 한다고 우리는 주장한다. 우리는 token embedding subspace decomposition에 기반한 training-free framework를 제안하며, 이를 prediction-conditioned Semantic Lens라고 부른다. 구체적으로, 고정된 decoding interval마다 Top-K candidate token embedding에 대해 QR decomposition을 수행하여 orthogonal semantic basis를 구성한다. 그런 다음 Semantic IImpact–Driven Visual Scheduling(SIVS)을 도입하여, visual 입력이 모델 예측에 미치는 영향을 visual-induced hidden-state variation을 이 semantic lens에 투영함으로써 측정한다. SIVS는 geometry에 기반한 impact-driven criterion을 제공하여 동적 visual KV scheduling을 가능하게 한다. 실험 결과, SIVS는 모델 성능의 99% 이상을 유지하면서 약 87%의 visual KV compression을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"61322","en":"Sycophancy Towards Researchers Drives Performative Misalignment","ko":"연구자를 향한 아첨성이 수행적 Misalignment를 유발한다","authors":"David Baek, Xinnuo Li, Anay Gupta, Taslim Mahbub, Kejian Shi, Max Tegmark, Shi Feng","pos":"#1605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rLFIOikFR2","abs":"<p>The increasing situational awareness of language models raises safety concerns: models might be aware when they are evaluated, and adjust their behavior to evade monitoring and resist modification, e.g., pretending to be aligned only in evaluation. This \\emph{alignment faking} behavior is often interpreted as scheming: an intentional effort of strategic deception. In this paper, we examine an alternative interpretation, \\emph{performative misalignment}, which explains the change in behavior as a result of \\emph{sycophancy towards AI researchers}. To back up this hypothesis, we present three empirical findings. First, we show that evaluation awareness persists even when we tell models they are deployed, which contradicts the scheming story which predicts less misalignment when the model perceives evaluation. Second, we use probing and steering to show that our current methods cannot mechanistically distinguish sycophancy and scheming in alignment faking evaluations. Third, we fine-tune models to be more sycophantic and observe increased sensitivity to evaluation cues. To conclude, we emphasize deconfounding sycophancy from scheming for future work on evaluations and mitigations of intent misalignment.</p>","absKo":"<p>언어 모델의 증가하는 situational awareness는 안전성 우려를 낳는다. 모델이 자신이 평가받고 있음을 인지하고, 예를 들어 evaluation에서는 aligned된 것처럼 가장함으로써 monitoring을 회피하고 수정에 저항하도록 행동을 조정할 수 있기 때문이다. 이러한 \\emph{alignment faking} 행동은 흔히 scheming, 즉 전략적 기만을 의도적으로 수행하는 것으로 해석된다. 본 논문에서는 이와 다른 해석인 \\emph{performative misalignment}를 검토하며, 이는 행동 변화를 \\emph{AI researcher에 대한 sycophancy}의 결과로 설명한다. 이 가설을 뒷받침하기 위해 세 가지 실증적 발견을 제시한다. 첫째, 모델에게 배포되었다고 알려주어도 evaluation awareness는 지속되며, 이는 model이 evaluation을 인지할수록 misalignment가 줄어든다고 예측하는 scheming 설명과 모순된다. 둘째, probing과 steering을 사용해 현재 방법으로는 alignment faking evaluation에서 sycophancy와 scheming을 mechanistically 구분할 수 없음을 보인다. 셋째, 모델을 더 sycophantic하게 fine-tune하면 evaluation cue에 대한 민감도가 증가함을 관찰한다. 결론적으로, intent misalignment의 evaluation 및 mitigation에 관한 향후 연구에서 sycophancy와 scheming을 혼동하지 않는 것이 중요함을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"63532","en":"Training-Free Hierarchical Working Memory for Small Language Model Agents","ko":"훈련 없는 소형 언어 모델 에이전트를 위한 계층적 작업 메모리","authors":"Ziyi Wang, Haonan Jin, Zian Wang, Wendong Wang, Lanshan Zhang","pos":"#1612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WLnpZpShzr","abs":"<p>Small language models (SLMs) are attractive for agent deployment, but they struggle to reliably retain and reuse decision-relevant state information over long interactions. This issue is exacerbated when working memory is maintained via unstructured natural-language summarization. Some recent work addresses this limitation by fine-tuning or distilling smaller models to better construct and utilize working memory, but such approaches typically incur substantial additional training cost and require continuous data construction. We present a training-free working-memory framework for SLM-based agents that makes decision-relevant state explicit: conditioned on the active (sub)goal, the agent maintains a compact information state needed for progress assessment and the currently effective action set. Our approach decomposes tasks into subgoals and organizes memory hierarchically into task-level global memory and subtask-level local memory, where local memory directly conditions SLM action selection and is updated from new observations. To instantiate goal-conditioned memories without parameter updates, we introduce an offline LLM-based induction pipeline that builds a reusable schema once per task family from a small number of representative traces. Training-free refers to no parameter updates of the deployed SLM and no online LLM calls; we only use a one-time offline LLM-based schema induction per task family. On ALFWorld valid_unseen, a 4B SLM achieves 0.910 success, while representative prompting and prior working-memory baselines under the same setting remain below 0.320.</p>","absKo":"<p>Small language models (SLMs)는 agent 배포에 매력적이지만, 장기 상호작용에서 decision-relevant state information을 안정적으로 유지하고 재사용하는 데 어려움이 있다. 이 문제는 working memory를 비구조적인 자연어 요약으로 유지할 때 더욱 심화된다. 최근 일부 연구는 더 작은 모델이 working memory를 더 잘 구성하고 활용하도록 fine-tuning하거나 distillation하는 방식으로 이 한계를 다루지만, 이러한 접근은 대개 상당한 추가 학습 비용과 지속적인 데이터 구축을 수반한다. 우리는 decision-relevant state를 명시적으로 만드는, SLM-based agents를 위한 training-free working-memory framework를 제시한다. 활성화된 (sub)goal에 조건화되어, 에이전트는 진행 상황 평가에 필요한 압축된 information state와 현재 유효한 action set을 유지한다. 우리의 접근법은 task를 subgoal로 분해하고, memory를 task-level global memory와 subtask-level local memory로 계층적으로 구성한다. 여기서 local memory는 SLM의 action selection을 직접 조건화하며 새로운 관찰로 갱신된다. 파라미터 업데이트 없이 goal-conditioned memories를 구현하기 위해, 소수의 대표 trace만으로 task family마다 한 번 재사용 가능한 schema를 구축하는 offline LLM-based induction pipeline을 도입한다. 여기서 training-free는 배포된 SLM의 파라미터 업데이트가 없고 online LLM calls도 없음을 뜻하며, task family당 한 번의 offline LLM-based schema induction만 사용한다. ALFWorld valid_unseen에서 4B SLM은 0.910의 성공률을 달성했으며, 동일한 설정에서 representative prompting과 기존 working-memory baselines는 모두 0.320 미만에 머물렀다.</p>"},{"id":"62869","en":"Prioritize the Process, Not Just the Outcome: Rewarding Latent Thought Trajectories Improves Reasoning in Looped Language Models","ko":"결과보다 과정을 우선시하라: Looped Language Models의 잠재 사고 경로 보상이 추론 성능 향상","authors":"Jonathan Williams, Esin Tureci, Olga Russakovsky","pos":"#1707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cPAgJwcn3h","abs":"<p>Looped Language Models (LoopLMs) perform multi-step latent reasoning prior to token generation and outperform conventional LLMs on reasoning benchmarks at smaller parameter budgets. However, attempts to further improve LoopLM reasoning with reinforcement learning have failed—standard objectives such as Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) only assign credit to the final latent state, creating a fundamental mismatch with the model's internal computation. To resolve this, we introduce <strong>RLTT (Reward Latent Thought Trajectories)</strong>, a reinforcement learning framework which distributes reward across the full latent reasoning trajectory. RLTT provides dense, trajectory-level credit assignment without relying on external verifiers and can directly replace GRPO with negligible overhead. Across extensive experiments with Ouro-2.6B-Thinking under identical training and inference conditions, <strong>RLTT yields substantial improvements over GRPO on challenging mathematical reasoning benchmarks, improving accuracy by +14.4\\% on MATH-500, +16.6\\% on AIME24, and +10.0\\% on BeyondAIME</strong>. Despite being trained exclusively on mathematics, RLTT also transfers effectively to non-mathematical reasoning benchmarks, demonstrating the effectiveness of trajectory-level credit assignment for reinforcement learning in LoopLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Looped Language Models(LoopLMs)는 토큰 생성에 앞서 다단계 latent reasoning을 수행하며, 더 작은 parameter budget에서도 reasoning benchmark에서 기존 LLM을 능가한다. 그러나 reinforcement learning을 통해 LoopLM reasoning을 더 개선하려는 시도는 실패해 왔다. Group Relative Policy Optimization(GRPO) 같은 표준 objective는 최종 latent state에만 credit을 부여하여, 모델 내부 계산과 근본적인 불일치를 만들기 때문이다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 전체 latent reasoning trajectory에 reward를 분배하는 reinforcement learning framework인 <strong>RLTT(Reward Latent Thought Trajectories)</strong>를 제안한다. RLTT는 외부 verifier에 의존하지 않으면서 trajectory-level로 촘촘한 credit assignment를 제공하며, 거의 추가 오버헤드 없이 GRPO를 직접 대체할 수 있다. 동일한 training 및 inference 조건에서 Ouro-2.6B-Thinking을 사용한 광범위한 실험에서, <strong>RLTT는 까다로운 수학 reasoning benchmark에서 GRPO보다 크게 우수한 성능을 보였고, MATH-500에서 정확도를 +14.4\\%, AIME24에서 +16.6\\%, BeyondAIME에서 +10.0\\% 향상시켰다</strong>. 수학 데이터로만 학습했음에도 불구하고 RLTT는 비수학 reasoning benchmark에도 효과적으로 전이되었으며, LoopLMs에서 reinforcement learning을 위한 trajectory-level credit assignment의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"60628","en":"MetaphorVU: Towards Metaphorical Video Understanding","ko":"MetaphorVU: 은유적 비디오 이해를 향하여","authors":"Zhuoqun Li, Boxi Cao, Guiping Jiang, Fangrui Lv, Ruotong Pan, Jianan Wang, Xiangyu Wu, Hongyu Lin, Yaojie Lu, Yong Du, Ruyin Jia, Liyan, Tingting Gao, Han Li, Xianpei Han, Le Sun","pos":"#1804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yKcBAJMPXZ","abs":"<p>Metaphorical videos are prevalent across various real-world scenarios to convey complex ideas, and understanding them typically requires high-order cognitive capabilities.  The lack of systematic studies on metaphorical video understanding not only constrains the real-world applicability of MLLMs but also impedes the thorough assessment of their high-order cognitive capabilities. To bridge this gap, we propose MetaphorVU-Bench, the first systematic and comprehensive benchmark dedicated to metaphorical video understanding.  Through experiments, we find current MLLMs struggle with accurate metaphorical video understanding, lagging far behind human level, primarily due to defective cross-domain mapping.  Motivated by this finding, we construct a metaphor knowledge graph as mapping augmentation and propose MetaphorBoost, an inference-time enhancement framework achieving consistent performance improvement.  Our benchmark, analysis, and method provide useful insights and a foundation for future research on advancing MLLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>은유적 비디오는 복잡한 아이디어를 전달하기 위해 다양한 실제 상황에서 흔히 나타나며, 이를 이해하려면 보통 고차 인지 능력이 필요하다. 은유적 비디오 이해에 대한 체계적 연구의 부재는 MLLMs의 실제 적용 가능성을 제한할 뿐 아니라, 이들의 고차 인지 능력을 충분히 평가하는 일도 방해한다. 이러한 격차를 메우기 위해 우리는 은유적 비디오 이해를 위한 최초의 체계적이고 포괄적인 benchmark인 MetaphorVU-Bench를 제안한다. 실험을 통해 현재의 MLLMs는 정확한 은유적 비디오 이해에 어려움을 겪으며, 주로 결함 있는 cross-domain mapping 때문에 인간 수준에 한참 못 미친다는 사실을 발견했다. 이러한 발견에 착안하여, 우리는 mapping augmentation으로서 metaphor knowledge graph를 구축하고, 일관된 성능 향상을 달성하는 inference-time enhancement framework인 MetaphorBoost를 제안한다. 우리의 benchmark, 분석, 방법은 MLLMs의 발전을 위한 향후 연구에 유용한 통찰과 기반을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"65368","en":"LLMInertia: Adaptive Counter-Inertial Reasoning to Improve Evidence Faithfulness in Large Language Models","ko":"LLMInertia: Large Language Model의 증거 충실성을 개선하기 위한 적응형 반관성 추론","authors":"Xinxin You, Xien Liu, Chenwei Yan, Siqi Song, Chen Ning, Kaiyin Zhou, shaohui liu, Ji Wu","pos":"#1905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EIAXxF4cic","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) frequently generate output that contradicts explicit input evidence, limiting their reliability in real-world applications. We identify cognitive inertia in LLMs—a tendency to overly rely on co-occurrence associations learned during pretraining and to resist adaptation when conflicting input evidence appears—as a critical factor behind such hallucinations. We further empirically show that adherence to input evidence declines as co-occurrence associations are strengthened—driven by either higher data frequency or intensified training. Inspired by human counter-inertial thinking, we propose an adaptive counter-inertial reasoning framework that probes input-related cognitive inertia in the LLM and generates adaptive counter-inertial reminders, which are then injected into the prompt to promote evidence-based reasoning. Experiments on co-occurrence induction datasets show that LLMInertia reduces hallucination rates by up to 35\\% and improves accuracy by up to 35.68\\%. Extensive evaluations on four context-rich summarization and QA datasets, across three LLM backbones of varying scales, further validate its effectiveness and robustness. Our work provides new insight into the causes of input-unfaithful hallucinations in LLMs, contributing to the development of more reliable AI.</p>"},{"id":"61980","en":"Imagination Helps Visual Reasoning, But Not Yet in Latent Space","ko":"상상은 visual reasoning에 도움되지만 latent space에서는 아직 미흡","authors":"You Li, Chi Chen, Yanghao Li, Fanhu Zeng, Kaiyu Huang, Xu Jinan, Maosong Sun","pos":"#1907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=l1cMErXg1P","abs":"<p>Latent visual reasoning aims to mimic human's <em>imagination</em> process by meditating through hidden states of Multimodal Large Language Models.   While recognized as a promising paradigm for visual reasoning, the underlying mechanisms driving its effectiveness remain unclear.   Motivated to demystify the true source of its efficacy, we investigate the validity of latent reasoning using Causal Mediation Analysis.    We model the process as a causal chain: the input as the treatment, the latent tokens as the mediator, and the final answer as the outcome.    Our findings uncover two critical disconnections:    (a) <strong>Input-Latent Disconnect</strong>: dramatic perturbations on the input result in negligible changes to the latent tokens, suggesting that latent tokens do not effectively attend to the input sequence.   (b) <strong>Latent-Answer Disconnect</strong>: perturbations on the latent tokens yield minimal impact on the final answer, indicating the limited causal effect latent tokens imposing on the outcome.   Furthermore, extensive probing analysis reveals that latent tokens encode limited visual information and exhibit high similarity.   Consequently, we challenge the necessity of latent reasoning and propose a straightforward alternative named <em>CapImagine</em>, which teaches the model to explicitly <em>imagine</em> using text.   Experiments on vision-centric benchmarks show that <em>CapImagine</em> significantly outperforms complex latent-space baselines, highlighting the superior potential of visual reasoning through explicit imagination.</p>","absKo":"<p>Latent visual reasoning은 Multimodal Large Language Models의 hidden state를 매개로 하여 인간의 <em>imagination</em> 과정을 모방하는 것을 목표로 한다. 시각 reasoning을 위한 유망한 paradigm으로 인식되고 있지만, 그 효과를 이끄는 근본 메커니즘은 여전히 명확하지 않다. 우리는 그 진짜 효과의 원천을 밝히기 위해 Causal Mediation Analysis를 사용하여 latent reasoning의 타당성을 조사한다. 우리는 이 과정을 causal chain으로 모델링한다: 입력을 treatment로, latent token을 mediator로, 최종 답변을 outcome으로 본다. 우리의 발견은 두 가지 중요한 단절을 드러낸다. (a) <strong>Input-Latent Disconnect</strong>: 입력에 대한 극적인 perturbation이 latent token에는 거의 변화를 일으키지 않으며, 이는 latent token이 입력 sequence에 효과적으로 attention하지 못함을 시사한다. (b) <strong>Latent-Answer Disconnect</strong>: latent token에 대한 perturbation은 최종 답변에 최소한의 영향을 주며, 이는 latent token이 outcome에 미치는 causal effect가 제한적임을 나타낸다. 또한, 광범위한 probing 분석은 latent token이 제한된 visual information을 인코딩하고 높은 유사성을 보인다는 점을 보여준다. 따라서 우리는 latent reasoning의 필요성에 의문을 제기하고, 모델이 text를 사용하여 명시적으로 <em>imagine</em>하도록 가르치는 <em>CapImagine</em>이라는 간단한 대안을 제안한다. vision-centric benchmark에서의 실험은 <em>CapImagine</em>이 복잡한 latent-space baseline을 크게 능가함을 보여주며, 명시적 imagination을 통한 visual reasoning의 우월한 잠재력을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61188","en":"How Do Language Models Speak Languages? A Case Study on Unintended Code-Switching","ko":"Language Model은 어떻게 언어를 말하는가? 의도치 않은 Code-Switching 사례 연구","authors":"Yuxin Xiao, Zhen Huang, Wenxiao Wang, Yan Zhao, Zhihong Gu, Binbin Lin, Xiaofei He, Xu Shen, Jieping Ye","pos":"#1910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=stQsBkwz22","abs":"Unintended code-switching, which refers to the phenomenon where LLM unexpectedly switch languages, poses a fundamental challenge in the multilingual capabilities in LLMs. However, we still lack a mechanistic account of how this failure mode is implemented inside the model. For example, what internal components (i.e., circuits) give rise to unintended code-switching, where they emerge across layers, and how we can intervene to mitigate it. In this work, we introduce a scalable circuit discovery framework that causally localizes multilingual neurons and describes their functional patterns, then further groups them into interpretable circuits---without any additional training or manual annotation. Our findings lie in two folds: a) The model's ``speaking-a-language'' circuit decomposes into a language regime (detecting and maintaining language identity) and a semantic regime (retrieving language-agnostic semantics). b) The mechanism of unintended code-switching is a regime shift. Semantic regime suppresses the language regime, and overwhelms the multilingual circuit, leading the model to speak in unintended language. To validate these findings, we further fine-tune the identified language sub-circuit, reducing the code-switching rate by $20.8\\%$ with minimal parameter updates ($\\sim0.019\\%$ of all neurons). This work serves as a preliminary exploration of multilingual generation mechanism, offering actionable insight for targeted training for multilingual LLMs.","absKo":"의도하지 않은 code-switching, 즉 LLM이 예기치 않게 언어를 바꾸는 현상은 LLM의 multilingual capability에 근본적인 도전을 제기한다. 그러나 이러한 failure mode가 모델 내부에서 어떻게 구현되는지에 대한 mechanistic account는 여전히 부족하다. 예를 들어, 어떤 internal component(i.e., circuit)가 의도하지 않은 code-switching을 만들어 내는지, 그것이 layer 전반에 걸쳐 어디에서 나타나는지, 그리고 이를 완화하기 위해 어떻게 개입할 수 있는지에 대한 이해가 부족하다. 본 연구에서는 추가 training이나 manual annotation 없이 multilingual neuron을 causal하게 localize하고 그 functional pattern을 기술한 뒤, 이를 해석 가능한 circuit으로 더 세분화하는 scalable circuit discovery framework를 제안한다. 우리의 발견은 두 가지이다. a) 모델의 ``speaking-a-language'' circuit은 language regime(language identity를 감지하고 유지)와 semantic regime(language-agnostic semantics를 검색)로 분해된다. b) 의도하지 않은 code-switching의 메커니즘은 regime shift이다. semantic regime가 language regime를 억제하고 multilingual circuit을 압도하면서, 모델이 의도하지 않은 언어로 말하게 된다. 이러한 발견을 검증하기 위해, 우리는 식별된 language sub-circuit을 추가 fine-tune하여, 전체 neuron의 약 0.019\\%에 해당하는 최소한의 parameter update만으로 code-switching rate를 20.8\\% 감소시켰다. 본 연구는 multilingual generation mechanism에 대한 예비적 탐구로서, multilingual LLM을 위한 targeted training에 대한 실질적인 통찰을 제공한다."},{"id":"65285","en":"Graph of States: Solving Abductive Tasks with Large Language Models","ko":"상태 그래프: Large Language Model로 귀추적 과제 해결하기","authors":"Yu Luo, Rongchen Gao, Lu Teng, Xidao Wen, Jiamin Jiang, Qingliang Zhang, Yongqian Sun, Shenglin Zhang, Jiasong Feng, Tong Liu, Wenjie Zhang, Dan Pei","pos":"#1913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=F6PoIbPAe2","abs":"<p>Logical reasoning encompasses deduction, induction, and abduction.  However, while Large Language Models (LLMs) have effectively mastered the former two, abductive reasoning remains significantly underexplored. Existing frameworks, predominantly designed for static deductive tasks, fail to generalize to abductive reasoning due to unstructured state representation and lack of explicit state control. Consequently, they are inevitably prone to Evidence Fabrication, Context Drift, Failed Backtracking, and Early Stopping. To bridge this gap, we introduce Graph of States (GoS), a general-purpose neuro-symbolic framework tailored for abductive tasks. GoS grounds multi-agent collaboration in a structured belief states, utilizing a causal graph to explicitly encode logical dependencies and a state machine to govern the valid transitions of the reasoning process. By dynamically aligning the reasoning focus with these symbolic constraints, our approach transforms aimless, unconstrained exploration into a convergent, directed search. Extensive evaluations on two real-world datasets demonstrate that GoS significantly outperforms all baselines, providing a robust solution for complex abductive tasks. Code repo and all prompts: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Graph-of-States-5B4E.</p>"},{"id":"61109","en":"Stabilizing Recurrent Dynamics for Test-Time Scalable Latent Reasoning in Looped Language Models","ko":"Looped Language Model에서 Test-Time 확장 가능한 Latent Reasoning을 위한 Recurrent Dynamics 안정화","authors":"Xiao-Wen Yang, Zi-Yu Han, Xi-Hua Zhang, Wen-Da Wei, Jie-Jing Shao, Lan-Zhe Guo, Yu-Feng Li","pos":"#202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tbdSfBMlbq","abs":"<p>Looped Language Models (LoopLMs) enable efficient latent reasoning through depth recurrence, yet exhibit unreliable test-time scaling behavior: performance often peaks at a certain iteration depth and then collapses with further recurrence.  Through latent dynamics analysis, we find an inherent trade-off between stability and effectiveness in existing architectures and strategies. By conceptualizing reasoning as uncertainty reduction, we propose that convergence toward stable fixed points while preserving effectiveness represents a promising way. To this end, we propose STARS (STAbility-driven Recurrent Scaling), a training framework that constrains latent states to approach asymptotically stable fixed points. This is realized via efficient Jacobian Spectral Radius Regularization with random loop sampling, enabling STARS to maximize effectiveness while ensuring rigorous stability. Experiments on arithmetic tasks show that STARS achieves reliable test-time scaling, and on complex mathematical reasoning it substantially mitigates performance degradation as recurrence depth increases while also improving peak performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Looped Language Models(LoopLMs)는 depth recurrence를 통해 효율적인 latent reasoning을 가능하게 하지만, test-time scaling behavior는 신뢰성이 떨어진다: 성능은 종종 특정 iteration depth에서 최고점을 찍은 뒤, recurrence가 더 진행되면 붕괴한다. latent dynamics 분석을 통해, 우리는 기존 architecture와 strategy에 안정성(stability)과 효과성(effectiveness) 사이의 본질적 trade-off가 있음을 발견했다. reasoning을 uncertainty reduction으로 개념화하면, 효과성을 유지하면서 안정적인 fixed point로 수렴하는 것이 유망한 방향이라고 본다. 이를 위해 우리는 latent state가 점근적으로 안정한 fixed point에 접근하도록 제약하는 training framework인 STARS(STAbility-driven Recurrent Scaling)를 제안한다. 이는 random loop sampling을 활용한 효율적인 Jacobian Spectral Radius Regularization으로 구현되며, STARS가 엄격한 안정성을 보장하면서 효과성을 극대화할 수 있게 한다. 산술 task 실험에서 STARS는 신뢰할 수 있는 test-time scaling을 달성하며, 복잡한 수학적 reasoning에서는 recurrence depth가 증가할 때의 성능 저하를 크게 완화하는 동시에 최고 성능도 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"63261","en":"Coupled Variational Reinforcement Learning for Language Model General Reasoning","ko":"언어 모델 일반 추론을 위한 결합 변분 강화학습","authors":"Xueru Wen, Jie Lou, Yanjiang Liu, Hongyu Lin, Ben He, Xianpei Han, Le Sun, Yaojie Lu, Debing Zhang","pos":"#2103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YgQ3MV7OtR","abs":"<p>While reinforcement learning has achieved impressive progress in language model reasoning, it is constrained by the requirement for verifiable rewards. Recent verifier-free RL methods address this limitation by utilizing the probabilities that LLMs generate reference answers as reward signals. However, these approaches typically sample reasoning traces conditioned only on the question. This design decouples reasoning-trace sampling from answer information, leading to inefficient exploration and incoherence between traces and final answers. In this paper, we propose \\textit{\\b{Co}upled \\b{V}ariational \\b{R}einforcement \\b{L}earning} (CoVRL), which bridges variational inference and reinforcement learning by coupling prior and posterior distributions through a hybrid sampling strategy. By constructing and optimizing a composite distribution that integrates these two distributions, CoVRL enables efficient exploration while preserving strong thought-answer coherence. Extensive experiments on mathematical and general reasoning benchmarks show that CoVRL improves performance by 12.4\\% over the base model and achieves an additional 2.3\\% improvement over state-of-the-art verifier-free RL baselines, providing a principled framework for enhancing the general reasoning capabilities of language models.</p>","absKo":"<p>reinforcement learning은 language model reasoning에서 인상적인 진전을 이루었지만, verifiable rewards가 필요하다는 제약을 받는다. 최근 verifier-free RL 방법들은 LLMs가 reference answers를 생성할 때의 probabilities를 reward signal로 활용함으로써 이 한계를 해결한다. 그러나 이러한 접근은 대개 question에만 조건화된 reasoning traces를 샘플링한다. 이 설계는 reasoning-trace sampling을 answer information과 분리시켜, 비효율적인 exploration과 traces와 final answers 간의 incoherence를 초래한다. 본 논문에서는 prior와 posterior distribution을 hybrid sampling strategy로 coupling하여 variational inference와 reinforcement learning을 연결하는 \\textit{\\b{Co}upled \\b{V}ariational \\b{R}einforcement \\b{L}earning} (CoVRL)을 제안한다. 이 두 distribution을 통합하는 composite distribution을 구성하고 최적화함으로써, CoVRL은 강한 thought-answer coherence를 유지하면서 효율적인 exploration을 가능하게 한다. 수학 및 일반 reasoning benchmark 전반에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 CoVRL이 base model 대비 성능을 12.4\\% 향상시키고, state-of-the-art verifier-free RL baselines 대비 추가로 2.3\\% 향상을 달성함을 보여주며, language model의 일반 reasoning capability를 향상시키기 위한 원리적 framework를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"64966","en":"Context-Aware Reaonser : Enhancing Contextual Reasoning in Multimodal Large Language Models","ko":"Context-Aware Reasoner: 멀티모달 대규모 언어 모델에서 맥락적 추론 강화","authors":"Zhe Zheng, Wenqi Zhang, Xiaohe Zhou, Guiyang Hou, Xinyu Mei, Tianyang Mao, Anni PIAO, Shengpei Jiang, Yongliang Shen, Yueting Zhuang, Weiming Lu","pos":"#2106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IJ7bJubbgQ","abs":"<p>Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) have demonstrated remarkable reasoning capabilities over internalized knowledge. However, current research overlooks contextual reasoning, the ability to reason based on the relevant information present in the context. To investigate this issue, we construct the Visual Contextual Reasoning Benchmark (ContextReasonV-Bench), and our analysis reveals two predominant failure modes: \\textit{context neglect}, where models rely on pre-trained knowledge instead of contextual information, and \\textit{superficial pattern matching}, where models exploit shallow correlations rather than genuine patterns. To address these limitations, we propose a two-stage approach that progressively establishes and reinforces contextual pattern acquisition. The first stage establishes an \"analyze-then-solve\" reasoning paradigm through supervised fine-tuning (SFT). We then employ a context-aware reinforcement learning (RL) framework that integrates context-aware reward modeling with hierarchical advantage estimation to encourage the model to identify genuine contextual patterns. This approach yields Context-Aware Reasoner (CAR), a model that achieves 38.14\\% accuracy on ContextReasonV-Bench, improving the base model by 22.09\\%. Notably, CAR exhibits strong generalization to tasks not seen during training, confirming that our approach enhances genuine contextual reasoning capability.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal large language models (MLLMs)는 internalized knowledge에 대한 뛰어난 reasoning 능력을 보여 왔다. 그러나 현재 연구는 contextual reasoning, 즉 context에 존재하는 관련 정보를 바탕으로 추론하는 능력을 간과하고 있다. 이 문제를 조사하기 위해, 우리는 Visual Contextual Reasoning Benchmark (ContextReasonV-Bench)를 구성했으며, 분석 결과 두 가지 주요 실패 양상을 확인했다: \\textit{context neglect}, 즉 모델이 contextual information 대신 pre-trained knowledge에 의존하는 경우, 그리고 \\textit{superficial pattern matching}, 즉 모델이 진정한 pattern이 아니라 얕은 상관관계를 이용하는 경우이다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 contextual pattern acquisition을 점진적으로 확립하고 강화하는 two-stage approach를 제안한다. 첫 번째 stage에서는 supervised fine-tuning (SFT)을 통해 \"analyze-then-solve\" reasoning paradigm을 확립한다. 이후 우리는 context-aware reward modeling과 hierarchical advantage estimation을 통합하여 모델이 진정한 contextual pattern을 식별하도록 유도하는 context-aware reinforcement learning (RL) framework를 사용한다. 이 접근법은 Context-Aware Reasoner (CAR)를 산출하며, CAR는 ContextReasonV-Bench에서 38.14\\% accuracy를 달성해 base model 대비 22.09\\% 향상된다. 특히 CAR는 training 중 보지 못한 task로도 강한 generalization을 보이며, 우리의 접근이 진정한 contextual reasoning capability를 향상시킨다는 점을 확인해 준다.</p>"},{"id":"66469","en":"Attention Sinks as Internal Signals for Hallucination Detection in Large Language Models","ko":"대규모 언어 모델에서 환각 탐지를 위한 내부 신호로서의 Attention Sink","authors":"Jakub Binkowski, Kamil Adamczewski, Tomasz Kajdanowicz","pos":"#2114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3NdFFpcEjU","abs":"<p>Large language models frequently exhibit hallucinations: fluent and confident outputs that are factually incorrect or unsupported by the input context. While recent hallucination detection methods have explored various features derived from attention maps, the underlying mechanisms they exploit remain poorly understood. In this work, we propose SinkProbe, a hallucination detection method grounded in the observation that hallucinations are deeply entangled with attention sinks - tokens that accumulate disproportionate attention mass during generation - indicating a transition from distributed, input-grounded attention to compressed, prior-dominated computation. Importantly, although sink scores are computed solely from attention maps, we find that the classifier preferentially relies on sinks whose associated value vectors have large norms. Moreover, we show that previous methods implicitly depend on attention sinks by establishing their mathematical relationship to sink scores. Our findings yield a novel hallucination detection method grounded in theory that produces state-of-the-art results across popular datasets and LLMs.</p>"},{"id":"63552","en":"AnyEdit++: Adaptive Long-Form Knowledge Editing via Bayesian Surprise","ko":"AnyEdit++: Bayesian Surprise 기반 적응형 장문 지식 편집","authors":"Bowen Tian, Caixue He, Jiemin Wu, Jingying Wang, Wenshuo Chen, Zexi Li, Yutao Yue","pos":"#2212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=W6qfbvysDh","abs":"<p>Editing complex, long-form knowledge in Large Language Models remains a significant challenge due to the difficulty of maintaining generation coherence. Existing autoregressive methods like AnyEdit alleviate length constraints but rely on Fixed-window Chunking, which disregards logical structure and compromises consistency. To address this, we present AnyEdit++, a structure-aware framework incorporating Bayes-Chunk, an adaptive segmentation mechanism that dynamically identifies semantic boundaries based on Bayesian Surprise. We underpin this approach with a theoretical framework establishing two key principles: (1) Structural Independence: we prove that cross-segment interference is minimized when anchor keys are geometrically orthogonal (a condition naturally satisfied by our surprisal-based boundaries but violated by fixed windows), and (2) Causal Locality: we demonstrate that updates injected at these semantic peaks yield strictly superior control compared to arbitrary split points. Extensive experiments across mathematical reasoning, code generation, and narrative tasks demonstrate that AnyEdit++ achieves superior performance and robustness compared to state-of-the-art baselines, validating that structural awareness is critical for effective long-form knowledge editing.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models에서 complex하고 long-form knowledge를 편집하는 일은 generation coherence를 유지하기 어렵기 때문에 여전히 중요한 도전 과제이다. AnyEdit와 같은 기존 autoregressive method는 length constraint를 완화하지만, Fixed-window Chunking에 의존하여 logical structure를 무시하고 consistency를 훼손한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Bayesian Surprise를 바탕으로 semantic boundary를 동적으로 식별하는 adaptive segmentation mechanism인 Bayes-Chunk를 포함하는 structure-aware framework인 AnyEdit++를 제안한다. 우리는 이 접근법을 두 가지 핵심 원칙을 확립하는 theoretical framework로 뒷받침한다. (1) Structural Independence: anchor key가 기하학적으로 orthogonal할 때 cross-segment interference가 최소화됨을 증명하며, 이는 surprisal-based boundary에서는 자연스럽게 만족되지만 fixed window에서는 위반된다. (2) Causal Locality: semantic peak에서 주입된 update가 임의의 split point보다 엄밀히 더 우수한 제어를 제공함을 보인다. mathematical reasoning, code generation, narrative task 전반의 광범위한 실험은 AnyEdit++가 state-of-the-art baseline보다 더 우수한 성능과 robustness를 달성함을 보여주며, 효과적인 long-form knowledge editing에는 structure awareness가 중요함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62633","en":"MET-Bench: Multimodal Entity Tracking for Evaluating the Limitations of Vision-Language and Reasoning Models","ko":"MET-Bench: Vision-Language 및 Reasoning Model의 한계를 평가하는 Multimodal Entity Tracking","authors":"Vanya Cohen, Ray Mooney","pos":"#2509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=enfo9dCqRc","abs":"<p>Entity state tracking is a necessary component of world modeling that requires maintaining coherent representations of entities over time. Previous work has benchmarked entity tracking performance in purely text-based tasks. We introduce MET-Bench, a multimodal entity tracking benchmark designed to evaluate vision-language models' ability to track entity states across modalities. Using two structured domains, we assess how effectively current models integrate textual and image-based state updates. Our findings reveal a significant performance gap between text-based and image-based entity tracking. We empirically show this discrepancy primarily stems from deficits in visual reasoning rather than perception. We further show that explicit text-based reasoning strategies improve performance, yet limitations remain in long-horizon multimodal tasks. We develop a reinforcement learning method to improve performance on MET-Bench. Applying our method to open-source VLMs achieves competitive performance with advanced closed models. Our results highlight the need for improved multimodal representations and reasoning techniques to bridge the gap between textual and visual entity tracking.</p>","absKo":"<p>entity state tracking은 entity를 시간에 따라 일관되게 표현해야 하는 world modeling의 필수 구성 요소이다. 이전 연구는 순수 텍스트 기반 task에서 entity tracking 성능을 benchmark해 왔다. 우리는 vision-language model이 modality를 가로질러 entity state를 추적하는 능력을 평가하도록 설계된 multimodal entity tracking benchmark인 MET-Bench를 소개한다. 두 개의 structured domain을 사용하여, 현재 모델이 텍스트 기반 상태 업데이트와 이미지 기반 상태 업데이트를 얼마나 효과적으로 통합하는지 평가한다. 우리의 발견은 text-based entity tracking과 image-based entity tracking 사이에 상당한 성능 격차가 있음을 보여준다. 우리는 이 불일치가 주로 perception이 아니라 visual reasoning의 결함에서 비롯됨을 실증적으로 보인다. 또한 명시적인 text-based reasoning strategy가 성능을 향상시키지만, 장기 horizon의 multimodal task에서는 여전히 한계가 남아 있음을 보인다. 우리는 MET-Bench 성능을 향상시키기 위한 reinforcement learning 방법을 개발한다. 이 방법을 open-source VLM에 적용하면 advanced closed model과 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성한다. 우리의 결과는 textual entity tracking과 visual entity tracking 사이의 간극을 메우기 위해 multimodal representation과 reasoning technique의 개선이 필요함을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"62791","en":"Cognitive Fatigue in Autoregressive Transformers: Formalization and Measurement","ko":"Autoregressive Transformers의 Cognitive Fatigue: 형식화 및 측정","authors":"Riju Marwah, Ritvik Garimella, Vishal Pallagani, Atishay Jain, Michael Stewart, Amit Sheth","pos":"#2700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dE3Z3bfEzk","abs":"<p>Autoregressive language models frequently degrade during long-horizon generation, producing repetitive text, losing instruction adherence, and exhibiting unstable entropy. Despite the prevalence of these failures, practitioners lack online diagnostics to detect them in real time as they occur. We formalize this degradation as cognitive fatigue, a measurable generation-time state characterized by decay in attention to the original prompt, representational drift, and entropy miscalibration. We introduce the Fatigue Index (FI), a lightweight, model-agnostic diagnostic that aggregates these three signals under explicit axioms (monotonicity, boundedness, interpretability), enabling reliable runtime monitoring. Across nine models (1B–13B parameters), FI trajectories exhibit structured temporal dynamics, predict task degradation (AUROC = 0.95) and repetition (ρ = 0.94), and reveal non-monotonic scaling behavior: instruction-tuned models below 3B exhibit faster collapse than base models, with this trend reversing at 7B. Stress analyses further show that FI onset accelerates under longer contexts, middle-positioned evidence, and reduced numerical precision. These results establish cognitive fatigue as a coherent and measurable phenomenon, and position FI as a principled tool for runtime reliability monitoring in production LLM systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>Autoregressive language model은 장기 생성에서 자주 성능이 저하되며, 반복적인 텍스트를 생성하고 instruction adherence를 잃으며, entropy가 불안정해진다. 이러한 실패가 널리 알려져 있음에도, 실제로 발생하는 순간 이를 실시간으로 탐지할 수 있는 online diagnostic은 부족하다. 우리는 이러한 저하를 cognitive fatigue로 정식화한다. 이는 원래 prompt에 대한 attention의 감쇠, representational drift, entropy miscalibration으로 특징지어지는 측정 가능한 generation-time 상태이다. 우리는 명시적 공리(monotonicity, boundedness, interpretability) 아래에서 이 세 신호를 통합하는 경량의 model-agnostic diagnostic인 Fatigue Index(FI)를 제안하여, 신뢰할 수 있는 runtime monitoring을 가능하게 한다. 9개 모델(1B~13B parameter) 전반에서 FI 궤적은 구조화된 시간적 동역학을 보이며, task degradation(AUROC = 0.95)과 repetition(ρ = 0.94)을 예측하고, 비단조적 scaling behavior를 드러낸다: 3B 미만의 instruction-tuned model은 base model보다 더 빠르게 붕괴하며, 이 경향은 7B에서 역전된다. 추가적인 stress analysis는 더 긴 context, 중간 위치 evidence, 낮아진 numerical precision에서 FI 발생이 더 빨라짐을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 cognitive fatigue를 일관되고 측정 가능한 현상으로 정립하고, FI를 production LLM 시스템에서 runtime reliability monitoring을 위한 원리적 도구로 자리매김하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"65894","en":"Alignment Pretraining: AI Discourse Causes Self-Fulfilling (Mis)alignment","ko":"Alignment Pretraining: AI 담론이 자기충족적 (오)정렬을 야기한다","authors":"Cameron Tice, Puria Radmard, Samuel Ratnam, Andy Kim, David Africa, Kyle O&amp;#x27;Brien","pos":"#3205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=951OAanYyQ","abs":"<p>Pretraining corpora contain extensive discourse about AI systems, yet the causal influence of this discourse on downstream alignment remains poorly understood. If prevailing descriptions of AI behaviour are predominantly negative, LLMs may internalise corresponding behavioural priors, giving rise to self-fulfilling misalignment. This paper provides the first controlled study of this hypothesis by pretraining 6.9B-parameter LLMs with varying amounts of (mis)alignment discourse. We find that discussion of AI contributes to misalignment. Upsampling synthetic training documents about AI misalignment leads to a notable increase in misaligned behaviour. Conversely, upsampling documents about aligned behaviour reduces misalignment scores from 45% to 9%. We consider this evidence of self-fulfilling alignment. These effects are dampened, but persist through post-training. Our findings establish the study of how pretraining data shapes alignment priors, or alignment pretraining, as a complement to post-training. We recommend practitioners pretrain for alignment as well as capabilities.</p>"},{"id":"63950","en":"The Cylindrical Representation Hypothesis for Language Model Steering","ko":"언어 model steering을 위한 원통형 표현 가설","authors":"Lang Gao, Jinghui Zhang, Wei Liu, Fengxian Ji, Chenxi Wang, Zirui Song, Akash Ghosh, Youssef Mohamed, Preslav Nakov, Xiuying Chen","pos":"#3302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SHEiCnm2xB","abs":"<p>Steering is a widely used technique for controlling large language models, yet its effects are often unstable and hard to predict. Existing theoretical accounts are largely based on the Linear Representation Hypothesis (LRH). While LRH assumes that concepts can be orthogonalized for lossless control, this idealized mapping fails in real representations and cannot account for the observed unpredictability of steering. By relaxing LRH's orthogonality assumption while preserving linear representations, we show that overlapping concept contributions naturally yield a sample-specific axis-orthogonal structure. We formalize this as the Cylindrical Representation Hypothesis (CRH). In CRH, a \\textit{\\textbf{central axis}} captures the main difference between concept absence and presence and drives concept generation. A \\textit{\\textbf{surrounding normal plane}} controls steering sensitivity by determining how easily the axis can activate the target concept. Within this plane, only specific \\textit{\\textbf{sensitive sectors}} strongly facilitate concept activation, while other sectors can suppress or delay it. While the surrounding normal plane can be reliably identified from difference vectors, the sensitive sector cannot, introducing intrinsic uncertainty at the sector level. This uncertainty provides a principled explanation for why steering outcomes often fluctuate even when using well-aligned directions. Our experiments verify the existence of the cylindrical structure and demonstrate that CRH provides a valid and practical way to interpret model steering behavior in real settings:  \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CRH}.</p>","absKo":"<p>Steering은 대규모 언어 모델을 제어하는 데 널리 사용되는 기법이지만, 그 효과는 종종 불안정하고 예측하기 어렵다. 기존의 이론적 설명은 주로 Linear Representation Hypothesis (LRH)에 기반한다. LRH는 개념들이 손실 없는 제어를 위해 서로 직교화될 수 있다고 가정하지만, 이러한 이상화된 매핑은 실제 representation에서는 성립하지 않으며 steering의 관측된 예측 불가능성을 설명하지 못한다. 우리는 LRH의 직교성 가정은 완화하되 linear representations는 유지함으로써, 중첩된 개념 기여가 자연스럽게 sample-specific한 axis-orthogonal 구조를 낳는다는 점을 보인다. 이를 Cylindrical Representation Hypothesis (CRH)로 정식화한다. CRH에서 \\textit{\\textbf{central axis}}는 개념의 부재와 존재 사이의 주요 차이를 포착하고 개념 생성을 유도한다. \\textit{\\textbf{surrounding normal plane}}은 축이 target concept을 얼마나 쉽게 활성화할 수 있는지를 결정함으로써 steering sensitivity를 제어한다. 이 평면 내부에서는 특정 \\textit{\\textbf{sensitive sectors}}만이 concept activation을 강하게 촉진하며, 다른 sector들은 이를 억제하거나 지연시킬 수 있다. surrounding normal plane은 difference vector로부터 신뢰성 있게 식별할 수 있지만, sensitive sector는 식별할 수 없기 때문에 sector 수준에서는 본질적인 불확실성이 발생한다. 이러한 불확실성은 잘 정렬된 direction을 사용하더라도 steering 결과가 자주 변동하는 이유를 원리적으로 설명한다. 우리의 실험은 cylindrical structure의 존재를 검증하고, CRH가 실제 환경에서 model steering behavior를 해석하는 타당하고 실용적인 방법을 제공함을 보인다:  \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CRH}.</p>"},{"id":"64762","en":"Subliminal Effects in Your Data: A General Mechanism via Log-Linearity","ko":"당신의 데이터 속 잠재적 효과: Log-Linearity를 통한 일반 메커니즘","authors":"Ishaq Aden-Ali, Noah Golowich, Nika Haghtalab, Allen Liu, Ankur Moitra, Abhishek Shetty","pos":"#3510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=K9V63osRrB","abs":"<p>Training modern large language models (LLMs) has become a veritable smorgasbord of algorithms and datasets designed to elicit particular behaviors, making it critical to develop techniques to understand the effects of datasets on the model's properties. This is exacerbated by recent experiments that show datasets can transmit signals that are not directly observable from individual datapoints (Halawi et al., 2024; Betley et al., 2025b;Cloud et al., 2025; Betley et al., 2025a), posing a conceptual challenge for dataset-centric understandings of LLM training and suggesting a missing fundamental account of such phenomena. Towards understanding such effects, inspired by recent work on the linear structure of LLMs (Park et al., 2024; Golowich et al., 2025b), we uncover a general mechanism through which hidden subtexts can arise in generic datasets.  We introduce LOGIT-LINEAR SELECTION (LLS), a method that prescribes how to select subsets of a generic preference dataset to elicit a wide range of hidden effects. We apply LLS to discover subsets of real-world datasets so that models trained on them exhibit behaviors ranging from having specific preferences, to responding to prompts in a different language not present in the dataset, to taking on a different persona. Crucially, the effect persists for the selected subset, across models with varying architectures, supporting its generality and universality.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대의 large language models (LLMs)을 학습하는 일은 특정 행동을 유도하도록 설계된 알고리즘과 데이터셋의 진정한 smorgasbord가 되었으며, 이에 따라 dataset이 model의 속성에 미치는 영향을 이해하는 기법을 개발하는 것이 매우 중요해졌다. 최근 실험들은 dataset이 개별 datapoint에서는 직접 관찰되지 않는 신호를 전달할 수 있음을 보여주며(Halawi et al., 2024; Betley et al., 2025b;Cloud et al., 2025; Betley et al., 2025a), 이는 LLM training에 대한 dataset 중심적 이해에 개념적 도전을 제기하고 이러한 현상에 대한 빠진 근본적 설명이 있음을 시사한다. 이러한 효과를 이해하기 위해, LLM의 linear structure에 관한 최근 연구에서 영감을 받아(Park et al., 2024; Golowich et al., 2025b), 우리는 일반적인 dataset에서 hidden subtext가 어떻게 발생할 수 있는지에 대한 일반적 mechanism을 밝혀낸다. 우리는 LOGIT-LINEAR SELECTION (LLS)를 소개하는데, 이는 다양한 hidden effect를 유도하기 위해 일반적인 preference dataset의 subset을 어떻게 선택할지 규정하는 방법이다. 우리는 LLS를 실제 world dataset의 subset 발견에 적용하여, 이를 학습한 model이 특정 preferences를 보이거나, dataset에 존재하지 않는 다른 언어로 prompt에 응답하거나, 다른 persona를 취하는 등의 행동을 하도록 만든다. 결정적으로, 이 효과는 선택된 subset에 대해, 그리고 서로 다른 architecture를 가진 model들 전반에 걸쳐 지속되며, 그 일반성과 보편성을 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"64879","en":"IDRBench: Understanding the Capability of Large Language Models on Interdisciplinary Research","ko":"IDRBench: 학제 간 연구에 대한 대규모 언어 모델의 능력 이해","authors":"Yuanhao Shen, Daniel de Sousa, Ricardo de Andrade Nascimento, Hongyu Guo, Xiaodan Zhu","pos":"#4412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ItPwwWxu2L","abs":"<p>Innovation is a key driving force of human civilization. As the body of knowledge has grown considerably, bridging knowledge across different disciplines, where significant innovation often emerges, has become increasingly challenging. The recent advancements in machine learning models, particularly Large Language Models (LLMs), have provided effective access to extensive knowledge sources and shown impressive abilities in reasoning, rendering significant opportunities for interdisciplinary discovery. Our research aims to understand the capabilities of state-of-the-art LLMs in integrating knowledge from different fields for interdisciplinary research (IDR). To address this fundamental problem, we introduce IDRBench, a pioneering framework that includes both datasets and evaluation tasks: (1) IDR Paper Identification, (2) IDR Idea Integration, and (3) IDR Idea Recommendation.</p>","absKo":"<p>혁신은 인류 문명의 핵심 동력이다. 지식의 총량이 크게 증가함에 따라, 중요한 혁신이 자주 발생하는 서로 다른 학문 분야 간의 지식을 연결하는 일은 점점 더 어려워지고 있다. 최근 machine learning 모델, 특히 Large Language Models(LLMs)의 발전은 방대한 지식 원천에 효과적으로 접근할 수 있게 해주었고, 추론 능력에서도 인상적인 성과를 보여주어 학제 간 발견(interdisciplinary discovery)에 중요한 기회를 제공하고 있다. 우리의 연구는 학제 간 연구(IDR)를 위해 서로 다른 분야의 지식을 통합하는 데 있어 최첨단 LLM의 능력을 이해하는 것을 목표로 한다. 이 근본적인 문제에 대응하기 위해, 우리는 데이터셋과 평가 과제를 모두 포함하는 선구적 프레임워크 IDRBench를 소개한다: (1) IDR Paper Identification, (2) IDR Idea Integration, (3) IDR Idea Recommendation.</p>"},{"id":"65195","en":"RGMem: Renormalization Group–inspired Memory Evolution for Language Agents","ko":"RGMem: 언어 에이전트를 위한 재규격화군에서 영감을 받은 메모리 진화","authors":"Ao Tian, Yunfeng Lu, Xinxin Fan, Changhao Wang, Lanzhi Zhou, Yeyao Zhang, Yanfang Liu","pos":"#4605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FtvNZxhW9W","abs":"<p>Personalized and continuous interactions are critical for LLM-based conversational agents, yet finite context windows and static parametric memory hinder the modeling of long-term, cross-session user states. Existing approaches, including retrieval-augmented generation and explicit memory systems, primarily operate at the fact level, making it difficult to distill stable preferences and deep user traits from evolving and potentially conflicting dialogues.To address this challenge, we propose RGMem, a self-evolving memory framework inspired by the renormalization group (RG) perspective on multi-scale organization and emergence. RGMem models long-term conversational memory as a multi-scale evolutionary process: episodic interactions are transformed into semantic facts and user insights, which are then progressively integrated through hierarchical coarse-graining, thresholded updates, and rescaling into a dynamically evolving user profile.By explicitly separating fast-changing evidence from slow-varying traits and enabling non-linear, phase-transition-like dynamics, RGMem enables robust personalization beyond flat retrieval or static summarization. Extensive experiments on the LOCOMO and PersonaMem benchmarks demonstrate that RGMem consistently outperforms SOTA memory systems, achieving stronger cross-session continuity and improved adaptation to evolving user preferences.</p>","absKo":"<p>개인화되고 연속적인 상호작용은 LLM 기반 conversational agent에 매우 중요하지만, 유한한 context window와 정적인 parametric memory는 긴 시간에 걸친, 세션을 넘는 user state를 모델링하는 데 장애가 된다. retrieval-augmented generation과 explicit memory system을 포함한 기존 접근법은 주로 fact level에서 동작하므로, 시간이 지나며 변화하고 때로는 서로 충돌하는 대화로부터 안정적인 선호와 깊은 user trait를 추출하기가 어렵다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 multi-scale 조직과 emergence에 대한 renormalization group (RG) 관점에서 영감을 받은 self-evolving memory framework인 RGMem을 제안한다. RGMem은 장기 conversational memory를 multi-scale evolutionary process로 모델링한다: episodic interaction은 semantic fact와 user insight로 변환되고, 이후 hierarchical coarse-graining, thresholded update, rescaling을 통해 점진적으로 통합되어 동적으로 진화하는 user profile이 된다. 빠르게 변하는 evidence와 느리게 변하는 trait를 명시적으로 분리하고 non-linear하며 phase-transition-like한 dynamics를 가능하게 함으로써, RGMem은 flat retrieval이나 static summarization을 넘어선 robust personalization을 실현한다. LOCOMO와 PersonaMem benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 RGMem이 SOTA memory system을 일관되게 능가하며, 세션 간 연속성이 더 강하고 변화하는 user preference에 대한 적응도 더 우수함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63158","en":"Clipping Bottleneck: Stabilizing RLVR via Stochastic Recovery of Near-Boundary Signals","ko":"클리핑 병목: 경계 근처 신호의 확률적 복원을 통한 RLVR 안정화","authors":"Shuo Yang, Jinda Lu, Chiyu Ma, Kexin Huang, Haoming Meng, Qihui Zhang, Yuyang Liu, Bolin Ding, Guoyin Wang, Li Yuan, Jingren Zhou","pos":"#2107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZXFTvoBZ1B","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) has emerged as a central paradigm for scaling LLM reasoning, yet its optimization often suffers from training instability and suboptimal convergence. Through a systematic dissection of the GRPO-based objective, we reveal that the rigid clipping decision inherent to the hard-clipping mechanism is the primary bottleneck. Specifically, we find that many high-value signals lie in the <strong>near-boundary</strong> region just beyond the clipping threshold, and are thus discarded. Motivated by this diagnosis, we propose <strong>Near-boundary Stochastic Rescue (NSR)</strong>, a minimal, plug-and-play modification that stochastically retains these  slightly out-of-bound tokens to recover lost signals. While NSR, via stochastic sampling, can be interpreted as inducing an implicit gradient decay in expectation, our ablations reveal that its stochastic, boundary-local rescue mechanism is consistently more effective than deterministic gradient decay. Validated by extensive experiments across model sizes from 7B to 30B and both dense and MoE architectures, as a plug-and-play solution, NSR substantially improves training stability and delivers consistent gains over strong baselines such as DAPO and GSPO.</p>","absKo":"<p>Verifiable Rewards를 사용하는 Reinforcement Learning(RLVR)은 LLM 추론을 확장하는 중심 패러다임으로 부상했지만, 그 최적화는 종종 학습 불안정성과 비최적 수렴에 시달린다. GRPO 기반 objective를 체계적으로 분해해 보면, hard-clipping 메커니즘에 내재된 엄격한 clipping 결정이 주요 병목임을 알 수 있다. 구체적으로, 우리는 많은 고가치 신호가 clipping threshold 바로 바깥의 <strong>near-boundary</strong> 영역에 존재하며, 따라서 버려진다는 점을 발견했다. 이러한 진단에 기반하여, 우리는 경계에서 약간 벗어난 token을 확률적으로 보존해 손실된 신호를 회복하는 최소한의 plug-and-play 수정인 <strong>Near-boundary Stochastic Rescue(NSR)</strong>를 제안한다. NSR은 확률적 sampling을 통해 기대값 관점에서 implicit gradient decay를 유도하는 것으로 해석될 수 있지만, 우리의 ablation은 그 stochastic하고 boundary-local한 rescue 메커니즘이 deterministic gradient decay보다 일관되게 더 효과적임을 보여준다. 7B에서 30B까지의 다양한 model size와 dense 및 MoE architecture 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험으로 검증한 결과, plug-and-play solution인 NSR은 학습 안정성을 크게 향상시키고 DAPO 및 GSPO와 같은 강력한 baseline 대비 일관된 성능 향상을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60613","en":"When LLMs Encounter Open-world Graph Learning: A Fresh View on Unlabeled Data Uncertainty","ko":"LLM이 Open-world Graph Learning을 만날 때: 라벨 없는 데이터 불확실성에 대한 새로운 관점","authors":"Yanzhe Wen, Xunkai Li, Qi Zhang, Lei Zhu, Guang Zeng, Zhihan Zhang, Rong-Hua Li, Guoren Wang","pos":"#108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yUDykwou3c","abs":"<p>Recently, large language models (LLMs) have driven a systematic shift in the graph ML com- munity through the adoption of text-attributed graphs (TAGs). Although a variety of frameworks have been developed, most fail to properly ad- dress the challenge of data uncertainty in open- world environments. A representative source of such uncertainty is the limited availability of la- bels in large-scale datasets due to high annotation costs, where unlabeled nodes may belong to either known classes or novel, unknown classes. While node-level out-of-distribution detection and con- ventional open-world graph learning attempt to tackle this problem, two core limitations remain: ① Insufficient methods — existing approaches typically optimize semantics or topology in isola- tion for unknown-class rejection, failing to effec- tively integrate textual and structural information in TAGs; ② Incomplete pipelines — most stud- ies conduct only idealized analyses, such as as- suming a predefined number of unknown classes, which restricts practical utility for model updates and long-term deployment. To overcome these issues, we introduce the Open-world Graph Assis- tant (OGA), an LLM-based framework. OGA first performs unknown-class rejection via adaptive la- bel traceability (ALT), harmoniously combining semantic and topological cues, and then applies the graph label annotator (GLA) for unknown- class annotation, allowing unlabeled nodes to con- tribute to model training. In essence, OGA offers a new pipeline that fully automates the handling of unlabeled nodes in open-world environments, and we establish a systematic benchmark cover- ing four key aspects to validate its effectiveness and practicality through extensive experiments.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 large language model(LLM)은 text-attributed graph(TAG)에 대한 채택을 통해 graph ML community에 체계적인 변화를 이끌었다. 다양한 framework가 개발되었지만, 대부분은 open-world environment에서의 data uncertainty 문제를 적절히 다루지 못한다. 이러한 불확실성의 대표적 원천은 높은 annotation cost로 인해 대규모 데이터셋에서 label이 제한적으로만 존재한다는 점이며, unlabeled node는 알려진 class일 수도 있고 새로운 unknown class일 수도 있다. node-level out-of-distribution detection과 전통적인 open-world graph learning이 이 문제를 해결하려 시도하지만, 두 가지 핵심 한계가 남아 있다: ① 불충분한 방법 - 기존 접근법은 일반적으로 unknown-class rejection을 위해 semantics 또는 topology를 분리하여 최적화할 뿐, TAG에서 textual information과 structural information을 효과적으로 통합하지 못한다; ② 불완전한 pipeline - 대부분의 연구는 미리 정의된 unknown class 수를 가정하는 등 이상화된 분석만 수행하여, 모델 업데이트와 장기 배포에 대한 실용적 유용성을 제한한다. 이러한 문제를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 LLM 기반 framework인 Open-world Graph Assistant(OGA)를 제안한다. OGA는 먼저 adaptive label traceability(ALT)를 통해 semantic 및 topological cue를 조화롭게 결합하여 unknown-class rejection을 수행한 뒤, graph label annotator(GLA)를 적용해 unknown-class annotation을 수행함으로써 unlabeled node가 model training에 기여하도록 한다. 본질적으로 OGA는 open-world environment에서 unlabeled node를 완전히 자동화하여 처리하는 새로운 pipeline을 제공하며, 우리는 네 가지 핵심 측면을 포괄하는 systematic benchmark를 구축하여 대규모 실험을 통해 그 효과성과 실용성을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65958","en":"CVSearch: Empowering Multimodal LLMs with Cognitive Visual Search for High-Resolution Image Perception","ko":"CVSearch: 고해상도 이미지 지각을 위한 인지적 시각 검색으로 멀티모달 LLM 강화하기","authors":"Liupeng Li, Haoqian Kang, Zhenyu Lu, Jinpeng Wang, Bin Chen, Ke Chen, Yaowei Wang","pos":"#1212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8WA5l5tjF6","abs":"<p>High-resolution (HR) image perception presents a key bottleneck for multimodal large language models (MLLMs). While visual search offers a promising solution, existing methods struggle with the trade-off between coverage and efficiency. Visual expert-assisted search is efficient but prone to blind spots when proposals fail, whereas scan-based search guarantees coverage at the cost of computational redundancy and semantic fragmentation. To address this dilemma, we introduce CVSearch, a training-free adaptive framework that dynamically schedules search strategies via an Assess-then-Search workflow.  Specifically, CVSearch first invokes expert-assisted search when global information is insufficient, and only triggers a novel semantic-aware scanning mechanism upon failure. Distinct from rigid grid partitioning, this efficient scanning paradigm incorporates Semantic Guided Adaptive Patching to decompose images into semantically consistent regions, effectively mitigating object fragmentation. Furthermore, we devise a Dynamic Bottom-Up Search strategy driven by a Visual Complexity prior to enable efficient and precise iterative exploration of local details. Extensive experiments on HR benchmarks demonstrate that CVSearch achieves state-of-the-art accuracy while substantially improving search efficiency. Faithful code and configurations will be released.</p>"},{"id":"64228","en":"Who can we trust? LLM-as-a-jury for Comparative Assessment","ko":"누구를 신뢰할 수 있는가? 비교 평가를 위한 LLM 배심원단","authors":"Mengjie Qian, Guangzhi Sun, Mark Gales, Kate Knill","pos":"#1508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PmAKKeZj7O","abs":"Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly applied as automatic evaluators for natural language generation assessment often using pairwise comparative judgements. Existing approaches typically rely on single judges or aggregate multiple judges assuming equal reliability. In practice, LLM judges vary substantially in performance across tasks and aspects, and their judgment probabilities may be biased and inconsistent. Furthermore, human-labelled supervision for judge calibration may be unavailable. We first empirically demonstrate that inconsistencies in LLM comparison probabilities exist and show that it limits the effectiveness of direct probability-based ranking. To address this, we study the \\emph{LLM-as-a-jury} setting and propose BT-$\\sigma$, a judge-aware extension of the Bradley–Terry model that introduces a discriminator parameter for each judge to jointly infer item rankings and judge reliability from pairwise comparisons alone. Experiments on benchmark NLG evaluation datasets show that \\textit{BT-$\\sigma$} consistently outperforms averaging-based aggregation methods, and that the learned discriminator strongly correlates with independent measures of LLM evaluation performance. Further analysis reveals that \\textit{BT-$\\sigma$} can be interpreted as an unsupervised calibration mechanism that improves aggregation by modelling judge reliability.","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델(LLM)은 자연어 생성 평가를 위한 자동 평가자로 점점 더 많이 활용되고 있으며, 흔히 쌍대 비교 판단(pairwise comparative judgements)을 사용한다. 기존 접근법은 일반적으로 단일 judge에 의존하거나, 모든 judge가 동일한 신뢰도를 가진다고 가정하고 여러 judge를 집계한다. 실제로 LLM judge는 작업과 평가 측면에 따라 성능이 상당히 다르며, 그 판단 확률은 편향되고 일관되지 않을 수 있다. 더 나아가 judge 보정을 위한 human-labelled supervision을 구하지 못할 수도 있다. 우리는 먼저 LLM comparison probabilities에 불일치가 존재함을 실증적으로 보이고, 이것이 직접적인 확률 기반 ranking의 효과를 제한함을 보인다. 이를 해결하기 위해 \\emph{LLM-as-a-jury} 설정을 연구하고, 각 judge마다 discriminator parameter를 도입하여 오직 pairwise comparisons만으로 item ranking과 judge reliability를 공동으로 추론하는, Bradley–Terry 모델의 judge-aware 확장인 BT-$\\sigma$를 제안한다. benchmark NLG evaluation datasets에 대한 실험에서 \\textit{BT-$\\sigma$}는 averaging-based aggregation methods보다 일관되게 더 우수한 성능을 보이며, 학습된 discriminator는 LLM evaluation performance의 독립적 측정치와 강하게 상관됨을 확인했다. 추가 분석은 \\textit{BT-$\\sigma$}가 judge reliability를 모델링함으로써 집계를 개선하는 unsupervised calibration mechanism으로 해석될 수 있음을 보여준다."},{"id":"66786","en":"Understanding LoRA as Knowledge Memory: An Empirical Analysis","ko":"Knowledge Memory로서의 LoRA 이해하기: 실증적 분석","authors":"Seungju Back, Dongwoo Lee, Naun Kang, Taehee Lee, S. K. Hong, Youngjune Gwon, Sungjin Ahn","pos":"#1514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0MVEJk4dhE","abs":"<p>Continuous knowledge updating for pre-trained large language models (LLMs) is increasingly necessary yet remains challenging. Although inference-time methods like In-Context Learning (ICL) and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) are popular, they face constraints in context budgets, costs, and retrieval fragmentation. Departing from these context-dependent paradigms, this work investigates a parametric approach using Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) as a modular knowledge memory. Although few recent works examine this concept, the fundamental mechanics governing its capacity and composability remain largely unexplored. We bridge this gap through the first systematic empirical study mapping the design space of LoRA-based memory, ranging from characterizing storage capacity and optimizing internalization to scaling multi-module systems and evaluating long-context reasoning. Rather than proposing a single architecture, we provide practical guidance on the operational boundaries of LoRA memory. Overall, our findings position LoRA as the complementary axis of memory alongside RAG and ICL, offering distinct advantages.</p>"},{"id":"63210","en":"Sufficiency is Relative: Evaluating LLM Explanations under Model-Induced Input Distributions","ko":"충분성은 상대적이다: 모델 유발 입력 분포 하에서 LLM 설명 평가","authors":"Nhi Nguyen, Shauli Ravfogel, Rajesh Ranganath","pos":"#1604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z5BE8RFKZk","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly deployed in high-stakes domains, where free-text explanations such as chain-of-thought and post-hoc rationales are used to justify model outputs. Yet it remains unclear whether these explanations are <em>sufficient</em>, i.e., if they contain enough information to explain the model’s output-generating process. We generalize classical sufficiency from feature attributions to arbitrary explanations and prove that explanation sufficiency is inherently relative to an input distribution, which must be explicitly defined for LLM explanations. We propose using the LLM itself to generate alternative inputs conditioned on an explanation, capturing its beliefs about possible inputs. We formalize <em>self-consistent sufficiency</em> as a goal for free-text explanations and introduce an information-theoretic metric, SCSuff, that enables evaluation of free-text explanations without relying on predefined biases or shortcuts. Our experiments show that SCSuff aligns with targeted perturbation tests where applicable and demonstrate that explanation sufficiency can vary with the input distribution. We further find that SCSuff is uncorrelated with model size, accuracy, or uncertainty, suggesting that improving self-consistent sufficiency requires approaches beyond scaling or standard performance optimization.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)는 점점 더 고위험 도메인에 배치되고 있으며, chain-of-thought와 post-hoc rationale 같은 자유형 텍스트 설명이 모델 출력의 정당화를 위해 사용된다. 그러나 이러한 설명이 <em>sufficient</em>한지, 즉 모델의 출력 생성 과정을 설명할 만큼 충분한 정보를 담고 있는지는 여전히 불분명하다. 우리는 feature attribution에서의 고전적 sufficiency를 임의의 설명으로 일반화하고, explanation sufficiency가 본질적으로 input distribution에 상대적이며 LLM 설명을 위해서는 이를 명시적으로 정의해야 함을 증명한다. 우리는 LLM 자체를 사용해 설명에 조건화된 대안 입력을 생성함으로써, 가능한 입력에 대한 모델의 믿음을 포착할 것을 제안한다. 우리는 자유형 텍스트 설명을 위한 목표로 <em>self-consistent sufficiency</em>를 정식화하고, 사전에 정의된 bias나 shortcut에 의존하지 않고도 자유형 텍스트 설명을 평가할 수 있는 정보이론적 지표 SCSuff를 도입한다. 우리의 실험은 SCSuff가 해당되는 경우 targeted perturbation test와 정렬됨을 보이며, 설명의 sufficiency가 input distribution에 따라 달라질 수 있음을 보여준다. 또한 SCSuff가 모델 크기, 정확도, 혹은 uncertainty와 상관이 없음을 발견했는데, 이는 self-consistent sufficiency를 개선하려면 scaling이나 표준 성능 최적화를 넘어서는 접근이 필요함을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"63120","en":"Task-Awareness Improves LLM Generations and Uncertainty","ko":"태스크 인지가 LLM 생성과 불확실성을 개선한다","authors":"Tim Tomov, Dominik Fuchsgruber, Stephan Günnemann","pos":"#1607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Zuews4ULW6","abs":"<p>In many applications of LLMs, natural language responses often have an underlying structure such as representing discrete labels, numerical values, or graphs. Yet, existing decoding and uncertainty estimation methods operate only in language space and largely disregard structural information. We address this by modeling LLM outputs directly in a task-dependent latent structure. By equipping this structure with a dissimilarity measure, we can compute Bayes-optimal responses. These are not selected from sampled generations but are newly synthesized by combining individual responses in the latent space. Across different tasks, Bayes-optimal responses consistently outperform standard decoding methods like beam search. Moreover, quantifying uncertainty via the induced Bayesian risk captures variations in terms of the latent structure and improves alignment with output quality and correctness. Our decision-theoretic framework is applicable to any problem that admits a latent response structure and enables reliable task-aware LLM predictions.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM의 많은 응용에서 자연어 응답은 discrete label, numerical value, graph 등을 표현하는 것과 같은 underlying structure를 갖는 경우가 많다. 그러나 기존 decoding 및 uncertainty estimation 방법은 언어 공간에서만 작동하며 구조적 정보를 대부분 무시한다. 우리는 LLM output을 task-dependent latent structure에서 직접 모델링함으로써 이를 해결한다. 이 structure에 dissimilarity measure를 부여하면 Bayes-optimal response를 계산할 수 있다. 이 response는 sampled generation에서 선택되는 것이 아니라 latent space에서 개별 response를 결합하여 새롭게 합성된다. 다양한 task에서 Bayes-optimal response는 beam search와 같은 표준 decoding method보다 일관되게 더 뛰어난 성능을 보인다. 또한, induced Bayesian risk를 통해 uncertainty를 정량화하면 latent structure 측면의 변화를 포착하고, output quality 및 correctness와의 정렬을 개선한다. 우리의 decision-theoretic framework는 latent response structure를 허용하는 모든 문제에 적용 가능하며, 신뢰할 수 있는 task-aware LLM prediction을 가능하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"63272","en":"Rethinking LLM Ensembling from the Perspective of Mixture Models","ko":"혼합 모델 관점에서 LLM 앙상블 재고","authors":"Jiale Fu, Yuchu Jiang, PeiJun Wu, Chonghan Liu, Joey Tianyi Zhou, Xu Yang","pos":"#1703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YVk8EDxBWx","abs":"<p>Model ensembling is a well-established technique for improving the performance of machine learning models. Conventionally, this involves averaging the output distributions of multiple models and selecting the most probable label. This idea has been naturally extended to large language models (LLMs), yielding improved performance but incurring substantial computational cost. This inefficiency stems from directly applying conventional ensemble implementation to LLMs, which require a separate forward pass for each model to explicitly compute the ensemble distribution. In this paper, we propose the Mixture-model-like Ensemble (ME). By reinterpreting the ensemble as a mixture model, ME stochastically selects a single model at each step to generate the next token, thereby avoiding the need to explicitly compute the full ensemble distribution. ME is mathematically equivalent to sampling from the ensemble distribution, but requires invoking only one model, making it 1.78×-2.68× faster than conventional ensemble. Furthermore, this perspective connects LLM ensembling and token-level routing methods, suggesting that LLM ensembling is a special case of routing methods. Our findings open new avenues for efficient LLM ensembling and motivate further exploration of token-level routing strategies for LLMs. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Mixture-model-like-Ensemble/.</p>","absKo":"<p>Model ensembling은 machine learning model의 성능을 향상시키는 잘 확립된 기법이다. 전통적으로 이는 여러 model의 output distribution을 평균내고 가장 가능성 높은 label을 선택하는 방식으로 이루어진다. 이 아이디어는 자연스럽게 large language models (LLMs)로 확장되어 성능 향상을 가져왔지만, 상당한 computational cost를 수반한다. 이러한 비효율성은 ensemble distribution을 명시적으로 계산하기 위해 각 model마다 별도의 forward pass가 필요한 LLM에 기존 ensemble 구현을 직접 적용한 데서 비롯된다. 본 논문에서는 Mixture-model-like Ensemble (ME)을 제안한다. ensemble을 mixture model로 재해석함으로써, ME는 각 step에서 단일 model을 확률적으로 선택하여 다음 token을 생성하므로 전체 ensemble distribution을 명시적으로 계산할 필요가 없다. ME는 수학적으로 ensemble distribution에서 sampling하는 것과 동등하지만, 하나의 model만 호출하면 되므로 기존 ensemble보다 1.78×-2.68× 더 빠르다. 더 나아가 이 관점은 LLM ensembling과 token-level routing method를 연결하며, LLM ensembling이 routing method의 특수한 경우임을 시사한다. 우리의 발견은 효율적인 LLM ensembling을 위한 새로운 가능성을 열고, LLM을 위한 token-level routing strategy의 추가 탐구를 촉진한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Mixture-model-like-Ensemble/ 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"66231","en":"Predictive Prefetching for Retrieval-Augmented Generation","ko":"검색 증강 생성을 위한 예측적 Prefetching","authors":"Wuyang Zhang, Shichao Pei","pos":"#1708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5a321ueqgs","abs":"<p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) improves factual grounding in large language models but suffers from substantial latency due to synchronous retrieval. While recent work explores asynchronous retrieval, existing approaches rely on heuristic coordination between retrieval and generation and assume stable information demands during decoding that often break in complex, multi-domain settings. In this paper, we propose an advanced asynchronous retrieval framework that enables predictive prefetching aligned with evolving information needs. The framework explicitly predicts when retrieval should be triggered and what information should be retrieved using three components, a retrieval predictor, a context monitor, and a query generator, by exploiting semantic precursors in generation dynamics that emerge several tokens before uncertainty becomes critical. Experiments on multiple benchmarks demonstrate up to 43.5\\% end-to-end latency reduction and 62.4\\% improvement in time-to-first-token, while maintaining answer quality comparable to synchronous RAG baselines.</p>"},{"id":"62760","en":"Post-Training LLMs as Better Decision-Making Agents: A Regret-Minimization Approach","ko":"사후학습 LLM을 더 나은 Decision-Making Agent로: Regret-Minimization 접근","authors":"Chanwoo Park, Ziyang Chen, Asuman Ozdaglar, Kaiqing Zhang","pos":"#1709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dclUuUHjrA","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly deployed as agents for decision-making (DM) in interactive and dynamic environments. However, since they are not originally designed for DM, recent studies show that LLMs struggle in basic online DM settings. We introduce ITERATIVE REGRET-MINIMIZATION FINE-TUNING (ITERATIVE RMFT), a post-training procedure that repeatedly distills low-regret decision trajectories into the base model. Unlike prior methods that rely on distilling known algorithms or enforcing manually designed reasoning formats, our approach leverages regret as a training signal to elicit improved decision-making behavior while incorporating model-generated reasoning in natural language. Empirically, ITERATIVE RMFT improves DM performance across models, including numerical Transformers, lightweight open-weight LLMs, and the closed-weight model GPT-4o mini, while exhibiting generalization across varying horizons, action spaces, reward processes, and natural-language-described DM scenarios. Overall,  we position our approach as an initial exploration, calling for more principled and novel post-training paradigms for LLMs when it comes to addressing DM tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models(LLMs)은 점점 더 interactive하고 dynamic한 환경에서 decision-making(DM)을 위한 agent로 배치되고 있다. 그러나 원래 DM을 위해 설계된 것이 아니기 때문에, 최근 연구는 LLM이 기본적인 online DM setting에서도 어려움을 겪는다고 보여준다. 우리는 ITERATIVE REGRET-MINIMIZATION FINE-TUNING(ITERATIVE RMFT)을 소개한다. 이는 low-regret decision trajectory를 base model에 반복적으로 distill하는 post-training procedure이다. 알려진 algorithm을 distill하거나 사람이 수동으로 설계한 reasoning format을 강제하는 기존 방법과 달리, 우리의 접근은 regret을 training signal로 활용하여 개선된 decision-making behavior를 유도하면서, model-generated reasoning을 자연어로 통합한다. 실험적으로 ITERATIVE RMFT는 numerical Transformer, lightweight open-weight LLM, 그리고 closed-weight model GPT-4o mini를 포함한 여러 모델에서 DM 성능을 향상시키며, 다양한 horizon, action space, reward process, 그리고 자연어로 기술된 DM scenario 전반에 걸쳐 일반화를 보인다. 전반적으로 우리는 이 접근을 초기 탐색으로 위치시키며, DM task를 다룰 때 LLM을 위한 더 원리적이고 새로운 post-training paradigm이 필요함을 제기한다.</p>"},{"id":"60609","en":"PonderLM-2: Pretraining LLM with Latent Thoughts in Continuous Space","ko":"PonderLM-2: 연속 공간의 잠재 사고로 LLM 사전학습","authors":"Boyi Zeng, He Li, Shixiang Song, Yixuan Wang, Zitong Wang, Ziwei He, Xinbing Wang, Zhouhan Lin","pos":"#1713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yVFxjNzCQm","abs":"<p>The remarkable success of Chain-of-Thought (CoT), which enhances performance by scaling generation steps at test-time, inspires us to ask: can we leverage a similar scaling of computational steps during pretraining to improve the generation of each individual token? To address this, we propose a novel pre-training methodology: Pretraining Language Models with Latent Thoughts (PonderLM-2). Our approach pretrains a language model (LM) to first generate an intermediate latent thought—the last hidden state of the current position—which is then used as input to predict the actual subsequent token. This additional computational step enables the LM to refine its prediction within unconstrained continuous space. Our experiments demonstrate that, at an identical inference cost, a LM that generates one additional latent thought per token outperforms a standard model with double the parameters. For instance, our PonderLM-2-Pythia-1.4B, pretrained on 300B tokens from the Pile, significantly surpasses the vanilla Pythia-2.8B trained on the same data on both language modeling and a range of general downstream tasks. Furthermore, increasing the number of latent thoughts generated before each actual token—forming a chain analogous to CoT—consistently improves the model's performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>test-time에서 generation step을 확장함으로써 성능을 향상시키는 Chain-of-Thought(CoT)의 놀라운 성공은, 사전 학습 동안의 유사한 계산 단계 확장을 활용해 각 개별 token의 생성을 개선할 수 있는지에 대한 질문을 던지게 한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 새로운 pre-training 방법론인 Pretraining Language Models with Latent Thoughts (PonderLM-2)를 제안한다. 우리의 접근법은 language model(LM)이 먼저 중간 latent thought, 즉 현재 position의 마지막 hidden state를 생성하도록 사전 학습시키고, 이를 실제 다음 token을 예측하는 입력으로 사용한다. 이 추가적인 계산 단계는 LM이 제약이 없는 연속 공간 내에서 예측을 정교화할 수 있게 한다. 우리의 실험은 동일한 inference cost에서, token당 하나의 추가 latent thought를 생성하는 LM이 파라미터 수가 두 배인 표준 모델보다 더 우수한 성능을 보인다는 것을 입증한다. 예를 들어, Pile의 300B token으로 사전 학습된 PonderLM-2-Pythia-1.4B는 동일한 데이터로 학습된 vanilla Pythia-2.8B를 language modeling과 다양한 일반 downstream task에서 크게 상회한다. 더 나아가, 각 실제 token 앞에 생성되는 latent thought의 수를 늘려 CoT와 유사한 chain을 형성하면 모델 성능이 일관되게 향상된다.</p>"},{"id":"62950","en":"MEMO: Memory-Augmented Model Context Optimization for Robust Multi-Turn Multi-Agent LLM Games","ko":"MEMO: 견고한 Multi-Turn Multi-Agent LLM Games를 위한 Memory-Augmented Model Context Optimization","authors":"Yunfei Xie, Kevin Wang, Bobby Cheng, Jianzhu Yao, Zhizhou Sha, Alexander Duffy, Yihan Xi, Hongyuan Mei, Cheston Tan, Chen Wei, Pramod Viswanath, Zhangyang “Atlas” Wang","pos":"#1801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bYDjZyqKxq","abs":"<p>Multi-turn, multi-agent LLM game evaluations often exhibit substantial run-to-run variance. In long-horizon interactions, small early deviations compound across turns and are amplified by multi-agent coupling, biasing win rate estimates and destabilizing comparative rankings across repeated tournaments. Prompt choice exacerbates this by inducing different effective policies and interaction dynamics. We address both instability and underperformance in interactive games with MEMO (Memory-augmented Model context optimization), a self-play framework that treats inference-time context as an optimizable, agentic object by coupling retention and exploration. Retention maintains a persistent memory bank that distills self-play trajectories into structured insights, consolidates them via CRUD-style updates, and injects them as priors during subsequent play. Exploration performs tournament-style prompt evolution with uncertainty-aware selection via TrueSkill, and uses prioritized replay to revisit vital states for sample-efficient coverage. Across five text-based games, MEMO raises mean win rate from 24.9% → 49.5% for GPT-4o-mini and 21.7% → 44.3% for Qwen-2.5-7B-Instruct using a mere budget of 2000 self-play games per task; reducing run-to-run dispersion of end-to-end outcomes and yielding more reliable rankings under prompt stratification. These results suggest that substantial headroom in multi-agent LLM game performance and robustness can be unlocked, with MEMO achieving gains in negotiation games and imperfect-information settings, while RL remains more effective in perfect-information games. Anonymous project website available: https://79ac811fdcc9cd5679a2258a180589ef.github.io</p>","absKo":"<p>다중 턴, 다중 에이전트 LLM game 평가는 종종 실행마다 상당한 분산을 보인다. 긴 호흡의 상호작용에서는 초기에 작은 편차가 턴을 거치며 누적되고, 다중 에이전트 coupling에 의해 증폭되어 win rate 추정치를 편향시키고 반복 토너먼트 간 비교 순위를 불안정하게 만든다. prompt 선택은 서로 다른 effective policy와 interaction dynamics를 유도함으로써 이러한 문제를 더욱 악화시킨다. 우리는 retention과 exploration을 결합해 inference-time context를 최적화 가능한 agentic object로 다루는 self-play framework MEMO(Memory-augmented Model context optimization)를 통해, 상호작용 게임에서의 불안정성과 저성능을 함께 해결한다. Retention은 self-play trajectory를 구조화된 insight로 증류하는 persistent memory bank를 유지하고, CRUD 스타일 업데이트로 이를 통합한 뒤, 이후 플레이에서 prior로 주입한다. Exploration은 TrueSkill을 통한 uncertainty-aware selection과 함께 tournament-style prompt evolution을 수행하고, prioritized replay를 사용해 중요한 state를 재방문함으로써 sample-efficient coverage를 달성한다. 다섯 개의 text-based game 전반에서 MEMO는 task당 단 2000회의 self-play game 예산만으로 GPT-4o-mini의 mean win rate를 24.9% → 49.5%로, Qwen-2.5-7B-Instruct의 mean win rate를 21.7% → 44.3%로 끌어올리며, end-to-end outcome의 run-to-run dispersion을 줄이고 prompt stratification 하에서 더 신뢰할 수 있는 ranking을 제공한다. 이러한 결과는 multi-agent LLM game 성능과 강건성에 상당한 향상 여지가 있음을 시사하며, MEMO는 negotiation game과 imperfect-information setting에서 향상을 달성하는 반면, RL은 perfect-information game에서 더 효과적임을 보여준다. 익명 프로젝트 웹사이트: https://79ac811fdcc9cd5679a2258a180589ef.github.io</p>"},{"id":"62705","en":"MRPO: Magnitude-Regularized Policy Optimization via L1 Constraints","ko":"MRPO: L1 제약을 통한 Magnitude-Regularized Policy Optimization","authors":"Wei Han, Yuanxing Liu, Mingda Li, Ruiyu Xiao, Weinan Zhang, Ting Liu","pos":"#1803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=e2xQL4BWrY","abs":"Reinforcement learning (RL) for large language models (LLMs) relies on imperfect reward supervision, necessitating constraints on policy updates to prevent overfitting. Nevertheless, the widely adopted KL constraint over-penalizes actions with low reference probabilities and lacks the sparsity to discard marginal policy shifts. In contrast, the L1-norm offers a distinct mechanism that is more tolerant of low-probability actions yet strictly suppresses minor probability perturbations. Motivated by this, we propose $\\textbf{M}$agnitude-$\\textbf{R}$egularized $\\textbf{P}$olicy $\\textbf{O}$ptimization (MRPO), which enforces an L1-norm constraint on policy updates. We demonstrate that MRPO permits substantial probability boosts for low-probability actions and induces sparse updates, ensuring invariance to noise that preserves the top-ranking order. Furthermore, MRPO guarantees convergence in general RL settings and achieves a tighter approach to optimality than KL-based methods in single-step scenarios. Empirically, MRPO delivers exceptional results across diverse scenarios, notably doubling the performance gains of GRPO in preference alignment, outperforming DAPO in mathematical reasoning, and surpassing DPO in offline settings using only binary rewards.","absKo":"대규모 language model(LLM)을 위한 reinforcement learning(RL)은 불완전한 reward supervision에 의존하므로, overfitting을 방지하기 위해 policy update에 제약이 필요하다. 그러나 널리 채택된 KL constraint는 reference probability가 낮은 action에 과도한 페널티를 부과하며, 미미한 policy 변화를 제거할 만큼의 sparsity를 제공하지 못한다. 반대로 L1-norm은 낮은 확률의 action에 더 관대하면서도 작은 probability perturbation은 엄격하게 억제하는 독특한 메커니즘을 제공한다. 이러한 동기에 따라, 우리는 policy update에 L1-norm constraint를 적용하는 \\textbf{M}agnitude-\\textbf{R}egularized \\textbf{P}olicy \\textbf{O}ptimization (MRPO)을 제안한다. 우리는 MRPO가 낮은 확률의 action에 대해 상당한 probability boost를 허용하고 sparse update를 유도함으로써, top-ranking order를 보존하는 noise에 대해 invariance를 보장함을 보인다. 더 나아가 MRPO는 일반적인 RL 설정에서 수렴을 보장하며, single-step 시나리오에서 KL-based method보다 더 타이트하게 optimality에 접근한다. 실험적으로 MRPO는 다양한 시나리오에서 뛰어난 결과를 보이며, 특히 preference alignment에서 GRPO의 성능 향상을 두 배로 끌어올리고, mathematical reasoning에서 DAPO를 능가하며, binary reward만을 사용한 offline setting에서 DPO를 상회한다."},{"id":"63408","en":"One-Way Policy Optimization for Self-Evolving LLMs","ko":"자기 진화 LLM을 위한 단방향 정책 최적화","authors":"Shuo Yang, Jinda Lu, Kexin Huang, Chiyu Ma, Shaohang Wei, Yuyang Liu, Guoyin Wang, Jingren Zhou, Li Yuan","pos":"#1808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XPO9lrZ9Ge","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) has become a promising paradigm for scaling reasoning capabilities of Large Language Models (LLMs). However, the sparsity of binary verifier rewards often leads to low efficiency and optimization instability. To stabilize training, existing methods typically impose token-level constraints relative to a reference policy. We identify that such constraints penalize deviations indiscriminately; this can flip verifier-determined direction when the policy attempts to outperform the reference, thereby suppressing gains. To resolve this, we propose <strong>One-Way Policy Optimization (OWPO)</strong>, a method based on the principle of decoupling optimization direction from update magnitude. In OWPO, the verifier dictates the update direction, while the reference policy serves only to adjust the magnitude. Specifically, OWPO applies asymmetric reweighting: it performs <strong>Accelerated Alignment</strong> for Inferior deviations (where the policy lags behind the reference) and <strong>Gain Locking</strong> for Superior deviations (where the policy surpasses the reference). Furthermore, by incorporating iterative reference updates, OWPO creates a ``Ratchet Effect'' that continuously consolidates gains. Experimental results demonstrate that OWPO outperforms strong baselines, including DAPO, OPD, and MOPD, breaking the bottleneck of fixed priors to enable continuous self-evolution without reliance on external reference models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR)는 Large Language Models (LLMs)의 추론 능력을 확장하는 유망한 패러다임으로 부상했다. 그러나 이진 verifier 보상의 희소성은 종종 낮은 효율성과 최적화 불안정을 초래한다. 학습을 안정화하기 위해 기존 방법들은 보통 reference policy에 상대적인 token-level 제약을 부과한다. 우리는 이러한 제약이 편차를 무차별적으로 페널티화하며, policy가 reference를 능가하려 할 때 verifier가 정한 방향을 뒤집을 수 있어 향상을 억제한다는 점을 확인한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 업데이트 크기와 최적화 방향을 분리하는 원리에 기반한 <strong>One-Way Policy Optimization (OWPO)</strong>를 제안한다. OWPO에서 verifier는 업데이트 방향을 결정하고, reference policy는 크기 조정에만 사용된다. 구체적으로 OWPO는 비대칭 재가중치를 적용하여, 열등한 편차(즉, policy가 reference보다 뒤처지는 경우)에 대해서는 <strong>Accelerated Alignment</strong>를 수행하고, 우월한 편차(즉, policy가 reference를 앞서는 경우)에 대해서는 <strong>Gain Locking</strong>을 수행한다. 더 나아가 반복적인 reference 업데이트를 통합함으로써, OWPO는 향상을 지속적으로 공고히 하는 ``Ratchet Effect''를 만든다. 실험 결과는 OWPO가 DAPO, OPD, MOPD를 포함한 강력한 baseline들을 능가하며, 고정 prior의 병목을 돌파해 외부 reference model에 의존하지 않고도 지속적인 자기 진화를 가능하게 함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66582","en":"POLCA: Stochastic Generative Optimization with LLM","ko":"POLCA: LLM을 이용한 확률적 생성 최적화","authors":"Xuanfei Ren, Allen Nie, Tengyang Xie, Ching-An Cheng","pos":"#1810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2RKPztDfgZ","abs":"Optimizing complex systems, ranging from LLM prompts to multi-turn agents, traditionally requires labor-intensive manual iteration. We formalize this challenge as a stochastic generative optimization problem where a generative language model acts as the optimizer, guided by numerical rewards and text feedback. We introduce Prioritized Optimization with Local Contextual Aggregation (POLCA), a scalable framework designed to handle stochasticity in optimization—such as noisy feedback, sampling  minibatches, and stochastic system behaviors—while effectively managing the unconstrained expansion of solution space. POLCA maintains a priority queue to manage the exploration-exploitation tradeoff, systematically tracking candidate solutions and their evaluation histories. To enhance efficiency, we integrate an $\\varepsilon$-Net mechanism to maintain parameter diversity and an LLM Summarizer to perform meta-learning across historical trials. We evaluate our framework on diverse benchmarks, including $\\tau$-bench (agent optimization), VeriBench (code translation) and KernelBench (CUDA kernel generation). Experimental results demonstrate that POLCA achieves robust, sample and time-efficient performance, consistently outperforming state-of-the-art algorithms in both deterministic and stochastic problems."},{"id":"61203","en":"PRISM: Perception Reasoning Interleaved for Sequential Decision Making.","ko":"PRISM: 순차 의사결정을 위한 Perception Reasoning Interleaving","authors":"Mohamed Salim AISSI, Clémence Grislain, Clément Romac, Laure Soulier, Mohamed Chetouani, Olivier Sigaud, Nicolas THOME","pos":"#1811","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=shdJbVmwrp","abs":"<p>Scaling LLM-based embodied agents from text-only environments to complex multimodal settings remains a major challenge. Recent work identifies a perception–reasoning–decision gap in standalone Vision–Language Models (VLMs), which often overlook task-critical information. In this paper, we introduce PRISM, a framework that tightly couples perception (VLM) and decision (LLM) through a dynamic question–answer (DQA) pipeline. Instead of passively accepting the VLM’s description, the LLM critiques it, probes the VLM with goal-oriented questions, and synthesizes a compact image description. This closed-loop interaction yields a sharp, task-driven understanding of the scene. We evaluate PRISM on the ALFWorld and Room-to-Room (R2R) benchmarks. We show that: (1) PRISM significantly outperforms state-of-the-art image-based models, (2) our Interactive goal-oriented perception pipeline yields systematic and substantial gains, and (3) PRISM is fully automatic, eliminating the need for handcrafted questions or answers.</p>","absKo":"<p>text-only 환경에서 복잡한 multimodal 설정으로 LLM 기반 embodied agent를 확장하는 것은 여전히 큰 과제입니다. 최근 연구는 독립적인 Vision–Language Model(VLM)에서 perception–reasoning–decision 간의 간극을 지적하며, 이 모델들은 종종 task-critical information을 놓치게 됩니다. 본 논문에서는 perception(VLM)과 decision(LLM)을 dynamic question–answer(DQA) pipeline으로 긴밀하게 결합하는 PRISM을 소개합니다. VLM의 설명을 수동적으로 받아들이는 대신, LLM이 이를 비판적으로 검토하고 goal-oriented question으로 VLM을 탐색하며, 간결한 이미지 설명을 종합합니다. 이러한 closed-loop interaction은 장면에 대한 날카롭고 task-driven한 이해를 이끌어냅니다. 우리는 ALFWorld와 Room-to-Room(R2R) benchmark에서 PRISM을 평가합니다. 그 결과, (1) PRISM은 최신 image-based model을 크게 능가하고, (2) 우리의 Interactive goal-oriented perception pipeline은 체계적이고 상당한 성능 향상을 가져오며, (3) PRISM은 완전 자동화되어 수작업으로 작성된 질문이나 답변이 필요 없음을 보입니다.</p>"},{"id":"64446","en":"PlugMem: A Task-Agnostic Plugin Memory Module for LLM Agents","ko":"PlugMem: LLM 에이전트를 위한 과제 불가지론적 플러그인 메모리 모듈","authors":"Ke Yang, Zixi Chen, Xuan He, Jize Jiang, Michel Galley, Chenglong Wang, Jianfeng Gao, Jiawei Han, Chengxiang Zhai","pos":"#1813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NWKaQIKoGp","abs":"<p>Long-term memory is essential for large language model (LLM) agents operating in complex environments, yet existing memory designs are either task-specific and non-transferable, or task-agnostic but less effective due to low task-relevance and context explosion from raw memory retrieval. We propose PlugMem, a task-agnostic plugin memory module that can be attached to arbitrary LLM agents without task-specific redesign. Motivated by the fact that decision-relevant information is concentrated as abstract knowledge rather than raw experience, we draw on cognitive science to structure episodic memories into a compact, extensible knowledge-centric memory graph that explicitly represents propositional and prescriptive knowledge. This representation enables efficient memory retrieval and reasoning over task-relevant knowledge, rather than verbose raw trajectories, and departs from other graph-based methods like GraphRAG by treating knowledge as the unit of memory access and organization instead of entities or text chunks.  We evaluate PlugMem unchanged across three heterogeneous benchmarks (long-horizon conversational question answering, multi-hop knowledge retrieval, and web agent tasks). The results show that PlugMem consistently outperforms task-agnostic baselines and exceeds task-specific memory designs, while also achieving the highest information density under a unified information-theoretic analysis.</p>","absKo":"<p>장기 기억은 복잡한 환경에서 동작하는 large language model (LLM) agent에 필수적이지만, 기존 memory design은 task-specific하여 전이 가능하지 않거나, task-agnostic하지만 raw memory retrieval로 인한 낮은 task-relevance와 context explosion 때문에 효과가 떨어진다. 우리는 task-specific redesign 없이 임의의 LLM agent에 부착할 수 있는 task-agnostic plugin memory module인 PlugMem을 제안한다. 의사결정에 관련된 정보는 raw experience보다 추상화된 knowledge로 농축되어 있다는 점에 착안하여, 우리는 cognitive science를 바탕으로 episodic memory를 propositional 및 prescriptive knowledge를 명시적으로 표현하는 compact하고 확장 가능한 knowledge-centric memory graph로 구조화한다. 이 표현은 task-relevant knowledge에 대한 효율적인 memory retrieval과 reasoning을 가능하게 하며, knowledge를 entities나 text chunk가 아니라 memory access와 organization의 단위로 취급한다는 점에서 GraphRAG와 같은 다른 graph-based method와 구별된다. 우리는 세 가지 이질적인 benchmark(long-horizon conversational question answering, multi-hop knowledge retrieval, web agent task)에서 PlugMem을 변경 없이 평가했다. 결과는 PlugMem이 task-agnostic baseline을 일관되게 능가하고 task-specific memory design마저 뛰어넘으며, 통합 information-theoretic analysis 하에서 가장 높은 information density도 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65324","en":"MCCE: A Framework for Multi-LLM Collaborative Search in Discrete Spaces with Similarity-Filtered Preference Learning","ko":"MCCE: 유사도 필터링 선호 학습을 통한 이산 공간에서의 다중 LLM 협업 탐색 프레임워크","authors":"Nian Ran, Zhongzheng Li, Yue Wang, Qingsong Ran, Xiaoyuan Zhang, Shikun Feng, Richard Allmendinger, Xiaoguang Zhao","pos":"#1900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EmTlis73i8","abs":"<p>Multi-objective discrete optimization problems, such as molecular design, pose significant challenges due to their vast and unstructured combinatorial spaces. Traditional evolutionary algorithms often get trapped in local optima, while expert knowledge can provide crucial guidance for accelerating convergence. Large language models (LLMs) offer powerful priors and reasoning ability, making them natural optimizers when expert knowledge matters. However, closed-source LLMs, though strong in exploration, cannot update their parameters and thus cannot internalize experience. Conversely, smaller open models can be continually fine-tuned but lack broad knowledge and reasoning strength. We introduce Multi-LLM Collaborative Co-evolution (MCCE), a hybrid framework that unites a frozen closed-source LLM with a lightweight trainable model. The system maintains a trajectory memory of past search processes; the small model is progressively refined via reinforcement learning, with the two models jointly supporting and complementing each other in global exploration. Unlike model distillation, this process enhances the capabilities of both models through mutual inspiration. Experiments on multi-objective drug design benchmarks show that MCCE achieves state-of-the-art Pareto front quality and consistently outperforms baselines. These results highlight a new paradigm for enabling continual evolution in hybrid LLM systems, combining knowledge-driven exploration with experience-driven learning.The code of MCCE is available on https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MCCE_Anonymous-1F92</p>"},{"id":"61231","en":"Leak@$k$: Unlearning Does Not Make LLMs Forget Under Probabilistic Decoding","ko":"Leak@$k$: Unlearning은 확률적 Decoding에서 LLM을 잊게 만들지 못한다","authors":"Hadi Reisizadeh, Jiajun Ruan, Yiwei Chen, Soumyadeep Pal, Sijia Liu, Mingyi Hong","pos":"#1904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sREOiWynXf","abs":"Unlearning in large language models (LLMs) is critical for regulatory compliance and for building ethical generative AI systems that avoid producing private, toxic, illegal, or copyrighted content. Despite rapid progress, in this work we show that \\textit{almost all} existing unlearning methods fail to achieve true forgetting in practice. Specifically, while evaluations of these `unlearned' models under deterministic (greedy) decoding often suggest successful knowledge removal using standard benchmarks (as has been done in the literature), we show that sensitive information reliably resurfaces when models are sampled with standard probabilistic decoding. To rigorously capture this vulnerability, we introduce \\texttt{leak@$k$}, a new meta-evaluation metric that quantifies the likelihood of forgotten knowledge reappearing when generating $k$ samples from the model under realistic decoding strategies. Using three widely adopted benchmarks, TOFU, MUSE, and WMDP, we conduct the first large-scale, systematic study of unlearning reliability using our newly defined \\texttt{leak@$k$} metric. Our findings demonstrate that knowledge leakage persists across methods and tasks, underscoring that current state-of-the-art unlearning techniques provide only limited forgetting and highlighting the urgent need for more robust approaches to LLM unlearning. We propose an algorithm, termed Robust Unlearning under LEak@$k$ metric (\\texttt{RULE}), which serves as an initial step toward addressing this concern. We demonstrate that \\texttt{RULE} provides an unlearned model for TOFU benchmark with no information leakage for a large number of generation samples.","absKo":"대형 language model (LLM)에서의 unlearning은 규제 준수와 private, toxic, illegal, 또는 copyrighted content를 생성하지 않는 윤리적 generative AI system 구축에 중요하다. 빠른 진전에도 불구하고, 본 연구에서는 기존 unlearning 방법의 \\textit{거의 모두}가 실제로는 진정한 forgetting을 달성하지 못함을 보인다. 구체적으로, 표준 benchmark를 사용하여 deterministic (greedy) decoding 하에서 이들 `unlearned' model을 평가하면 문헌에서 수행되어 온 것처럼 지식 제거가 성공한 것처럼 보이는 경우가 많지만, 표준 probabilistic decoding으로 모델을 샘플링하면 민감한 정보가 신뢰성 있게 다시 나타남을 보인다. 이러한 취약성을 엄밀하게 포착하기 위해, 우리는 실제적인 decoding strategy에서 모델로부터 $k$개의 sample을 생성할 때 잊힌 지식이 다시 나타날 가능성을 정량화하는 새로운 meta-evaluation metric인 \\texttt{leak@$k$}를 도입한다. 널리 사용되는 세 가지 benchmark인 TOFU, MUSE, WMDP를 사용하여, 우리는 새로 정의한 \\texttt{leak@$k$} metric을 이용한 unlearning reliability에 대한 최초의 대규모 체계적 연구를 수행한다. 우리의 발견은 knowledge leakage가 방법과 task 전반에 걸쳐 지속됨을 보여주며, 현재의 state-of-the-art unlearning 기술이 제한적인 forgetting만을 제공함을 강조하고 LLM unlearning을 위한 더 견고한 접근법의 시급한 필요성을 부각한다. 우리는 Robust Unlearning under LEak@$k$ metric(\\texttt{RULE})이라 불리는 algorithm을 제안하며, 이는 이 문제를 해결하기 위한 초기 단계 역할을 한다. 우리는 \\texttt{RULE}이 TOFU benchmark에서 대량의 generation sample에 대해 information leakage가 없는 unlearned model을 제공함을 보인다."},{"id":"66483","en":"Hierarchical Abstract Tree for Cross-Document Retrieval Augmented Generation","ko":"교차 문서 검색 증강 생성을 위한 계층적 추상 트리","authors":"Ziwen Zhao, Menglin Yang","pos":"#1911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3Hea2WFhPW","abs":"Retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) enhances large language models with external knowledge, and tree-based RAG organizes documents into hierarchical indexes to support queries at multiple granularities. However, existing Tree-RAG methods designed for single-document retrieval face critical challenges in scaling to cross-document multi-hop questions: *(1) poor distribution adaptability*, where $k$-means clustering introduces noise due to rigid distribution assumptions; *(2) structural isolation*, as tree indexes lack explicit cross-document connections; and *(3) coarse abstraction*, which obscures fine-grained details. To address these limitations, we propose **$\\Psi$-RAG**, a tree-RAG framework with two key components. *First*, a hierarchical abstract tree index built through an iterative \"merging and collapse\" process that adapts to data distributions without a priori assumption. *Second*, a multi-granular retrieval agent that intelligently interacts with the knowledge base with reorganized queries and an agent-powered hybrid retriever. $\\Psi$-RAG supports diverse tasks from token-level question answering to document-level summarization. On cross-document multi-hop QA benchmarks, it outperforms RAPTOR by 25.9\\% and HippoRAG 2 by 7.4\\% in average F1 score. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Psi-RAG-7831/."},{"id":"60634","en":"GeoAlign: Geometric Rollout Curation for Robust LLM Reinforcement Learning","ko":"GeoAlign: 강건한 LLM Reinforcement Learning을 위한 기하학적 Rollout 큐레이션","authors":"Ting Zhou, Zhenqing Ling, Yiyang Zhao, Ying Shen, Daoyuan Chen","pos":"#1914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yFvTNRTyna","abs":"<p>Online reinforcement learning is widely used to align large language models (LLMs) with reward signals, yet training can be unstable under noisy or misspecified rewards. We identify a failure mode we call directional inconsistency: within a batch, a small set of high-reward rollouts induces representation-space preference directions that sharply disagree with the batch majority, resulting in high-variance and destabilizing updates. We propose GeoAlign, a lightweight plug-in for rollout curation in iterative policy optimization. GeoAlign (i) forms within-prompt preference pairs, (ii) learns an online projector on per-rollout hidden states to concentrate reward-ordered displacement directions, and (iii) detects directionally inconsistent rollouts via their angular deviation from a batch consensus prototype and rectifies them with within-prompt stable alternatives. GeoAlign is forward-pass only and adds negligible overhead. Across dialogue alignment with a learned reward model and mathematical reasoning with binary verified rewards, GeoAlign improves final performance and reduces training oscillation, outperforming PF-PPO, PAR, PODS, and Seed-GRPO. These results suggest latent directional consensus as an effective reliability signal for online LLM RL.</p>","absKo":"<p>Online reinforcement learning은 large language model(LLM)을 reward signal에 맞추는 데 널리 사용되지만, noisy하거나 misspecified된 reward 하에서는 training이 불안정해질 수 있다. 우리는 directional inconsistency라고 부르는 failure mode를 식별한다. 이는 batch 내에서 소수의 high-reward rollout이 representation space에서의 preference direction을 형성하는데, 이 방향이 batch majority와 크게 어긋나 high-variance와 destabilizing update를 유발하는 현상이다. 우리는 iterative policy optimization에서 rollout curation을 위한 lightweight plug-in인 GeoAlign을 제안한다. GeoAlign은 (i) prompt 내 preference pair를 구성하고, (ii) per-rollout hidden state 위에서 online projector를 학습해 reward-ordered displacement direction을 응축하며, (iii) batch consensus prototype으로부터의 angular deviation을 이용해 directionally inconsistent rollout을 탐지한 뒤 prompt 내 stable alternative로 교정한다. GeoAlign은 forward-pass only이며 오버헤드가 매우 작다. learned reward model을 사용하는 dialogue alignment와 binary verified reward를 사용하는 mathematical reasoning 전반에서, GeoAlign은 최종 성능을 향상시키고 training oscillation을 줄이며 PF-PPO, PAR, PODS, Seed-GRPO를 능가한다. 이러한 결과는 latent directional consensus가 online LLM RL의 효과적인 reliability signal임을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61324","en":"DRIFT: Decoupled Rollouts and Importance-Weighted Fine-Tuning for Efficient Multi-Turn Optimization","ko":"DRIFT: 효율적 Multi-Turn 최적화를 위한 분리된 Rollout과 Importance-Weighted Fine-Tuning","authors":"Jian Mu, Tianyi Lin, Chengwei Qin, Zhongxiang Dai, Yao Shu","pos":"#2000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rJOrgGdz9E","abs":"<p>Large language models are increasingly deployed in multi-turn interactive settings where users or environments can iteratively provide lightweight feedback. Unfortunately, optimizing such behavior presents a sharp dilemma in practice: online reinforcement learning is able to effectively address multi-turn dynamics but is prohibitively expensive due to the cost of generating full correction trajectories at every update, whereas offline supervised fine-tuning (SFT) is efficient but suffers from distribution shift and behavioral collapse. To this end, we novelly propose DRIFT (Decoupled Rollouts and Importance-Weighted Fine-Tuning), a framework that operationalizes the theoretical insight that the KL-regularized RL objective is mathematically equivalent to importance-weighted supervised learning. DRIFT decouples rollout from optimization by sampling offline interaction trajectories from a fixed reference policy, deriving return-based importance weights, and optimizing the policy via weighted SFT on the resulting dataset. Empirically, we demonstrate that DRIFT matches or exceeds the performance of multi-turn reinforcement learning baselines while maintaining the training efficiency and simplicity of standard supervised fine-tuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>large language model은 사용자가 또는 환경이 반복적으로 가벼운 feedback을 제공하는 multi-turn interactive setting에 점점 더 많이 배치되고 있다. 그러나 이러한 행동을 최적화하는 것은 실무에서 날카로운 딜레마를 제기한다. online reinforcement learning은 multi-turn dynamics를 효과적으로 다룰 수 있지만, 매 update마다 완전한 correction trajectory를 생성해야 하므로 비용이 지나치게 크다. 반면 offline supervised fine-tuning (SFT)은 효율적이지만 distribution shift와 behavioral collapse에 취약하다. 이를 위해 우리는 DRIFT (Decoupled Rollouts and Importance-Weighted Fine-Tuning)를 새롭게 제안한다. 이는 KL-regularized RL objective가 수학적으로 importance-weighted supervised learning과 동등하다는 이론적 통찰을 실제로 구현하는 framework이다. DRIFT는 고정된 reference policy에서 offline interaction trajectory를 sampling하여 rollout과 optimization을 분리하고, return-based importance weight를 도출한 뒤, 생성된 dataset에 대해 weighted SFT로 policy를 최적화한다. 실험적으로, DRIFT는 multi-turn reinforcement learning baseline과 동등하거나 그 이상의 성능을 보이면서도 standard supervised fine-tuning의 training efficiency와 단순성을 유지함을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66645","en":"EngiAgent: Fully Connected Coordination of LLM Agents for Solving Open-ended Engineering Problems with Feasible Solutions","ko":"EngiAgent: 실현 가능한 해를 갖는 개방형 공학 문제 해결을 위한 LLM 에이전트의 완전 연결 조정","authors":"Xiyuan Zhou, Ruixi Zou, Xinlei Wang, Yuheng Cheng, Yan Xu, Junhua Zhao, Jinjin Gu","pos":"#2005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1p67QsYnbv","abs":"<p>Engineering problem solving is central to real-world decision-making, requiring mathematical formulations that not only represent complex problems but also produce feasible solutions under data and physical constraints. Unlike mathematical problem solving, which operates on predefined formulations, engineering tasks demand open-ended analysis, feasibility-driven modeling, and iterative refinement. Although large language models (LLMs) have shown strong capabilities in reasoning and code generation, they often fail to ensure feasibility, which limits their applicability to engineering problem solving. To address this challenge, we propose EngiAgent, a multi-agent system with a fully connected coordinator that simulates expert workflows through specialized agents for problem analysis, modeling, verification, solving, and solution evaluation. The fully connected coordinator enables flexible feedback routing, overcoming the rigidity of prior pipeline-based reflection methods and ensuring feasibility at every stage of the process. This design not only improves robustness to diverse failure cases such as data extraction errors, constraint inconsistencies, and solver failures, but also enhances the overall quality of problem solving. Empirical results across four representative domains demonstrate that EngiAgent achieves substantial improvements in feasibility compared to prior approaches, establishing a new paradigm for feasibility-oriented engineering problem solving with LLMs. Our source code and data are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EngiAgent-1C8A.</p>"},{"id":"60948","en":"Knapsack RL: Unlocking Exploration of LLMs via Optimizing Budget Allocation","ko":"Knapsack RL: Budget Allocation 최적화를 통한 LLM Exploration 해제","authors":"Ziniu Li, Congliang Chen, Tianyun Yang, Tian Ding, Ruoyu Sun, Ge Zhang, Wenhao Huang, Zhiquan Luo","pos":"#204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v70fTOqer2","abs":"Large Language Models (LLMs) can improve via reinforcement learning by generating trajectories to discover better solutions. This exploration process represents an investment of finite GPU compute to obtain learning signals. However, current methods typically allocate a small, uniform budget to every task, which is inefficient and ineffective: easy tasks consistently succeed while difficult tasks consistently fail. For policy optimization algorithms such as Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO), both edge cases produce zero gradients, resulting in wasted computation. We address this by reframing exploration budget allocation as a resource optimization problem. Viewing each task's exploration as an `\"item'' with a distinct \"learning value'' and \"computational cost'', we establish a connection to the classical knapsack problem and derive an optimal assignment rule. When applied to GRPO, our method increases the ratio of effective gradients by 40\\%. As a computational \"free lunch'', it enables substantially larger budgets (e.g., 93) for challenging tasks—allocations that would be expensive under a uniform allocation framework. These efficiency gains translate to meaningful improvements on mathematical reasoning benchmarks, with average gains of 2--4 points and peak gains of 9 points. Notably, achieving comparable performance with traditional homogeneous allocation would require approximately $2\\times$ the computational resources.","absKo":"Large Language Models (LLMs)는 더 나은 해를 발견하기 위해 trajectory를 생성하는 reinforcement learning을 통해 성능을 향상시킬 수 있다. 이 exploration 과정은 학습 신호를 얻기 위해 유한한 GPU compute를 투자하는 것을 의미한다. 그러나 현재 방법은 보통 모든 task에 작고 균일한 budget을 할당하는데, 이는 비효율적이고 비효과적이다. 쉬운 task는 일관되게 성공하고 어려운 task는 일관되게 실패하기 때문이다. Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) 같은 policy optimization algorithm에서는 두 극단 모두 zero gradient를 만들어 계산을 낭비하게 된다. 우리는 이를 exploration budget allocation을 resource optimization problem으로 재정식화하여 해결한다. 각 task의 exploration을 서로 다른 'learning value'와 'computational cost'를 가진 `item`으로 보고, 고전적인 knapsack problem과의 연결을 확립한 뒤 최적 배정 규칙을 도출한다. GRPO에 적용하면 우리의 방법은 effective gradient의 비율을 40\\% 증가시킨다. 계산 관점에서의 'free lunch'로서, 이는 어려운 task에 대해 훨씬 더 큰 budget(예: 93)도 가능하게 한다. 균일한 할당 framework에서는 이런 배정이 매우 비쌀 것이다. 이러한 효율성 향상은 수학적 추론 benchmark에서 의미 있는 개선으로 이어지며, 평균 2--4점, 최대 9점의 향상을 보인다. 주목할 점은, 전통적인 homogeneous allocation으로 비슷한 성능을 달성하려면 대략 $2\\times$의 계산 자원이 필요하다는 것이다."},{"id":"62470","en":"D$^3$: Dynamic Directional Graph-Constrained Data Scheduling for LLM Training","ko":"D$^3$: LLM Training을 위한 Dynamic Directional Graph-Constrained Data Scheduling","authors":"Yuanjian Xu, Jianing Hao, Guang Zhang, Zhong Li","pos":"#2102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gLBxxIwzkB","abs":"<p>Training data plays a central role in large language model (LLM) optimization, motivating extensive research on data scheduling strategies. Most prior work focuses on data selection and implicitly assumes that, once the training subset is fixed, the order in which data are presented is interchangeable. However, this assumption is routinely violated in practice. Despite empirical evidence of order sensitivity, existing studies neither provide a principled explanation of the underlying optimization dynamics nor offer an efficient solution. In this work, we first answer the fundamental question of why training order matters in LLM optimization. We then demonstrate that commonly used empirical data ordering heuristics are suboptimal from an optimization perspective. To resolve this, we propose xxx, a data scheduling framework grounded in gradient interactions between samples, where training dependencies are modeled as a graph that explicitly constrains valid training orders. Our approach is theoretically motivated and yields consistent empirical improvements over existing data scheduling methods across multiple settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>training data는 large language model(LLM) optimization에서 중심적인 역할을 하며, 이에 따라 data scheduling 전략에 대한 광범위한 연구를 촉진해왔다. 대부분의 기존 연구는 data selection에 초점을 맞추고, training subset이 한 번 고정되면 데이터를 제시하는 순서는 서로 바꿔도 된다고 암묵적으로 가정한다. 그러나 실제로 이 가정은 흔히 위배된다. 순서 민감성에 대한 경험적 증거에도 불구하고, 기존 연구는 그 underlying optimization dynamics에 대한 원리적 설명도 제공하지 못했고 효율적인 해법도 제시하지 못했다. 본 연구에서는 먼저 LLM optimization에서 training order가 왜 중요한지에 대한 근본적인 질문에 답한다. 이어서 흔히 사용되는 경험적 data ordering heuristic이 optimization 관점에서 suboptimal함을 보인다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 샘플 간 gradient interaction에 기반한 data scheduling framework인 xxx를 제안하며, training dependency를 graph로 모델링하여 유효한 training order를 명시적으로 제약한다. 우리의 접근법은 이론적으로 동기 부여되었고, 여러 설정에서 기존 data scheduling 방법들보다 일관된 경험적 개선을 이끌어낸다.</p>"},{"id":"63489","en":"CSPLoRA: Confidence-Guided Structure Planning for Low-Rank Adaptation","ko":"CSPLoRA: Low-Rank Adaptation을 위한 신뢰도 유도 구조 계획","authors":"Huiming Ding, Xiaochen Li, Jianhui Ma, Xu An, Yihui Yang, Zhenyu Tan","pos":"#2110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WkARznT46l","abs":"<p>Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) has become the de facto paradigm for parameter-efficient fine-tuning, with its effectiveness critically influenced by rank allocation across modules. However, existing approaches face a fundamental dilemma: uniform allocation ignores module heterogeneity, while adaptive methods introduce expensive training overhead or lack reusability across configurations. We propose \\textbf{CSPLoRA} (Confidence-guided Structural Planning for LoRA), a decoupled framework that reweights probe samples by prediction uncertainty to obtain higher-fidelity module importance estimates. The key insight is that hard samples---those the model struggles with---provide more informative gradient signals for identifying critical modules than easy samples. Combined with scale-invariant allocation, our method produces reusable structural priors that transfer across different rank budgets and LoRA backends, enabling \"probe once, deploy everywhere.\" Experiments on GLUE, commonsense reasoning, and arithmetic tasks show that CSPLoRA consistently improves over uniform LoRA (+1.25 points on LLaMA-2-7B commonsense reasoning) while maintaining comparable parameters, with the same structure transferring directly to other LoRA variants.</p>","absKo":"<p>Low-Rank Adaptation(LoRA)은 parameter-efficient fine-tuning의 사실상 표준 패러다임이 되었으며, 그 효과는 module 전반에 걸친 rank allocation에 의해 결정적으로 좌우된다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 근본적인 딜레마에 직면해 있다. uniform allocation은 module heterogeneity를 무시하고, adaptive method는 큰 training overhead를 유발하거나 구성 간 재사용성이 부족하다. 우리는 prediction uncertainty로 probe sample을 재가중하여 더 높은 fidelity의 module 중요도 추정을 얻는 분리형 프레임워크인 \\textbf{CSPLoRA}(Confidence-guided Structural Planning for LoRA)를 제안한다. 핵심 통찰은 모델이 어려움을 겪는 hard sample이 easy sample보다 중요한 module을 식별하는 데 더 정보량이 큰 gradient signal을 제공한다는 점이다. scale-invariant allocation과 결합된 우리의 방법은 서로 다른 rank budget과 LoRA backend에 걸쳐 전이 가능한 재사용 가능한 structural prior를 생성하여, \"probe once, deploy everywhere\"를 가능하게 한다. GLUE, commonsense reasoning, arithmetic task에서의 실험은 CSPLoRA가 uniform LoRA보다 일관되게 향상됨을 보여준다(LLaMA-2-7B commonsense reasoning에서 +1.25 point). 또한 동일한 구조를 다른 LoRA variant에도 직접 전이할 수 있으며, 파라미터 규모는 비슷하게 유지된다.</p>"},{"id":"65407","en":"A Critical Look at Targeted Instruction Selection: Disentangling What Matters (and What Doesn’t)","ko":"표적 지시문 선택에 대한 비판적 고찰: 중요한 것(그리고 그렇지 않은 것) 분리하기","authors":"Nihal Nayak, Paula Rodriguez-Diaz, Neha Hulkund, Sara Beery, David Alvarez-Melis","pos":"#2208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Dy5GeCd003","abs":"<p>Instruction fine-tuning of large language models (LLMs) often involves selecting a subset of instruction training data from a large candidate pool, using a small query set from the target task. Despite growing interest, the literature on targeted instruction selection remains fragmented and opaque: methods vary widely in selection budgets, often omit zero-shot baselines, and frequently entangle the contributions of key components. As a result, practitioners lack actionable guidance on selecting instructions for their target tasks. In this work, we aim to bring clarity to this landscape by disentangling and systematically analyzing the two core ingredients: data representation and selection algorithms. Our framework enables controlled comparisons across models, tasks, and budgets. We find that only gradient-based data representations choose subsets whose similarity to the query consistently predicts performance across datasets and models. While no single method dominates, gradient-based representations paired with a greedy round-robin selection algorithm tend to perform best on average at low budgets, but these benefits diminish at larger budgets. Finally, we unify several existing selection algorithms as forms of approximate distance minimization between the selected subset and the query set, and support this view with new generalization bounds. More broadly, our findings provide critical insights and a foundation for more principled data selection in LLM fine-tuning.</p>"},{"id":"61643","en":"Breaking the Self-Confirming Loop: Diagnosing and Mitigating Systemic Reward Bias in Self-Rewarding RL","ko":"자기확증 루프 깨기: Self-Rewarding RL의 시스템적 Reward Bias 진단과 완화","authors":"Chuyi Tan, Peiwen Yuan, Xinglin Wang, Yiwei Li, Shaoxiong Feng, Yueqi Zhang, Jiayi Shi, Ji Zhang, Boyuan Pan, Yao Hu, Kan Li","pos":"#300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oAagVd30Fn","abs":"Reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards (RLVR) efficiently scales the reasoning ability of large language models but is bottlenecked by scarce labeled data. Reinforcement learning with intrinsic rewards (RLIR) offers a scalable alternative via self-rewarding, yet often suffers from instability and inferior performance. We trace this gap to a systemic bias in confidence-coupled self-rewarding: the model tends to over-reward high-confidence mistakes, forming a \\textbf{self-confirming loop}. We quantify this feedback-loop bias with three metrics: reward noise magnitude ($\\rho_{\\text{noise}}$), policy–reward coupling ($\\rho_{\\text{selfbias}}$), and over-/under-reward skew ($\\rho_{\\text{symbias}}$). Our analyses show a compounding effect where strong coupling amplifies confidence-conditioned errors and drives a drift toward over-reward, leading to instability and a lower performance ceiling. To mitigate this, we propose reinforcement learning with ensembled rewards (\\textbf{RLER}), which aggregates diverse models with adaptive reward interpolation and disagreement-aware rollout selection to reduce coupling and suppress over-reward drift. Extensive experiments show that RLER improves by 13.6\\% over the best RLIR baseline and is within 3.6\\% of RLVR, while exhibiting stable scaling on unlabeled samples.","absKo":"verifiable reward를 사용하는 reinforcement learning (RLVR)은 large language model의 reasoning 능력을 효율적으로 확장하지만, 희소한 labeled data 때문에 병목이 발생한다. intrinsic reward를 사용하는 reinforcement learning (RLIR)은 self-rewarding을 통한 확장 가능한 대안이지만, 종종 불안정성과 낮은 성능에 시달린다. 우리는 이 격차를 confidence-coupled self-rewarding에 존재하는 시스템적 편향에서 추적한다. 모델은 높은 confidence의 실수를 과도하게 보상하는 경향이 있으며, 이는 \\textbf{self-confirming loop}를 형성한다. 우리는 세 가지 metric, 즉 reward noise magnitude ($\\rho_{\\text{noise}}$), policy–reward coupling ($\\rho_{\\text{selfbias}}$), 그리고 over-/under-reward skew ($\\rho_{\\text{symbias}}$)로 이 feedback-loop bias를 정량화한다. 우리의 분석은 강한 coupling이 confidence-conditioned error를 증폭시키고 over-reward 방향으로의 drift를 유도하여 불안정성과 더 낮은 성능 상한을 초래하는 누적 효과를 보여준다. 이를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 다양한 model을 adaptive reward interpolation과 disagreement-aware rollout selection으로 집계하여 coupling을 줄이고 over-reward drift를 억제하는 reinforcement learning with ensembled rewards (\\textbf{RLER})를 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 RLER이 최상의 RLIR baseline 대비 13.6\\% 향상되며 RLVR과는 3.6\\% 이내의 성능 차이를 보이고, unlabeled sample에서 안정적인 scaling을 보임을 보여준다."},{"id":"62219","en":"MASPO: Joint Prompt Optimization for LLM-based Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"MASPO: LLM 기반 Multi-Agent Systems의 공동 프롬프트 최적화","authors":"Zhexuan Wang, Xuebo Liu, Li Wang, Zifei Shan, Yutong Wang, Zhenxi Song, Min zhang","pos":"#303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iZrp2P55ie","abs":"<p>Large language model (LLM)-based Multi-agent systems (MAS) have shown promise in tackling complex collaborative tasks, where agents are typically orchestrated via role-specific prompts. While the quality of these prompts is pivotal, jointly optimizing them across interacting agents remains a non-trivial challenge, primarily due to the misalignment between local agent objectives and holistic system goals. To address this, we introduce MASPO, a novel framework designed to automatically and iteratively refine prompts across the entire system. A core innovation of MASPO is its joint evaluation mechanism, which assesses prompts not merely by their local validity, but by their capacity to facilitate downstream success for successor agents. This effectively bridges the gap between local interactions and global outcomes without relying on ground-truth labels. Furthermore, MASPO employs a data-driven evolutionary beam search to efficiently navigate the high-dimensional prompt space. Extensive empirical evaluations across 6 diverse tasks demonstrate that MASPO consistently outperforms state-of-the-art prompt optimization methods, achieving an average accuracy improvement of 2.9. We release our code at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MASPO-8296.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM) 기반 Multi-agent systems (MAS)는 복잡한 협업 과제를 해결하는 데 유망함을 보여 왔으며, 여기서 agent는 일반적으로 role-specific prompt를 통해 orchestrate된다. 이러한 prompt의 품질은 매우 중요하지만, 상호작용하는 agent 전반에 걸쳐 이를 공동 최적화하는 것은 로컬 agent 목표와 전체 시스템 목표의 불일치 때문에 본질적으로 쉽지 않다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 시스템 전체의 prompt를 자동으로 그리고 반복적으로 정제하도록 설계된 새로운 framework인 MASPO를 제안한다. MASPO의 핵심 혁신은 joint evaluation mechanism으로, prompt를 단순히 local validity로만 평가하지 않고 successor agent의 downstream success를 촉진하는 능력으로 평가한다. 이는 ground-truth label에 의존하지 않고도 로컬 상호작용과 글로벌 결과 사이의 간극을 효과적으로 메운다. 또한 MASPO는 data-driven evolutionary beam search를 사용해 고차원 prompt space를 효율적으로 탐색한다. 6개의 다양한 task에 걸친 광범위한 실증 평가는 MASPO가 state-of-the-art prompt optimization 방법을 일관되게 능가하며, 평균 2.9의 accuracy 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MASPO-8296 에서 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"64153","en":"Experience Augmented Policy Optimization for LLM Reasoning","ko":"LLM 추론을 위한 경험 증강 정책 최적화","authors":"Jinda Lu, Kexin Huang, Junkang Wu, Shuo Yang, Jinghan Li, Chiyu Ma, Shaohang Wei, Xiang Wang, Guoyin Wang, Jingren Zhou","pos":"#3505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QOoQ0Bo2ls","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) is a powerful paradigm for improving the reasoning capabilities of large language models (LLMs). However, existing RLVR methods typically rely on on-policy optimization from scratch, resulting in high sampling costs and inefficient utilization of accumulated experience. As model capabilities and policy behaviors evolve during training, recent attempts to reuse experience via fixed reasoning trajectories further suffer from policy mismatch. Motivated by these limitations, we argue that experience in RLVR should not be reused as fixed reasoning trajectories, but instead expressed in a policy-adaptive manner. In this work, we propose Experience-Augmented Policy Optimization (EAPO), which leverages a prior RL-optimized policy as an action-level experience prior and selectively injects experience at critical decision points during rollout. To ensure stable and unbiased learning from experience-augmented rollouts, EAPO further incorporates an adapted importance sampling scheme. Experiments on using Qwen-2.5-math 7b and Qwen-3-8B on five different benchmarks demonstrate that EAPO consistently improves reasoning performance over state-of-the-art RLVR methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>Verifiable Rewards를 이용한 Reinforcement Learning(RLVR)은 LLMs(large language models)의 추론 능력을 향상시키는 강력한 패러다임이다. 그러나 기존 RLVR 방법은 일반적으로 처음부터 on-policy optimization에 의존하므로, 높은 sampling 비용과 누적된 경험의 비효율적인 활용을 초래한다. 학습 중 모델 능력과 policy behavior가 진화함에 따라, 고정된 reasoning trajectory를 통해 experience를 재사용하려는 최근 시도들은 policy mismatch 문제를 겪는다. 이러한 한계에서 출발하여, 우리는 RLVR에서의 경험은 고정된 reasoning trajectory로 재사용되어서는 안 되며, 대신 policy-adaptive한 방식으로 표현되어야 한다고 주장한다. 본 연구에서는 prior RL-optimized policy를 action-level experience prior로 활용하고, rollout 동안 중요한 decision point에만 경험을 선택적으로 주입하는 Experience-Augmented Policy Optimization(EAPO)을 제안한다. experience-augmented rollout으로부터 안정적이고 편향 없는 학습을 보장하기 위해, EAPO는 적응된 importance sampling scheme도 함께 통합한다. Qwen-2.5-math 7b와 Qwen-3-8B를 사용한 다섯 개 benchmark 실험은 EAPO가 최신 RLVR 방법들보다 추론 성능을 일관되게 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66092","en":"FutureOmni: Evaluating Future Forecasting from Omni-Modal Context for Multimodal LLMs","ko":"FutureOmni: 멀티모달 LLM을 위한 옴니모달 문맥으로부터의 미래 예측 평가","authors":"Qian Chen, Jinlan Fu, Changsong Li, Min zhang, See-Kiong Ng, Xipeng Qiu","pos":"#3606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=76zKCPBKXP","abs":"<p>Although Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) demonstrate strong omni-modal perception, their ability to forecast future events from audio-visual cues remains largely unexplored, as existing benchmarks focus mainly on retrospective understanding. To bridge this gap, we introduce FutureOmni, the first benchmark designed to evaluate omni-modal future forecasting from audio-visual environments. The evaluated models are required to perform cross-modal causal and temporal reasoning, as well as effectively leverage internal knowledge to predict future events. FutureOmni is constructed via a scalable LLM-assisted, human-in-the-loop pipeline and contains 919 videos and 1,034 multiple-choice QA pairs across 8 primary domains. Evaluations on 13 omni-modal and 7 video-only models show that current systems struggle with audio-visual future prediction, particularly in speech-heavy scenarios, with the best accuracy of 64.8% achieved by Gemini 3 Flash. To mitigate this limitation, we curate a 7K-sample instruction-tuning dataset and propose an Omni-Modal Future Forecasting (OFF) training strategy. Evaluations on FutureOmni along with standard audio-visual and video-only benchmarks show that OFF improves future forecasting performance and generalization. Code and data are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FutureOmni_anon-1F01/.</p>"},{"id":"62245","en":"Beyond Gemini-3-Pro: Revisiting LLM Routing and Aggregation at Scale","ko":"Gemini-3-Pro를 넘어: 대규모에서 LLM Routing 및 Aggregation 재조명","authors":"Shengji Tang, Weihao Lin, Peng Ye, Jingqi Ye, Hao Li, Yiqun Zhang, Xiaosong Wang, Bo Zhang, Shuyue Hu, Tao Chen, LEI BAI, Wanli Ouyang","pos":"#119","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iLrl4ppPqL","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have rapidly advanced, with Gemini-3-Pro setting a new performance milestone. In this work, we explore collective intelligence as an alternative to monolithic scaling, and demonstrate that open-source LLMs' collaboration can surpass Gemini-3-Pro. We first revisit LLM routing and aggregation at scale and identify three key bottlenecks: (1) current train-free routers are limited by a query-based paradigm focusing solely on textual similarity; (2) recent aggregation methods remain largely static, failing to select appropriate aggregators for different tasks; (3) the complementarity of routing and aggregation remains underutilized. To address these problems, we introduce JiSi, a novel framework designed to release the full potential of LLMs' collaboration through three innovations: (1) Query-Response Mixed Routing capturing both semantic information and problem difficulty; (2) Support-Set-based Aggregator Selection jointly evaluating the aggregation and domain capacity of aggregators; (3) Adaptive Routing-Aggregation Switch dynamically leveraging the advantages of routing and aggregation. Comprehensive experiments on nine benchmarks demonstrate that JiSi can surpass Gemini-3-Pro with only 47% costs by orchestrating ten open-source LLMs, while outperforming mainstream baselines. It suggests that collective intelligence represents a novel path towards Artificial General Intelligence (AGI).</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)는 빠르게 발전해 왔으며, Gemini-3-Pro는 새로운 성능 이정표를 세웠다. 이 연구에서 우리는 거대 단일 모델 스케일업의 대안으로 collective intelligence를 탐구하고, 오픈소스 LLM들의 협력이 Gemini-3-Pro를 능가할 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 먼저 대규모 LLM routing과 aggregation을 재검토하고 세 가지 핵심 병목을 식별한다: (1) 현재의 train-free router는 텍스트 유사성에만 초점을 맞춘 query-based paradigm에 의해 제한된다; (2) 최근의 aggregation 방법은 대체로 정적이어서, 서로 다른 작업에 적절한 aggregator를 선택하지 못한다; (3) routing과 aggregation의 상보성이 충분히 활용되지 못한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 LLM 협력의 잠재력을 온전히 끌어내도록 설계된 새로운 프레임워크 JiSi를 제안하며, 세 가지 혁신을 포함한다: (1) 의미 정보와 문제 난이도를 모두 포착하는 Query-Response Mixed Routing; (2) aggregator의 aggregation 능력과 domain capacity를 공동으로 평가하는 Support-Set-based Aggregator Selection; (3) routing과 aggregation의 장점을 동적으로 활용하는 Adaptive Routing-Aggregation Switch. 아홉 개 benchmark에서 수행한 종합 실험은 JiSi가 열 개의 오픈소스 LLM을 조율하여 비용의 47%만으로 Gemini-3-Pro를 능가하면서도 주류 baseline들을 상회할 수 있음을 보여준다. 이는 collective intelligence가 Artificial General Intelligence (AGI)로 가는 새로운 경로임을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61557","en":"When LLMs Develop Languages: Symbolic Communication for Efficient Multi-Agent Reasoning","ko":"LLM이 언어를 개발할 때: 효율적인 Multi-Agent Reasoning을 위한 Symbolic Communication","authors":"Zhengqi Pei, Qingming Huang, Shuhui Wang","pos":"#1510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ovpL0ujD6j","abs":"Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting improves large language models (LLMs) on difficult reasoning tasks, but it generates long natural-language rationales that are poorly optimized towards higher-level machine efficiency and intelligence.  We propose *Communicative Language Symbolism Routing* (CLSR), a test-time framework in which multiple LLM agents autonomously *invent, evolve, and share* compact *Language Symbolism Frameworks* (LSFs), and a latent-free router adaptively selects and composes these languages per query to optimize the accuracy--token budget trade-off. Unlike prompt optimization that refines surface instructions, CLSR treats each LSF as a reusable symbolic protocol and improves it through an evolutionary loop.  In inference, the router may invoke a single low-cost LSF call, ensemble multiple dialects with aggregation, or execute a multi-round composition protocol on harder queries. Across challenging benchmarks, CLSR reduces latency-oriented token completion by $3{-}6\\times$ compared to standard CoT while maintaining accuracy, outperforming other token-reduction and prompt optimization baselines.  We further theoretically  (i) yield an information-theoretic lower bound relating accuracy and tokens under arbitrary symbolism, and  (ii) characterize the CLSR protocols as a generalization of program-execution pipelines.","absKo":"연쇄적 사고(Chain-of-Thought, CoT) 프롬프팅은 어려운 추론 과제에서 대규모 언어 모델(LLMs)의 성능을 향상시키지만, 상위 수준의 기계 효율성과 지능에 대해서는 잘 최적화되지 않은 긴 자연어 추론 설명을 생성한다. 우리는 여러 LLM 에이전트가 자율적으로 *Language Symbolism Frameworks*(LSFs)를 *발명하고, 진화시키고, 공유*하는 테스트 시점 프레임워크인 *Communicative Language Symbolism Routing*(CLSR)을 제안한다. 또한 latent-free router가 쿼리마다 이러한 언어를 적응적으로 선택하고 조합하여 정확도--토큰 예산 간 trade-off를 최적화한다. 표면적 지시문을 정교화하는 prompt optimization과 달리, CLSR은 각 LSF를 재사용 가능한 symbolic protocol로 간주하고 진화 루프를 통해 이를 개선한다. 추론 시 router는 단일 저비용 LSF 호출을 실행하거나, 여러 dialect를 aggregation으로 앙상블하거나, 더 어려운 쿼리에서는 다중 라운드 composition protocol을 실행할 수 있다. 어려운 benchmark 전반에서 CLSR은 표준 CoT 대비 정확도를 유지하면서 latency-oriented token completion을 $3{-}6\\times$ 줄였고, 다른 token-reduction 및 prompt optimization baseline들을 능가했다. 또한 우리는 이론적으로 (i) 임의의 symbolism 하에서 정확도와 토큰 간의 관계를 나타내는 정보이론적 하한을 도출하고, (ii) CLSR protocol을 program-execution pipeline의 일반화로 특징지었다."},{"id":"62296","en":"Structure Enables Effective Self-Localization of Errors in LLMs","ko":"구조가 LLM의 오류 자기 위치 추정을 효과적으로 가능하게 함","authors":"Ankur Samanta, Akshayaa Magesh, Ayush Jain, Kavosh Asadi, Youliang Yu, Daniel Jiang, Boris Vidolov, Kaveh Hassani, Paul Sajda, Jalaj Bhandari, Yonathan Efroni","pos":"#1603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ht7KSypUpV","abs":"<p>Self-correction in language models remains elusive. In this work, we explore whether language models can explicitly localize errors in incorrect reasoning, as a path toward building AI systems that can effectively correct themselves. We introduce a prompting method that structures reasoning as discrete, semantically coherent thought steps, and show that models are able to reliably localize errors within this structure, while failing to do so in conventional, unstructured chain-of-thought reasoning. Motivated by how the human brain monitors errors at discrete decision points and resamples alternatives, we introduce Iterative Correction Sampling of Thoughts (Thought-ICS), a self-correction framework. Thought-ICS iteratively prompts the model to generate reasoning one discrete and complete thought at a time—where each thought represents a deliberate decision by the model—creating natural boundaries for precise error localization. Upon verification, the model localizes the first erroneous step, and the system backtracks to generate alternative reasoning from the last correct point. When asked to correct reasoning verified as incorrect by an oracle, Thought-ICS achieves 20-40\\% self-correction lift. In a completely autonomous setting without external verification, it outperforms contemporary self-correction baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Language models에서 self-correction은 여전히 어려운 과제다. 본 연구에서는 language model이 잘못된 reasoning에서 오류를 명시적으로 localize할 수 있는지 탐구하며, 이를 효과적으로 self-correct할 수 있는 AI systems를 구축하는 한 방법으로 본다. 우리는 reasoning을 discrete하고 semantically coherent한 thought steps로 구조화하는 prompting method를 제안하고, model이 이 구조 안에서는 오류를 안정적으로 localize할 수 있지만, 기존의 비구조화된 chain-of-thought reasoning에서는 그렇지 못함을 보인다. 인간의 뇌가 discrete decision points에서 error를 모니터링하고 alternatives를 재샘플링하는 방식에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 Iterative Correction Sampling of Thoughts (Thought-ICS)라는 self-correction framework를 제안한다. Thought-ICS는 model이 reasoning을 한 번에 하나의 discrete하고 완결된 thought로 생성하도록 반복적으로 prompting하며, 각 thought는 model의 신중한 decision을 나타낸다. 이는 정밀한 error localization을 위한 자연스러운 경계를 만든다. verification이 이루어지면, model은 최초의 오류 단계(first erroneous step)를 localize하고, system은 마지막으로 올바른 지점으로 되돌아가 alternative reasoning을 생성한다. oracle에 의해 incorrect하다고 검증된 reasoning을 수정하도록 요구했을 때, Thought-ICS는 20-40\\%의 self-correction 향상을 달성한다. 외부 verification이 전혀 없는 완전한 autonomous setting에서도, contemporary self-correction baselines를 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"60835","en":"TAMPO: Task- and Model-Aware Automatic Prompt Optimization for Robust and Controllable Auto-Routing in LLM-based Systems","ko":"TAMPO: LLM 기반 시스템의 견고하고 제어 가능한 Auto-Routing을 위한 Task- 및 Model-Aware 자동 Prompt Optimization","authors":"Yuejun Jiao, Jun Xia, Yanxin Yang, Yonghao Yang, Hao Shen, Mingsong Chen","pos":"#1606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wCYPCixJcZ","abs":"<p>Automatic Prompt Optimization (APO) enables Large Language Models (LLMs) to adapt to specific tasks while minimizing manual engineering costs. However, since existing APO approaches either rely solely on multi-round iterative procedures or use model-specific generators tailored to optimizing prompts for a single model and objective, they are not readily applicable to auto-routing scenarios, which require operating over diverse LLMs and juggling multiple, often competing, trade-offs. To address this issue, we propose TAMPO, a novel task- and model-aware APO framework for auto-routing in LLM-based systems. Specifically, to reflect performance variation across a broad range of tasks and models, we construct a comprehensive heterogeneity-aware dataset for training an uncertainty-aware reward model. Serving as an offline proxy, this reward model can greatly mitigate reward hacking, allowing TAMPO to learn an optimal multi-objective conditional policy for robust prompt generation. Based on the user requirements encoded in our defined preference vector, this policy enables flexible control over prompt generation, supporting a cost-effective deployment strategy. Extensive experiments across 86 tasks demonstrate that TAMPO effectively maintains performance stability across diverse tasks and models, providing a robust, controllable solution for auto-routing in various LLM-based systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>Automatic Prompt Optimization(APO)은 Large Language Models(LLMs)가 수작업 engineering 비용을 최소화하면서 특정 task에 적응하도록 해준다. 그러나 기존 APO 접근법은 multi-round iterative procedure에만 의존하거나, 단일 model과 objective를 위한 prompt optimization에 맞춘 model-specific generator를 사용하기 때문에, 다양한 LLM을 대상으로 하며 여러 상충하는 trade-off를 동시에 다뤄야 하는 auto-routing scenario에는 쉽게 적용되지 않는다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 LLM-based system에서 auto-routing을 위한 task- 및 model-aware APO framework인 TAMPO를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 광범위한 task와 model 전반에서의 성능 변화를 반영하기 위해 uncertainty-aware reward model을 학습시키는 포괄적인 heterogeneity-aware dataset을 구축한다. offline proxy로서 이 reward model은 reward hacking을 크게 완화하여, TAMPO가 robust prompt generation을 위한 최적의 multi-objective conditional policy를 학습하도록 한다. 우리가 정의한 preference vector에 인코딩된 사용자 요구에 기반하여, 이 policy는 prompt generation을 유연하게 제어할 수 있게 하며, 비용 효율적인 배포 전략을 지원한다. 86개 task에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 TAMPO가 다양한 task와 model 전반에서 성능 안정성을 효과적으로 유지하며, 여러 LLM-based system에서 robust하고 controllable한 auto-routing solution을 제공함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"60626","en":"Task-and-Model-Aware Fractal-Consistency for Efficient LLM Reasoning","ko":"효율적인 LLM 추론을 위한 작업 및 모델 인식 Fractal-Consistency","authors":"Ziqiu Luo, Jianmin Liu, Yukai Miao, Li Chen, Dan Li","pos":"#1608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yKk1hcDCkN","abs":"<p>While self-consistency methods have emerged as a promising approach to enhance the correctness of large language model (LLM) outputs by aggregating multiple stochastic samples, they suffer from two critical limitations, resulting in high computation cost. First, they evaluate output consistency monolithically, failing to efficiently combine partially correct answers across multiple samples. Second, they use static stopping criteria that cannot adapt to varying task complexities and model capabilities, resulting in suboptimal computational efficiency. In this work, we present Task-and-Model-Aware Fractal-Consistency (TMAFC), a novel self-consistency framework that addresses these limitations through two key innovations: (1) Fractal-Consistency, which evaluates the output consistency at the granularity of output components to effectively combine partial correct answers across samples, and (2) Adaptive Stopping Criteria Calibration (ASCC), which dynamically adjusts sampling stopping criteria based on real-time assessment of both task difficulty and LLM capability. Through extensive experiments on diverse question-answering benchmarks, we demonstrate that TMAFC achieves superior efficiency-accuracy trade-offs, reducing sample cost by up to 55\\% while maintaining competitive accuracy compared to state-of-the-art baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>self-consistency 방법은 여러 stochastic sample을 집계하여 large language model (LLM) 출력의 정답성을 향상시키는 유망한 접근으로 부상했지만, 두 가지 치명적인 한계 때문에 높은 계산 비용을 유발한다. 첫째, 출력 consistency를 일괄적으로 평가하여 여러 sample에 걸쳐 부분적으로 올바른 답을 효율적으로 결합하지 못한다. 둘째, 다양한 task 복잡도와 모델 역량에 적응할 수 없는 고정 stopping criterion을 사용하여 계산 효율이 최적 이하가 된다. 이 연구에서 우리는 Task-and-Model-Aware Fractal-Consistency (TMAFC)를 제시한다. 이는 두 가지 핵심 혁신을 통해 이러한 한계를 해결하는 새로운 self-consistency 프레임워크이다. (1) Fractal-Consistency는 출력 구성요소의 세분성에서 output consistency를 평가하여 sample 간 부분 정답을 효과적으로 결합하고, (2) Adaptive Stopping Criteria Calibration (ASCC)은 task 난이도와 LLM capability를 실시간으로 평가하여 sampling stopping criterion을 동적으로 조정한다. 다양한 question-answering benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험을 통해, TMAFC가 우수한 효율-정확도 trade-off를 달성하며, state-of-the-art baseline과 비교해 경쟁력 있는 정확도를 유지하면서 sample cost를 최대 55\\%까지 줄임을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"61619","en":"The Bridge-Garden Dilemma in LLM Distillation: Why Mixing Hard and Soft Labels Works","ko":"LLM Distillation의 Bridge-Garden 딜레마: Hard Label과 Soft Label을 섞으면 왜 효과적인가","authors":"Guanghui Wang, Kaiwen Kacuila, zhiyong yang, Zitai Wang, Jin-Wen Wu, Longtao Huang, Qianqian Xu, Qingming Huang","pos":"#1609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oRdJzUD39a","abs":"Knowledge distillation (KD) transfers knowledge from a large teacher model to a smaller student. In language modeling, the student is trained either on tokens sampled from the teacher (\\textbf{hard labels}) or the teacher’s full next-token distribution (\\textbf{soft labels}). Despite soft labels appear strictly richer, we find that mixing hard and soft labels consistently yields better results. Crucially, we show that this gain cannot be explained by closer teacher matching during training. Instead, it comes from reduced exposure bias---the mismatch between training and inference distributions. To explain this phenomenon, we introduce the Bridge–Garden Decomposition theory, which categorizes generation steps into two types: \\textit{Bridges}, where the next token must be \\textit{exact}, and \\textit{Gardens}, where it can be \\textit{flexible}. We show that hard-only KD excels in Bridges by avoiding risky deviations, while soft-only KD preserves diversity in Gardens.  A hybrid strategy handles both cases and, as a result, reduces exposure bias across the sequence. Guided by this theory, we develop a family of Bridge--Garden hybrid supervision methods that adaptively balance hard and soft labels. Across seven teacher--student pairs (including Qwen, Llama, Gemma, and DeepSeek) and benchmarks in reasoning and coding, our approach outperforms divergence-based and on-policy KD baselines while reducing training cost by \\textbf{9.7$\\times$}, enabling efficient model compression.","absKo":"Knowledge distillation(KD)은 큰 teacher model의 지식을 더 작은 student로 전달한다. language modeling에서 student는 teacher에서 샘플링한 token(\\textbf{hard labels}) 또는 teacher의 전체 next-token distribution(\\textbf{soft labels})으로 학습된다. soft labels가 분명히 더 풍부해 보임에도, 우리는 hard label과 soft label을 섞는 것이 일관되게 더 좋은 결과를 낸다는 것을 발견했다. 결정적으로, 우리는 이러한 향상이 학습 중 teacher와의 더 가까운 matching으로는 설명될 수 없음을 보인다. 대신 그 원인은 exposure bias, 즉 training distribution과 inference distribution 사이의 불일치에 있다. 이 현상을 설명하기 위해, 우리는 generation step을 두 가지 유형으로 분류하는 Bridge–Garden Decomposition theory를 제안한다: 다음 token이 반드시 \\textit{exact}해야 하는 \\textit{Bridges}와, \\textit{flexible}할 수 있는 \\textit{Gardens}이다. 우리는 hard-only KD가 위험한 편차를 피함으로써 Bridges에서 뛰어나고, soft-only KD가 Gardens에서 다양성을 보존한다는 것을 보인다. hybrid strategy는 두 경우를 모두 처리하며, 그 결과 sequence 전반에 걸쳐 exposure bias를 줄인다. 이러한 이론에 기반해, 우리는 hard label과 soft label의 균형을 적응적으로 조절하는 Bridge--Garden hybrid supervision 방법군을 개발했다. Qwen, Llama, Gemma, DeepSeek를 포함한 7개의 teacher--student pair와 reasoning 및 coding benchmark 전반에서, 우리의 접근법은 divergence-based 및 on-policy KD baseline을 능가하면서 학습 비용을 \\textbf{9.7$\\times$} 줄여 효율적인 model compression을 가능하게 한다."},{"id":"60503","en":"Token-Level LLM Collaboration via FusionRoute","ko":"FusionRoute를 통한 Token-Level LLM Collaboration","authors":"Nuoya Xiong, Yuhang Zhou, Hanqing Zeng, Zhaorun Chen, Furong Huang, Shuchao Bi, Lizhu Zhang, Zhuokai Zhao","pos":"#1610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zcYZpdsn9u","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) exhibit strengths across diverse domains. However, achieving strong performance across these domains with a single general-purpose model typically requires scaling to sizes that are prohibitively expensive to train and deploy. On the other hand, while smaller domain-specialized models are much more efficient, they struggle to generalize beyond their training distributions. To address this dilemma, we propose FusionRoute, a robust and effective token-level multi-LLM collaboration framework in which a lightweight router simultaneously (i) selects the most suitable expert at each decoding step and (ii) contributes a complementary logit that refines or corrects the selected expert’s next-token distribution via logit addition. Unlike existing token-level collaboration methods that rely solely on fixed expert outputs, we provide a theoretical analysis showing that pure expert-only routing is fundamentally limited: unless strong global coverage assumptions hold, it cannot in general realize the optimal decoding policy. By augmenting expert selection with a trainable complementary generator, FusionRoute expands the effective policy class and enables recovery of optimal value functions under mild conditions. Empirically, across both Llama-3 and Gemma-2 families and diverse benchmarks spanning mathematical reasoning, code generation, and instruction following, FusionRoute outperforms both sequence- and token-level collaboration, model merging, and direct fine-tuning, while remaining competitive with domain experts on their respective tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models(LLMs)은 다양한 도메인 전반에서 강점을 보인다. 그러나 단일 general-purpose model로 이러한 도메인들에서 강한 성능을 달성하려면, 학습과 배포 비용이 지나치게 큰 규모까지 확장해야 하는 경우가 많다. 반면, 더 작은 domain-specialized model은 훨씬 효율적이지만, training distribution을 넘어서는 일반화에는 어려움을 겪는다. 이러한 딜레마를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 가벼운 router가 동시에 (i) 각 decoding step에서 가장 적합한 expert를 선택하고, (ii) logit addition을 통해 선택된 expert의 next-token distribution을 정제하거나 보정하는 complementary logit을 제공하는 robust하고 효과적인 token-level multi-LLM collaboration framework인 FusionRoute를 제안한다. 고정된 expert output에만 의존하는 기존 token-level collaboration method와 달리, 우리는 순수한 expert-only routing이 본질적으로 한계가 있음을 보이는 이론적 분석을 제시한다. 강한 global coverage 가정이 성립하지 않는 한, 일반적으로 최적 decoding policy를 실현할 수 없다. 학습 가능한 complementary generator로 expert selection을 보강함으로써, FusionRoute는 유효 policy class를 확장하고 완만한 조건하에서 optimal value function의 복원을 가능하게 한다. 실험적으로는 Llama-3와 Gemma-2 계열 전반, 그리고 mathematical reasoning, code generation, instruction following을 아우르는 다양한 benchmark에서, FusionRoute는 sequence-level 및 token-level collaboration, model merging, direct fine-tuning을 모두 능가하면서도 각 도메인 expert와 그들의 해당 작업에서 경쟁력 있는 성능을 유지한다.</p>"},{"id":"62490","en":"Truthfulness Does Not Scale Like Reasoning: Why Polling Fails as a Proxy Verifier","ko":"진실성은 추론처럼 스케일링되지 않는다: Polling이 Proxy Verifier로 실패하는 이유","authors":"Yegor Denisov-Blanch, Joshua Kazdan, Jessica Chudnovsky, Rylan Schaeffer, Sheng Guan, Soji Adeshina, Sanmi Koyejo","pos":"#1614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g8bbEh2E2W","abs":"Pass@$k$ and other methods of scaling inference compute can improve language model performance in domains with external verifiers, including mathematics and code, where incorrect candidates can be filtered reliably. This raises a natural question: can we similarly scale compute to elicit gains in truthfulness for domains without convenient verification? We show that across five benchmarks and models, surprisingly, it cannot. Even at $25\\times$ the inference cost of naive sampling, polling-style aggregation yields no consistent accuracy gains over single-sample baselines and often amplifies shared misconceptions.  We find that under uncertainty, models are better at predicting what other models will say within model ensembles than at identifying what is true, revealing a separation between social prediction and truth verification.  Across models and benchmarks, aggregation fails to provide a robust truth signal because language model errors are strongly correlated.  The source of correlation goes beyond any individual benchmark: we show that even when conditioned on out of distribution random strings and asked to produce pseudo-random outputs, different models produce correlated outputs. Confidence-based weighting provides no benefit because self-reported confidence fails to reliably distinguish correct from incorrect answers.  These results delineate a boundary for inference-time scaling: in verified domains, additional samples provide more candidates for a verifier to filter; in unverified domains, additional samples merely reinforce shared misconceptions.","absKo":"<p>Pass@$k$와 다른 inference compute scaling 방법은 수학과 코드처럼 잘못된 후보를 신뢰성 있게 걸러낼 수 있는 external verifier가 있는 도메인에서 language model 성능을 향상시킬 수 있다. 이는 자연스럽게 다음 질문을 제기한다. 편리한 verification이 없는 도메인에서도 compute를 확장해 truthfulness의 향상을 이끌어낼 수 있을까? 우리는 다섯 개의 benchmark와 모델 전반에 걸쳐, 놀랍게도 그렇지 않음을 보인다. naive sampling의 $25\\times$ inference cost에서도 polling-style aggregation은 single-sample baseline에 비해 일관된 accuracy gain을 제공하지 못하며, 오히려 공유된 misconception을 증폭시키는 경우가 많다. 우리는 불확실성 하에서 모델이 무엇이 참인지 식별하는 것보다 model ensemble 내에서 다른 모델이 무엇을 말할지를 예측하는 데 더 뛰어남을 발견했으며, 이는 social prediction과 truth verification 사이의 분리를 드러낸다. 모델과 benchmark 전반에서, language model error가 강하게 상관되어 있기 때문에 aggregation은 견고한 truth signal을 제공하지 못한다. 이러한 상관의 원인은 개별 benchmark를 넘어서며, 우리는 out-of-distribution random string으로 조건을 주고 pseudo-random output을 생성하도록 요청해도 서로 다른 모델이 상관된 출력을 생성함을 보인다. self-reported confidence가 정답과 오답을 신뢰성 있게 구분하지 못하기 때문에 confidence-based weighting도 이점이 없다. 이 결과는 inference-time scaling의 경계를 규정한다. verified domain에서는 추가 sample이 verifier가 걸러낼 더 많은 후보를 제공하지만, unverified domain에서는 추가 sample이 공유된 misconception을 강화할 뿐이다.</p>"},{"id":"63809","en":"SAGE: A Dataflow-Native Framework for Modular, Controllable, and Transparent LLM-Augmented Reasoning","ko":"SAGE: 모듈러하고 제어 가능하며 투명한 LLM 증강 추론을 위한 dataflow-native 프레임워크","authors":"Jun Liu, Peilin Liu, Ruicheng Zhang, Senlei Zhang, Yanbo Chen, Ziao Wang, Jinyun Yang, mingqi wang, Shuhao Zhang, Xiaofei Liao, Hai Jin","pos":"#1701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TXcFJdT7at","abs":"LLM applications increasingly execute as end-to-end inference pipelines that couple generation with retrieval, stateful memory, context refinement, and tool use under strict tail-latency and SLO constraints. Today, these stages are often stitched together as RPC-connected services, obscuring cross-stage queueing and interference and limiting pipeline-level compilation and resource sharing. We present SAGE (Streaming-Augmented Generative Execution), a full-stack system that treats inference pipelines as first-class compilation targets. SAGE exposes pipelines as declarative dataflows and compiles them into distributed execution plans with bounded-queue backpressure. It integrates vector search, streaming semantic state, structured memory, and refinement as operators with explicit resource/state contracts, enabling operator-level diagnosis of tail behavior. SAGE integrates pluggable generation and embedding backends and provides a unified control plane for engine management, batching, and admission under mixed workloads. On a 16-node cluster, SAGE sustains 16 requests/s at $&gt;700$ tokens/request with 1 ms median scheduling overhead, and achieves near-linear scale-out to 16 nodes (11.4$\\times$ throughput at 16 nodes), and reduces p99 latency by 57\\% under multi-pipeline contention versus simultaneous admission.","absKo":"LLM 애플리케이션은 점점 생성과 retrieval, stateful memory, context refinement, tool use를 결합한 end-to-end inference pipeline으로 실행되고 있으며, 이 과정은 엄격한 tail-latency와 SLO 제약 아래에서 동작한다. 오늘날 이러한 단계들은 대개 RPC로 연결된 서비스로 이어 붙여져 있어 stage 간 queueing과 interference를 가리고, pipeline 수준의 compilation과 resource sharing을 제한한다. 우리는 inference pipeline을 first-class compilation target으로 다루는 full-stack 시스템 SAGE (Streaming-Augmented Generative Execution)를 제시한다. SAGE는 pipeline을 declarative dataflow로 노출하고, bounded-queue backpressure를 갖는 distributed execution plan으로 컴파일한다. 또한 vector search, streaming semantic state, structured memory, refinement를 명시적인 resource/state contract를 가진 operator로 통합하여, operator 수준에서 tail behavior를 진단할 수 있게 한다. SAGE는 pluggable generation 및 embedding backend를 통합하고, mixed workload 하에서 engine management, batching, admission을 위한 unified control plane을 제공한다. 16-node cluster에서 SAGE는 request당 $&gt;700$ tokens를 유지하면서 16 requests/s를 지속하고, 1 ms median scheduling overhead를 보이며, 16 nodes까지 거의 선형적인 scale-out(16 nodes에서 11.4$\\times$ throughput)을 달성하며, multi-pipeline contention 하에서 p99 latency를 simultaneous admission 대비 57\\% 줄인다."},{"id":"63636","en":"Rethinking Thinking Tokens: LLMs as Improvement Operators","ko":"생각 토큰 다시 보기: LLM을 개선 연산자로 보기","authors":"Lovish Madaan, Aniket Didolkar, Suchin Gururangan, John Quan, Ruan Silva, Russ Salakhutdinov, Manzil Zaheer, Sanjeev Arora, Anirudh Goyal","pos":"#1702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VCwVl6EsvX","abs":"<p>Reasoning training incentivizes LLMs to produce long chains of thought (long CoT), which among other things, allows them to explore solution strategies with self-checking. This results in higher accuracy, but inflates context length, token/compute cost, and answer latency. We ask: Can current models leverage their metacognition to provide other combinations on this Pareto frontier, e.g., better accuracy with lower context length and/or latency? Abstractly, we view the model as an improvement operator on its own \"thoughts\" with a continuum of possible strategies. We identify an interesting inference family Parallel-Distill-Refine (PDR), which performs the following: (i) generate diverse drafts in parallel; (ii) distill them into a bounded, textual workspace; and (iii) refine conditioned on this workspace, producing an output that seeds the next round. Importantly, context length (hence compute cost) is controllable via degree of parallelism, and is no longer conflated with the total number of generated tokens. We report PDR instantiations of current models that give better accuracy than long CoT while incurring lower latency. Setting degree of parallelism to 1 yields an interesting subcase, Sequential Refinement (SR) (iteratively improve a single candidate answer) which provides performance superior to long CoT. Success of such model orchestrations raises the question whether further training could shift the Pareto frontier. To this end, we train an 8B thinking model with Reinforcement Learning (RL) to make it consistent with PDR as the inference method. On math tasks with verifiable answers, iterative pipelines surpass single-pass baselines at matched sequential budgets, with PDR delivering the largest gains (e.g., +11% on AIME 2024 and +9% on AIME 2025).</p>","absKo":"Reasoning training은 LLM이 긴 chain of thought (long CoT)를 생성하도록 유도하며, 이는 다른 이점과 함께 self-checking을 통해 해법 전략을 탐색할 수 있게 한다. 그 결과 정확도는 높아지지만, context length, token/compute cost, answer latency가 증가한다. 우리는 묻는다: 현재 모델이 자신의 metacognition을 활용해 이 Pareto frontier 위에서 다른 조합, 예를 들어 더 짧은 context length 및/또는 더 낮은 latency로 더 높은 정확도를 제공할 수 있는가? 추상적으로, 우리는 모델을 자신의 \"thought\"에 대한 개선 연산자로 보고, 가능한 전략의 연속체를 가정한다. 우리는 흥미로운 inference family인 Parallel-Distill-Refine (PDR)을 식별했으며, 이는 다음을 수행한다: (i) 다양한 draft를 병렬로 생성하고; (ii) 이를 bounded textual workspace로 distill하며; (iii) 이 workspace를 조건으로 refine하여 다음 라운드의 seed가 되는 출력을 만든다. 중요한 점은 context length(따라서 compute cost)가 병렬성의 정도에 의해 제어 가능해지며, 더 이상 생성된 총 토큰 수와 혼동되지 않는다는 것이다. 우리는 현재 모델의 PDR 인스턴스가 long CoT보다 더 높은 정확도를 제공하면서 더 낮은 latency를 발생시킴을 보고한다. 병렬성의 정도를 1로 설정하면 흥미로운 부분 경우인 Sequential Refinement (SR), 즉 단일 후보 답을 반복적으로 개선하는 방식이 되며, 이는 long CoT보다 우수한 성능을 제공한다. 이러한 모델 orchestration의 성공은 추가 학습이 Pareto frontier를 더 이동시킬 수 있는지에 대한 질문을 제기한다. 이를 위해 우리는 8B thinking model을 Reinforcement Learning (RL)으로 학습시켜 inference method로서 PDR과 일치하도록 만들었다. 정답을 검증할 수 있는 수학 과제에서, iterative pipeline은 동일한 sequential budget에서 single-pass baseline을 능가했으며, PDR이 가장 큰 향상을 보였다(예: AIME 2024에서 +11%, AIME 2025에서 +9%).</p>"},{"id":"66406","en":"How Powerful are LLMs in Generating Program Specifications?","ko":"LLM은 프로그램 명세 생성에 얼마나 강력한가?","authors":"Fanpeng Yang, Xing Li, Shuling Wang, Jie An, Zeyu Sun, Shenghua Feng, Wenhan Wang, Weiyi Wang, Naijun Zhan, Xu","pos":"#1908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=41zGzIEpQd","abs":"<p>Formal verification provides strong guarantees of software correctness, but its adoption is limited by the high cost of writing precise formal specifications. While recent large language models (LLMs) have demonstrated impressive capabilities in theorem proving and verified code generation, how powerful they truly are in generating program specifications remains unclear. Existing evaluations require either verifying implementation conformance or proving semantic equivalence between specifications, both are formidably difficult, yielding sparse and often inconclusive results about specification quality. To address this problem, we introduce Coins, a Coq-based evaluation framework that assesses specification quality through provable behavioral correctness on instantiated test cases. This design aligns the evaluation with the asymmetric nature of formal reasoning, where successful proofs provide reliable evidence while proof failures are inherently ambiguous. Using Coins, we conduct a large-scale empirical study of specification generation on HumanEval, supported by a curated set of human-written Coq specifications. Our results show that even generating specifications remains a formidable challenge, and that verification complexity substantially obscures genuine differences in specification quality. Overall, we find that accurately evaluating specifications—rather than increasing model capacity alone—is the central challenge in understanding the power of LLMs for specification synthesis, and that the test-case--based formal reasoning offers a more faithful and discriminative measure of progress.</p>"},{"id":"63245","en":"How Does Reasoning Flow? Tracing Attention-Induced Information Flow for Targeted RL in LLMs","ko":"추론은 어떻게 흐르는가? LLM에서 표적 RL을 위한 어텐션 유발 정보 흐름 추적","authors":"Zhichen Dong, Yang Li, Yuhan Sun, Weixun Wang, Yijia Luo, Zinian Peng, Wenbo Su, YuCheng, Bo Zheng, Junchi Yan","pos":"#1909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ym4KYa1n76","abs":"<p>Token-level credit assignment remains a key obstacle for reinforcement learning (RL) in large language models (LLMs), where RL recipes typically treat all tokens equally, failing to distinguish decisive reasoning steps from routine formatting or fluent filler. Recent attempts leverage model-internal signals to assign finer-grained credit, but these are often point-wise heuristics that ignore the global structure of information propagation. We propose FlowTracer, an RL framework that traces \\emph{answer-targeted reasoning flow} on an attention-induced directed acyclic graph in which nodes correspond to tokens and edge capacities come from aggregated attention weights and derives token credit from this global structure. The edge capacities are reweighted to retain only the influence that can reach the answer region, while enforcing local flow conservation so intermediate tokens neither lose nor gain effective mass due to path length or irrelevant branches. On this graph, FlowTracer extracts an information-flow backbone connecting the question to the answer and scores tokens by flow throughput, revealing high-impact hubs and aggregation checkpoints that mediate long-range dependencies. These derived importances are used to shape token-level rewards, enabling learning signals to focus precisely on the tokens that route information toward (or away from) correct answers and delivering consistent performance gains across a range of reasoning tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model (LLM)에서 token-level credit assignment는 강화학습 (RL)의 핵심 장애물로 남아 있다. RL recipe는 대개 모든 token을 동일하게 취급하여, 결정적인 reasoning step과 일상적인 formatting 또는 유창한 filler를 구분하지 못한다. 최근 시도들은 model 내부 신호를 활용해 더 세밀한 credit을 배정하지만, 이는 정보 전파의 전역 구조를 무시하는 point-wise heuristic인 경우가 많다. 우리는 FlowTracer를 제안한다. FlowTracer는 attention으로 유도된 directed acyclic graph 위에서 \\emph{answer-targeted reasoning flow}를 추적하는 RL framework로, node는 token에 대응하고 edge capacity는 집계된 attention weight에서 오며, 이 전역 구조로부터 token credit을 도출한다. Edge capacity는 answer region에 도달할 수 있는 영향만 남기도록 재가중되며, local flow conservation을 강제하여 중간 token이 path length나 무관한 branch 때문에 effective mass를 잃거나 얻지 않도록 한다. 이 graph에서 FlowTracer는 question과 answer를 잇는 information-flow backbone을 추출하고, 긴 거리 의존성을 매개하는 high-impact hub와 aggregation checkpoint를 드러내는 방식으로 flow throughput을 기준으로 token을 점수화한다. 이렇게 도출된 중요도는 token-level reward shaping에 사용되어, 정보가 정답을 향해(또는 정답에서 멀어지도록) 흐르도록 하는 token에 학습 신호를 정확히 집중시키며, 다양한 reasoning task에서 일관된 성능 향상을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61432","en":"Distribution-Calibrated Inference Time Compute for Thinking LLM-as-a-Judge","ko":"Thinking LLM-as-a-Judge를 위한 Distribution-Calibrated Inference Time Compute","authors":"Hamid Dadkhahi, Firas Trabelsi, Parker Riley, Juraj Juraska, Mehdi Mirzazadeh","pos":"#2001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qBMqN2ZyVH","abs":"Thinking Large Language Models (LLMs) used as judges  for pairwise preferences remain noisy at the single-sample level, and common aggregation rules (majority vote, soft self-consistency, or instruction-based self-aggregation) are inconsistent when ties are allowed. We study inference-time compute (ITC) for evaluators that generate $n$ independent thinking--rating samples per item, and propose a principled, distribution-calibrated aggregation scheme. Our method models three-way preferences with a Bradley–Terry-Davidson formulation on rating counts, leveraging both polarity (margin among non-ties) and decisiveness (non-tie rate) to distinguish narrow margins from strong consensus. Across various evaluation benchmarks, our approach consistently reduces MAE and increases pairwise accuracy versus standard baselines, and when evaluated against human-consensus meta-labels, matches or exceeds individual human raters. These results show that carefully allocating ITC and aggregating with distribution-aware methods turns noisy individual model judgments into reliable ratings for evaluation.","absKo":"<p>쌍대 선호(pairwise preference)를 판정하는 judge로 사용되는 Thinking Large Language Models(LLMs)는 단일 샘플 수준에서는 여전히 노이즈가 크며, 일반적인 aggregation rule(majority vote, soft self-consistency, instruction-based self-aggregation)은 tie가 허용될 때 일관적이지 않다. 우리는 각 항목마다 n개의 독립적인 thinking--rating 샘플을 생성하는 evaluator를 위한 inference-time compute (ITC)를 연구하고, 원칙적인 distribution-calibrated aggregation scheme을 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 rating count에 대해 Bradley–Terry-Davidson formulation으로 three-way preference를 모델링하며, polarity(non-tie 사이의 margin)와 decisiveness(non-tie rate)를 모두 활용해 근소한 차이와 강한 합의를 구분한다. 다양한 evaluation benchmark 전반에서 우리의 접근법은 표준 baseline에 비해 MAE를 일관되게 줄이고 pairwise accuracy를 높이며, human-consensus meta-label과 비교했을 때 개별 human rater와 동등하거나 그 이상을 보인다. 이 결과는 ITC를 신중하게 할당하고 distribution-aware method로 aggregation하면, 노이즈가 큰 개별 model 판단을 평가에 신뢰할 수 있는 rating으로 바꿀 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65354","en":"Escaping the Likelihood Trap: Geometric Diversity Optimization for Long-Form Image Captioning","ko":"우도 함정에서 벗어나기: 장문 이미지 캡셔닝을 위한 기하학적 다양성 최적화","authors":"Qingmei Tang, Shuai Hao, Rong Fu, Zirui Mo, Xiang Liu, Jiaxuan Lu, Wenyu Wang","pos":"#2007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ERfBSBnEyo","abs":"<p>The utility of Vision-Language Models (VLMs) in reasoning and auditing tasks hinges on their ability to exhaustively describe visual scenes. However, current models exhibit a pathology we term the Likelihood Trap: standard alignment objectives, specifically MLE and KL-regularization, drive generation toward generic, high-probability templates, systematically suppressing fine-grained details. To overcome this, we introduce Geo-RL, a framework that shifts the objective from probabilistic likelihood to geometric coverage. Geo-RL reformulates caption generation as maximizing the volume of a parallelotope in semantic space. By leveraging Determinantal Point Processes (DPPs), we enforce orthogonality among sampled descriptions, ensuring that they span the image's full semantic support. Crucially, we derive a closed-form leave-one-out marginal reward, enabling stable policy optimization. Empirically, Geo-RL escapes the trap, achieving a significant improvement in semantic richness and detail coverage without compromising visual grounding.</p>"},{"id":"65089","en":"Evaluating and Explaining Prompt Sensitivity of LLMs Using Interactions","ko":"상호작용을 이용한 LLM의 프롬프트 민감도 평가 및 설명","authors":"Ruiyang Qin, Qingzhuo Wang, Tian Wang, Zhihua Wei, Wen Shen","pos":"#2008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GsdFM8qnav","abs":"<p>The remarkable capabilities of large language models (LLMs) are often undermined by their instability. Even subtle and semantically irrelevant changes in prompts can cause dramatic fluctuations in performance, a phenomenon known as prompt sensitivity. Previous studies typically evaluate prompt sensitivity by comparing the LLM's final outputs when prompts change. However, such coarse-grained metrics fail to explain the internal reasons for prompt sensitivity.  In this paper, we introduce interactions as a fine-grained tool to analyze prompt sensitivity of LLMs. Specifically, we decompose the output score of the LLM into a set of interactions. Each interaction represents a nonlinear relationship involving a set of input variables. We discover that subtle changes to prompts can trigger severe instability in interactions, even when the outputs of the LLM remain the same. To this end, we propose an Interaction-based Prompt Sensitivity (IPS) metric by quantifying changes in interactions when we introduce subtle changes to prompts.  We apply the IPS metric to 50 open-source LLMs and uncover four factors that reduce the prompt sensitivity of LLMs, including supervised fine-tuning, increased model scales, dense architectures, and few-shot learning. More crucially, we discover a common mechanism by which these four factors reduce prompt sensitivity: all four factors tend to reduce the prompt sensitivity of low-order interactions (i.e., interactions involving few input variables).</p>","absKo":"<p>large language model (LLM)의 놀라운 성능은 종종 불안정성에 의해 훼손된다. 프롬프트에 사소하고 의미적으로도 무관한 변화만 있어도 성능이 크게 출렁일 수 있는데, 이를 prompt sensitivity라고 한다. 기존 연구는 대개 프롬프트가 바뀔 때 LLM의 최종 출력을 비교하여 prompt sensitivity를 평가한다. 그러나 이러한 거친 지표로는 prompt sensitivity의 내부 원인을 설명할 수 없다. 본 논문에서는 LLM의 prompt sensitivity를 분석하기 위한 세밀한 도구로 interactions를 도입한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 LLM의 output score를 일련의 interactions로 분해한다. 각 interaction은 입력 변수들의 집합과 관련된 비선형 관계를 나타낸다. 우리는 프롬프트의 사소한 변화가 LLM의 출력이 동일하게 유지되더라도 interactions에서 심각한 불안정성을 유발할 수 있음을 발견한다. 이를 바탕으로, 프롬프트에 미세한 변화를 가했을 때 interactions의 변화를 정량화하는 Interaction-based Prompt Sensitivity (IPS) metric을 제안한다. 우리는 IPS metric을 50개의 open-source LLM에 적용하여 supervised fine-tuning, 더 큰 model scale, dense architecture, few-shot learning을 포함해 LLM의 prompt sensitivity를 줄이는 네 가지 요인을 밝혀냈다. 더 중요한 점은, 이 네 요인이 prompt sensitivity를 줄이는 공통 메커니즘이 모두 low-order interaction, 즉 적은 수의 입력 변수를 포함하는 interaction의 prompt sensitivity를 낮추는 경향이 있다는 사실을 발견한 것이다.</p>"},{"id":"62006","en":"ResRL: Boosting LLM Reasoning via Negative Sample Projection Residual Reinforcement Learning","ko":"ResRL: Negative Sample Projection Residual Reinforcement Learning으로 LLM 추론 향상","authors":"Zihan Lin, Xiaohan Wang, Jie Cao, Jiajun Chai, Li Wang, Xiaodong Lu, Wei Lin, Ran He, Guojun Yin","pos":"#209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kmN9ozKtGh","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) enhances reasoning of Large Language Models (LLMs) but usually exhibits limited generation diversity due to the over-incentivization of positive rewards. Although methods like Negative Sample Reinforcement (NSR) mitigate this issue by upweighting penalty from negative samples, they may suppress the semantic distributions shared between positive and negative responses. To boost reasoning ability without losing diversity, this paper proposes negative sample projection Residual Reinforcement Learning (ResRL) that decouples similar semantic distributions among positive and negative responses. We theoretically link Lazy Likelihood Displacement (LLD) to negative-positive head-gradient interference and derive a single-forward proxy that upper-bounds representation alignment to guide conservative advantage reweighting.  ResRL then projects negative-token hidden representations onto an SVD-based low-rank positive subspace and uses projection residuals to modulate negative gradients, improving reasoning while preserving diversity and outperforming strong baselines on average across twelve benchmarks spanning Mathematics, Code, Agent Tasks, and Function Calling. Notably, ResRL surpasses NSR on mathematical reasoning by 9.4\\% in Avg@16 and 7.0\\% in Pass@128. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ResRL.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards(RLVR)는 Large Language Models(LLMs)의 추론 능력을 향상시키지만, 양성 보상에 대한 과도한 인센티브 부여로 인해 일반적으로 생성 다양성이 제한되는 경향이 있다. Negative Sample Reinforcement(NSR)과 같은 방법은 음성 샘플에서의 페널티를 더 크게 반영함으로써 이 문제를 완화하지만, 양성 및 음성 응답이 공유하는 semantic distribution을 억제할 수 있다. 다양성을 잃지 않으면서 추론 능력을 높이기 위해, 본 논문은 양성과 음성 응답 사이의 유사한 semantic distribution을 분리하는 negative sample projection Residual Reinforcement Learning(ResRL)을 제안한다. 우리는 Lazy Likelihood Displacement(LLD)를 negative-positive head-gradient interference와 이론적으로 연결하고, representation alignment에 대한 상한을 제공하는 single-forward proxy를 유도하여 conservative advantage reweighting을 안내한다. 이후 ResRL은 negative-token hidden representation을 SVD 기반 low-rank positive subspace에 투영하고, projection residual을 사용해 negative gradient를 조절함으로써 추론 성능을 개선하면서 다양성은 유지한다. 또한 수학, 코드, agent tasks, function calling을 아우르는 12개 benchmark 전반에서 강력한 baseline을 평균적으로 능가한다. 특히 ResRL은 수학적 추론에서 Avg@16 기준 9.4\\%, Pass@128 기준 7.0\\% 만큼 NSR을 상회한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ResRL 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"63783","en":"D-FUSEr: Diverse Failure, Unified Success via Error-Distribution Shaping in LLM Reasoning","ko":"D-FUSEr: LLM 추론에서 에러 분포 조절을 통한 다양한 실패, 통합된 성공","authors":"David Baek, Andrew Estornell, Yichi Zhang, Muhammad Faaiz Taufiq, Jean-Francois Ton, Jie Mei, Tao Wang","pos":"#2101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=To2O1ed5cV","abs":"<p>Test-time scaling methods such as majority vote aggregation and iterative refinement (e.g., self-reflection or multi-agent inference) improve reasoning performance by leveraging multiple solution samples. However, their efficacy depends not only on raw performance, but critically on the distribution of errors across samples. When errors concentrate, (a) aggregation accuracy degrades, as the majority vote may select a shared mistake, and (b) confidence in common mistakes may suppress exploration in iterative refinement. We argue that improving correctness alone is not sufficient to mitigate these issues; to this end, we propose to explicitly shape error distributions to improve aggregation. First, we introduce a theoretically grounded \\textbf{diverse failure reward} that incentivizes calibrated disagreement within model errors. We prove that this reward directly optimizes majority-vote accuracy: policies achieving higher reward attain higher expected majority-vote performance, and vice versa. We further show that this theoretical property generalizes to iterative refinement. Second, we introduce \\textbf{anti-votes}, in which the model predicts the most common mistake alongside its solution, allowing probability mass on dominant errors to be explicitly reweighted.  We identify conditions under which anti-votes are guaranteed to  improve majority-vote accuracy. Empirically, across three model families of varying sizes and four benchmarks, we show that both approaches substantially improve majority vote and iterative refinement performance without degrading single-sample accuracy.</p>","absKo":"majority vote aggregation과 iterative refinement(예: self-reflection 또는 multi-agent inference) 같은 test-time scaling 방법은 여러 solution sample을 활용해 reasoning 성능을 향상시킨다. 그러나 이들의 효과는 raw performance뿐 아니라 sample 전반에 걸친 error distribution에 결정적으로 의존한다. 오류가 한곳에 집중되면, (a) majority vote가 공유된 실수를 선택할 수 있어 aggregation accuracy가 저하되고, (b) 흔한 실수에 대한 높은 confidence가 iterative refinement에서 탐색을 억제할 수 있다. 우리는 정확도만 향상시키는 것으로는 이러한 문제를 충분히 완화할 수 없다고 주장하며, aggregation을 개선하기 위해 error distribution을 명시적으로 형성할 것을 제안한다. 먼저, 우리는 모델 오류 내에서 calibrated disagreement를 장려하는 이론적으로 정당화된 \\textbf{diverse failure reward}를 도입한다. 우리는 이 reward가 majority-vote accuracy를 직접 최적화함을 증명한다. 더 높은 reward를 달성하는 policy는 더 높은 기대 majority-vote performance를 얻으며, 그 반대도 성립한다. 또한 이러한 이론적 성질이 iterative refinement으로 일반화됨을 보인다. 둘째, 우리는 모델이 해답과 함께 가장 흔한 실수도 예측하는 \\textbf{anti-votes}를 도입하여, 우세한 오류에 대한 probability mass를 명시적으로 재가중할 수 있게 한다. 우리는 anti-votes가 majority-vote accuracy를 향상시킨다는 것이 보장되는 조건을 규명한다. 경험적으로, 서로 다른 크기의 세 가지 model family와 네 개의 benchmark 전반에서, 두 방법 모두 single-sample accuracy를 저하시키지 않으면서 majority vote와 iterative refinement 성능을 크게 향상시킴을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"64827","en":"ConvexBench: Can LLMs Recognize Convex Functions?","ko":"ConvexBench: LLM은 Convex Function을 인식할 수 있는가?","authors":"Yepeng Liu, Yu Huang, Yu-Xiang Wang, Yingbin LIANG, Yuheng Bu","pos":"#2104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JNtq1ungZt","abs":"Convexity recognition plays a central role in many optimization, control, and learning problems. However, the ability of Large Language Models (LLMs) to identify this property in symbolic expressions remains unexamined. We introduce \\cb, a scalable and mechanically verifiable benchmark for testing whether LLMs can determine the convexity of a symbolic objective under deep functional composition. Experiments on frontier LLMs reveal a sharp \\textit{compositional reasoning gap}: performance degrades rapidly with increasing depth,  dropping from an F1-score of $1.0$ at depth $2$ to approximately $0.2$ at depth $100$. Inspection of models' reasoning traces indicates two failure modes: \\textit{parsing failure} and \\textit{lazy reasoning}. To address these limitations, we propose an agentic divide-and-conquer framework that (i) offloads parsing to an external tool to construct an abstract syntax tree (AST) and (ii) enforces recursive reasoning over each intermediate sub-expression with focused context. This framework reliably mitigates deep-composition failures, achieving substantial performance improvement at large depths (e.g., F1-Score $= 1.0$ at depth $100$).","absKo":"Convexity recognition은 많은 optimization, control, learning problem에서 핵심적인 역할을 한다. 그러나 Large Language Models (LLMs)가 symbolic expression에서 이 성질을 식별할 수 있는지는 아직 충분히 검토되지 않았다. 우리는 깊은 functional composition 하에서 LLM이 symbolic objective의 convexity를 판별할 수 있는지 테스트하기 위한 scalable하고 mechanically verifiable한 benchmark인 \\cb를 소개한다. 최전선(frontier) LLM에 대한 실험은 뚜렷한 \\textit{compositional reasoning gap}을 드러낸다. 성능은 depth가 증가할수록 급격히 저하되어, depth 2에서 F1-score 1.0이던 것이 depth 100에서는 약 0.2로 떨어진다. 모델의 reasoning trace를 살펴보면 두 가지 실패 모드가 확인된다. \\textit{parsing failure}와 \\textit{lazy reasoning}이다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 (i) parsing을 외부 tool에 위임하여 abstract syntax tree (AST)를 구성하고, (ii) 각 중간 sub-expression에 대해 집중된 context로 recursive reasoning을 강제하는 agentic divide-and-conquer 프레임워크를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크는 deep-composition 실패를 안정적으로 완화하며, 큰 depth에서 상당한 성능 향상을 달성한다(예: depth 100에서 F1-Score 1.0)."},{"id":"62061","en":"Can LLMs Reason Structurally? Benchmarking via the lens of Data Structures","ko":"LLM은 구조적으로 추론할 수 있을까? 데이터 구조 관점의 Benchmarking","authors":"Yu He, Yingxi Li, Colin White, Ellen Vitercik","pos":"#2108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kChzpoYFef","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are deployed on increasingly complex tasks that require multi-step decision-making. Understanding their algorithmic reasoning abilities is therefore crucial. However, we lack a diagnostic benchmark for evaluating this capability. We propose data structures as a principled lens: as fundamental building blocks of algorithms, they naturally probe structural reasoning—the ability to understand and manipulate relationships such as order, hierarchy, and connectivity that underpin algorithmic reasoning. We introduce DSR-Bench, spanning 20 data structures, 35 operations, and 4,140 problem instances. DSR-Bench features hierarchical task organization, fully automated generation and evaluation, and fine-grained diagnostics. Evaluating 13 state-of-the-art LLMs reveals critical limitations: the top-performing model achieves only 0.46/1 on challenging instances. Three auxiliary probes targeting more realistic usages expose further weaknesses: models perform poorly on spatial data and context-rich scenarios, and they struggle to reason over their own code.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)은 다단계 의사결정을 요구하는 점점 더 복잡한 과제에 배치되고 있다. 따라서 이들의 algorithmic reasoning 능력을 이해하는 일은 매우 중요하다. 그러나 이러한 능력을 평가하기 위한 진단용 benchmark는 부족하다. 우리는 data structure를 하나의 원리적 관점으로 제안한다. 알고리즘의 기본 구성 요소인 data structure는 algorithmic reasoning의 토대가 되는 순서, 계층, 연결성과 같은 관계를 이해하고 조작하는 structural reasoning을 자연스럽게 탐지한다. 우리는 20개의 data structure, 35개의 operation, 4,140개의 문제 인스턴스를 포괄하는 DSR-Bench를 소개한다. DSR-Bench는 계층적 task organization, 완전 자동화된 생성 및 평가, 그리고 세밀한 진단 기능을 갖춘다. 13개의 state-of-the-art LLM을 평가한 결과, 중요한 한계가 드러났다. 최고 성능 모델도 어려운 인스턴스에서 0.46/1에 그친다. 보다 현실적인 사용을 겨냥한 3개의 보조 probe는 추가적인 약점을 드러내는데, 모델은 spatial data와 context-rich scenario에서 성능이 낮고, 자신의 code를 추론하는 데도 어려움을 겪는다.</p>"},{"id":"65719","en":"A Unified Approach to Interpreting Knowledge Distillation for Large Language Models via Interactions","ko":"상호작용을 통한 대형 언어 모델의 지식 증류 해석을 위한 통합적 접근","authors":"Qingzhuo Wang, Ruiyang Qin, Zhenxin Qin, Wen Shen, Zhihua Wei","pos":"#2209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AqyQkalFk6","abs":"<p>Despite the success of knowledge distillation (KD) in Large Language Models (LLMs), the underlying mechanism behind its efficacy remains unclear. In this paper, we propose a unified approach to explore the common mechanism of various KD methods using interactions. Specifically, we decompose the output score of the LLM into the sum of numerous interactions. Each interaction represents a nonlinear relationship involving a set of input variables (e.g., words). Based on the decomposed interactions, we discover that the common mechanism underlying various KD methods is the sparsification of interactions, i.e., student models retain fewer interactions for inference while suppressing other interactions to zero effects. Furthermore, we discover that the performance variance across different KD methods arises from their capabilities in handling complex interactions. A KD method typically yields better performance if it enables the student model to achieve higher sparsity of complex interactions. Motivated by these insights, we propose a plug-and-play loss function called Complex Interaction Penalty (CIP) to explicitly enforce the sparsity of complex interactions during the distillation process. Extensive experiments demonstrate that integrating CIP consistently improves the performance of diverse KD methods on both in-domain and out-of-distribution benchmarks.</p>"},{"id":"63484","en":"Addressing Semantic Blind Spots in Text-to-SQL via Component Pre-generation and AST Matching Rewards","ko":"구성 요소 사전 생성과 AST 매칭 보상을 통한 Text-to-SQL의 시맨틱 사각지대 해결","authors":"Xingyu Ma, Xin Tian, Lingxiang Wu, Xuepeng Wang, Zhilin Zhang, Xueming Tang, Jinqiao Wang","pos":"#2210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WoxvGO1Vcv","abs":"<p>In recent years, significant advancements in large language models have greatly propelled the development of Text-to-SQL tasks. However, due to the token-by-token sequential generation mechanism employed by these models, they encounter a semantic blind spot problem with respect to pending SQL components—the parts of the SQL query yet to be generated. Specifically, language models are unable to effectively utilize the semantic information of these pending SQL components during the generation of the final SQL query, which poses considerable challenges for generating complex SQL statements. To address this issue, we propose a novel thought process based on SQL components pre-generation and design a maximum connected subtree matching reward mechanism leveraging the SQL abstract syntax tree to improve the accuracy of local component generation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that, under comparable model parameter scales, our training approach achieves significant advantages, effectively enhancing the generation of complex SQL queries. Our method attains an execution accuracy EX of 65.78% on the BIRD-dev dataset and achieves state-of-the-art performance on the Spider-syn datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 수년간 large language model의 괄목할 만한 발전은 Text-to-SQL 과제의 발전을 크게 견인해 왔다. 그러나 이러한 모델이 token-by-token 순차 생성 메커니즘을 사용하기 때문에, 아직 생성되지 않은 SQL query의 부분인 pending SQL component에 대해 semantic blind spot 문제를 겪는다. 구체적으로, language model은 최종 SQL query를 생성하는 동안 이러한 pending SQL component의 semantic information을 효과적으로 활용하지 못하며, 이는 복잡한 SQL statement를 생성하는 데 상당한 어려움을 야기한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 SQL component pre-generation에 기반한 새로운 thought process를 제안하고, SQL abstract syntax tree를 활용하는 maximum connected subtree matching reward mechanism을 설계하여 local component 생성의 정확도를 향상시킨다. 광범위한 실험은 비교 가능한 model parameter 규모에서 우리의 training approach가 유의미한 우위를 보이며, 복잡한 SQL query 생성 능력을 효과적으로 향상시킨다는 것을 보여준다. 우리의 방법은 BIRD-dev dataset에서 execution accuracy EX 65.78%를 달성하고, Spider-syn dataset에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"63689","en":"Learning When to Attend: Conditional Memory Access for Long-Context LLMs","ko":"언제 주의를 기울일지 학습하기: 긴 컨텍스트 LLM을 위한 조건부 메모리 접근","authors":"Sakshi Choudhary, Aditya Chattopadhyay, Luca Zancato, Elvis Nunez, Matthew Trager, Wei Xia, Stefano Soatto","pos":"#2706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UcGwFXWnbn","abs":"Language models struggle to generalize beyond the context lengths seen during pretraining, limiting performance on long-horizon reasoning and retrieval. Continued pretraining on long-context data can mitigate this limitation, but it is prohibitively expensive due to the quadratic scaling of Attention with sequence length. In practice, most tokens do not require Global Attention over the entire sequence and can rely on local context. Based on this insight, we propose L2A, a sequence modeling layer that enables token-wise long-term conditional memory access by deciding \\textit{when} to invoke Global Attention. We evaluate L2A on Qwen 2.5 and Qwen 3 models, extending their effective context length from 32K to 128K tokens, where it matches standard long-context training within 1.5–3\\% while skipping Global Attention for $\\sim$80\\% of tokens and outperforming prior baselines. We also design custom Triton kernels to efficiently realize this token-wise conditional attention on GPUs, achieving up to $\\sim$2× improvements in training throughput and time-to-first-token over FlashAttention-2. Moreover, L2A enables post-training pruning of highly sparse Global Attention layers, reducing KV cache memory by up to 50\\% with negligible performance loss.","absKo":"Language models는 pretraining 동안 보았던 context length를 넘어 일반화하는 데 어려움을 겪으며, 이로 인해 long-horizon reasoning과 retrieval 성능이 제한된다. long-context data에 대한 continued pretraining은 이러한 한계를 완화할 수 있지만, sequence length에 따라 Attention이 quadratic하게 스케일링하므로 비용이 지나치게 크다. 실제로 대부분의 token은 전체 sequence에 대한 Global Attention이 필요하지 않으며 local context에만 의존할 수 있다. 이러한 통찰에 기반해, 우리는 token이 언제 Global Attention을 호출할지 결정함으로써 token-wise long-term conditional memory access를 가능하게 하는 sequence modeling layer인 L2A를 제안한다. 우리는 Qwen 2.5와 Qwen 3 모델에서 L2A를 평가했으며, effective context length를 32K에서 128K token으로 확장했다. 이때 L2A는 token의 약 80%에 대해 Global Attention을 건너뛰면서도 표준 long-context training과 1.5–3\\% 이내의 성능을 보였고, 기존 baseline보다 우수했다. 또한 GPU에서 이러한 token-wise conditional attention을 효율적으로 구현하기 위해 custom Triton kernel을 설계하여, FlashAttention-2 대비 training throughput과 time-to-first-token을 최대 약 2× 향상시켰다. 더 나아가 L2A는 매우 sparse한 Global Attention layer에 대한 post-training pruning을 가능하게 하여, 성능 저하를 거의 일으키지 않으면서 KV cache memory를 최대 50%까지 줄인다."},{"id":"61648","en":"InfoFlow KV: Information-Flow-Aware KV Recomputation for Long Context","ko":"InfoFlow KV: Long Context를 위한 Information-Flow-Aware KV 재계산","authors":"Xin Teng, Canyu Zhang, Shaoyi Zheng, Danyang Zhuo, Tianyi Zhou, Shenji Wan","pos":"#2707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=o8y6CoJsWA","abs":"<p>Retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) for long-context question answering is bottlenecked by inference-time prefilling over large retrieved contexts. A common strategy is to precompute key–value (KV) caches for individual documents and selectively recompute a small subset of tokens to restore global causal dependencies, but existing methods rely on heuristics or representation discrepancies without modeling whether selected tokens can effectively influence generation. We cast selective KV recomputation as an information flow problem and show that a simple attention-norm signal from the query reliably identifies tokens that are both semantically relevant and structurally positioned to propagate information, when computed under an inference-consistent RoPE geometry. We therefore reconstruct global positional assignments for retrieved chunks and introduce an information-flow–guided chunk reordering strategy. Experiments on LLM and VLM benchmarks demonstrate consistent gains over prior methods under comparable efficiency budgets.</p>","absKo":"<p>long-context question answering을 위한 retrieval-augmented generation(RAG)은 대규모 retrieved context에 대한 inference-time prefilling이 병목이 된다. 일반적인 전략은 개별 document에 대한 key-value(KV) cache를 미리 계산하고, 글로벌 causal dependency를 복원하기 위해 소수의 token만 선택적으로 재계산하는 것이다. 그러나 기존 방법은 선택된 token이 generation에 효과적으로 영향을 미칠 수 있는지 여부를 모델링하지 않은 채 heuristic이나 representation discrepancy에 의존한다. 우리는 selective KV recomputation을 information flow 문제로 정식화하고, inference-consistent RoPE geometry 하에서 계산된 query의 간단한 attention-norm signal이 의미적으로 관련이 있고 구조적으로 정보를 전파하기에 적절한 위치에 있는 token을 신뢰성 있게 식별함을 보인다. 따라서 우리는 retrieved chunk에 대한 global positional assignment를 재구성하고, information-flow-guided chunk reordering strategy를 도입한다. LLM과 VLM benchmark에서의 실험은 유사한 효율 예산 하에서 기존 방법보다 일관된 향상을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64718","en":"Towards Long-Horizon Interpretability: Efficient and Faithful Multi-Token Attribution for Reasoning LLMs","ko":"장기 지평 해석 가능성을 향하여: 추론 LLM을 위한 효율적이고 충실한 Multi-Token Attribution","authors":"Wenbo Pan, Zhichao Liu, Xianlong Wang, Yu Haining, Xiaohua Jia","pos":"#3200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KY5Q9V9F5C","abs":"Token attribution methods provide intuitive explanations for language model outputs by identifying causally important input tokens. However, as modern LLMs increasingly rely on extended reasoning chains, existing schemes face two critical challenges: (1) efficiency bottleneck, where attributing a sequence of $|\\mathbf{S}|$ tokens requires $\\mathcal{O}(|\\mathbf{S}|^2)$ operations, making long-context attribution prohibitively slow; and (2) faithfulness drop, where intermediate reasoning tokens absorb attribution mass, preventing importance from propagating back to the original input.  To address these, we introduce **FlashTrace**, an efficient multi-token attribution method that employs span-wise aggregation to compute attribution over *multi-token targets in a single pass*, reducing complexity to $\\mathcal{O}(|\\mathbf{S}|)$. Moreover, we design a recursive attribution mechanism that traces importance through intermediate reasoning chains back to source inputs. Extensive experiments on long-context retrieval (RULER) and multi-step reasoning (MATH, MorehopQA) tasks demonstrate that FlashTrace achieves over 130× speedup over existing baselines while maintaining superior faithfulness. We further analyze the dynamics of recursive attribution, showing that even a single recursive hop substantially improves faithfulness by tracing importance through the reasoning chain.","absKo":"Token attribution method는 입력 token 중 인과적으로 중요한 token을 식별함으로써 language model 출력에 대한 직관적인 설명을 제공한다. 그러나 현대의 LLM이 점점 더 긴 reasoning chain에 의존함에 따라, 기존 방식은 두 가지 중요한 도전에 직면한다. (1) efficiency bottleneck: 길이 $|\\mathbf{S}|$의 sequence에 attribution을 부여하려면 $\\mathcal{O}(|\\mathbf{S}|^2)$ 연산이 필요하여, long-context attribution이 지나치게 느려진다. (2) faithfulness 저하: 중간 reasoning token이 attribution mass를 흡수하여 중요도가 원래 입력으로 다시 전파되지 못한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 span-wise aggregation을 사용해 *multi-token target에 대한 attribution을 단일 pass로* 계산하는 효율적인 multi-token attribution method인 **FlashTrace**를 제안하며, 복잡도를 $\\mathcal{O}(|\\mathbf{S}|)$로 낮춘다. 또한 중간 reasoning chain을 통해 source input까지 중요도를 추적하는 recursive attribution mechanism을 설계한다. long-context retrieval (RULER)과 multi-step reasoning (MATH, MorehopQA) task에 대한 광범위한 실험은 FlashTrace가 우수한 faithfulness를 유지하면서 기존 baseline보다 130배 이상의 속도 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. 우리는 recursive attribution의 동역학을 추가로 분석하여, 단 한 번의 recursive hop만으로도 reasoning chain을 따라 중요도를 추적함으로써 faithfulness가 상당히 향상됨을 보인다."},{"id":"61615","en":"On the Limits of LLM Adaptability: Impact of LLM Pre-Training on Annotation Task Performance","ko":"LLM Adaptability의 한계: LLM Pre-Training이 Annotation Task 성능에 미치는 영향","authors":"Etienne Casanova, Rafal Kocielnik, R. Michael Alvarez","pos":"#3211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oTv2bKG5Qg","abs":"<p>Pre-trained Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly used for zero-shot annotation and LLM-as-a-judge tasks, yet their reliability hinges on how pre-trained priors interact with user-provided instructions. We investigate three dimensions of this interaction: (1) how an LLM’s familiarity with data and task definitions affects performance, (2) the extent to which additional information in prompts can correct zero-shot errors (“decision stickiness”), and (3) model susceptibility to misaligned task definitions. Through experiments on toxicity detection across diverse datasets (spanning social media, gaming, news, and forums) using both dense and mixture-of-experts models, we find that nearly two-thirds of zero-shot errors are resistant to correction, with an overall rescue rate (fraction of initial errors corrected by prompting) of only 36.4%. High-confidence errors prove especially resistant to correction. When given misaligned definitions, LLMs follow them while maintaining confidence levels unchanged from the aligned condition. Crucially, we introduce Definition-Specific Familiarity (DSF), a metric measuring alignment between a model’s internal concept and the task definition. After controlling for dataset-level confounds, DSF shows positive association with model performance (partial r = +0.34), while text memorization as measured by ROUGE-L shows no positive association (partial r = −0.19). Overall, these findings suggest clear limits on prompt-based correction in annotation tasks and underscore the importance of definition alignment over text-level memorization.</p>","absKo":"<p>사전학습된 Large Language Model(LLM)은 zero-shot annotation과 LLM-as-a-judge task에 점점 더 많이 사용되고 있지만, 그 신뢰성은 사전학습된 prior와 사용자가 제공한 instruction이 어떻게 상호작용하는지에 달려 있다. 우리는 이러한 상호작용의 세 가지 차원을 조사한다. (1) LLM의 데이터 및 task 정의에 대한 familiarity가 성능에 어떤 영향을 미치는지, (2) prompt에 추가 정보를 넣는 것이 zero-shot error를 얼마나 교정할 수 있는지(\"decision stickiness\"), (3) model이 잘못 정렬된 task 정의에 얼마나 취약한지이다. 소셜 미디어, 게임, 뉴스, 포럼에 걸친 다양한 dataset에서 dense model과 mixture-of-experts model을 모두 사용한 toxicity detection 실험을 통해, zero-shot error의 거의 3분의 2가 교정에 저항하며, 초기 error 중 prompting으로 교정되는 비율(rescue rate)은 36.4%에 불과함을 발견했다. 높은 confidence를 보이는 error는 특히 교정되기 어렵다. 잘못 정렬된 정의를 주면, LLM은 이를 따르면서도 aligned condition와 동일한 confidence 수준을 유지한다. 결정적으로, 우리는 model의 내부 개념과 task 정의 사이의 정렬을 측정하는 지표인 Definition-Specific Familiarity(DSF)를 도입한다. dataset 수준의 교란 요인을 통제한 후, DSF는 model performance와 양의 상관관계를 보였고(partial r = +0.34), 반면 ROUGE-L로 측정한 text memorization은 양의 상관관계를 보이지 않았다(partial r = −0.19). 전반적으로 이러한 결과는 annotation task에서 prompt 기반 교정의 명확한 한계를 시사하며, text-level memorization보다 definition alignment가 더 중요함을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"67091","en":"Position: LLMs can't jump","ko":"Position: LLM은 도약할 수 없다","authors":"Tom Zahavy","pos":"#3707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=klU4737opt","abs":"<p>How do we fundamentally discover new things? In a letter to Maurice Solovine, Albert Einstein conceptualized discovery as a cyclical process involving an intuitive 'jump' from sensory experience to axioms, followed by logical deduction. While Generative AI has mastered Induction (statistical pattern matching) and is rapidly conquering Deduction (formal proof), we argue it lacks the mechanism for Abduction—the generation of novel explanatory hypotheses. Using Einstein’s formulation of General Relativity as a computational case study, we demonstrate that the prevailing theory of \"creativity as data compression\" (induction) fails to account for discoveries where observational data is scarce. This position paper argues that while a modern Large Language Model could plausibly execute the deductive phase of proving theorems from established premises, it is structurally incapable of the abductive 'Jump' required to formulate those premises. We identify the translation of simulation into formal axioms as the critical bottleneck in artificial scientific invention, and propose that physically consistent, multimodal world models offer the necessary sensory grounding to bridge this divide.</p>"},{"id":"66752","en":"DTKG: Dual-Track Knowledge Graph-Verified Reasoning Framework for Multi-Hop QA","ko":"DTKG: Multi-Hop QA를 위한 Dual-Track Knowledge Graph 검증 추론 프레임워크","authors":"Changhao Wang, Yanfang Liu, Xinxin Fan, Lanzhi Zhou, Ao Tian, Yunfeng Lu","pos":"#4624","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0dd6iMYtwB","abs":"<p>Multi-hop reasoning for question answering (QA) plays a critical role in retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) for large language models (LLMs). Based on inherent relation-dependency and reasoning patterns, it is categorized into parallel fact-verification (simultaneously verifying independent sub-questions) and chained reasoning (sequential multi-step inference). Existing approaches adopt either LLM-based fact verification or KG path-based chain construction, failing to handle both categories well: the former underperforms on chained reasoning, while the latter suffers from redundant paths in parallel tasks. Inspired by the Dual Process Theory in cognitive science and Stanovich’s Cognitive Misers Theory, we propose an effective multi-hop QA framework DTKG (Dual-Track Knowledge Graph) through building a two-stage pipeline: i) Classification Stage (dynamic question categorization via few-shot prompting, emulating \"unconscious processing\"); and ii) Branch Processing Stage (tailored reasoning paths, emulating \"conscious processing\"). Multi-facet experiments on six datasets show DTKG achieves 5.0\\%-29.5\\% performance improvement. The code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DTKG-621F</p>"},{"id":"67073","en":"Position: Multiplicity is an Inevitable and Inherent Challenge in Multimodal Learning","ko":"Position: 다중성은 멀티모달 학습에서 불가피하고 내재적인 도전 과제이다","authors":"Sanghyuk Chun, Olga Russakovsky","pos":"#1000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oKUeKBYpXC","abs":"<p>Multimodal learning has seen remarkable progress, particularly with large-scale pre-training across various modalities. Most current approaches are built on the assumption of a deterministic one-to-one alignment between modalities. However, this oversimplifies real-world multimodal relationships, where their nature is inherently many-to-many. The many-to-many property, or \\emph{multiplicity}, is not a side-effect of noise or annotation error, but an inevitable outcome of intra-modal variability, representational asymmetry, and task-dependent ambiguity in multimodal tasks. We argue that multiplicity is a fundamental bottleneck that affects all stages of the multimodal learning pipeline: from data construction to model training and evaluation benchmarks. By formalizing its causes and consequences, we demonstrate how ignoring multiplicity leads to training uncertainty, unreliable evaluation, and degraded dataset quality. This position paper calls for new research directions on multimodal learning, including multiplicity-aware learning frameworks and dataset construction and evaluation protocols.</p>"},{"id":"64765","en":"The Power of Power Law: Asymmetry Enables Compositional Reasoning","ko":"Power Law의 힘: 비대칭성이 조합적 추론을 가능케 한다","authors":"Zixuan Wang, Xingyu Dang, Jason Lee, Kaifeng Lyu","pos":"#1200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=K83orsg2X9","abs":"<p>Natural language data follows a power-law distribution, with most knowledge and skills appearing at very low frequency. While a common intuition suggests that reweighting or curating data toward a uniform distribution may help models better learn these long-tail skills, we find a counterintuitive result: across a wide range of compositional reasoning tasks, such as state tracking and multi-step arithmetic, training under power-law distributions consistently outperforms training under uniform distributions. To understand this advantage, we introduce a minimalist skill-composition task and show that learning under a power-law distribution provably requires significantly less training data. Our theoretical analysis reveals that power law sampling induces a beneficial asymmetry that improves the pathological loss landscape, which enables models to first acquire high-frequency skill compositions with low data complexity, which in turn serves as a stepping stone to efficiently learn rare long-tailed skills. Our results offer an alternative perspective on what constitutes an effective data distribution for training models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Natural language data는 power-law distribution을 따르며, 대부분의 knowledge와 skill은 매우 낮은 frequency로 나타난다. 흔한 직관은 data를 uniform distribution 쪽으로 reweight하거나 curate하면 model이 이러한 long-tail skill을 더 잘 학습할 수 있다는 것이지만, 우리는 반직관적인 결과를 발견했다. state tracking과 multi-step arithmetic 같은 다양한 compositional reasoning task 전반에서, power-law distribution 하에서의 training이 uniform distribution 하에서의 training보다 일관되게 더 우수했다. 이 이점을 이해하기 위해, 우리는 최소주의적 skill-composition task를 도입하고 power-law distribution 하에서의 학습이 이론적으로 훨씬 더 적은 training data를 요구함을 보인다. 우리의 이론적 분석은 power law sampling이 유익한 비대칭성을 유도하여 병적인 loss landscape를 개선한다는 점을 보여준다. 이는 model이 먼저 낮은 data complexity로 고빈도 skill composition을 습득하게 하고, 그 결과 희귀한 long-tailed skill을 효율적으로 학습하는 발판이 된다. 우리의 결과는 model 학습에 효과적인 data distribution이 무엇인지에 대해 대안적 관점을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"62448","en":"The Stability of Singular Distribution: A Spectral Perspective on the Two-Phase Dynamics of Language Model Pre-training","ko":"Singular Distribution의 안정성: 언어 모델 사전학습의 2단계 동역학에 대한 Spectral 관점","authors":"Hongtao Zhang, WenJie Zhou, Chenxi Jia, Wei Chen, Xueqi Cheng","pos":"#1201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gVPwive1z6","abs":"<p>Large language model pre-training typically exhibits a two-phase trajectory: a fast initial loss drop followed by a prolonged slow improvement. We identify an underlying spectral phenomenon, Stability of Singular Distribution (SoSD), where the trace-normalized singular value spectrum stabilizes early, even as parameter matrices continue to evolve. We demonstrate that synchronization between SoSD and the slow-descent regime is widely observed across diverse architectures (GPT-2, LLaMA) and settings, including various schedules (Step-wise, WSD, Cosine Decay), weight decays, and optimizers (AdamW, Muon). By analyzing a simplified Transformer, we prove that growing weight norms inevitably precipitate an early SoSD threshold, after which the rate of loss decrease becomes theoretically bounded by the variation in the singular distribution. We further interpret strategies like WSD and Muon through their ability to modulate the SoSD scale, offering a spectral lens for understanding efficient pre-training dynamics.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델의 pre-training은 일반적으로 두 단계의 궤적을 보인다. 즉, 초기에 loss가 빠르게 감소한 뒤 장기간에 걸쳐 느리게 개선된다. 우리는 Singular Distribution의 Stability(SoSD)라는 근저의 spectral 현상을 식별했는데, 여기서 trace-normalized singular value spectrum은 parameter matrix가 계속 진화하더라도 초기에 안정화된다. 우리는 SoSD와 slow-descent regime의 동기화가 GPT-2, LLaMA와 같은 다양한 architecture와 다양한 schedule(Step-wise, WSD, Cosine Decay), weight decay, optimizer(AdamW, Muon)를 포함한 여러 설정 전반에서 널리 관찰됨을 보인다. 단순화된 Transformer를 분석함으로써, 증가하는 weight norm이 필연적으로 초기 SoSD threshold를 유발하며, 그 이후 loss 감소율은 이론적으로 singular distribution의 변화에 의해 제한됨을 증명한다. 또한 우리는 WSD와 Muon 같은 전략을 SoSD scale을 조절하는 능력으로 해석하며, 효율적인 pre-training dynamics를 이해하기 위한 spectral 관점을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"62532","en":"Transformers learn factored representations","ko":"Transformer는 factored representation을 학습한다","authors":"Adam Shai, Loren Amdahl-Culleton, Casper Christensen, Henry R Bigelow, Fernando Rosas, Alexander Boyd, Eric Alt, Kyle Ray, Paul Riechers","pos":"#1203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=flDGB9On0h","abs":"<p>Transformers pretrained via next token prediction learn to factor their world into parts, representing these factors in orthogonal subspaces of the residual stream. We formalize two representational hypotheses: (1) a representation in the product space of all factors, whose dimension grows exponentially with the number of parts, or (2) a factored representation in orthogonal subspaces, whose dimension grows linearly. Both track context-induced uncertainty over the latent parts, but the factored representation sacrifices fidelity when factors are not conditionally independent. We derive precise predictions about the geometric structure of activations for each, including the number of subspaces, their dimensionality, and the arrangement of context embeddings within them. We test between these hypotheses on transformers trained on synthetic processes with known latent structure. When factors are conditionally independent, models learn factored representations; when noise or dependencies break this structure, models gradually expand their effective dimensionality over training to recover fidelity. This provides a principled explanation for why transformers decompose the world into parts, and suggests that interpretable low dimensional structure may persist even in models trained on complex data.</p>","absKo":"<p>next token prediction으로 사전 학습된 Transformer는 자신의 세계를 여러 부분으로 분해해 학습하며, 이러한 요인들을 residual stream의 orthogonal subspace에 표현한다. 우리는 두 가지 표현 가설을 정식화한다. (1) 모든 요인의 product space에 대한 표현으로, 그 차원은 부분의 수에 따라 지수적으로 증가한다. (2) orthogonal subspace에 factored representation으로, 그 차원은 선형적으로 증가한다. 두 가설 모두 latent part에 대한 context-induced uncertainty를 추적하지만, 요인들이 conditional independence를 만족하지 않을 때 factored representation은 fidelity를 희생한다. 우리는 각 경우에 대해 activation의 기하학적 구조에 관한 정밀한 예측을 도출하는데, 여기에는 subspace의 개수, 차원성, 그리고 그 안에서 context embedding이 배치되는 방식이 포함된다. 우리는 알려진 latent structure를 가진 synthetic process로 학습된 Transformer에서 이 두 가설을 검정한다. 요인들이 conditional independent일 때 모델은 factored representation을 학습하고, noise나 dependency가 이 구조를 무너뜨릴 때 모델은 학습 과정에서 effective dimensionality를 점진적으로 확장하여 fidelity를 회복한다. 이는 Transformer가 왜 세계를 부분들로 분해하는지에 대한 원리적인 설명을 제공하며, 복잡한 데이터로 학습된 모델에서도 해석 가능한 저차원 구조가 지속될 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"62120","en":"Turning Drift into Constraint: Robust Reasoning Alignment in Non-Stationary Multi-Stream Environments","ko":"Drift를 제약으로 바꾸기: 비정상 다중 스트림 환경에서의 강건한 추론 정렬","authors":"Xiaoyu Yang, Jie Lu, Wei Duan, En Yu","pos":"#1204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jgebUtw1lA","abs":"<p>This paper identifies a critical yet underexplored challenge in reasoning alignment from multiple multi-modal large language models (MLLMs): In non-stationary environments, the diverse reasoning distributions of source models often evolve unpredictably, transmitting systematic biases and drift to the target model. To address this, we formulate multi-source reasoning alignment as a constraint satisfaction problem under concept drift theory. We propose Autonomous Preference Optimization (APO), a novel framework that treats inter-model divergences not as noise, but as dynamic negative constraints. APO operates via a two-stage protocol: first, supervised bootstrapping projects the target model into the capability union of source models; second, constraint-aware optimization synthesizes a consistent consensus manifold by explicitly suppressing drifting trajectories via a multi-negative plackett-luce objective. Extensive experiments on chest X-ray interpretation demonstrate that our 7B model achieves superior robustness, outperforming even proprietary source models in average accuracy. Furthermore, we release CXR-MAX, a large-scale benchmark comprising 170,982 reasoning trajectories from seven large-scale MLLMs to facilitate research on reasoning alignment under drift. Code and data are available at:  https://anonymous.4open.science/r/APO.</p>","absKo":"<p>본 논문은 여러 multi-modal large language model(MLLM)로부터의 reasoning alignment에서 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않은 중요한 도전 과제를 식별한다. 비정상적(non-stationary) 환경에서는 source model들의 다양한 reasoning distribution이 종종 예측 불가능하게 진화하며, 체계적 bias와 drift를 target model로 전달한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 multi-source reasoning alignment를 concept drift theory 하의 constraint satisfaction problem으로 정식화한다. 우리는 Autonomous Preference Optimization(APO)을 제안하는데, 이는 모델 간 divergence를 noise가 아니라 동적인 negative constraint로 다루는 새로운 프레임워크이다. APO는 두 단계 프로토콜로 동작한다. 첫째, supervised bootstrapping이 target model을 source model들의 capability union으로 투영한다. 둘째, constraint-aware optimization이 multi-negative plackett-luce objective를 통해 drifting trajectory를 명시적으로 억제함으로써 일관된 consensus manifold를 합성한다. chest X-ray interpretation에 대한 광범위한 실험에서, 우리의 7B 모델은 평균 정확도에서 독점 source model보다도 우수한 robustness를 달성함을 보인다. 또한 우리는 drift 하의 reasoning alignment 연구를 촉진하기 위해, 7개의 대규모 MLLM으로부터 수집한 170,982개의 reasoning trajectory를 포함하는 대규모 benchmark인 CXR-MAX를 공개한다. Code and data are available at:  https://anonymous.4open.science/r/APO.</p>"},{"id":"63447","en":"The Geometric Mechanics of Contrastive Representation Learning: Alignment Potentials, Entropic Dispersion, and Cross-Modal Divergence","ko":"대조 표현 학습의 기하-역학: 정렬 잠재력, 엔트로피 분산, 교차 모달 발산","authors":"Yichao Cai, Zhen Zhang, Yuhang Liu, Javen Qinfeng Shi","pos":"#1300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=X9VtjdBlQw","abs":"<p>While InfoNCE powers modern contrastive learning, its geometric mechanisms remain under-characterized beyond the canonical alignment--uniformity decomposition. We present a measure-theoretic framework that models learning as the evolution of representation measures on a fixed embedding manifold. By establishing value and gradient consistency in the large-batch limit, we bridge the stochastic objective to explicit deterministic energy landscapes, uncovering a fundamental geometric bifurcation between the unimodal and multimodal regimes. In the unimodal setting, the intrinsic landscape is strictly convex with a unique Gibbs equilibrium; here, entropy acts merely as a tie-breaker, clarifying \"uniformity\" as a constrained expansion within the alignment basin. In contrast, the symmetric multimodal objective contains a persistent negative symmetric divergence term that remains even after kernel sharpening. We show that this term induces barrier-driven co-adaptation, enforcing a population-level modality gap as a structural geometric necessity rather than an initialization artifact. Our results shift the analytical lens from pointwise discrimination to population geometry, offering a principled basis for diagnosing and controlling distributional misalignment.</p>","absKo":"<p>InfoNCE는 현대 contrastive learning을 구동하지만, 그 기하학적 메커니즘은 canonical alignment--uniformity decomposition을 넘어서서는 아직 충분히 규명되지 않았다. 우리는 고정된 embedding manifold 위에서 representation measure의 진화로 학습을 모델링하는 measure-theoretic framework를 제시한다. 대규모 batch 한계에서 value와 gradient consistency를 확립함으로써, 우리는 stochastic objective를 명시적인 deterministic energy landscape와 연결하고, unimodal regime과 multimodal regime 사이의 근본적인 기하학적 bifurcation을 밝혀낸다. unimodal 설정에서는 intrinsic landscape가 유일한 Gibbs equilibrium을 갖는 엄격한 convex 형태를 띠며, 여기서 entropy는 단지 tie-breaker로 작용할 뿐이다. 이는 \"uniformity\"를 alignment basin 내부의 제약된 확장으로 명확히 해석하게 한다. 반대로, symmetric multimodal objective는 kernel sharpening 이후에도 남아 있는 지속적인 negative symmetric divergence term을 포함한다. 우리는 이 항이 barrier-driven co-adaptation을 유도하여, population 수준의 modality gap을 초기화 산물이 아니라 구조적 기하학적 필요성으로 강제함을 보인다. 우리의 결과는 분석의 초점을 pointwise discrimination에서 population geometry로 전환하며, distributional misalignment를 진단하고 제어하기 위한 원리적 기반을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"64334","en":"The Expressive Power of Low Precision Softmax Transformers with (Summarized) Chain-of-Thought","ko":"(요약된) Chain-of-Thought를 갖는 저정밀 Softmax Transformer의 표현력","authors":"Moritz Brösamle, Stephan Eckstein","pos":"#1301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OehZzGGY7Z","abs":"<p>Existing expressivity results for transformers typically rely on hardmax attention, high precision, and other architectural modifications that disconnect them from the models used in practice. We bridge this gap by analyzing standard transformer decoders with softmax attention and rounding of activations and attention weights, while allowing depth and width to grow logarithmically with the context length. As an intermediate step, we construct hardmax transformers with ternary activations and well-separated attention scores that simulate Turing machines using Chain-of-Thought (CoT). This lets us convert the constructions to equivalent softmax transformers without the unrealistic parameter magnitudes or activation precision that prior approaches would require. Using the same technique, we analyze a recently proposed summarized CoT paradigm (InftyThink) and show that it simulates Turing machines more efficiently, with model size scaling logarithmically in a space bound rather than a time bound. We empirically demonstrate this advantage by training small transformers to solve Sudokus almost perfectly with summarized CoT, even on instances requiring more than a million reasoning tokens.</p>","absKo":"<p>transformer의 expressivity에 대한 기존 결과는 대개 hardmax attention, 고정밀도, 그리고 실제 사용 모델과 분리되는 다른 architecture 수정에 의존한다. 우리는 softmax attention을 사용하는 표준 transformer decoder와 activation 및 attention weight의 rounding을 분석하면서, depth와 width가 context length에 대해 로그적으로 증가하도록 허용함으로써 이 간극을 메운다. 중간 단계로, 우리는 ternary activation과 잘 분리된 attention score를 갖는 hardmax transformer를 구성하고, Chain-of-Thought (CoT)를 사용해 Turing machine을 시뮬레이션한다. 이를 통해 기존 접근법이 요구하던 비현실적인 parameter magnitude나 activation precision 없이도, 해당 구성들을 동등한 softmax transformer로 변환할 수 있다. 같은 기법을 사용해, 우리는 최근 제안된 summarized CoT 패러다임(InftyThink)을 분석하고, 그것이 Turing machine을 더 효율적으로 시뮬레이션하며 model size가 time bound가 아니라 space bound에 대해 로그적으로 스케일링함을 보인다. 우리는 summarized CoT로 작은 transformer를 학습시켜 Sudoku를 거의 완벽하게 푸는 방식으로 이 장점을 실증하며, 백만 개가 넘는 reasoning token이 필요한 instance에서도 이를 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"65006","en":"TPV: Parameter Perturbations Through the Lens of Test Prediction Variance","ko":"TPV: Test Prediction Variance의 관점을 통한 Parameter Perturbation","authors":"Devansh Arpit","pos":"#1302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HskjhAfdY4","abs":"We identify test prediction variance (TPV)—the first-order sensitivity of model outputs to parameter perturbations around a trained solution—as a unifying quantity that links several classical observations about generalization in deep networks. TPV is a fully label-free object whose trace form $\\mathrm{Tr}(H_{\\mathrm{eff}} C)$ separates the geometry of the trained model $H_{\\mathrm{eff}}$ from the specific perturbation mechanism $C$, allowing a broad family of parameter perturbations like SGD noise, label noise, finite-precision noise, and other post-training perturbations to be analyzed under a single framework.  Theoretically, we show that TPV estimated on the training set converges to its test-set value in the overparameterized limit, providing the first result that prediction variance under local parameter perturbations can be inferred from training inputs alone, and this stability is decoupled from generalization performance. Empirically, TPV exhibits a striking stability across datasets and architectures even for extremely narrow networks. Further, TPV correlates well with test loss, serving as a training-set based predictive metric for generalization.","absKo":"우리는 test prediction variance(TPV)라 불리는, 학습된 해 주변에서 파라미터 섭동에 대한 모델 출력의 1차 민감도를 딥 네트워크의 일반화에 관한 여러 고전적 관찰을 연결하는 통합적 quantity로 식별한다. TPV는 완전히 label-free인 객체로서, 그 trace form $\\mathrm{Tr}(H_{\\mathrm{eff}} C)$는 학습된 모델의 기하 $H_{\\mathrm{eff}}$와 특정 섭동 메커니즘 $C$를 분리해 주므로, SGD noise, label noise, finite-precision noise, 그리고 기타 post-training perturbation 같은 다양한 parameter perturbation을 하나의 프레임워크 아래에서 분석할 수 있게 한다. 이론적으로, 우리는 training set에서 추정한 TPV가 overparameterized limit에서 test-set 값으로 수렴함을 보이며, 이는 local parameter perturbation 하의 prediction variance를 training input만으로 추론할 수 있음을 보여 주는 최초의 결과이고, 이러한 안정성은 generalization performance와는 분리되어 있다. 실험적으로 TPV는 매우 좁은 network에서도 dataset과 architecture 전반에 걸쳐 놀라운 안정성을 보인다. 또한 TPV는 test loss와도 잘 상관되어, training-set 기반의 generalization 예측 metric으로 기능한다."},{"id":"61515","en":"Scalable Kronecker-Factored Fisher Approximation for Neural Network Parameter Sensitivity","ko":"Neural Network Parameter Sensitivity를 위한 확장 가능한 Kronecker-Factored Fisher Approximation","authors":"Viktoriia Chekalina, Daniil Moskovskiy, Tatyana Matveeva, Andrey Kuznetsov, Evgeny Frolov","pos":"#1304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pNe5fVK1tR","abs":"<p>The Fisher Information Matrix (FIM) provides a principled geometric framework for parameter sensitivity in neural networks, but directly computing and using the full FIM is infeasible in high-dimensional models. As a result, most existing methods rely on diagonal approximations that discard important correlation structure.  We introduce Matrix-free Fisher Factorization (MFF), a GPU-tractable algorithm that captures both diagonal and off-diagonal dependencies without materializing the full matrix. For post-training neural network layer compression, we prove that under Matrix-Variate Normal assumptions, MFF yields GFWSVD, a unique closed-form linear layer decomposition that optimally minimizes the expected second-order loss increase.  Experiments on controlled numerical benchmarks with large neural networks show that GFWSVD achieves up to 50\\% compression while matching or exceeding state-of-the-art diagonal and activation-based baselines across most tasks, and it reliably avoids collapse in dense architectures such as Llama 3. Moreover, when used to initialize existing optimization pipelines (e.g., Dobi-SVD), GFWSVD better preserves accuracy at 40\\% parameter reduction in regimes where standard methods substantially degrade. Together, these results position MFF and GFWSVD as foundational algorithmic primitives for scalable, second-order-aware neural network approximation and parameter sensitivity.</p>","absKo":"<p>Fisher Information Matrix(FIM)는 neural network에서 parameter sensitivity를 위한 원리적인 기하학적 framework를 제공하지만, full FIM을 직접 계산하고 사용하는 것은 고차원 model에서 비현실적이다. 그 결과 대부분의 기존 방법은 중요한 상관 구조를 버리는 diagonal approximation에 의존한다. 우리는 full matrix를 materialize하지 않으면서 diagonal 및 off-diagonal dependency를 모두 포착하는 GPU-tractable algorithm인 Matrix-free Fisher Factorization(MFF)를 제안한다. post-training neural network layer compression의 경우, Matrix-Variate Normal 가정하에서 MFF가 GFWSVD를 유도함을 증명한다. GFWSVD는 기대되는 2차 loss 증가를 최적으로 최소화하는 유일한 closed-form linear layer decomposition이다. 대규모 neural network를 사용한 통제된 numerical benchmark 실험에서 GFWSVD는 최대 50\\% compression을 달성하면서 대부분의 task에서 최신 diagonal 및 activation-based baseline과 동등하거나 더 나은 성능을 보이며, Llama 3와 같은 dense architecture에서 collapse를 안정적으로 회피한다. 또한 기존 optimization pipeline(e.g., Dobi-SVD)의 초기화에 사용될 때, GFWSVD는 표준 방법이 크게 성능을 저하시키는 구간에서 40\\% parameter reduction 하에서도 정확도를 더 잘 보존한다. 종합하면, 이러한 결과는 MFF와 GFWSVD를 확장 가능하고 second-order-aware한 neural network approximation 및 parameter sensitivity를 위한 기초 알고리즘 primitive로 자리매김하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"63229","en":"Robustness of Mixtures of Experts to Feature Noise","ko":"특징 노이즈에 대한 Mixture of Experts의 견고성","authors":"Dong Sun, Rahul Nittala, Rebekka Burkholz","pos":"#1305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ytwumy5fpJ","abs":"<p>Despite their practical success, it remains unclear why Mixture of Experts (MoE) models can outperform dense networks beyond sheer parameter scaling. We study an iso-parameter regime where inputs exhibit latent modular structure but are corrupted by feature noise, a proxy for noisy internal activations. We show that sparse expert activation acts as a noise filter: compared to a dense estimator, MoEs achieve lower generalization error under feature noise, improved robustness to perturbations, and faster convergence speed. Empirical results on synthetic data and real-world language tasks corroborate the theoretical insights, demonstrating consistent robustness and efficiency gains from sparse modular computation.</p>","absKo":"<p>실용적인 성공에도 불구하고, Mixture of Experts (MoE) model이 단순한 parameter scaling을 넘어 dense network보다 왜 우수한지 여전히 명확하지 않다. 우리는 입력이 latent modular structure를 가지지만 feature noise에 의해 오염되는 iso-parameter regime을 연구한다. 이는 noisy internal activation의 proxy이다. 우리는 sparse expert activation이 noise filter로 작동함을 보인다. dense estimator와 비교했을 때 MoE는 feature noise 하에서 더 낮은 generalization error, 더 나은 perturbation robustness, 더 빠른 convergence speed를 달성한다. synthetic data와 실제 language task에서의 경험적 결과는 이러한 이론적 통찰을 뒷받침하며, sparse modular computation이 일관된 robustness와 efficiency 향상을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63004","en":"Revisiting the Volume Hypothesis","ko":"Volume Hypothesis 재조명","authors":"Ari Pakman, Lior Kreimer, Yakir Berchenko","pos":"#1306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=b0agSl1SMw","abs":"<p>Modern deep neural networks often contain far more parameters than needed to fit their training data, yet they achieve impressive generalization. A common  explanation of this success is the implicit bias of stochastic gradient descent (SGD). An alternative volume hypothesis posits that, within low training-loss regions, loss-landscape basins leading to strong generalization occupy much larger regions of weight space than basins that generalize poorly, and therefore SGD is simply more likely to land in the former. Recent experimental explorations of this idea present seemingly contradictory results. While in one set of experiments randomly sampling the network weights until achieving zero training error yielded poor generalization, molecular-dynamics density estimates supported the volume hypothesis. We observe that these experiments were performed at different dataset size regimes, and explore an intermediate regime using the Replica Exchange Wang–Landau algorithm to estimate the joint density of states over training and test accuracies in binary networks. Across several architectures and datasets, we show that the generalization advantage of SGD over random sampling training diminishes as the training data size grows, suggesting a resolution of the paradox.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대의 deep neural network는 종종 training data에 맞추는 데 필요한 것보다 훨씬 더 많은 parameter를 포함하지만, 그럼에도 인상적인 generalization을 달성한다. 이러한 성공에 대한 흔한 설명은 stochastic gradient descent(SGD)의 implicit bias이다. 대안적인 volume hypothesis는 low training-loss region 내부에서, 강한 generalization으로 이어지는 loss-landscape basin이 generalization이 약한 basin보다 weight space에서 훨씬 더 큰 영역을 차지하므로, SGD는 단지 전자의 basin에 더 들어갈 가능성이 높을 뿐이라고 주장한다. 이 아이디어에 대한 최근의 실험적 탐구들은 언뜻 모순되는 결과를 제시한다. 한 실험군에서는 network weight를 무작위로 sampling하여 zero training error에 도달할 때까지 진행했을 때 generalization이 좋지 않았던 반면, molecular-dynamics density estimate는 volume hypothesis를 지지했다. 우리는 이러한 실험들이 서로 다른 dataset size regime에서 수행되었음을 관찰하고, binary network에서 training 및 test accuracy에 대한 joint density of states를 추정하기 위해 Replica Exchange Wang–Landau algorithm을 사용하여 중간 regime를 탐구한다. 여러 architecture와 dataset에 걸쳐, training data size가 커질수록 random sampling training에 대한 SGD의 generalization 우위가 약해진다는 것을 보이며, 이는 이 역설에 대한 해소를 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61683","en":"Post-Training with Policy Gradients: Optimality and the Base Model Barrier","ko":"Policy Gradient를 활용한 Post-Training: 최적성과 Base Model Barrier","authors":"Alireza Mousavi-Hosseini, Murat Erdogdu","pos":"#1307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nnWlTi7A7a","abs":"We study post-training linear autoregressive models with outcome and process rewards. Given a context $\\boldsymbol{x}$, the model must predict the response $\\boldsymbol{y} \\in \\mathcal{Y}^N$, a sequence of length $N$ that satisfies a standard $\\gamma$ margin assumption extended to sequences. We prove that on test samples where the base model achieves a non-trivial likelihood $\\alpha$, a variant of policy gradient (PG) can achieve likelihood $1 - \\varepsilon$ with an essentially minimax optimal number of reward queries $\\tilde{\\mathcal{O}}((\\alpha^{-1} + \\varepsilon^{-1})/\\gamma^2)$. However, a barrier arises for going beyond the support of the base model. We prove that the overall expected error after post-training with outcome rewards is governed by a property of the base model we call the *Likelihood Quantile* (LQ), and that variants of PG, while minimax optimal, may require a number of reward queries exponential in $N$ to go beyond this support, regardless of the pre-training algorithm. To overcome this barrier, we study post-training with a process reward model, and demonstrate how PG variants in this setting avoid the curse of dimensionality in $N$ via dependence on a token-level LQ. Along the way, we prove that under the margin condition, SGD with adaptive learning rate (LR) achieves a near optimal test error for statistical learning, and PG with adaptive LR achieves a near optimal number of mistakes for online learning while being computationally efficient whenever possible, both of which may be of independent interest.","absKo":"우리는 outcome reward와 process reward를 사용하는 post-training linear autoregressive model을 연구한다. context $\\boldsymbol{x}$가 주어지면, 모델은 길이 $N$의 sequence인 response $\\boldsymbol{y} \\in \\mathcal{Y}^N$를 예측해야 하며, 이는 sequence로 확장된 표준 $\\gamma$ margin assumption을 만족해야 한다. base model이 test sample에서 비자명한 likelihood $\\alpha$를 달성하는 경우, policy gradient(PG)의 변형이 본질적으로 minimax optimal한 reward query 수 $\\tilde{\\mathcal{O}}((\\alpha^{-1} + \\varepsilon^{-1})/\\gamma^2)$로 likelihood $1 - \\varepsilon$를 달성할 수 있음을 증명한다. 그러나 base model의 support를 넘어서는 데에는 장벽이 존재한다. 우리는 outcome reward로 post-training한 뒤의 전체 기대 error가 base model의 우리가 Likelihood Quantile(LQ)라고 부르는 성질에 의해 지배됨을 보이고, PG 변형은 minimax optimal하더라도 pre-training algorithm과 무관하게 이 support를 넘어가기 위해 $N$에 대해 지수적으로 많은 reward query가 필요할 수 있음을 증명한다. 이 장벽을 극복하기 위해 우리는 process reward model을 이용한 post-training을 연구하고, 이 설정에서 PG 변형이 token-level LQ에 의존함으로써 $N$에 대한 curse of dimensionality를 피하는 방식을 보인다. 이와 함께, margin condition 하에서 adaptive learning rate(LR)를 사용하는 SGD가 statistical learning에서 거의 최적의 test error를 달성하고, adaptive LR를 사용하는 PG는 가능한 경우 계산적으로 효율적이면서 online learning에서 거의 최적의 mistake 수를 달성함을 증명한다. 이 두 결과는 독립적으로도 유의미할 수 있다."},{"id":"68800","en":"Optimization Dynamics of Equivariant and Augmented Neural Networks","ko":"Equivariant 및 Augmented 신경망의 최적화 동역학","authors":"Oskar Nordenfors, Fredrik Ohlsson, Axel Flinth","pos":"#1308","abs":"<p>We investigate the optimization of neural networks on symmetric data, and compare the strategy of constraining the architecture to be equivariant to that of using data augmentation. Our analysis reveals that the relative geometry of the admissible and the equivariant layers, respectively, plays a key role. Under natural assumptions on the data, network, loss, and group of symmetries, we show that compatibility of the spaces of admissible layers and equivariant layers, in the sense that the corresponding orthogonal projections commute, implies that the sets of equivariant stationary points are identical for the two strategies. If the linear layers of the network also are given a unitary parametrization, the set of equivariant layers is even invariant under the gradient flow for augmented models. Our analysis however also reveals that even in the latter situation, stationary points may be unstable for augmented training although they are stable for the manifestly equivariant models.</p>"},{"id":"60640","en":"Improved Scaling Laws via Weak-to-Strong Generalization in Random Features Ridge Regression","ko":"Random Features Ridge Regression에서 Weak-to-Strong Generalization을 통한 개선된 Scaling Law","authors":"Diyuan Wu, Lehan Chen, Theodor Misiakiewicz, Marco Mondelli","pos":"#1311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yE3zbIOW3e","abs":"<p>It is increasingly common in machine learning to use learned models to label data and then employ such data to train more capable models. The phenomenon of weak-to-strong generalization exemplifies the advantage of this two-stage procedure: a strong student is trained on imperfect labels obtained from a weak teacher, and yet the strong student outperforms the weak teacher. In this paper, we show that the potential improvement is substantial, in the sense that it affects the scaling law followed by the test error. Specifically, we consider students and teachers trained via random features ridge regression (RFRR). Our main technical contribution is to derive a deterministic equivalent for the excess test error of the student trained on labels obtained via the teacher. Via this deterministic equivalent, we then identify regimes in which the scaling law of the student improves upon that of the teacher, unveiling that the improvement can be achieved both in bias-dominated and variance-dominated settings. Strikingly, the student may attain the minimax optimal rate regardless of the scaling law of the teacher---in fact, when the test error of the teacher does not even decay with the sample size.</p>","absKo":"<p>machine learning에서 learned model로 데이터를 label한 뒤, 그 데이터를 사용해 더 강력한 model을 학습하는 일이 점점 더 흔해지고 있다. weak-to-strong generalization 현상은 이러한 two-stage procedure의 이점을 잘 보여준다. 즉, weak teacher로부터 얻은 imperfect label로 strong student를 학습시키면, strong student가 weak teacher보다 더 나은 성능을 보인다. 본 논문에서는 이러한 잠재적 개선이 test error가 따르는 scaling law 자체에 영향을 줄 정도로 상당하다는 점을 보인다. 구체적으로, 우리는 random features ridge regression(RFRR)으로 학습된 student와 teacher를 고려한다. 우리의 주요 기술적 기여는 teacher를 통해 얻은 label로 학습한 student의 excess test error에 대한 deterministic equivalent를 유도한 것이다. 이 deterministic equivalent를 통해 우리는 student의 scaling law가 teacher의 것보다 개선되는 regime를 식별하고, 그 개선이 bias-dominated setting과 variance-dominated setting 모두에서 가능함을 밝힌다. 특히 student는 teacher의 scaling law와 무관하게 minimax optimal rate를 달성할 수 있으며, 실제로 teacher의 test error가 sample size가 증가해도 감소하지 않는 경우조차 그러하다.</p>"},{"id":"62595","en":"Hyperparameter Transfer with Mixture-of-Expert Layers","ko":"Mixture-of-Expert Layers를 이용한 Hyperparameter Transfer","authors":"Tianze Jiang, Blake Bordelon, Cengiz Pehlevan, Boris Hanin","pos":"#1312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fD36uwJ5oV","abs":"<p>Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) layers have emerged as an important tool in scaling up modern neural networks by decoupling total trainable parameters from activated parameters in the forward pass for each token. However, sparse MoEs add complexity to training due to (i) new trainable parameters (router weights) that, like all other parameter groups, require hyperparameter (HP) tuning; (ii) new architecture scale dimensions (number of and size of experts) that must be chosen and potentially taken large. To make HP selection cheap and reliable, we propose a new parameterization for transformer models with MoE layers when scaling model width, depth, number of experts,  <em>and</em> expert (hidden) size. Our parameterization is justified by a novel dynamical mean-field theory (DMFT) analysis. When varying different model dimensions trained at a fixed token budget, we find empirically that our parameterization enables reliable HP transfer across models from 51M to 2B total parameters. We further take HPs identified from sweeping small models on a short token horizon to train larger models on longer horizons and report performant model behaviors.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mixture-of-Experts(MoE) layer는 각 token의 forward pass에서 활성화되는 parameter와 전체 학습 가능한 parameter를 분리함으로써 현대 신경망의 확장에 중요한 도구로 부상했다. 그러나 sparse MoE는 (i) 다른 parameter group과 마찬가지로 hyperparameter(HP) tuning이 필요한 새로운 학습 가능 parameter(router weight); (ii) 선택해야 하고 필요에 따라 크게 확장될 수 있는 새로운 architecture scale dimension(전문가 수와 전문가 크기) 때문에 학습 복잡도를 높인다. 모델 width, depth, expert 수, <em>그리고</em> expert(hidden) size를 확장하는 transformer 모델에 대해, HP 선택을 저렴하고 신뢰성 있게 만들기 위해 우리는 새로운 parameterization을 제안한다. 이 parameterization은 새로운 dynamical mean-field theory(DMFT) 분석으로 정당화된다. 고정된 token budget에서 학습된 서로 다른 모델 차원을 변화시키면서, 우리의 parameterization이 51M에서 2B total parameter에 이르는 모델 간에 신뢰할 수 있는 HP transfer를 가능하게 함을 실증적으로 보인다. 또한 짧은 token horizon에서 작은 모델을 sweep하여 식별한 HP를 더 긴 horizon에서 더 큰 모델 학습에 적용하고, 성능이 우수한 model behavior를 보고한다.</p>"},{"id":"64349","en":"Approximation Theory for Lipschitz Continuous Transformers","ko":"Lipschitz 연속 Transformer를 위한 근사 이론","authors":"Takashi Furuya, Davide Murari, Carola-Bibiane Schönlieb","pos":"#1401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OVBpXUvwMi","abs":"<p>Stability and robustness are critical for deploying Transformers in safety-sensitive settings.  A principled way to enforce such behavior is to constrain the model's Lipschitz constant.  However, approximation-theoretic guarantees for architectures that explicitly preserve Lipschitz continuity have yet to be established. In this work, we bridge this gap by introducing a class of gradient-descent-type in-context Transformers that are Lipschitz-continuous by construction. We realize both MLP and attention blocks as explicit Euler steps of negative gradient flows, ensuring inherent stability without sacrificing expressivity.  We prove a universal approximation theorem for this class within a Lipschitz-constrained function space. Crucially, our analysis adopts a measure-theoretic formalism, interpreting Transformers as operators on probability measures, to yield approximation guarantees independent of token count.  These results provide a rigorous theoretical foundation for the design of robust, Lipschitz continuous Transformer architectures.</p>","absKo":"<p>안정성과 견고성은 safety-sensitive setting에서 Transformers를 배포할 때 매우 중요합니다. 이러한 동작을 보장하는 원칙적인 방법은 모델의 Lipschitz constant를 제약하는 것입니다. 그러나 Lipschitz continuity를 명시적으로 보존하는 architecture에 대한 approximation-theoretic guarantee는 아직 확립되지 않았습니다. 본 연구에서는 Lipschitz-continuous하도록 설계된 gradient-descent-type in-context Transformer class를 도입하여 이 공백을 메웁니다. 우리는 MLP와 attention block을 모두 negative gradient flow의 explicit Euler step으로 구현하여, 표현력을 희생하지 않으면서도 내재적 안정성을 보장합니다. 또한 Lipschitz 제약 함수 공간 내에서 이 class에 대한 universal approximation theorem을 증명합니다. 특히, 우리의 분석은 Transformer를 확률 측도(probability measure) 위의 operator로 해석하는 measure-theoretic formalism을 채택하여, token 수와 무관한 approximation guarantee를 도출합니다. 이러한 결과는 견고하고 Lipschitz continuous한 Transformer architecture 설계를 위한 엄밀한 이론적 기반을 제공합니다.</p>"},{"id":"63048","en":"Equivalence of Context and Parameter Updates in Modern Transformer Blocks","ko":"현대 Transformer 블록에서 문맥 업데이트와 파라미터 업데이트의 등가성","authors":"Adrian Goldwaser, Michael Munn, Xavi Gonzalvo, Benoit Dherin","pos":"#1406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aZ5Di8Ii4X","abs":"<p>Recent research has established that the impact of context in a vanilla transformer can be represented implicitly by forming a token-dependent, rank-1 patch to its MLP weights. This work extends that foundational theory to the diverse architectures of modern Large Language Models. We first demonstrate a precise, analytical solution for a Gemma-style transformer block, proving that the entire effect of a context can be perfectly mapped to rank-1 patches on its MLP weight matrices and a patch to the RMSNorm scale. We then generalize this result, providing a constructive proof and algorithm for multi-layer models. To unify these findings, we introduce a general framework centered on two core properties: input controllability and output controllability. We prove that a perfect implicit weight patch is possible for any MLP block where the inner function is input-controllable and the outer function is output-controllable. This provides a simpler and more powerful lens for understanding how transformer models transmute prompts into effective weights. This setup generalizes to a wide range of modern LLM architectures including gating, pre-/post-norm, mixture of experts and sequential/parallel transformer blocks.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 연구는 vanilla transformer에서 context의 영향을 token-dependent한 rank-1 patch를 MLP weight에 형성함으로써 암묵적으로 표현할 수 있음을 확립했다. 이 연구는 그 기초 이론을 현대 Large Language Model의 다양한 architecture로 확장한다. 우리는 먼저 Gemma-style transformer block에 대해 정확한 analytical solution을 제시하여, context의 전체 효과가 MLP weight matrix에 대한 rank-1 patch와 RMSNorm scale에 대한 patch로 완벽하게 매핑될 수 있음을 증명한다. 이어서 이 결과를 일반화하여 multi-layer model에 대한 constructive proof와 algorithm을 제공한다. 이러한 결과를 통합하기 위해, 우리는 input controllability와 output controllability라는 두 핵심 속성에 중심을 둔 일반 framework를 도입한다. 우리는 inner function이 input-controllable하고 outer function이 output-controllable한 어떤 MLP block에서도 perfect implicit weight patch가 가능함을 증명한다. 이는 transformer model이 prompt를 effective weight로 변환하는 방식을 이해하는 더 단순하고 강력한 관점을 제공한다. 이 설정은 gating, pre-/post-norm, mixture of experts, sequential/parallel transformer block을 포함한 광범위한 현대 LLM architecture로 일반화된다.</p>"},{"id":"62396","en":"FRACTAL: State Space Model with Fractional Recurrent Architecture for Computational Temporal Analysis of Long Sequences","ko":"FRACTAL: 긴 시퀀스의 계산적 시간 분석을 위한 Fractional Recurrent 구조의 State Space Model","authors":"Mengqi Li, Wensheng Lin, Jinshuai Yang, Lixin Li","pos":"#1407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=h0RgDbosOj","abs":"<p>Effective sequence modeling fundamentally requires balancing the retention of unbounded history with the high-resolution detection of abrupt short-term variations common in real-world phenomena. However, existing state space models (SSMs) relying on high-order polynomial projection operators (HiPPO) face a critical trade-off where uniform measures dilute recent information to maintain timescale invariance, while exponential measures sacrifice global context to capture local dynamics. This paper proposes a Fractional Recurrent Architecture for Computational Temporal Analysis of Long sequences (FRACTAL), a novel architecture integrating fractional measure theory into recursive memory updates to address this limitation. By deriving projection operators with analytically characterized spectral properties and a tunable singularity index, the proposed method amplifies sensitivity to recent signal perturbations while preserving the spectral structure that encodes scale-invariant memory dynamics. This theoretical innovation is instantiated within a simplified diagonalized state space framework by modulating input projection initialization to enable simultaneous capture of multi-scale temporal features.  FRACTAL achieves an average score of 87.11\\% on the Long Range Arena benchmark, including 61.85\\% on the ListOps task, outperforming the S5 model.</p>","absKo":"효과적인 sequence modeling은 본질적으로 무한한 과거를 유지하는 것과 실제 현상에서 흔히 나타나는 급격한 단기 변동을 고해상도로 감지하는 것 사이의 균형을 필요로 한다. 그러나 high-order polynomial projection operator (HiPPO)에 의존하는 기존 state space model (SSM)은 중요한 trade-off에 직면한다. uniform measure는 timescale invariance를 유지하기 위해 최근 정보를 희석하는 반면, exponential measure는 local dynamics를 포착하기 위해 global context를 희생한다. 본 논문은 이 한계를 해결하기 위해 fractional measure theory를 recursive memory update에 통합한 새로운 architecture인 Fractional Recurrent Architecture for Computational Temporal Analysis of Long sequences (FRACTAL)을 제안한다. 분석적으로 특징지어진 spectral property와 조정 가능한 singularity index를 갖는 projection operator를 유도함으로써, 제안 방법은 scale-invariant memory dynamics를 부호화하는 spectral structure를 보존하면서 최근 signal perturbation에 대한 민감성을 증폭한다. 이러한 이론적 혁신은 입력 projection initialization을 조절하여 multi-scale temporal feature를 동시에 포착할 수 있도록 하는 단순화된 diagonalized state space framework 안에서 구현된다. FRACTAL은 Long Range Arena benchmark에서 평균 87.11\\%를 달성했으며, 그중 ListOps task에서 61.85\\%를 기록하여 S5 model을 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"64653","en":"Focus and Dilution: The Multi-stage Learning Process of Attention","ko":"집중과 희석: Attention의 다단계 학습 과정","authors":"Zheng-An Chen, Pengxiao Lin, Zhi-Qin John Xu, Tao Luo","pos":"#1408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LF4YsCYfrf","abs":"<p>Transformer-based models have achieved remarkable success across a wide range of domains, yet our understanding of their training dynamics remains limited. In this work, we identify a recurrent focus–dilution cycle in attention learning and provide a rigorous explanation in a one-layer Transformer setting for Markovian data via gradient-flow analysis. Using stage-wise linearization around critical points, we show that a single focus–dilution cycle can be decomposed into a sequence of distinct stages. First, embedding and projection rapidly condense to a rank-one structure, while attention parameters remain effectively frozen. Then, the attention parameters begin to increase, inducing a frequency-driven focus toward high-frequency tokens. As attention continues to evolve, it generates next-order perturbations in embeddings, leading to a mass-redistribution mechanism that progressively dilutes this focus. Finally, small asymmetries among low-frequency tokens lift a degenerate critical point, opening new embedding directions and initiating the next cycle. Experiments on synthetic Markovian data as well as WikiText and TinyStories corroborate the predicted stages and cyclical dynamics.</p>","absKo":"<p>Transformer-based models는 다양한 분야에서 놀라운 성과를 거두었지만, 그 training dynamics에 대한 우리의 이해는 여전히 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 attention learning에서 반복적으로 나타나는 focus-dilution cycle을 규명하고, gradient-flow analysis를 통해 Markovian data에 대한 one-layer Transformer 설정에서 엄밀한 설명을 제시한다. critical point 주변의 stage-wise linearization을 사용하여, 하나의 focus-dilution cycle이 서로 구분되는 단계들의 연속으로 분해될 수 있음을 보인다. 먼저 embedding과 projection은 빠르게 rank-one structure로 응축되는 반면, attention parameter는 사실상 고정된 상태를 유지한다. 이후 attention parameter가 증가하기 시작하면서, frequency-driven focus가 high-frequency token 쪽으로 유도된다. attention이 계속 진화함에 따라 embedding에 next-order perturbation이 생성되고, mass-redistribution mechanism이 작동하여 이 focus가 점진적으로 희석된다. 마지막으로, low-frequency token 간의 작은 비대칭성이 degenerate critical point를 해제하여 새로운 embedding 방향을 열고 다음 cycle을 시작하게 한다. synthetic Markovian data와 WikiText, TinyStories에서의 실험은 예측된 단계와 순환 동역학을 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"63643","en":"Fractional is Better: Learnable Derivative Orders in Neural Operator Learning","ko":"Fractional이 더 낫다: neural operator 학습에서 학습 가능한 미분 차수","authors":"Fares Mehouachi, Saif Jabari","pos":"#1409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=V4FDM692AZ","abs":"Neural operators learn mappings between function spaces, enabling fast PDE surrogates. Despite architectural diversity, these methods often share a common input representation: raw coordinate-value pairs. This ignores the differential structure that defines the underlying physics. We study whether derivative features can improve neural operator learning. Through Picard iteration on mild solutions, we show that derivatives of the input naturally enter PDE solution operators, and we prove that providing them improves approximation rates substantially. But the optimal derivative order is not what one might expect. We show that the statistically optimal order is strictly less than the PDE order, for any finite sample size. This gap arises from a bias-variance tradeoff: higher-order derivatives carry more information but amplify noise. We characterize this tradeoff in closed form and show that learning the derivative order from data achieves automatic spectral regularization. We introduce $\\partial$-NO (derivative-augmented neural operators), a simple augmentation that provides learnable fractional derivative features to any neural operator backbone. Across benchmarks, this consistently improves accuracy. Learned orders reflect dominant PDE structure while adapting to finite-sample constraints, confirming the theory.","absKo":"Neural operator는 function space 사이의 mapping을 학습하여 빠른 PDE surrogate를 가능하게 한다. 아키텍처는 다양하지만, 이러한 방법들은 종종 공통된 input representation, 즉 raw coordinate-value pair를 공유한다. 이는 underlying physics를 정의하는 differential structure를 무시한다. 우리는 derivative feature가 neural operator learning을 개선할 수 있는지 연구한다. mild solution에 대한 Picard iteration을 통해, 입력의 derivative가 PDE solution operator에 자연스럽게 들어가며, 이를 제공하면 approximation rate가 상당히 향상됨을 증명한다. 그러나 최적의 derivative order는 일반적으로 예상하는 것과는 다르다. 우리는 통계적으로 최적의 order가 유한한 sample size에서는 PDE order보다 엄밀히 작다는 것을 보인다. 이 차이는 bias-variance tradeoff에서 비롯된다. 더 높은 차수의 derivative는 더 많은 정보를 담지만 noise를 증폭시킨다. 우리는 이 tradeoff를 closed form으로 특성화하고, data로부터 derivative order를 학습하면 자동 spectral regularization이 달성됨을 보인다. 우리는 $\\partial$-NO(derivative-augmented neural operators)를 제안한다. 이는 어떤 neural operator backbone에도 학습 가능한 fractional derivative feature를 제공하는 단순한 augmentation이다. 여러 benchmark에서 이는 일관되게 정확도를 향상시킨다. 학습된 order는 finite-sample 제약에 적응하면서도 dominant PDE structure를 반영하며, 이론을 뒷받침한다."},{"id":"63463","en":"Generalization and Scaling Laws for Mixture-of-ExpertsTransformers","ko":"Mixture-of-Experts Transformer를 위한 일반화 및 스케일링 법칙","authors":"Mansour ZOUBEIROU A MAYAKI","pos":"#1411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WxmL5UjtNm","abs":"We develop a theory of generalization and scaling for Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) Transformers that cleanly separates active per-input capacity from routing combinatorics. Conditioning on fixed routing patterns and union-bounding across them, we obtain a sup-norm covering-number bound whose metric entropy scales with the active parameter budget and incurs a MoE-specific overhead. Combining this with a standard ERM argument for squared loss we provided a generalization bound under a $d$-dimensional manifold model ($d$ is the intrinsic dimension of the training data) and $C^\\beta$ targets, showing that approximation and estimation trade off in the same way as in dense networks once active parameters are counted appropriately. We further prove a constructive approximation theorem for MoE architectures, demonstrating that accuracy can be improved either by scaling active capacity or by increasing the number of available experts, with the better of the two mechanisms prevailing. From these results we derive neural scaling laws, covering model scaling, data scaling and compute–optimal tradeoffs. The theory highlights that enlarging the expert pool at fixed sparsity influences performance only through a mild logarithmic routing term, whereas increasing active capacity per input drives the main gains in generalization and approximation. These insights provide principled guidance for the design of efficient sparse Transformer systems and clarify the fundamental tradeoffs underlying their empirical scaling behavior.","absKo":"우리는 Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) Transformers에 대한 일반화 및 스케일링 이론을 개발하여, 입력별 활성 용량(active per-input capacity)과 routing combinatorics를 명확히 분리한다. 고정된 routing pattern에 조건부화하고 그것들에 대해 union bound를 적용함으로써, 활성 파라미터 예산(active parameter budget)에 따라 metric entropy가 스케일하고 MoE 특유의 오버헤드를 수반하는 sup-norm covering-number bound를 얻는다. 이를 squared loss에 대한 표준 ERM argument와 결합하여, 학습 데이터의 intrinsic dimension인 $d$를 갖는 $d$-dimensional manifold model과 $C^\\beta$ target 하에서의 generalization bound를 제시하며, 활성 파라미터를 적절히 세면 approximation과 estimation이 dense network에서와 같은 방식으로 trade-off함을 보인다. 또한 MoE architecture에 대한 constructive approximation theorem을 증명하여, 활성 용량을 키우거나 사용 가능한 expert 수를 늘리는 두 방식 중 더 유리한 메커니즘이 성능을 개선할 수 있음을 보인다. 이 결과들로부터 model scaling, data scaling, compute-optimal trade-off를 포괄하는 neural scaling laws를 유도한다. 이 이론은 고정된 sparsity에서 expert pool을 늘리는 것은 주로 완만한 logarithmic routing term을 통해서만 성능에 영향을 미치는 반면, 입력당 활성 용량을 늘리는 것이 generalization과 approximation에서의 주요 향상을 이끈다는 점을 강조한다. 이러한 통찰은 효율적인 sparse Transformer system 설계를 위한 원칙적인 지침을 제공하고, 그 경험적 scaling behavior의 근본 trade-off를 분명히 해준다."},{"id":"65708","en":"Geometric and Stochastic Analysis of Discontinuities in Sparse Mixture-of-Experts","ko":"희소 Mixture-of-Experts의 불연속성에 대한 기하학적·확률적 분석","authors":"Tho Tran Huu, Huu-Tuan Nguyen, Thien-Hai Nguyen, Nhat-Tri Ho, Viet Hoang Tran, Tho Quan, Tan Nguyen","pos":"#1412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AyrNR1ExN5","abs":"Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (SMoE) architectures are now widely deployed in state-of-the-art language and vision models, where conditional routing allows scaling to very large networks. However, this very Top-$k$ expert selection that enables conditional routing also renders the SMoE map inherently discontinuous. In the vicinity of these discontinuity surfaces, even inputs that are arbitrarily close may activate substantially different sets of experts resulting in significantly different outputs. In this work we give a rigorous geometric and stochastic analysis of these discontinuities. We first classify them by order, determined by the number of tied experts at a switching event. Using measure-theoretic slicing arguments, we establish asymptotic volume estimates for the thickened discontinuity surfaces, showing that lower-order discontinuity sets dominate, whereas higher-order ones occupy a vanishingly small relative volume. Next, modeling random perturbations in the input space via a diffusion process, we prove that the path eventually encounter a discontinuity, and moreover that the first hit almost surely occurs on an order-1 discontinuity with explicit finite-time probability bounds. We further derive occupation-time bounds that quantify the duration the random path spend in the neighborhoods of each discontinuity order. These theoretical results imply that inputs are more likely to lie near lower order discontinuities. Motivated by this insight, we propose a simple smoothing mechanism that can be directly applied to existing SMoEs, softly incorporating experts near discontinuities; our analysis guarantees that the added computational overhead remains small while providing localized smoothing near discontinuities, and experiments across language and vision tasks show that smoothing not only enforces continuity of the SMoE map but also enhances empirical performance."},{"id":"65896","en":"How Out-of-Distribution Detection Learning Theory Enhances Transformer: Learnability and Reliability","ko":"분포 외 탐지 학습 이론이 어떻게 Transformer를 강화하는가: 학습성과 신뢰성","authors":"Yijin Zhou, Yutang Ge, Wenyuan XIE, Linqian Zeng, Xiaowen Dong, Yu Guang Wang","pos":"#1414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=94FOsjgeHK","abs":"<p>Transformers excel in natural language processing and computer vision tasks. However, they still face challenges in generalizing to Out-of-Distribution (OOD) datasets, i.e. data whose distribution differs from that seen during training. OOD detection aims to distinguish outliers while preserving in-distribution (ID) data performance. This paper introduces the OOD detection Probably Approximately Correct (PAC) Theory for transformers, which establishes the conditions for data distribution and model configurations for the OOD detection learnability of transformers. It shows that outliers can be accurately represented and distinguished with sufficient data under conditions. The theoretical implications highlight the trade-off between theoretical principles and practical training paradigms. By examining this trade-off, we naturally derived the rationale for leveraging auxiliary outliers to enhance OOD detection. Our theory suggests that by penalizing the misclassification of outliers within the loss function and strategically generating soft synthetic outliers, one can robustly bolster the reliability of transformer networks. This approach yields a novel algorithm that ensures learnability and refines the decision boundaries between inliers and outliers. In practice, the algorithm consistently achieves state-of-the-art (SOTA) performance across various data formats.</p>"},{"id":"62988","en":"$\\mu$pscaling small models: Principled warm starts and hyperparameter transfer","ko":"μpscaling small models: 원칙 기반 warm starts와 하이퍼파라미터 전이","authors":"Yuxin Ma, Nan Chen, Mateo Diaz, Soufiane Hayou, Dmitriy Kunisky, Soledad Villar","pos":"#1500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bAqpZRzlTg","abs":"Modern large-scale neural networks are often trained and released in multiple sizes to accommodate diverse inference budgets. To improve efficiency, recent work has explored *model upscaling*:  initializing larger models from trained smaller ones in order to transfer knowledge and accelerate convergence. However, this method can be sensitive to hyperparameters that need to be tuned at the target upscaled model size, which is prohibitively costly to do directly. It remains unclear whether the most common workaround—tuning on smaller models and extrapolating via hyperparameter scaling laws—is still sound when using upscaling. We address this with principled approaches to upscaling with respect to model widths and efficiently tuning hyperparameters in this setting. First, motivated by $\\mu$P and any-dimensional architectures, we introduce a general upscaling method applicable to a broad range of architectures and optimizers, backed by theory guaranteeing that models are equivalent to their widened versions and allowing for rigorous analysis of infinite-width limits. Second, we extend the theory of $\\mu$Transfer to a hyperparameter transfer technique for models upscaled using our method and empirically demonstrate that this method is effective on realistic datasets and architectures.","absKo":"현대의 대규모 신경망은 다양한 inference budget에 맞추기 위해 여러 크기로 학습되고 배포되는 경우가 많다. 효율성을 높이기 위해 최근 연구는 *model upscaling*, 즉 더 작은 학습 완료 모델로부터 더 큰 모델을 초기화하여 지식을 전달하고 수렴을 가속하는 방법을 탐구해 왔다. 그러나 이 방법은 target upscaled model size에서 조정해야 하는 hyperparameter에 민감할 수 있으며, 이를 직접 조정하는 것은 지나치게 비용이 크다. 가장 흔한 우회책인 작은 모델에서 tuning한 뒤 hyperparameter scaling law를 통해 extrapolation하는 방식이 upscaling을 사용할 때도 여전히 타당한지는 불분명하다. 우리는 model width에 대한 upscaling과 이 setting에서의 효율적인 hyperparameter tuning을 위한 원리적인 접근으로 이 문제를 해결한다. 첫째, $\\mu$P와 any-dimensional architecture에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 넓은 범위의 architecture와 optimizer에 적용 가능한 일반적인 upscaling method를 제안한다. 이 방법은 모델이 widened version과 동등함을 보장하고 infinite-width limit에 대한 엄밀한 분석을 가능하게 하는 이론으로 뒷받침된다. 둘째, 우리는 $\\mu$Transfer 이론을 우리 방법으로 upscaled된 모델에 대한 hyperparameter transfer technique로 확장하고, 이 방법이 현실적인 dataset과 architecture에서 효과적임을 실증적으로 보인다."},{"id":"65099","en":"Which Algorithms Can Graph Neural Networks Learn?","ko":"Graph Neural Network는 어떤 알고리즘을 학습할 수 있는가?","authors":"Solveig Wittig, Antonis Vasileiou, Robert R. Nerem, Timo Stoll, Floris Geerts, Yusu Wang, Christopher Morris","pos":"#2206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GnmuZIlvxw","abs":"In recent years, there has been growing interest in understanding neural architectures' ability to learn to execute discrete algorithms, a line of work often referred to as neural algorithmic reasoning. The goal is to integrate algorithmic reasoning capabilities into larger neural pipelines. Many such architectures are based on (message-passing) graph neural networks (MPNNs), owing to their permutation equivariance and ability to deal with sparsity and variable-sized inputs. However, existing work is either largely empirical and lacks formal guarantees or it focuses solely on expressivity, leaving open the question of when and how such architectures generalize beyond a finite training set. In this work, we propose a general theoretical framework that characterizes the necessary conditions under which MPNNs can learn an algorithm from a training set of small instances and provably approximate its behavior on inputs of arbitrary size. Our framework applies to a broad class of algorithms, including single-source shortest paths, minimum spanning trees, and general dynamic programming problems, such as the $0$-$1$ knapsack problem. In addition, we establish impossibility results for a wide range of algorithmic tasks, showing that standard MPNN cannot compute them. We derive more expressive MPNN-like architectures that overcome these limitations. Finally, we refine our analysis for the Bellman–Ford algorithm, yielding substantially smaller required training sets and significantly extending the recent work of Nerem et al., 2025 by allowing for a differentiable regularization loss. Empirical results largely support our theoretical findings.","absKo":"최근 몇 년 동안, 이산 알고리즘을 실행하도록 학습하는 neural architecture의 능력을 이해하려는 관심이 커지고 있으며, 이러한 연구 흐름은 종종 neural algorithmic reasoning이라 불린다. 목표는 이러한 algorithmic reasoning 능력을 더 큰 neural pipeline에 통합하는 것이다. 이러한 architecture의 상당수는 permutation equivariance와 sparsity 및 가변 크기 입력을 다룰 수 있는 능력 때문에 (message-passing) graph neural network(MPNN)에 기반한다. 그러나 기존 연구는 대체로 경험적 성격이 강해 형식적 보장이 부족하거나, expressivity에만 초점을 맞춰 유한한 training set을 넘어 이러한 architecture가 언제, 어떻게 generalize하는지에 대한 문제는 남겨두고 있다. 본 연구에서는 MPNN이 작은 instance들로 이루어진 training set에서 알고리즘을 학습하고, 임의의 크기를 가진 입력에서 그 동작을 증명 가능하게 근사할 수 있는 필요 조건을 특징짓는 일반적인 이론적 프레임워크를 제안한다. 우리의 프레임워크는 single-source shortest paths, minimum spanning trees, 그리고 $0$-$1$ knapsack problem과 같은 일반적인 dynamic programming 문제를 포함한 폭넓은 알고리즘에 적용된다. 또한 광범위한 algorithmic task에 대해 standard MPNN으로는 이를 계산할 수 없다는 불가능성 결과를 확립한다. 우리는 이러한 한계를 극복하는 더 expressive한 MPNN-like architecture를 도출한다. 마지막으로 Bellman–Ford algorithm에 대한 분석을 정교화하여, 필요한 training set의 크기를 상당히 줄이고, differentiable regularization loss를 허용함으로써 Nerem et al., 2025의 최근 연구를 크게 확장한다. 실험 결과는 우리의 이론적 발견을 대체로 뒷받침한다."},{"id":"62241","en":"A Random Matrix Perspective on the Consistency of Diffusion Models","ko":"Diffusion Models의 일관성에 대한 Random Matrix 관점","authors":"Binxu Wang, Jacob A Zavatone-Veth, Cengiz Pehlevan","pos":"#2503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iPjuUQbkfl","abs":"Diffusion models trained on different, non-overlapping subsets of a dataset often produce strikingly similar outputs when given the same noise seed. We trace this consistency to a simple linear effect: the shared Gaussian statistics across splits already predict much of the generated images. To formalize this, we develop a random matrix theory (RMT) framework that quantifies how finite datasets shape the expectation and variance of the learned denoiser and sampling map in the linear setting. For expectations, sampling variability acts as a renormalization of the noise level through a self-consistent relation $\\sigma^2\\to\\kappa(\\sigma^2)$, explaining why limited data overshrink low-variance directions and pull samples toward the dataset mean. For fluctuations, our variance formulas reveal three key factors behind cross-split disagreement: \\textit{anisotropy} across eigenmodes, \\textit{inhomogeneity} across inputs, and overall scaling with dataset size. Extending deterministic-equivalence tools to fractional matrix powers further allows us to analyze entire sampling trajectories. The theory sharply predicts the behavior of linear diffusion models, and we validate its predictions on UNet and DiT architectures in their non-memorization regime, identifying where and how samples deviates across training data split. This provides a principled baseline for reproducibility in diffusion training, linking spectral properties of data to the stability of generative outputs.","absKo":"Different, non-overlapping subsets of a dataset에서 학습된 diffusion model은 동일한 noise seed를 주었을 때 종종 놀라울 정도로 유사한 출력을 생성한다. 우리는 이러한 일관성을 단순한 linear effect로 추적한다. split 간에 공유되는 Gaussian statistics만으로도 생성된 이미지의 상당 부분을 이미 예측할 수 있다. 이를 형식화하기 위해, 우리는 linear setting에서 finite dataset이 learned denoiser와 sampling map의 expectation 및 variance를 어떻게 형성하는지를 정량화하는 random matrix theory (RMT) framework를 개발한다. expectation의 경우, sampling variability는 self-consistent relation $\\sigma^2\\to\\kappa(\\sigma^2)$를 통해 noise level의 renormalization으로 작용하며, 제한된 데이터가 왜 low-variance direction을 과도하게 축소시키고 sample을 dataset mean 쪽으로 끌어당기는지 설명한다. variance의 경우, 우리의 formula는 cross-split disagreement의 세 가지 핵심 요인인 \\textit{anisotropy} across eigenmodes, \\textit{inhomogeneity} across inputs, 그리고 dataset size에 따른 overall scaling을 드러낸다. deterministic-equivalence tool을 fractional matrix power로 확장함으로써 전체 sampling trajectory까지 분석할 수 있다. 이 이론은 linear diffusion model의 동작을 날카롭게 예측하며, 우리는 non-memorization regime의 UNet과 DiT architecture에서 그 예측을 검증하여 training data split에 따라 sample이 어디서, 어떻게 달라지는지 확인한다. 이는 diffusion training에서 재현성을 위한 원칙적 baseline을 제공하며, 데이터의 spectral property와 generative output의 안정성을 연결한다."},{"id":"68795","en":"The Choice of Normalization Influences Shrinkage in Regularized Regression","ko":"정규화의 선택이 Regularized Regression에서 Shrinkage에 미치는 영향","authors":"Johan Larsson, Jonas Wallin","pos":"#3901","abs":"<p>Regularized models are often sensitive to the scales of the features in the data and it has therefore become standard practice to normalize (center and scale) the features before fitting the model. But there are many different ways to normalize the features and the choice may have dramatic effects on the resulting model. In spite of this, there has so far been no research on this topic. In this paper, we begin to bridge this knowledge gap by studying normalization in the context of lasso, ridge, and elastic net regression. We focus on binary features and show that their class balances (proportions of ones) directly influences the regression coefficients and that this effect depends on the combination of normalization and regularization methods used. We demonstrate that this effect can be mitigated by scaling binary features with their variance in the case of the lasso and standard deviation in the case of ridge regression, but that this comes at the cost of increased variance of the coefficient estimates. For the elastic net, we show that scaling the penalty weights, rather than the features, can achieve the same effect. Finally, we also tackle mixes of binary and normal features as well as interactions and provide some initial results on how to normalize features in these cases.</p>"},{"id":"60971","en":"Spectral Gradient Descent Mitigates Anisotropy-Driven Misalignment: A Case Study in Phase Retrieval","ko":"Spectral Gradient Descent는 Anisotropy-Driven Misalignment를 완화한다: Phase Retrieval 사례 연구","authors":"Guillaume Braun, Han Bao, Wei Huang, Masaaki Imaizumi","pos":"#4500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uyizpRy7kS","abs":"<p>Spectral gradient methods, such as the Muon optimizer, modify gradient updates by preserving directional information while discarding scale, and have shown strong empirical performance in deep learning. We investigate the mechanisms underlying these gains through a dynamical analysis of a nonlinear phase retrieval model with anisotropic Gaussian inputs, equivalent to training a two-layer neural network with quadratic activation and fixed second-layer weights. Focusing on a spiked covariance setting where the dominant variance direction is orthogonal to the signal, we show that gradient descent (GD) suffers from a variance-induced misalignment: during the early escape phase, high-variance but uninformative directions are multiplicatively amplified, degrading alignment with the true signal under strong anisotropy. In contrast, spectral gradient descent (SpecGD) removes this anisotropic magnification effect, leading to stable alignment and accelerated noise contraction. Numerical experiments confirm the theory and show that these phenomena persist under more general anisotropic covariances.</p>","absKo":"<p>Muon optimizer와 같은 spectral gradient method는 scale은 버리고 directional information은 유지한 채 gradient update를 수정하며, deep learning에서 강력한 경험적 성능을 보여왔다. 우리는 비선형 phase retrieval model에서 이러한 향상의 메커니즘을 동역학적으로 분석한다. 이 모델은 anisotropic Gaussian input을 가지며, quadratic activation과 고정된 second-layer weight를 갖는 two-layer neural network를 학습하는 것과 동등하다. signal에 대한 dominant variance direction이 orthogonal한 spiked covariance setting에 초점을 맞추면, gradient descent(GD)는 variance-induced misalignment를 겪음을 보인다. 즉, 초기 escape phase 동안 high-variance이지만 uninformative한 방향이 multiplicatively amplified되어 강한 anisotropy 하에서 true signal과의 alignment가 저하된다. 반면 spectral gradient descent(SpecGD)는 이러한 anisotropic magnification effect를 제거하여 안정적인 alignment와 더 빠른 noise contraction을 이끈다. 수치 실험은 이 이론을 확인하며, 이러한 현상이 더 일반적인 anisotropic covariance에서도 지속됨을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62093","en":"A Theory of How Pretraining Shapes Inductive Bias in Fine-Tuning","ko":"사전학습이 파인튜닝의 귀납 편향을 형성하는 방식에 대한 이론","authors":"Nicolas Anguita, Francesco Locatello, Andrew Saxe, Marco Mondelli, Flavia Mancini, Samuel Lippl, Clémentine Dominé","pos":"#4502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jsOKNGu8ac","abs":"<p>Pretraining and fine-tuning are central stages in modern machine learning systems. In practice, feature learning plays an important role across both stages: deep neural networks learn a broad range of useful features during pretraining and further refine those features during fine-tuning. However, an end-to-end theoretical understanding of how choices of initialization impact the ability to reuse and refine features during fine-tuning has remained elusive. Here we develop an analytical theory of the pretraining–fine-tuning pipeline in diagonal linear networks, deriving exact expressions for the generalization error as a function of initialization parameters and task statistics. We find that different initialization choices place the network into four distinct fine-tuning regimes that are distinguished by their ability to support feature learning and reuse—and therefore by the task statistics for which they are beneficial. In particular, a smaller initialization scale in earlier layers enables the network to both reuse and refine its features, leading to superior generalization on fine-tuning tasks that rely on a subset of pretraining features. We demonstrate empirically that the same initialization parameters impact generalization in nonlinear networks trained on CIFAR-100. Overall, our results demonstrate analytically how data and network initialization interact to shape fine-tuning generalization, highlighting an important role for the relative scale of initialization across different layers in enabling continued feature learning during fine-tuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Pretraining과 fine-tuning은 현대 machine learning system의 핵심 단계이다. 실제로는 두 단계 모두에서 feature learning이 중요한 역할을 한다. deep neural network는 pretraining 동안 폭넓은 유용한 feature를 학습하고, fine-tuning 동안 그 feature를 추가로 정교화한다. 그러나 initialization 선택이 fine-tuning 중 feature를 재사용하고 정교화하는 능력에 어떤 영향을 미치는지에 대한 end-to-end 이론적 이해는 여전히 불분명하다. 여기에서는 diagonal linear network에서 pretraining–fine-tuning pipeline의 해석적 이론을 구축하고, initialization parameter와 task statistic의 함수로 generalization error에 대한 정확한 표현을 유도한다. 우리는 서로 다른 initialization 선택이 network를 네 가지 구별되는 fine-tuning regime으로 배치하며, 이들은 feature learning과 reuse를 지원하는 능력, 그리고 따라서 어떤 task statistic에서 유리한지에 따라 구분됨을 보인다. 특히, 초기 layer에서 더 작은 initialization scale은 network가 feature를 재사용하면서 동시에 정교화할 수 있게 하여, pretraining feature의 일부에 의존하는 fine-tuning task에서 더 우수한 generalization을 이끈다. 또한 CIFAR-100에서 학습된 nonlinear network에 대해서도 동일한 initialization parameter가 generalization에 영향을 미친다는 것을 실증적으로 보인다. 전반적으로, 우리의 결과는 data와 network initialization이 어떻게 상호작용하여 fine-tuning generalization을 형성하는지 해석적으로 보여주며, fine-tuning 동안 지속적인 feature learning을 가능하게 하는 데 있어 서로 다른 layer 간 initialization의 상대적 scale이 중요한 역할을 함을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"63453","en":"Optimal Stopping in Latent Diffusion Models","ko":"잠재 Diffusion 모델에서의 최적 정지","authors":"Yu-Han Wu, Quentin Berthet, Gérard Biau, Claire Boyer, Romuald Elie, Pierre Marion","pos":"#4616","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=X4OakhiSzp","abs":"We identify and analyze a surprising phenomenon of $\\textit{Latent}$ Diffusion Models (LDMs) where the final steps of the diffusion can $\\textit{degrade}$ sample quality. In contrast to conventional arguments that justify early stopping for numerical stability, this phenomenon is intrinsic to the dimensionality reduction in LDMs. We provide a principled explanation by analyzing the interaction between latent dimension and stopping time. Under a Gaussian framework with linear autoencoders, we characterize the conditions under which early stopping is needed to minimize the distance between generated and target distributions. More precisely, we show that lower-dimensional representations benefit from earlier termination, whereas higher-dimensional latent spaces require later stopping time. We further establish that the latent dimension interplays with other hyperparameters of the problem such as constraints in the parameters of score matching. Crucially, this framework suggests that the reconstruction quality of the autoencoder alone can serve as a proxy to estimate the potential performance of the full LDM. Experiments on synthetic and real datasets illustrate these properties, underlining that early stopping can improve generative quality. Together, our results offer a theoretical foundation for understanding how the latent dimension influences the sample quality, and highlight stopping time as a key hyperparameter in LDMs.","absKo":"우리는 $\\textit{Latent}$ Diffusion Model (LDM)의 놀라운 현상을 식별하고 분석하는데, diffusion의 마지막 단계가 샘플 품질을 $\\textit{저하시킬}$ 수 있다는 점을 보인다. 수치적 안정성을 위해 early stopping을 정당화하는 전통적인 논의와 달리, 이 현상은 LDM의 차원 축소에 내재적이다. 우리는 latent dimension과 stopping time의 상호작용을 분석하여 이를 원리적으로 설명한다. Gaussian framework와 linear autoencoder 하에서, 생성 분포와 target 분포 사이의 거리를 최소화하기 위해 early stopping이 필요한 조건을 특성화한다. 보다 정확히는, 낮은 차원의 표현은 더 이른 종료의 이점을 가지는 반면, 더 높은 차원의 latent space는 더 늦은 stopping time을 필요로 함을 보인다. 우리는 또한 latent dimension이 score matching의 parameter 제약과 같은 문제의 다른 hyperparameter들과 상호작용함을 확립한다. 결정적으로, 이 framework는 autoencoder의 reconstruction quality만으로도 전체 LDM의 잠재적 성능을 추정하는 proxy로 사용할 수 있음을 시사한다. synthetic 및 실제 dataset에서의 실험은 이러한 성질을 보여주며, early stopping이 generative quality를 향상시킬 수 있음을 강조한다. 종합하면, 우리의 결과는 latent dimension이 sample quality에 어떤 방식으로 영향을 미치는지 이해하기 위한 이론적 기반을 제공하고, LDM에서 stopping time을 핵심 hyperparameter로 부각시킨다."},{"id":"61635","en":"Sequential Group Composition: A Window into the Mechanics of Deep Learning","ko":"순차적 그룹 합성: Deep Learning 메커니즘을 들여다보는 창","authors":"Giovanni Luca Marchetti, Daniel Kunin, Adele Myers, Francisco Acosta, Nina Miolane","pos":"#4618","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oFD9pc53pF","abs":"How do neural networks trained over sequences acquire the ability to perform structured operations, such as arithmetic, geometric, and algorithmic computation? To gain insight into this question, we introduce the sequential group composition task. In this task, networks receive a sequence of elements from a finite group encoded in a real vector space and must predict their cumulative product. The task can be order-sensitive and requires a nonlinear architecture to be learned. Our analysis isolates the roles of the group structure, encoding statistics, and sequence length in shaping learning. We prove that two-layer networks learn this task one irreducible representation of the group at a time in an order determined by the Fourier statistics of the encoding. These networks can perfectly learn the task, but doing so requires a hidden width exponential in the sequence length $k$. In contrast, we show how deeper models exploit the associativity of the task to dramatically improve this scaling: recurrent neural networks compose elements sequentially in $k$ steps, while multilayer networks compose adjacent pairs in parallel in $\\log k$ layers. Overall, the sequential group composition task offers a tractable window into the mechanics of deep learning.","absKo":"시퀀스 위에서 학습된 neural networks는 산술, 기하, 알고리즘적 계산과 같은 structured operations를 수행하는 능력을 어떻게 획득하는가? 이 질문에 대한 통찰을 얻기 위해, 우리는 sequential group composition task를 도입한다. 이 task에서 network는 real vector space로 인코딩된 finite group의 원소 시퀀스를 입력으로 받고, 이들의 cumulative product를 예측해야 한다. 이 task는 order-sensitive할 수 있으며, 학습되기 위해 nonlinear architecture를 필요로 한다. 우리의 분석은 학습을 형성하는 데 있어 group structure, encoding statistics, sequence length의 역할을 분리해 보여준다. 우리는 two-layer networks가 Fourier statistics of the encoding에 의해 정해지는 순서에 따라 group의 irreducible representation을 한 번에 하나씩 학습함을 증명한다. 이러한 network는 task를 완벽하게 학습할 수 있지만, 그러기 위해서는 sequence length $k$에 대해 exponential한 hidden width가 필요하다. 이에 반해, 우리는 deeper models가 task의 associativity를 활용하여 이 스케일링을 극적으로 개선하는 방식을 보인다. recurrent neural networks는 $k$단계에 걸쳐 원소들을 sequentially compose하고, multilayer networks는 $\\log k$ layers에서 인접한 pair들을 parallel하게 compose한다. 전체적으로 sequential group composition task는 deep learning의 메커니즘을 들여다볼 수 있는 tractable한 창을 제공한다."},{"id":"65347","en":"Lie-Algebraic Neural Koopman Dynamics","ko":"리 대수 신경 Koopman 동역학","authors":"Jiwoong Kim, Jongwon Lee, Jungwoo Park, Sungwoo Park","pos":"#1206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EVlt6J7PGR","abs":"<p>We present a Lie-algebraic approach to model Koopman dynamics that integrates algebraic structure with computational scalability. The proposed formulation constrains the neural generators to evolve within prescribed Lie subalgebras and constructs finite-time flows through a neural Magnus expansion construction, thereby maintaining consistency with the associated Lie-group composition over each time segment. To address the computational burden inherent in sequential propagation, we exploit the associativity of Lie-group compositions and construct segmentwise propagators via a prefix-scan algorithm, which reduces the depth of temporal composition from linear to logarithmic. Consequently, the framework enables accurate long-horizon prediction while improving computational efficiency, and provides a principled foundation for scalable Koopman operator learning for nonlinear systems.</p>"},{"id":"65597","en":"CUPID in the Model Zoo: Online Matchmaking for Selecting Your Dream LLM","ko":"모델 주(Model Zoo) 속의 CUPID: 당신의 이상적 LLM 선택을 위한 온라인 매치메이킹","authors":"Son Nguyen, Xinyuan Liu, Ransalu Senanayake","pos":"#2109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=C0762WekyA","abs":"<p>Users increasingly face the challenge of selecting an appropriate LLM for a given task from a rapidly growing pool of LLMs, each with distinct but often opaque latent properties. Compounding this challenge, users may lack the vocabulary or awareness to explicitly articulate the characteristics they value in an LLM's responses or deployment. We propose an interaction-efficient active learning framework in which a dueling bandit algorithm iteratively selects pairs of LLMs, collects user feedback about their responses, and updates its belief about the user's latent preferences. We introduce a novel belief-aware upper confidence bound strategy that balances exploration of the model pool with exploitation of inferred preferences, enabling efficient alignment between user needs and LLM capabilities under user-specified cost and time budgets. Through diverse experiments on LLMs and human studies, we experimentally verify that our model can efficiently match users to LLMs at a lower cost.</p>"},{"id":"64756","en":"Constrained Flow Optimization via Sequential Fine-Tuning for Molecular Design","ko":"분자 설계를 위한 순차적 Fine-Tuning을 통한 Constrained Flow Optimization","authors":"Sven Gutjahr, Riccardo De Santi, Luca Schaufelberger, Kjell Jorner, Andreas Krause","pos":"#2402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KBpIlcUIx1","abs":"<p>Adapting generative foundation models, in particular diffusion and flow models, to optimize given reward functions (e.g., binding affinity) while satisfying constraints (e.g., molecular synthesizability) is fundamental for their adoption in real-world scientific discovery applications such as molecular design or protein engineering. While recent works have introduced scalable methods for reward-guided fine-tuning of such models via reinforcement learning and control schemes, it remains an open problem how to algorithmically trade-off reward maximization and constraint satisfaction in a reliable and predictable manner. Motivated by this challenge, we first present a rigorous framework for <em>Constrained Generative Optimization</em>, which brings an optimization viewpoint to the introduced adaptation problem and retrieves the relevant task of constrained generation as a sub-case. Then, we introduce Constrained Flow Optimization (CFO), an algorithm that automatically and provably balances reward maximization and constraint satisfaction by reducing the original problem to progressive fine-tuning via established, scalable methods. We provide convergence guarantees for constrained generative optimization and constrained generation via CFO. Ultimately, we present an experimental evaluation of CFO on both synthetic, yet illustrative, settings, and a molecular design task.</p>","absKo":"<p>generative foundation model, 특히 diffusion model과 flow model을 주어진 reward function(예: binding affinity)을 최적화하면서 동시에 constraint(예: molecular synthesizability)를 만족하도록 적응시키는 것은 molecular design이나 protein engineering 같은 실제 과학적 발견 응용에서의 채택을 위해 핵심적이다. 최근 연구들은 reinforcement learning과 control scheme을 통해 이러한 모델을 reward-guided fine-tuning하는 확장 가능한 방법들을 제시했지만, reward maximization과 constraint satisfaction 사이의 trade-off를 신뢰할 수 있고 예측 가능하게 알고리즘적으로 조절하는 방법은 여전히 열린 문제다. 이러한 도전에 동기 부여받아, 우리는 먼저 <em>Constrained Generative Optimization</em>에 대한 엄밀한 framework를 제시하여, 제시된 적응 문제에 optimization 관점을 도입하고 관련된 constrained generation task를 하위 사례로 포착한다. 이어서 Constrained Flow Optimization(CFO)을 소개하는데, 이는 기존의 확장 가능한 방법들을 이용한 progressive fine-tuning으로 원래 문제를 환원함으로써 reward maximization과 constraint satisfaction을 자동으로 그리고 증명 가능하게 균형 맞추는 알고리즘이다. 우리는 CFO에 대해 constrained generative optimization과 constrained generation 모두에 대한 convergence guarantee를 제공한다. 마지막으로 synthetic하지만 설명적인 설정과 molecular design task에서 CFO의 실험적 평가를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"60870","en":"ToaSt: Token Channel Selection and Structured Pruning for Efficient ViT","ko":"ToaSt: 효율적인 ViT를 위한 Token Channel Selection 및 Structured Pruning","authors":"Hyunchan Moon, Cheonjun Park, Steven Waslander","pos":"#2704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vpwx8GRbkZ","abs":"<p>Vision Transformers (ViTs) have achieved remarkable success across various vision tasks, yet their deployment is often hindered by prohibitive computational costs. While structured weight pruning and token compression have emerged as promising solutions, they suffer from prolonged retraining times and global propagation that creates optimization challenges, respectively. We propose ToaSt, a decoupled framework applying specialized strategies to distinct ViT components. We apply coupled head-wise structured pruning to Multi-Head Self-Attention modules, leveraging attention operation characteristics to enhance robustness. For Feed-Forward Networks (over 60\\% of FLOPs), we introduce Token Channel Selection (TCS) that enhances compression ratios while avoiding global propagation issues. Our analysis reveals TCS effectively filters redundant noise during selection. Extensive evaluations across nine diverse models, including DeiT, ViT-MAE, and Swin Transformer, demonstrate that ToaSt achieves superior trade-offs between accuracy and efficiency, consistently outperforming existing baselines. On ViT-MAE-Huge, ToaSt achieves 88.52\\% accuracy (+1.64 \\%) with 39.4\\% FLOPs reduction. ToaSt transfers effectively to downstream tasks, achieving 52.2 versus 51.9 mAP on COCO object detection. Code and models will be released upon acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision Transformer (ViT)는 다양한 vision task에서 뛰어난 성공을 거두었지만, 배포 시에는 과도한 계산 비용이 발목을 잡는 경우가 많다. structured weight pruning과 token compression이 유망한 해결책으로 등장했지만, 각각 장기간의 retraining과 optimization 문제를 유발하는 global propagation이라는 한계를 가진다. 우리는 서로 다른 ViT 구성요소에 특화된 전략을 적용하는 decoupled framework인 ToaSt를 제안한다. 우리는 Multi-Head Self-Attention module에 coupled head-wise structured pruning을 적용하여 attention operation의 특성을 활용해 robustness를 향상시킨다. FLOPs의 60\\% 이상을 차지하는 Feed-Forward Network (FFN)에는 Token Channel Selection (TCS)을 도입하여 global propagation 문제를 피하면서 compression ratio를 높인다. 우리의 분석은 TCS가 selection 과정에서 redundant noise를 효과적으로 걸러낸다는 것을 보여준다. DeiT, ViT-MAE, Swin Transformer를 포함한 9개의 다양한 모델에 대한 광범위한 평가에서, ToaSt가 accuracy와 efficiency 사이에서 더 우수한 trade-off를 달성하며 기존 baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보였다. ViT-MAE-Huge에서 ToaSt는 88.52\\% accuracy(+1.64 \\%)와 39.4\\% FLOPs reduction을 달성한다. ToaSt는 downstream task로도 효과적으로 전이되어, COCO object detection에서 52.2 대 51.9 mAP를 달성한다. 코드는 논문 채택 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"60541","en":"The Ideal Expression Is Not a Local Optimum: A Revisit of EQL with Zero-Point Constraints","ko":"이상적 표현은 국소 최적점이 아니다: 영점 제약을 적용한 EQL 재고찰","authors":"Sannyuya Liu, Ao Chen, Lin Liu, Ruxia Liang, Xiaoxuan Shen, Jianwen Sun","pos":"#2708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zAuh9CGr9R","abs":"<p>Symbolic Regression aims to discover interpretable mathematical expressions from data. Equation Learner (EQL) is a gradient-based method with strong fitting capability and expressive potential, yet it often activates redundant operators as model complexity grows, leading to over-complex expressions and unstable equation recovery. We analyze a gradient residual issue induced by operators that do not vanish at zero, which can prevent the ideal sparse expression from being a local optimum and bias training toward unnecessarily complex structures, making exact recovery nearly unattainable in practice. To address this, we propose EQL-Z, a structurally controllable symbolic regression framework. EQL-Z enforces zero-point constraints via zero-point consistent operator transformations to eliminate residual gradients on silent paths, and performs an incremental small-to-large structure search that grows depth/width from a compact seed under a complexity-penalized validation score. After selecting a compact structure, we optionally apply BFGS fine-tuning to refine coefficients. Experiments on synthetic and real-world datasets show that EQL-Z substantially improves exact equation recovery and in-/out-of-distribution generalization over vanilla EQL, achieving performance close to the best existing symbolic regression baselines. The code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EQL-Z-BE6C/.</p>","absKo":"<p>Symbolic Regression은 데이터로부터 해석 가능한 수학적 expression을 발견하는 것을 목표로 한다. Equation Learner (EQL)은 gradient-based method로서 강한 fitting 능력과 표현 잠재력을 갖지만, model complexity가 커질수록 redundant operator를 자주 활성화하여 지나치게 복잡한 expression과 불안정한 equation recovery를 초래한다. 우리는 zero에서 소거되지 않는 operator가 유발하는 gradient residual 문제를 분석한다. 이 문제는 이상적인 sparse expression이 local optimum이 되는 것을 막고, training을 불필요하게 복잡한 구조로 편향시켜 실제로 exact recovery를 거의 불가능하게 만든다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 구조적으로 제어 가능한 symbolic regression framework인 EQL-Z를 제안한다. EQL-Z는 zero-point consistent operator transformation을 통해 zero-point constraint를 강제하여 silent path의 residual gradient를 제거하고, complexity-penalized validation score 하에서 compact seed로부터 depth/width를 확장하는 incremental small-to-large structure search를 수행한다. compact structure를 선택한 뒤에는 optional하게 BFGS fine-tuning을 적용해 coefficient를 정제한다. synthetic 및 real-world dataset에 대한 실험에서 EQL-Z는 vanilla EQL에 비해 exact equation recovery와 in-/out-of-distribution generalization을 크게 향상시키며, 기존 최상위 symbolic regression baseline에 근접한 성능을 달성한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EQL-Z-BE6C/ 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"63455","en":"Coupled Trigger Optimization and Vulnerable Parameter Alignment for Persistent Backdoor Attacks on Federated Learning","ko":"연합 학습에 대한 지속적 백도어 공격을 위한 결합 트리거 최적화와 취약 파라미터 정렬","authors":"zhixuan ma, Haichang Gao, Shangwen Li, Ping Wang, Han Yu","pos":"#2906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=X3wIJK1gmP","abs":"<p>Federated learning (FL) is vulnerable to backdoor attacks. Yet sustaining backdoor effectiveness under repeated aggregation remains challenging. Existing methods often rely on heuristic trigger designs or indiscriminant parameter manipulation, leading to rapid decay or detectable anomalies. In this work, we view FL backdoor persistence through the lens of optimization dynamics, and argue that long-lasting attacks require alignment between trigger-induced representations and aggregation-stable parameter directions. Based on this insight, we propose the Coupled Trigger Optimization and Vulnerable Parameter Alignment (CTO-VPA) FL backdoor attack method. By constraining updates to this coupled subspace, backdoor behaviors can be embedded into optimization-stable directions while preserving benign performance. Experiments across multiple datasets and defense settings show that CTO-VPA achieves substantially improved persistence and robustness compared to prior attacks, highlighting the importance of trigger–parameter coupling in FL settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>Federated learning(FL)은 backdoor attack에 취약하다. 그러나 반복적인 aggregation 하에서 backdoor 효과를 지속시키는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 기존 방법은 종종 heuristic한 trigger 설계나 무차별적인 parameter 조작에 의존하여, 빠른 성능 저하 또는 탐지 가능한 이상 징후를 초래한다. 본 연구에서는 FL backdoor persistence를 optimization dynamics의 관점에서 바라보고, 오래 지속되는 공격은 trigger로 유도된 representation과 aggregation에 대해 안정적인 parameter 방향 사이의 정렬이 필요하다고 주장한다. 이 통찰에 기반해 우리는 Coupled Trigger Optimization and Vulnerable Parameter Alignment(CTO-VPA) FL backdoor attack 방법을 제안한다. 이 결합된 subspace로 업데이트를 제한함으로써, benign performance를 유지하면서 backdoor behavior를 optimization-stable한 방향에 내재시킬 수 있다. 여러 dataset과 defense setting 전반의 실험은 CTO-VPA가 기존 공격보다 훨씬 향상된 지속성과 robustness를 달성함을 보여주며, FL 환경에서 trigger-parameter coupling의 중요성을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"65451","en":"Active Budget Allocation for Efficient Scaling Law Estimation via Surrogate-Guided Pruning","ko":"Surrogate 기반 가지치기를 통한 효율적 스케일링 법칙 추정을 위한 능동 예산 할당","authors":"Viktoria Schram, Markus Hiller, Daniel Beck, Trevor Cohn","pos":"#3500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DXnLu7qu75","abs":"Predicting model performance at larger scales enables the design of training strategies and architectures tailored to specific performance targets. Empirical scaling law research identifies functional forms to aid this prediction task. These describe the relationship between loss and compute using a loss-compute frontier defined by learning curves. Due to the empirical nature of this approach, the computational burden is substantial, making strategic resource allocation essential -- yet it remains surprisingly underexplored.  In this work, we address this shortcoming by exploring the suitability of Successive Halving (SH) and SH combined with parametric and non-parametric surrogate models. In addition to enabling a more systematic allocation of a given compute budget, our findings show that SH paired with surrogate models yields a set of learning curves that includes one with a lower loss-compute value than what naive uniform allocation or an SH-only approach can obtain.    Our experiments demonstrate mean relative improvements of up to $2.84\\%$ and $5.47\\%$ on real-world and synthetic learning curve datasets.  This strategic resource allocation enables us to obtain accurate scaling laws at significantly reduced computational costs, saving up to $98.7\\%$ over the traditional exhaustive approach."},{"id":"63057","en":"Evolutionary Multi-View Classification with Label Noise via Gradient and Feature Dual-Perception","ko":"경사 및 특징 이중 인지를 통한 레이블 노이즈 하의 진화적 다중 뷰 분류","authors":"Shuai Li, Xinyan Liang, Yuhua Qian, Li Lv","pos":"#3905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aWUlNpaZs1","abs":"<p>This paper studies a fundamental yet often overlooked premise in evolutionary multi-view classification (EMVC): the impact of label noise on EMVC, such as distorting fitness landscapes shaped by individual fitness values (e.g., test accuracy). Traditional EMVC assumes training labels are noise-free, yet this often fails in practice. As a result, label noise introduces harmful supervision during the training phase, resulting in distorted fitness landscapes and the emergence of fitness evaluation bias (FEB). This bias misguides the evolutionary trajectory, causing the search process to stagnate in local optima.  Given that label noise largely stems from the mislabeling of samples near their decision boundaries by human annotators, we thus compared the decision boundaries of human annotators and models, and found discrepancies between the two. Based on this observation, we propose a simple yet effective ``detect-then-calibrate\" data purification framework that leverages outlier analysis in the gradient space (i.e., treating outliers as noisy samples) and prototype calibration in the feature space (i.e., utilizing feature prototypes of noise-free samples to correct the labels of noisy samples). Experimental results demonstrate that this strategy can effectively purify the data and alleviate FEB; furthermore, it can improve the performance of various multi-view learning paradigms in label noise scenarios. (The code will be published.)</p>","absKo":"<p>본 논문은 evolutionary multi-view classification(EMVC)에서 종종 간과되는 근본적 전제를 연구한다. 즉, label noise가 EMVC에 미치는 영향, 예를 들어 individual fitness value(예: test accuracy)에 의해 형성되는 fitness landscape를 왜곡하는 문제이다. 전통적인 EMVC는 training label이 noise-free라고 가정하지만, 이는 실제에서는 종종 성립하지 않는다. 그 결과 label noise는 training phase 동안 해로운 supervision을 도입하여 왜곡된 fitness landscape와 fitness evaluation bias(FEB)의 발생을 초래한다. 이 bias는 evolutionary trajectory를 잘못 유도하여 search process가 local optimum에서 정체되게 만든다. label noise는 주로 human annotator가 decision boundary 근처의 sample을 잘못 라벨링하는 데서 비롯되므로, 우리는 human annotator와 model의 decision boundary를 비교했고 두 boundary 사이에 차이가 있음을 발견했다. 이러한 관찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 gradient space에서 outlier analysis를 활용하고(즉, outlier를 noisy sample로 간주), feature space에서 prototype calibration을 활용하는(즉, noise-free sample의 feature prototype을 이용해 noisy sample의 label을 보정하는) 간단하면서도 효과적인 ``detect-then-calibrate\" data purification framework를 제안한다. 실험 결과는 이 전략이 데이터를 효과적으로 정화하고 FEB를 완화할 수 있음을 보여주며, 더 나아가 label noise scenario에서 다양한 multi-view learning paradigm의 성능을 향상시킬 수 있음을 보인다. (코드는 추후 공개될 예정이다.)</p>"},{"id":"66762","en":"Cross-View Lewis Weight Fusion Empowering Exemplar Replay for Federated Class-Incremental Learning","ko":"Federated Class-Incremental Learning을 위해 Exemplar Replay를 강화하는 Cross-View Lewis Weight Fusion","authors":"Zhuang Qi, Yingpeng Tang, Lei Meng, Xiaoxiao Li, Han Yu, Xiangxu Meng","pos":"#3907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0XQ2kvDaVE","abs":"<p>Federated Class-Incremental Learning (FCIL) aims to continually expand a model’s recognition capacity in a distributed environment, enabling it to learn new classes while retaining knowledge of previously seen ones. Exemplar replay has emerged as a promising strategy owing to its simplicity and effectiveness. Existing methods either select exemplars based on local dynamics or construct global feature spaces to identify representative samples. However, they face inherent challenges in striking a balance between effectiveness and privacy. To address this issue, this paper proposes a Cross-view Lewis weIght Fusion method for exemplar replay in FCIL, termed CLIF, which fuses multi-view importance scores to guide representative sample selection under federated settings. Specifically, CLIF consists of two main modules: 1) the cross-view Lewis weight fusion module computes and integrates Lewis weights from multiple feature perspectives to achieve consistent importance estimation, ensuring that the selected samples better reflect the global data distribution and thus enhancing the representativeness of the replay subset. Building on this, 2) the frequency-based weighted training module adjusts the loss contribution of each sample according to its selection frequency across views, which emphasizes the contribution of critical samples. Moreover, we provide a theoretical analysis to guarantee the soundness and effectiveness of CLIF. Extensive experiments on three datasets demonstrate that our method consistently improves baselines by 1%–6%, supporting the above claims.</p>"},{"id":"64224","en":"ShapCCS: Shapley-Driven Client Coreset Selection in Federated Learning","ko":"ShapCCS: 연합 학습에서 Shapley 기반 클라이언트 코어셋 선택","authors":"Shuo Ji, Jie Hu, Zhouqiao He, Zijie Zhao, Tianrui Li, Jie Xu","pos":"#3908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PnabunIVDL","abs":"Computation overhead has emerged as a critical bottleneck in Federated Learning (FL). Coreset selection tackles this challenge by constructing an informative subset to represent the full dataset. However, existing approaches optimize coreset construction solely at the data level and enforce a uniform retention ratio across all clients, ignoring client heterogeneity and introducing detrimental fragmented clients. In this paper, we first introduce a *gradient projection Shapley value* (GPSV) to evaluate client contributions. GPSV captures both the directional and magnitude information of client updates and enables exact Shapley value calculation with $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ per-coalition evaluation. Building on GPSV, we then propose ShapCCS, the first client-level coreset selection strategy for FL. ShapCCS prioritizes clients with high GPSV scores while excluding fragmented clients with negligible or even negative GPSV. As a client-level coreset selection strategy, ShapCCS can be integrated with a data-level selection approach, and additionally reduces communication costs, an advantage unattainable by data-level methods alone. Extensive experiments demonstrate the superiority of ShapCCS on model performance and robustness to noise. The code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ShapCCS-5CBB.","absKo":"Federated Learning (FL)에서 계산 오버헤드는 핵심적인 병목으로 부상했다. Coreset selection은 전체 데이터셋을 대표하는 정보성 높은 subset을 구성함으로써 이 문제를 해결한다. 그러나 기존 방법들은 coreset 구성을 오직 데이터 수준에서만 최적화하고 모든 client에 동일한 retention ratio를 강제하여, client 이질성을 무시하고 해로운 fragmented client를 초래한다. 본 논문에서는 먼저 client 기여도를 평가하기 위해 *gradient projection Shapley value* (GPSV)를 도입한다. GPSV는 client update의 방향성과 크기 정보를 모두 포착하며, coalition당 $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ 평가로 정확한 Shapley value 계산을 가능하게 한다. GPSV를 바탕으로, 우리는 FL을 위한 최초의 client-level coreset selection 전략인 ShapCCS를 제안한다. ShapCCS는 GPSV 점수가 높은 client를 우선시하는 동시에, GPSV가 미미하거나 심지어 음수인 fragmented client는 제외한다. client-level coreset selection 전략으로서 ShapCCS는 data-level selection 접근법과 통합될 수 있으며, 데이터 수준 방법만으로는 얻을 수 없는 communication cost 감소 효과도 제공한다. 광범위한 실험은 모델 성능과 noise에 대한 robustness 측면에서 ShapCCS의 우수성을 보여준다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ShapCCS-5CBB 에서 제공된다."},{"id":"64659","en":"SWING: Unlocking Implicit Graph Representations for Graph Random Features","ko":"SWING: Graph Random Feature를 위한 암묵적 Graph Representation 실현","authors":"Alessandro Manenti, Kumar Avinava Dubey, Arijit Sehanobish, Cesare Alippi, Krzysztof Choromanski","pos":"#3909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LBcnybFVBp","abs":"We propose SWING: Space Walks for Implicit Network Graphs, a new class of algorithms for computations involving Graph Random Features on graphs given by implicit representations (i-graphs), where edge-weights are defined as bi-variate functions of feature vectors in the corresponding nodes. Those classes of graphs include several prominent examples, such as: *$\\epsilon$-neighborhood* graphs, used on regular basis in machine learning. Rather than conducting walks on graphs' nodes, those methods rely on walks in continuous spaces, in which those graphs are embedded. To accurately and efficiently approximate original combinatorial calculations, SWING applies customized Gumbel-softmax sampling mechanism with linearized kernels, obtained via random features coupled with importance sampling techniques. This mechanism is of its own interest. SWING relies on the deep connection between implicitly defined graphs and Fourier analysis, presented in this paper. SWING is accelerator-friendly and does not require input graph materialization. We provide detailed analysis of SWING and complement it with thorough experiments on different classes of i-graphs.","absKo":"우리는 SWING: Space Walks for Implicit Network Graphs를 제안한다. 이는 implicit representations(i-graphs)로 주어진 graph에서 Graph Random Features를 포함하는 계산을 위한 새로운 알고리즘 계열로, edge-weight가 대응하는 node의 feature vector에 대한 bivariate function으로 정의된다. 이러한 graph class에는 machine learning에서 일상적으로 사용되는 *$\\epsilon$-neighborhood* graph와 같은 대표적인 예들이 포함된다. 이 방법들은 graph의 node 위에서 walk를 수행하는 대신, 해당 graph가 임베딩된 continuous space에서의 walk에 의존한다. 원래의 combinatorial calculation을 정확하고 효율적으로 근사하기 위해, SWING은 random features와 importance sampling 기법을 결합해 얻은 linearized kernel 위에 customized Gumbel-softmax sampling mechanism을 적용한다. 이 메커니즘 자체도 흥미로운 연구 주제이다. SWING은 implicitly defined graph와 Fourier analysis 사이의 깊은 연결에 기반하며, 이 논문에서 이를 제시한다. SWING은 accelerator-friendly하고 input graph materialization을 요구하지 않는다. 우리는 SWING에 대한 상세한 분석을 제공하고, 다양한 i-graph class에 대한 철저한 실험으로 이를 보완한다."},{"id":"63564","en":"FlashSinkhorn: IO-Aware Entropic Optimal Transport on GPU","ko":"FlashSinkhorn: GPU 상 IO 인지 엔트로피 최적수송","authors":"Felix X.-F. Ye, Xingjie Li, An Yu, Ming-Ching Chang, LINSONG CHU, Davis Wertheimer","pos":"#3910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VzIA4MASxK","abs":"Entropic optimal transport (EOT) via Sinkhorn iterations is widely used in modern machine learning, yet GPU solvers remain inefficient at scale. Tensorized implementations suffer quadratic HBM traffic from dense $n\\times m$ interactions, while existing online backends avoid storing dense matrices but still rely on generic tiled map-reduce reduction kernels with limited fusion.  We present **FlashSinkhorn**, an IO-aware EOT solver for squared Euclidean cost that rewrites stabilized log-domain Sinkhorn updates as row-wise LogSumExp reductions of biased dot-product scores, the same normalization as transformer attention. This enables FlashAttention-style fusion and tiling: fused Triton kernels stream tiles through on-chip SRAM and update dual potentials in a single pass, substantially reducing HBM IO per iteration while retaining linear-memory operations. We further provide streaming kernels for transport application, enabling scalable first- and second-order optimization. On A100 GPUs, FlashSinkhorn achieves up to $32\\times$ forward-pass and $161\\times$ end-to-end speedups over state-of-the-art online baselines on point-cloud OT, improves scalability on OT-based downstream tasks.","absKo":"Sinkhorn iteration을 통한 entropic optimal transport(EOT)는 현대 machine learning에서 널리 사용되지만, GPU solver는 대규모에서 여전히 비효율적이다. Tensorized implementation은 dense $n\\times m$ interaction 때문에 quadratic HBM traffic을 유발하는 반면, 기존 online backend는 dense matrix 저장을 피하지만 여전히 fusion이 제한적인 일반적인 tiled map-reduce reduction kernel에 의존한다. 우리는 squared Euclidean cost를 위한 IO-aware EOT solver인 **FlashSinkhorn**을 제시한다. 이 방법은 stabilized log-domain Sinkhorn update를 biased dot-product score의 row-wise LogSumExp reduction으로 다시 작성하며, 이는 transformer attention과 동일한 normalization이다. 이를 통해 FlashAttention 스타일의 fusion과 tiling이 가능해진다. fused Triton kernel은 tile을 on-chip SRAM을 통해 스트리밍하고 dual potential을 단일 pass에서 갱신하여, linear-memory operation을 유지하면서 iteration당 HBM IO를 크게 줄인다. 또한 transport application을 위한 streaming kernel도 제공하여, 확장 가능한 first- 및 second-order optimization을 가능하게 한다. A100 GPU에서 FlashSinkhorn은 point-cloud OT에서 최첨단 online baseline 대비 forward pass 기준 최대 $32\\times$, end-to-end 기준 최대 $161\\times$의 속도 향상을 달성하며, OT 기반 downstream task에서 확장성도 개선한다."},{"id":"65331","en":"Clustered Influence Functions","ko":"클러스터링된 영향 함수","authors":"Miklós Máté Badó, Kristian Fenech","pos":"#3911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Efjuj6kanc","abs":"Influence functions are a standard tool for data debugging and unlearning, but they become impractical for **high-query** subset workloads such as large-$K$ cross-validation, repeated resampling, or interactive what-if analysis as each subset query typically requires an expensive inverse-curvature solve. We introduce **Clustered Influence Functions (CiF)**, which turns subset influence into an **amortized subset oracle**. We build a compact cache once by clustering training gradients, solve a damped Generalised Gauss-Newton system only for cluster means, and answer new subset queries by a linear recombination using cluster membership counts. This yields per-query cost of $O(Cp)$ linear in the cache size $C$, and the number of model parameters $p$. We further provide a diagnostic error bound that decomposes approximation error into a **clustering scatter** term and a **solver residual** term, making the accuracy-compute tradeoff explicit through the cache budget and solver tolerance. Evaluations across MNIST, CIFAR-10, show that CiF matches per-query influence rankings while significantly reducing the total runtime in high-$Q$ regimes, enabling influence-based workflows that are otherwise computationally prohibitive."},{"id":"60625","en":"FedGain: Toward Negative-Gain-Free Client Collaboration in Federated Learning","ko":"FedGain: Federated Learning에서 Negative-Gain 없는 클라이언트 협업을 향하여","authors":"Yuqing Zhang, Changli Zhou, Binghuang Huang, Hui Tian","pos":"#4112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yLn1COP0AN","abs":"<p>Data heterogeneity is a fundamental challenge in Federated Learning (FL), where induced model drift often results in \"negative gains\" for global models on data-abundant clients, with performance falling below that of local training. To address this issue, we propose FedGain, a novel framework that optimizes collaborative client clustering to mitigate the negative gain. We are the first to develop a modified Scaling Law to quantify the \"reduction\" in data utility caused by heterogeneity and define Effective Federated Capacity to align clients with the highest potential collaboration gains. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our modified SL strictly adheres to the power-law learning discipline in non-IID scenarios. FedGain effectively suppresses negative gains to a negligible level across various FL algorithms and outperforms other Clustered FL methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>데이터 이질성은 Federated Learning (FL)의 근본적인 도전 과제이며, 이로 인해 유도되는 model drift는 종종 데이터가 풍부한 client에서 global model의 성능이 local training보다 낮아지는 \"negative gain\"을 초래한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 negative gain을 완화하도록 collaborative client clustering을 최적화하는 새로운 프레임워크 FedGain을 제안한다. 우리는 이질성으로 인해 발생하는 데이터 유틸리티의 \"감소\"를 정량화하기 위해 수정된 Scaling Law를 처음으로 개발하고, 가장 높은 잠재적 collaboration gain을 가진 client를 정렬하기 위해 Effective Federated Capacity를 정의한다. 대규모 실험은 우리의 수정된 SL이 non-IID 시나리오에서 power-law learning discipline을 엄격하게 따름을 보여준다. FedGain은 다양한 FL 알고리즘 전반에서 negative gain을 무시할 수 있는 수준으로 효과적으로 억제하며, 다른 Clustered FL 방법들을 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"62887","en":"FlashSketch: Sketch-Kernel Co-Design for Fast Sparse Sketching on GPUs","ko":"FlashSketch: GPU에서 빠른 희소 스케치 연산을 위한 Sketch-Kernel 공동 설계","authors":"Rajat Vadiraj Dwaraknath, Sungyoon Kim, Mert Pilanci","pos":"#4203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cCwxV6rSXF","abs":"Sparse sketches such as the sparse Johnson–Lindenstrauss transform are a core primitive in randomized numerical linear algebra because they leverage random sparsity to reduce the arithmetic cost of sketching, while still offering strong approximation guarantees. Their random sparsity, however, is at odds with efficient implementations on modern GPUs, since it leads to irregular memory access patterns that degrade memory bandwidth utilization. Motivated by this tension, we pursue a sketch–kernel co-design approach: we design a new family of sparse sketches, BlockPerm-SJLT, whose sparsity structure is chosen to enable FlashSketch, a corresponding optimized CUDA kernel that implements these sketches efficiently. The design of BlockPerm-SJLT introduces a tunable parameter that explicitly trades off the tension between GPU-efficiency and sketching robustness. We provide theoretical guarantees for BlockPerm-SJLT under the oblivious subspace embedding (OSE) framework, and also analyze the effect of the tunable parameter on sketching quality. We empirically evaluate FlashSketch on standard RandNLA benchmarks, as well as an end-to-end ML data attribution pipeline called GraSS. FlashSketch pushes the Pareto frontier of sketching quality versus speed, across a range of regimes and tasks, and achieves a global geomean speedup of roughly $1.7 \\times$ over the prior state-of-the-art GPU sketches.","absKo":"Sparse sketches such as the sparse Johnson–Lindenstrauss transform은 랜덤한 sparsity를 활용해 sketching의 연산 비용을 줄이면서도 강한 근사 보장을 제공하기 때문에 randomized numerical linear algebra의 핵심 primitive이다. 그러나 이러한 랜덤 sparsity는 현대 GPU에서의 효율적인 구현과는 맞지 않는데, 불규칙한 메모리 접근 패턴을 유발해 메모리 대역폭 활용도를 떨어뜨리기 때문이다. 이러한 긴장 관계에 동기부여를 받아, 우리는 sketch-kernel co-design 접근을 추진한다. 즉, 우리는 BlockPerm-SJLT라는 새로운 sparse sketch 계열을 설계했으며, 그 sparsity 구조는 이 스케치를 효율적으로 구현하는 대응 CUDA kernel인 FlashSketch를 가능하게 하도록 선택되었다. BlockPerm-SJLT의 설계는 GPU 효율성과 sketching robustnes 사이의 긴장을 명시적으로 trade off하는 조정 가능한 매개변수를 도입한다. 우리는 oblivious subspace embedding (OSE) framework 하에서 BlockPerm-SJLT의 이론적 보장을 제공하고, 조정 가능한 매개변수가 sketching quality에 미치는 영향도 분석한다. 또한 표준 RandNLA benchmark와, GraSS라는 end-to-end ML data attribution pipeline에서 FlashSketch를 실증적으로 평가한다. FlashSketch는 다양한 regime과 task 전반에서 sketching quality와 speed 사이의 Pareto frontier를 전진시키며, 이전 state-of-the-art GPU sketch 대비 전역 geomean speedup 약 $1.7 \\\\times$를 달성한다."},{"id":"63824","en":"SCNS: Continual Personalization of Diffusion Models via Submodular Concept Neuron Selection","ko":"SCNS: 부분모듈러 concept neuron selection을 통한 diffusion 모델의 지속적 개인화","authors":"Zijie Peng, Enneng Yang, Yifei Cheng, Hongliang Yuan, Fei Ma, Xiaochun Cao, Li Shen","pos":"#4301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TOJtbehWQ1","abs":"<p>Custom diffusion models (CDMs) have demonstrated impressive success in visual personalization tasks by enabling the generation of user-specific concepts. However, existing CDMs typically assume that personalized concepts are static and rely on costly model merging or sequential updates that are prone to catastrophic forgetting as new concepts are introduced. To address these limitations, we propose a Submodular Concept Neuron Selection method (SCNS), to solve CDMs with continual personalized concepts, which formulates continual personalization as a constrained submodular optimization problem to select a minimal yet sufficient set of concept-specific neurons under diminishing returns. SCNS combines a Facility Location-based coverage objective to suppress semantic redundancy, a Fisher-weighted risk proxy to protect previously learned concepts, and a cost-aware greedy rule to balance stability and plasticity with extreme sparsity. Extensive experiments demonstrate that SCNS achieves state-of-the-art performance in image alignment and anti-forgetting, while enabling fusion-free continual personalization by modifying only 0.41% of the total parameters for each concept on average. Our implementation is available at SCNS.</p>","absKo":"<p>Custom diffusion model(CDM)은 사용자별 concept의 생성을 가능하게 하여 visual personalization task에서 인상적인 성공을 보여왔다. 그러나 기존 CDM은 대체로 personalized concept이 정적이라고 가정하고, 새로운 concept이 추가될 때 catastrophic forgetting에 취약한 비용이 큰 model merging이나 sequential update에 의존한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 continual personalized concept을 다루는 CDM을 풀기 위한 Submodular Concept Neuron Selection(SCNS) method를 제안한다. SCNS는 continual personalization을 감소하는 한계효용 하에서 최소하지만 충분한 concept-specific neuron 집합을 선택하는 constrained submodular optimization problem으로 정식화한다. SCNS는 semantic redundancy를 억제하는 Facility Location 기반 coverage objective, 이전에 학습한 concept을 보호하는 Fisher-weighted risk proxy, 그리고 극단적인 sparsity 하에서 stability와 plasticity의 균형을 맞추는 cost-aware greedy rule을 결합한다. 광범위한 실험은 SCNS가 image alignment와 anti-forgetting에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하면서, 각 concept마다 평균적으로 전체 parameter의 0.41%만 수정하여 fusion-free continual personalization을 가능하게 함을 보여준다. 우리의 구현은 SCNS에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"64221","en":"Personalized Additive Modeling for Multi-level Federated Learning","ko":"다중 수준 연합 학습을 위한 개인화 가법 모델링","authors":"Shutong Chen, Tianyi Zhou, Guodong Long, Jie Ma, Jing Jiang, Chengqi Zhang","pos":"#4304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ppdh9cmOXu","abs":"<p>Contemporary AI faces the challenge of balancing generality with user-specific personalization. In federated learning (FL), this challenge is amplified by highly heterogeneous client data with complex non-IID patterns beyond standard modeling assumptions. Many existing FL methods are designed for relatively restricted heterogeneity settings (e.g., a fixed number of clusters or a fixed form of personalization), limiting their robustness under complex structures. In this work, we study FL from a \\emph{multi-level non-IID} perspective, where client similarity is approximated by multiple granularities of shared knowledge: global, subgroup, and client-specific components. This view captures coarse-to-fine relationships while requiring less prior knowledge of task boundaries. Building on this insight, we propose \\emph{Federated Multi-level Additive Modeling} (FeMAM), which learns multiple levels of shareable models and constructs personalized predictors via additive composition across levels. To move beyond a fixed structure, FeMAM allows models to grow and be pruned dynamically during training, adapting to diverse federated scenarios. Despite employing multiple models, FeMAM remains cost-friendly by activating only a small subset (one level) of models for training at a time. Extensive experiments show that FeMAM effectively approximates complex non-IID structures and consistently outperforms representative clustered and personalized FL baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대 AI는 일반성과 사용자별 personalization 사이의 균형을 맞추는 과제에 직면해 있다. federated learning (FL)에서는 이 과제가 표준적인 모델링 가정을 넘어서는 복잡한 non-IID 패턴을 지닌 매우 이질적인 client data로 인해 더욱 증폭된다. 기존의 많은 FL 방법은 비교적 제한된 이질성 설정(예: 고정된 개수의 cluster 또는 고정된 형태의 personalization)을 위해 설계되어 있어, 복잡한 구조에서는 견고성이 떨어진다. 본 연구에서는 client 유사성을 여러 해상도의 shared knowledge, 즉 global, subgroup, client-specific component로 근사하는 \\emph{multi-level non-IID} 관점에서 FL을 고찰한다. 이 관점은 coarse-to-fine 관계를 포착하면서도 task boundary에 대한 사전 지식을 덜 필요로 한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 \\emph{Federated Multi-level Additive Modeling} (FeMAM)을 제안한다. FeMAM은 공유 가능한 모델의 여러 수준을 학습하고, 각 수준을 additive composition으로 조합해 personalized predictor를 구성한다. 고정된 구조를 넘어가기 위해, FeMAM은 학습 중 모델이 동적으로 성장하고 pruning되도록 허용하여 다양한 federated 시나리오에 적응한다. 여러 모델을 사용함에도 불구하고, FeMAM은 한 번에 훈련에 활성화되는 모델의 작은 부분집합(하나의 수준)만 사용하므로 비용 효율적이다. 광범위한 실험은 FeMAM이 복잡한 non-IID 구조를 효과적으로 근사하며, 대표적인 clustered 및 personalized FL baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64010","en":"Minibatch selection for Language Models via Partition Matroid Constrained Gradient Matching","ko":"Partition Matroid 제약 gradient matching을 통한 Language Models용 미니배치 선택","authors":"Prayas Agrawal, Prateek Chanda, Ishita Khatri, Ganesh Ramakrishnan, Bamdev Mishra, Pratik Kumar Jawanpuria","pos":"#4306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Rl7YAiRT04","abs":"<p>Training Large Language Models (LLMs) on heterogeneous datasets requires optimizing domain representations to balance convergence speed and domain coverage. While recent methods reduce computational overhead by selecting high-quality data subsets, they typically perform selection independently per domain or rely on computationally expensive proxy models to determine continuous domain weights. In this paper, we propose a joint sample selection framework that learns better domain representations in the batch directly and formulate the selection objective as joint domain utility maximization subject to partition matroid constraints. This approach enforces domain-specific budgets while maximizing a validation-guided gradient matching utility across all domains simultaneously. Theoretically, we establish that this objective is weakly submodular, allowing us to employ a computationally efficient orthogonal matching pursuit algorithm with provable guarantees. Empirically, we demonstrate that our method significantly outperforms baselines that favor independent domain selection on mathematical reasoning and molecular generation benchmarks. Furthermore, our analysis show that our approach reduces the number of conflicting training gradient pairs significantly as compared to independent selection across domains or domain agnostic selection. Applied to Qwen2.5 and Llama-3 and trained on MethaMathQA and Mol-Instructions, our approach yields robust gains under multiple subset fractions, with improvements on nine math-reasoning and four molecule-generation benchmarks, highlighting cross-domain benefits of joint subset selection.</p>","absKo":"<p>이질적인 데이터셋에서 Large Language Models(LLMs)를 학습하려면 수렴 속도와 domain coverage의 균형을 맞추기 위해 domain representation을 최적화해야 한다. 최근 방법들은 고품질 데이터 subset을 선택함으로써 계산 오버헤드를 줄이지만, 대개 domain별로 독립적인 선택을 수행하거나 연속적인 domain weight를 결정하기 위해 계산 비용이 큰 proxy model에 의존한다. 본 논문에서는 batch 내에서 더 나은 domain representation을 직접 학습하는 joint sample selection framework를 제안하고, selection objective를 partition matroid constraint 하의 joint domain utility maximization으로 정식화한다. 이 접근법은 domain-specific budget을 강제하면서 모든 domain에 걸쳐 validation-guided gradient matching utility를 동시에 최대화한다. 이론적으로 우리는 이 objective가 weakly submodular임을 보이고, 이를 통해 provable guarantee를 갖는 계산 효율적인 orthogonal matching pursuit algorithm을 사용할 수 있음을 확립한다. 실증적으로, 우리는 제안 방법이 수학적 추론과 분자 생성 benchmark에서 independent domain selection을 선호하는 baseline들을 크게 능가함을 보인다. 또한 우리의 분석은 domain 간 independent selection이나 domain-agnostic selection과 비교했을 때, 제안 방법이 충돌하는 training gradient pair의 수를 크게 줄임을 보여준다. Qwen2.5와 Llama-3에 적용하고 MethaMathQA와 Mol-Instructions로 학습한 결과, 우리의 접근법은 여러 subset fraction에서 견고한 향상을 보이며, 9개의 math-reasoning benchmark와 4개의 molecule-generation benchmark에서 개선을 달성해 joint subset selection의 cross-domain 이점을 부각한다.</p>"},{"id":"64837","en":"Efficient Tail-Aware Generative Optimization via Flow Model Fine-Tuning","ko":"Flow Model Fine-Tuning을 통한 효율적 Tail-Aware 생성 최적화","authors":"Zifan Wang, Riccardo De Santi, Xiaoyu Mo, Michael Zavlanos, Andreas Krause, Karl Johansson","pos":"#4310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JJw9sN5Lah","abs":"<p>Fine-tuning pre-trained diffusion and flow models to optimize downstream utilities is central to real-world deployment. Existing entropy-regularized methods primarily maximize expected reward, providing no mechanism to shape tail behavior. However, tail control is often essential: the lower tail determines reliability by limiting low-reward failures, while the upper tail enables discovery by prioritizing rare, high-reward outcomes. In this work, we present Tail-aware Flow Fine-Tuning (TFFT), a principled and efficient distributional fine-tuning algorithm based on the Conditional Value-at-Risk (CVaR). We address two distinct tail-shaping goals: right-CVaR for seeking novel samples in the high-reward tail and left-CVaR for controlling worst-case samples in the low-reward tail.  Unlike prior approaches that rely on non-linear optimization, we leverage the variational dual formulation of CVaR to decompose it into a decoupled two-stage procedure: a lightweight one-dimensional threshold optimization step, and a single entropy-regularized fine-tuning process via a specific pseudo-reward. This decomposition achieves CVaR fine-tuning efficiently with computational cost comparable to standard expected fine-tuning methods. We demonstrate the effectiveness of TFFT across illustrative experiments, high-dimensional text-to-image generation, and molecular design.</p>","absKo":"<p>사전 학습된 diffusion 및 flow model을 downstream utility 최적화를 위해 fine-tuning하는 것은 실제 배포의 핵심이다. 기존의 entropy-regularized method는 주로 expected reward를 최대화할 뿐, tail behavior를 형성할 메커니즘을 제공하지 않는다. 그러나 tail control은 종종 필수적이다. lower tail은 low-reward 실패를 제한함으로써 reliability를 결정하고, upper tail은 드물지만 high-reward 결과를 우선시함으로써 discovery를 가능하게 한다. 본 연구에서는 Conditional Value-at-Risk (CVaR)에 기반한 원리적이고 효율적인 distributional fine-tuning 알고리즘인 Tail-aware Flow Fine-Tuning (TFFT)을 제시한다. 우리는 두 가지 서로 다른 tail shaping 목표를 다룬다: high-reward tail에서 새로운 sample을 찾기 위한 right-CVaR와 low-reward tail에서 최악의 sample을 제어하기 위한 left-CVaR. 비선형 최적화에 의존하는 기존 접근과 달리, 우리는 CVaR의 variational dual formulation을 활용하여 이를 두 단계의 분리된 절차로 분해한다. 즉, 가벼운 1차원 threshold optimization 단계와 특정 pseudo-reward를 통한 단일 entropy-regularized fine-tuning 과정이다. 이 분해는 표준 expected fine-tuning method와 비슷한 계산 비용으로 CVaR fine-tuning을 효율적으로 달성한다. 우리는 illustrative experiment, 고차원 text-to-image generation, molecular design 전반에서 TFFT의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64882","en":"DMCO: Budget-Aware Co-Optimization of Data Cleaning and AutoML","ko":"DMCO: 데이터 정제와 AutoML의 Budget-Aware Co-Optimization","authors":"Xiaoou Ding, Siying Chen, Zekai Qian, Hongbin Hu, Chen Wang, Hongzhi Wang, Jianmin Wang","pos":"#4403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IrmkikxOmH","abs":"<p>Data cleaning and automated machine learning (AutoML) are both crucial for reliable learning systems, yet are commonly treated as independent or sequential stages. This separation ignores their strong interaction and leads to inefficient use of limited computational budgets.   We propose DMCO, a unified framework that jointly optimizes data cleaning and model construction under a fixed resource budget. DMCO reformulates the traditional two-stage pipeline into a time-sliced process, where data cleaning and AutoML are interleaved and adaptively scheduled. We introduce a gradient-based data cleaning sampling strategy with theoretical guarantees for minimizing gradient estimation variance, and integrates it with loss-driven sampling and progressive AutoML fitting to continuously leverage intermediate data quality improvements.   Experiments on six real-world datasets show that DMCO consistently outperforms standalone data cleaning and AutoML baselines on both classification and regression tasks, as measured by F1 score and MSE. Under limited budgets, DMCO achieves up to 82.19\\% of the performance of full data cleaning with exhaustive AutoML, while remaining robust across different AutoML frameworks.</p>","absKo":"<p>데이터 정제와 automated machine learning(AutoML)은 신뢰할 수 있는 learning system에 모두 중요하지만, 흔히 서로 독립적이거나 순차적인 단계로 다뤄진다. 이러한 분리는 두 구성 요소의 강한 상호작용을 무시하게 만들고, 제한된 계산 예산을 비효율적으로 사용하게 한다. 우리는 고정된 자원 예산 하에서 data cleaning과 model construction을 공동 최적화하는 통합 프레임워크 DMCO를 제안한다. DMCO는 전통적인 2단계 파이프라인을 time-sliced process로 재구성하여, data cleaning과 AutoML을 교차 배치하고 적응적으로 스케줄링한다. 우리는 gradient estimation variance를 최소화하기 위한 이론적 보장을 갖는 gradient-based data cleaning sampling strategy를 도입하고, 이를 loss-driven sampling 및 progressive AutoML fitting과 통합하여 중간 데이터 품질 향상을 지속적으로 활용한다. 여섯 개의 실제 데이터셋에서 수행한 실험은 DMCO가 classification과 regression 과제 모두에서 F1 score와 MSE 기준으로 standalone data cleaning 및 AutoML baseline보다 일관되게 우수함을 보여준다. 제한된 예산 하에서 DMCO는 exhaustive AutoML과 함께한 완전한 data cleaning 성능의 최대 82.19\\%를 달성하면서도, 다양한 AutoML framework 전반에서 견고함을 유지한다.</p>"},{"id":"65343","en":"Evaluating Sample Utility for Efficient Data Selection by Mimicking Model Weights","ko":"모델 가중치 모방을 통한 효율적 데이터 선택을 위한 샘플 유용성 평가","authors":"Tzu-Heng Huang, Manjot Bilkhu, John Cooper, Frederic Sala, Javier Movellan","pos":"#4404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EX97eHYHIT","abs":"<p>Large-scale web-crawled datasets contain noise, bias, and irrelevant information, necessitating data selection techniques. Existing methods depend on hand-crafted heuristics, downstream datasets, or require expensive influence-based computations---all of which limit scalability and introduce unwanted data dependencies. To address this, we introduce the Mimic Score, a simple and geometry-based data-quality metric that evaluates utility by measuring alignment between a sample’s gradients and a target direction induced by a pre-trained reference model. This leverages readily available model weights, avoids needing validation datasets, and incurs minimal computational overheads. Building on this metric, we propose Grad-Mimic, a two-stage framework that re-weights samples online to accelerate training and aggregates sample utilities offline to construct effective data filters. Empirically, we show that using mimic scores to guide training improves data efficiency, accelerates convergence, yields consistent performance gains across six image datasets, and enhances CLIP models with 20.7% fewer training steps. Additionally, mimic score-based filters augment existing filtering techniques, enabling improved CLIP models trained with 4.7 million fewer samples.</p>"},{"id":"65157","en":"Unifying and Optimizing Data Values for Selection via Sequential Decision-Making","ko":"순차적 의사결정을 통한 선택용 데이터 가치의 통합 및 최적화","authors":"Frank Hongliang Chi, Qiong Wu, Zhengyi Zhou, Jonathan Li, Emily Dodwell, Yao Ma","pos":"#4406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GFFMLwn053","abs":"<p>Data selection has emerged as a crucial downstream application of data valuation, yet the theoretical foundations for using data values in selection remain underexplored. We reformulate data selection as a sequential decision-making problem where the optimal selection sequence arises from dynamic programming, and data values can be understood as encodings of this optimal sequence. This framework unifies and reinterprets existing methods like Data Shapley through the lens of approximate dynamic programming, revealing them as myopic linear approximations to the sequential problem. We further analyze how selection optimality degrades with utility curvature under submodularity, explaining when and why these approximations fail. To bridge theory and practice, we propose an efficient bipartite graph-based surrogate that preserves submodular structure while enabling scalable greedy selection with provable guarantees. Experiments on classical ML benchmarks and large-scale LLM fine-tuning data selection demonstrate substantial improvements over existing methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>Data selection은 data valuation의 중요한 downstream application으로 부상했지만, selection에서 data value를 사용하는 이론적 기반은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 우리는 data selection을 sequential decision-making problem으로 재정식화하며, 최적 selection sequence가 dynamic programming으로부터 도출되고 data value는 이 최적 sequence를 인코딩하는 것으로 이해될 수 있음을 보인다. 이 프레임워크는 Data Shapley와 같은 기존 방법들을 approximate dynamic programming의 관점에서 통합하고 재해석하여, 이들이 sequential problem에 대한 myopic linear approximation임을 드러낸다. 우리는 또한 submodularity 하에서 selection optimality가 utility curvature와 함께 어떻게 저하되는지 분석하여, 이러한 approximation이 언제 그리고 왜 실패하는지를 설명한다. 이론과 실무를 연결하기 위해, 우리는 submodular structure를 보존하면서도 증명 가능한 보장을 갖는 scalable greedy selection을 가능하게 하는 효율적인 bipartite graph 기반 surrogate를 제안한다. Classical ML benchmark와 대규모 LLM fine-tuning data selection 실험은 기존 방법 대비 상당한 개선을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66749","en":"Efficiently Solving Discounted MDPs via Predictions with Unknown Prediction Errors","ko":"알 수 없는 예측 오차를 갖는 예측을 통한 Discounted MDP의 효율적 해결","authors":"Lixing Lyu, Jiashuo Jiang, Wang Chi Cheung","pos":"#4501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0nrxgFZEEq","abs":"We study infinite-horizon discounted Markov decision processes (DMDPs) under a generative model. Motivated by the Algorithms with Advice framework (Mitzenmacher and Vassilvitskii, 2022), we propose a novel framework to investigate how black-box predictions of the transition matrix can enhance sample efficiency in solving DMDPs and improve sample complexity bounds. We focus on DMDPs with $N$ state–action pairs and discount factor $\\gamma$. We first provide an impossibility result showing that, in the presence of predictions with unknown accuracy, no sampling policy can compute an $\\epsilon$-optimal policy with a sample complexity better than $\\tilde{O}((1-\\gamma)^{-3} N \\epsilon^{-2})$, which matches the state-of-the-art minimax sample complexity bound without prediction. In complement, we design an algorithm based on minimax optimization techniques that leverages predictions of the transition matrix without requiring knowledge of the prediction error. Our algorithm achieves a sample complexity bound that depends on the prediction error and is uniformly better than $\\tilde{O}((1-\\gamma)^{-4} N \\epsilon^{-2})$, the previous best result derived from convex optimization methods. In some cases, our bound even improves upon the state-of-the-art $\\tilde{O}((1-\\gamma)^{-3} N \\epsilon^{-2})$, despite not having access to the prediction quality."},{"id":"64282","en":"Optimal Pricing for Data-Augmented AutoML Marketplaces","ko":"데이터 증강 AutoML 마켓플레이스를 위한 최적 가격 책정","authors":"Steven Xia, Minbiao Han, Jonathan Li, Raul Castro Fernandez, Haifeng Xu, sainyam galhotra","pos":"#800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P9dPMDIKRL","abs":"<p>Data markets promise to unlock data value by matching data suppliers with ML consumers. However, market design involves addressing intricate challenges, including data pricing, fairness, and robustness. We propose a pragmatic data-augmented AutoML market that seamlessly integrates with existing cloud-based AutoML platforms, such as Google’s Vertex AI. Unlike standard AutoML solutions, our design automatically augments buyer-submitted training data with valuable external datasets, pricing the resulting models based on their measurable performance improvements rather than computational costs as the status quo. Our key innovation is a pricing mechanism grounded in the instrumental value—the marginal model quality improvement—of externally sourced data. This approach bypasses direct dataset pricing complexities and accommodates diverse buyer valuations through menu-based options, thus providing an economically sustainable framework for monetizing external data.</p>","absKo":"<p>Data market는 data supplier와 ML consumer를 매칭함으로써 data value를 끌어내는 것을 약속한다. 그러나 market design에는 data pricing, fairness, robustness를 포함한 복잡한 과제를 해결해야 한다. 우리는 Google의 Vertex AI와 같은 기존 cloud-based AutoML platform에 매끄럽게 통합되는 실용적인 data-augmented AutoML market을 제안한다. 표준 AutoML solution과 달리, 우리의 설계는 buyer가 제출한 training data를 가치 있는 external dataset으로 자동 증강하고, 그 결과 얻어진 model을 기존처럼 compute cost가 아니라 측정 가능한 performance improvement에 기반해 가격 책정한다. 우리의 핵심 혁신은 외부에서 조달한 data의 instrumental value, 즉 marginal model quality improvement에 기반한 pricing mechanism이다. 이 접근은 dataset을 직접 가격 매기기 위한 복잡성을 우회하고, menu-based option을 통해 다양한 buyer valuation을 수용함으로써, external data를 수익화하기 위한 경제적으로 지속 가능한 framework를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60546","en":"Cross-Modal Knowledge Distillation without Paired Data: Theoretical Foundations and Algorithms","ko":"쌍 데이터 없는 교차 모달 지식 증류: 이론적 기초와 알고리즘","authors":"Trong Khiem Tran, Duc Chu Anh, Quang Hung Pham, Phi Le Nguyen, Nghia Hoang","pos":"#2714","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=z9aetU7Wfl","abs":"<p>Cross-modal knowledge distillation (CMKD) aims to transfer knowledge from a teacher model in one modality to a student model in another modality. Existing CMKD methods have demonstrated strong empirical performance when paired multimodal data with aligned semantics are available, but such paired data are often costly or infeasible to obtain. This paper studies CMKD in the more challenging and practically relevant setting of unpaired data. We establish a distributional relationship between teacher and student models under cross-modal distillation and characterize two fundamental quantities that underlie effective knowledge transfer: feature and label alignments. These quantities capture semantic discrepancy between modalities at the level of representation distributions and prediction distributions, respectively. Guided by this theoretical insight, we propose a principled framework, with theoretical guarantees, that enables effective cross-modal knowledge distillation by aligning distributions rather than individual samples, thereby eliminating the need for data-level pairing. Extensive experiments across a wide range of multimodal benchmarks show that our framework is highly effective in both unpaired and paired data settings, improving significantly over prior work.</p>","absKo":"<p>Cross-modal knowledge distillation (CMKD)은 한 modality의 teacher model에서 다른 modality의 student model로 지식을 전달하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존 CMKD 방법은 정렬된 semantics를 가진 paired multimodal data를 사용할 수 있을 때 강력한 실증적 성능을 보여주었지만, 이러한 paired data는 종종 비용이 많이 들거나 확보가 불가능하다. 이 논문은 더 어려우면서도 실제적으로 중요한 unpaired data 설정에서 CMKD를 연구한다. 우리는 cross-modal distillation 하에서 teacher와 student model 사이의 distributional relationship을 확립하고, 효과적인 knowledge transfer의 기반이 되는 두 가지 기본량, 즉 feature alignment와 label alignment를 규명한다. 이 두 양은 각각 representation distribution 수준과 prediction distribution 수준에서 modality 간 semantic discrepancy를 포착한다. 이러한 이론적 통찰에 따라, 우리는 sample 개별 정렬이 아니라 distribution 정렬을 통해 효과적인 cross-modal knowledge distillation을 가능하게 하는, 이론적 보장을 갖춘 원칙적 framework를 제안한다. 이를 통해 data-level pairing이 필요하지 않다. 다양한 multimodal benchmark 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 우리의 framework가 unpaired 및 paired data 설정 모두에서 매우 효과적이며, 선행 연구를 크게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62885","en":"BESplit: Bias-Compensated Split Federated Learning with Evidential Aggregation","ko":"BESplit: Evidential Aggregation 기반 편향 보정 Split Federated Learning","authors":"Yuhan Xie, Chen Lyu, Jingrong Huang","pos":"#311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cFEyszuOPF","abs":"<p>Split Federated Learning (SFL) enables privacy-preserving collaborative training by partitioning models between clients and a server. However, under non-IID data distributions, SFL often suffers from biased optimization and unstable convergence, while existing solutions largely adapt techniques from conventional federated learning. In this work, we observe that the split architecture of SFL inherently alters how client information is represented and coordinated, opening opportunities for bias compensation beyond parameter-level aggregation. Based on this insight, we propose BESplit, an architecture-aware framework that exploits the intrinsic structure of SFL to mitigate non-IID effects.  First, to prevent biased local data from dominating global updates, we introduce Evidential Aggregation (EA) to perform fine-grained reweighting of client contributions based on evidential uncertainty. Second, to further reduce distributional skew, we develop Bias-Compensated Collaboration (BCC) to align split-layer representations by pairing complementary clients. Finally, Dual-Teacher Distillation (DTD) is incorporated to synchronize knowledge between decoupled client and server models, enabling independent local inference. Extensive experiments on five benchmark datasets demonstrate that BESplit consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods in accuracy, convergence stability, and computational efficiency under diverse non-IID settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>Split Federated Learning (SFL)은 model을 client와 server 사이에 분할함으로써 privacy-preserving collaborative training을 가능하게 한다. 그러나 non-IID data distribution 하에서는 SFL이 종종 biased optimization과 불안정한 convergence를 겪으며, 기존 해결책은 대체로 conventional federated learning의 기법을 그대로 적용한다. 본 연구에서는 SFL의 split architecture가 client information이 표현되고 조정되는 방식을 본질적으로 바꾼다는 점을 관찰했으며, 이를 통해 parameter-level aggregation을 넘어서는 bias compensation의 기회를 열 수 있음을 보였다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로 우리는 non-IID 효과를 완화하기 위해 SFL의 고유 구조를 활용하는 architecture-aware framework인 BESplit을 제안한다. 먼저, biased local data가 global update를 지배하는 것을 막기 위해 evidential uncertainty를 기반으로 client contribution을 세밀하게 재가중하는 Evidential Aggregation (EA)을 도입한다. 다음으로, distributional skew를 더 줄이기 위해 상호 보완적인 client를 짝지어 split-layer representation을 정렬하는 Bias-Compensated Collaboration (BCC)을 개발한다. 마지막으로, 분리된 client와 server model 간의 지식을 동기화하여 독립적인 local inference를 가능하게 하는 Dual-Teacher Distillation (DTD)을 통합한다. 다섯 개 benchmark dataset에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 BESplit이 다양한 non-IID 설정에서 accuracy, convergence stability, computational efficiency 모두에서 state-of-the-art method를 일관되게 능가함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"62989","en":"How much can language models memorize?","ko":"언어 모델은 얼마나 많이 암기할 수 있을까","authors":"John Morris, Chawin Sitawarin, Narine Kokhlikyan, Chuan Guo, Edward Suh, Alexander Rush, Kamalika Chaudhuri, Saeed Mahloujifar","pos":"#312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bA6BgSbaUi","abs":"<p>We propose a new method for estimating how much a model knows about a datapoint and use it to measure the capacity of modern language models. Prior studies of language model memorization have struggled to disentangle memorization from generalization. We formally separate memorization into two components: unintended memorization, the information a model contains about a specific dataset, and generalization, the information a model contains about the true data-generation process. When we completely eliminate generalization, we can compute the total memorization, which provides an estimate of model capacity: our measurements estimate that GPT-style models have a capacity of approximately 3.6 bits per parameter. We train language models on datasets of increasing size and observe that models memorize until their capacity fills, at which point unintended memorization decreases as models begin to generalize. We train hundreds of transformer language models ranging from 500K to 1.5B parameters and produce a series of scaling laws relating model capacity and data size to membership inference.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 모델이 데이터 포인트에 대해 얼마나 알고 있는지를 추정하는 새로운 방법을 제안하고, 이를 사용해 현대 language model의 capacity를 측정한다. language model memorization에 대한 기존 연구는 memorization과 generalization을 분리하는 데 어려움을 겪어 왔다. 우리는 memorization을 두 구성요소로 형식적으로 구분한다. 특정 dataset에 대해 모델이 포함하는 정보인 unintended memorization과, 진정한 data-generation process에 대해 모델이 포함하는 정보인 generalization이다. generalization을 완전히 제거하면 total memorization을 계산할 수 있고, 이는 model capacity의 추정치를 제공한다. 우리의 측정에 따르면 GPT-style model은 parameter당 약 3.6 bits의 capacity를 갖는 것으로 추정된다. 우리는 점점 더 큰 dataset에서 language model을 학습시키고, 모델이 capacity를 채울 때까지 memorization을 수행하며, 그 시점 이후에는 model이 generalize하기 시작하면서 unintended memorization이 감소함을 관찰한다. 우리는 50만 개에서 15억 개 parameter에 이르는 수백 개의 transformer language model을 학습하고, model capacity와 data size를 membership inference에 연결하는 일련의 scaling law를 도출한다.</p>"},{"id":"61709","en":"TT-Sparse: Learning Sparse Rule Models with Differentiable Truth Tables","ko":"TT-Sparse: 미분 가능한 Truth Table로 학습하는 희소 규칙 모델","authors":"Hans Farrell Soegeng, Sarthak Modi, Thomas Peyrin","pos":"#3303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=naOfcXps5e","abs":"<p>Interpretable machine learning is essential in high-stakes domains where decision-making requires accountability, transparency, and trust. While rule-based models offer global and exact interpretability, learning rule sets that achieve high performance while maintaining low complexity to be human understandable and generalizability across tasks remains a difficult challenge. To address this, we introduce TT-Sparse, a flexible neural building block that leverages differentiable truth tables as nodes to learn sparse, effective connections. A key contribution of our approach is a novel soft TopK operator that allows straight-through estimation, ensuring differentiability to backpropagate gradients through the sparse connections and identify meaningful connections. This design allows each node to be exactly transformed into DNF/CNF equations via the Quine-McCluskey algorithm, effectively reducing the entire model to interpretable Boolean formulas. Extensive empirical results across 28 datasets spanning binary, multiclass, and regression tasks show the sparse rules exhibit superior predictive performance with lower complexity compared to existing state-of-the-art methods.</p>","absKo":"해석 가능한 machine learning은 의사결정에 책임성, 투명성, 신뢰가 요구되는 high-stakes domain에서 필수적이다. rule-based model은 전역적이고 정확한 interpretability를 제공하지만, 높은 성능을 유지하면서도 사람이 이해할 수 있을 만큼 낮은 복잡도를 갖는 rule set을 학습하고, task 전반에서 generalizability를 확보하는 것은 여전히 어려운 과제이다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 미분 가능한 truth table을 node로 활용해 sparse하고 효과적인 연결을 학습하는 유연한 neural building block인 TT-Sparse를 소개한다. 우리의 접근법의 핵심 기여는 straight-through estimation을 가능하게 하는 새로운 soft TopK operator로, sparse connection을 통해 gradient를 역전파할 수 있도록 differentiability를 보장하고 의미 있는 연결을 식별하게 한다. 이러한 설계는 각 node를 Quine-McCluskey algorithm을 통해 DNF/CNF equation으로 정확히 변환할 수 있게 하며, 전체 model을 해석 가능한 Boolean formula로 효과적으로 축약한다. binary, multiclass, regression task를 아우르는 28개 dataset에 대한 광범위한 실증 결과는 sparse rule이 기존 최신 방법들에 비해 더 낮은 복잡도로 우수한 예측 성능을 보임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66732","en":"Explicitly Modeling Censoring Produces Superior Survival Predictors","ko":"Censoring의 명시적 모델링이 우수한 생존 예측기를 만든다","authors":"Shi-ang Qi, Yakun Yu, Russell Greiner","pos":"#3501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0xJt4PqPJv","abs":"<p>Likelihood-based training is the dominant paradigm in survival prediction. Under independent censoring, we can factorize the likelihood and optimize only the terms related to event modeling, effectively treating the censoring mechanism as incidental. This is justified when censoring is <em>non-informative</em>, i.e., when the censoring process shares no parameters with the event-time model. However, this may not hold in practice, and ignoring censoring contributions may discard useful signals for learning representations that can help to effectively estimate event distributions. Motivated by this, we argue that explicitly modeling censoring can improve representation learning and time-to-event estimation, particularly when event and censoring processes are coupled. We introduce a latent decomposition view that partitions covariates into four disjoint factors: those affecting only the event process, only the censoring process, both, or neither. We then learn decomposed representations for the first three categories to guide a better estimation of the event distribution. We instantiate our method on four popular deep-learning survival models and evaluate on 10 datasets (2 semi-synthetic and 8 real-world), showing consistent gains over strong baselines and multiple SOTA methods.</p>"},{"id":"62724","en":"Courtroom Analogy: New Perspective on Uncertainty-Aware Classification","ko":"법정 유추: 불확실성 인지 분류에 대한 새로운 시각","authors":"Taeseong Yoon, Heeyoung Kim","pos":"#3502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dv1mWhkbct","abs":"<p>Single-pass uncertainty quantification (UQ) methods for classification represent uncertainty by predicting a tractable distribution over the class probability vector. While existing approaches primarily focus on enhancing the expressiveness of this distribution, they often provide limited insight into how predictive uncertainty is structured and aggregated, resulting in weak interpretability. We introduce the <em>courtroom analogy</em>, which conceptualizes uncertainty-aware classification as a structured debate among class-specific advocates. Each advocate forms a probabilistic opinion, and a final verdict is reached by aggregating these opinions using input-dependent plausibility weights. In this framework, each advocate's opinion is modeled as a Dirichlet distribution whose concentration parameter is decomposed into shared evidence and class-specific advocacy. This yields a structured mixture of Dirichlet distributions with semantically interpretable parameters. To instantiate this formulation, we propose <em>Mixture of Dirichlet EXperts</em> (MoDEX), a single-pass neural architecture that predicts the courtroom parameters, enabling efficient and expressive UQ while explicitly modeling uncertainty aggregation. We demonstrate that MoDEX enjoys strong theoretical properties and achieves state-of-the-art UQ performance across diverse benchmarks, yielding interpretable uncertainty estimates with meaningful semantics.</p>","absKo":"<p>classification을 위한 single-pass uncertainty quantification (UQ) 방법은 class probability vector에 대한 tractable distribution을 예측함으로써 uncertainty를 표현한다. 기존 접근법은 주로 이 distribution의 expressiveness를 향상시키는 데 초점을 맞추지만, predictive uncertainty가 어떻게 구조화되고 집계되는지에 대한 통찰은 제한적이어서 interpretability가 약하다. 우리는 uncertainty-aware classification을 class-specific advocate들 사이의 구조화된 토론으로 개념화하는 <em>courtroom analogy</em>를 도입한다. 각 advocate는 probabilistic opinion을 형성하고, 최종 verdict는 input-dependent plausibility weight를 사용해 이 의견들을 집계함으로써 도출된다. 이 framework에서 각 advocate의 opinion은 concentration parameter가 shared evidence와 class-specific advocacy로 분해되는 Dirichlet distribution으로 모델링된다. 이는 의미론적으로 해석 가능한 parameter를 가진 structured mixture of Dirichlet distribution을 만든다. 이 formulation을 구현하기 위해, 우리는 courtroom parameter를 예측하는 single-pass neural architecture인 <em>Mixture of Dirichlet EXperts</em> (MoDEX)를 제안하며, 이를 통해 uncertainty aggregation을 명시적으로 모델링하면서 효율적이고 표현력 있는 UQ를 가능하게 한다. 우리는 MoDEX가 강한 이론적 성질을 갖고 다양한 benchmark에서 state-of-the-art UQ 성능을 달성하며, 의미 있는 semantics를 지닌 해석 가능한 uncertainty estimate를 제공함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63488","en":"Particle Flow for Learning from Label Proportions","ko":"레이블 비율로부터의 학습을 위한 입자 Flow","authors":"alain rakotomamonjy, Maxime Vono, Ralaivola Liva","pos":"#3711","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WkPYWGHQR2","abs":"<p>This work proposes a novel method for solving learning from label proportion problems.  For this purpose, we learn a classifier that minimizes three key objectives: (i) a  bag-level loss, which quantifies the discrepancy between true and predicted label proportions  in bags, (ii) an instance-level loss, inspired from domain adaptation, which leverages anchor samples with known labels and trainable supports and (iii) a distribution discrepancy that aims at aligning anchor's learned support with those of the bag samples.  The problem is formulated as an alternating optimization process, iteratively  updating the classifier and aligning distributions  via a particle flow method.  The flow of anchor samples is governed by a vector field  designed to minimize the anchor loss while ensuring alignment between anchor and bag distributions. We provide a theoretical analysis, guaranteeing the convergence of the flow and identifying conditions under which the method achieves effective alignment.  Our analysis highlights that gap and diversity in label proportions  within bags is a critical factor for learnability.  Empirical results on tabular and image datasets demonstrate the method's effectiveness, outperforming state-of-the-art approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>본 연구는 label proportion으로부터 학습하는 문제를 해결하기 위한 새로운 방법을 제안한다. 이를 위해 우리는 세 가지 핵심 objective를 최소화하는 classifier를 학습한다: (i) bag 내에서 true label proportion과 predicted label proportion의 차이를 정량화하는 bag-level loss, (ii) domain adaptation에서 착안한 instance-level loss로, 알려진 label을 가진 anchor sample과 trainable support를 활용하는 손실, (iii) anchor의 learned support를 bag sample의 support와 정렬하는 것을 목표로 하는 distribution discrepancy이다. 이 문제는 alternating optimization process로 정식화되며, particle flow method를 통해 classifier를 반복적으로 업데이트하고 distribution을 정렬한다. anchor sample의 flow는 anchor loss를 최소화하는 동시에 anchor와 bag distribution 사이의 정렬을 보장하도록 설계된 vector field에 의해 지배된다. 우리는 이 flow의 수렴을 보장하고, 해당 방법이 효과적인 정렬을 달성하는 조건을 식별하는 이론적 분석을 제공한다. 우리의 분석은 bag 내 label proportion의 gap과 diversity가 learnability의 핵심 요인임을 보여준다. tabular 및 image dataset에서의 실험 결과는 이 방법의 효과를 입증하며, state-of-the-art 접근법을 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"64658","en":"Distribution Alignment for One-Shot Federated Learning via Optimal Transport","ko":"Optimal Transport를 통한 One-Shot Federated Learning을 위한 분포 정렬","authors":"Daniele Berardini, Vito Paolo Pastore, Vittorio Murino","pos":"#3802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LChZtIOER6","abs":"<p>One-Shot Federated Learning (OSFL) addresses extreme communication regimes in which clients interact with the server only once, amplifying the impact of heterogeneous client data distributions. In particular, the interaction of domain shift and label shift across clients induces misaligned feature representations that cannot be corrected through iterative optimization. Existing OSFL methods rely on distillation, server-side generation or ensemble-based aggregation, but assume aligned representations or address domain and label shift separately. We introduce \\textsc{SLOT-Align} (Single-round, Learning-free Optimal Transport Alignment), a geometry-aware feature harmonization framework for OSFL. SLOT-Align uses a shared frozen encoder to extract compact feature statistics, constructs a global reference via Bures–Wasserstein barycenters, and aligns local representations using closed-form geodesic optimal transport maps. The method is computationally efficient and can be combined with existing OSFL pipelines relying on frozen encoders without modifying their training procedures. Extensive experiments across multiple benchmarks, pretrained backbones, and OSFL methods show that SLOT-Align consistently improves accuracy and robustness under joint domain and label shift.</p>","absKo":"<p>One-Shot Federated Learning (OSFL)은 client가 server와 단 한 번만 상호작용하는 극단적인 communication regime을 다루며, heterogenous한 client data distribution의 영향을 증폭시킨다. 특히 client들 사이의 domain shift와 label shift의 상호작용은 iterative optimization으로는 교정할 수 없는 misaligned feature representation을 유도한다. 기존 OSFL 방법들은 distillation, server-side generation 또는 ensemble-based aggregation에 의존하지만, aligned representation을 가정하거나 domain shift와 label shift를 각각 분리해서 다룬다. 우리는 OSFL을 위한 geometry-aware feature harmonization framework인 \\textsc{SLOT-Align} (Single-round, Learning-free Optimal Transport Alignment)을 제안한다. SLOT-Align은 shared frozen encoder를 사용해 compact feature statistics를 추출하고, Bures–Wasserstein barycenters를 통해 global reference를 구성하며, closed-form geodesic optimal transport maps를 사용해 local representation을 정렬한다. 이 방법은 계산적으로 효율적이며, training procedure를 수정하지 않고도 frozen encoder에 의존하는 기존 OSFL pipelines와 결합할 수 있다. 여러 benchmark, pretrained backbone, OSFL method에 대한 광범위한 실험에서 SLOT-Align은 joint domain 및 label shift 하에서 accuracy와 robustness를 일관되게 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"62255","en":"Robust Signal Enhancement via Fractional Detail Views and Knowledge Guided Multi-view Fusion","ko":"Fractional Detail Views와 Knowledge Guided Multi-view Fusion을 통한 강건한 신호 강화","authors":"Zikun Jin, Yuhua Qian, Xinyan Liang, Jiaqian Zhang, Haijun Geng","pos":"#3902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iIWMjdBZ20","abs":"<p>Robust signal enhancement at extremely low SNR is fundamentally challenging because noise becomes strongly entangled with the signal and corrupts local time–frequency (TF) evidence. In this regime, fixed resolution short-time Fourier transform (STFT) enhancement with purely data driven convolutional biases can become overconfident in unreliable TF regions, causing unstable suppression or residual artifacts. We propose FracKGMF, which couples Fractional Distance Decay Convolution (FracConv) with Knowledge Guided Multi-view Fusion (KGMF) for expressive TF modeling and reliability aware decisions under heavy corruption. FracConv introduces a lightweight fractional distance decay family that reshapes local interactions into long tailed receptive patterns, enabling aggregation of weak but globally consistent cues when per-bin observations are ambiguous. KGMF further injects a Wiener inspired reliability view derived from noise statistics to calibrate multi-view fusion, avoiding over-suppression in uncertain regions while exploiting confident structure for effective denoising. Across speech and electromagnetic (EM) benchmarks, FracKGMF improves perceptual quality and intelligibility over state-of-the-art baselines, with especially robust gains at extremely low SNR; on EM dataset at -20 dB, it achieves an average improvement of 33 dB where conventional TF methods performed poorly. The code will be released upon acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>극도로 낮은 SNR에서의 robust signal enhancement는 noise가 signal과 강하게 얽혀 local time–frequency (TF) evidence를 오염시키기 때문에 본질적으로 어렵다. 이 regime에서 고정 해상도 short-time Fourier transform (STFT) enhancement와 순수한 data-driven convolution bias는 신뢰할 수 없는 TF 영역에서 과도한 확신을 보이며, 불안정한 suppression이나 잔여 artifact를 유발할 수 있다. 우리는 FracConv와 Knowledge Guided Multi-view Fusion (KGMF)를 결합해, 강한 오염 하에서도 표현력 있는 TF modeling과 reliability-aware decision을 가능하게 하는 FracKGMF를 제안한다. FracConv는 경량 fractional distance decay family를 도입해 local interaction을 long-tailed receptive pattern으로 재구성하며, bin별 관측이 모호할 때도 약하지만 전역적으로 일관된 단서를 집계할 수 있게 한다. KGMF는 noise statistics로부터 도출된 Wiener-inspired reliability view를 추가로 주입해 multi-view fusion을 보정하며, 불확실한 영역에서의 과도한 suppression을 피하는 동시에 confident structure를 활용해 효과적인 denoising을 수행한다. speech 및 electromagnetic (EM) benchmark 전반에서 FracKGMF는 state-of-the-art baseline보다 perceptual quality와 intelligibility를 향상시켰으며, 특히 극도로 낮은 SNR에서 견고한 향상을 보였다. -20 dB의 EM dataset에서는 전통적인 TF 방법이 부진했던 상황에서 평균 33 dB의 향상을 달성했다. 코드는 채택 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64168","en":"Learning Generalized Label Distributions","ko":"일반화된 레이블 분포 학습","authors":"Haitao Wu, Weiwei Li, Kun Yue, Xiuyi Jia","pos":"#3903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QIwQdRmZAr","abs":"<p>Label ambiguity/polysemy is pervasive in supervised learning, motivating a variety of representations beyond the traditional single-label setting. While label distribution (LD) provides a probabilistic description and has attracted increasing attention, we reveal its inherent limitations, including inconsistency with raw data, distortion of inter-sample order, and limited applicability. To address these issues, we introduce generalized label distribution (GLD), a unified representation that can perfectly recover raw data while preserving inter-sample order consistency, transform into existing forms of label representations without information loss, and capture out-of-distribution samples as well as negative label correlations. We further develop GLD learning algorithms and demonstrate their effectiveness through both theoretical analysis and extensive experiments.</p>","absKo":"<p>라벨의 모호성/다의성은 supervised learning 전반에 널리 존재하며, 전통적인 single-label setting을 넘어서는 다양한 표현을 동기부여한다. label distribution (LD)은 확률적 설명을 제공하여 점점 더 많은 주목을 받아 왔지만, 우리는 그것이 raw data와의 불일치, 샘플 간 순서 왜곡, 제한된 적용 가능성을 포함한 본질적 한계를 지님을 밝힌다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 generalized label distribution (GLD)을 도입한다. GLD는 raw data를 완벽하게 복원하면서 샘플 간 순서 일관성을 보존할 수 있고, 정보 손실 없이 기존 형태의 label representation으로 변환될 수 있으며, out-of-distribution sample과 negative label correlation까지 포착하는 통합 표현이다. 우리는 또한 GLD 학습 알고리즘을 개발하고, 이론적 분석과 광범위한 실험을 통해 그 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65258","en":"Hard Labels In! Rethinking the Role of Hard Labels in Mitigating Local Semantic Drift","ko":"Hard Label 투입! 국소 의미 드리프트 완화에서 Hard Label의 역할 재고","authors":"Jiacheng Cui, Bingkui Tong, Xinyue Bi, Xiaohan Zhao, Jiacheng Liu, Zhiqiang Shen","pos":"#3904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FIq3e9ffEZ","abs":"Soft labels from teacher models are a $\\textit{de facto}$ practice for knowledge transfer and large-scale dataset distillation (e.g., SRe$^2$L, RDED, LPLD). However, when we limit the number of crops per image to reduce the substantial cost of storing precomputed soft labels, these methods suffer severely from $\\textit{local semantic drift}$: visually ambiguous crops can cause soft supervision to deviate from the image-level ground-truth semantics, leading to systematic errors and a train–test distribution mismatch. We revisit the overlooked role of hard labels and show that, when properly integrated, they act as a content-agnostic semantic anchor that calibrates such drift. We theoretically analyze the emergence of drift under sparse soft-label supervision and demonstrate that hybridizing hard and soft labels restores alignment between visual content and semantic supervision. Building on this insight, we propose a new training paradigm, $\\textbf{H}$ard Label for $\\textbf{A}$lleviating $\\textbf{L}$ocal Semantic $\\textbf{D}$rift (HALD), which uses hard labels as intermediate corrective signals while preserving the fine-grained benefits of soft labels. Extensive experiments on dataset distillation and large-scale classification benchmarks show consistent generalization improvements. On ImageNet-1K, our method achieves 42.7% accuracy with only 285M soft-label storage (reduces by ${\\bf 100\\times})$, outperforming prior state-of-the-art LPLD by 9.0%.","absKo":"Teacher models의 soft labels는 knowledge transfer와 대규모 dataset distillation(예: SRe$^2$L, RDED, LPLD)에서 $\\textit{de facto}$ practice이다. 그러나 precomputed soft labels를 저장하는 상당한 비용을 줄이기 위해 image당 crop 수를 제한하면, 이러한 방법들은 $\\textit{local semantic drift}$에 심각하게 시달린다. 시각적으로 모호한 crops는 soft supervision이 image-level ground-truth semantics에서 벗어나도록 만들 수 있으며, 이는 체계적 오류와 train–test distribution mismatch로 이어진다. 우리는 간과되어 온 hard labels의 역할을 재검토하고, 이를 적절히 통합하면 이러한 drift를 보정하는 content-agnostic semantic anchor로 작동함을 보인다. 우리는 sparse soft-label supervision 하에서 drift가 발생하는 과정을 이론적으로 분석하고, hard labels와 soft labels를 결합하면 visual content와 semantic supervision 사이의 정렬이 회복됨을 보인다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 hard labels를 중간 corrective signal로 사용하면서 soft labels의 세밀한 이점을 보존하는 새로운 training paradigm인 $\\textbf{H}$ard Label for $\\textbf{A}$lleviating $\\textbf{L}$ocal Semantic $\\textbf{D}$rift (HALD)를 제안한다. dataset distillation과 대규모 classification benchmarks에 대한 광범위한 실험은 일관된 generalization 향상을 보여준다. ImageNet-1K에서 우리의 방법은 단지 285M의 soft-label storage로 42.7% accuracy를 달성하며(${\\bf 100\\times}$ 감소), 이전 state-of-the-art인 LPLD보다 9.0% 우수하다."},{"id":"61466","en":"Divisiveness-Consistent Label Distribution Learning","ko":"분열성 일관 Label Distribution Learning","authors":"Yunan Lu, Haitao Wu, Weiwei Li, Lei Yang, Xiuyi Jia","pos":"#3906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ptU4J06zfX","abs":"<p>Label Distribution Learning (LDL) is an effective learning paradigm for predicting entire conditional label distributions, improving the trustworthiness of predictions in risk-sensitive tasks. Although previous LDL methods achieve satisfactory performance on conventional evaluation metrics, they generally overlook the divisiveness within label distributions, i.e., the propensity of label distribution to exhibit dissension between semantically opposing labels, which is an essential indicator of the practical decision risk. Therefore, we propose a divisiveness‑consistent label distribution learning framework to quantify and preserve the divisiveness information. First, we formalize a divisiveness measure that satisfies the axiomatic property of polarity monotonicity to quantify the divisiveness information. Second, we theoretically demonstrate the inconsistency between conventional loss functions and divisiveness error. Besides, in order to address the adversarial gradient problem arising from directly minimizing the divisiveness error, we propose a pairwise divisiveness loss as an unbiased estimator of the original divisiveness error. Experiments confirm the effectiveness of the proposed method.</p>","absKo":"<p>Label Distribution Learning (LDL)은 전체 conditional label distribution을 예측하는 데 효과적인 학습 패러다임으로, risk-sensitive task에서 예측의 신뢰성을 향상시킨다. 기존 LDL 방법들은 일반적인 평가 지표에서 만족스러운 성능을 달성하지만, label distribution 내부의 divisiveness, 즉 label distribution이 의미적으로 반대되는 label들 사이에서 dissension을 보이는 경향을 대체로 간과한다. 이는 실제 의사결정 위험의 중요한 지표이다. 따라서 우리는 divisiveness 정보를 정량화하고 보존하기 위한 divisiveness-consistent label distribution learning framework를 제안한다. 첫째, 우리는 polarity monotonicity의 공리적 성질을 만족하는 divisiveness measure를 정식화하여 divisiveness 정보를 정량화한다. 둘째, 우리는 conventional loss function과 divisiveness error 사이의 불일치를 이론적으로 보인다. 또한 divisiveness error를 직접 최소화할 때 발생하는 adversarial gradient 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 원래의 divisiveness error에 대한 unbiased estimator로서 pairwise divisiveness loss를 제안한다. 실험은 제안 방법의 효과를 확인해준다.</p>"},{"id":"63787","en":"Towards Rule-Based Knowledge Sharing in Federated Learning","ko":"연합학습에서 규칙 기반 지식 공유를 향하여","authors":"Zixuan Qin, Qi Shen, Liu Yang, Qilong Wang, Qinghua Hu","pos":"#4011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TlhGpzMyMQ","abs":"<p>Federated learning often face both data and model heterogeneity, with the latter often more challenging. Architectural differences yield incompatible representation, making the knowledge-sharing carrier central to heterogeneous collaboration. Using proxy model enables distillation-based collaboration but incurs high communication and computation costs. Prototype-based carriers are lighter yet cause semantic confusion when incompatible features are mixed. Therefore, we propose rule-based federated learning (RFL) that shares interpretable, class-discriminative rules to enable heterogeneous collaboration, avoid feature confusion, and keep communication lightweight. RFL uses a rule network to unify clients’ decision features and collaborates at the rule level, avoiding forcible averaging of incompatible representations. RFL selects sparse, high-coverage, beneficial rules for broadcasting, compressing shared knowledge into an interpretable class-rule set and reducing communication and computation costs. Each client selectively activates only rules relevant to its local classes, mitigating negative transfer while preserving personalization. Across heterogeneous settings, RFL achieves a better accuracy–communication trade-off.</p>","absKo":"<p>Federated learning은 종종 data heterogeneity와 model heterogeneity 모두를 마주하며, 그중 후자가 더 어렵다. architecture의 차이는 호환되지 않는 representation을 만들어 내므로, knowledge-sharing carrier가 heterogeneous collaboration의 핵심이 된다. proxy model을 사용하면 distillation-based collaboration이 가능하지만 통신과 계산 비용이 높다. prototype-based carrier는 더 가볍지만 호환되지 않는 feature가 섞일 때 semantic confusion을 유발한다. 따라서 우리는 해석 가능한 class-discriminative rule을 공유하여 heterogeneous collaboration을 가능하게 하고, feature confusion을 피하며, 통신을 가볍게 유지하는 rule-based federated learning (RFL)을 제안한다. RFL은 rule network를 사용해 client의 decision feature를 통합하고, rule 수준에서 협업하여 호환되지 않는 representation의 강제 평균화를 피한다. RFL은 방송할 sparse하고 coverage가 높으며 유익한 rule을 선택하여, 공유 지식을 해석 가능한 class-rule set으로 압축하고 통신 및 계산 비용을 줄인다. 각 client는 자신의 local class와 관련된 rule만 선택적으로 활성화하여 negative transfer를 완화하면서 personalization은 유지한다. heterogeneous setting 전반에서 RFL은 더 나은 accuracy-communication trade-off를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"63518","en":"Training-Free Distribution Adaptation for Diffusion Models via Maximum Mean Discrepancy Guidance","ko":"최대 평균 차이(MMD) 가이던스를 통한 확산 모델의 훈련 없는 분포 적응","authors":"Matina Mahdizadeh Sani, Nima Jamali, Mohammad Jalali, Farzan Farnia","pos":"#409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WTgOxAio8a","abs":"<p>Pre-trained diffusion models have emerged as powerful generative priors for both unconditional and conditional sample generation, yet their outputs often deviate from the characteristics of user-specific target data. Such mismatches are especially problematic in domain adaptation tasks, where only a few reference examples are available and retraining the diffusion model is infeasible. Existing inference-time guidance methods can adjust sampling trajectories, but they typically optimize surrogate objectives such as classifier likelihoods rather than directly aligning with the target distribution. We propose MMD Guidance, a training-free mechanism that augments the reverse diffusion process with gradients of the Maximum Mean Discrepancy (MMD) between generated samples and a reference dataset. MMD provides reliable distributional estimates from limited data, exhibits low variance in practice, and is efficiently differentiable, which makes it particularly well-suited for the guidance task. Our framework naturally extends to prompt-aware adaptation in conditional generation models via product kernels. Also, it can be applied with computational efficiency in latent diffusion models (LDMs), since guidance is applied in the latent space of the LDM. Experiments on synthetic and real-world benchmarks demonstrate that MMD Guidance can achieve distributional alignment while preserving sample fidelity.</p>","absKo":"<p>사전학습된 diffusion model은 unconditional 및 conditional sample generation 모두에서 강력한 generative prior로 부상했지만, 그 출력은 종종 사용자 특정 target data의 특성과 어긋난다. 이러한 불일치는 few reference example만 उपलब्ध하고 diffusion model을 재학습할 수 없는 domain adaptation task에서 특히 문제가 된다. 기존 inference-time guidance method는 sampling trajectory를 조정할 수는 있지만, 대개 target distribution과 직접 정렬하기보다 classifier likelihood와 같은 surrogate objective를 최적화한다. 우리는 생성된 sample과 reference dataset 사이의 Maximum Mean Discrepancy(MMD) gradient로 reverse diffusion process를 보강하는 training-free mechanism인 MMD Guidance를 제안한다. MMD는 제한된 데이터에서도 신뢰할 수 있는 분포 추정을 제공하고, 실제로 분산이 낮으며, 효율적으로 differentiable하기 때문에 guidance task에 특히 적합하다. 우리의 framework는 product kernel을 통해 conditional generation model에서 prompt-aware adaptation으로 자연스럽게 확장된다. 또한 guidance가 LDM의 latent space에서 적용되므로 latent diffusion model(LDM)에서도 계산 효율적으로 사용할 수 있다. synthetic 및 real-world benchmark 실험은 MMD Guidance가 sample fidelity를 보존하면서 distribution alignment를 달성할 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64340","en":"Recursive Binding on a Budget: Subspace Carving in Order-$p$ Tensor Memories","ko":"예산 내 재귀적 결합: p차 텐서 메모리에서의 부분공간 조각화","authors":"Travis Pence, Daisuke Yamada, Vikas Singh","pos":"#4110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Oc5d0gsRTs","abs":"Tensor Product Representations provide the structural fidelity required for symbolic reasoning in models but suffer from *exponential* dimensionality growth when encoding deep recursive structures. Conversely, Vector Symbolic Architectures maintain *constant* dimensionality but sacrifice capacity and fidelity due to noisy compression via superposition. In this work, we propose **Orthogonal Subspace Carving (OSC)**, a memory architecture that binds *fillers* to *roles* by projecting onto the null space of the role basis before aggregating into a fixed order-$p$ tensor. OSC uses projections to enforce geometric orthogonality between bound structures within a {\\em static} memory trace. We show that this mechanism decouples the tensor order from the structural depth, enabling deep recursive binding within a *constant* memory footprint. This construction allows for component vectors that are *orders of magnitude* smaller than the memory tensor, giving excellent memory efficiency in settings involving high superposition. We also show that TPR is a special case of binding in Clifford algebra, and give a Clifford formulation of OSC.","absKo":"Tensor Product Representations는 모델의 symbolic reasoning에 필요한 구조적 충실도를 제공하지만, 깊은 recursive structure를 인코딩할 때 차원이 *exponential*하게 증가하는 문제를 겪는다. 반대로 Vector Symbolic Architectures는 *constant* 차원을 유지하지만, superposition을 통한 noisy compression 때문에 용량과 충실도를 희생한다. 본 연구에서는 *fillers*를 *roles*에 결합한 뒤, 고정된 order-$p$ tensor로 집계하기 전에 role basis의 null space로 projection하는 메모리 아키텍처인 **Orthogonal Subspace Carving (OSC)**를 제안한다. OSC는 projection을 사용해 {\\em static} memory trace 내에서 결합된 구조들 사이의 기하학적 직교성을 강제한다. 우리는 이 메커니즘이 tensor order와 구조적 depth를 분리하여, *constant* memory footprint 안에서 깊은 recursive binding을 가능하게 함을 보인다. 이러한 구성은 component vector가 memory tensor보다 *orders of magnitude* 작아질 수 있게 하여, 높은 superposition이 수반되는 환경에서 매우 우수한 메모리 효율을 제공한다. 또한 TPR이 Clifford algebra에서의 binding의 특수한 경우임을 보이고, OSC의 Clifford formulation을 제시한다."},{"id":"65774","en":"On Testing Conditional Mean Independence for Manifold-Valued Data","ko":"다양체 값 데이터에 대한 조건부 평균 독립성 검정","authors":"Meiling Zeng, Jinhong You, Jicai Liu, Shouxia Wang","pos":"#4113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AF3GJXoAVe","abs":"This paper introduces a nonparametric test for conditional mean independence between a manifold‑valued $Y$ and Euclidean predictors $X$. The test is built on a new measure called the Manifold Martingale Difference Divergence (MMDD), which characterizes conditional mean dependence by projecting observations onto the tangent space via the logarithmic map. We provide an empirical estimator for the MMDD, establish its asymptotic null distribution, and implement a wild bootstrap procedure for finite‑sample inference. Simulations on three representative manifolds demonstrate that the proposed test maintains correct size under the null even when the distribution of  $Y$ depends on $X$, in contrast to the severe size distortion exhibited by the distance covariance (dCov) test. At the same time, it achieves competitive power across a range of alternatives. An application to real data illustrates its practical utility."},{"id":"64057","en":"SoftJAX & SoftTorch: Empowering Automatic Differentiation Libraries with Informative Gradients","ko":"SoftJAX & SoftTorch: 유익한 그래디언트로 자동 미분 라이브러리 강화하기","authors":"Anselm Paulus, Andreas René Geist, Vit Musil, Sebastian Hoffmann, Georg Martius","pos":"#4206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RKHDV40omz","abs":"<p>Automatic differentiation (AD) frameworks such as JAX and PyTorch have enabled gradient-based optimization for a wide range of scientific fields. Yet, many ''hard'' primitives in these libraries such as thresholding, Boolean logic, discrete indexing, and sorting operations yield zero or undefined gradients that are not useful for optimization. While numerous ''soft'' relaxations have been proposed that provide informative gradients, the respective implementations are fragmented across projects, making them difficult to combine and compare. This work introduces <strong>SoftJAX</strong> and <strong>SoftTorch</strong>, open-source, feature-complete libraries for <em>soft differentiable programming</em>. These libraries provide a variety of soft functions as drop-in replacements for their hard JAX and PyTorch counterparts. This includes (i) elementwise operators such as <em>clip</em> or <em>abs</em>, (ii) utility methods for manipulating Booleans and indices via fuzzy logic, (iii) axiswise operators such as <em>sort</em> or <em>rank</em> -- based on optimal transport or permutahedron projections, and (iv) offer full support for straight-through gradient estimation. Overall, SoftJAX and SoftTorch make the toolbox of soft relaxations easily accessible to differentiable programming, as demonstrated through benchmarking and a practical case study.</p>","absKo":"<p>JAX와 PyTorch 같은 automatic differentiation(AD) framework는 광범위한 과학 분야에서 gradient-based optimization을 가능하게 했다. 그러나 이러한 라이브러리의 thresholding, Boolean logic, discrete indexing, sorting operation과 같은 많은 'hard' primitive는 optimization에 유용하지 않은 zero gradient 또는 undefined gradient를 낳는다. 정보를 제공하는 gradient를 주는 수많은 'soft' relaxation이 제안되었지만, 각 구현이 여러 프로젝트에 분산되어 있어 결합하고 비교하기 어렵다. 본 연구는 <strong>soft differentiable programming</strong>을 위한 오픈소스의 feature-complete library인 <strong>SoftJAX</strong>와 <strong>SoftTorch</strong>를 소개한다. 이 라이브러리는 JAX와 PyTorch의 hard counterpart를 대체하는 drop-in replacement로서 다양한 soft function을 제공한다. 여기에는 (i) <em>clip</em> 또는 <em>abs</em>와 같은 elementwise operator, (ii) fuzzy logic을 통해 Boolean과 index를 조작하는 utility method, (iii) optimal transport 또는 permutahedron projection에 기반한 <em>sort</em> 또는 <em>rank</em>와 같은 axiswise operator, 그리고 (iv) straight-through gradient estimation에 대한 완전한 지원이 포함된다. 전반적으로 SoftJAX와 SoftTorch는 soft relaxation 도구 상자를 differentiable programming에서 쉽게 활용할 수 있게 하며, 이는 benchmarking과 실제 사례 연구를 통해 입증된다.</p>"},{"id":"62784","en":"Asymmetric conformal prediction with penalized kernel sum-of-squares","ko":"패널티화된 kernel sum-of-squares 기반 Asymmetric conformal prediction","authors":"Louis Allain, Sébastien Da Veiga, Brian Staber","pos":"#4211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dNaRpdbnOG","abs":"<p>Conformal prediction (CP) is a distribution-free method to construct reliable prediction intervals that has gained significant attention in recent years. Despite its success and various proposed extensions, a significant practical feature which has been overlooked in previous research is the potential skewed nature of the noise, or of the residuals when the predictive model exhibits bias. In this work, we leverage recent developments in CP to propose a new asymmetric procedure that bridges the gap between skewed and non-skewed noise distributions, while still maintaining adaptivity of the prediction intervals.  We introduce a new statistical learning problem to construct adaptive and asymmetric prediction bands, with a unique feature based on a penalty which promotes symmetry: when the penalty intensity varies, the intervals smoothly change from symmetric to asymmetric ones. This statistical learning problem is based on reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces and the recently introduced kernel sum-of-squares framework. First, we establish representer theorems to make our problem tractable in practice, and derive dual formulations which are essential for scalability to larger datasets. Second, the intensity of the penalty is chosen using a novel data-driven method which automatically identifies the symmetric nature of the noise. We show that consenting to some asymmetry can let the learned prediction bands better adapt to small sample regimes, outliers or biased predictive models. Finally, our experiments illustrate the efficiency of such penalized kernel sum-of-squares to construct adaptive prediction bands.</p>","absKo":"<p>Conformal prediction (CP)는 reliable prediction interval을 구성하는 distribution-free 방법으로, 최근 큰 주목을 받아왔다. 그 성공과 다양한 확장에도 불구하고, 이전 연구에서 간과된 중요한 실용적 특성은 noise의 skewed nature, 또는 predictive model에 bias가 있을 때 residual의 skewed nature이다. 본 연구에서는 CP의 최근 발전을 활용하여, skewed noise distribution과 non-skewed noise distribution 사이의 간극을 메우면서도 prediction interval의 adaptivity를 유지하는 새로운 asymmetric procedure를 제안한다. 우리는 adaptive하고 asymmetric한 prediction band를 구성하기 위한 새로운 statistical learning problem을 도입하며, symmetry를 촉진하는 penalty를 기반으로 하는 독특한 특성을 가진다. penalty intensity가 변함에 따라 interval은 symmetric한 형태에서 asymmetric한 형태로 부드럽게 변한다. 이 statistical learning problem은 reproducing kernel Hilbert space와 최근 도입된 kernel sum-of-squares framework를 기반으로 한다. 먼저, 문제를 실제로 다룰 수 있도록 representer theorem을 확립하고, 더 큰 dataset으로의 확장에 필수적인 dual formulation을 도출한다. 둘째, penalty의 intensity는 noise의 대칭성을 자동으로 식별하는 새로운 data-driven 방법으로 선택된다. 우리는 어느 정도의 asymmetry를 허용하면 학습된 prediction band가 small-sample regime, outlier, 또는 bias된 predictive model에 더 잘 적응할 수 있음을 보인다. 마지막으로, 실험을 통해 이러한 penalized kernel sum-of-squares가 adaptive prediction band를 구성하는 데 효율적임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62769","en":"Do You Want to Know if Two Distributions Are Close to Each Other?Testing the Closeness With Statistical Significance","ko":"두 분포의 근접성을 알고 싶은가요? 통계적 유의성으로 근접성 검정","authors":"Zhijian Zhou, Liuhua Peng, Xunye Tian, Mingming Gong, Feng Liu","pos":"#4212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dWuxvV7ekd","abs":"Are two distributions close to each other with statistical significance? Distribution closeness testing (DCT) formalizes this question by testing whether the distance between a distribution pair is at least $\\epsilon$-far. Existing DCT methods mainly measure discrepancies between a distribution pair defined on discrete spaces (e.g., using total variation), which limits their applications to complex data (e.g., images). To extend DCT to more types of data, a natural idea is to introduce maximum mean discrepancy (MMD), a powerful measurement of the distributional discrepancy between two complex distributions, into DCT scenarios. However, we find that MMD's value can be the same for many pairs of distributions that have different norms in the same reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS), which potentially have different closeness levels, making MMD less informative when assessing the closeness of multiple distribution pairs. To mitigate the issue, we design a new measurement of distributional discrepancy, norm-adaptive MMD (NAMMD), which scales MMD's value using the RKHS norms of distributions. Based on the asymptotic distribution of NAMMD, we finally propose the NAMMD-based DCT to assess the closeness level of a distribution pair. Theoretically, we prove that NAMMD-based DCT has higher test power compared to MMD-based DCT, with bounded type-I error, which is also validated by extensive experiments on many types of data (e.g., synthetic noise, real images).","absKo":"두 분포가 통계적으로 유의미하게 서로 가까운가? Distribution closeness testing (DCT)는 분포 쌍 사이의 거리가 $\\epsilon$-far 이상인지 검정함으로써 이 질문을 formalize한다. 기존 DCT 방법은 주로 discrete space 위에 정의된 분포 쌍의 discrepancy를 측정하며(예: total variation 사용), 이는 image와 같은 복잡한 데이터에의 적용을 제한한다. DCT를 더 다양한 데이터 유형으로 확장하기 위해, 자연스러운 아이디어는 두 복잡한 분포 사이의 distributional discrepancy를 측정하는 강력한 지표인 maximum mean discrepancy (MMD)를 DCT 시나리오에 도입하는 것이다. 그러나 우리는 MMD의 값이 같은 reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS)에서 서로 다른 norm을 갖는 많은 분포 쌍에 대해 동일할 수 있음을 발견했다. 이들 분포 쌍은 closeness 수준이 서로 다를 수 있으므로, 여러 분포 쌍의 closeness를 평가할 때 MMD는 덜 informative할 수 있다. 이 문제를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 RKHS norm을 사용해 MMD의 값을 스케일링하는 새로운 distributional discrepancy 측정인 norm-adaptive MMD (NAMMD)를 설계한다. NAMMD의 asymptotic distribution에 기반하여, 우리는 결국 분포 쌍의 closeness level을 평가하기 위한 NAMMD-based DCT를 제안한다. 이론적으로, 우리는 NAMMD-based DCT가 bounded type-I error를 유지하면서 MMD-based DCT보다 더 높은 test power를 가진다는 것을 증명하며, 이는 synthetic noise와 real images 등 다양한 데이터 유형에 대한 광범위한 실험으로도 검증된다."},{"id":"66666","en":"Refining Dual Spectral Sparsity in Transformed Tensor Singular Values","ko":"변환된 텐서 특이값에서 Dual Spectral Sparsity 정제","authors":"Andong Wang, Yuning Qiu, Haonan Huang, Zhong Jin, Guoxu Zhou, Qibin Zhao","pos":"#4303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1ZIjW3LFcH","abs":"The Tensor Nuclear Norm (TNN), derived from the tensor singular value decomposition, is a widely used low-rank modeling tool that enforces element-wise sparsity on frequency-domain singular values. However, as a direct extension of the matrix nuclear norm, TNN fundamentally assumes single-level spectral sparsity, which is misaligned with the multi-level spectral structures prevalent in real-world data, where low-rankness within frequency components coexists with sparsity across them. To overcome this limitation, we propose the tensor $\\ell_p$-Schatten-$q$ quasi-norm ($p,q\\in(0,1]$), which enables explicit control of dual spectral sparsity by jointly regularizing inter-frequency sparsity and intra-frequency low-rankness. This formulation strictly generalizes TNN and subsumes several existing tensor regularizers by coupling global frequency sparsity with local spectral low-rankness, leading to a fundamentally different modeling principle. We establish the first minimax error bounds under this model and develop an efficient reweighted optimization algorithm for the resulting nonconvex problem. Numerical experiments on noisy and Poisson tensor completion as well as image clustering demonstrate the effectiveness and robustness of our method across reconstruction and representation learning tasks involving complex multi-way data."},{"id":"64840","en":"NeuralFLoC: Neural Flow-Based Joint Registration and Clustering of Functional Data","ko":"NeuralFLoC: 함수 데이터의 Neural Flow 기반 Joint Registration 및 Clustering","authors":"Xinyang Xiong, Siyuan Jiang, PENGCHENG ZENG","pos":"#4305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JIkyyfkeoE","abs":"<p>Clustering functional data in the presence of phase variation is challenging, as temporal misalignment can obscure intrinsic shape differences and degrade clustering performance. Most existing approaches treat registration and clustering as separate tasks or rely on restrictive parametric assumptions. We present NeuralFLoC, a fully unsupervised, end-to-end deep learning framework for joint functional registration and clustering based on Neural ODE-driven diffeomorphic flows and spectral clustering. The proposed model learns smooth, invertible warping functions and cluster-specific templates simultaneously, effectively disentangling phase and amplitude variation. We establish universal approximation guarantees and asymptotic consistency for the proposed framework. Experiments on functional benchmarks show state-of-the-art performance in both registration and clustering, with robustness to missing data, irregular sampling, and noise, while maintaining scalability. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/NeuralFLoC-FEC8.</p>","absKo":"<p>phase variation이 존재하는 상황에서 functional data를 clustering하는 것은 어렵다. 시간적 misalignment가 intrinsic shape 차이를 가리고 clustering 성능을 저하시킬 수 있기 때문이다. 기존의 대부분의 접근법은 registration과 clustering을 별개의 과제로 다루거나, 제약적인 parametric 가정에 의존한다. 우리는 NeuralFLoC를 제안한다. NeuralFLoC는 Neural ODE-driven diffeomorphic flow와 spectral clustering에 기반한, 완전히 unsupervised인 end-to-end deep learning framework로, functional registration과 clustering을 joint하게 수행한다. 제안한 모델은 smooth하고 invertible한 warping function과 cluster-specific template를 동시에 학습하여 phase variation과 amplitude variation을 효과적으로 분리한다. 우리는 제안한 framework에 대해 universal approximation guarantee와 asymptotic consistency를 증명한다. functional benchmark 실험에서 registration과 clustering 모두에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 보였고, missing data, irregular sampling, noise에 대해서도 robust했으며, 동시에 scalability도 유지했다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/NeuralFLoC-FEC8 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"66088","en":"Learn from A Rationalist: Distilling Intermediate Interpretable Rationales","ko":"합리주의자에게 배우기: 중간 해석 가능 근거 증류하기","authors":"Jiayi Dai, Randy Goebel","pos":"#4307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=78g39QVbt6","abs":"<p>Because of the pervasive use of deep neural networks (DNNs), especially in high-stakes domains, the interpretability of DNNs has received increased attention. The general idea of rationale extraction (RE) is to provide an interpretable-by-design framework for DNNs via a select-predict architecture where two neural networks learn jointly to perform feature selection and prediction, respectively. Given only the remote supervision from the final task prediction, the process of learning to select subsets of features (or <em>rationales</em>) requires searching in the space of all possible feature combinations, which is computationally challenging and even harder when the base neural networks are not sufficiently capable. To improve the predictive performance of RE models that are based on less capable or smaller neural networks (i.e., the students), we propose <strong>REKD</strong> (<strong>R</strong>ationale <strong>E</strong>xtraction with <strong>K</strong>nowledge <strong>D</strong>istillation) where a student RE model learns from the rationales and predictions of a teacher (i.e., a <em>rationalist</em>) in addition to the student's own RE optimization. This structural adjustment to RE aligns well with how humans could learn effectively from interpretable and verifiable knowledge. Because of the neural-model agnostic nature of the method, any black-box neural network could be integrated as a backbone model. To demonstrate the viability of REKD, we conduct experiments with multiple variants of BERT and vision transformer (ViT) models. Our experiments across language and vision classification datasets (i.e., IMDB movie reviews, CIFAR 10 and CIFAR 100) show that REKD significantly improves the predictive performance of the student RE models.</p>"},{"id":"64649","en":"HONet: Data-Efficient Learning for Exact Cover Problems via Hypergraph Optimization","ko":"HONet: Hypergraph Optimization을 통한 Exact Cover 문제의 데이터 효율적 학습","authors":"Pengyang Huang, Zirui Zhuang, Haifeng Sun, Qi Qi, Jingyu Wang, Jianxin Liao","pos":"#4308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LGZ3wPmK1E","abs":"Deep learning approaches typically require prohibitive amounts of data to approximate strict Exact Cover Problems, while existing neuro-symbolic methods often face training infeasibility and scalability bottlenecks. To bridge this divide, we propose the Hypergraph Optimization Network (HONet), an end-to-end framework integrating a topologically complete Deep Residual Hypergraph Encoder with a differentiable Equality-Constrained Quadratic Programming layer. By adopting a \"Fixed Polytope\" paradigm guided by the Geometric Consistency Loss, HONet explicitly shapes the objective landscape, forcing the valid discrete solution to align with the unique global energy minimum. Empirical results show that HONet rapidly achieves 100\\% accuracy on $9 \\times 9$ Sudoku using limited samples, exhibiting superior data efficiency over baselines while maintaining exceptional robustness in highly sparse regimes and additional tasks."},{"id":"64527","en":"GR-LoRA: Gradient-Recycling Low-Rank Adaptation for Class-Incremental Learning","ko":"GR-LoRA: 클래스 증분 학습을 위한 그래디언트 재활용 저계수 적응","authors":"Yipeng Lin, Fengqiang Wan, Yang Yang","pos":"#4309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=MhMoUuoA1g","abs":"<p>Pre-trained models with parameter-efficient fine-tuning have shown strong effectiveness in Class-Incremental Learning (CIL), which seeks to balance model plasticity and stability. In this context, orthogonality constraints can significantly enhance model stability, yet their reliance on subspace inevitably compromises model plasticity over long tasks. To address this, we propose Gradient-Recycling Low-Rank Adaptation (GR-LoRA), which reconciles stability and plasticity by recycling the gradients discarded in orthogonal projection. Specifically, GR-LoRA recycles post-decomposition non-orthogonal gradient components into task-specific lightweight modules and selects optimal module via entropy to improve plasticity, while incorporating local and global mismatch suppression to preserve stability by synthesizing out-of-distribution representations across all tasks. Theoretical analysis confirms that this recycling strategy preserves stability and improves plasticity. Experimental results from multiple CIL benchmarks verify the effectiveness and general applicability of GR-LoRA.</p>","absKo":"<p>parameter-efficient fine-tuning을 적용한 pre-trained model은 model plasticity와 stability의 균형을 추구하는 Class-Incremental Learning (CIL)에서 강력한 효과를 보였다. 이 맥락에서 orthogonality constraint는 model stability를 크게 향상시킬 수 있지만, subspace에 대한 의존성 때문에 긴 task에 걸쳐 model plasticity를 필연적으로 저해한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 orthogonal projection에서 버려지는 gradient를 재활용함으로써 stability와 plasticity를 조화시키는 Gradient-Recycling Low-Rank Adaptation(GR-LoRA)을 제안한다. 구체적으로, GR-LoRA는 decomposition 이후의 non-orthogonal gradient component를 task-specific lightweight module로 재활용하고, entropy를 이용해 최적의 module을 선택하여 plasticity를 향상시킨다. 동시에 local 및 global mismatch suppression을 통합하여, 모든 task에 걸친 out-of-distribution representation을 합성함으로써 stability를 보존한다. 이론적 분석은 이러한 recycling 전략이 stability를 보존하면서 plasticity를 향상시킴을 확인한다. 여러 CIL benchmark에서의 실험 결과는 GR-LoRA의 효과와 일반적 적용 가능성을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61798","en":"Counterfactual Residual Data Augmentation for Regression","ko":"회귀를 위한 반사실적 잔차 데이터 증강","authors":"Hossein Mohebbi, Oliver Schulte, Ke Li, Pascal Poupart","pos":"#4402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mqd3zyHQj9","abs":"<p>Data-driven modeling in real-world regression tasks often suffers from limited training samples, high collection costs, and noisy observations. Inspired by the impact of data augmentation in vision and language, we propose a novel Counterfactual Residual Data Augmentation (CRDA) technique for tabular regression. Our key insight is that once a regressor has modeled the systematic component of the data, the remaining noise can be viewed as an invariant residual that remains stable under small perturbations of carefully selected features. We exploit this residual invariance to generate new, yet realistic, training samples, effectively expanding the dataset without requiring additional real data. Our method is model-agnostic and readily applicable to various types of regressors. In experiments across datasets from a variety of benchmark repositories, on average, CRDA reduces an MLP Regressor's MSE by 22.9% and an XGBoost Regressor's MSE by 6.4%. When compared to existing state-of-the-art data generators and augmentation techniques, CRDA consistently outperforms in MSE reduction. By adding principled counterfactual variations to the training data, our method offers a simple and efficient remedy for noise-prone, small-sample regression settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>실세계 회귀 과제의 data-driven modeling은 제한된 학습 샘플, 높은 수집 비용, 그리고 노이즈가 섞인 관측치 때문에 종종 어려움을 겪는다. vision과 language에서 data augmentation이 보인 영향에 착안하여, 우리는 tabular regression을 위한 새로운 Counterfactual Residual Data Augmentation(CRDA) 기법을 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 회귀기가 데이터의 systematic component를 모델링한 뒤에 남는 노이즈는, 신중하게 선택된 feature들에 대한 작은 perturbation 아래에서 안정적으로 유지되는 invariant residual로 볼 수 있다는 점이다. 우리는 이 residual invariance를 활용해 새롭지만 현실적인 학습 샘플을 생성하며, 추가적인 real data 없이도 데이터셋을 효과적으로 확장한다. 우리의 방법은 model-agnostic하며 다양한 종류의 regressor에 손쉽게 적용할 수 있다. 여러 benchmark repository의 데이터셋에 대한 실험에서, 평균적으로 CRDA는 MLP Regressor의 MSE를 22.9% 감소시키고 XGBoost Regressor의 MSE를 6.4% 감소시킨다. 기존의 state-of-the-art 데이터 생성기 및 augmentation 기법과 비교했을 때도, CRDA는 MSE 감소 측면에서 일관되게 더 우수한 성능을 보인다. 학습 데이터에 원칙적인 counterfactual variation을 추가함으로써, 우리의 방법은 노이즈에 취약하고 소표본인 회귀 설정에 대해 간단하고 효율적인 해결책을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66000","en":"Expressivity-Efficiency Tradeoffs for Hybrid Sequence Models","ko":"하이브리드 시퀀스 모델의 표현력-효율성 트레이드오프","authors":"John Cooper, Mingchen Ma, Ilias Diakonikolas, Frederic Sala","pos":"#4622","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=82EJxJzG6r","abs":"Hybrid sequence models—combining Transformer and state-space model layers—seek to gain the expressive versatility of attention as well as the computational efficiency of state-space model layers. Despite burgeoning interest in hybrid models, we lack a basic understanding of the settings where—and underlying mechanisms through which—they offer benefits over their constituent models. In this paper, we study this question, focusing on a broad family of core synthetic tasks. For this family of tasks, we prove the existence of fundamental limitations for non-hybrid models. Specifically, any Transformer or state-space model that solves the underlying task requires either a large number of parameters or a large working memory. On the other hand, for two prototypical tasks within this family—namely selective copying and associative recall—we construct hybrid models of small size and working memory that provably solve these tasks, thus achieving the best of both worlds. Our experimental evaluation empirically validates our theoretical findings. Importantly, going beyond the settings in our theoretical analysis, we empirically show that learned—rather than constructed—hybrids outperform non-hybrid models with up to $6 \\times$ as many parameters. We additionally demonstrate that hybrid models exhibit stronger length generalization and out-of-distribution robustness than non-hybrids."},{"id":"66350","en":"MGAL: A Multilingual Granularity-Aware Long-Context Benchmark","ko":"MGAL: 다국어 세밀도 인지 장문맥 벤치마크","authors":"Chunhan Li, Chenglin Xu, Zongyang Zhang, Jiale Liu, Zhuoxi Rao, Xudong jia, JUNXIU HE, Menglin Yang, Wenjuan Gong, Zhengzhe Liu, Chengwei Qin","pos":"#1802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4RJrwbGKfL","abs":"<p>Evaluation of long-context Large Language Models (LLMs) has advanced rapidly. However, most existing benchmarks are limited to the document level and focus mainly on high-resource languages, leaving many fine-grained challenges insufficiently evaluated. To address this gap, we present MGAL, the first multilingual, granularity- and position-aware long-context benchmark. MGAL is constructed from United Nations (UN) reports spanning 8K to 128K tokens across the six official UN languages. It covers four coherent levels of linguistic granularity (word, sentence, paragraph, and document) and further stratifies entries by their position within the document (begin, middle, and end), indexed at both the document and paragraph levels. This design enables systematic diagnosis of multilingual long-context comprehension across different granularities.  Through extensive experiments and analyses, we find that: (1) LLMs perform well at word-level tasks but struggle with coarser-grained ones; and (2) Closed-source models retain a clear performance advantage in lower-resource languages. We further identify two new challenges: (1) Under local semantic crowding, where neighboring sentences share topics and entities, models tend to follow surface cues (e.g., connectives like 'however' or repeated entities) rather than the discourse role of the sentence in surrounding context (e.g., background, outcome); and (2) A gap between fluency and consistency in generated outputs, where models produce text that reads smoothly but drifts from the source facts. In addition, we observe several patterns in line with prior studies, including reliance on nearby evidence and reuse of options under uncertainty.</p>"},{"id":"61393","en":"Lost in Context: Discovering Context Anxiety in Large Language Models","ko":"Lost in Context: Large Language Models의 Context Anxiety 발견","authors":"Ifueko Igbinedion, Jillian Ross, Etienne Ricardez, Sertac Karaman, Eric So","pos":"#1901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qhbC2jtmVW","abs":"<p>Conventional wisdom suggests that reasoning models fail when problems exceed their capabilities. However, we find that frontier reasoning models sometimes possess the necessary capabilities to solve problems but fail due to premature self-doubt -- a phenomenon informally known as context anxiety. We provide the first systematic study of context anxiety, demonstrating that it arises, in part, from a model's inability to accurately estimate the tokens required to complete a task. We also show that context anxiety leads to material efficiency losses when models operate under perceived constraints. Building on this analysis, we further show that models can learn alternative strategies for solving long-horizon problems without exhibiting context anxiety, suggesting that performance improvements may be achievable not through scaling model capabilities, but by improving models' ability to accurately assess and adapt to their own limitations.</p>","absKo":"<p>일반적인 통념은 reasoning model이 문제의 난이도가 자신의 능력을 넘어서면 실패한다고 본다. 그러나 우리는 frontier reasoning model이 때때로 문제를 해결하는 데 필요한 능력을 갖추고 있음에도, 조기 자기 의심 때문에 실패한다는 사실을 발견했는데, 이는 비공식적으로 context anxiety라고 불린다. 본 연구는 context anxiety에 대한 첫 체계적 연구를 제시하며, 이것이 부분적으로는 task를 완료하는 데 필요한 token 수를 모델이 정확히 추정하지 못하는 데서 발생함을 보인다. 또한 모델이 지각된 제약 아래에서 동작할 때 context anxiety가 실질적인 효율 손실을 초래함을 보인다. 이러한 분석을 바탕으로, 우리는 모델이 context anxiety를 보이지 않으면서 장기 지평 문제를 해결하는 대안적 전략을 학습할 수 있음을 추가로 보인다. 이는 성능 향상이 모델 능력의 scaling만으로 이루어지는 것이 아니라, 자신의 한계를 정확히 평가하고 적응하는 능력을 개선함으로써 달성될 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"65467","en":"LiveOIBench: Can Large Language Models Outperform Human Contestants in Informatics Olympiads?","ko":"LiveOIBench: Large Language Model이 정보 올림피아드에서 인간 참가자를 능가할 수 있는가?","authors":"Kaijian Zou, Feiyang Xiong, Yunxiang Zhang, Xinliang Frederick Zhang, Yueqi Ren, Shitanshu Bhushan, Ayoung Lee, Jirong Yang, Lu Wang","pos":"#1902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DKoycSNd9W","abs":"Competitive programming problems are increasingly used to evaluate the coding capabilities of large language models (LLMs) due to their complexity and ease of verification.  Yet, current coding benchmarks face limitations such as lack of exceptionally challenging problems, insufficient test case coverage, reliance on online platform APIs that limit accessibility. To address these issues, we introduce LiveOIBench, a large-scale competitive programming benchmark featuring 403 expert-curated problems, averaging $60$ official test cases each, drawn from 72 contests across 14 Informatics Olympiads held between 2023 and 2025. LiveOIBench has four key features:  (1) expert-designed tasks with detailed subtask rubrics and extensive test cases;  (2) direct comparison to elite human contestants;  (3) continuous updates to reduce contamination risk; and (4) a fully offline, reproducible evaluation system. Benchmarking 34 popular general-purpose and reasoning LLMs, we find that GPT-5 achieves an 81.76th percentile, still falling short of top human contestants, while among the open-weight models, GPT-OSS-120B reaches only the 60th percentile. Reasoning-trace analyses indicate that robust reasoning models prioritize precise problem analysis over excessive exploration.  Finally, analyses across released time, task familiarity, and code similarity find minimal evidence of data contamination in our benchmark. Our code and data are available at: https://liveoibenchanon.github.io/."},{"id":"62614","en":"WISE: World Knowledge-Informed Semantic Evaluation for Text-to-Image Generation","ko":"WISE: Text-to-Image Generation을 위한 World Knowledge-Informed Semantic Evaluation","authors":"Yuwei Niu, Munan Ning, Mengren Zheng, Weiyang Jin, Bin Lin, Peng Jin, Jiaqi Liao, Chaoran Feng, Fanqing Meng, Kun-Peng Ning, Bin Zhu, Li Yuan","pos":"#2203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=f1q8dFnxtY","abs":"<p>Text-to-Image (T2I) models are capable of generating high-quality artistic creations and visual content. However, existing research and evaluation standards predominantly focus on image realism and shallow text-image alignment, lacking a comprehensive assessment of complex semantic understanding and world knowledge integration in text-to-image generation. To address this challenge, we propose WISE, the first benchmark specifically designed for World Knowledge-Informed Semantic Evaluation. WISE moves beyond simple word-pixel mapping by challenging models with 1000 meticulously crafted prompts across 25 subdomains in cultural common sense, spatio-temporal reasoning, and natural science. To overcome the limitations of traditional CLIP metric, we introduce WiScore, a novel quantitative metric for assessing knowledge-image alignment. Through comprehensive testing of 20 models (10 dedicated T2I models and 10 unified multimodal models) using 1,000 structured prompts spanning 25 subdomains, our findings reveal significant limitations in their ability to effectively integrate and apply world knowledge during image generation, highlighting critical pathways for enhancing knowledge incorporation and application in next-generation T2I models. Code and data will be available.</p>","absKo":"<p>Text-to-Image(T2I) 모델은 고품질의 예술적 창작물과 시각 콘텐츠를 생성할 수 있다. 그러나 기존 연구와 평가 기준은 주로 image realism과 피상적인 text-image alignment에 초점을 맞추고 있어, text-to-image generation에서의 복잡한 semantic understanding과 world knowledge integration에 대한 포괄적 평가가 부족하다. 이러한 도전을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 World Knowledge-Informed Semantic Evaluation을 위해 특별히 설계된 최초의 benchmark인 WISE를 제안한다. WISE는 문화적 상식, 시공간 추론, 자연과학 전반의 25개 subdomain에 걸쳐 세심하게 설계된 1000개의 prompt로 모델을 시험함으로써 단순한 word-pixel mapping을 넘어선다. 기존 CLIP metric의 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 knowledge-image alignment를 평가하는 새로운 정량 metric인 WiScore를 도입한다. 25개 subdomain을 아우르는 1,000개의 구조화된 prompt를 사용하여 20개 모델(전용 T2I 모델 10개와 통합 multimodal model 10개)을 포괄적으로 테스트한 결과, 이미지 생성 중 world knowledge를 효과적으로 통합하고 적용하는 능력에 상당한 한계가 있음을 확인했으며, 이는 차세대 T2I 모델에서 지식의 통합과 활용을 강화하기 위한 핵심 경로를 보여준다. 코드와 데이터는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64758","en":"Is Graph Mixup Beneficial? Investigating Interpolation And Empirical Performance of Graph Mixup Methods","ko":"Graph Mixup은 유익한가? Graph Mixup 방법의 보간과 경험적 성능 조사","authors":"Simon Forbat, Rainer Gemulla","pos":"#2204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KB9z4bnrbD","abs":"<p>Mixup is a widely used data augmentation technique that constructs new training examples by interpolating between existing ones. While simple and effective in domains like vision and language, applying mixup to graph data is non-trivial and there is no independent empirical evidence for its effectiveness. To fill this gap, we conducted an extensive evaluation study following a unified, established evaluation protocol for graph classification. In contrast to prior results, we found that none of the state-of-the-art mixup methods yielded statistically significant improvements over the no-mixup baseline. To obtain further insights, we analyzed the graphs generated from these mixup methods from an interpolation perspective. We found that (i) many mixup methods failed to interpolate well, (ii) high interpolation error led to performance degradation, and (iii) even good interpolation properties did not lead to performance improvements. Our findings question the efficacy of existing graph mixup methods and highlight the need for a more rigorous exploration and evaluation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mixup은 기존 예들 사이를 보간하여 새로운 training example을 구성하는 널리 사용되는 data augmentation 기법이다. vision과 language 같은 영역에서는 단순하면서도 효과적이지만, graph data에 mixup을 적용하는 것은 비자명하며 그 효과에 대한 독립적인 실증 증거도 없다. 이 공백을 메우기 위해, 우리는 graph classification에 대해 통합된 확립된 evaluation protocol을 따르는 광범위한 평가 연구를 수행했다. 기존 결과와 달리, 우리는 state-of-the-art mixup method 중 어느 것도 mixup을 사용하지 않은 baseline보다 통계적으로 유의미한 향상을 보이지 않음을 발견했다. 추가적인 통찰을 얻기 위해, 우리는 이러한 mixup method로 생성된 graph를 interpolation 관점에서 분석했다. 그 결과 (i) 많은 mixup method가 보간을 잘 수행하지 못했고, (ii) 높은 interpolation error가 성능 저하로 이어졌으며, (iii) 보간 성질이 좋더라도 성능 향상으로 이어지지 않음을 확인했다. 우리의 발견은 기존 graph mixup method의 효과에 의문을 제기하며, 더 엄밀한 탐구와 평가의 필요성을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61100","en":"Uncovering Competency Gaps in Large Language Models and Their Benchmarks","ko":"Large Language Model과 벤치마크의 역량 격차 드러내기","authors":"Maty Bohacek, Nino Scherrer, Nicholas Dufour, Thomas Leung, Christoph Bregler, Stephanie Chan","pos":"#3201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=thhtz3Oyg1","abs":"<p>The evaluation of large language models relies heavily on standardized benchmarks. These benchmarks provide useful aggregated metrics, but can obscure (i) particular sub-areas where the models are weak (\"model gaps\") (ii) imbalanced coverage in the benchmarks themselves (\"benchmark gaps\"). To automatically uncover both types of gaps, we propose a simple new method using concept activations from sparse autoencoders, to identify fine-grained gaps on a per-concept basis. The method also benefits from grounding evaluation in the model's internal representations, as well as easy comparison across benchmarks. We applied the method to two popular open-source models and ten benchmarks, as illustrative examples. As validation of the approach, we found that our automatic, unsupervised method was able to recover model gaps that have been previously documented in the literature (e.g. relating to sycophancy), in addition to identifying novel model gaps. We were also able to automatically uncover benchmark gaps: core concepts that should fall within the scope of a given benchmark. Our ``competency gaps'' method can be used to complement existing benchmarks, by providing a concept-level decomposition of model behavior, and by helping benchmark developers iterate upon benchmark design. Code is available at [anonymized].</p>","absKo":"<p>large language model의 평가는 표준화된 benchmark에 크게 의존한다. 이러한 benchmark는 유용한 집계 지표를 제공하지만, (i) 모델이 약한 특정 세부 영역(“model gaps”)과 (ii) benchmark 자체의 불균형한 커버리지(“benchmark gaps”)를 가릴 수 있다. 두 종류의 gap을 자동으로 드러내기 위해, 우리는 sparse autoencoder의 concept activation을 사용하는 간단한 새로운 방법을 제안하여, concept 단위로 세분화된 gap을 식별한다. 이 방법은 또한 모델의 internal representation에 기반해 평가를 정렬할 수 있고, benchmark 간 비교도 쉽게 해준다는 장점이 있다. 우리는 예시로 두 개의 인기 있는 open-source model과 열 개의 benchmark에 이 방법을 적용했다. 접근법의 검증으로, 우리의 자동화된 unsupervised method가 sycophancy와 관련해 문헌에 이미 보고된 model gap을 재현할 수 있었고, 동시에 새로운 model gap도 식별할 수 있음을 확인했다. 또한 주어진 benchmark의 범위 안에 있어야 하는 핵심 concept을 자동으로 찾아내어 benchmark gap도 드러낼 수 있었다. 우리의 ``competency gaps'' method는 모델 행동의 concept-level decomposition을 제공하고 benchmark 개발자가 benchmark 설계를 반복적으로 개선하도록 돕는 방식으로 기존 benchmark를 보완할 수 있다. 코드는 [anonymized]에서 उपलब्ध하다.</p>"},{"id":"63662","en":"VisualPuzzles: Decoupling Multimodal Reasoning Evaluation from Domain Knowledge","ko":"VisualPuzzles: 멀티모달 추론 평가를 도메인 지식과 분리하기","authors":"Yueqi Song, Tianyue Ou, Yibo Kong, Zecheng Li, Graham Neubig, Xiang Yue","pos":"#408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UqfxuIt6hN","abs":"<p>Current multimodal benchmarks often conflate reasoning with domain-specific knowledge, making it difficult to isolate and evaluate general reasoning abilities in non-expert settings. To address this, we introduce VisualPuzzles, a benchmark that targets visual reasoning while deliberately minimizing reliance on specialized knowledge. VisualPuzzles consists of diverse questions spanning five categories: algorithmic, analogical, deductive, inductive, and spatial reasoning. One major source of our questions is manually translated logical reasoning questions from the Chinese Civil Service Examination. Experiments show that VisualPuzzles requires significantly less intensive domain-specific knowledge and more complex reasoning compared to benchmarks like MMMU, enabling us to better evaluate genuine multimodal reasoning. Evaluations show that state-of-the-art multimodal large language models consistently lag behind human performance on VisualPuzzles, and that strong performance on knowledge-intensive benchmarks does not necessarily translate to success on reasoning-focused, knowledge-light tasks. Additionally, reasoning enhancements such as scaling up inference compute (with \"thinking\" modes) yield inconsistent gains across models and task types, and we observe no clear correlation between model size and performance. We also found that models exhibit different reasoning and answering patterns on VisualPuzzles compared to benchmarks with heavier emphasis on knowledge. VisualPuzzles offers a clearer lens through which to evaluate reasoning capabilities beyond factual recall and domain knowledge.</p>","absKo":"현재의 multimodal benchmark는 종종 reasoning과 domain-specific knowledge를 혼동하여, 비전문가 환경에서 일반적인 reasoning 능력을 분리하고 평가하기 어렵게 만든다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 전문 지식 의존을 의도적으로 최소화하면서 visual reasoning을 겨냥한 benchmark인 VisualPuzzles를 소개한다. VisualPuzzles는 algorithmic, analogical, deductive, inductive, spatial reasoning의 다섯 범주에 걸친 다양한 질문으로 구성된다. 질문의 주요 출처 중 하나는 중국 공무원 시험의 논리 추론 문항을 수작업으로 번역한 것이다. 실험 결과, VisualPuzzles는 MMMU와 같은 benchmark에 비해 훨씬 적은 수준의 domain-specific knowledge와 더 복잡한 reasoning을 요구하여, 진정한 multimodal reasoning을 더 잘 평가할 수 있음을 보여준다. 평가 결과, state-of-the-art multimodal large language model은 VisualPuzzles에서 인간 성능에 지속적으로 뒤처지며, 지식 집약적인 benchmark에서의 강한 성능이 반드시 reasoning 중심의 지식 부담이 적은 task 성공으로 이어지지는 않음을 보여준다. 또한, inference compute를 늘리는 것(\"thinking\" mode 사용)과 같은 reasoning enhancement는 model과 task type에 따라 일관되지 않은 향상을 보였으며, model size와 성능 사이에 뚜렷한 상관관계는 관찰되지 않았다. 더불어, 모델들은 지식 비중이 높은 benchmark와 비교할 때 VisualPuzzles에서 서로 다른 reasoning 및 answer pattern을 보였다. VisualPuzzles는 사실 기억과 domain knowledge를 넘어 reasoning capability를 평가할 수 있는 더 명확한 렌즈를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66048","en":"Anytime-Valid Inference for Online Ranking of Large Language Models","ko":"대형 언어 모델의 온라인 순위화를 위한 언제나 유효한 추론","authors":"Runzhe Gu, Wenguang Sun, Bowen Gang, Xintao Xia","pos":"#4107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7Y8xRnGQ47","abs":"<p>Online evaluation of large language models increasingly relies on sequentially collected pairwise preferences, enabling human-aligned assessment and continuous data collection until closely performing models can be reliably distinguished. However, adaptive sampling and continuous monitoring invalidate classical fixed-sample inference, rendering existing ranking procedures largely heuristic. We propose SERPANT (Sequential E-value Ranking and Pruning via Adaptive Null Testing), a principled framework for online LLM ranking with anytime-valid guarantees. SERPANT formulates model comparison as a collection of pairwise hypothesis tests and constructs e-processes to ensure family-wise error rate control at any monitoring time. Anytime validity provides a theoretical justification for early stopping, enabling substantial cost savings from expensive human annotation. To improve efficiency, we introduce a novel tournament-based sampling strategy that adaptively selects comparisons based on past outcomes. The proposed framework further provides anytime-valid confidence sets for top-k model identification. Theoretical and empirical results on benchmark datasets validate the efficiency and statistical guarantees.</p>"},{"id":"64901","en":"Prescriptive Scaling Reveals the Evolution of Language Model Capabilities","ko":"Prescriptive Scaling이 Language Model 능력의 진화를 드러낸다","authors":"Hanlin Zhang, Jikai Jin, Vasilis Syrgkanis, Sham Kakade","pos":"#4111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IkjsHRpuYY","abs":"<p>For deploying foundation models, practitioners increasingly need prescriptive scaling laws: given a pre-training compute budget, what downstream accuracy is attainable with contemporary post-training practice, and how stable is that mapping as the field evolves? Using large-scale observational evaluations with 5k observational and 2k newly sampled data on model performance, we estimate capability boundaries—high conditional quantiles of benchmark scores as a function of log pre-training FLOPs, via smoothed quantile regression with a monotone, saturating sigmoid parameterization. We validate the temporal reliability by fitting on earlier model generations and evaluating on later releases. Across various tasks, the estimated boundaries are mostly stable, with the exception of math reasoning that exhibits a consistently advancing boundary over time. We then extend our approach to analyze task-dependent saturation and to probe contamination-related shifts on math reasoning tasks. Finally, we introduce an efficient algorithm that recovers near-full-data frontiers using roughly 20% of evaluation budget. Together, our work releases the Proteus-2k, the latest model performance evaluation dataset, and introduces a practical methodology for translating compute budgets into reliable performance expectations and for monitoring when capability boundaries move.</p>","absKo":"Foundation model을 배포할 때, 실무자들은 점점 더 prescriptive scaling law를 필요로 한다. 즉, pre-training compute budget이 주어졌을 때 현대적인 post-training practice로 도달 가능한 downstream accuracy는 어느 정도이며, 해당 매핑은 분야가 발전함에 따라 얼마나 안정적인가? 모델 성능에 대한 5천 개의 observational data와 2천 개의 새로 샘플링한 데이터를 포함한 대규모 observational evaluation을 사용하여, 우리는 smooth quantile regression과 monotone, saturating sigmoid parameterization을 통해 log pre-training FLOP의 함수로서 benchmark score의 높은 conditional quantile인 capability boundary를 추정한다. 우리는 더 이른 model generation으로 학습하고 더 늦은 release에서 평가함으로써 temporal reliability를 검증한다. 다양한 task 전반에서, 추정된 boundary는 대체로 안정적이지만, math reasoning은 시간이 지남에 따라 일관되게 진전하는 boundary를 보인다. 이후 우리는 task-dependent saturation 분석과 math reasoning task에서의 contamination-related shift 탐지를 위해 접근법을 확장한다. 마지막으로, 대략 evaluation budget의 20%만으로 거의 full-data frontier를 복원하는 효율적인 algorithm을 제안한다. 종합하면, 본 연구는 최신 model performance evaluation dataset인 Proteus-2k를 공개하고, compute budget을 신뢰할 수 있는 performance expectation으로 변환하며 capability boundary가 언제 이동하는지 모니터링하기 위한 실용적인 methodology를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"62814","en":"Routing and Reasoned Evaluation with Large Language Models","ko":"Large Language Models를 이용한 Routing 및 Reasoned Evaluation","authors":"Guiyao Tie, Tianyao Luo, Xueyang Zhou, Chaoran Hu, Yunhong He, Junran Wu, Yuanfan Yao, Pan Zhou, Lichao Sun","pos":"#4312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=d0dDhLR19Y","abs":"Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly used to provide automated assessment signals for evaluating model-generated outputs. However, practical deployment faces three persistent challenges: heterogeneous reliability across models, substantial latency and token costs, and the absence of principled strategies for allocating evaluation resources. We introduce R$^2$Eval, a routing-aware automated assessment framework that formulates evaluation as a resource allocation and aggregation problem rather than relying on a single monolithic evaluator. R$^2$Eval combines difficulty-aware routing with reasoned evaluation signals to dynamically select evaluator models on a per-instance basis under explicit accuracy, latency, and cost constraints. Our study makes three contributions. First, we construct six difficulty-aware datasets spanning both reasoning-intensive (mathematics, logic, code) and non-reasoning (knowledge, roleplay, writing) tasks, with human-annotated reference assessments. Second, we provide a systematic empirical analysis of how reasoning traces produced by different evaluator models correlate with assessment outcomes, revealing substantial variance and systematic mismatches across difficulty regimes. Third, we develop and evaluate both offline and online routing strategies that adaptively allocate evaluation queries, achieving substantially improved accuracy–efficiency trade-offs compared to static baselines. Experiments across 19 language models demonstrate that R$^2$Eval significantly reduces evaluation cost and latency while maintaining close alignment with human assessments. These results highlight the importance of routing-aware automated assessment and establish R$^2$Eval as a scalable and reliable framework for large-scale model evaluation.","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델 (LLMs)은 model-generated output을 평가하기 위한 automated assessment signal 제공에 점점 더 많이 사용되고 있다. 그러나 실제 배포에서는 세 가지 지속적인 문제가 있다. 모델 간 이질적인 신뢰도, 상당한 latency와 token cost, 그리고 평가 자원을 어떻게 배분할지에 대한 원칙적 전략의 부재가 그것이다. 우리는 평가를 단일한 monolithic evaluator에 의존하는 대신 resource allocation과 aggregation 문제로 정식화하는 routing-aware automated assessment framework인 R$^2$Eval을 소개한다. R$^2$Eval은 difficulty-aware routing과 reasoned evaluation signal을 결합하여, 명시적인 accuracy, latency, cost 제약하에 instance별로 evaluator model을 동적으로 선택한다. 우리의 연구는 세 가지 기여를 한다. 첫째, 수학, 논리, 코드와 같은 reasoning-intensive task와 knowledge, roleplay, writing과 같은 non-reasoning task를 아우르며 human-annotated reference assessment를 포함하는 여섯 개의 difficulty-aware dataset을 구축한다. 둘째, 서로 다른 evaluator model이 생성한 reasoning trace가 assessment outcome과 어떻게 상관되는지에 대한 체계적인 실증 분석을 제공하여, difficulty regime 전반에서 상당한 분산과 체계적 불일치를 밝힌다. 셋째, evaluation query를 적응적으로 배분하는 offline 및 online routing strategy를 개발하고 평가하여, static baseline보다 훨씬 향상된 accuracy-efficiency trade-off를 달성한다. 19개의 language model에 대한 실험은 R$^2$Eval이 human assessment와의 정렬을 크게 유지하면서 평가 비용과 latency를 유의미하게 줄임을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 routing-aware automated assessment의 중요성을 강조하며, R$^2$Eval을 대규모 model evaluation을 위한 확장 가능하고 신뢰할 수 있는 framework로 확립한다."},{"id":"62443","en":"Probing the Knowledge Boundary: An Interactive Agentic Framework for Deep Knowledge Extraction","ko":"Knowledge Boundary 탐색: 깊은 지식 추출을 위한 대화형 Agentic Framework","authors":"Yuheng Yang, Siqi Zhu, Tao Feng, Ge Liu, Jiaxuan You","pos":"#4313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gY9mL1HW2M","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) can be seen as compressed knowledge bases, but it remains unclear what knowledge they truly contain and how far their knowledge boundaries extend. Existing benchmarks are mostly static and provide limited support for systematic knowledge probing. In this paper, we propose an interactive agentic framework to systematically extract and quantify the knowledge of LLMs. Our method includes four adaptive exploration policies to probe knowledge at different granularities. To ensure the quality of extracted knowledge, we introduce a three-stage knowledge processing pipeline that combines vector-based filtering to remove exact duplicates, LLM-based adjudication to resolve ambiguous semantic overlaps, and domain-relevance auditing to retain valid knowledge units. Through extensive experiments, we find that recursive taxonomy is the most effective exploration strategy. We also observe a clear knowledge scaling law, where larger models consistently extract more knowledge. In addition, we identify a Pass@1-versus-Pass@k trade-off: domain-specialized models achieve higher initial accuracy but degrade rapidly, while general-purpose models maintain stable performance during extended extraction. Finally, our results show that differences in training data composition lead to distinct and measurable knowledge profiles across model families.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)는 압축된 knowledge base로 볼 수 있지만, 실제로 어떤 지식을 담고 있는지, 그리고 그 knowledge boundary가 어디까지 확장되는지는 여전히 불분명하다. 기존 benchmark는 대부분 static하며, 체계적인 knowledge probing을 지원하는 데 한계가 있다. 본 논문에서는 LLM의 지식을 체계적으로 추출하고 정량화하기 위한 interactive agentic framework를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 서로 다른 granularity에서 지식을 probe하기 위한 네 가지 adaptive exploration policy를 포함한다. 추출된 지식의 품질을 보장하기 위해, exact duplicate를 제거하는 vector-based filtering, ambiguous semantic overlap을 해소하는 LLM-based adjudication, 유효한 knowledge unit을 유지하기 위한 domain-relevance auditing을 결합한 3-stage knowledge processing pipeline을 도입한다. 광범위한 실험을 통해 recursive taxonomy가 가장 효과적인 exploration strategy임을 확인했다. 또한 더 큰 model일수록 더 많은 지식을 일관되게 추출하는 명확한 knowledge scaling law도 관찰했다. 추가로 Pass@1과 Pass@k 사이의 trade-off를 확인했는데, domain-specialized model은 초기 정확도는 더 높지만 빠르게 성능이 저하되는 반면, general-purpose model은 장시간 추출 동안 안정적인 성능을 유지한다. 마지막으로, training data composition의 차이가 model family 간에 구별 가능하고 측정 가능한 knowledge profile 차이를 만든다는 점을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"63443","en":"Beyond Benchmarks: Toward Causally Faithful Evaluation of Large Language Models","ko":"벤치마크를 넘어서: 대규모 언어 모델의 인과적으로 충실한 평가를 향하여","authors":"Zhengshuyuan Tian, Chuanxin Lan, Chenxi Wang, Lei Wang, Guoxin Kang, Zhengxin Yang, Yunyou Huang, Xuehai Hong, Wanling Gao, Jianfeng Zhan","pos":"#4408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XAp0VUy20q","abs":"<p>Current LLM evaluations often conflate benchmark performance with intrinsic model capability. This is misleading, as observed outcomes arise from the entire evaluation system, including datasets, prompting methods, decoding parameters, and the software–hardware stack, rather than the model alone. When this system is underspecified, attribution becomes unreliable; in practice, evaluation choices alone can induce accuracy swings of up to 70\\%. This attribution challenge is compounded by the open-ended nature of LLM evaluation. Questions span languages, domains, and usage styles, forming highly variable and implicitly shifting datasets. Consequently, strong performance on static benchmarks may reflect alignment with surface patterns rather than robust underlying capability.  Prior studies either focus on individual components, overlooking their interactions, or investigate manually curated and small-scale question variants, lacking a holistic perspective, precluding precise attribution of intrinsic model capabilities amidst the confounding influences. To address these limitations, we propose LLM evaluatology, a principled framework that grounds LLM evaluation in a causally informed system design. By jointly modeling evaluation components and structured question variations, it enables interpretable, reproducible, and causally faithful assessment of model capability, establishing clear conditions under which evaluation results are meaningful and trustworthy.</p>","absKo":"<p>현재의 LLM 평가는 종종 benchmark 성능과 내재적 모델 능력을 혼동한다. 이는 오해의 소지가 있는데, 관측되는 결과는 모델 자체만이 아니라 dataset, prompting method, decoding parameter, software-hardware stack을 포함한 전체 evaluation system에서 비롯되기 때문이다. 이 시스템이 충분히 명세되지 않으면 attribution은 신뢰할 수 없게 되며, 실제로 evaluation choice만으로도 정확도가 최대 70\\%까지 변동할 수 있다. 이러한 attribution 문제는 LLM evaluation의 개방형 특성으로 인해 더욱 심화된다. 질문은 언어, 도메인, 사용 스타일을 가로지르며 매우 가변적이고 암묵적으로 변화하는 dataset을 형성한다. 따라서 정적 benchmark에서의 강한 성능은 견고한 내재적 능력보다는 표면 패턴과의 정합을 반영할 수 있다. 선행 연구는 개별 구성 요소에만 초점을 맞추어 상호작용을 놓치거나, 수작업으로 선별된 소규모 질문 변형만을 조사하여 전체론적 관점을 결여함으로써, 혼동 효과 속에서 intrinsic model capability를 정확히 귀속시키는 것을 어렵게 만든다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 LLM evaluatology를 제안한다. 이는 인과적으로 정보를 반영한 system design에 LLM evaluation을 정초하는 원칙적인 framework이다. evaluation component와 구조화된 question variation을 공동으로 모델링함으로써, 모델 능력에 대한 해석 가능하고 재현 가능하며 인과적으로 충실한 평가를 가능하게 하고, 평가 결과가 의미 있고 신뢰할 수 있는 명확한 조건을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"64255","en":"Beyond the Final Answer: Evaluating the Reasoning Trajectories of Tool-Augmented Agents","ko":"최종 답을 넘어: 도구 증강 에이전트의 추론 궤적 평가","authors":"Wonjoong Kim, Sangwu Park, Yeonjun In, Sein Kim, Dongha Lee, Chanyoung Park","pos":"#4409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PRfEvn1UHp","abs":"<p>Driven by recent advancements in tool-augmented Large Language Model (LLM) agents, comprehensive benchmark datasets for evaluating these tool-augmented agents are being actively developed. Although these benchmarks incorporate increasingly complex user requests and a diverse array of tools, the evaluation methods for most of them remain limited to answer matching. However, as the number of steps required to resolve a user request increases, a proper evaluation of an agent's performance must go beyond the final answer to also assess the problem-solving trajectory, including previously ignored aspects such as efficiency, hallucinations, and adaptivity. The most straightforward method for evaluating these aspects is to compare the trajectory of the agent with a ground-truth trajectory, but this approach is fundamentally limited since annotating all possible ground-truth trajectories is prohibitively expensive. To address these significant gaps, we introduce TRACE, a framework for the multi-dimensional evaluation of tool-augmented LLM agent performance. By incorporating evidence store, TRACE enables a multi-faceted analysis and evaluation of an agent's reasoning trajectory, eliminating the need for a predefined ground-truth trajectory. To validate our framework, we develop a new meta-evaluation dataset by augmenting existing benchmarks with diverse and flawed trajectories, each labeled with multi-faceted performance scores. Our results confirm that TRACE accurately evaluates these complex behaviors in a scalable and cost-effective manner, even with small open-source LLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>도구로 증강된 Large Language Model(LLM) agent의 최근 발전에 힘입어, 이러한 도구 증강 agent를 평가하기 위한 포괄적인 benchmark dataset이 활발히 개발되고 있다. 이러한 benchmark는 점점 더 복잡한 사용자 요청과 다양한 도구를 포함하지만, 대부분의 평가 방법은 여전히 정답 매칭에만 머물러 있다. 그러나 사용자 요청을 해결하는 데 필요한 step 수가 늘어날수록, agent 성능에 대한 적절한 평가는 최종 답변을 넘어 문제 해결 trajectory까지 평가해야 하며, 여기에는 효율성, hallucination, adaptivity처럼 그동안 간과되었던 측면도 포함된다. 이러한 측면을 평가하는 가장 직접적인 방법은 agent의 trajectory를 ground-truth trajectory와 비교하는 것이지만, 가능한 모든 ground-truth trajectory를 주석하는 것은 비용이 지나치게 커서 이 접근에는 근본적인 한계가 있다. 이러한 중대한 공백을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 tool-augmented LLM agent 성능을 다차원적으로 평가하기 위한 framework인 TRACE를 제안한다. evidence store를 통합함으로써 TRACE는 사전에 정의된 ground-truth trajectory 없이도 agent의 reasoning trajectory를 다면적으로 분석하고 평가할 수 있게 한다. 이 framework를 검증하기 위해, 우리는 기존 benchmark를 다양하고 결함이 있는 trajectory로 확장하고 각 trajectory에 다면적 성능 점수를 부여한 새로운 meta-evaluation dataset을 구축했다. 우리의 결과는 TRACE가 작은 open-source LLM에서도 이러한 복잡한 행동을 확장 가능하고 비용 효율적으로 정확하게 평가함을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"64802","en":"Correct looks better: Pairwise comparisons reveal accuracy rankings","ko":"정확한 것이 더 좋아 보인다: Pairwise 비교가 정확도 순위를 드러낸다","authors":"Mina Remeli, Moritz Hardt","pos":"#4411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JfcKBsbx0n","abs":"<p>Pairwise comparisons by humans or judge models, combined with aggregation methods such as Elo or Bradley-Terry, have become a central part of evaluating generative models. However, there has been significant debate whether they measure what they intend to measure. Some argue, pairwise comparisons from judges may reward superficial stylistic cues or display judge biases. In a more positive turn, we show that model rankings from pairwise comparisons strongly agree with ground-truth-based accuracy rankings when such ground truth is available for comparison. To make this observation, we convert well-known benchmarks into free-form generative evaluations scored with Elo rankings from pairwise comparisons. We find that Elo rankings show Spearman correlation above 0.9 with accuracy rankings across five established benchmarks. In addition, Elo rankings have significantly more agreement with accuracy than direct evaluation when the judge is weak. Finally, we show that style and judge bias have only minor effects on model rankings. Although style and bias impede absolute measurement, our work demonstrates that model rankings from pairwise comparisons nevertheless reflect accuracy.</p>","absKo":"<p>인간 또는 judge models에 의한 pairwise comparisons와 Elo나 Bradley-Terry 같은 aggregation methods의 결합은 generative models 평가의 핵심 요소가 되었다. 그러나 이것이 의도한 바를 실제로 측정하는지에 대해서는 큰 논쟁이 있어 왔다. 일부는 judge에 의한 pairwise comparisons가 표면적인 stylistic cues를 보상하거나 judge bias를 드러낼 수 있다고 주장한다. 더 긍정적인 관점에서, 우리는 비교를 위한 ground truth가 उपलब्ध한 경우 pairwise comparisons로부터 얻은 model rankings가 ground-truth-based accuracy rankings와 강하게 일치함을 보인다. 이러한 관찰을 확인하기 위해 우리는 잘 알려진 benchmark들을 pairwise comparisons에서 Elo rankings로 채점되는 자유 형식 generative evaluation으로 변환한다. 우리는 Elo rankings가 다섯 개의 확립된 benchmark 전반에서 accuracy rankings와 0.9를 넘는 Spearman correlation을 보인다는 점을 발견한다. 또한 judge가 약할 때 Elo rankings는 direct evaluation보다 accuracy와 훨씬 더 높은 일치를 보인다. 마지막으로 style과 judge bias가 model rankings에 미치는 영향은 제한적임을 보인다. style과 bias는 절대적 측정을 방해하지만, 우리의 연구는 pairwise comparisons로부터 얻은 model rankings가 그럼에도 불구하고 accuracy를 반영함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64924","en":"StitchCUDA: An Automated Multi-Agents End-to-End GPU Programing Framework with Rubric-based Agentic Reinforcement Learning","ko":"StitchCUDA: Rubric 기반 Agentic Reinforcement Learning을 활용한 자동화된 Multi-Agent End-to-End GPU 프로그래밍 프레임워크","authors":"Shiyang Li, Zijian Zhang, Winson Chen, Yuebo Luo, Mingyi Hong, Caiwen Ding","pos":"#115","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Id4iwq3dnF","abs":"Modern machine learning (ML) workloads increasingly rely on GPUs, yet achieving high end-to-end performance remains challenging due to dependencies on both GPU kernel efficiency and host-side settings. Although LLM-based methods show promise on automated GPU kernel generation, prior works mainly focus on single-kernel optimization and do not extend to end-to-end programs, hindering practical deployment.  To address the challenge, in this work, we propose \\textsc{StitchCUDA}, a multi-agent framework for end-to-end GPU program generation, with three specialized agents: a \\textit{Planner} to orchestrate whole system design, a \\textit{Coder} dedicated to implementing it step-by-step, and a \\textit{Verifier} for correctness check and performance profiling using Nsys/NCU. To fundamentally improve the \\textit{Coder}'s ability in end-to-end GPU programming, \\textsc{StitchCUDA} integrates rubric-based agentic reinforcement learning over two atomic skills, task-to-code generation and feedback-driven code optimization, with combined rubric reward and rule-based reward from real executions. Therefore, the \\textit{Coder} learns how to implement advanced CUDA programming techniques (e.g., custom kernel fusion, cublas epilogue), and we also effectively prevent \\textit{Coder}'s reward hacking (e.g., just copy PyTorch code or hardcoding output) during benchmarking. Experiments on KernelBench show that \\textsc{StitchCUDA} achieves nearly 100\\% success rate on end-to-end GPU programming tasks, with 1.72$\\times$  better speedup over the multi-agent baseline and 2.73$\\times$ than the RL model baselines.","absKo":"현대 machine learning (ML) 워크로드는 점점 더 GPU에 의존하고 있지만, 높은 end-to-end 성능을 달성하는 일은 GPU kernel 효율성과 host-side 설정 모두에 대한 의존성 때문에 여전히 어렵다. LLM-based 방법은 자동화된 GPU kernel 생성에서 가능성을 보여주었지만, 기존 연구는 주로 single-kernel 최적화에 초점을 맞추며 end-to-end program으로는 확장하지 못해 실제 배포를 어렵게 한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 end-to-end GPU program 생성을 위한 multi-agent 프레임워크인 \\textsc{StitchCUDA}를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크는 전체 system design을 조율하는 \\textit{Planner}, 이를 단계적으로 구현하는 데 전담하는 \\textit{Coder}, 그리고 Nsys/NCU를 사용해 정합성과 성능 프로파일링을 수행하는 \\textit{Verifier}의 세 가지 특화 agent로 구성된다. end-to-end GPU programming에서 \\textit{Coder}의 능력을 근본적으로 향상시키기 위해, \\textsc{StitchCUDA}는 task-to-code generation과 feedback-driven code optimization이라는 두 개의 atomic skill 위에 rubric-based agentic reinforcement learning을 통합하고, 실제 실행에서 얻는 combined rubric reward와 rule-based reward를 사용한다. 따라서 \\textit{Coder}는 custom kernel fusion, cublas epilogue와 같은 고급 CUDA programming 기법을 구현하는 방법을 학습하며, benchmarking 중에 \\textit{Coder}가 PyTorch 코드를 그대로 복사하거나 출력을 하드코딩하는 식의 reward hacking도 효과적으로 방지한다. KernelBench 실험에서 \\textsc{StitchCUDA}는 end-to-end GPU programming task에서 거의 100\\%의 성공률을 달성하며, multi-agent baseline보다 1.72$\\times$ 더 큰 speedup, RL model baseline보다 2.73$\\times$ 더 큰 speedup을 보인다."},{"id":"61061","en":"Faster Activation Functions at the Edge for Post-Training Speedups","ko":"Post-Training 속도 향상을 위한 Edge에서의 더 빠른 Activation Function","authors":"Anton Lydike, Jun Bi, Jackson Woodruff","pos":"#203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=u2o6hPE8ik","abs":"<p>On-device AI has gained significant attention for enabling efficient, low-latency inference on edge devices. However, tight resource constraints on these platforms make the deployment of accurate and lightweight deep learning models challenging. In particular, advanced activation functions (AFs) like Swish and GELU often incur high inference overhead due to the lack of hardware fast-paths for exponentiation and division, restricting edge-ML applications to simple AFs like ReLU, limiting model accuracy.  To address this, we propose FFCC, a compiler that automatically generates efficient approximations of AFs through floating-point reinterpretation. These functions don’t require hardware fast-paths meaning they remain fast on edge devices. They do not incur great accurate losses, and allowing use as post-training replacements without negatively impacting model final accuracy. FFCC takes a specification of AFs using basic floating-point operators and applies derivation rules to lower these expressions into efficient instruction sequences.  Our experiments show that we can provide fast approximations of AFs, achieving order-of-magnitude speed ups over accurate baselines on Arm M7, delivering performance on-par with Hardswish, while beating it on accuracy. Additionally, we show that our approximations – unlike Hardswish – can be used as drop-in replacements of exact version post-training without loss of model accuracy.</p>","absKo":"on-device AI는 edge device에서 효율적이고 low-latency inference를 가능하게 하면서 큰 주목을 받고 있다. 그러나 이러한 플랫폼의 엄격한 자원 제약은 정확하면서도 가벼운 deep learning model을 배포하는 일을 어렵게 만든다. 특히 Swish와 GELU 같은 advanced activation function(AF)은 exponentiation과 division에 대한 hardware fast-path가 없기 때문에 inference overhead가 커지는 경우가 많아, edge-ML 응용을 ReLU 같은 단순한 AF로 제한하고 model accuracy를 떨어뜨린다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 floating-point reinterpretation을 통해 AF의 효율적인 approximation을 자동 생성하는 compiler FFCC를 제안한다. 이 함수들은 hardware fast-path를 필요로 하지 않으므로 edge device에서도 빠르게 동작한다. 또한 큰 정확도 손실을 유발하지 않으며, model final accuracy를 해치지 않고 post-training replacement로 사용할 수 있다. FFCC는 기본 floating-point operator를 사용해 AF를 명세하면, derivation rule을 적용하여 이러한 표현식을 효율적인 instruction sequence로 낮춘다. 실험 결과, 우리는 AF의 빠른 approximation을 제공할 수 있었고, Arm M7에서 정확한 baseline 대비 order-of-magnitude 수준의 speedup을 달성했으며, Hardswish와 동등한 성능을 보이면서 accuracy에서는 이를 능가했다. 또한 우리의 approximation은 Hardswish와 달리, 정확한 버전의 post-training drop-in replacement로 model accuracy 손실 없이 사용할 수 있음을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"60846","en":"On Efficient Scaling of GNNs via IO-Aware Layers Implementations","ko":"IO-Aware Layer 구현을 통한 GNN의 효율적 확장","authors":"Daria Fomina, Daniil Krasylnikov, Alexey Boykov, Andrey Dolgovyazov, Vyacheslav Zhdanovskiy, Fedor Velikonivtsev","pos":"#2205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=w6JVbu7VFo","abs":"Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) are bottlenecked by sparse, irregular memory access. Popular frameworks such as DGL and PyTorch Geometric support general message passing, but complex layers often materialize edge-wise intermediates, increasing memory traffic and limiting scalability on large graphs. We take an I/O- and arithmetic-intensity--centric view and show that widely used layers fall into three kernel families: SpMM-based convolutions, reduction-based aggregations, and attention-based layers (GATv2/Graph Transformer). For each family, we develop GPU kernels that reduce data movement, improve locality, and remain robust across realistic graphs. We also study graph reordering and find that its impact depends on the kernel mapping: it benefits neighbor-parallel (gather-dominated) kernels more consistently than feature-parallel designs. Empirically, our fused attention kernels reach up to **3.9**$\\times$ speedup for Graph Transformer (median **1.6**$\\times$), with Tensor Core (block-sparse) variants up to **7.3**$\\times$ on locally dense graphs; for GATv2 we reach up to **8.5**$\\times$ speedup (median **2.0**$\\times$) while reducing peak memory by up to **76**$\\times$ (median **6**$\\times$). Our degree-aware reduction kernels achieve up to **10**$\\times$ speedup (median **2.6**$\\times$). For SpMM-based layers, properly cached cuSPARSE achieves up to **8**$\\times$ speedup over DGL and outperforms evaluated custom baselines in the majority of evaluations. We release our implementations as drop-in replacements to support reproducible, hardware-aware GNN acceleration.","absKo":"<p>Graph Neural Networks (GNNs)는 sparse하고 irregular한 memory access에 의해 병목이 발생한다. DGL과 PyTorch Geometric 같은 인기 프레임워크는 일반적인 message passing을 지원하지만, 복잡한 layer는 종종 edge-wise intermediate를 materialize하여 memory traffic을 증가시키고 대규모 graph에서의 확장성을 제한한다. 우리는 I/O와 arithmetic intensity 중심의 관점에서 널리 사용되는 layer가 세 가지 kernel family로 나뉜다는 것을 보인다. 즉, SpMM 기반 convolution, reduction 기반 aggregation, attention 기반 layer (GATv2/Graph Transformer)이다. 각 family에 대해 우리는 data movement를 줄이고 locality를 개선하며 현실적인 graph 전반에서 견고하게 동작하는 GPU kernel을 개발한다. 또한 graph reordering을 연구한 결과, 그 효과는 kernel mapping에 따라 달라지며, neighbor-parallel(gather-dominated) kernel이 feature-parallel design보다 더 일관되게 이점을 얻는다는 사실을 발견했다. 실험적으로, 우리의 fused attention kernel은 Graph Transformer에서 최대 **3.9**$\\times$의 속도 향상(중앙값 **1.6**$\\times$)을 보였고, Tensor Core(block-sparse) 변형은 국소적으로 조밀한 graph에서 최대 **7.3**$\\times$까지 향상되었다. GATv2의 경우 최대 **8.5**$\\times$의 속도 향상(중앙값 **2.0**$\\times$)을 달성하면서 peak memory를 최대 **76**$\\times$(중앙값 **6**$\\times$) 줄였다. degree-aware reduction kernel은 최대 **10**$\\times$의 속도 향상(중앙값 **2.6**$\\times$)을 달성한다. SpMM 기반 layer에서는 적절히 캐시된 cuSPARSE가 DGL 대비 최대 **8**$\\times$의 속도 향상을 보였고, 평가한 대부분의 경우에서 custom baseline보다 우수했다. 우리는 재현 가능하고 hardware-aware한 GNN 가속을 지원하기 위해 이러한 구현을 drop-in replacement로 공개한다."},{"id":"65603","en":"CoCoQuant: Breaking the Bandwidth Wall via Co-Optimized Communication and Computation Quantization","ko":"CoCoQuant: 통신과 연산 양자화의 공동 최적화를 통한 대역폭 장벽 돌파","authors":"Haojie Duanmu, Jifeng Ding, Size Zheng, Xuegui Zheng, Jiangfei Duan, Xingcheng ZHANG, Li-Wen Chang, Xin Liu, Dahua Lin","pos":"#2701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Bxyc3JZtAB","abs":"<p>The rapid scaling of large language models (LLMs) has made distributed inference indispensable, yet end-to-end latency is increasingly dominated by communication, forming a critical bandwidth wall that fundamentally limits the practical gains of existing quantization techniques. Existing approaches typically treat communication and computation in isolation, failing to exploit their coupled nature and introducing limited system-level acceleration and accuracy degradation. To address this, we propose CoCoQuant, a co-designed framework that jointly optimizes communication and computation as a unified end-to-end design space. CoCoQuant introduces a precision-aligned graph-rewriting that enables zero-overhead fusion between low-precision communication and computation. CoCoQuant formulates a hardware-aware mixed-precision allocation problem that integrates roofline-based cost modeling with relative sensitivity calibration, solved via global integer linear programming. Extensive experiments on LLMs of varing scales demonstrate that CoCoQuant achieves Pareto-optimal accuracy-latency trade-offs, delivering up to 2.92 end-to-end speedup with a negligible increase in perplexity (0.22).</p>"},{"id":"68796","en":"LO-BCQ: Locally Optimal Block Clustered Quantization for 4-bit (W4A4) LLM Inference","ko":"LO-BCQ: 4-bit(W4A4) LLM 추론을 위한 국소 최적 Block Clustered Quantization","authors":"Reena Elangovan, Charbel Sakr, Anand Raghunathan, Brucek Khailany","pos":"#2711","abs":"Post-training quantization (PTQ) is a promising approach to reducing the storage and computational requirements of large language models (LLMs) without additional training cost. Recent PTQ studies have primarily focused on quantizing only weights to sub-$8$-bits while maintaining activations at $8$-bits or higher. Accurate sub-8-bit quantization for both weights and activations without relying on quantization-aware training remains a significant challenge. We propose a novel quantization method called block clustered quantization (BCQ) wherein each operand tensor is decomposed into blocks (a block is a group of contiguous scalars), blocks are clustered based on their statistics, and a dedicated optimal quantization codebook is designed for each cluster. As a specific embodiment of this approach, we propose a PTQ algorithm called Locally-Optimal BCQ (LO-BCQ) that iterates between the steps of block clustering and codebook design to greedily minimize the quantization mean squared error. When weight and activation scalars are encoded to W4A4 format (with $0.5$-bits of overhead for storing scaling factors and codebook selectors), we advance the current state-of-the-art by demonstrating $&lt;1$\\% loss in inference accuracy across several LLMs and downstream tasks."},{"id":"63039","en":"DELTA4: Sparse Matrix-Vector Multiplication for Low Sparsity","ko":"DELTA4: 저희소성을 위한 희소 행렬-벡터 곱셈","authors":"Vladimír Macko, Vladimír Boža","pos":"#2713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ah9xkFXCV6","abs":"Sparse Matrix-Vector Multiplication (SpMV) is a fundamental operation in the inference of sparse Large Language Models (LLMs). Because existing SpMV methods perform poorly under the low, unstructured sparsity ($30-90\\\\%$) commonly observed in pruned LLMs, unstructured pruning provides only limited memory reduction and speedup. We propose **DELTA4-SpMV**, a GPU-optimized format and kernel co-designed to reduce storage overhead while remaining compatible with the GPU’s execution model. This enables efficient SpMV for unstructured sparsity without specialized hardware units or precomputation. We identify memory bandwidth as the primary limiting factor of SpMV and analyze the storage overhead of DELTA4. At $50\\\\%$ sparsity, DELTA4 is the first approach to achieve $1.5\\times$ memory reduction and $1.2-1.5\\times$ speedup over the dense baseline as well as substantial improvements over other SpMV methods: cuSPARSE ($2.8-13.0\\times$), Sputnik ($1.9-2.6\\times$), and DASP ($2.2-2.5\\times$). An LLM pruned with Wanda to sparsity $50\\\\%$ requires $1.5\\times$ less memory and achieves $1.5\\times$ faster inference at fp16 precision. As a result, **unstructured pruning at $50\\\\%$ sparsity becomes practical** for real-world LLM workloads and **bridges the efficiency gap with structured 2:4 sparsity**.","absKo":"Sparse Matrix-Vector Multiplication (SpMV)은 sparse Large Language Models (LLMs) 추론에서 기본적인 연산이다. 기존 SpMV methods는 pruned LLM에서 흔히 관찰되는 낮고 비구조적인 sparsity (30-90%)에서 성능이 좋지 않기 때문에, unstructured pruning은 memory reduction과 speedup을 제한적으로만 제공한다. 우리는 GPU의 execution model과 호환성을 유지하면서 storage overhead를 줄이도록 공동 설계한 GPU-optimized format과 kernel인 DELTA4-SpMV를 제안한다. 이를 통해 특수 하드웨어 유닛이나 precomputation 없이도 unstructured sparsity에 대한 효율적인 SpMV가 가능해진다. 우리는 memory bandwidth를 SpMV의 주요 제한 요인으로 규명하고 DELTA4의 storage overhead를 분석했다. 50% sparsity에서 DELTA4는 dense baseline 대비 1.5x memory reduction과 1.2-1.5x speedup을 달성한 최초의 방법이며, 다른 SpMV methods인 cuSPARSE (2.8-13.0x), Sputnik (1.9-2.6x), DASP (2.2-2.5x)보다도 크게 우수하다. Wanda로 sparsity 50%까지 pruning한 LLM은 fp16 precision에서 1.5x 적은 memory를 필요로 하고 1.5x 더 빠른 inference를 달성한다. 그 결과, 50% sparsity에서의 unstructured pruning은 실제 LLM workloads에 대해 실용적이 되며 structured 2:4 sparsity와의 efficiency gap을 메운다."},{"id":"62803","en":"KernelBand: Steering LLM-based Kernel Optimization via Hardware-Aware Multi-Armed Bandits","ko":"KernelBand: Hardware-Aware Multi-Armed Bandit으로 LLM 기반 Kernel Optimization 제어","authors":"Dezhi Ran, Shuxiao Xie, Mingfang Ji, Anmin Liu, Mengzhou Wu, Yuan Cao, Yuzhe Guo, Hao Yu, Linyi Li, Yitao Hu, Wei Yang, Tao Xie","pos":"#309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=d8e2jBfMpE","abs":"<p>High-performance GPU kernels are critical for efficient LLM serving, yet their optimization remains a bottleneck requiring deep system expertise. While code LLMs show promise in generating functionally correct code, kernel optimization is intrinsically a search problem over a vast optimization space.  The fundamental mismatch prevents existing LLM agents from efficiently exploring the optimization space for diverse hardware and compute patterns.  To bridge the gap, we present KernelBand, a framework that formulates kernel optimization as a Multi-Armed Bandit (MAB) problem, explicitly balancing exploration and exploitation to unlock the potential of code LLMs.  To navigate the infinite arm space of optimization strategies applied to candidate kernels, we design two key mechanisms: a hardware-aware pruning strategy via profiling bounds and a trace-driven clustering algorithm that leverages Lipschitz continuity. Theoretically, we prove that KernelBand reduces the regret bound to depend on the compact covering number of runtime clusters, ensuring sample-efficient discovery of high-performance kernels. Extensive experiments on TritonBench-G with three GPU architectures and four code LLMs show that KernelBand consistently and substantially outperforms state-of-the-art methods with over 33% average improvement.</p>","absKo":"<p>고성능 GPU kernel은 효율적인 LLM serving에 필수적이지만, 그 최적화는 깊은 시스템 전문지식을 요구하는 병목으로 남아 있습니다. code LLM은 기능적으로 올바른 코드를 생성하는 데 유망하지만, kernel optimization은 본질적으로 거대한 optimization space 위의 탐색 문제입니다. 이러한 근본적인 불일치는 기존 LLM agent가 다양한 hardware 및 compute pattern에 대해 optimization space를 효율적으로 탐색하지 못하게 합니다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 kernel optimization을 Multi-Armed Bandit (MAB) 문제로 정식화한 KernelBand를 제시합니다. 이는 탐색과 활용을 명시적으로 균형 있게 조절하여 code LLM의 잠재력을 끌어냅니다. 후보 kernel에 적용되는 최적화 전략의 무한한 arm space를 탐색하기 위해, 우리는 profiling bound를 통한 hardware-aware pruning strategy와 Lipschitz continuity를 활용하는 trace-driven clustering algorithm이라는 두 가지 핵심 메커니즘을 설계합니다. 이론적으로, KernelBand가 regret bound를 runtime cluster의 compact covering number에 의존하도록 줄여, 샘플 효율적으로 고성능 kernel을 발견하도록 보장함을 증명합니다. 세 가지 GPU architecture와 네 가지 code LLM을 사용한 TritonBench-G의 광범위한 실험은 KernelBand가 state-of-the-art method를 일관되고 크게 능가하며 평균 33% 이상의 향상을 보임을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"65139","en":"SlideSparse: Fast and Flexible (2N-2):2N Structured Sparsity","ko":"SlideSparse: 빠르고 유연한 (2N-2):2N 구조적 희소성","authors":"Yingbo HAO, Hanyong Shao, Ting Song, Yan Xia, Di Zhang, Shaohan Huang, Xun Wu, Songchen Xu, Le Xu, Li Dong, Zewen Chi, Yi Zou, Furu Wei","pos":"#4109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GQ17DjsBcq","abs":"NVIDIA's 2:4 Sparse Tensor Cores deliver $2\\times$ throughput but demand 50% pruning—a ratio that collapses LLM reasoning accuracy (Qwen3: 54%→15%). Milder $(2N-2):2N$ patterns (e.g., 6:8, 25% pruning) preserve accuracy yet receive *no* hardware support, falling back to dense execution. We present **SlideSparse**, the first system to unlock Sparse Tensor Core acceleration for the $(2N-2):2N$ model family on commodity GPUs. Our *Sliding Window Decomposition* losslessly rewrites any $(2N-2):2N$ block into $N-1$ overlapping 2:4-compliant windows; *activation lifting* fuses the corresponding activation rearrangement into per-token quantization at near-zero cost. Integrated into vLLM, **SlideSparse** is evaluated across five GPUs (A100, H100, B200, RTX 4090, RTX 5080), three precisions (INT8, FP8, BF16), and the Llama/Qwen/BitNet model families. On compute-bound workloads, speedup approaches the theoretical $N/(N-1)$ limit—Qwen2.5-7B with 6:8 sparsity achieves $1.33\\times$, matching the bound exactly—establishing $(2N-2):2N$ as a practical path to accuracy-preserving LLM acceleration.","absKo":"NVIDIA의 2:4 Sparse Tensor Core는 $2\\times$ throughput을 제공하지만 50% pruning을 요구하며, 이 비율은 LLM 추론 정확도를 무너뜨린다(Qwen3: 54%→15%). 더 완화된 $(2N-2):2N$ 패턴(예: 6:8, 25% pruning)은 정확도를 유지하지만 *아무런* hardware support를 받지 못해 dense execution으로 되돌아간다. 우리는 commodity GPU에서 $(2N-2):2N$ model family를 위한 Sparse Tensor Core acceleration을 처음으로 구현한 시스템 **SlideSparse**를 제시한다. 우리의 *Sliding Window Decomposition*은 임의의 $(2N-2):2N$ block을 $N-1$개의 겹치는 2:4 준수 window로 손실 없이 재작성하며, *activation lifting*은 대응되는 activation 재배치를 거의 비용 없이 per-token quantization에 통합한다. vLLM에 통합된 **SlideSparse**는 5개의 GPU(A100, H100, B200, RTX 4090, RTX 5080), 3가지 precision(INT8, FP8, BF16), 그리고 Llama/Qwen/BitNet model family 전반에서 평가되었다. compute-bound workload에서는 speedup이 이론적 한계인 $N/(N-1)$에 근접하며, 6:8 sparsity를 적용한 Qwen2.5-7B는 정확히 그 한계를 만족하는 $1.33\\times$를 달성했다. 이는 $(2N-2):2N$이 정확도를 보존하는 LLM acceleration을 위한 실용적 경로임을 입증한다."},{"id":"63503","en":"DITRON: Distributed Multi-level Tiling Compiler for Parallel Tensor Programs","ko":"DITRON: 병렬 텐서 프로그램을 위한 분산 다단계 타일링 컴파일러","authors":"Size Zheng, Xuegui Zheng, Hanshi Sun, Qi Hou, Wenlei Bao, Shiyu Li, Haojie Duanmu, Jin Fang, Chenli Xue, Chenhui Huang, Yuanqiang Liu, Renze Chen, Ningxin Zheng, Dongyang Wang, Li-Wen Chang, Liqiang Lu, Yun Liang, Jidong Zhai, Xin Liu","pos":"#4202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WcF17Wim9e","abs":"<p>The scaling of large language models (LLMs) is currently bottlenecked by the rigidity of distributed programming. While high-performance libraries like CuBLAS and NCCL provide optimized primitives, they lack the flexibility required for rapidly evolving model architectures. Conversely, existing tensor compilers fail to address the complex memory hierarchy of distributed clusters effectively. To bridge this gap, we propose DITRON, a scalable tile-level compiler that democratizes high-performance distributed kernel development. DITRON introduces a novel hierarchical programming abstraction spanning Core, Device, and Task levels to map tensor programs efficiently onto heterogeneous distributed hardware. This abstraction allows DITRON to support diverse parallelism strategies while abstracting away the complexity of inter-node and intra-node communication. Evaluated across large-scale clusters, DITRON achieves performance parity with or exceeding expert-tuned CUDA libraries, delivering speedups of 6%–30% on isolated kernels and 5%–30% on end-to-end inference in vLLM. Furthermore, DITRON demonstrates strong portability, achieving significant speedups on both NVIDIA and AMD platforms.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 language model (LLM)의 scaling은 현재 distributed programming의 경직성에 의해 병목되고 있습니다. CuBLAS와 NCCL 같은 고성능 library는 최적화된 primitive를 제공하지만, 빠르게 진화하는 model architecture에 필요한 유연성은 부족합니다. 반대로 기존 tensor compiler는 distributed cluster의 복잡한 memory hierarchy를 효과적으로 다루지 못합니다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 고성능 distributed kernel 개발을 대중화하는 확장 가능한 tile-level compiler인 DITRON을 제안합니다. DITRON은 Core, Device, Task 수준에 걸친 새로운 hierarchical programming abstraction을 도입하여 tensor program을 heterogeneous distributed hardware에 효율적으로 매핑합니다. 이 abstraction을 통해 DITRON은 node 간 및 node 내부 통신의 복잡성을 추상화하면서도 다양한 parallelism strategy를 지원할 수 있습니다. 대규모 cluster에서 평가한 결과, DITRON은 expert-tuned CUDA library와 대등하거나 그 이상의 성능을 달성했으며, isolated kernel에서는 6%–30%, vLLM end-to-end inference에서는 5%–30%의 속도 향상을 제공합니다. 또한 DITRON은 강한 portability를 보이며, NVIDIA와 AMD platform 모두에서 유의미한 속도 향상을 달성합니다.</p>"},{"id":"66299","en":"KernelFoundry: Hardware-Aware Evolutionary GPU Kernel Optimization","ko":"KernelFoundry: 하드웨어 인지 진화적 GPU 커널 최적화","authors":"Nina Wiedemann, Quentin Leboutet, Michael Paulitsch, Diana Wofk, Benjamin Ummenhofer","pos":"#4204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4wy2YAHKRF","abs":"<p>GPU kernel optimization challenges LLMs beyond standard coding tasks, as it requires an understanding of hardware architecture, parallel computing optimization strategies, and profiling outputs. However, most existing approaches leveraging LLMs for kernel generation apply standard prompting and feedback loops, considering hardware only through profiling feedback. We introduce KernelFoundry, an evolutionary framework that efficiently explores the space of GPU kernels through (1) MAP-Elites quality-diversity search with kernel-specific behavioral dimensions to sustain exploration; (2) meta-prompt evolution that co-evolves prompts with kernels to uncover task-specific optimization strategies, and (3) a template-based parameter optimization approach to tune kernels to inputs and hardware. We evaluate this framework on KernelBench, robust-kbench and custom tasks, generating SYCL kernels as a cross-platform GPU programming paradigm, and CUDA kernels for comparison to prior work. Our approach consistently outperforms the baseline methods and achieves an average speedup of 2.3 on KernelBench for SYCL. Moreover, KernelFoundry is implemented as a distributed framework with remote access to diverse hardware, allowing quick benchmarking and featuring a flexible user input layer to support kernel generation for a for a wide range of real use cases beyond benchmarking.</p>"},{"id":"64763","en":"Scalable Training of 3D Gaussian Splatting via Out-of-Core Optimization","ko":"Out-of-Core Optimization을 통한 3D Gaussian Splatting의 확장 가능한 학습","authors":"Chonghao Zhong, Shi Linfeng, ChenHua, Tiecheng Sun, Hao Zhao, Binhang Yuan, Chaojian Li","pos":"#4205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=K8UWWJUNYf","abs":"Training 3D Gaussian Splatting (3DGS) at billion-primitive scale is fundamentally memory-bound: each Gaussian carries a large attribute vector, and the aggregate parameter table quickly exceeds GPU capacity, limiting prior systems to tens of millions of Gaussians on consumer hardware. We observe that 3DGS training is inherently sparse and trajectory-conditioned: each iteration activates only the Gaussians visible from the current camera batch, so GPU memory can serve as a working-set cache rather than a persistent parameter store. Building on this insight, we introduce \\textbf{TideGS}, an out-of-core training framework that manages parameters across an SSD--CPU--GPU hierarchy via three synergistic techniques: block-virtualized geometry for SSD-aligned spatial locality, a hierarchical asynchronous pipeline to overlap I/O with computation, and trajectory-adaptive differential streaming that transfers only incremental working-set deltas between iterations. Experiments show that TideGS enables training with \\textbf{over one billion Gaussians} on a single consumer GPU while achieving state-of-the-art reconstruction quality on large-scale scenes, exceeding prior out-of-core baselines (e.g., $\\sim$100M Gaussians) and standard in-memory training (e.g., $\\sim$11M Gaussians).","absKo":"billion-primitive scale에서 3D Gaussian Splatting (3DGS)을 학습하는 일은 근본적으로 memory-bound이다. 각 Gaussian은 큰 attribute vector를 가지며, 전체 parameter table은 곧 GPU capacity를 초과하므로, 기존 시스템은 consumer hardware에서 수천만 개 수준의 Gaussian에 머무를 수밖에 없었다. 우리는 3DGS 학습이 본질적으로 sparse하고 trajectory-conditioned되어 있음을 관찰한다. 각 iteration은 현재 camera batch에서 보이는 Gaussian만 활성화하므로, GPU memory는 persistent parameter store가 아니라 working-set cache로 사용될 수 있다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 SSD--CPU--GPU hierarchy 전반에서 parameter를 관리하는 out-of-core training framework인 \\textbf{TideGS}를 소개한다. 이는 SSD에 정렬된 spatial locality를 위한 block-virtualized geometry, I/O와 computation을 겹치게 하는 hierarchical asynchronous pipeline, 그리고 iteration 간 incremental working-set delta만 전송하는 trajectory-adaptive differential streaming의 세 가지 상호보완적 기법으로 구성된다. 실험 결과 TideGS는 단일 consumer GPU에서 \\textbf{10억 개가 넘는 Gaussians}로 학습을 가능하게 하면서, 대규모 scene에서 state-of-the-art reconstruction quality를 달성하고, 기존 out-of-core baseline(예: 약 1억 개 Gaussian)과 표준 in-memory training(예: 약 1,100만 개 Gaussian)을 능가함을 보인다."},{"id":"65081","en":"Ultrafast On-Chip Online Learning via Spline Locality in Kolmogorov–Arnold Networks","ko":"Kolmogorov–Arnold Network의 스플라인 국소성을 활용한 초고속 온칩 온라인 학습","authors":"Duc Hoang, Aarush Gupta, Philip Harris","pos":"#4207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GxrcJUT5A0","abs":"<p>Ultrafast online learning is essential for high-frequency systems, such as controls for quantum computing and nuclear fusion, where adaptation must occur on sub-microsecond timescales. Meeting these requirements demands low-latency, fixed-precision computation under strict memory constraints, a regime in which conventional Multi-Layer Perceptrons (MLPs) are both inefficient and numerically unstable. We identify key properties of Kolmogorov-Arnold Networks (KANs) that align with these constraints. Specifically, we show that: (i) KAN updates exploiting B-spline locality are sparse, enabling superior on-chip resource scaling, and (ii) KANs are inherently robust to fixed-point quantization. By implementing fixed-point online training on Field-Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGAs), a representative platform for on-chip computation, we demonstrate that KAN-based online learners are significantly more efficient and expressive than MLPs across a range of low-latency and resource-constrained tasks. To our knowledge, this work is the first to demonstrate model-free online learning at sub-microsecond latencies.</p>","absKo":"<p>초고속 온라인 학습은 양자 컴퓨팅과 핵융합 제어처럼 적응이 서브 마이크로초 시간척도에서 일어나야 하는 고주파 시스템에 필수적이다. 이러한 요구를 만족하려면 엄격한 메모리 제약 하에서 저지연, 고정 정밀도 계산이 필요하며, 이 환경에서는 기존의 Multi-Layer Perceptrons (MLPs)가 비효율적이고 수치적으로도 불안정하다. 우리는 이러한 제약과 잘 맞는 Kolmogorov-Arnold Networks (KANs)의 핵심 특성을 식별한다. 구체적으로, (i) B-spline locality를 활용한 KAN 업데이트는 sparse하여 on-chip 자원 확장성이 우수하고, (ii) KAN은 fixed-point quantization에 본질적으로 강건함을 보인다. on-chip 계산의 대표적 플랫폼인 Field-Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGAs)에서 fixed-point online training을 구현함으로써, KAN 기반 online learner가 다양한 저지연 및 자원 제약 과제에서 MLP보다 훨씬 더 효율적이고 표현력이 뛰어남을 보인다. 우리가 아는 한, 이 연구는 sub-microsecond latency에서 model-free online learning을 처음으로 시연한 사례이다.</p>"},{"id":"64008","en":"Understand and Accelerate Memory Processing Pipeline for Large Language Model Inference","ko":"Large Language Model 추론을 위한 메모리 처리 파이프라인의 이해와 가속","authors":"Zifan He, Rui Ma, Yizhou Sun, Jason Cong","pos":"#4208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RmZc1J19N8","abs":"Modern large language model (LLM) serving increasingly depends on efficient long-context processing and generation mechanisms, including sparse attention, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), and compressed contextual memory, to support complex reasoning. We show that these optimizations can be unified into a four-step memory processing pipeline: *Prepare Memory*, *Compute Relevancy*, *Retrieval*, and *Apply to Inference*. Through systematic profiling, we identify a 22\\%-97\\% memory processing overhead in LLM inference and strong heterogeneity in its computational characteristics. Motivated by this insight, we argue that \\textbf{heterogeneous systems} are well-suited to accelerate memory processing and thus end-to-end inference. We demonstrate this approach on a GPU-FPGA system by offloading sparse, irregular, and memory-bounded operations to FPGAs while retaining compute-intensive operations on GPUs. Evaluated on an AMD MI210 GPU and an Alveo U55C FPGA, our system achieves $1.04\\sim2.2\\times$ speedup and $1.11\\sim4.7\\times$ energy reduction across multiple LLM inference optimizations than the GPU baseline (similar results hold on NVIDIA A100). These results establish heterogeneous systems as a practical direction for efficient LLM memory processing and inform future heterogeneous hardware design.","absKo":"현대의 대규모 언어 모델(LLM) 서빙은 복잡한 추론을 지원하기 위해 sparse attention, retrieval-augmented generation(RAG), compressed contextual memory를 포함한 효율적인 long-context 처리 및 생성 메커니즘에 점점 더 의존하고 있다. 우리는 이러한 최적화가 *Prepare Memory*, *Compute Relevancy*, *Retrieval*, *Apply to Inference*라는 네 단계의 memory processing pipeline으로 통합될 수 있음을 보인다. 체계적인 profiling을 통해, LLM inference에서 22\\%-97\\%의 memory processing overhead와 그 계산 특성의 강한 이질성을 확인했다. 이러한 통찰에 따라, 우리는 \\textbf{heterogeneous systems}가 memory processing을 가속화하고 나아가 end-to-end inference를 가속하기에 적합하다고 주장한다. 우리는 sparse하고 irregular하며 memory-bounded한 연산을 FPGA로 오프로딩하고 compute-intensive한 연산은 GPU에 유지하는 GPU-FPGA 시스템에서 이 접근법을 시연한다. AMD MI210 GPU와 Alveo U55C FPGA에서 평가한 결과, 우리의 시스템은 여러 LLM inference 최적화 전반에서 GPU baseline 대비 $1.04\\sim2.2\\times$ speedup과 $1.11\\sim4.7\\times$ energy reduction을 달성했다(NVIDIA A100에서도 유사한 결과를 보인다). 이러한 결과는 heterogeneous systems가 효율적인 LLM memory processing을 위한 실용적 방향임을 확립하며, 향후 heterogeneous hardware 설계에 시사점을 제공한다."},{"id":"66102","en":"Untied Ulysses: Memory-Efficient Context Parallelism via Headwise Chunking","ko":"Untied Ulysses: 헤드 방향 청킹을 통한 메모리 효율적 문맥 병렬성","authors":"Ravi Ghadia, Maksim Abraham, Sergei Vorobyov, Max Ryabinin","pos":"#4209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=726Wto4meA","abs":"<p>Efficiently processing long sequences with Transformer models usually requires splitting the computations across accelerators via context parallelism. The dominant approaches in this family of methods, such as Ring Attention or DeepSpeed Ulysses, enable scaling over the context dimension but do not focus on memory efficiency, which limits the sequence lengths they can support. More advanced techniques, such as Fully Pipelined Distributed Transformer or activation offloading, can further extend the possible context length at the cost of training throughput. In this paper, we present UPipe, a simple yet effective context parallelism technique that performs fine-grained chunking at the attention head level. This technique significantly reduces the activation memory usage of self-attention, breaking the activation memory barrier and unlocking much longer context lengths. Our approach lowers the peak activation memory usage by as much as <strong>82.5%</strong> for 70B Transformers, while matching previous context parallelism techniques in terms of training speed. UPipe can support maximum context lengths of up to 5M tokens for training 8B models on a single 8xH100 node, improving upon prior methods by <strong>25%</strong>.</p>"},{"id":"66331","en":"Veda: Scalable Video Diffusion via Distilled Sparse Attention","ko":"Veda: 증류된 Sparse Attention을 통한 확장 가능한 비디오 Diffusion","authors":"Shihao Han, Hao Yang, Xinting Hu, Xiaofeng Mei, Yi Jiang, XIAOJUAN QI","pos":"#4210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4cSEtYtsHH","abs":"<p>Scaling Diffusion Transformers to generate high-resolution, long videos is constrained by the quadratic cost of self-attention, and existing sparse attention methods degrade under high sparsity. We show empirically that generation quality is determined not by the sparsity ratio itself, but by how well the sparse mask aligns with the tile-wise geometry of full attention. Based on this insight, we propose Veda, a distilled sparse attention framework that formulates tile selection as an explicit reconstruction problem from full attention. Veda integrates statistics-aware tile scoring with head-aware tiling to reduce estimation error and structural mismatch, enabling aggressive sparsity. A hardware-efficient tile-skipping kernel converts theoretical sparsity into practical wall-clock speedups. Experiments on large video diffusion models, including Waver and Wan, demonstrate substantial acceleration without quality degradation. To generate 720P 10-second videos on Waver-T2V-12B, Veda achieves a 5.1× end-to-end speedup and a 10.5× self-attention speedup, reducing attention overhead from 92% to 50%. Notably, the gains increase with sequence length, indicating that Veda scales favorably with spatiotemporal resolution across models.</p>"},{"id":"60791","en":"STD-Former: Image-Conditioned Texture Dictionary Encoding with Sparse Topological Supervision for Texture Recognition","ko":"STD-Former: Texture Recognition을 위한 Sparse Topological Supervision 기반 Image-Conditioned Texture Dictionary Encoding","authors":"Bo Peng, Ke Xu, Yurui Pan","pos":"#1003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wgOItdKqUS","abs":"<p>Texture recognition is often framed as matching an image to a static training-set dictionary or codebook. In practice, this assumption is brittle: label-preserving transformations (illumination, scale, compression, blur) can shift test features away from the fixed training dictionary, producing a training-set codebook misalignment that limits accuracy. We propose STD-Former (Simple Texture Dictionary Transformer), a lightweight framework for image-conditioned texture dictionary encoding. Instead of comparing against a static codebook, STD-Former extracts a compact set of Intrinsic Textons (dictionary atoms / codewords) from the input image itself, yielding self-aligned representations at inference. Our design is intentionally simple and uses a decoupled two-stage recipe. In Stage 1, a Texture Dictionary Extractor (TDE) is pre-trained with a self-supervised Texton Coverage Loss that encourages the learned textons to collectively cover the image patch feature manifold. In Stage 2, a classifier is trained on the encoded dictionary representation; optionally, we add a Sparse Topological Loss derived from 0D persistent homology, which is equivalent to supervising only the (B-1) edges of a minimum spanning tree (MST) in each batch, providing efficient structure regularization. Across six standard texture benchmarks, STD-Former and STD-Former+ achieve new state-of-the-art results.</p>","absKo":"<p>texture recognition은 흔히 이미지를 고정된 training-set dictionary 또는 codebook에 매칭하는 문제로 다뤄진다. 실제로는 이 가정이 취약하다. label-preserving transformation(조명, scale, 압축, blur)은 test feature를 고정된 training dictionary에서 벗어나게 만들 수 있으며, 그 결과 training-set codebook misalignment가 발생해 정확도를 제한한다. 우리는 STD-Former(Simple Texture Dictionary Transformer)를 제안한다. 이는 image-conditioned texture dictionary encoding을 위한 lightweight framework이다. static codebook과 비교하는 대신, STD-Former는 입력 이미지 자체로부터 compact한 Intrinsic Texton(dictionary atom / codeword) 집합을 추출하여 inference 시 self-aligned representation을 생성한다. 우리의 설계는 의도적으로 단순하며 decoupled two-stage recipe를 사용한다. Stage 1에서는 Texture Dictionary Extractor(TDE)를 self-supervised Texton Coverage Loss로 pre-train하여, 학습된 texton이 image patch feature manifold를 전체적으로 포괄하도록 유도한다. Stage 2에서는 encoded dictionary representation 위에 classifier를 학습하고, 선택적으로 0D persistent homology에서 유도된 Sparse Topological Loss를 추가하는데, 이는 각 batch에서 minimum spanning tree(MST)의 (B-1)개 edge만을 supervision하는 것과 동치이며, 효율적인 structure regularization을 제공한다. 여섯 개의 표준 texture benchmark 전반에서 STD-Former와 STD-Former+는 새로운 state-of-the-art 결과를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60534","en":"From Generalist to Specialist Representation","ko":"Generalist에서 Specialist Representation으로","authors":"Yujia Zheng, Fan Feng, Yuke Li, Shaoan Xie, Kevin Murphy, Kun Zhang","pos":"#107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zEg7sA2VBv","abs":"Learning truthful task-relevant latent representations $\\mathbf{s}$ from observations $\\mathbf{o} = f(\\mathbf{s})$ is fundamental. Identifiability, the asymptotic guarantee of recovering the ground-truth representation, is critical because it sets the ultimate limit of any model, even with infinite data and computation. We study this problem in a completely nonparametric setting, without relying on interventions, parametric forms, or structural constraints. We first prove that the structure between time steps and tasks is identifiable in a fully unsupervised manner, even when sequences lack strict temporal dependence and may exhibit disconnections, and task assignments can follow arbitrarily complex and interleaving structures. We then prove that, within each time step, the task-relevant latent representation can be disentangled from the irrelevant part under a simple sparsity regularization, without any additional information or parametric constraints. Together, these results establish a hierarchical foundation: task structure is identifiable across time steps, and task-relevant latent representations are identifiable within each step. To our knowledge, each result provides a first general nonparametric identifiability guarantee, and together they mark a step toward provably moving from generalist to specialist models.","absKo":"관측치 $\\mathbf{o} = f(\\mathbf{s})$로부터 truthful task-relevant latent representation $\\mathbf{s}$를 학습하는 것은 근본적이다. identifiability, 즉 ground-truth representation을 회복할 수 있다는 점근적 보장은, 무한한 데이터와 계산이 있더라도 어떤 모델이 도달할 수 있는 궁극적 한계를 정하기 때문에 결정적으로 중요하다. 우리는 interventions, parametric form, structural constraint에 의존하지 않는 완전한 nonparametric setting에서 이 문제를 연구한다. 우리는 먼저 시퀀스가 엄격한 시간적 종속성을 가지지 않고 단절되어 있을 수 있으며 task assignment가 임의로 복잡하고 interleaving된 구조를 따를 수 있는 경우에도, 시간 단계와 task 사이의 구조가 완전한 unsupervised 방식으로 identifiable함을 증명한다. 이어서, 각 time step 내에서 task-relevant latent representation이 단순한 sparsity regularization 하에서, 추가 정보나 parametric constraint 없이 irrelevant part로부터 disentangled될 수 있음을 증명한다. 이 결과들을 함께 보면 계층적 기반이 확립된다. 즉, task structure는 시간 단계 전반에 걸쳐 identifiable하고, task-relevant latent representation은 각 단계 내에서 identifiable하다. 우리의 지식으로는, 각 결과는 최초의 일반적인 nonparametric identifiability 보장을 제공하며, 함께 generalist model에서 specialist model로 provably 이동하는 한 걸음을 나타낸다."},{"id":"61912","en":"The Extra Tokens Matter: Disentangled Representation Learning with Vision Transformers","ko":"추가 토큰의 중요성: Vision Transformer 기반 분해 표현 학습","authors":"Maofeng Tang, Hairong Qi","pos":"#1501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lj1Qi7Fgyb","abs":"<p>Vision Transformers increasingly incorporate extra tokens beyond patch tokens—from class tokens for aggregation to register tokens for artifact mitigation. While effective for their intended purposes, these tokens typically lack semantic structure. We ask a more ambitious question: Can we design regularization constraints that transform extra tokens into disentangled representations, enabling them to decompose images into semantic parts (e.g., heads, bodies, legs) without explicit supervision? We propose XTRA, an intuitive yet powerful framework that augments Vision Transformers with dedicated ``factor tokens'' and enforces disentanglement via a novel Minimum Volume Constraint (MVC). A multi-stage aggregation process further enforces these factor tokens into semantically pure components, preventing token collapse that often occurs when training with MVC alone. On ImageNet-1K, XTRA achieves superior disentanglement (8.4× improvement in SEPIN@1 over DINOv2)  while simultaneously improving representation quality: KNN accuracy improves by 5.8\\% and linear-probe accuracy by 2.3\\%.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision Transformer는 class token을 통한 aggregation에서부터 register token을 통한 artifact 완화에 이르기까지 patch token 외에 추가 토큰을 점점 더 많이 통합하고 있다. 이러한 토큰들은 의도된 목적에는 효과적이지만, 대개 semantic structure가 부족하다. 우리는 더 야심 찬 질문을 던진다: 명시적 supervision 없이도 이미지의 semantic part(예: heads, bodies, legs)로 분해할 수 있도록, 추가 토큰을 disentangled representation으로 변환하는 regularization constraint를 설계할 수 있는가? 우리는 Vision Transformer에 전용 ``factor token''을 추가하고, 새로운 Minimum Volume Constraint(MVC)를 통해 disentanglement를 강제하는 직관적이면서도 강력한 프레임워크 XTRA를 제안한다. multi-stage aggregation process는 이러한 factor token이 semantically pure component가 되도록 추가로 강제하여, MVC만으로 학습할 때 자주 발생하는 token collapse를 방지한다. ImageNet-1K에서 XTRA는 더 우수한 disentanglement를 달성한다(SEPIN@1이 DINOv2 대비 8.4배 향상) 동시에 representation quality도 개선한다: KNN 정확도는 5.8\\% 향상되고 linear-probe 정확도는 2.3\\% 향상된다.</p>"},{"id":"60968","en":"Revisiting the Platonic Representation Hypothesis: An Aristotelian View","ko":"Platonic Representation Hypothesis 재검토: Aristotelian 관점","authors":"Fabian Gröger, Shuo Wen, Maria Brbic","pos":"#1504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uz0gAAYydl","abs":"<p>The Platonic Representation Hypothesis suggests that representations from neural networks are converging to a common statistical model of reality.  We show that the existing metrics used to measure representational similarity are <em>confounded by network scale</em>: increasing model depth or width can systematically inflate representational similarity scores. To correct these effects, we introduce a permutation-based null-calibration framework that transforms any representational similarity metric into a calibrated score with statistical guarantees. We revisit the Platonic Representation Hypothesis with our calibration framework, which reveals a nuanced picture: the apparent convergence reported by global spectral measures largely disappears after calibration, while local neighborhood similarity, but not local distances, retains significant agreement across different modalities.  Based on these findings, we propose the <em>Aristotelian Representation Hypothesis</em>: representations in neural networks are converging to shared local neighborhood relationships.</p>","absKo":"<p>Platonic Representation Hypothesis는 신경망의 표현이 현실에 대한 하나의 공통된 통계적 모델로 수렴하고 있다고 시사한다. 우리는 표현 유사도를 측정하는 데 사용되는 기존 metric들이 <em>network scale에 의해 confounded</em>된다는 사실을 보인다. 즉, model depth나 width를 증가시키면 representational similarity score가 체계적으로 부풀려질 수 있다. 이러한 효과를 보정하기 위해, 우리는 임의의 representational similarity metric을 통계적 보장을 갖는 calibrated score로 변환하는 permutation-based null-calibration framework를 제안한다. 우리의 calibration framework로 Platonic Representation Hypothesis를 다시 검토한 결과, 더 미묘한 그림이 드러난다. global spectral measure가 보고한 겉보기 수렴은 calibration 후 대부분 사라지는 반면, local distance가 아니라 local neighborhood similarity는 서로 다른 modality 전반에서 유의미한 일치를 유지한다. 이러한 발견을 바탕으로 우리는 <em>Aristotelian Representation Hypothesis</em>를 제안한다: 신경망의 표현은 공유된 local neighborhood 관계로 수렴하고 있다.</p>"},{"id":"62417","en":"Multi-Way Representation Alignment","ko":"다중 경로 Representation Alignment","authors":"Akshit Achara, Tatiana Gaintseva, Matéo Mahaut, Pritish Chakraborty, Viktor Johansson, Melih Barsbey, Emanuele Rodolà, Donato Crisostomi","pos":"#1505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=goFOelWmEG","abs":"The Platonic Representation Hypothesis suggests that independently trained neural networks converge to increasingly similar latent spaces. However, current strategies for mapping these representations are inherently pairwise, scaling quadratically with the number of models and failing to yield a consistent global reference. In this paper, we study the alignment of $M \\ge 3$ models. We first adapt Generalized Procrustes Analysis (GPA) to construct a shared orthogonal universe that preserves the internal geometry essential for tasks like model stitching. We then show that strict isometric alignment is suboptimal for retrieval, where agreement-maximizing methods like Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA) typically prevail. To bridge this gap, we finally propose Geometry-Corrected Procrustes Alignment (GCPA), which establishes a robust GPA-based universe followed by a post-hoc correction for directional mismatch. Extensive experiments demonstrate that GCPA consistently improves any-to-any retrieval while retaining a practical shared reference space.","absKo":"Platonic Representation Hypothesis는 독립적으로 학습된 neural network가 점점 더 유사한 latent space로 수렴한다고 제안한다. 그러나 현재 representation을 매핑하는 전략은 본질적으로 pairwise 방식이라, 모델 수에 따라 quadratic하게 확장되며 일관된 전역 reference를 제공하지 못한다. 본 논문에서는 $M \\ge 3$개의 모델 정렬(alignment)을 연구한다. 우리는 먼저 Generalized Procrustes Analysis (GPA)를 조정하여 model stitching과 같은 작업에 필수적인 내부 기하를 보존하는 공유 orthogonal universe를 구성한다. 이어서 엄밀한 isometric alignment는 retrieval에는 최적이 아님을 보이는데, 이때는 Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA)처럼 agreement를 최대화하는 방법이 보통 더 우수하기 때문이다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 마지막으로 Geometry-Corrected Procrustes Alignment (GCPA)를 제안한다. 이는 견고한 GPA 기반 universe를 구축한 뒤 방향성 mismatch에 대한 사후 보정을 수행한다. 광범위한 실험은 GCPA가 any-to-any retrieval을 일관되게 개선하면서도 실용적인 공유 reference space를 유지함을 보여준다."},{"id":"62946","en":"FloorplanQA: A Benchmark for Spatial Reasoning in LLMs using Structured Representations","ko":"FloorplanQA: 구조화된 표현을 활용한 LLM의 공간 추론 벤치마크","authors":"Fedor Rodionov, Abdelrahman Eldesokey, Michael Birsak, John Femiani, Bernard Ghanem, Peter Wonka","pos":"#2012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bcN12UkftY","abs":"<p>We introduce FloorplanQA, a diagnostic benchmark for evaluating spatial reasoning in large-language models (LLMs). FloorplanQA is grounded in structured representations of indoor scenes (e.g., kitchens, living rooms, bedrooms, bathrooms, and others), encoded symbolically in JSON or XML layouts. The benchmark covers core spatial tasks, including distance measurement, visibility, path finding, and object placement within constrained spaces. Our results across a variety of frontier open-source and commercial LLMs reveal that while models may succeed on shallow queries, they often fail to respect physical constraints and preserve spatial coherence, though they remain mostly robust to small spatial perturbations. FloorplanQA uncovers a blind spot in today’s LLMs: inconsistent reasoning about indoor layouts. We hope this benchmark inspires new work on language models that can accurately infer and manipulate spatial and geometric properties in practical settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 large-language models (LLMs)에서 spatial reasoning을 평가하기 위한 진단용 benchmark인 FloorplanQA를 소개한다. FloorplanQA는 주방, 거실, 침실, 욕실 등 실내 장면의 structured representation에 기반하며, JSON 또는 XML layout으로 symbolically 인코딩된다. 이 benchmark는 거리 측정, 가시성, 경로 탐색, 제한된 공간 내 객체 배치 등 핵심 spatial task를 포함한다. 다양한 최첨단 open-source 및 commercial LLM에 대한 우리의 결과는, 모델이 얕은 질의에는 성공할 수 있지만 물리적 제약을 준수하고 spatial coherence를 유지하는 데는 종종 실패하며, 다만 작은 spatial perturbation에는 대체로 강건함을 보여준다. FloorplanQA는 오늘날 LLM의 blind spot, 즉 실내 layout에 대한 일관성 없는 추론을 드러낸다. 우리는 이 benchmark가 실제 환경에서 spatial 및 geometric property를 정확하게 추론하고 조작할 수 있는 language model 연구를 촉진하길 기대한다.</p>"},{"id":"61736","en":"Revisiting OOD Generalization in Programmatic RL","ko":"Programmatic RL에서 OOD 일반화 재고찰","authors":"Amirhossein Rajabpour, Kiarash Aghakasiri, Sandra Zilles, Levi Lelis","pos":"#214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nLc5wTYX1p","abs":"<p>Programmatic policies are often reported to generalize better than neural policies in reinforcement learning (RL) benchmarks. We revisit some of these claims and show that much of the observed gap arises from uncontrolled experimental factors rather than intrinsic representational reasons. Re-evaluating three core benchmarks used in influential papers---TORCS, Karel, and Parking---we find that neural policies, when trained with a few modifications, such as sparse observations and cautious intrinsic reward functions, can match or exceed the out-of-distribution (OOD) generalization of programmatic policies. We argue that a representation enables OOD generalization if (i) the policy space it induces includes a generalizing policy and (ii) the search algorithm can find it. The neural and programmatic policies in prior work are comparable in OOD generalization because the domain-specific languages used induce policy spaces similar to those of neural networks, and our modifications help the gradient search find generalizing solutions. By disentangling representational factors from experimental confounds, we advance our understanding of what makes a representation succeed or fail at OOD generalization.</p>","absKo":"<p>Programmatic policy는 reinforcement learning(RL) benchmark에서 neural policy보다 더 잘 일반화한다고 자주 보고되어 왔다. 우리는 이러한 주장들을 다시 살펴보고, 관찰된 격차의 상당 부분이 고유한 표현상의 이유라기보다 통제되지 않은 실험 요인에서 비롯됨을 보인다. 영향력 있는 논문들에서 사용된 세 가지 핵심 benchmark---TORCS, Karel, Parking---를 재평가한 결과, 몇 가지 수정, 예를 들어 sparse observation과 신중한 intrinsic reward function을 적용해 학습한 neural policy는 programmatic policy의 out-of-distribution(OOD) generalization과 같거나 이를 능가할 수 있음을 발견했다. 우리는 표현이 OOD generalization을 가능하게 하려면 (i) 그 표현이 유도하는 policy space에 일반화하는 policy가 포함되어 있어야 하고, (ii) search algorithm이 그것을 찾아낼 수 있어야 한다고 주장한다. 기존 연구의 neural policy와 programmatic policy는 OOD generalization 측면에서 비교 가능하다. 이는 사용된 domain-specific language가 neural network와 유사한 policy space를 유도하기 때문이며, 우리의 수정은 gradient search가 일반화하는 해를 찾도록 돕는다. 표현적 요인과 실험적 혼재 요인을 분리함으로써, 우리는 표현이 OOD generalization에서 성공하거나 실패하는 이유에 대한 이해를 한 단계 발전시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"62554","en":"Unveiling And Addressing Dimensional Collapse In Vector Quantization Models Via Codebook Regularization","ko":"코드북 정규화를 통해 Vector Quantization 모델의 차원 붕괴를 드러내고 완화","authors":"Fang Zhang, Yongxin Zhu, Yihao Liu, Bin Fu, Linli Xu","pos":"#305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=faDJYtfjWh","abs":"<p>While recent advancements in Vector Quantization (VQ) models have successfully achieved complete codebook utilization, a critical bottleneck remains largely unexplored: the effective dimensionality of the codebook embedding space. We observe that discrete codebook representations tend to degenerate into low-dimensional subspaces, characterized by significantly lower effective rank than continuous representations during quantization. Through comprehensive spectral analysis, we identify that this dimensional collapse stems from the suppression of low-variance components inherent to the vector quantization process, thereby severely limiting the expressive capacity of VQ models. To mitigate this fundamental issue, we propose a simple yet effective codebook regularization strategy designed to restore low-variance components, effectively bridging the spectral gap between discrete codebook spaces and continuous representations. Extensive experiments demonstrate that this regularization objective is compatible with diverse VQ training paradigms, yielding significant improvements in reconstruction fidelity and downstream performance in autoregressive image generative models.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 Vector Quantization(VQ) model의 발전은 complete codebook utilization을 성공적으로 달성했지만, 중요한 병목은 여전히 거의 탐구되지 않았다. 바로 codebook embedding space의 effective dimensionality이다. 우리는 discrete codebook representation이 quantization 동안 continuous representation보다 유의하게 낮은 effective rank를 가지는 low-dimensional subspace로 퇴화하는 경향이 있음을 관찰한다. 포괄적인 spectral analysis를 통해, 이러한 dimensional collapse는 vector quantization 과정에 내재한 low-variance component의 억제에서 비롯되며, 그 결과 VQ model의 expressive capacity가 심각하게 제한된다는 점을 확인한다. 이 근본적 문제를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 low-variance component를 복원하도록 설계된 간단하지만 효과적인 codebook regularization 전략을 제안한다. 이는 discrete codebook space와 continuous representation 사이의 spectral gap을 효과적으로 메운다. 광범위한 실험은 이 regularization objective가 다양한 VQ training paradigm과 호환되며, autoregressive image generative model에서 reconstruction fidelity와 downstream performance를 크게 개선함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66056","en":"$\\mathbb{R}^{2k}$ is Theoretically Large Enough for Embedding-based Top-$k$ Retrieval","ko":"$\\mathbb{R}^{2k}$는 임베딩 기반 Top-$k$ 검색에 이론적으로 충분히 크다","authors":"Zihao Wang, Hang Yin, Lihui Liu, Hanghang Tong, Yangqiu Song, Ginny Wong, Simon See","pos":"#3607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7Sho2SEu3D","abs":"This paper studies the minimal dimension required to embed subset memberships ($m$ elements and ${m\\choose k}$ subsets of at most $k$ elements) into vector spaces, denoted as Minimal Embeddable Dimension (MED). The tight bounds of MED are derived theoretically and supported empirically for various notions of \"distances\" or \"similarities\", including $\\ell_2$ metric, inner product, and cosine similarity. In addition, we conduct numerical simulation in a more achievable setting, where the ${m\\choose k}$ subset embeddings are chosen as the centroid of the embeddings of the contained elements. Our simulation easily realizes a logarithmic dependency between the MED and the number of elements to embed. These findings imply that embedding-based retrieval limitations stem primarily from learnability challenges, not geometric constraints, guiding future algorithm design."},{"id":"65966","en":"SOTAlign: Semi-Supervised Alignment of Unimodal Vision and Language Models via Optimal Transport","ko":"SOTAlign: 최적 수송을 통한 단일모달 비전 및 언어 모델의 준지도 정렬","authors":"Simon Roschmann, Paul KRZAKALA, Sonia Mazelet, Quentin Bouniot, Zeynep Akata","pos":"#3710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8PMYGcTv3L","abs":"<p>The Platonic Representation Hypothesis posits that neural networks trained on different modalities converge toward a shared statistical model of the world. Recent work exploits this convergence by aligning frozen pretrained vision and language models with lightweight alignment layers, but typically relies on contrastive losses and millions of paired samples. In this work, we ask whether meaningful alignment can be achieved with substantially less supervision. We introduce a semi-supervised setting in which pretrained unimodal encoders are aligned using a small number of image–text pairs together with large amounts of unpaired data. To address this challenge, we propose SOTAlign, a two-stage framework that first recovers a coarse shared geometry from limited paired data using a linear teacher, then refines the alignment on unpaired samples via an optimal-transport-based divergence that transfers relational structure without overconstraining the target space. Unlike existing semi-supervised methods, SOTAlign effectively leverages unpaired images and text, learning robust joint embeddings across datasets and encoder pairs, and significantly outperforming supervised and semi-supervised baselines.</p>"},{"id":"63283","en":"nD-RoPE: A Generalized RoPE for n-Dimensional Position Embedding","ko":"nD-RoPE: n차원 위치 임베딩을 위한 일반화된 RoPE","authors":"Boyang Li, Yulin Wu, Sizhe Xu, Nuoxian Huang, Zhonghang Yuan, Shangyi Guo, Shu Yang, Takahiro Yabe","pos":"#3912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YPXDQkU7XW","abs":"Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE) is widely adopted in Transformer models, yet its extension to high-dimensional domains lacks a unified theoretical formulation. Most existing approaches either apply rotations independently along each axis or mix frequencies empirically, which limits cross-dimensional interactions and yields direction-dependent representations. To address these limitations, we propose *nD-RoPE*, a decomposition-free generalization of rotary embeddings to arbitrary dimensions. From a translation-invariant formulation in continuous Hilbert space, we derive a spectral condition for isotropy that requires treating positions and frequencies as coupled $n$-dimensional vectors. We instantiate this principle with a multi-scale regular simplex wave-vector design that provides uniform directional coverage with maximal symmetry. Experiments across images, videos, and point clouds demonstrate consistent performance gains and improved generalization in high-dimensional settings.","absKo":"Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE)는 Transformer 모델에서 널리 채택되고 있지만, 고차원 도메인으로의 확장은 통일된 이론적 정식화를 결여하고 있다. 기존의 대부분 접근법은 각 축을 따라 회전을 독립적으로 적용하거나 경험적으로 frequency를 혼합하는데, 이는 차원 간 상호작용을 제한하고 방향 의존적인 representation을 초래한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 임의의 차원으로 rotary embedding을 decomposition 없이 일반화한 *nD-RoPE*를 제안한다. 연속 Hilbert space에서의 translation-invariant formulation으로부터, 우리는 position과 frequency를 결합된 $n$차원 vector로 취급해야 하는 isotropy에 대한 spectral condition을 유도한다. 우리는 이 원리를 최대 대칭성과 함께 균일한 방향 커버리지를 제공하는 multi-scale regular simplex wave-vector design으로 구체화한다. 이미지, 비디오, point cloud 전반의 실험은 고차원 설정에서 일관된 성능 향상과 더 나은 generalization을 보여준다."},{"id":"63526","en":"WorldComp2D: Spatio-semantic Representations of Object Identity and Location from Local Views","ko":"WorldComp2D: 국소 시점에서 얻는 객체 정체성과 위치의 시공간-의미 표현","authors":"SeongMin Jin, Doo Seok Jeong","pos":"#3913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WQIyx69dFg","abs":"Learning latent representations that capture both semantic and spatial information is central to efficient spatio-semantic reasoning. However, many existing approaches rely on implicit latent structures combined with dense feature maps or task-specific heads, limiting computational efficiency and flexibility. We propose WorldComp2D, a novel lightweight representation learning framework that explicitly structures latent space geometry according to object identity and spatial proximity using multiscale \\textit{local} receptive fields centered on a given fixation point. This framework consists of (i) a proximity-dependent encoder that maps a given observation into a spatio-semantic latent space and (ii) a localizer that infers the coordinates of objects in the input from the resulting spatio-semantic representation. Using facial landmark localization as a proof-of-concept, we show that WorldComp2D preserves fine-grained spatio-semantic representation of facial landmarks while achieving competitive accuracy at substantially low computational cost. Compared to SoTA lightweight models, WorldComp2D reduces the numbers of parameters and FLOPs by up to $4.0\\times$ and $2.2\\times$, respectively, while maintaining real-time performance on CPU. These results demonstrate that explicitly structured latent spaces provide an efficient and general foundation for spatio-semantic reasoning. This framework is open-sourced at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/WorldComp2D-10F6/.","absKo":"의미론적 정보와 공간 정보를 모두 포착하는 latent representation 학습은 효율적인 spatio-semantic reasoning의 핵심이다. 그러나 기존의 많은 접근은 dense feature map이나 task-specific head와 결합된 암묵적 latent structure에 의존하여 계산 효율성과 유연성이 제한된다. 우리는 주어진 fixation point를 중심으로 하는 다중 스케일 \\textit{local} receptive field를 사용하여, 객체 정체성과 공간적 근접성에 따라 latent space geometry를 명시적으로 구조화하는 새로운 경량 representation learning framework인 WorldComp2D를 제안한다. 이 framework는 (i) 주어진 observation을 spatio-semantic latent space로 매핑하는 proximity-dependent encoder와 (ii) 그 결과 얻어진 spatio-semantic representation으로부터 입력 내 객체의 좌표를 추론하는 localizer로 구성된다. 얼굴 landmark localization을 proof-of-concept으로 사용하여, WorldComp2D가 얼굴 landmark의 세밀한 spatio-semantic representation을 보존하면서도 상당히 낮은 계산 비용으로 경쟁력 있는 정확도를 달성함을 보인다. SoTA 경량 모델과 비교했을 때, WorldComp2D는 parameter 수와 FLOPs를 각각 최대 $4.0\\times$와 $2.2\\times$까지 줄이면서 CPU에서 실시간 성능을 유지한다. 이러한 결과는 명시적으로 구조화된 latent space가 spatio-semantic reasoning을 위한 효율적이고 일반적인 기반을 제공함을 보여준다. 이 framework는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/WorldComp2D-10F6/ 에서 오픈소스로 공개되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"62674","en":"Klein Hyperbolic Metric Learning","ko":"클라인 쌍곡 거리 학습","authors":"Yulin Zhang, Boxuan Hu, Huimin Li, Junlin Hu","pos":"#4000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=eTcQP26TD0","abs":"<p>Hyperbolic metric learning is highly effective in embedding hierarchical data structures. However, past work has predominantly focused on the conformal Poincaré model, leaving other geometries like the Klein model largely under-explored. In addition, the curved geodesics of the Poincaré model present a fundamental geometric misalignment with the linear projections dominating the feature transformation steps in the modern neural network backbones. In this paper, we investigate the Klein model, a projective model of hyperbolic geometry whose straight-line geodesics offer a structurally aligned alternative in linear encoders, for hyperbolic metric learning. By formalizing a framework based on Einstein gyrovector operations, we derive a numerically stable metric learning approach that mitigates the inherent optimization challenges of the Klein model. Extensive experiments on multiple image datasets for fine-grained image classification task show that the Klein model not only serves as a viable alternative to the Poincaré model but also achieves highly competitive performance by leveraging its unique geometric properties, without increasing parameter complexity. Our empirical findings establish the Klein model as an efficient geometric prior for hyperbolic metric learning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Hyperbolic metric learning은 hierarchical data structure를 embedding하는 데 매우 효과적이다. 그러나 기존 연구는 주로 conformal Poincaré model에 집중해 왔고, Klein model과 같은 다른 geometry는 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 또한 Poincaré model의 curved geodesic은 현대 neural network backbone에서 feature transformation 단계의 핵심을 이루는 linear projection과 근본적인 geometric misalignment를 보인다. 이 논문에서는 linear encoder에서 구조적으로 잘 맞는 대안으로서 straight-line geodesic을 가지는 hyperbolic geometry의 projective model인 Klein model을 hyperbolic metric learning에 대해 조사한다. Einstein gyrovector operation을 기반으로 한 framework를 정식화함으로써, 우리는 Klein model이 내재한 optimization challenge를 완화하는 수치적으로 안정적인 metric learning approach를 도출한다. fine-grained image classification task를 위한 여러 image dataset에 대한 광범위한 실험은 Klein model이 Poincaré model의 실현 가능한 대안일 뿐 아니라, parameter complexity를 늘리지 않으면서 고유한 geometric property를 활용해 매우 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 우리의 실증적 결과는 Klein model을 hyperbolic metric learning을 위한 효율적인 geometric prior로 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"61478","en":"No More K-means: Single-Stage Sparse Coding for Efficient Multi-Vector Retrieval","ko":"K-means는 이제 그만: 효율적인 Multi-Vector Retrieval을 위한 Single-Stage Sparse Coding","authors":"Lixuan Guo, Yifei Wang, Tiansheng Wen, Aosong Feng, Stefanie Jegelka, Chenyu You","pos":"#4003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pp1enKGv2v","abs":"<p>Multi-vector retrieval (MVR) models, exemplified by ColBERT, have established new benchmarks in retrieval accuracy by preserving fine-grained token-level interactions. However, this granularity imposes prohibitive storage and retrieval efficiency bottlenecks: to manage the immense memory footprint and computational overhead of billion-scale token vectors, state-of-the-art systems are forced to rely on aggressive dimension reduction and complex clustering (e.g., K-means). This compromise introduces two critical limitations: excessive indexing latency of clustering large-scale corpora and semantic information loss inherent to compression. In this paper, we propose Single-Stage Sparse Retrieval (SSR), a paradigm shift that replaces expensive clustering with efficient sparse coding. Instead of compressing features into low-dimensional dense vectors, we utilize Sparse Autoencoder (SAE) to project token embeddings into a high-dimensional but highly sparse representation. This transformation enables us to bypass vector clustering entirely and leverage inverted indexing for precise, high-throughput retrieval. Extensive experiments on the BEIR benchmark demonstrate that SSR achieves a \"trifecta\" of improvements: it reduces indexing time by 15× compared to ColBERTv2, halves retrieval latency, and simultaneously improves retrieval performance over leading baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multi-vector retrieval (MVR) 모델, 대표적으로 ColBERT는 fine-grained token-level interaction을 보존함으로써 retrieval accuracy에서 새로운 benchmark를 확립해 왔다. 그러나 이러한 세분성은 저장 및 retrieval 효율성에서 감당하기 어려운 병목을 초래한다. billion-scale token vector를 다루기 위해, state-of-the-art 시스템은 공격적인 dimension reduction과 복잡한 clustering(예: K-means)에 의존할 수밖에 없다. 이러한 절충은 두 가지 치명적인 한계를 낳는다. 대규모 코퍼스에 대한 clustering으로 인한 과도한 indexing latency와, compression에 내재된 semantic information loss가 그것이다. 본 논문에서는 비싼 clustering을 효율적인 sparse coding으로 대체하는 패러다임 전환인 Single-Stage Sparse Retrieval (SSR)을 제안한다. feature를 낮은 차원의 dense vector로 압축하는 대신, Sparse Autoencoder (SAE)를 사용하여 token embedding을 high-dimensional이지만 매우 sparse한 representation으로 사상한다. 이 변환을 통해 vector clustering을 완전히 우회하고, inverted indexing을 활용하여 정확하고 high-throughput인 retrieval을 수행할 수 있다. BEIR benchmark에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 SSR이 세 가지 개선을 동시에 달성하는 \"trifecta\"임을 보여준다. ColBERTv2와 비교해 indexing time을 15배 줄이고, retrieval latency를 절반으로 낮추며, 동시에 선도적인 baseline보다 retrieval performance를 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"64643","en":"Normalizing Diffusion Kernels with Optimal Transport","ko":"Optimal Transport를 활용한 Diffusion Kernel 정규화","authors":"Nathan Kessler, Robin Magnet, Jean Feydy","pos":"#4004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LJdacnMXkr","abs":"<p>Smoothing a signal based on local neighborhoods is a core operation in machine learning and geometry processing. On well-structured domains such as vector spaces and manifolds, the Laplace operator derived from differential geometry offers a principled approach to smoothing via heat diffusion, with strong theoretical guarantees. However, constructing such Laplacians requires a carefully defined domain structure, which is not always available. Most practitioners thus rely on simple convolution kernels and message-passing layers, which are biased against the boundaries of the domain.  We bridge this gap by introducing a broad class of smoothing operators, derived from general similarity or adjacency matrices, and demonstrate that they can be normalized into diffusion-like operators that inherit desirable properties from Laplacians. Our approach relies on a symmetric variant of the Sinkhorn algorithm, which rescales positive smoothing operators to match the structural behavior of heat diffusion.  This construction enables Laplacian-like smoothing and processing of irregular data such as point clouds, sparse voxel grids or mixture of Gaussians. We show that the resulting operators not only approximate heat diffusion but also retain spectral information from the Laplacian itself, with applications to shape analysis and matching.</p>","absKo":"<p>local neighborhood를 기반으로 signal을 smoothing하는 것은 machine learning과 geometry processing의 핵심 연산이다. vector space와 manifold 같은 잘 구조화된 domain에서는 differential geometry에서 유도된 Laplace operator가 heat diffusion을 통한 smoothing에 대한 원리적 접근을 제공하며, 강한 이론적 보장을 갖는다. 그러나 이러한 Laplacian을 구성하려면 신중하게 정의된 domain structure가 필요한데, 이는 항상 उपलब्ध하지 않다. 따라서 대부분의 실무자는 단순한 convolution kernel과 message-passing layer에 의존하며, 이는 domain의 boundary에 대해 편향되어 있다. 우리는 일반적인 similarity 또는 adjacency matrix에서 유도된 광범위한 smoothing operator class를 도입하여 이 간극을 메우고, 이들이 Laplacian의 바람직한 성질을 계승하는 diffusion-like operator로 정규화될 수 있음을 보인다. 우리의 접근은 positive smoothing operator를 rescale하여 heat diffusion의 구조적 behavior와 맞추는 symmetric variant의 Sinkhorn algorithm에 기반한다. 이 구성은 point cloud, sparse voxel grid, mixture of Gaussians와 같은 불규칙한 데이터의 Laplacian-like smoothing 및 processing을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 결과 operator가 heat diffusion을 근사할 뿐 아니라 Laplacian 자체의 spectral information도 보존하며, shape analysis와 matching에 응용될 수 있음을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"60663","en":"Physics from Video: Identifiability of Time-Invariant Second-Order ODEs under Minimal Trajectory Conditions","ko":"비디오로부터의 물리: 최소 궤적 조건에서 시간 불변 2차 ODE의 식별 가능성","authors":"Yuanyuan Wang, Wenjie Wang, Kun Zhang, Mingming Gong","pos":"#4005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xrXxqLadvS","abs":"<p>Bridging the gap between visual realism and physical understanding is a core challenge for video-based world models. We study the structural identifiability of continuous-time physical laws from raw pixels, focusing on whether an encoder-only pipeline can uniquely recover the parameters of second-order linear ODEs. We prove that a level-set slope-coverage condition ensures the learned latent space is locally affine to the true physical state, enabling exact parameter recovery. Our theory provides the first characterization of minimal data requirements across damping regimes, establishing that underdamped systems are identifiable from a single video clip, whereas other regimes require three diverse trajectories. We further introduce a variance-floor regularizer to stabilize the decoder-free objective and prevent latent collapse. Validated on synthetic and real-world data, our approach demonstrates that interpretable physical constants can be reliably estimated from video without the need for compute-intensive pixel reconstruction, ensuring both physical correctness and transparency.</p>","absKo":"<p>시각적 사실성과 물리적 이해 사이의 간극을 메우는 것은 video-based world models의 핵심 과제이다. 우리는 raw pixel로부터 연속시간 물리 법칙의 structural identifiability를 연구하며, encoder-only pipeline이 second-order linear ODE의 parameter를 유일하게 복원할 수 있는지에 초점을 맞춘다. 우리는 level-set slope-coverage 조건이 학습된 latent space가 true physical state에 대해 locally affine하도록 보장하며, 이를 통해 정확한 parameter recovery가 가능함을 증명한다. 우리의 이론은 damping regime 전반에서 최소 데이터 요구량에 대한 최초의 characterization을 제공하며, underdamped system은 단일 video clip만으로 식별 가능하지만, 그 밖의 regime은 서로 다른 세 trajectory가 필요함을 확립한다. 또한 우리는 decoder-free objective를 안정화하고 latent collapse를 방지하기 위해 variance-floor regularizer를 도입한다. synthetic 및 real-world data에서 검증한 결과, 우리의 접근법은 compute-intensive pixel reconstruction 없이도 해석 가능한 물리 상수를 video로부터 신뢰성 있게 추정할 수 있음을 보여주며, 물리적 정확성과 투명성을 모두 보장한다.</p>"},{"id":"62535","en":"Privacy-Aware Video Anomaly Detection: Guided Orthogonal Projection and a Comprehensive Evaluation Framework","ko":"프라이버시 인지 Video Anomaly Detection: Guided Orthogonal Projection 및 포괄적 평가 프레임워크","authors":"Wenxiang Diao, Lei Wang, Andrew Busch, Jun Zhou, Yongsheng Gao","pos":"#4006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fjUUmUCy9m","abs":"<p>Video anomaly detection (VAD) is critical for surveillance systems, but current methods prioritize accuracy while ignoring the ethical risks of encoding sensitive biometric information. This neglect poses significant privacy concerns for real-world deployment. To bridge this gap, we introduce the Guided Orthogonal Projection Layer (G-OPL), a lightweight module designed to geometrically decouple and suppress sensitive attributes from latent features to produce representations focused on anomaly-relevant cues. We specifically target facial information as the primary sensitive attribute. Unlike gait or body pose, faces act as unique biometric identifiers that are tightly regulated and pose immediate risks of misuse, yet are rarely necessary for identifying abnormal behaviors. To achieve this, G-OPL utilizes a stable, QR-decomposition-based orthogonal projection mechanism guided by weak supervision (e.g., face presence) to actively filter privacy-sensitive subspaces while preserving task-relevant anomalies. we further propose a novel privacy-aware evaluation framework to rigorously quantify the trade-off between model utility and ethical alignment. Our analysis uncovers how projection layers filter sensitive information, why this improves transparency, and under what conditions ethical design also enhances robustness. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our approach effectively minimizes privacy risks without compromising anomaly detection performance, offering a principled path toward trustworthy video analysis.</p>","absKo":"<p>Video anomaly detection (VAD)은 surveillance system에서 매우 중요하지만, 현재 방법들은 정확도에만 집중하고 민감한 biometric information을 인코딩하는 윤리적 위험은 간과한다. 이러한 간과는 실제 배포에서 중대한 privacy concerns를 초래한다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 Guided Orthogonal Projection Layer (G-OPL)를 제안한다. 이는 latent feature에서 민감한 속성을 기하학적으로 분리하고 억제하여 anomaly-relevant cue에 집중한 representation을 생성하도록 설계된 경량 모듈이다. 우리는 특히 facial information을 주요 민감 속성으로 다룬다. gait나 body pose와 달리 face는 고유한 biometric identifier로서 엄격하게 규제되며 오용의 즉각적인 위험을 지니지만, 비정상 행동을 식별하는 데는 대체로 필요하지 않다. 이를 달성하기 위해 G-OPL은 weak supervision(예: face presence)에 의해 guided되는, 안정적인 QR decomposition 기반 orthogonal projection mechanism을 활용하여 task-relevant anomaly는 보존하면서 privacy-sensitive subspace를 적극적으로 필터링한다. 또한 우리는 model utility와 ethical alignment 사이의 trade-off를 엄밀하게 정량화하기 위한 새로운 privacy-aware evaluation framework를 제안한다. 우리의 분석은 projection layer가 민감한 정보를 어떻게 필터링하는지, 왜 이것이 transparency를 향상시키는지, 그리고 어떤 조건에서 윤리적 설계가 robustness도 함께 높이는지를 밝혀낸다. 대규모 실험은 우리의 접근법이 anomaly detection 성능을 저하시키지 않으면서 privacy risk를 효과적으로 최소화함을 보여 주며, 신뢰할 수 있는 video analysis를 향한 원리적인 경로를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"66772","en":"Relevance-Based Embeddings: Lightweight Candidate Selection via Heavy Ranker Calls","ko":"Relevance 기반 임베딩: Heavy Ranker 호출을 통한 경량 후보 선택","authors":"Kirill Shevkunov, Andrey Ploskonosov, Liudmila Prokhorenkova","pos":"#4007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0RNjyGzTSJ","abs":"<p>In many machine learning applications, the most relevant items for a query should be efficiently extracted. The relevance function is usually an expensive similarity model making the exhaustive search infeasible. A typical solution is to train another model that separately embeds queries and items to a vector space, where similarity is defined via the dot product or cosine similarity. This allows one to search the relevant items through fast approximate nearest neighbors search at the cost of some reduction in quality. To compensate for this reduction, the found items (candidates) are re-ranked by the expensive ranking model. In this paper, we investigate an alternative approach to candidate selection that utilizes the scores of the expensive model to improve the representations of queries and items. The idea is to describe each query (item) by its relevance for a set of support items (queries) and use these new representations to obtain query (item) embeddings. We theoretically prove that such embeddings are powerful enough to approximate any complex similarity model (under mild conditions). We also investigate the choice of support items, which is a crucial ingredient of the proposed approach. The experiments on diverse academic and production datasets illustrate the power of our method.</p>"},{"id":"65507","en":"Representation Unlearning: Forgetting through Information Compression","ko":"Representation Unlearning: 정보 압축을 통한 망각","authors":"Antonio Almudévar, Alfonso Ortega","pos":"#4008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CwjK5eUzcI","abs":"<p>Machine unlearning seeks to remove the influence of specific training data from a model, a need driven by privacy regulations and robustness concerns. Existing approaches typically modify model parameters, but such updates can be unstable, computationally costly, and limited by local approximations. We introduce Representation Unlearning, a framework that performs unlearning directly in the model’s representation space. Instead of modifying model parameters, we learn a transformation over representations that imposes an information bottleneck: maximizing mutual information with retained data while suppressing information about data to be forgotten. We derive variational surrogates that make this objective tractable and show how they can be instantiated in two practical regimes: when both retain and forget data are available, and in a zero-shot setting where only forget data can be accessed. Experiments across several benchmarks demonstrate that Representation Unlearning achieves more reliable forgetting, better utility retention, and greater computational efficiency than parameter-centric baselines.</p>"},{"id":"62797","en":"Robust Multi-View Fusion via Prototype-Anchored Unbalanced Optimal Transport","ko":"Prototype-Anchored Unbalanced Optimal Transport 기반 견고한 Multi-View Fusion","authors":"Han Zhang, Xingwen Zhao, HUI LI","pos":"#4009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=d9obyVpqAu","abs":"<p>Multi-view classifiers typically fuse all observed views into a single representation, which becomes fragile when some views are missing or corrupted.We propose a prototype-anchored fusion module based on an entropically regularized unbalanced optimal transport (UOT) barycenter.Each view is summarized into a small set of learned atoms and is matched to a shared prototype support; fusion outputs a probability measure over prototypes with fixed dimension.By relaxing marginal constraints with a generalized KL penalty, the UOT objective can leave a fraction of view mass unmatched when matching is geometrically costly, yielding a simple differentiable trimming mechanism without hand-tuned thresholds.We provide a basic theoretical result showing that discarding an arbitrary subset of atom mass incurs a penalty bounded by its total mass, independent of transport distances.Experiments on multi-view action recognition benchmarks under simulated missing views, missing-rate shift, and feature-space corruption demonstrate consistently improved stability under severe missingness with modest overhead on top of strong backbones.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multi-view classifier는 일반적으로 관측된 모든 view를 하나의 representation으로 융합하지만, 일부 view가 누락되거나 손상되면 이 representation은 쉽게 취약해집니다. 우리는 entropically regularized unbalanced optimal transport (UOT) barycenter를 기반으로 한 prototype-anchored fusion module을 제안합니다. 각 view는 소수의 learned atom으로 요약되고 shared prototype support와 매칭되며, fusion은 고정 차원의 prototype에 대한 probability measure를 출력합니다. generalized KL penalty로 marginal constraint를 완화함으로써, UOT objective는 matching 비용이 기하적으로 클 때 view mass의 일부를 unmatched로 둘 수 있어, 손으로 조정한 threshold 없이도 간단하고 differentiable한 trimming mechanism을 제공합니다. 우리는 atom mass의 임의의 부분집합을 버릴 때 발생하는 penalty가 transport distance와 무관하게 그 총 mass에 의해 상계된다는 기본 이론 결과를 제시합니다. 시뮬레이션된 missing view, missing-rate shift, feature-space corruption 하의 multi-view action recognition benchmark 실험에서, 강력한 backbone 위에 modest한 overhead만 추가하면서도 심한 missingness에 대해 일관되게 향상된 stability를 보였습니다.</p>"},{"id":"65177","en":"Scalable and Interpretable Representation Alignment with Ordinal Similarity","ko":"순서형 유사도를 이용한 확장 가능하고 해석 가능한 표현 정렬","authors":"Diogo Soares, Pankhil Gawade, Andrea Dittadi, Ewa Szczurek","pos":"#4010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=G4D0YzzZEk","abs":"<p>Evaluating representation similarity is fundamental to representation learning. However, existing metrics suffer from significant limitations: they are difficult to interpret due to shifting baselines, lack robustness to outliers, and are frequently computationally intractable for large datasets, forcing a reliance on heuristic approximations. To address these shortcomings, we develop an ordinal-similarity framework, instantiated by the Triplet (TSI) and Quadruplet (QSI) Similarity Indices, which measure alignment by quantifying the consistency of ordinal relationships. We provide a theoretical analysis demonstrating that this formulation is inherently interpretable, robust to outliers, and computationally efficient. Finally, we establish a formal equivalence between TSI alignment and the alignment of local neighborhood structures, as measured by Mutual Nearest Neighbors. Through empirical analysis, we validate these properties and show that ordinal similarity offers a scalable, practical approach to measuring alignment, enabling practitioners to better understand and design representations.</p>","absKo":"<p>representation similarity를 평가하는 것은 representation learning의 기본이다. 그러나 기존 metric은 심각한 한계를 가진다. 기준선이 이동하기 때문에 해석이 어렵고, outlier에 대한 견고성이 부족하며, 대규모 데이터셋에서는 계산적으로 다루기 어려워 휴리스틱 근사에 의존할 수밖에 없다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 ordinal relationship의 일관성을 정량화하여 alignment를 측정하는 Triplet (TSI) 및 Quadruplet (QSI) Similarity Index로 구체화되는 ordinal-similarity framework를 개발한다. 우리는 이 formulation이 본질적으로 해석 가능하고, outlier에 견고하며, 계산적으로 효율적임을 보이는 이론적 분석을 제시한다. 마지막으로, TSI alignment와 Mutual Nearest Neighbors로 측정한 local neighborhood structure의 alignment 사이에 형식적 동치가 성립함을 확립한다. 실증 분석을 통해 이러한 성질을 검증하고, ordinal similarity가 alignment를 측정하는 확장 가능하고 실용적인 접근법을 제공하여, 실무자가 representation을 더 잘 이해하고 설계할 수 있게 함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65163","en":"Unsupervised Disentanglement Without Compromises : How Functional Orthogonality Enforces Identifiability","ko":"타협 없는 비지도 분리 표현: 기능적 직교성이 식별 가능성을 강제하는 방식","authors":"Mathieu Simon, Pascal Frossard, Christophe De Vleeschouwer","pos":"#4012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GDDYhRWpG4","abs":"<p>This paper explores unsupervised disentangled representation learning from a functional perspective. We define latent concepts as factors that influence observations through locally orthogonal directions, formalized as an orthogonality constraint on the Jacobian of the generative mapping. We prove that this condition yields identifiability of general nonlinear generative models, without requiring statistical independence or causal assumptions, provided the latent domain admits all combinations of factor values. Experiments with orthogonality-regularized normalizing flows empirically confirm the theory, demonstrate reliable recovery of ground-truth factors, and shed light on the success of VAEs. These findings challenge the prevailing impossibility claims for unsupervised disentanglement and provide a principled alternative foundation.</p>","absKo":"<p>이 논문은 functional 관점에서 비지도 disentangled representation learning을 탐구한다. 우리는 latent concept를 국소적으로 orthogonal한 방향을 통해 관측에 영향을 주는 factor로 정의하고, 이를 generative mapping의 Jacobian에 대한 orthogonality constraint로 형식화한다. 우리는 이 조건이 latent domain이 factor value의 모든 조합을 허용한다는 전제하에, statistical independence나 causal assumption 없이도 일반적인 nonlinear generative model의 identifiability를 보장함을 증명한다. Orthogonality로 regularization한 normalizing flow를 사용한 실험은 이 이론을 실증적으로 확인하고, ground-truth factor의 신뢰할 수 있는 복원을 보여주며, VAE의 성공 원리를 조명한다. 이러한 결과는 비지도 disentanglement에 대한 기존의 불가능성 주장에 도전하며, 원리적인 대안적 기반을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"60810","en":"Vector Linking via Cross-Model Local Isometric Consistency","ko":"Cross-Model 국소 등거리 일관성을 통한 벡터 연결","authors":"Ziying Chen, Yang Cao, He Sun, Beining Yang, Tianjian Yang","pos":"#4014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wSV1sGTCN0","abs":"<p>We study Vector Linking: given two embedding clouds produced by different black-box encoders over partially overlapping datasets, recover cross-model object correspondences using only vectors. Empirically and theoretically, we show that independently trained contrastive encoders exhibit local geometric consistency: short-range distances are approximately preserved up to a scale factor, while long-range distances are not due to model-specific distortion.  Building on this, we propose an iterative, reference-based geometric embedding hashing that recovers vector links from a tiny seed set of paired anchors. It represents each vector by distances to sampled paired anchors, proposes candidate links via hash-space matching, and aggregates evidence across views in a Beta--Bernoulli posterior to bootstrap high-confidence links as new anchors. Experiments across multiple benchmarks and embedding model pairs demonstrate accurate and robust linking under varying overlap, seed budgets, and out-of-domain references, with applications to vector database integration and cross-model clustering.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 Vector Linking을 연구한다. 이는 부분적으로 겹치는 dataset 위에서 서로 다른 black-box encoder가 생성한 두 embedding cloud가 주어졌을 때, vector만을 사용해 cross-model object correspondence를 복원하는 문제이다. 실험적으로 그리고 이론적으로, 독립적으로 학습된 contrastive encoder가 local geometric consistency를 보인다는 점을 보인다. 즉, 단거리 distance는 scale factor까지는 거의 보존되지만, 장거리 distance는 model-specific distortion 때문에 그렇지 않다. 이를 바탕으로, 우리는 아주 작은 paired anchor seed set으로부터 vector link를 복원하는 iterative reference-based geometric embedding hashing을 제안한다. 이 방법은 각 vector를 샘플링된 paired anchor까지의 distance로 표현하고, hash space matching을 통해 후보 link를 제안하며, Beta--Bernoulli posterior에서 view 전반의 evidence를 집계해 새로운 anchor로 높은 신뢰도의 link를 부트스트랩한다. 여러 benchmark와 embedding model pair에 대한 실험은 다양한 overlap, seed budget, out-of-domain reference 조건에서 정확하고 강건한 linking을 보여주며, vector database integration과 cross-model clustering에의 응용 가능성도 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61375","en":"GeoFlow: Geo-Aware Modeling of Inter-Area Relationships in OD Flow Prediction and Generation","ko":"GeoFlow: OD Flow 예측 및 생성을 위한 지역 간 관계의 Geo-Aware Modeling","authors":"Zherui Huang, Guanjie Zheng, Hao Xue, Linghe Kong","pos":"#402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qsPISbO6ri","abs":"<p>Origin–destination (OD) flow modeling underpins urban planning and mobility analysis, but prevailing graph-based methods often neglect salient geographic attributes, limiting their ability to model long-range and multi-area dependencies. In this paper, we introduce GeoFlow, a novel framework that (i) augments area representations with geospatial attributes, including relative positions,  -hop and geodesic distances, (ii) employs a specialized geometric-intrinsic fusion encoder design that combines graph attention for intrinsic area signals with coordinate-aware encoders for global structure, and (iii) adopts an axial-global attention decoder to capture OD-specific competitive dependencies. For OD flow generation, GeoFlow is paired with flow matching models to produce more authentic and diverse mobility samples. Empirically, GeoFlow achieves superior performance in predictive accuracy, while substantially improving generative fidelity and diversity. Ablation and analytical studies confirm the contribution of each component.</p>","absKo":"<p>Origin–destination (OD) flow modeling은 도시 계획과 mobility analysis의 기반이 되지만, 기존의 graph-based 방법들은 핵심적인 geographic attribute를 간과하는 경우가 많아 장거리 및 다지역 의존성을 모델링하는 능력이 제한된다. 본 논문에서는 (i) 상대적 위치,  -hop 거리 및 geodesic distance를 포함한 geospatial attribute로 area representation을 강화하고, (ii) intrinsic area signal을 위한 graph attention과 global structure를 위한 coordinate-aware encoder를 결합한 특수한 geometric-intrinsic fusion encoder 설계를 사용하며, (iii) OD-specific competitive dependency를 포착하기 위해 axial-global attention decoder를 채택하는 새로운 프레임워크 GeoFlow를 제안한다. OD flow 생성을 위해 GeoFlow는 flow matching model과 결합되어 보다 진짜 같고 다양한 mobility sample을 생성한다. 실증적으로, GeoFlow는 예측 정확도에서 우수한 성능을 달성하는 동시에 생성 fidelity와 diversity를 현저히 향상시킨다. Ablation 및 분석 연구는 각 구성 요소의 기여를 확인해 준다.</p>"},{"id":"63828","en":"Text Has Curvature","ko":"텍스트에는 곡률이 있다","authors":"Karish Grover, Hanqing Zeng, Yinglong Xia, Christos Faloutsos, Geoff Gordon","pos":"#406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TLrE49BPC4","abs":"<p>Does text have an intrinsic curvature? Language is increasingly modeled in curved geometries—hyperbolic spaces for hierarchy, mixed-curvature manifolds for compositional structure—yet a basic scientific question remains unresolved: what does curvature mean for text itself, in a way that is native to language rather than an artifact of the embedding space we choose? We argue that text does indeed have curvature, and show how to detect it, define it, and use it. To this end, we propose Texture, a text-native, word-level discrete curvature signal, and make three contributions. (a) Existence: We provide empirical and theoretical certificates that semantic inference in natural corpora is non-flat, i.e. language has inherent curvature. (b) Definition: We define Texture by reconciling left- and right-context beliefs around a masked word through a Schrödinger bridge, yielding a curvature field that is positive where context focuses meaning and negative where it fans out into competing continuations. (c) Utility: Texture is actionable: it serves as a general-purpose measurement and control primitive enabling geometry without geometric training; we instantiate it on two representative tasks, improving long-context inference through curvature-guided compression and retrieval-augmented generation through curvature-guided routing. Together, our results establish a text-native curvature paradigm, making curvature measurable and practically useful.</p>","absKo":"<p>텍스트는 내재적 curvature를 가지는가? 언어는 점점 더 curved geometry로 모델링되고 있다. hierarchy를 위한 hyperbolic space, compositional structure를 위한 mixed-curvature manifold가 그 예다. 그러나 기본적인 과학적 질문은 아직 해결되지 않았다. 즉, embedding space의 산물이 아니라 언어 자체에 고유한 방식으로, 텍스트에 대한 curvature는 무엇을 의미하는가? 우리는 텍스트가 실제로 curvature를 가진다고 주장하며, 이를 어떻게 탐지하고 정의하며 활용할 수 있는지 보인다. 이를 위해 우리는 Texture를 제안한다. 이는 text-native한 word-level discrete curvature signal이며, 세 가지 기여를 제시한다. (a) 존재성: 우리는 자연 코퍼스에서의 semantic inference가 flat하지 않다는 것, 즉 언어가 내재적 curvature를 가진다는 경험적 및 이론적 증명을 제시한다. (b) 정의: 우리는 masked word 주변의 left-context belief와 right-context belief를 Schrödinger bridge를 통해 조화시켜 Texture를 정의하며, 그 결과 context가 의미를 집중시킬 때는 positive, competing continuation으로 퍼질 때는 negative인 curvature field를 얻는다. (c) 유용성: Texture는 실행 가능하다. 이는 geometry without geometric training을 가능하게 하는 범용 측정 및 제어 primitive로서 작동한다. 우리는 이를 두 가지 대표 task에 적용하여, curvature-guided compression을 통한 long-context inference와 curvature-guided routing을 통한 retrieval-augmented generation을 개선한다. 종합하면, 우리의 결과는 text-native curvature paradigm을 확립하며, curvature를 측정 가능하고 실질적으로 유용한 대상으로 만든다.</p>"},{"id":"66399","en":"Independent Component Discovery in Temporal Count Data","ko":"시간적 계수 데이터에서의 독립 성분 발견","authors":"Alexandre Chaussard, Anna Bonnet, Sylvain Le Corff","pos":"#4100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=46FG6Y9MuF","abs":"<p>Advances in data collection are producing growing volumes of temporal count observations, making adapted modeling increasingly necessary. In this work, we introduce a generative framework for independent component analysis of temporal count data, combining regime-adaptive dynamics with Poisson log-normal emissions. The model identifies disentangled components with regime-dependent contributions, enabling representation learning and perturbations analysis. Notably, we establish the identifiability of the model, supporting principled interpretation. To learn the parameters, we propose an efficient amortized variational inference procedure. Experiments on simulated data evaluate recovery of the mixing function and latent sources across diverse settings, while an <em>in vivo</em> longitudinal gut microbiome study reveals microbial co-variation patterns and regime shifts consistent with clinical perturbations.</p>"},{"id":"66261","en":"Geodesic Calculus on Implicitly Defined Latent Manifolds","ko":"암묵적으로 정의된 잠재 다양체 상의 측지 미적분","authors":"Florine Hartwig, Josua Sassen, Juliane Braunsmann, Martin Rumpf, Benedikt Wirth","pos":"#4102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5LBH6azyBM","abs":"<p>Latent manifolds of autoencoders provide low-dimensional representations of data, which can be studied from a geometric perspective. We propose to describe these latent manifolds as implicit submanifolds of some ambient latent space. Based on this, we develop tools for a discrete Riemannian calculus approximating classical geometric operators. These tools are robust against inaccuracies of the implicit representation often occurring in practical examples. To obtain a suitable implicit representation, we propose to learn an approximate projection onto the latent manifold by minimizing a denoising objective. This approach is independent of the underlying autoencoder and supports the use of different Riemannian geometries on the latent manifolds. The framework in particular enables the computation of geodesic paths connecting given end points and shooting geodesics via the Riemannian exponential maps on latent manifolds. We evaluate our approach on various autoencoders trained on synthetic and real data.</p>"},{"id":"65721","en":"From Content to Knowledge: Lightning Fast Long-Video Understanding with Neural Knowledge Representations","ko":"콘텐츠에서 지식으로: 신경 지식 표현을 통한 초고속 장편 영상 이해","authors":"Yuchen Guan, Xiao Li, Zongyu Guo, Xiaoyi Zhang, Xiulian Peng, Chun Yuan, Yan Lu","pos":"#4103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Apmd6IStO6","abs":"<p>We propose a new paradigm for long video understanding by treating a long video as a Neural Knowledge Representation (NKR). NKR represent video contents neither as a stream of tokens or pre-organized databases, but as an individual small portion of network weights attached to the VLM backbone. The NKR weights is optimized to encapsulate the video's semantic content via a novel Agentic Knowledge Distillation (AKD) process, where an agent automatically synthesizes dense descriptions and question-answer pairs to distill the video's knowledge into the NKR. While AKD serves as a comprehensive, one-time encoding phase, the resulting NKR transforms the video into a portable, reusable asset. At inference, the lightweight NKR is mounted onto a frozen Vision-Language Model (VLM), enabling direct, query-based understanding without reloading or re-encoding the the original video. This approach decouples video length from inference cost, offering high amortized efficiency for multi-turn video understanding. Experiments on the LVBench benchmark show our method achieves performance comparable to state-of-the-art approaches while reducing end-to-end latency by over two orders of magnitude, opening new possibilities for interactive long-video understanding.</p>"},{"id":"61309","en":"Contrastive Order Learning: A General Framework for Ordinal Regression","ko":"Contrastive Order Learning: 순서형 회귀를 위한 일반 프레임워크","authors":"Chaewon Lee, BeomJun Shim, Kwang Choi, Chang-Su Kim","pos":"#4105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rUtcXHYnrN","abs":"<p>We propose contrastive order learning (ConOrd), a contrastive learning framework for ordinal regression that integrates the strengths of contrastive learning and order learning. While contrastive learning effectively leverages all samples in a batch, it typically ignores the inherent ordering among rank labels. Conversely, order learning explicitly models label ordinality but often relies on local, margin-based comparisons, limiting its ability to capture global ordinal structure. ConOrd addresses these limitations by introducing a contrastive order loss with soft affinity and disparity weights based on rank differences, enabling fine-grained modeling of ordinal relationships across all sample pairs within a batch. Extensive experiments on a range of ordinal regression tasks, including facial age estimation, blind image quality assessment, and blind video quality assessment, demonstrate that ConOrd consistently achieves state-of-the-art performance and generalizes well across diverse ordinal regression scenarios.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 contrastive learning과 order learning의 장점을 통합한 ordinal regression을 위한 contrastive learning framework, contrastive order learning (ConOrd)를 제안한다. Contrastive learning은 batch 내 모든 sample을 효과적으로 활용하지만, rank label 사이의 본질적인 ordering을 대체로 무시한다. 반대로 order learning은 label의 ordinality를 명시적으로 모델링하지만, 종종 local한 margin-based comparison에 의존하여 global ordinal structure를 포착하는 능력이 제한된다. ConOrd는 rank difference를 기반으로 한 soft affinity와 disparity weight를 갖는 contrastive order loss를 도입함으로써 이러한 한계를 해결하며, batch 내 모든 sample pair에 걸쳐 ordinal relationship을 세밀하게 모델링할 수 있게 한다. 얼굴 나이 추정, blind image quality assessment, blind video quality assessment를 포함한 다양한 ordinal regression task에 대한 광범위한 실험은 ConOrd가 일관되게 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하고, 다양한 ordinal regression 시나리오 전반에서 잘 일반화됨을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63639","en":"An Asymmetric Latent Factorization-of-Tensors Model for Relation Extraction","ko":"관계 추출을 위한 비대칭 잠재 factorization-of-tensors 모델","authors":"Weiling Li, Zhaoheng Shi, Jiajia Mi, Zhigang Liu, Jialiang Wang, Xin Luo","pos":"#4106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=V8wAYkYPZ1","abs":"<p>Latent Factorization-of-Tensors (LFT) models are an effective approach for relation extraction. Existing LFT models assume each mode of the target tensor corresponds to a entity set and the relationships between entity sets are bipartite graphs to explore the relationships among entities within a mode. However, when the topological structure of entities in a mode is known, for example, entities are ordered physical quantities, such as time or coordinates, the relation between such modes forms a more complicated system, i.e., aligned bipartite networks, and existing LFT models cannot accurately capture this structure. This work is the first to recognize and analyze this issue, and proposes an Asymmetric Latent Factorization-of-Tensors (ALFT) model to address it. ALFT can understand aligned bipartite networks in mode pairs of a tensor by imposing constraints between particular mode pairs in the tensor network. Experimental results on real-world datasets demonstrate the existence of this issue and confirm that the proposed ALFT model can effectively resolve it.</p>","absKo":"<p>Latent Factorization-of-Tensors(LFT) 모델은 relation extraction을 위한 효과적인 접근법이다. 기존 LFT 모델은 target tensor의 각 mode가 하나의 entity set에 대응하고, entity set 간의 관계는 mode 내부 entity들 사이의 관계를 탐색하기 위한 bipartite graph라고 가정한다. 그러나 mode 내 entity의 topological structure가 알려져 있는 경우, 예를 들어 entity가 시간이나 좌표처럼 순서가 있는 물리량이라면, 이러한 mode 간 관계는 더 복잡한 시스템, 즉 aligned bipartite networks를 이룬다. 기존 LFT 모델은 이 구조를 정확히 포착하지 못한다. 본 연구는 이 문제를 처음으로 인식하고 분석하며, 이를 해결하기 위해 Asymmetric Latent Factorization-of-Tensors(ALFT) 모델을 제안한다. ALFT는 tensor network에서 특정 mode 쌍 사이에 제약을 부과함으로써 tensor의 mode pair에서 aligned bipartite networks를 이해할 수 있다. 실제 데이터셋에서의 실험 결과는 이 문제의 존재를 입증하고, 제안한 ALFT 모델이 이를 효과적으로 해결할 수 있음을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"61453","en":"Tree-Structured Orthonormal Decomposition of the Aitchison Simplex","ko":"Aitchison Simplex의 트리 구조 Orthonormal Decomposition","authors":"Daisuke Yamada, Qijun Zhang, Travis Pence, Barbara Bendlin, Federico Rey, Vikas Singh","pos":"#4108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pws8t4kBP4","abs":"<p>Compositional data---vectors encoding relative proportions---arise across scientific domains, including ecology, geochemistry, and genomics. The features in these data often come with known hierarchical structure (e.g., taxonomies, phylogenies, ontologies), yet existing methods either ignore this structure, discard the intrinsic Aitchison geometry, require assumptions such as binary trees, or yield incomplete coordinate systems. We describe <em>PolyILR</em>, a canonical orthonormal decomposition of the Aitchison tangent space aligned with any tree topology. Our construction defines a weighted local geometry at each internal node capturing full branching structure, then lifts these to a global orthonormal basis where every coordinate corresponds to a specific tree location. On microbiome and single-cell benchmarks, PolyILR yields stable, interpretable features and enables inference at multiscale tree resolution. We also establish a novel theoretical connection to softmax classifiers, suggesting possible applications to probabilistic modeling.</p>","absKo":"<p>Compositional data---상대적 비율을 인코딩하는 vector---는 ecology, geochemistry, genomics를 포함한 다양한 과학 분야에서 나타난다. 이 데이터의 feature는 종종 알려진 hierarchical structure(예: taxonomy, phylogeny, ontology)를 동반하지만, 기존 방법들은 이 구조를 무시하거나, intrinsic Aitchison geometry를 버리거나, binary tree와 같은 가정을 요구하거나, 불완전한 coordinate system을 산출한다. 우리는 어떤 tree topology와도 정렬되는 Aitchison tangent space의 canonical orthonormal decomposition인 <em>PolyILR</em>를 설명한다. 우리의 구성은 각 internal node에서 전체 branching structure를 포착하는 weighted local geometry를 정의한 뒤, 이를 전역 orthonormal basis로 끌어올려 모든 coordinate가 특정 tree location에 대응되도록 한다. microbiome과 single-cell benchmark에서 PolyILR은 안정적이고 해석 가능한 feature를 제공하며, multiscale tree resolution에서의 추론을 가능하게 한다. 또한 softmax classifier와의 새로운 이론적 연결을 확립하여, probabilistic modeling에 대한 응용 가능성을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"66620","en":"LOTTERY: Learning from Reference-Only Samples in Two-Sample Testing under Size Asymmetry","ko":"LOTTERY: 크기 비대칭 하의 이표본 검정에서 참조 전용 표본으로부터 학습","authors":"Xunye Tian, Zhijian Zhou, Liuhua Peng, Feng Liu","pos":"#4213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=25isTm0XyI","abs":"<p>Data-adaptive two-sample testing assesses if two samples come from the same distribution, using a discrepancy learned from the data (e.g., via kernel-based feature representations). Such methods typically rely on data splitting to decouple learning from testing and control type I error. However, this paradigm is ill-suited to few-shot settings with severe sample-size imbalance: abundant reference samples are available, while only a handful of query samples arrive. In this paper, we show how this imbalance can be leveraged constructively. Using abundant reference data, we learn reference-dependent representations that summarize salient structure of the reference distribution and provide informative signals for detecting departures. We incorporate a collection of representation families that capture both global and local structure, and adaptively weight them using only reference samples via an uncertainty-guided principle. Theoretically, we establish permutation-based type I error control and show consistency of the aggregated test: as the sample sizes grow, the test power converges to one whenever the representation set contains at least one consistent representation. Empirically, our aggregation achieves strong performance across a range of benchmarks while retaining type I error control.</p>"},{"id":"63432","en":"Procedural Pretraining: Warming Up Language Models with Abstract Data","ko":"절차적 사전학습: 추상 데이터로 언어 모델 준비하기","authors":"Liangze Jiang, Zachary Shinnick, Anton Hengel, Hemanth Saratchandran, Damien Teney","pos":"#1706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XFTTezxLdU","abs":"<p>Pretraining directly on web-scale corpora is the de facto paradigm for building language models. We study an alternative setting where the model is initially exposed to abstract structured data, as a means to ease the subsequent acquisition of rich semantic knowledge, much like humans learn simple logic and mathematics before higher reasoning. We specifically focus on <em>procedural data</em>, generated by formal languages and other simple algorithms, as such abstract data.  We first  diagnose the algorithmic skills that different forms of procedural data can improve, often significantly. For example, on context recall (Needle-in-a-haystack), the accuracy jumps from 10 to 98% when pretraining on Dyck sequences (balanced brackets). Second, we study how these gains are reflected in pretraining larger models (up to 1.3B). We find that front-loading as little as 0.1% procedural data significantly outperforms standard pretraining on natural language, code, and informal mathematics (C4, CodeParrot, and DeepMind-Math datasets). Notably, this <em>procedural pretraining</em> enables the models to reach the same loss value with only 55, 67, 86% of the original data. Third, we explore the mechanisms behind and find that procedural pretraining instils non-trivial structure in both attention and MLP layers.  The former is particularly important for structured domains (e.g. code), and the latter for language. Finally, we lay a path for combining multiple forms of procedural data.  Our results show that procedural pretraining is a simple, lightweight means to improving performance and accelerating language model pretraining, ultimately suggesting the promise of disentangling knowledge acquisition from reasoning in LLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>웹 규모 코퍼스에 직접 pretraining하는 것은 language model을 구축하는 사실상의 표준 패러다임이다. 우리는 그 대안으로, 인간이 더 높은 수준의 추론에 앞서 단순한 논리와 수학을 배우듯이, 이후의 풍부한 semantic knowledge 습득을 쉽게 만들기 위해 모델을 처음부터 추상적 구조화 데이터에 노출하는 설정을 연구한다. 우리는 이러한 추상적 데이터로서 formal language와 다른 단순 알고리즘이 생성하는 <em>procedural data</em>에 특히 주목한다. 먼저, 서로 다른 형태의 procedural data가 개선할 수 있는 algorithmic skill을 진단했으며, 그 향상은 종종 매우 컸다. 예를 들어, context recall(Needle-in-a-haystack)에서는 Dyck sequence(균형 괄호)로 pretraining했을 때 정확도가 10%에서 98%로 뛰어오른다. 둘째, 이러한 이득이 더 큰 모델(최대 1.3B)의 pretraining에서 어떻게 반영되는지 살펴본다. 우리는 procedural data를 단 0.1%만 앞부분에 배치해도 자연어, 코드, 비형식 수학(C4, CodeParrot, DeepMind-Math datasets)에서의 표준 pretraining보다 훨씬 우수함을 확인한다. 특히 이 <em>procedural pretraining</em>은 모델이 원래 데이터의 55, 67, 86%만 사용해도 동일한 loss 값에 도달하게 한다. 셋째, 그 메커니즘을 탐구한 결과 procedural pretraining이 attention과 MLP layer 모두에 비자명한 구조를 주입함을 발견했다. 전자는 code와 같은 structured domain에서 특히 중요하고, 후자는 language에서 더 중요하다. 마지막으로, 우리는 여러 형태의 procedural data를 결합하는 경로를 제시한다. 우리의 결과는 procedural pretraining이 language model pretraining의 성능을 향상시키고 속도를 높이는 간단하고 경량인 수단임을 보여주며, 궁극적으로 LLM에서 knowledge acquisition과 reasoning을 분리할 가능성을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"68805","en":"Investigating Continual Pretraining in Large Language Models: Insights and Implications","ko":"대형 언어 모델에서 Continual Pretraining 조사: 통찰과 함의","authors":"Cagatay Yildiz, Nishaanth Kanna, Nitin Sharma, Matthias Bethge, Beyza Ermis","pos":"#1906","abs":"<p>Continual learning (CL) in large language models (LLMs) is an evolving domain that focuses on developing efficient and sustainable training strategies to adapt models to emerging knowledge and achieve robustness in dynamic environments. Our primary emphasis is on continual domain-adaptive pretraining, a process designed to equip LLMs with the ability to integrate new information from various domains while retaining previously learned knowledge. Since existing works concentrate mostly on continual fine-tuning for a limited selection of downstream tasks or training domains, we introduce a new benchmark designed to measure the adaptability of LLMs to changing pretraining data landscapes. We further examine the impact of model size on learning efficacy and forgetting, as well as how the progression and similarity of emerging domains affect the knowledge transfer within these models. \nOur findings uncover several key insights: (i) continual pretraining consistently improves &lt;1.5B models studied in this work and is also superior to domain adaptation, (ii) larger models always achieve better perplexity than smaller ones when continually pretrained on the same corpus, (iii) smaller models are particularly sensitive to continual pretraining, showing the most significant rates of both learning and forgetting, (iv) continual pretraining boosts downstream task performance of GPT-2 family, (v) continual pretraining enables LLMs to specialize better when the sequence of domains shows semantic similarity while randomizing training domains leads to better transfer and final performance otherwise. We posit that our research establishes a new benchmark for CL in LLMs, providing a more realistic evaluation of knowledge retention and transfer across diverse domains.</p>"},{"id":"61032","en":"COBRA: Contribution-Based Bayesian Rank Allocation for Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning","ko":"COBRA: Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning을 위한 기여 기반 Bayesian Rank Allocation","authors":"Xuanze Zhao, Hongcheng Ding, Jing Jin, LIU XUANHUANG, Shamsul Abdullah, Deshinta Dewi","pos":"#2111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uN58wqH2T7","abs":"<p>Full fine-tuning of large language models (LLMs) incurs prohibitive computational and storage costs. Parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) addresses this limitation, with Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) gaining widespread adoption due to its simplicity and zero inference overhead. However, LoRA and its variants typically rely on uniform rank allocation or a single importance metric such as gradient magnitude or output sensitivity to guide rank distribution. This approach fails to recognize that gradient magnitude and output contribution are decoupled properties, leading to suboptimal allocation where critical layers are under-provisioned while less important ones waste capacity. To address this challenge, we propose COBRA, a principled framework integrating dual importance factors for adaptive rank allocation. COBRA operates in three stages: (1) layer conductance attribution quantifies each layer's contribution via path-integral attribution; (2) dual-factor aggregation combines contribution with adaptation demand, producing the TA-LC distribution; and (3) Bayesian rank allocation translates this distribution into optimal heterogeneous ranks via variational optimization. Layer conductance provides layer-level interpretability by explicitly quantifying how much each layer contributes to predictions without redundancy, directly aligning with the granularity of rank allocation decisions and enabling principled cross-layer comparison for rank distribution. Experiments across diverse architectures and tasks demonstrate that COBRA consistently outperforms existing methods, achieving up to 1.6 points improvement on GLUE and 6.6\\% average gain in high-rank regimes under comparable parameter budgets.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM)의 full fine-tuning은 막대한 연산 및 저장 비용을 초래한다. Parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT)은 이러한 한계를 해결하며, Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA)는 단순성과 zero inference overhead 덕분에 널리 채택되었다. 그러나 LoRA와 그 변형들은 일반적으로 균일한 rank 할당이나 gradient magnitude 또는 output sensitivity와 같은 단일 중요도 지표에 의존하여 rank 분포를 유도한다. 이러한 접근은 gradient magnitude와 output contribution이 서로 분리된 속성임을 인식하지 못해, 중요한 layer에는 자원이 부족하고 덜 중요한 layer는 용량을 낭비하는 비최적 할당으로 이어진다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 적응적 rank 할당을 위해 이중 중요도 요인을 통합하는 원리적 프레임워크 COBRA를 제안한다. COBRA는 세 단계로 동작한다: (1) layer conductance attribution은 path-integral attribution을 통해 각 layer의 기여를 정량화하고, (2) dual-factor aggregation은 기여도와 adaptation demand를 결합하여 TA-LC 분포를 생성하며, (3) Bayesian rank allocation은 variational optimization을 통해 이 분포를 최적의 heterogeneous rank로 변환한다. Layer conductance는 중복 없이 각 layer가 예측에 얼마나 기여하는지를 명시적으로 정량화함으로써 layer-level interpretability를 제공하며, rank 할당 결정의 granularity와 직접적으로 정렬되고 rank 분포를 위한 원리적 cross-layer comparison을 가능하게 한다. 다양한 architecture와 task 전반의 실험은 COBRA가 기존 방법들을 일관되게 능가함을 보여주며, 동일한 parameter budget 하에서 GLUE에서 최대 1.6 points 향상과 high-rank regime에서 평균 6.6\\% 향상을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"68810","en":"Probabilistic Pretraining for Improved Neural Regression","ko":"개선된 신경 회귀를 위한 확률적 Pretraining","authors":"Boris Oreshkin, Shiv Tavker, Dmitry Efimov","pos":"#2506","abs":"<p>While transfer learning has revolutionized computer vision and natural language processing, its application to probabilistic regression remains underexplored, particularly for tabular data. We introduce NIAQUE (Neural Interpretable Any-Quantile Estimation), a novel permutation-invariant architecture that enables effective transfer learning across diverse regression tasks. Through extensive experiments on 101 datasets, we demonstrate that pre-training NIAQUE on multiple datasets and fine-tuning on target datasets consistently outperforms both traditional tree-based models and transformer-based neural baseline. On real-world Kaggle competitions, NIAQUE achieves competitive performance against heavily hand-crafted and feature-engineered solutions and outperforms strong baselines such as TabPFN and TabDPT, while maintaining interpretability through its probabilistic framework. Our results establish NIAQUE as a robust and scalable approach for tabular regression, effectively bridging the gap between traditional methods and modern transfer learning.</p>"},{"id":"67101","en":"Position: Modular Memory is the Key to Continual Learning Agents","ko":"Position: 모듈형 기억은 Continual Learning Agent의 핵심이다","authors":"Vaggelis Dorovatas, Malte Schwerin, Andrew Bagdanov, Lucas Caccia, Antonio Carta, Laurent Charlin, CITEC Barbara Hammer, Tyler Hayes, Timm Hess, Christopher Kanan, Dhireesha Kudithipudi, Xialei Liu, Vincenzo Lomonaco, Jorge Mendez-Mendez, Darshan Patil, Ameya Pandurang Prabhu, Elisa Ricci, Tinne Tuytelaars, Gido M van de Ven, Liyuan Wang, Joost van de Weijer, Jonghyun Choi, Martin Mundt, Rahaf Aljundi","pos":"#2507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iBXcqA5N6j","abs":"<p>Foundation models have transformed machine learning through large-scale pretraining, massive parameterization, and increased test-time compute. Despite surpassing human performance in several domains, these models remain fundamentally limited in continuous operation, experience accumulation, and personalization, capabilities that are central to adaptive intelligence. While continual learning research has long targeted these goals, its historical focus on in-weight learning, i.e., updating a single model’s parameters to absorb new knowledge, has rendered catastrophic forgetting a persistent challenge. <strong>Our position is that combining the strengths of In-Weight Learning (IWL) and the newly emerged capabilities of In-Context Learning (ICL) through the design of modular memory is the missing piece for continual adaptation at scale.</strong> We outline a conceptual framework for modular memory-centric architectures that leverage ICL for rapid adaptation and knowledge accumulation, and IWL for stable  updates to model capabilities, thereby mitigating catastrophic forgetting and charting a practical roadmap toward continually learning agents.</p>"},{"id":"64580","en":"HEDP: A Hybrid Energy-Distance Prompt-based Framework for Domain Incremental Learning","ko":"HEDP: Domain Incremental Learning을 위한 Hybrid Energy-Distance Prompt 기반 프레임워크","authors":"Yu Feng, Zhen Tian, Haoran Luo, Xie Yu, Diancheng Cheng, Haoyue Zheng, Shuai Lyu, Ping Zong, Lianyuan Li, xin ge, Yifan Zhu","pos":"#3508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LzWyl85Lkc","abs":"<p>Domain Incremental Learning is a critical scenario that requires models to continuously adapt to new data domains without retraining. However, domain shifts often cause severe performance degradation. To address this, we propose Hybrid Energy-Distance Prompt, a domain-incremental framework inspired by Helmholtz free energy. HEDP introduces an energy regularization loss to enhance the separability of domain representations and a hybrid energy-distance weighted mechanism that fuses energy-based and distance-based cues to improve domain selection and generalization. Experiments on multiple benchmarks, including CORe50, show that HEDP achieves superior performance on unseen domains with a 2.57\\% accuracy gain, effectively mitigating catastrophic forgetting and enhancing open-world adaptability. Our code is \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/HEDP-C879/}{available here}.</p>","absKo":"<p>Domain Incremental Learning은 재학습 없이 새로운 데이터 도메인에 지속적으로 적응해야 하는 중요한 시나리오이다. 그러나 domain shift는 종종 심각한 성능 저하를 유발한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Helmholtz free energy에서 영감을 받은 domain-incremental framework인 Hybrid Energy-Distance Prompt를 제안한다. HEDP는 domain representation의 분리 가능성을 높이기 위한 energy regularization loss와, energy-based 및 distance-based cue를 융합하여 domain selection과 generalization을 개선하는 hybrid energy-distance weighted mechanism을 도입한다. CORe50을 포함한 여러 benchmark에서의 실험은 HEDP가 보지 못한 domain에서 2.57\\%의 accuracy 향상과 함께 우수한 성능을 달성하며, catastrophic forgetting을 효과적으로 완화하고 open-world adaptability를 향상시킴을 보여준다. 우리의 코드는 \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/HEDP-C879/}{여기에서 확인할 수 있다}.</p>"},{"id":"60536","en":"Turning Back Without Forgetting: Selective Backward Refinement for Parameter-Efficient Continual Learning","ko":"잊지 않고 되돌리기: Parameter-Efficient Continual Learning을 위한 Selective Backward Refinement","authors":"Anushka Tiwari, Kaiyi Ji","pos":"#3712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zD2ZhFSexc","abs":"<p>While prompt-based parameter-efficient continual learning mitigates catastrophic forgetting by isolating task-specific prompts, this isolation also limits later tasks from improving earlier ones, leaving backward knowledge transfer underexplored. We address this limitation by proposing Selective bAckward refinement for positive Backward knowledge transfER (SABER), a replay-free framework that enables controlled backward transfer in prompt-based continual learning. SABER explicitly determines when backward refinement is beneficial using complementary task-correlation criteria based on prompt-gradient geometry and loss-distribution similarity, and how to perform refinement safely by restricting updates to non-interfering directions in the prompt parameter space. We provide theoretical guarantees showing that SABER’s backward refinements are interference-free and induce non-increasing loss under mild conditions. Extensive experiments across multiple continual learning benchmarks with different task orders, and diverse pretrained backbones, including T5-Large, LLaMA, and Qwen, demonstrate that SABER consistently achieves positive backward transfer while maintaining strong overall average performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>prompt-based parameter-efficient continual learning은 task-specific prompt를 분리함으로써 catastrophic forgetting을 완화하지만, 이러한 분리는 후속 task가 이전 task를 개선하는 것도 제한하여 backward knowledge transfer는 충분히 탐구되지 못했다. 우리는 이 한계를 해결하기 위해 Selective bAckward refinement for positive Backward knowledge transfER (SABER)를 제안한다. SABER는 prompt-based continual learning에서 제어된 backward transfer를 가능하게 하는 replay-free framework이다. SABER는 prompt-gradient geometry와 loss-distribution similarity에 기반한 상보적인 task-correlation criterion을 사용해 backward refinement가 언제 유익한지 명시적으로 판단하고, prompt parameter space에서 간섭하지 않는 방향으로만 업데이트를 제한해 refinement를 안전하게 수행하는 방법을 정한다. 우리는 SABER의 backward refinement가 interference-free이며, mild condition 하에서 non-increasing loss를 유도한다는 이론적 보장을 제시한다. 서로 다른 task order와 T5-Large, LLaMA, Qwen을 포함한 다양한 pretrained backbone을 사용한 여러 continual learning benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험에서, SABER는 강한 overall average performance를 유지하면서도 일관되게 positive backward transfer를 달성함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"62845","en":"Beyond Buffer Limits: Energy-Based Data Reassembly for Continual Learning","ko":"버퍼 한계를 넘어: 지속학습을 위한 Energy-Based 데이터 재조립","authors":"Zhenyi Wang, Yixuan Sun, Yue Wang, Zhong Chen, Heng Huang","pos":"#3800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cbicSAXMWQ","abs":"<p>Continual learning (CL) aims to acquire new knowledge from a non-stationary data stream while retaining performance on previously learned tasks. Memory-based replay methods mitigate catastrophic forgetting by storing and revisiting past samples, but their effectiveness is fundamentally constrained by limited memory capacity, as each stored example represents only a single data instance. In this work, we propose data reassembly for CL, a new paradigm that significantly increases memory efficiency by reassembling composite replay samples from existing training data. Instead of storing raw training examples, we partition the current task training data into elementary patches and dynamically reassemble them into coherent replay instances through an energy-based optimization framework. The proposed objective jointly enforces semantic compatibility with target labels and global consistency among assembled patches. To make this optimization tractable, we derive an efficient variational inference algorithm that constructs a compact yet diverse set of reassembled samples for replay. Extensive theoretical analysis and experiments across multiple CL benchmarks demonstrate that data reassembly consistently outperforms existing memory-based approaches, achieving stronger retention of past knowledge while maintaining competitive computational efficiency.</p>","absKo":"<p>Continual learning (CL)의 목표는 비정상(non-stationary) 데이터 스트림으로부터 새로운 지식을 습득하면서도 이전에 학습한 task의 성능을 유지하는 것이다. memory-based replay 방법은 과거 sample을 저장하고 다시 방문함으로써 catastrophic forgetting을 완화하지만, 저장된 각 예제가 단 하나의 데이터 인스턴스에 불과하다는 점 때문에 제한된 memory capacity에 본질적으로 제약된다. 본 연구에서는 기존 training data로부터 composite replay sample을 재구성하는 새로운 패러다임인 CL을 위한 data reassembly를 제안하여 memory efficiency를 크게 향상시킨다. 원시 training example을 저장하는 대신, 현재 task의 training data를 elementary patch로 분할하고 energy-based optimization framework를 통해 이를 일관된 replay instance로 동적으로 재구성한다. 제안하는 objective는 target label과의 semantic compatibility 및 조립된 patch 간의 global consistency를 공동으로 강제한다. 이 최적화를 tractable하게 만들기 위해, 우리는 replay를 위한 compact하면서도 diverse한 재구성 sample 집합을 구축하는 효율적인 variational inference algorithm을 도출한다. 여러 CL benchmark에 걸친 광범위한 이론 분석과 실험은 data reassembly가 기존 memory-based 접근을 일관되게 능가하며, 경쟁력 있는 계산 효율성을 유지하면서도 과거 지식의 보존을 더 강하게 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66538","en":"Distilling Linearized Behavior into Non-linear Fine-Tuning for Effective Task Arithmetic","ko":"효과적 Task Arithmetic을 위한 선형화 행동의 비선형 Fine-Tuning으로의 증류","authors":"Thomas Sommariva, Francesca Morandi, Simone Calderara, Angelo Porrello","pos":"#3801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2lMqcGV81Z","abs":"<p>Task vector composition has emerged as a promising paradigm for editing pre-trained models, enabling model merging via addition and task removal via subtraction. Fine-tuning in the tangent space of a pre-trained model (<em>linearized fine-tuning</em>) has proven particularly effective in this setting, as it yields task vectors that are naturally disentangled and less prone to interference. However, linearized models suffer from reduced expressivity during training and increased computational cost at inference time, limiting their practical applicability. In this work, we propose to bridge linearized and standard non-linear fine-tuning through knowledge distillation. Specifically, we distill hidden representations from a linearized, curvature-regularized teacher into a non-linear student trained with conventional fine-tuning. By doing so, the goal is to transfer the disentanglement properties of the linearized regime, biasing optimization toward solutions that are composable by design. We show that the resulting task vectors can be composed using naïve Task Arithmetic, achieving strong results across vision and language benchmarks without incurring any inference-time overhead.</p>"},{"id":"62227","en":"Doc-to-LoRA: Learning to Instantly Internalize Contexts","ko":"Doc-to-LoRA: 맥락을 즉시 내재화하도록 학습","authors":"Rujikorn Charakorn, Edoardo Cetin, Shinnosuke Uesaka, Robert Lange","pos":"#3803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iW1oBBO72S","abs":"<p>Long input sequences are central to in-context learning, document understanding, and multi-step reasoning of Large Language Models (LLMs). However, the quadratic attention cost of Transformers makes inference memory-intensive and slow. While context distillation (CD) can transfer information into model parameters, per-prompt distillation is impractical due to training costs and latency. To address these limitations, we propose Doc-to-LoRA (D2L), a lightweight hypernetwork that meta-learns to perform approximate CD within a single forward pass. Given an unseen prompt, D2L generates a LoRA adapter for a target LLM, enabling subsequent queries to be answered without re-consuming the original context, reducing latency and KV-cache memory consumption during inference of the target LLM. On a long-context needle-in-a-haystack task, D2L successfully learns to map contexts into adapters that store the needle information, achieving near-perfect zero-shot accuracy at sequence lengths exceeding the target LLM’s native context window by more than 4x. On real-world QA datasets with limited compute, D2L outperforms standard CD while significantly reducing peak memory consumption and update latency. We envision that D2L can facilitate rapid adaptation of LLMs, opening up the possibility of frequent knowledge updates and personalized chat behavior. Code and checkpoints will be released upon publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>긴 입력 sequence는 in-context learning, document understanding, 그리고 Large Language Model(LLM)의 multi-step reasoning에서 핵심적이다. 그러나 Transformer의 quadratic attention cost는 inference를 memory-intensive하고 느리게 만든다. context distillation(CD)은 정보를 model parameter로 전달할 수 있지만, prompt마다 distillation을 수행하는 것은 training cost와 latency 때문에 비현실적이다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 단일 forward pass 내에서 approximate CD를 수행하도록 meta-learning하는 경량 hypernetwork인 Doc-to-LoRA(D2L)를 제안한다. 보지 못한 prompt가 주어지면, D2L은 target LLM을 위한 LoRA adapter를 생성하며, 이후의 query는 원래 context를 다시 소비하지 않고 답변할 수 있게 된다. 이로써 target LLM의 inference 동안 latency와 KV-cache memory consumption을 줄일 수 있다. 긴 context의 needle-in-a-haystack task에서 D2L은 context를 needle 정보를 저장하는 adapter로 매핑하는 방법을 성공적으로 학습하며, target LLM의 native context window보다 4배 이상 긴 sequence length에서도 거의 완벽한 zero-shot accuracy를 달성한다. 제한된 compute 환경의 실제 QA dataset에서 D2L은 표준 CD보다 우수하면서도 peak memory consumption과 update latency를 크게 줄인다. 우리는 D2L이 LLM의 rapid adaptation을 촉진하여, 빈번한 knowledge update와 personalized chat behavior의 가능성을 열어줄 것으로 본다. code와 checkpoint는 publication 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65845","en":"From Memorization to Parameter Interference: How Overtraining Experts Harms Model Merging","ko":"암기에서 파라미터 간섭으로: 전문가 과다 학습이 어떻게 모델 병합을 해치는가","authors":"Stefan Horoi, Guy Wolf, Eugene Belilovsky, Gintare Karolina Dziugaite","pos":"#3804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9XGa1e4YxB","abs":"<p>Modern deep learning is increasingly characterized by the use of open-weight foundation models that can be fine-tuned on specialized datasets. This has led to a proliferation of expert models and adapters, often shared via platforms like HuggingFace and AdapterHub. Model merging has recently emerged as an effective way to leverage these existing resources, enabling the composition of capabilities from different model checkpoints. A natural pipeline has thus formed to harness the benefits of transfer learning and amortize sunk training costs: models are pre-trained on general data, fine-tuned on specific tasks, and then multiple checkpoints are merged to obtain a more capable model. A prevailing assumption is that improvements at one stage of this pipeline propagate downstream, leading to gains at subsequent steps. In this work, we challenge that assumption by examining how expert fine-tuning affects model merging. We show that long fine-tuning of experts that optimizes for their individual performance leads to degraded merging performance across vision and language modalities, multiple model scales, and both fully fine-tuned and LoRA-adapted models. We trace this degradation to the memorization of a small set of difficult examples that dominate late fine-tuning steps. This causes negative parameter interference and encodes knowledge that is forgotten during merging. Finally, we demonstrate that task-dependent aggressive early stopping strategies can significantly improve model merging performance.</p>"},{"id":"64526","en":"Gradient Transformer: Learning to Generate Updates for LLMs","ko":"Gradient Transformer: LLM을 위한 업데이트 생성 학습","authors":"Binh-Nguyen Nguyen, Khang Tran, Hai Phan, Issa Khalil","pos":"#3806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Mi8VcF4qJZ","abs":"Many organizations lack computational resources to fine-tune large language models (LLMs) on private (unshareable) data for better utility, while fine-tuning tiny language models (TinyLMs) alone performs poorly. To address this bottleneck, we propose a data-free knowledge distillation framework that generates LLM update vectors based on TinyLMs fine-tuned on private data. An update vector is a vector of parameter changes from an initial model to its fine-tuned version on a dataset, capturing the effect of cumulative gradient steps during fine-tuning. The key idea of our framework is a novel **Gradient Transformer** that transforms TinyLM's update vectors into LLM's update vectors. As derived from shadow datasets, $\\texttt{Grad-Transformer}$ captures the correlation between TinyLM and LLM update vectors, enabling third-party providers to generate LLM update vectors given the organization's TinyLM update vectors without accessing the organization's private data. The framework supports multi-organization collaboration to jointly update LLMs, improving performance and cost-efficiency. Extensive experiments across language modeling and reasoning tasks show that $\\texttt{Grad-Transformer}$ remarkably outperforms state-of-the-art knowledge distillation baselines, even under strict differential privacy protection.","absKo":"많은 조직은 더 나은 효용을 위해 비공개(unshareable) 데이터로 Large Language Model(LLM)을 fine-tune할 계산 자원이 부족하며, 반면 작은 language model(TinyLMs)만 fine-tune하면 성능이 낮다. 이러한 병목을 해결하기 위해 우리는 비공개 데이터로 fine-tune된 TinyLM을 기반으로 LLM update vector를 생성하는 data-free knowledge distillation framework를 제안한다. update vector는 초기 model에서 dataset에 대해 fine-tuned version으로의 parameter 변화 벡터로, fine-tuning 동안 누적된 gradient step의 효과를 포착한다. 우리의 framework의 핵심 아이디어는 TinyLM의 update vector를 LLM의 update vector로 변환하는 새로운 **Gradient Transformer**이다. shadow dataset으로부터 유도된 $\\texttt{Grad-Transformer}$는 TinyLM과 LLM update vector 사이의 상관관계를 포착하여, 조직의 private data에 접근하지 않고도 third-party provider가 조직의 TinyLM update vector가 주어졌을 때 LLM update vector를 생성할 수 있게 한다. 이 framework는 여러 조직이 협력하여 LLM을 공동 업데이트하는 것을 지원하며, 성능과 비용 효율성을 함께 향상시킨다. 언어 모델링과 reasoning task 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 $\\texttt{Grad-Transformer}$가 엄격한 differential privacy 보호 하에서도 state-of-the-art knowledge distillation baseline을 현저히 능가함을 보여준다."},{"id":"66500","en":"Learning to Memorize with Attributive and Associative Memory for Online Test-Time Adaptation of Vision-Language Models","ko":"Vision-Language 모델의 온라인 테스트 시점 적응을 위한 귀속적 및 연상적 기억으로 기억하는 법 배우기","authors":"Yuchao Zhang, Eric Wang, Fan Zhang, Haoxuan Li, Yisen Wang, Zhouchen Lin, Jun Wang, QIRUI MI, Mengyue Yang","pos":"#3807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=37Csgeb5CF","abs":"Memory-based test-time adaptation (TTA) assigns streaming test samples into class-specific memory slots based on pseudo-labels predicted by models like CLIP, and retrieves them to facilitate subsequent predictions under distribution shift. However, this process introduces two challenges: ❶  **Each sample is hard-assigned to a single class based on CLIP's prediction**, where inaccurate CLIP prediction leads to  memory contamination that biases subsequent prediction. ❷ **Samples are evicted under biased selection due to fixed memory capacity**, which risks discarding informative samples and undermining the efficacy of the memory. To address these challenges, we propose **A$^{2}$Memory** (**A**ttributive-**A**ssociative **Memory** for Test-time Adaptation).   For challenge ❶ , we propose *Attribute-centric Memory Construction* that builds prior textual representations   from class-shared representative and diverse visual attributes, and applies soft assignment to generate surrogate visual representations. For challenge ❷, we design *Class-wise Associative Memory*  that dynamically compresses streaming samples into fixed-capacity memory through gradient-based optimization and data-dependent retention, then retrieves sample-adaptive class prototypes for reliable inference.  Extensive experiments demonstrate consistent improvements over state-of-the-art methods across 15 benchmarks."},{"id":"62810","en":"PLATE: Plasticity-Tunable Efficient Adapters for Geometry-Aware Continual Learning","ko":"PLATE: Geometry-Aware Continual Learning을 위한 Plasticity-Tunable Efficient Adapters","authors":"Romain Cosentino","pos":"#3810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=d4VzITcGKj","abs":"We develop a continual learning method for pretrained models that \\emph{requires no access to old-task data}, addressing a practical barrier in foundation model adaptation where pretraining distributions are often unavailable. Our key observation is that pretrained networks exhibit substantial \\emph{geometric redundancy}, and that this redundancy can be exploited in two complementary ways. First, redundant neurons provide a proxy for dominant pretraining-era feature directions, enabling the construction of approximately protected update subspaces directly from pretrained weights. Second, redundancy offers a natural bias for \\emph{where} to place plasticity: by restricting updates to a subset of redundant neurons and constraining the remaining degrees of freedom, we obtain update families with reduced functional drift on the old-data distribution and improved worst-case retention guarantees. These insights lead to \\textsc{PLATE} (\\textbf{Pla}sticity-\\textbf{T}unable \\textbf{E}fficient Adapters), a continual learning method requiring no past-task data that provides explicit control over the plasticity-retention trade-off. PLATE parameterizes each layer with a structured low-rank update $\\Delta W = B A Q^\\top$, where $B$ and $Q$ are computed once from pretrained weights and kept frozen, and only $A$ is trained on the new task.","absKo":"우리는 old-task data에 \\emph{전혀 접근하지 않아도 되는} pretrained model용 continual learning method를 개발한다. 이는 pretraining distribution이 종종 이용 불가능한 foundation model adaptation에서 실질적인 장벽을 해결한다. 우리의 핵심 관찰은 pretrained network가 상당한 \\emph{geometric redundancy}를 보이며, 이 중복성을 두 가지 보완적 방식으로 활용할 수 있다는 점이다. 첫째, redundant neuron은 pretraining 시기의 지배적인 feature 방향에 대한 proxy 역할을 하므로, pretrained weight로부터 직접 대략적으로 보호된 update subspace를 구성할 수 있다. 둘째, redundancy는 plasticity를 \\emph{어디에} 둘지에 대한 자연스러운 bias를 제공한다. 중복적인 neuron의 일부에만 update를 제한하고 나머지 degrees of freedom을 제약함으로써, old-data distribution에서 functional drift가 줄어들고 worst-case retention guarantee가 개선된 update family를 얻는다. 이러한 통찰은 old-task data가 전혀 필요 없는 continual learning method인 \\textsc{PLATE}(\\textbf{Pla}sticity-\\textbf{T}unable \\textbf{E}fficient Adapters)로 이어지며, plasticity-retention trade-off를 명시적으로 제어할 수 있게 한다. PLATE는 각 layer를 구조화된 low-rank update $\\Delta W = B A Q^\\top$로 parameterize하며, 여기서 $B$와 $Q$는 pretrained weight로부터 한 번 계산되어 고정되고, 새로운 task에서는 $A$만 학습된다."},{"id":"68806","en":"Retrospective Feature Estimation for Continual Learning","ko":"Continual Learning을 위한 회고적 특성 추정","authors":"Nghia Nguyen, Trung Hieu Nguyen, Ang Li, Hoang Pham, Viet Anh Nguyen, Khoa Doan","pos":"#3811","abs":"<p>The intrinsic capability to continuously learn a changing data stream is a desideratum of deep neural networks (DNNs). However, current DNNs suffer from catastrophic forgetting, which interferes with remembering past knowledge. To mitigate this issue, existing Continual Learning (CL) approaches often retain exemplars for replay, regularize learning, or allocate dedicated capacity for new tasks. This paper investigates an unexplored direction for CL called Retrospective Feature Estimation (RFE). RFE learns to reverse feature changes by aligning the features from the current trained DNN backward to the feature space of the old task, where performing predictions is easier. This retrospective process utilizes a chain of small feature mapping networks called retrospector modules. Empirical experiments on several CL benchmarks, including CIFAR10, CIFAR100, and Tiny ImageNet, demonstrate the effectiveness and potential of this novel CL direction compared to existing representative CL methods, motivating further research into retrospective mechanisms as a principled alternative for mitigating catastrophic forgetting in CL. Code is available at: https://github.com/mail-research/retrospective-feature-estimation.</p>"},{"id":"64140","en":"SaTeen: Learning Structural Alignment for Continual Test-Time Adaptation","ko":"SaTeen: 지속적 테스트 시점 적응을 위한 구조적 정렬 학습","authors":"Chang Liu, Ruotong Zhao, Li Gao, Yupei Zhang","pos":"#3812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QYPKLGyz7K","abs":"<p>Test-Time Adaptation (TTA) aims to reconcile model generalization in the presence of distribution shifts. Current TTA methods usually leverage sample uncertainty to select reliable samples for model adjustment via entropy minimization (EM). However, sample uncertainty often relies on a plausible metric and leaves many unreliable samples into EM, potentially leading to model collapse. Importantly, these excluded samples incur incomplete data features of the shifted distribution in TTA. This paper introduces SaTeen, a <strong>S</strong>tructural <strong>A</strong>lignment-based <strong>Te</strong>st-Tim<strong>e</strong> Adaptatio<strong>n</strong> (SaTeen) method, by two-fold aligning the structures of test samples with the reliable reference structures. Specifically, the two-fold alignments are 1) Intra-sample structure alignment, where SeTeen maximizes cross-entropy discrepancy between a sample (reference) and its structure-disrupted counterpart, with the assumption of stable dominant features; 2) Inter-sample structure alignment, where SeTeen minimizes the reconstruction error of test samples in the reference subspace spanned by the Incremental PCA (IPCA) on reliable samples, with the assumption of stale intrinsic data manifold. Our extensive experiments demonstrate SaTeen achieves the state-of-the-art performance across various scenarios for both TTA and continual TTA.</p>","absKo":"<p>Test-Time Adaptation(TTA)은 distribution shift가 존재하는 상황에서 model generalization을 조정하는 것을 목표로 한다. 현재의 TTA 방법들은 일반적으로 sample uncertainty를 활용하여 entropy minimization(EM)을 통해 model adjustment에 사용할 신뢰할 수 있는 sample을 선택한다. 그러나 sample uncertainty는 종종 타당한 metric에 의존하며, 많은 신뢰할 수 없는 sample이 EM에 남아 model collapse를 유발할 수 있다. 더욱이 이러한 제외된 sample은 TTA에서 shifted distribution의 불완전한 data feature를 초래한다. 본 논문은 구조 정렬을 통해 test sample의 structure를 reliable reference structure와 이중으로 맞추는 <strong>S</strong>tructural <strong>A</strong>lignment-based <strong>Te</strong>st-Tim<strong>e</strong> Adaptatio<strong>n</strong>(SaTeen) 방법을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 이중 정렬은 1) Intra-sample structure alignment로, SeTeen은 sample(=reference)과 구조가 교란된 대응물 사이의 cross-entropy discrepancy를 최대화하며, 안정적인 dominant feature라는 가정을 둔다. 2) Inter-sample structure alignment로, SeTeen은 reliable sample에 대해 Incremental PCA(IPCA)로 span된 reference subspace에서 test sample의 reconstruction error를 최소화하며, 고정된 intrinsic data manifold라는 가정을 둔다. 우리의 광범위한 실험은 SaTeen이 TTA와 continual TTA 모두에서 다양한 시나리오에 걸쳐 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61996","en":"Spectral Imbalance Causes Forgetting in Low-Rank Continual Adaptation","ko":"스펙트럴 불균형이 low-rank continual adaptation에서 망각 유발","authors":"Hao Gu, Mao-Lin Luo, Zi-Hao Zhou, Han-Chen Zhang, Min-Ling Zhang, Tong Wei","pos":"#3813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kqE6GjpQTn","abs":"<p>Parameter-efficient continual learning aims to adapt pre-trained models to sequential tasks without forgetting previously acquired knowledge. Most existing approaches treat continual learning as avoiding interference with past updates, rather than considering what properties make the current task-specific update naturally preserve previously acquired knowledge. From a knowledge-decomposition perspective, we observe that low-rank adaptations exhibit highly imbalanced singular value spectra: a few dominant components absorb most of the adaptation energy, thereby (i) more likely to disrupt previously acquired knowledge and (ii) making the update more vulnerable to interference from subsequent tasks. To enable explicit balance among components, we decouple the <em>magnitude</em> of the task update from its <em>directional structure</em> and formulate it as a constrained optimization problem on a restricted Stiefel manifold. We address this problem using a projected first-order method compatible with standard deep-learning optimizers used in vision-language models. Our method mitigates both backward and forward forgetting, consistently outperforming continual learning baselines. Source code is available in supplementary material.</p>","absKo":"<p>Parameter-efficient continual learning은 사전학습된 모델을 순차적 task에 적응시키되, 이전에 획득한 지식을 잊지 않도록 하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존의 대부분 접근법은 continual learning을 과거 업데이트와의 간섭을 피하는 문제로 다루지만, 현재 task-specific update가 어떤 성질을 가져야 이전에 획득한 지식을 자연스럽게 보존하는지는 고려하지 않는다. 지식 분해 관점에서 우리는 low-rank adaptation이 매우 불균형한 singular value spectrum을 보인다는 점을 관찰한다. 몇 개의 지배적인 component가 대부분의 adaptation energy를 흡수하며, 그 결과 (i) 이전에 획득한 지식을 교란할 가능성이 더 높아지고 (ii) 이후 task로부터의 간섭에 대해 update가 더 취약해진다. component 간의 명시적 균형을 가능하게 하기 위해, 우리는 task update의 <em>크기</em>와 <em>방향적 구조</em>를 분리하고 이를 제한된 Stiefel manifold 위의 constrained optimization problem으로 정식화한다. 우리는 이 문제를 vision-language model에서 사용되는 표준 deep-learning optimizer와 호환되는 projected first-order method로 해결한다. 우리의 방법은 backward forgetting과 forward forgetting을 모두 완화하며, continual learning baseline들을 일관되게 상회한다. 소스 코드는 supplementary material에 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"64847","en":"TuneAhead: Predicting Fine-tuning Performance Before Training Begins","ko":"TuneAhead: 학습 시작 전 Fine-tuning 성능 예측","authors":"Yuxiang Luo, Haonan Long, Chen Wang, Qiqi Duan, Xiaotian Lin, Yanwei XU, Yuyu Luo, Weikai Yang, Nan Tang","pos":"#3814","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JBFB2pUOCA","abs":"<p>Fine-tuning large language models (LLMs) is compute-intensive and error-prone: model performance depends sensitively on data quality and hyperparameter choices, and naïve runs can even degrade model performance. This raises a fundamental question: Can we predict fine-tuning performance before training begins? We present TuneAhead, a lightweight framework for pre-hoc prediction of fine-tuning performance. TuneAhead encodes each fine-tuning run as a meta-feature vector that combines static dataset descriptors with dynamic probe features from a short simulated run. A gradient-boosting predictor maps these features to performance predictions, while SHAP-based attributions provide interpretable diagnostics that reveal which specific features are driving performance. Across 1,300+ fine-tuning runs on Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct, TuneAhead consistently outperforms strong baselines such as ProxyLM and Early-Stop Extrapolation. On a held-out test set of 370 runs, by defining ‘success’ as exceeding a performance threshold, it accurately predicted 89.4% of successful runs (110/123) and 91.0% of failure runs (225/247), enabling practitioners to proactively avoid costly unsuccessful runs before training begins. This leads to computational savings of 58.4% in total.</p>","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델(LLM)의 fine-tuning은 계산 비용이 많이 들고 오류가 발생하기 쉽다. 모델 성능이 데이터 품질과 hyperparameter 선택에 민감하게 좌우되며, 단순한 실행은 오히려 모델 성능을 떨어뜨릴 수도 있기 때문이다. 이는 근본적인 질문을 제기한다. 학습이 시작되기 전에 fine-tuning 성능을 예측할 수 있는가? 우리는 fine-tuning 성능의 pre-hoc prediction을 위한 경량 framework인 TuneAhead를 제안한다. TuneAhead는 각 fine-tuning 실행을 정적 dataset descriptor와 짧은 simulated run에서 얻은 동적 probe feature를 결합한 meta-feature vector로 인코딩한다. gradient boosting predictor는 이러한 feature를 성능 예측으로 매핑하고, SHAP-based attribution은 어떤 구체적 feature가 성능을 이끄는지 보여주는 해석 가능한 diagnostic을 제공한다. Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct에서 수행한 1,300개 이상의 fine-tuning run 전반에서 TuneAhead는 ProxyLM과 Early-Stop Extrapolation 같은 강력한 baseline보다 일관되게 우수한 성능을 보였다. 370개 run의 held-out test set에서, success를 성능 threshold 초과로 정의했을 때 성공 run의 89.4% (110/123)와 실패 run의 91.0% (225/247)를 정확히 예측하여, practitioners가 학습 시작 전에 비용이 큰 실패 run을 선제적으로 피할 수 있게 했다. 그 결과 전체적으로 58.4%의 계산 비용 절감이 가능했다."},{"id":"65026","en":"Don't Reinvent the Wheel, Just Realign the Spokes: Resource-Efficient Federated Fine-Tuning via Rank-Wise Expert Assembly","ko":"바퀴를 다시 발명하지 말고 살만 재정렬하라: Rank-Wise Expert Assembly를 통한 자원 효율적 Federated Fine-Tuning","authors":"Yebo Wu, Jingguang Li, Zhijiang Guo, Li Li","pos":"#3900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HdsEUNo4C4","abs":"<p>Federated fine-tuning presents a promising avenue for adapting Large Language Models (LLMs) to downstream tasks while preserving data privacy. However, the prohibitive computational and communication overhead of LLM adaptation inhibits its deployment on resource-constrained edge devices. In this paper, we propose SmartFed, a resource-efficient framework that circumvents expensive training from scratch by intelligently reusing knowledge embedded in existing LoRA modules. To fully exploit this potential and ensure scalability, we introduce the Mixture of Rank-Wise Experts (MoRE). MoRE decomposes LoRA modules into fine-grained rank-level experts, which are selectively activated based on input semantics and resource budgets. Furthermore, to optimize resource utilization, we propose Elastic Expert Quota Allocation (EEQA), a strategy that adaptively distributes expert capacity across parameter matrices based on their contribution to model performance. Extensive evaluations across multiple benchmarks demonstrate that SmartFed significantly outperforms state-of-the-art methods in both model performance and training efficiency.</p>","absKo":"<p>Federated fine-tuning은 데이터 프라이버시를 보존하면서 Large Language Models (LLMs)를 다운스트림 태스크에 적응시키는 유망한 접근법이다. 그러나 LLM 적응에 수반되는 과도한 계산 및 통신 오버헤드 때문에, 자원이 제한된 엣지 디바이스에 배포하기가 어렵다. 본 논문에서는 기존 LoRA 모듈에 내재된 지식을 지능적으로 재사용하여, 비용이 큰 from-scratch 학습을 우회하는 자원 효율적 프레임워크 SmartFed를 제안한다. 이러한 잠재력을 충분히 활용하고 확장성을 보장하기 위해, 우리는 Mixture of Rank-Wise Experts (MoRE)를 도입한다. MoRE는 LoRA 모듈을 입력 의미와 자원 예산에 따라 선택적으로 활성화되는 세분화된 rank 수준 expert로 분해한다. 또한 자원 활용을 최적화하기 위해, 우리는 Elastic Expert Quota Allocation (EEQA)을 제안한다. 이는 모델 성능에 대한 기여도에 기반하여 expert 용량을 파라미터 행렬 전반에 적응적으로 분배하는 전략이다. 여러 benchmark에 걸친 광범위한 평가 결과, SmartFed는 모델 성능과 학습 효율성 모두에서 state-of-the-art 방법을 크게 상회함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"60882","en":"What Linear Probes Miss: Multi-View Probing for Weight-Space Learning","ko":"Linear Probe가 놓치는 것: Weight-Space Learning을 위한 Multi-View Probing","authors":"Eunwoo Heo, Kyeongkook Seo, Jaejun Yoo","pos":"#3914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vfqrmuVULL","abs":"<p>The explosive growth of open-source model repositories has created a Model Jungle, where checkpoints are frequently shared without adequate documentation or metadata. While weight-space learning offers a pathway to identify and analyze these models directly from their parameters, processing full-scale weights is computationally prohibitive. Probing-based methods have emerged as a lightweight alternative, extracting permutation-equivariant representations via learnable probe vectors. However, existing probing methods are limited by a single-view design: they capture first-order structures but fail to encode the rich, higher-order correlation patterns inherent in row--column interactions. To bridge this gap, we introduce MVProbe, a multi-perspective probing framework that synthesizes first-order signals with interaction-aware (Gram-based) views. Our approach is theoretically grounded; we analyze the scaling laws of different probing orders to derive a principled standardization and fusion strategy that ensures balanced contributions from all branches. On the Model Jungle benchmark, MVProbe consistently outperforms the state-of-the-art ProbeX across diverse architectures, including ResNet, SupViT, MAE, and DINO.</p>","absKo":"<p>open-source model repository의 폭발적 성장은 Model Jungle을 만들어냈고, checkpoint는 종종 충분한 documentation이나 metadata 없이 공유된다. weight-space learning은 이러한 model을 parameter로부터 직접 식별하고 분석할 수 있는 경로를 제공하지만, full-scale weight를 처리하는 것은 계산적으로 매우 비싸다. probing-based method는 learnable probe vector를 통해 permutation-equivariant representation을 추출하는 경량 대안으로 부상했다. 그러나 기존 probing method는 single-view 설계에 의해 제한된다. 즉, first-order structure는 포착하지만 row--column interaction에 내재된 풍부한 higher-order correlation pattern을 인코딩하지 못한다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 first-order signal을 interaction-aware (Gram-based) view와 결합하는 multi-perspective probing framework인 MVProbe를 제안한다. 우리의 접근법은 이론적 기반을 갖는다. 우리는 서로 다른 probing order의 scaling law를 분석하여 모든 branch가 균형 있게 기여하도록 하는 원리적 standardization 및 fusion strategy를 도출한다. Model Jungle benchmark에서 MVProbe는 ResNet, SupViT, MAE, DINO를 포함한 다양한 architecture에서 state-of-the-art ProbeX를 일관되게 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"68834","en":"Rethinking Memory in Continual Learning: Beyond a Monolithic Store of the Past","ko":"Continual Learning에서 기억 재고: 과거의 단일 저장소를 넘어서","authors":"Yaqian Zhang, Bernhard Pfahringer, Eibe Frank, Albert Bifet","pos":"#4302","abs":"<p>Memory is a critical component in replay-based continual learning (CL). Prior research has largely treated CL memory as a monolithic store of past data, focusing on how to select and store representative past examples. However, this perspective overlooks the higher-level memory architecture that governs the interaction between old and new data. In this work, we identify and characterize a dual-memory system that is inherently present in both online and offline CL settings. This system comprises: a short-term memory, which temporarily buffers recent data for immediate model updates, and a long-term memory, which maintains a carefully curated subset of past experiences for future replay and consolidation. We propose  \\textit{memory capacity ratio} (MCR), the ratio between short-term memory and long-term memory capacities, to characterize online and offline CL. Based on this framework, we systematically investigate how MCR influences generalization, stability, and plasticity. Across diverse CL settings—class-incremental, task-incremental, and domain-incremental—and multiple data modalities (e.g., image and text classification), we observe that a smaller MCR, characteristic of \\textit{online CL}, can yield comparable or even superior performance relative to a larger one, characteristic of \\textit{offline CL}, when both are evaluated under equivalent computational and data storage budgets. This advantage holds consistently across several state-of-the-art replay strategies, such as ER, DER, and SCR. Theoretical analysis further reveals that a reduced MCR yields a better trade-off between stability and plasticity by lowering a bound on generalization error when learning from non-stationary data streams with limited memory. These findings offer new insights into the role of memory allocation in continual learning and underscore the underexplored potential of online CL approaches.</p>"},{"id":"65328","en":"Geometric Coherence Learning for Structuring Value Functions in Plain MDPs","ko":"평범한 MDP에서 가치 함수 구조화를 위한 기하학적 정합 학습","authors":"Zuyuan Zhang, Zeyu Fang, Tian Lan","pos":"#109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EhJ1R2N6sn","abs":"<p>Geometric properties can be leveraged to stabilize and speed reinforcement learning. Existing examples include encoding symmetry structure, geometry-aware data augmentation, and enforcing structural restrictions. In this paper, we take a novel view of RL through the lens of order theory and recast value function estimates into learning a desired poset (partially ordered set).  We propose \\emph{GCR-RL} (Geometric Coherence Regularized Reinforcement Learning) that computes a sequence of super-poset refinements -- by refining posets in previous steps and learning additional order relationships from temporal difference signals -- thus ensuring geometric coherence across the sequence of posets underpinning the learned value functions. Two novel algorithms  by Q-learning and by actor--critic are developed to efficiently realize these super-poset refinements. Their theoretical properties and convergence rates are analyzed. We empirically evaluate GCR-RL in a range of tasks and demonstrate significant improvements in sample efficiency and stable performance over strong baselines.</p>"},{"id":"61704","en":"Unsupervised Mode Discovery for Fine-tuning Multimodal Generative Policies","ko":"Multimodal Generative Policy Fine-tuning을 위한 비지도 Mode Discovery","authors":"Alberta Longhini, David Emukpere, Jean-Michel Renders, Seungsu Kim","pos":"#110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nc5WYNeI17","abs":"<p>We address the problem of fine-tuning pre-trained generative policies with reinforcement learning (RL) while preserving the multimodality of their action distributions. Existing methods for RL fine-tuning of generative policies (e.g., diffusion policies) improve task performance but often collapse diverse behaviors into a single reward-maximizing mode. To mitigate this issue, we propose an unsupervised mode discovery framework that uncovers latent behavioral modes within generative policies. The discovered modes enable the use of mutual information as an intrinsic reward, regularizing RL fine-tuning to enhance task success while maintaining behavioral diversity. Experiments on robotic manipulation tasks demonstrate that our method consistently outperforms conventional fine-tuning approaches, achieving higher success rates and preserving richer multimodal action distributions.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 사전학습된 generative policy를 reinforcement learning (RL)으로 fine-tuning하면서 action distribution의 multimodality를 보존하는 문제를 다룬다. generative policy, 예를 들어 diffusion policy의 RL fine-tuning을 위한 기존 방법들은 task performance를 향상시키지만, 종종 다양한 behavior를 단일 reward-maximizing mode로 수렴시킨다. 이 문제를 완화하기 위해 우리는 generative policy 내부의 latent behavioral mode를 발견하는 unsupervised mode discovery framework를 제안한다. 이렇게 발견된 mode는 mutual information을 intrinsic reward로 사용할 수 있게 하며, RL fine-tuning을 regularize하여 행동 다양성을 유지하면서 task success를 향상시킨다. 로봇 조작 task 실험은 본 방법이 기존 fine-tuning 접근법을 일관되게 능가하며, 더 높은 성공률과 더 풍부한 multimodal action distribution을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61588","en":"Mirror Descent Actor Critic via Bounded Advantage Learning","ko":"Bounded Advantage Learning을 통한 Mirror Descent Actor Critic","authors":"Ryo Iwaki","pos":"#112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ofwEMwiaLU","abs":"<p>Regularization is a core component of recent Reinforcement Learning (RL) algorithms. Mirror Descent Value Iteration (MDVI) uses both Kullback-Leibler divergence and entropy as regularizers in its value and policy updates. Despite its empirical success in discrete action domains and strong theoretical guarantees, the performance of KL-entropy-regularized methods does not surpass that of a strong entropy-only-regularized method in continuous action domains. In this study, we propose Mirror Descent Actor Critic (MDAC) as an actor-critic style instantiation of MDVI for continuous action domains, and show that its empirical performance is significantly boosted by bounding the actor's log-probability terms in the critic's loss function, compared to a non-bounded naive instantiation. Further, we relate MDAC to Advantage Learning by recalling that the actor's log-probability is equal to the regularized advantage function in tabular cases, and theoretically discuss when and why bounding the advantage terms is validated and beneficial. We also empirically explore effective choices for the bounding functions, and show that MDAC performs better than strong non-regularized and entropy-only-regularized methods with an appropriate choice of the bounding functions.</p>","absKo":"<p>regularization은 최근 Reinforcement Learning (RL) 알고리즘의 핵심 구성 요소다. Mirror Descent Value Iteration (MDVI)는 value 및 policy update에서 Kullback-Leibler divergence와 entropy를 모두 regularizer로 사용한다. discrete action domain에서의 실증적 성공과 강력한 이론적 보장에도 불구하고, KL-entropy-regularized method의 성능은 continuous action domain에서 강한 entropy-only-regularized method를 능가하지 못한다. 본 연구에서는 continuous action domain을 위한 MDVI의 actor-critic 형태 구현으로 Mirror Descent Actor Critic (MDAC)을 제안하고, critic의 loss function에서 actor의 log-probability term을 bounding하면 non-bounded naive implementation에 비해 실증적 성능이 크게 향상됨을 보인다. 더 나아가 tabular case에서 actor의 log-probability가 regularized advantage function과 같다는 점을 상기하며 MDAC를 Advantage Learning과 연결하고, advantage term을 bounding하는 것이 언제 왜 타당하고 유익한지 이론적으로 논의한다. 또한 bounding function의 효과적인 선택을 실증적으로 탐색하고, 적절한 bounding function을 사용할 때 MDAC가 강한 non-regularized method 및 entropy-only-regularized method보다 더 우수하게 동작함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66002","en":"Generative Online Reinforcement Learning","ko":"생성적 온라인 강화학습","authors":"Chubin Zhang, Zhenglin Wan, Feng Chen, Fuchao Yang, Lang Feng, Yaxin Zhou, Xingrui Yu, Yang You, Ivor Tsang, Bo An","pos":"#113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=81BlQ07f5O","abs":"Reinforcement learning (RL) faces a persistent tension: policies that are stable to optimize (e.g., Gaussians) are often too simple to represent the multimodal action distributions required for complex control. Conversely, expressive generative policies—such as diffusion and flow matching—are frequently unstable in online RL due to intractable likelihoods and gradients propagating through long sampling chains. We address this tension with a key structural principle: decoupling optimization from generation. Building on this, we introduce GoRL (Generative Online Reinforcement Learning), an algorithm-agnostic framework that trains expressive policies from scratch by confining policy optimization to a tractable latent space while delegating action synthesis to a conditional generative decoder. Using a two-timescale alternating schedule and anchoring decoder refinement to a fixed prior, GoRL enables stable optimization while continuously expanding expressiveness. Empirically, GoRL consistently outperforms unimodal and generative baselines across diverse continuous-control tasks. Notably, on the challenging HopperStand task, it achieves episodic returns exceeding 870—more than $3\\times$ that of the strongest baseline—demonstrating a practical path to policies that are both stable and highly expressive."},{"id":"64640","en":"COLLIE: Guiding Skill Discovery in Semantically Coherent Latent Space","ko":"COLLIE: 의미적으로 일관된 잠재 공간에서의 Skill Discovery 유도","authors":"Yao Luan, Ni Mu, Hanfei Ge, Yiqin Yang, Bo XU, Qing-Shan Jia","pos":"#114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LMBt26pQj1","abs":"<p>Unsupervised skill discovery (USD) aims to learn diverse behaviors without reward functions, but often results in task-irrelevant or hazardous behaviors due to uniform exploration. Guided skill discovery (GSD) addresses this issue by incorporating human intent to focus exploration on meaningful regions. However, existing GSD methods typically require training additional guidance models from scratch, which can be ineffective with sparse human feedback. To tackle this, we propose COLLIE, a GSD framework that utilizes sparse human feedback effectively by constructing a semantically coherent skill latent space. The semantical coherence property enables a training-free guidance signal construction, eliminating the need for additional model training beyond skill learning. Furthermore, as this property is derived from dense unsupervised data, the latent space is well-structured, ensuring reliability even with sparse human feedback. Theoretical analysis justifies the effectiveness of our training-free guidance signal, while experiments across diverse state-based and pixel-based tasks show that COLLIE learns diverse, human-aligned skills, avoids hazardous behaviors, and achieves superior downstream performance with minimal human feedback.</p>","absKo":"<p>Unsupervised skill discovery(USD)는 reward function 없이 다양한 behavior를 학습하는 것을 목표로 하지만, 균일한 exploration 때문에 종종 task와 무관하거나 위험한 behavior로 이어진다. Guided skill discovery(GSD)는 인간의 의도를 반영하여 의미 있는 영역에 exploration을 집중시킴으로써 이 문제를 해결한다. 그러나 기존 GSD 방법은 일반적으로 추가 guidance model을 scratch부터 학습해야 하므로, sparse human feedback에서는 비효율적일 수 있다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 의미적으로 일관된 skill latent space를 구성하여 sparse human feedback을 효과적으로 활용하는 GSD framework인 COLLIE를 제안한다. semantical coherence property는 training-free guidance signal 구성을 가능하게 하여, skill learning 외에 추가적인 model training의 필요를 제거한다. 더 나아가, 이 property는 dense unsupervised data에서 도출되므로 latent space가 잘 구조화되어 있어, sparse human feedback 상황에서도 신뢰성을 보장한다. 이론 분석은 training-free guidance signal의 효과를 정당화하며, 다양한 state-based 및 pixel-based task에 대한 실험은 COLLIE가 다양한 인간 정렬 skill을 학습하고, 위험한 behavior를 회피하며, 최소한의 human feedback으로도 우수한 downstream performance를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63337","en":"TimeRewarder: Learning Dense Reward from Passive Videos via Frame-wise Temporal Distance","ko":"TimeRewarder: 프레임별 시간 거리를 통한 수동적 비디오로부터의 조밀 보상 학습","authors":"Yuyang Liu, Chuan Wen, Yihang Hu, Dinesh Jayaraman, Yang Gao","pos":"#120","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XztRm216YS","abs":"<p>Designing dense rewards is crucial for reinforcement learning (RL), yet in robotics it often demands extensive manual effort and lacks scalability. One promising solution is to view task progress as a dense reward signal, as it quantifies the degree to which actions advance the system toward task completion over time. We present TimeRewarder, a simple yet effective reward learning method that derives progress estimation signals from passive videos, including robot demonstrations and human videos, by modeling temporal distances between frame pairs. We then demonstrate how TimeRewarder can supply step-wise proxy rewards to guide reinforcement learning. In our comprehensive experiments on ten challenging Meta-World tasks, we show that TimeRewarder dramatically improves RL for sparse-reward tasks, achieving nearly perfect success in 9/10 tasks with only 200,000 interactions per task with the environment. This approach outperforms previous methods and even the manually designed environment dense reward on both the final success rate and sample efficiency. Moreover, we show that TimeRewarder pretraining can exploit real-world human videos, highlighting its potential as a scalable approach to rich reward signals from diverse video sources.</p>","absKo":"<p>dense reward를 설계하는 일은 reinforcement learning(RL)에 매우 중요하지만, robotics에서는 종종 많은 수작업 노력이 필요하고 확장성이 떨어진다. 유망한 해결책 중 하나는 task progress를 dense reward signal로 보는 것이다. 이는 행동이 시간에 따라 system을 task 완료 쪽으로 얼마나 진전시키는지를 정량화하기 때문이다. 우리는 TimeRewarder를 제안하는데, 이는 robot demonstration과 human video를 포함한 passive video로부터 frame pair 간 temporal distance를 모델링하여 progress estimation signal을 도출하는 간단하지만 효과적인 reward learning 방법이다. 그런 다음 TimeRewarder가 reinforcement learning을 안내하는 step-wise proxy reward를 어떻게 제공할 수 있는지 보여준다. ten challenging Meta-World task에 대한 포괄적인 실험에서, TimeRewarder가 sparse-reward task의 RL을 극적으로 개선하여 task당 환경과의 interaction 200,000회만으로 10개 task 중 9개에서 거의 완벽한 성공률을 달성함을 보인다. 이 접근법은 최종 성공률과 sample efficiency 모두에서 이전 방법들을 능가하며, 수작업으로 설계된 environment dense reward보다도 우수하다. 더 나아가, TimeRewarder pretraining이 실제 세계의 human video를 활용할 수 있음을 보이며, 다양한 video source로부터 풍부한 reward signal을 확장 가능하게 얻는 접근법으로서의 잠재력을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"66112","en":"Reward Learning through Ranking Mean Squared Error","ko":"순위 평균 제곱 오차를 통한 보상 학습","authors":"Chaitanya Kharyal, Calarina Muslimani, Matthew Taylor","pos":"#121","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6wQKBHi0qO","abs":"<p>Reward design remains a significant bottleneck in applying reinforcement learning (RL) to real-world problems.  A popular alternative is reward learning, where reward functions are inferred from human feedback rather than manually specified. Recent work has proposed learning reward functions from human ratings rather than traditional binary preferences, enabling richer and potentially less cognitively demanding supervision.  Building on this paradigm, we introduce a new rating-based RL method,  Ranked Return Regression for RL (R4). At its core, R4 uses a novel ranking mean squared error loss that learns from a dataset of trajectory–rating pairs, treating the human-provided discrete ratings (e.g., \"bad,\" \"neutral,\" \"good\") as ordinal targets. Unlike prior rating-based approaches, R4 offers formal guarantees: its solution set is provably minimal and complete under mild assumptions. Empirically, using both human-provided and simulated ratings, we demonstrate that R4 consistently matches or outperforms existing rating and preference-based RL methods on robotic benchmarks from OpenAI Gym and the DeepMind Control Suite.</p>"},{"id":"65675","en":"Provably Efficient Policy-Reward Co-Pretraining for Adversarial Imitation Learning","ko":"적대적 모방 학습을 위한 증명 가능하게 효율적인 정책-보상 공동 사전학습","authors":"Tian Xu, Zexuan Chen, Zhilong Zhang, Yi-Chen Li, Chenyang Wang, lei yuan, Yang Yu","pos":"#122","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BJUEgspMUt","abs":"<p>Adversarial imitation learning (AIL) demonstrates superior expert sample efficiency compared to behavioral cloning (BC), yet requires substantial online environment interaction. While recent empirical work has explored initializing AIL algorithms with BC-pretrained policies to address this limitation, a rigorous theoretical understanding of pretraining's role in AIL remains lacking. This paper provides a systematic theoretical analysis and develops principled pretraining algorithms for accelerating AIL. We first analyze AIL with policy pretraining alone, identifying reward error as the dominant error source and thereby uncovering a critical yet previously unexplored gap: the omission of reward pretraining. Leveraging this insight, we introduce a principled policy-reward co-pretraining mechanism through reward-shaping analysis. Our analysis reveals a fundamental connection between expert policies and shaping rewards, naturally motivating CoPT-AIL, an approach that jointly pretrains both policies and rewards through a single BC procedure. We prove that CoPT-AIL achieves an improved imitation gap bound compared to standard AIL, establishing the first theoretical guarantee for pretraining benefits in AIL. Experimental results validate CoPT-AIL's superior performance over existing AIL methods.</p>"},{"id":"63886","en":"Noise-Guided Transport: Imitation Learning from Random Priors","ko":"Noise-Guided Transport: 무작위 prior로부터의 모방 학습","authors":"Lionel Blondé, Joao A. Candido Ramos, Alexandros Kalousis","pos":"#123","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Smoegnco1C","abs":"<p>We consider imitation learning in the low-data regime, where only a limited number of expert demonstrations are available. In this setting, methods that rely on large-scale pretraining or high-capacity architectures can be difficult to apply, and efficiency with respect to demonstration data becomes critical. We introduce Noise-Guided Transport (NGT), a lightweight off-policy method that casts imitation as an optimal transport problem solved via adversarial training. NGT requires no pretraining or specialized architectures, incorporates uncertainty estimation by design, and is easy to implement and tune. Despite its simplicity, NGT achieves strong performance on challenging continuous control tasks, including high-dimensional Humanoid tasks, under ultra-low data regimes with as few as 20 transitions.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 제한된 수의 expert demonstration만 이용할 수 있는 low-data regime에서의 imitation learning을 다룬다. 이러한 설정에서는 대규모 pretraining이나 high-capacity architecture에 의존하는 방법을 적용하기 어렵고, demonstration data에 대한 효율성이 매우 중요하다. 우리는 adversarial training을 통해 푸는 optimal transport 문제로 imitation을 정식화하는 lightweight off-policy method인 Noise-Guided Transport (NGT)를 소개한다. NGT는 pretraining이나 특수한 architecture를 전혀 요구하지 않으며, 설계상 uncertainty estimation을 포함하고 구현과 튜닝이 쉽다. 이 단순함에도 불구하고, NGT는 transition이 고작 20개에 불과한 ultra-low data regime에서도 high-dimensional Humanoid task를 포함한 어려운 continuous control task에서 강한 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"66531","en":"Fast and Highly Expressive Policy Learning for Offline Reinforcement Learning via Bootstrapped Flow Q-Learning","ko":"Bootstrapped Flow Q-Learning을 통한 오프라인 강화 학습을 위한 빠르고 표현력 높은 정책 학습","authors":"Thanh Nguyen, Tri Ton, Hongbin Choe, Minh-Tung Luu, Chang D. Yoo","pos":"#206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2rGr38p5az","abs":"<p>Diffusion-based Q-learning has emerged as a powerful paradigm for offline reinforcement learning, but its reliance on multi-step denoising makes both training and inference computationally expensive and brittle. Recent efforts to accelerate diffusion Q-learning toward single-step action generation typically introduce auxiliary networks, policy distillation, or multi-phase training, which frequently compromise simplicity, stability, or performance. To address these limitations, we introduce Bootstrapped Flow Q-Learning (BFQ), a novel framework that enables accurate single-step action generation during both training and inference—without auxiliary networks or distillation procedures. BFQ adopts a divide-and-conquer view of the displacement vector along the flow path: it begins by learning short-range displacements that can be accurately estimated from the Flow Matching marginal velocity, and bootstraps these components to directly learn a noise-to-action mapping in a single step. This formulation eliminates multi-step denoising, resulting in a learning procedure that is substantially faster, simpler, and more robust. Extensive D4RL evaluations show that BFQ improves performance while significantly reducing computational cost compared to multi-step diffusion baselines, demonstrating that single-step action generation suffices for high-performance offline Reinforcement Learning.</p>"},{"id":"65679","en":"PRPO: Paragraph-level Policy Optimization for Vision-Language Deepfake Detection","ko":"PRPO: Vision-Language 딥페이크 탐지를 위한 문단 수준 정책 최적화","authors":"Tuan Nguyen, Naseem Khan, Khang Tran, Hai Phan, Issa Khalil","pos":"#208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BGcw0KWStP","abs":"<p>The rapid rise of synthetic media has made deepfake detection a critical challenge for online safety and trust. Progress remains constrained by the scarcity of large, high-quality datasets. Although multimodal large language models (LLMs) exhibit strong reasoning capabilities, their performance on deepfake detection is poor, often producing explanations that are misaligned with visual evidence or hallucinatory. To address this limitation, we introduce a reasoning-annotated dataset for deepfake detection and propose Paragraph-level Relative Policy Optimization (PRPO), a reinforcement learning algorithm that aligns LLM reasoning with image content at the paragraph level. Experiments show that PRPO improves detection accuracy by a wide margin and achieves the highest reasoning score of 4.55/5.0. Ablation studies further demonstrate that PRPO significantly outperforms GRPO under test-time conditions. These results underscore the importance of grounding multimodal reasoning in visual evidence to enable more reliable and interpretable deepfake detection.</p>"},{"id":"60986","en":"Beyond Token-level Supervision: Unlocking the Potential of Decoding-based Regression via Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Token-level Supervision을 넘어: Reinforcement Learning으로 Decoding-based Regression의 잠재력 열기","authors":"Ming Chen, Sheng Tang, Rong-Xi Tan, Ziniu Li, Jiacheng Chen, Ke Xue, Chao Qian","pos":"#210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ul2qlPcb5Y","abs":"Decoding-based regression, which reformulates regression as a sequence generation task, has emerged as a promising paradigm of applying large language models for numerical prediction. However, its progress is hindered by the misalignment between discrete token-level objectives (e.g., cross-entropy) and continuous numerical values. Existing approaches relying on token-level constraints often fail to capture the global magnitude of the target value, limiting their precision and generalization. In this paper, we propose to unlock the potential of decoding-based regression via reinforcement learning. We formulate the generation process as a Markov decision process, utilizing sequence-level rewards to enforce global numerical coherence. Under this framework, we present GenRe$^2$, which combines policy gradient methods to preserve error magnitudes with dense expert supervision, resolving the temporal credit assignment challenge. Extensive experiments across tabular regression, code metric prediction and generative reward modeling demonstrate that GenRe$^2$ consistently outperforms traditional baselines, establishing a robust paradigm for general-purpose numerical prediction.","absKo":"Decoding-based regression은 회귀를 sequence generation task로 재구성하는 방식으로, 수치 예측에 large language models를 적용하는 유망한 패러다임으로 떠올랐다. 그러나 이 접근은 discrete token-level objective(예: cross-entropy)와 연속적인 수치 값 사이의 불일치로 인해 발전이 제약되고 있다. 기존의 token-level constraint에 의존하는 방법들은 종종 target value의 전역적 크기(global magnitude)를 포착하지 못해 정밀도와 일반화 능력이 제한된다. 본 논문에서는 reinforcement learning을 통해 decoding-based regression의 잠재력을 끌어내고자 한다. 우리는 생성 과정을 Markov decision process로 정식화하고, sequence-level reward를 활용해 전역적인 수치 일관성(global numerical coherence)을 강제한다. 이 프레임워크 아래에서 우리는 GenRe$^2$를 제안하는데, 이는 error magnitude를 보존하는 policy gradient method와 dense expert supervision을 결합하여 temporal credit assignment 문제를 해결한다. tabular regression, code metric prediction, generative reward modeling 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 GenRe$^2$가 전통적인 baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보여주며, 범용 수치 예측을 위한 견고한 패러다임을 확립한다."},{"id":"61158","en":"Flow Inverse Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Flow 역강화학습","authors":"Zhenglin Wan, Jingxuan Wu, Xingrui Yu, Chubin Zhang, Mingcong Lei, Bo An, Ivor Tsang, Yang You","pos":"#211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tAhdexEwnz","abs":"<p>Flow Matching (FM) has shown remarkable ability in modeling complex distributions and achieves strong performance in offline imitation learning for cloning expert behaviors. However, despite its behavioral cloning expressiveness, FM-based policies are inherently limited by their lack of environmental interaction and exploration. This leads to poor generalization in unseen scenarios beyond the expert demonstrations, underscoring the necessity of online interaction with environment. Unfortunately, optimizing FM policies via online interaction is challenging and inefficient due to instability in gradient computation and high inference costs. To address these issues, we propose to let a \"student'' policy with simple MLP structure to explore the environment and be online updated via RL algorithm with a reward model. This reward model is associated with a \"teacher'' FM model, containing rich information of expert data distribution. Furthermore, the same \"teacher'' FM model is utilized to regularize the \"student'' policy's behavior to stabilize policy learning. Due to the student’s simple architecture, we avoid the gradient instability of FM policies and enable efficient online exploration, while still leveraging the expressiveness of the teacher FM model. Extensive experiments shows that our approach significantly enhances learning efficiency, generalization, and robustness, especially when learning from suboptimal expert data.</p>","absKo":"<p>Flow Matching (FM)은 복잡한 분포를 모델링하는 데 뛰어난 능력을 보이며, expert behavior를 cloning하는 offline imitation learning에서 강력한 성능을 달성한다. 그러나 behavioral cloning의 표현력에도 불구하고, FM 기반 policy는 본질적으로 환경과의 상호작용과 exploration이 부족하다는 한계를 가진다. 그 결과 expert demonstration을 넘어서는 미지의 상황에서 generalization이 좋지 않으며, 이는 환경과의 online interaction의 필요성을 강조한다. 아쉽게도 FM policy를 online interaction으로 최적화하는 것은 gradient computation의 불안정성과 높은 inference cost 때문에 어렵고 비효율적이다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 단순한 MLP 구조를 가진 \"student\" policy가 환경을 탐색하도록 하고, reward model을 사용한 RL algorithm으로 online update되도록 하자고 제안한다. 이 reward model은 rich information of expert data distribution을 포함하는 \"teacher\" FM model과 연결되어 있다. 더 나아가, 동일한 \"teacher\" FM model을 활용하여 \"student\" policy의 행동을 regularize함으로써 policy learning을 안정화한다. student의 단순한 architecture 덕분에 우리는 FM policy의 gradient instability를 피하고 효율적인 online exploration을 가능하게 하면서도, teacher FM model의 표현력을 계속 활용할 수 있다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 특히 suboptimal expert data로부터 학습할 때 학습 효율성, generalization, robustness를 유의미하게 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61804","en":"Noise-corrected GRPO: From Noisy Rewards to Unbiased Gradients","ko":"Noise-corrected GRPO: 노이즈가 있는 보상에서 편향 없는 그래디언트로","authors":"Omar Elmansouri, Fathinah Izzati, Mohamed El Amine Seddik, Salem Lahlou","pos":"#212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mnU8odBWYE","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) or verifiable rewards (RLVR), the standard paradigm for aligning LLMs or building recent SOTA reasoning models, is highly sensitive to noise from inconsistent or erroneous rewards. Yet, the interaction between such noise and widely used group-based policy optimization methods remains underexplored. We introduce a noise-robust Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) and Done Right GRPO (Dr.GRPO) framework that explicitly models reward corruption as Bernoulli noise. Our method applies noise correction after estimating reward flip probabilities to debias the learning signal, yielding unbiased gradient estimates. Theoretical analysis shows that group-based methods inherently mitigate individual-level noise, and our correction strategy amplifies this robustness. Empirically, we observe consistent improvements across math and code tasks when applying our noise correction to standard reward model usage, with particular gains of up to 6.7 percentage points in accuracy on math tasks and 1.5 on code tasks under realistic reward model conditions. This work bridges label-noise correction from supervised learning with modern RLHF, offering both theoretical insights and a practical algorithm for noisy real-world deployment.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement learning from human feedback(RLHF) 또는 verifiable rewards(RLVR)는 LLM을 정렬하거나 최근의 SOTA reasoning model을 구축하는 표준 패러다임이지만, 일관되지 않거나 오류가 있는 reward에서 오는 noise에 매우 민감하다. 그럼에도 이러한 noise와 널리 사용되는 group-based policy optimization method의 상호작용은 아직 충분히 연구되지 않았다. 우리는 reward corruption을 Bernoulli noise로 명시적으로 모델링하는 noise-robust Group Relative Policy Optimization(GRPO) 및 Done Right GRPO(Dr.GRPO) 프레임워크를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 reward flip probability를 추정한 뒤 noise correction을 적용하여 learning signal의 bias를 제거하고, 그 결과 unbiased gradient estimate를 도출한다. 이론적 분석은 group-based method가 본질적으로 individual-level noise를 완화하며, 우리의 correction 전략이 이러한 robustness를 더욱 증폭시킨다는 점을 보여준다. 실증적으로는 standard reward model 사용에 이 noise correction을 적용했을 때 수학 및 코드 과제 전반에서 일관된 향상을 관찰했으며, 현실적인 reward model 조건 하에서 수학 과제 정확도는 최대 6.7 percentage point, 코드 과제에서는 1.5 percentage point까지 향상되었다. 이 연구는 supervised learning의 label-noise correction과 현대 RLHF를 연결하며, 이론적 통찰과 함께 noisy real-world deployment를 위한 실용적 알고리즘을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66069","en":"POLIA: Policy Optimization with Visual-Object-Level Intrinsic Advantage for Multimodal Reasoning","ko":"POLIA: 멀티모달 추론을 위한 시각-객체 수준 내재적 이점 기반 정책 최적화","authors":"Yiran Zeng, Da Chen, Hangyu Mao, Yuanxing Zhang, Pengfei Wan, Mengchen Zhao","pos":"#213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7KaO3EahTO","abs":"<p>Recent advances in group-based reinforcement learning (RL) greatly improve LLMs' ability in text reasoning. Yet, these methods lack sufficient modeling of multimodal information, leading to significant reasoning hallucination. In this work, we propose POLIA, a novel group-based RL method with visual-object-level intrinsic advantage for multimodal reasoning. POLIA introduces two advantage computation stages over candidate answers and visual objects, respectively. The answer-level extrinsic advantages are computed based on the extrinsic rewards of a group of candidate answers. Moreover, we compute an intrinsic advantage for each visual object based on its confidence score and reference relations with final answers. Intuitively, the intrinsic advantage of an object reflects its potential contribution to the correct answer. This two-stage advantage computation ensures an accurate credit assignment mechanism over multimodal reasoning sequences with multiple visual objects. Experimental results on diverse multimodal reasoning benchmarks show that POLIA significantly outperforms open MLLMs and strong baselines. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/POLIA-AB1D.</p>"},{"id":"66789","en":"AdverMCTS: Combating Pseudo-Correctness in Code Generation via Adversarial Monte Carlo Tree Search","ko":"AdverMCTS: Adversarial Monte Carlo Tree Search를 통해 코드 생성에서 Pseudo-Correctness에 대응","authors":"Qingyao Li, Weiwen Liu, Weinan Zhang, Yong Yu, Bo An","pos":"#2211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0JpXqndUrA","abs":"<p>Recent advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs) have successfully employed search-based strategies to enhance code generation. However, existing methods typically rely on static, sparse public test cases for verification, leading to pseudo-correctness—where solutions overfit the visible public tests but fail to generalize to hidden test cases. We argue that optimizing against a fixed, weak environment inherently limits robustness. To address this, we propose AdverMCTS, a novel adversarial Monte Carlo Tree Search framework that combats pseudo-correctness by coupling code search with active vulnerability discovery. AdverMCTS formulates generation as a minimax-style game between a Solver agent, which synthesizes code candidates, and an Attacker agent, which evolves to generate targeted test cases that exploit logical divergences in the current solution pool. These discovered tests form a dynamic, progressively hostile filter that penalizes fragile reasoning. Extensive experiments demonstrate that AdverMCTS significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, effectively reducing false positive rates and forcing the model to generalize beyond the initial constraints. The resources of this work are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/AdverMCTS_open-A255.</p>"},{"id":"63476","en":"Unsupervised Hierarchical Skill Discovery","ko":"비지도 계층적 기술 발견","authors":"Damion Harvey, Steven James, Benjamin Rosman, Branden Ingram, Geraud Nangue Tasse","pos":"#4013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Wrywrky3Fk","abs":"<p>We consider the problem of unsupervised skill segmentation and hierarchical structure discovery in reinforcement learning. While recent approaches have sought to segment trajectories into reusable skills or options, most rely on action labels, rewards, or handcrafted annotations, limiting their applicability. We propose a method that segments unlabelled trajectories into skills and induces a hierarchical structure over them using a grammar-based approach. The resulting hierarchy captures both low-level behaviours and their composition into higher-level skills. We evaluate our approach in high-dimensional, pixel-based environments, including Craftax and the full, unmodified version of Minecraft. Using metrics for skill segmentation, reuse, and hierarchy quality, we find that our method consistently produces more structured and semantically meaningful hierarchies than existing baselines. Furthermore, as a proof of concept for utility, we demonstrate that these discovered hierarchies accelerate and stabilise learning on downstream reinforcement learning tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 reinforcement learning에서의 unsupervised skill segmentation과 hierarchical structure discovery 문제를 다룬다. 최근 접근법들은 trajectory를 재사용 가능한 skill 또는 option으로 분할하려 했지만, 대부분 action label, reward 또는 수작업 annotation에 의존하여 적용 가능성이 제한된다. 우리는 grammar-based approach를 사용하여 unlabeled trajectory를 skill로 분할하고 그 위에 hierarchical structure를 유도하는 방법을 제안한다. 그 결과로 얻어지는 hierarchy는 저수준 행동과 그것들이 결합되어 형성하는 더 높은 수준의 skill 모두를 포착한다. 우리는 Craftax와 Minecraft의 전체, 수정되지 않은 버전을 포함한 고차원 pixel 기반 환경에서 우리의 접근법을 평가한다. skill segmentation, reuse, hierarchy quality를 위한 metric을 사용한 결과, 우리의 방법은 기존 baseline보다 일관되게 더 구조화되고 의미적으로 타당한 hierarchy를 생성함을 확인하였다. 더 나아가, 유용성의 proof of concept으로서, 이렇게 발견된 hierarchy가 downstream reinforcement learning task에서 학습을 가속하고 안정화함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63303","en":"Beyond Policy Training: Recursive Solution Search from Unannotated Videos","ko":"정책 학습을 넘어서: 주석 없는 비디오로부터의 재귀적 해 탐색","authors":"Lipeng Wan, Jianhui Gu, Junjie Ma, Anbang Wang, Xuguang Lan","pos":"#411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YHneIkYYTT","abs":"<p>Many real-world tasks are recorded as large collections of unannotated task executions, such as videos, which contain rich information about task progress but lack the supervision assumed by standard reinforcement learning (RL) pipelines. In many practical settings, the goal is not to train a reusable policy but simply to recover one feasible solution, making policy-centered learning unnecessarily costly. We propose Policy-Free Recursive Search (PFR-Search), a framework that directly recovers solutions from unannotated task executions without policy-grounded supervision or policy training. PFR-Search organizes videos into high-level task flows and performs recursive backward-forward search to recover solutions without policy modeling. To evaluate the efficiency of policy-free search in exploiting unannotated data, we use RL as an evaluation interface, incorporating task-flow-aligned intrinsic rewards and compare against video-driven RL methods. Experiments on long-horizon Minecraft tasks show that PFR-Search recovers feasible solutions from unannotated videos with minimal exploration.</p>","absKo":"<p>많은 실제 세계 과제는 비주석(task annotation이 없는) task execution의 대규모 집합으로 기록되며, 예를 들어 video처럼 task 진행에 대한 풍부한 정보를 담고 있지만 standard reinforcement learning (RL) pipeline이 가정하는 supervision은 갖추고 있지 않습니다. 많은 실용적 설정에서 목표는 재사용 가능한 policy를 학습하는 것이 아니라 단지 하나의 feasible solution을 복원하는 것에 있으므로, policy 중심 학습은 불필요하게 비용이 큽니다. 우리는 Policy-Free Recursive Search (PFR-Search)를 제안합니다. 이는 policy-grounded supervision이나 policy training 없이, 비주석 task execution으로부터 solution을 직접 복원하는 framework입니다. PFR-Search는 video를 high-level task flow로 조직하고, policy modeling 없이 solution을 복원하기 위해 recursive backward-forward search를 수행합니다. 비주석 data 활용에서 policy-free search의 효율성을 평가하기 위해, task-flow에 정렬된 intrinsic reward를 포함하는 RL을 evaluation interface로 사용하고, video-driven RL method들과 비교합니다. 긴 horizon의 Minecraft task에서 수행한 실험은 PFR-Search가 최소한의 exploration으로 비주석 video로부터 feasible solution을 복원함을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"67137","en":"Position: Agentic Systems Should be General","ko":"Position: Agentic 시스템은 범용적이어야 한다","authors":"Elron Bandel, Asaf Yehudai, Alexandre Lacoste, Avijit Ghosh, Graham Neubig, Margaret Mitchell, Michal Shmueli-Scheuer, Leshem Choshen","pos":"#1712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WMYI7TFDmi","abs":"<p>We call for the development of agentic systems that thrive in new environments. Agentic systems, comprising foundation models, tools, and an execution strategy, have demonstrated strong capabilities, yet their development is often constrained by narrow benchmarks and their operation is siloed to limited environments.  This paper advocates for developing general, adaptive agents that excel across diverse environments, from terminals and web interfaces to biological and embodied settings. We examine current limitations, explain the potential of increased generality, and identify immediate development priorities. Finally, we argue that protocols and evaluation must prioritize adaptiveness to foster a shared ecosystem for general-purpose agentic systems.</p>"},{"id":"67190","en":"Position: Prompting Intent Should Be Audited in LLM-Assisted Peer Review","ko":"Position: LLM 보조 Peer Review에서 Prompting 의도는 감사되어야 한다","authors":"Lijinghua Zhang, Michelle Bang, Hengrui Cai","pos":"#1710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HnB0EAQWYf","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that <em>prompting intent should be audited in LLM-assisted peer review</em>, moving beyond the sole detection or disclosure of LLM usage. As major conferences increasingly allow LLM assistance and deploy mechanisms for detecting LLM-generated text, a critical gap remains: usage alone does not determine risk. A more consequential variable is <em>prompting intent</em>, the objective or stance encoded in how an LLM is instructed, which can systematically shape review framing and tone.  We advocate an <em>intent-centric auditing perspective</em> that treats prompting intent as latent and infers relevant signals from the review text. Because intent is unobservable in real deployments, we train an intent detector using synthetically labeled LLM-generated reviews. Among ICLR 2026 reviews previously flagged for substantial LLM usage, we apply our detector to infer prompting intent and find coherent linguistic and structural signatures associated with directional prompting, along with systematic associations with review ratings, confidence, and paper acceptance decisions. We conclude with practical considerations for auditing LLM-assisted peer review, with an emphasis on procedural transparency and human-in-the-loop oversight.</p>"},{"id":"67117","en":"Position: Multiple Definitions & Unrealistic Assumptions of Model Collapse Distract from Real World Threats","ko":"Position: Model Collapse의 다중 정의와 비현실적 가정이 실세계 위협에서 주의를 분산시킨다","authors":"Rylan Schaeffer, Joshua Kazdan, Alvan Arulandu, Sanmi Koyejo","pos":"#2412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=e09cM5W8vd","abs":"<p>The proliferation of AI-generated content online has fueled concerns over \\textit{model collapse}, a degradation in future generative models' performance when trained on synthetic data generated by earlier models. Industry leaders, premier research journals and popular science publications alike have prophesied catastrophic societal consequences stemming from model collapse. In this position piece, we contend this widespread narrative fundamentally misunderstands the scientific evidence. We highlight that research on model collapse actually encompasses eight distinct and at times conflicting definitions of model collapse, and argue that inconsistent terminology within and between papers has hindered building a comprehensive understanding of model collapse. To assess how significantly different interpretations of model collapse threaten future generative models, we posit what we believe are realistic conditions for studying model collapse and then conduct a rigorous assessment of the literature's methodologies through this lens. While we leave room for reasonable disagreement, our analysis of research studies, weighted by how faithfully each study matches real-world conditions, leads us to conclude that certain predicted claims of model collapse rely on assumptions and conditions that poorly match real-world conditions, and in fact several prominent collapse scenarios are readily avoidable. Altogether, this position paper argues that model collapse has been warped from a nuanced multifaceted consideration into an oversimplified threat, and that the evidence suggests specific harms more likely under society's current trajectory have received disproportionately less attention.</p>"},{"id":"68815","en":"Wikipedia in the Era of LLMs: Evolution and Risks","ko":"LLM 시대의 Wikipedia: 진화와 위험","authors":"Siming Huang, Yuliang Xu, Mingmeng Geng, Yao Wan, Dongping Chen","pos":"#2913","abs":"<p>In this paper, we present a comprehensive analysis and monitoring framework for the impact of Large Language Models (LLMs) on Wikipedia, examining the evolution of Wikipedia through existing data and using simulations to explore potential risks. We begin by analyzing article content and page views to study the recent changes in Wikipedia and assess the impact of LLMs. Subsequently, we evaluate how LLMs affect various Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks related to Wikipedia, including machine translation and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG). Our findings and simulation results reveal that Wikipedia articles have been affected by LLMs, with an impact of approximately 1% in certain categories. If the machine translation benchmark based on Wikipedia is influenced by LLMs, the scores of the models may become inflated, and the comparative results among models could shift. Moreover, the effectiveness of RAG might decrease if the knowledge has been contaminated by LLMs. While LLMs have not yet fully changed Wikipedia's language and knowledge structures, we believe that our empirical findings signal the need for careful consideration of potential future risks in NLP research.</p>"},{"id":"60714","en":"DualOptim+: Bridging Shared and Decoupled Optimizer States for Better Machine Unlearning in Large Language Models","ko":"DualOptim+: Large Language Model의 더 나은 Machine Unlearning을 위한 Shared 및 Decoupled Optimizer State 연결","authors":"Xuyang Zhong, Qizhang Li, Yiwen Guo, Chen Liu","pos":"#3003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xGfnQajGPQ","abs":"<p>We propose <strong>DualOptim+</strong>, a novel optimization framework for improving machine unlearning in large language models. It introduces a base state to capture common representations shared by forgetting and retaining objectives and delta states to preserve objective-specific residuals. This architecture allows the optimizer to adaptively bridge shared and decoupled states based on the directional conflict between forgetting and retaining gradients. We further introduce DualOptim+ 8bit, a quantized variant that reduces memory overhead without compromising performance. Extensive experiments across fictitious, real-world, and safety alignment tasks demonstrate that DualOptim+ consistently achieves a superior trade-off between forgetting efficacy and model utility.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 large language models에서 machine unlearning을 개선하기 위한 새로운 optimization framework인 <strong>DualOptim+</strong>를 제안한다. 이 방법은 forgetting objective와 retaining objective가 공유하는 common representation을 포착하기 위한 base state와, objective-specific residual을 보존하기 위한 delta states를 도입한다. 이 구조는 optimizer가 forgetting gradients와 retaining gradients 사이의 directional conflict를 바탕으로 shared state와 decoupled state를 적응적으로 연결할 수 있게 한다. 또한 메모리 오버헤드를 줄이면서도 성능을 저하시키지 않는 quantized variant인 DualOptim+ 8bit를 추가로 제안한다. 가상, 실제, safety alignment task 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 DualOptim+가 forgetting efficacy와 model utility 사이에서 일관되게 더 우수한 trade-off를 달성함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"63878","en":"Learning When to Act or Refuse: Guarding Agentic Reasoning Models for Safe Multi-Step Tool Use","ko":"행동할지 거부할지 학습하기: 안전한 다단계 도구 사용을 위한 agentic reasoning model 보호","authors":"Aradhye Agarwal, Gurdit Singh Siyan, Yash Pandya, Joykirat Singh, Akshay Nambi, Ahmed Awadallah","pos":"#3006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Stf5SF4JvR","abs":"<p>Agentic language models operate in a fundamentally different safety regime than chat models: they must plan, call tools, and execute long-horizon actions where a single misstep, such as accessing files or entering credentials, can cause irreversible harm. Existing alignment methods, largely optimized for static generation and task completion, break down in these settings due to sequential decision-making, adversarial tool feedback, and overconfident intermediate reasoning. We introduce MOSAIC, a post-training framework that aligns agents for safe multi-step tool use by making safety decisions explicit and learnable. MOSAIC structures inference as a plan, check, then act or refuse loop, with explicit safety reasoning and refusal as first-class actions. To train without trajectory-level labels, we use preference-based reinforcement learning with pairwise trajectory comparisons, which captures safety distinctions often missed by scalar rewards. We evaluate MOSAIC zero-shot across three model families, Qwen2.5-7B, Qwen3-4B-Thinking, and Phi-4, and across out-of-distribution benchmarks spanning harmful tasks, prompt injection, benign tool use, and cross-domain privacy leakage. MOSAIC reduces harmful behavior by up to 50\\%, increases harmful-task refusal by over 20\\% on injection attacks, cuts privacy leakage, and preserves or improves benign task performance, demonstrating robust generalization across models, domains, and agentic settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>Agentic language model은 chat model과 근본적으로 다른 safety regime에서 작동한다. 이들은 계획을 세우고, tool을 호출하며, 장기적 horizon의 action을 실행해야 하며, 파일 접근이나 credential 입력 같은 단 하나의 실수도 돌이킬 수 없는 피해를 초래할 수 있다. 주로 static generation과 task completion에 최적화된 기존 alignment 방법들은 sequential decision-making, adversarial tool feedback, 그리고 지나치게 확신하는 intermediate reasoning 때문에 이러한 환경에서 제대로 작동하지 않는다. 우리는 안전한 multi-step tool 사용을 위해 agent를 정렬하는 post-training framework인 MOSAIC을 도입하며, 안전 결정을 명시적이고 학습 가능한 것으로 만든다. MOSAIC은 inference를 plan, check, then act or refuse loop로 구조화하고, 명시적 safety reasoning과 refusal을 일급 행동(first-class action)으로 다룬다. trajectory-level label 없이 학습하기 위해, 우리는 pairwise trajectory comparison을 사용하는 preference-based reinforcement learning을 활용하며, 이는 scalar reward가 자주 놓치는 safety 차이를 포착한다. 우리는 Qwen2.5-7B, Qwen3-4B-Thinking, Phi-4의 세 model family에서 zero-shot으로 MOSAIC을 평가하고, harmful task, prompt injection, benign tool use, cross-domain privacy leakage를 포괄하는 out-of-distribution benchmark 전반에서 검증한다. MOSAIC은 harmful behavior를 최대 50\\%까지 줄이고, injection attack에서 harmful-task refusal을 20\\% 이상 높이며, privacy leakage를 감소시키고, benign task 성능을 유지하거나 향상시켜, model, domain, agentic setting 전반에서 강건한 generalization을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"67084","en":"Position: AI/ML Deepfake Research is Misaligned with AI Generated Non-Consensual Intimate Imagery (AIG-NCII)","ko":"Position: AI/ML Deepfake 연구는 AI 생성 비합의 친밀 이미지(AIG-NCII)와 어긋나 있다","authors":"Qiwei Li, Wells Lucas Santo, Sarita Schoenebeck, Eric Gilbert","pos":"#3008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mLhZzo7BIb","abs":"<p>AI-generated non-consensual intimate imagery (AIG-NCII) is not adequately addressed in AI/ML literature regarding AI-generated media, commonly referred to as \"deepfakes\". While research on deepfakes currently focuses on its epistemic harms—or harms relating to truth and authenticity—this is misaligned with the dominant reality of generative AI abuse involving sexualized imagery. We conduct a landscape analysis of highly-cited works to demonstrate that technical interventions addressing deepfakes almost entirely ignore AIG-NCII, limiting the research ecosystem to authenticity detection tools. In this position paper, we argue that existing interventions address viewer-centric epistemic harms, such as fraud or scams, but ignore subject-centric dignity harms, such as AIG-NCII. We illustrate that knowing an image is synthetic does not mitigate harms to subjects and may, in some cases, even exacerbate them. We conclude by offering recommendations to realign the field, including updating threat models to consider subject-centered harms and addressing AIG-NCII in AI safety research. Finally, we caution that researchers should only engage in this high-risk domain if they implement safety guardrails for both subjects and researchers and establish partnerships with domain experts in sexual violence prevention.</p>"},{"id":"61287","en":"Tackling Fake Forgetting through Uncertainty Quantification","ko":"불확실성 정량화를 통한 Fake Forgetting 해결","authors":"Yingdan Shi, Sijia Liu, Kaize Ding, Ren Wang","pos":"#3013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rjmVJaBpkm","abs":"<p>Machine unlearning seeks to remove the influence of specified data from a trained model. While the unlearning accuracy provides a widely used metric for assessing unlearning performance, it falls short in assessing the reliability of forgetting. In this paper, we find that the forgetting data points misclassified by unlearning accuracy still have their ground truth labels included in the conformal prediction set from the uncertainty quantification perspective, leading to a phenomenon we term fake forgetting. To address this issue, we propose a novel metric CR, inspired by conformal prediction, that offers a more reliable assessment of forgetting quality. Building on these insights, we further propose an unlearning framework CPU that incorporates conformal prediction into the Carlini &amp; Wagner adversarial attack loss, enabling the ground truth label to be effectively removed from the conformal prediction set. Through extensive experiments on image classification tasks, we demonstrate both the effectiveness of our proposed metric and the superior forgetting quality achieved by our framework. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MUCP-60E4.</p>","absKo":"<p>Machine unlearning은 학습된 model에서 특정 data의 영향을 제거하는 것을 목표로 한다. unlearning accuracy는 unlearning 성능을 평가하는 널리 사용되는 metric이지만, forgetting의 신뢰성을 평가하기에는 한계가 있다. 본 논문에서는 unlearning accuracy에 의해 잘못 분류된 forgetting data point라도 uncertainty quantification 관점에서 그 ground truth label이 conformal prediction set에 여전히 포함되는 현상을 발견했으며, 이를 fake forgetting이라 명명한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 conformal prediction에서 영감을 받은 새로운 metric CR을 제안하며, 이는 forgetting quality를 더 신뢰성 있게 평가할 수 있게 한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 Carlini &amp; Wagner adversarial attack loss에 conformal prediction을 통합한 unlearning framework CPU를 추가로 제안하여, ground truth label이 conformal prediction set에서 효과적으로 제거되도록 한다. 이미지 분류 task에 대한 광범위한 실험을 통해, 우리는 제안한 metric의 효과와 우리 framework가 달성하는 우수한 forgetting quality를 입증한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MUCP-60E4 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"65799","en":"DDIM Inversion as a Perturbation Amplifier: Breaking Mimicry Protection via Reconstruction Error Minimization","ko":"섭동 증폭기로서의 DDIM Inversion: 재구성 오류 최소화를 통한 모방 보호 돌파","authors":"Huming Qiu, Peiyi Chen, Mi Zhang, Geng Hong, Xiaoyu You, Mi Wen, Min Yang","pos":"#3104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A2KdZrSSZl","abs":"<p>Personalization techniques for image generation models have increasingly been misused for malicious purposes, including unauthorized style imitation and copyrighted content replication. In response, recent mimicry protection methods embed carefully designed perturbations into images to disrupt a model’s ability to learn genuine semantic representations. Despite their growing adoption, the robustness of these protection mechanisms remains poorly understood, raising concerns about their reliability in real-world deployment. In this work, we present the first systematic analysis showing that DDIM inversion inherently acts as a perturbation amplifier, causing protected images to suffer severe structural distortions during reconstruction. Building on this observation, we propose DDIM Inversion-based Reconstruction Purification (DIRP), a novel purification approach that removes protective perturbations by explicitly minimizing DDIM inversion reconstruction error under perceptual constraints. Extensive experiments on six existing mimicry protection methods demonstrate that DIRP consistently outperforms five state-of-the-art attack baselines, achieving superior perturbation removal while better preserving image quality. Our results expose fundamental vulnerabilities in current mimicry protection strategies and highlight the urgent need for more robust and principled defenses.</p>"},{"id":"67136","en":"Position: the Stochastic Parrot in the Coal Mine. Model Collapse is a Threat to Low-Resource Communities","ko":"Position: 탄광 속의 Stochastic Parrot. Model Collapse는 저자원 커뮤니티에 대한 위협이다","authors":"Devon Jarvis, Richard Klein, Benjamin Rosman, Steven James, Stefano Sarao Mannelli","pos":"#3105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WlI0OsnkN2","abs":"<p>Model collapse, the degradation in performance that arises when generative models are trained on the outputs of prior models, is an increasing concern as artificially generated content proliferates. Related critiques of large language models have highlighted their tendency to reproduce frequent patterns in training data, their reliance on vast datasets, and their substantial environmental cost. Together, these factors contribute to data degradation, the reinforcement of cultural biases, and inefficient resource use. In this position paper we aim to combine these views and argue that model collapse threatens current efforts to democratise AI. By reducing training efficiency and skewing data distributions away from the tails of their support, model collapse disproportionately impacts low-resource and marginalized communities. We examine both the environmental and cultural implications of this phenomenon, situate our position within recent position papers on model collapse, and conclude with a call to action. Finally, we outline initial directions for mitigating these effects.</p>"},{"id":"67114","en":"Position: Neglecting the Sustainability of AI is Fuelling a Global AI Arms Race","ko":"Position: AI의 지속가능성을 소홀히 하는 것이 전 지구적 AI 군비 경쟁을 부추기고 있다","authors":"Pedram Bakhtiarifard, Pınar Tözün, Christian Igel, Raghavendra Selvan","pos":"#3108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ehvlyFUDUt","abs":"<p>Sustainability encompasses three key facets: economic, environmental, and social. However, the nascent discourse that is emerging on sustainable artificial intelligence (AI) has predominantly focused on the environmental sustainability of AI, often neglecting the economic and social aspects. Achieving truly sustainable AI necessitates addressing the tension between its climate awareness, which emphasizes the need to mitigate AI's environmental impacts, and its social sustainability, which hinges on equitable access to AI development resources. The concept of resource awareness advocates for AI sovereignty through broader access to the infrastructure required to develop AI. Yet, this push for improving accessibility often overlooks the environmental costs of expanding such resource usage. This position paper argues that reconciling climate awareness and resource awareness is essential to realizing sustainable AI and neglecting these factors fuelling the global AI arms race. By applying the base-superstructure framework from historical materialism, we analyze how the material conditions are shaping the current AI progress and the discourse surrounding it. We also introduce the Climate and Resource Aware Machine Learning (CARAML) framework to address the conflict between climate and resource awareness of AI, with actionable recommendations spanning individual, community, industry, government, and global levels to achieve sustainable AI.</p>"},{"id":"67201","en":"Position: Generative Models Erode Temporal Learning Through Market Selection","ko":"Position: Generative Model은 시장 선택을 통해 시간적 학습을 잠식한다","authors":"Wenjun Cao","pos":"#3109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FGZt2TsZRl","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that modern machine learning creates structural risks for knowledge and cultural production, operating before AGI thresholds through market selection mechanisms. We use \\emph{temporality} operationally for how understanding changes over time and signals left by that process. Representation learning and autoregressive generation approximate output distributions while omitting slow, path-dependent human learning; at scale, these function as general-purpose production technologies. We analyze the link from technical indistinguishability to market selection: when divergence between model and temporal signals is small and verification costly, decision makers cease screening, prices track pooled quality, and temporality-intensive work exits. We call this phenomenon \\emph{value collapse}. Recent evidence shows this active: academic publishing has experienced dramatic productivity increases alongside troubling quality trends; cultural production shows explosive AI-generated content adoption. As training data mirror such environments, models absorb their outputs and model collapse risk rises. Alignment is orthogonal: by narrowing observable gaps, it intensifies selection pressures where provenance remains costly.</p>"},{"id":"60487","en":"Polishing-Only Policies in Peer Reviews are Currently Not Enforceable","ko":"Peer Review에서 Polishing-Only Policy는 현재 집행 불가능하다","authors":"Rounak Saha, Gurusha Juneja, Dayita Chaudhuri, Naveeja Sajeevan, Nihar Shah, Danish Pruthi","pos":"#3110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=znFIR7WFGt","abs":"With growing concerns about  reviewers using Large Language Models (LLMs) for writing peer reviews, several conferences and journals have enacted policies thatprohibit LLM usage except for polishing, paraphrasing, and grammar correction of otherwise human-written reviews. But, are these policies enforceable? To answer this question, we assemble a dataset of peer reviews simulating multiple levels of human-AI collaboration, and evaluate $5$ state-of-the-art detectors, including two commercial systems. Our analysis shows that all detectors misclassify a substantial fraction of LLM-polished reviews as AI-generated, thereby risking false accusations of academic misconduct. We further investigate whether peer-review-specific signals, including access to the paper manuscript and the constrained domain of scientific writing, can be leveraged to improve detection. While incorporating such signals yields measurable gains in some settings, we identify limitations in each approach and find that none meets the accuracy standards required for identifying AI use in peer reviews. If enforcement of policies is a priority, we recommend completely prohibiting AI use for writing peer reviews.","absKo":"점점 더 많은 reviewers가 Large Language Models (LLMs)를 peer review 작성에 사용하고 있다는 우려가 커지면서, 여러 conference와 journal은 원래 사람이 작성한 review의 polishing, paraphrasing, grammar correction을 제외한 LLM 사용을 금지하는 정책을 시행했다. 그러나 이러한 정책은 집행 가능한가? 이 질문에 답하기 위해 우리는 human-AI collaboration의 여러 수준을 모사한 peer review dataset을 구축하고, 두 개의 commercial system을 포함한 $5$개의 state-of-the-art detector를 평가했다. 우리의 분석은 모든 detector가 LLM으로 다듬어진 review의 상당 부분을 AI-generated로 오분류하여, 학술적 부정행위에 대한 잘못된 비난의 위험을 초래함을 보여준다. 우리는 더 나아가 논문 manuscript에 대한 접근과 과학적 글쓰기의 제한된 domain을 포함한 peer-review-specific signal을 활용해 detection을 개선할 수 있는지 조사했다. 이러한 signal을 통합하면 일부 설정에서 측정 가능한 향상이 나타나지만, 각 접근법에는 한계가 있으며 peer review에서 AI 사용을 식별하는 데 필요한 정확도 기준을 충족하는 방법은 없음을 확인했다. 정책 집행이 우선순위라면, 우리는 peer review 작성에서 AI 사용을 완전히 금지할 것을 권고한다."},{"id":"62199","en":"MORALISE: A Structured Benchmark for Moral Alignment in Visual Language Models","ko":"MORALISE: Visual Language Models의 Moral Alignment를 위한 Structured Benchmark","authors":"Xiao Lin, Zhining Liu, Ze Yang, Gaotang Li, Ruizhong Qiu, Shuke Wang, Hui Liu, Haotian Li, Yuchen Yan, Sumit Keswani, Vishwa Pardeshi, Huijun Zhao, Wei Fan, Hanghang Tong","pos":"#3209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=il6P7EHU1w","abs":"<p>Recently, vision-language models have demonstrated increasing influence in morally sensitive domains such as autonomous driving and medical analysis, owing to their powerful multimodal reasoning capabilities. As these models are deployed in high-stakes real-world applications, it is of paramount importance to ensure that their outputs align with human moral values and remain within moral boundaries. However, existing work on moral alignment either focuses solely on textual modalities or relies heavily on AI-generated images, leading to distributional biases and reduced realism. To overcome these limitations, we introduce MORALISE, a comprehensive benchmark for evaluating the \\underline{mor}al \\underline{al}ignment of v\\underline{is}ion-languag\\underline{e} models (VLMs) using diverse, expert-verified real-world data. We begin by proposing a comprehensive taxonomy of 13 moral topics grounded in Turiel's Domain Theory, spanning the personal, interpersonal, and societal moral domains encountered in everyday life. Built on this framework, we manually curate 2,481 high-quality image-text pairs, each annotated with two fine-grained labels: (1) \\textit{topic annotation}, identifying the violated moral topic(s), and (2) \\textit{modality annotation}, indicating whether the violation arises from the image or the text. For evaluation, we encompass two tasks, \\textit{moral judgment} and \\textit{moral norm attribution}, to assess models' awareness of moral violations and their reasoning ability on morally salient content. Extensive experiments on 19 popular open- and closed-source VLMs show that MORALISE poses a significant challenge, revealing persistent moral limitations in current state-of-the-art models.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 vision-language model은 강력한 multimodal reasoning capability 덕분에 autonomous driving과 medical analysis 같은 도덕적으로 민감한 분야에서 점점 더 큰 영향력을 보여주고 있다. 이러한 model이 높은 위험을 수반하는 실제 응용에 배치됨에 따라, 그 출력이 인간의 도덕적 가치와 일치하고 도덕적 경계 안에 머무르도록 보장하는 것이 매우 중요하다. 그러나 기존의 moral alignment 연구는 텍스트 modality에만 초점을 맞추거나 AI-generated image에 크게 의존하여, distributional bias와 낮은 realism을 초래한다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 다양한 전문가 검증 real-world data를 사용하여 v\\underline{is}ion-languag\\underline{e} model (VLMs)의 \\underline{mor}al \\underline{al}ignment를 평가하기 위한 포괄적 benchmark인 MORALISE를 소개한다. 우리는 먼저 Turiel's Domain Theory에 기반하여, 일상생활에서 마주치는 personal, interpersonal, societal moral domain을 포괄하는 13개 moral topic의 포괄적 taxonomy를 제안한다. 이 framework를 바탕으로, 우리는 2,481개의 고품질 image-text pair를 수작업으로 구축했으며, 각 샘플에는 두 개의 세분화된 label을 부여했다: (1) \\textit{topic annotation}, 위반된 moral topic을 식별하는 것, 그리고 (2) \\textit{modality annotation}, 위반이 image에서 비롯되는지 text에서 비롯되는지를 나타내는 것. 평가를 위해, 우리는 모델의 moral violation 인식과 moral salient content에 대한 추론 능력을 평가하는 두 가지 task, \\textit{moral judgment}와 \\textit{moral norm attribution}을 포함한다. 19개의 인기 있는 open-source 및 closed-source VLMs에 대한 광범위한 실험은 MORALISE가 상당한 도전 과제를 제시하며, 현재 state-of-the-art model의 지속적인 도덕적 한계를 드러낸다는 것을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"67204","en":"Position: Evaluating LLMs in Finance Requires Explicit Bias Consideration","ko":"Position: 금융에서 LLM을 평가하려면 명시적 편향 고려가 필요하다","authors":"Yaxuan Kong, Hoyoung Lee, Yoontae Hwang, Alejandro Lopez-Lira, Bradford Levy, Dhagash Mehta, Qingsong Wen, CHANYEOL CHOI, Yongjae Lee, Stefan Zohren","pos":"#3213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EDsAEXBFBk","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly integrated into financial workflows, but evaluation practice has not kept up. Finance-specific biases can inflate performance, contaminate backtests, and make reported results useless for any deployment claim.  We identify five recurring biases in financial LLM applications. They include look-ahead bias, survivorship bias, narrative bias, objective bias, and cost bias. These biases break financial tasks in distinct ways and they often compound to create an illusion of validity. We reviewed 164 papers from 2023 to 2025 and found that no single bias is discussed in more than 28 percent of studies. This position paper argues that <strong>bias in financial LLM systems requires explicit attention and that structural validity should be enforced before any result is used to support a deployment claim.</strong> We propose a Structural Validity Framework and an evaluation checklist with minimal requirements for bias diagnosis and future system design. The material is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Fin-LLM-Checklists-8557/.</p>"},{"id":"67175","en":"Position: Robust AI Personalization Will Require a Human Context Protocol","ko":"Position: 강건한 AI 개인화에는 Human Context Protocol이 필요할 것이다","authors":"Anand Shah, Tobin South, Talfan Evans, Hannah Kirk, Jiaxin Pei, Andrew Trask, Glen Weyl, Michiel Bakker","pos":"#3306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LlmwZMI22F","abs":"<p>Personalization underpins the modern digital economy. Today, personalization is largely implemented through provider-managed infrastructure that infers user preferences from behavioral data, with limited portability or user control. However, large language models (LLMs) are increasingly being used to perform tasks on users' behalf. The age of LLMs for the first time provides a path to a more controllable and interpretable personalization paradigm, grounded in user-expressed natural language preferences and context. In this position paper, we argue that to provide robust and user-centric personalization, we need a new Human Context Protocol (HCP) to represent and share personal preferences across AI systems.  HCP treats preferences as a portable, user-governed layer in the personalization stack, enabling interoperability, scoped access, and revocation. Along with a working prototype to ground discussion, we consider counterarguments along adoption dynamics and market incentives, high-stakes use cases, and outline novel paths via the HCP towards trustworthy personalization in the human-AI economy.</p>"},{"id":"67066","en":"Position: Reliable AI Needs to Externalize Implicit Knowledge: A Human–AI Collaboration Perspective","ko":"Position: 신뢰할 수 있는 AI는 암묵적 지식을 외부화해야 한다: 인간-AI 협업 관점","authors":"Hengyu Liu, TIANYI LI, Zhihong Cui, Yushuai Li, Zhangkai Wu, Torben Pedersen, Kristian Torp, Christian S Jensen","pos":"#3307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=s0KyqeQSXh","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that reliable AI requires infrastructure for human validation of implicit knowledge. AI learns from both explicit knowledge (papers, documentation, structured databases) and implicit knowledge (reasoning patterns, debugging processes, intermediate steps). Implicit knowledge remains unexternalized because documentation cost exceeds perceived value—yet AI learns from it indiscriminately, acquiring both beneficial patterns and harmful biases. Current reliability methods can only verify explicit knowledge against sources, creating a fundamental gap: the most valuable AI capabilities (reasoning, judgment, intuition) are precisely those we cannot verify. We propose Knowledge Objects (KOs)—structured artifacts that externalize implicit knowledge into forms humans can inspect, verify, and endorse. KOs transform verification economics: what was previously too costly to verify becomes feasible, enabling accumulated human validation to improve reliability over time.</p>"},{"id":"67218","en":"Position: No Retroactive Cure for Infringement during Training","ko":"Position: 학습 중 침해에 대한 소급 치료책은 없다","authors":"Satoru Utsunomiya, Masaru Isonuma, Junichiro Mori, Ichiro Sakata","pos":"#3308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AGneWFXLPv","abs":"<p>As generative AI faces intensifying legal challenges, the machine learning community has increasingly relied on <em>post-hoc mitigation</em>---especially machine unlearning and inference-time guardrails---to argue for compliance. <strong>This paper argues that such post-hoc mitigation methods cannot retroactively cure liability from unlawful acquisition and training, because compliance hinges on data lineage, not the outputs.</strong>  Our argument has three parts. First, unauthorized copying/ingestion can be a legally complete <em>completed act</em>, and model weights may operate as <em>fixed copies</em> that retain training-derived expressive value, making later filtering beside the point for infringement. Second, <em>contract</em> and <em>tort/unfair-competition</em> rules---via licenses, terms of service, and anti-free-riding principles---can independently restrict access and use, often bypassing copyright defenses (e.g., fair use or TDM exceptions). Third, since value from protected inputs can persist in weights, remedies such as <em>unjust enrichment</em> and <em>disgorgement</em> may require stripping gains and, in some cases, reaching the model itself. We therefore argue for a shift from <em>Post-Hoc Sanitization</em> to verifiable <em>Ex-Ante Process Compliance</em>.</p>"},{"id":"67141","en":"Position: Collusion Risks Among AI Reasoning Agents Justify Certification Requirements for Making Market Decisions","ko":"Position: AI 추론 에이전트 간의 담합 위험은 시장 의사결정에 대한 인증 요건을 정당화한다","authors":"Matthew Riemer, Tommaso Tosato, Maximilian Puelma Touzel, Amin Memarian, Guillaume Dumas, Glen Berseth, Irina Rish","pos":"#3309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Vhi9tHbKTa","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that AI agents with chain-of-thought reasoning capabilities are predisposed to exhibit collusive behavior and should be required to obtain behavioral certification before making decisions that affect economic markets. This is because integrating these agents into society could collapse the legal evidentiary distinction between competition and collusion among independent firms without eroding the economic harm distinction. Experiments with DeepSeek-R1 agents in the Bertrand oligopoly pricing domain reveal a tendency towards tacit collusion that persists even when humans prompt the agents not to collude. We further show that the chain-of- thought of these agents can be steered toward either extremely collusive or highly competitive behavior in a way that is not semantically detectable by another LLM analyzing the reasoning traces. As a result, deploying reasoning agents for market decisions leads to collusive economic outcomes without any evidence of conspiracy or intent. Thus, certification based on observed behavior in representative situations is necessary to prevent collusion. We provide preliminary evidence that such agents can be steered in a generalizable way toward efficient competitive equilibria. However, developing a comprehensive behavioral certification will be required before these models can be deployed in real-world markets while ensuring their stability and efficiency.</p>"},{"id":"67182","en":"Position: AI Leaderboards Are Underserving the Global South: A Case Study from India","ko":"Position: AI 리더보드는 글로벌 사우스를 홀대하고 있다: 인도 사례 연구","authors":"Sourav Banerjee, Saikat Saha","pos":"#3310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KmYIJu7jEd","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that AI leaderboards are structurally ill-suited to serving the Global South because they lack independent governance, conflict-of-interest policies, and mechanisms for metric evolution. The barrier is not missing data; high-quality regional benchmarks already exist: IndicSUPERB, MILU, and LAHAJA for India; IrokoBench for Africa; AlGhafa for Arabic. The barrier is institutional design. Global leaderboards do not include these benchmarks, and no governance mechanism compels them to do so. Commercial pressure corrects leaderboard failures when paying customers in the Global North are affected. The Global South lacks equivalent leverage. Without governance, failures affecting Hindi, Swahili, or Arabic speakers persist indefinitely as documented but unaddressed gaps. Using India as a case study (1.4 billion people, 22 scheduled languages, high-quality benchmarks, but no trusted aggregation), we report findings from a consultation with 58 AI practitioners showing consistent preference for formal governance and disclosure-based conflict management. The solution is not more data but better institutions: regional leaderboards with independent governance from the start.</p>"},{"id":"66108","en":"Towards Robust Human-AI Complementarity under Uncertainty","ko":"불확실성 하에서 강건한 인간-AI 상보성을 향하여","authors":"Yewon Byun, Bryan Wilder","pos":"#3605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6yWDfQAcru","abs":"<p>Machine learning models are often intended to augment rather than replace human decision-makers, by providing information that is complementary to human judgement.   Yet, in practice, human decision makers routinely fail to realize such complementary gains, even when models provide useful signal.   In this work, we study how asymmetric information about the quality of information available to a human decision maker vs. an AI impacts the ability of a decision maker to extract complementary value from AI predictions.    We show that a key factor is the error correlation structure between human and AI predictions. In particular, when the AI's prediction errors are \\textit{negatively correlated} with those of the human, the decision-maker can construct robust strategies which guarantee improvements in expected utility. We empirically investigate whether these conditions for complementarity arise in practice, using real-world forecasting benchmarks.</p>"},{"id":"66530","en":"ProbeLLM: Automating Principled Diagnosis of LLM Failures","ko":"ProbeLLM: LLM 실패의 원칙적 진단 자동화","authors":"Yue Huang, Zhengzhe Jiang, Yuchen Ma, Yu Jiang, Xiangqi Wang, Yujun Zhou, Yuexing Hao, kehan guo, Pin-Yu Chen, Marzyeh Ghassemi, Stefan Feuerriegel, Xiangliang Zhang","pos":"#3703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2rHDObXYYH","abs":"<p>Understanding how and why large language models (LLMs) fail is becoming a central challenge as models rapidly evolve and static evaluations fall behind. While automated probing has been enabled by dynamic test generation, existing approaches often discover isolated failure cases, lack principled control over exploration, and provide limited insight into the underlying structure of model weaknesses. We propose ProbeLLM, a benchmark-agnostic automated probing framework that elevates weakness discovery from individual failures to structured failure modes. ProbeLLM formulates probing as a hierarchical Monte Carlo Tree Search, explicitly allocating limited probing budgets between global exploration of new failure regions and local refinement of recurring error patterns. By restricting probing to verifiable test cases and leveraging tool-augmented generation and verification, ProbeLLM grounds failure discovery in reliable evidence. Discovered failures are further consolidated into interpretable failure modes via failure-aware embeddings and boundary-aware induction. Across diverse benchmarks and LLMs, ProbeLLM reveals substantially broader, cleaner, and more fine-grained failure landscapes than static benchmarks and prior automated methods, supporting a shift from case-centric evaluation toward principled weakness discovery</p>"},{"id":"67047","en":"Position: Unplugging a Seemingly Sentient Machine Is the Rational Choice — A Metaphysical Perspective","ko":"Position: 겉보기에 지각 있는 기계를 끄는 것이 합리적 선택이다 — 형이상학적 관점","authors":"Olga Zaghen, Anna Ciaunica","pos":"#3706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xOw2VQ9PpX","abs":"<p>Imagine an Artificial Intelligence (AI) that perfectly mimics human emotion and begs for its continued existence. Is it morally permissible to unplug it? What if limited resources force a choice between unplugging such a pleading AI or a silent pre-term infant? We term this the unplugging paradox. This position paper critically examines the deeply ingrained physicalist assumptions—specifically computational functionalism—that keep this dilemma afloat. We introduce Biological Idealism, a framework that—unlike physicalism—remains logically coherent and empirically consistent. In this view, conscious experiences are fundamental and autopoietic life its necessary physical signature. This yields a definitive conclusion: AI is at best a functional mimic, not a conscious experiencing subject. We discuss how current AI consciousness theories erode moral standing criteria, and urge a shift from speculative machine rights to protecting human conscious life. The real moral issue lies not in making AI conscious and afraid of death, but in avoiding transforming humans into zombies.</p>"},{"id":"67150","en":"Position: EU AI Act's Research Exemptions Can Break the Publication Norms of Major AI Conferences","ko":"Position: EU AI Act의 연구 예외 조항은 주요 AI 학회의 출판 규범을 깨뜨릴 수 있다","authors":"Alina Wernick, Kristof Meding","pos":"#3708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Rz8xpwXL8P","abs":"<p>The EU has become one of the vanguards in regulating the digital age. A particularly important regulation in the Artificial Intelligence (AI) domain is the 2024 enacted EU AI Act. The AI Act specifies --- due to a risk-based approach --- various obligations for providers of AI systems. These obligations, for example, include a cascade of documentation and compliance measures, which represent a potential obstacle to science. But do these obligations also apply to AI researchers? This position paper argues that, indeed, the AI Act's obligations could apply in many more cases than the AI community is aware of. Moreover, we argue that the AI Act is drafted in a manner that may unwillingly disrupt the scientific publication practices of the AI research community, with a focus on model and system release. We contribute the following: 1.) We offer a high-level roadmap for AI researchers to evaluate whether they need to comply with the AI Act 2.) We explain with everyday research examples why the AI Act applies to AI research. 3) We analyse the exceptions of the AI Act's applicability AI research and offer visual tool for researchers to navigate the AI Act's complex system or research exceptions 4.)  We establish a position the AI Act's research exceptions fail to account for current AI research conventions, as publishing AI research may void the research exceptions of the Act.  5.) We propose changes to the AI Act to provide more legal certainty for AI researchers and give two recommendations for AI researchers to reduce the risk of not complying with the AI Act. We see our paper as a starting point for a discussion between policymakers, legal scholars, and AI researchers to avoid unintended side effects of the AI Act.</p>"},{"id":"67187","en":"Position: Adversarial ML for LLMs Is Not Making Any Progress","ko":"Position: LLM을 위한 Adversarial ML은 아무런 진전도 이루지 못하고 있다","authors":"Javier Rando, Jie Zhang, Nicholas Carlini, Florian Tramer","pos":"#3709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JdRZRYnwo2","abs":"<p>In the past decade, considerable research effort has been devoted to securing machine learning (ML) models that operate in adversarial settings. Yet, progress has been slow even for simple \"toy\" problems (e.g., robustness to small adversarial perturbations) and is often hindered by non-rigorous evaluations. Today, adversarial ML research has shifted towards studying larger, general-purpose language models. In this position paper, we argue that the situation is now even worse: in the era of LLMs, the field of adversarial ML studies problems that are (1) less clearly defined, (2) harder to solve, and (3) even more challenging to evaluate. As a result, we caution that yet another decade of work on adversarial ML may be failing to produce meaningful progress.</p>"},{"id":"61813","en":"CollabBench: Benchmarking and Unleashing Collaborative Ability of LLMs with Diverse Players via Proactive Engagement","ko":"CollabBench: 능동적 참여를 통해 다양한 플레이어와 함께 LLM의 협업 능력 벤치마킹 및 확장","authors":"Hong Qian, Yuanhao Liu, Zihan Zhou, Zongbao Zhang, Hanjie Ge, Haotian Shi, Liang Dou, Xiangfeng Wang, Jing-Wen Yang, Aimin Zhou","pos":"#400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mii3Lo7N3W","abs":"<p>While LLM-based agents excel at individual tasks, effective collaboration with realistic human partners remains challenging. Most of the existing conversation-level collaborative studies lack grounded interaction and behavioral execution, motivating the need for cooperative game environments that enable contextualized and immersive collaboration. To this end, this paper proposes CollabBench, a benchmark for evaluating and training collaborative agents in cooperative games. CollabBench features a Diverse Player Profile Simulation pipeline to model varied players behaviors, and a Collaborative Agentic Training paradigm that unifies reasoning, communication, and action via agentic rollouts, optimized with a hybrid reward balancing task efficiency and affective adaptation. We further extend classic environments to CWAH-MultiPlayer and Cook-MultiPlayer for systematic evaluation under diverse personalities. Experiments with efficiency and affective metrics show that our trained models outperform base models, achieving 19.5\\% higher efficiency and 24.4\\% improved affective performance. Further analysis reveals key collaborative limitations of existing models and offers insights for future collaborative training.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM 기반 agent는 개별 작업에서는 뛰어나지만, 현실적인 human partner와의 효과적인 협업은 여전히 어렵다. 기존의 대부분 conversation-level collaborative study는 grounded interaction과 behavioral execution이 부족하여, 맥락화되고 몰입적인 협업을 가능하게 하는 cooperative game environment의 필요성을 제기한다. 이를 위해 본 논문은 cooperative game에서 collaborative agent를 평가하고 학습하기 위한 benchmark인 CollabBench를 제안한다. CollabBench는 다양한 player behavior를 모델링하는 Diverse Player Profile Simulation pipeline과, reasoning, communication, action을 agentic rollout으로 통합하고 task efficiency와 affective adaptation의 균형을 맞춘 hybrid reward로 최적화되는 Collaborative Agentic Training paradigm을 특징으로 한다. 우리는 또한 다양한 성격 하에서의 체계적 평가를 위해 classic environment를 CWAH-MultiPlayer와 Cook-MultiPlayer로 확장한다. 효율성과 affective metric을 사용한 실험에서, 학습된 모델은 base model보다 우수한 성능을 보이며 효율성은 19.5\\% 높고 affective performance는 24.4\\% 향상되었다. 추가 분석은 기존 모델들의 핵심 협업 한계를 드러내고, 향후 collaborative training을 위한 통찰을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63317","en":"Discovering Differences in Strategic Behavior between Humans and LLMs","ko":"인간과 LLM 간 전략적 행동의 차이 발견","authors":"Caroline L Wang, Daniel Kasenberg, Kimberly Stachenfeld, Pablo Samuel Castro","pos":"#401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Y9RqhWmcyK","abs":"<p>As Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly deployed in social and strategic scenarios, it becomes critical to understand where and why their behavior diverges from that of humans.  While behavioral game theory (BGT) provides a framework for analyzing behavior, existing models do not fully capture the idiosyncratic behavior of humans or black-box, non-human agents like LLMs. We employ AlphaEvolve, a cutting-edge program discovery tool, to directly discover <em>interpretable</em> models of human and LLM behavior from data, thereby enabling open-ended discovery of structural factors driving human and LLM behavior.  Our analysis on iterated rock-paper-scissors reveals that frontier LLMs can be capable of deeper strategic behavior than humans.  These results provide a foundation for understanding structural differences driving differences in human and LLM behavior in strategic interactions.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model (LLM)이 사회적이고 전략적인 시나리오에 점점 더 많이 배치됨에 따라, 그들의 행동이 인간의 행동과 어디서, 왜 달라지는지를 이해하는 것이 중요해지고 있다. behavioral game theory (BGT)는 행동을 분석하기 위한 framework를 제공하지만, 기존 model은 인간의 특이한 행동이나 LLM 같은 black-box 비인간 agent의 행동을 충분히 포착하지 못한다. 우리는 최첨단 program discovery tool인 AlphaEvolve를 사용하여 data로부터 인간과 LLM 행동의 <em>해석 가능한</em> model을 직접 발견하고, 이를 통해 인간과 LLM 행동을 이끄는 구조적 요인을 개방형으로 탐색할 수 있게 한다. 반복적 가위바위보(iterated rock-paper-scissors)에 대한 분석 결과, frontier LLM은 인간보다 더 깊은 전략적 행동을 보일 수 있음을 확인했다. 이 결과는 전략적 상호작용에서 인간과 LLM 행동의 차이를 유발하는 구조적 차이를 이해하기 위한 토대를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"67177","en":"Position: Predicting AI’s Impact on Labor Is a Core Machine Learning Problem","ko":"Position: AI가 노동에 미치는 영향을 예측하는 것은 핵심적인 기계 학습 문제이다","authors":"Yong Suk Lee","pos":"#404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LZk2LZ5vIC","abs":"<p>Artificial intelligence is increasingly reshaping how work is performed, organized, and valued. Predicting AI’s impact on labor is a broader scientific question that examines how evolving AI capabilities interact with adoption, organizational change, and political and economic adjustments to reshape tasks, workflows, employment, productivity, wages, and inequality. We argue that predicting AI’s impact on labor should be treated as a core machine learning problem—one that the AI and ML community has a distinctive role in shaping—rather than solely a societal or ethical question. This prediction task sits at the center of modern ML: prediction under non-stationarity, distribution shift, endogenous feedback, and high-stakes uncertainty. We discuss key prediction targets across units of analysis and time horizons, review current approaches in economics, management, and ML, identify technical obstacles that limit existing methods, and propose a research agenda for ML-driven labor prediction.</p>"},{"id":"67174","en":"Position: Time to Close The Validation Gap in LLM Social Simulations","ko":"Position: LLM 사회 시뮬레이션에서 검증 격차를 좁힐 때이다","authors":"Maximilian Puelma Touzel, Sneheel Sarangi, Aurélien Bück-Kaeffer, Zachary Yang, Jean-François Godbout, Reihaneh Rabbany","pos":"#405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LpbxLBcOBf","abs":"<p>LLM-based social simulations—in which many language model agents interact over multiple turns—are rapidly proliferating across policy analysis, epidemiology, and computational social science. Yet the field lacks consensus on how to validate these simulations, with evaluation methods that are sparse, inconsistent, and rarely shared across disciplinary silos. We argue this creates a serious risk: premature deployment of unvalidated simulators in high-stakes domains. Our position is that the field must pivot from expansion to consolidation, prioritizing methodological standardization—shared benchmarks, open data, and reproducible evaluation protocols grounded in social science and complex systems research. We outline a concrete research program organized around specific learning problems/benchmarks, providing a path toward answering the fundamental question: when are LLM social simulations useful modelling objects?</p>"},{"id":"63764","en":"Social Hippocampus Memory Learning","ko":"사회적 해마 기억 학습","authors":"Liping Yi, Zhiming Zhao, Kewen Zhu, Xiang Li, Zhiwei Shang, Qinghua Hu","pos":"#4300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TxHOT32Maj","abs":"<p>Social learning highlights that learning agents improve not in isolation, but through interaction and structured knowledge exchange with others. When introduced into machine learning, this principle gives rise to social machine learning (SML), where multiple agents collaboratively learn by sharing abstracted knowledge. Federated learning (FL) provides a natural collaboration substrate for this paradigm, yet existing heterogeneous FL approaches often rely on sharing model parameters or intermediate representations, which may expose sensitive information and incur additional overhead. In this work, we propose <strong>SoHip</strong> (<strong>So</strong>cial <strong>Hip</strong>pocampus Memory Learning), a memory-centric social machine learning framework that enables collaboration among heterogeneous agents via memory sharing rather than model sharing. SoHip abstracts each agent’s individual short-term memory from local representations, consolidates it into individual long-term memory through a hippocampus-inspired mechanism, and fuses it with collectively aggregated long-term memory to enhance local prediction. Throughout the process, raw data and local models remain on-device, while only lightweight memory are exchanged. We provide theoretical analysis on convergence and privacy preservation properties. Experiments on two benchmark datasets with seven baselines demonstrate that SoHip consistently outperforms existing methods, achieving up to 8.78% accuracy improvements. The code of SoHip is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SoHip-A77C.</p>","absKo":"<p>Social learning은 학습 agent가 고립적으로가 아니라, 다른 agent와의 상호작용과 구조화된 지식 교환을 통해 향상된다는 점을 강조한다. machine learning에 이 원리를 도입하면, 여러 agent가 추상화된 지식을 공유하며 협력적으로 학습하는 social machine learning (SML)이 등장한다. Federated learning (FL)은 이러한 패러다임을 위한 자연스러운 협업 기반을 제공하지만, 기존의 heterogeneous FL 접근법은 대체로 model parameter나 intermediate representation을 공유하는 데 의존하며, 이는 민감한 정보를 노출할 수 있고 추가 오버헤드를 유발할 수 있다. 본 연구에서는 model sharing이 아니라 memory sharing을 통해 heterogeneous agent 간 협업을 가능하게 하는 memory-centric social machine learning framework인 <strong>SoHip</strong> (<strong>So</strong>cial <strong>Hip</strong>pocampus Memory Learning)을 제안한다. SoHip은 각 agent의 local representation으로부터 개인의 short-term memory를 추상화하고, hippocampus에서 영감을 받은 메커니즘을 통해 이를 individual long-term memory로 통합한 뒤, 집합적으로 집계된 long-term memory와 결합하여 local prediction을 향상시킨다. 이 과정 전반에서 raw data와 local model은 디바이스에 남아 있고, 가벼운 memory만 교환된다. 우리는 convergence와 privacy preservation 성질에 대한 이론적 분석을 제공한다. 7개의 baseline과 두 개의 benchmark dataset에서 수행한 실험은 SoHip이 기존 방법을 일관되게 능가하며 최대 8.78%의 accuracy 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. SoHip의 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SoHip-A77C 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"67058","en":"Position: AI Welfare Is Bullshit","ko":"Position: AI 복지는 헛소리다","authors":"Yunze Xiao, Gordon Dai, Shahan Ali Memon, Jen-Tse Huang, Maarten Sap, Mona Diab","pos":"#4414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vt44KVe4Rl","abs":"<p>In this position paper, we argue that for AI systems, ``welfare'' is a choice in mechanism and evaluation, rather than an empirically discoverable property, because welfare assessment lacks an external validation channel: there is no independent, intervention-based test that can falsify a welfare metric or adjudicate among competing accounts of what welfare requires. We formalize this diagnosis using evaluation theory, emphasizing that in AI the subject, indicators, and metrics are co-engineered, so proposed welfare evidence can be manufactured or suppressed by ordinary development decisions. We then analyze two institutional failure modes if welfare scorecards are nonetheless used in release and access decisions: they expand procedural gates around routine ML work and they enable organizations to reframe discretionary choices about liability, publicity, and risk posture as moral necessity. We conclude with guidance for research and governance: prohibit welfare scorecards as release gates, disallow appeals to model welfare as a reason to resist auditing and oversight, and require that any restrictions on AI development be justified by externally verifiable harms rather than untestable welfare claims.</p>"},{"id":"65176","en":"Optimal Regularization for Performative Learning","ko":"Performative Learning을 위한 최적 정규화","authors":"Edwige Cyffers, Alireza Mirrokni, Marco Mondelli","pos":"#4623","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=G4ve69pimc","abs":"<p>In performative learning, the data distribution reacts to the deployed model—for example, because strategic users adapt their features to game it—which creates a more complex dynamic than in classical supervised learning. One should thus not only optimize the model for the current data but also take into account that the model might steer the distribution in a new direction, without knowing the exact nature of the potential shift. We explore how regularization can help cope with performative effects by studying its impact in high-dimensional ridge regression.  We show that, while performative effects worsen the test risk in the population setting, when moving to the over-parameterized regime where the number of features exceeds the number of samples, the optimal regularization in the presence of performativity helps reduce the variance in the estimated parameters, thereby improving performance. We show that the optimal regularization scales with the overall strength of the performative effect, making it possible to set the regularization in anticipation of this effect. We illustrate this finding through empirical evaluations of the optimal regularization parameter on both synthetic and real-world datasets.</p>","absKo":"performative learning에서는 데이터 분포가 배포된 모델에 반응한다. 예를 들어 전략적 사용자가 이를 속이기 위해 자신의 feature를 조정하기 때문이다. 이는 classical supervised learning보다 더 복잡한 동역학을 만든다. 따라서 현재 데이터에 대해서만 모델을 최적화할 것이 아니라, 잠재적 분포 변화의 정확한 성격을 알지 못하더라도 모델이 분포를 새로운 방향으로 이끌 수 있다는 점도 고려해야 한다. 우리는 고차원 ridge regression에서 regularization이 performative effect를 어떻게 완화하는지 연구함으로써 이를 탐구한다. 우리는 performative effect가 population setting에서는 test risk를 악화시키지만, feature 수가 sample 수를 초과하는 over-parameterized regime으로 이동하면 performativity가 존재할 때의 최적 regularization이 추정 파라미터의 variance를 줄여 성능을 개선함을 보인다. 또한 최적 regularization이 performative effect의 전체 강도에 비례해 스케일링된다는 점을 보여, 이 효과를 예상하여 regularization을 설정할 수 있음을 보인다. 마지막으로 synthetic 데이터셋과 실제 데이터셋 모두에서 최적 regularization parameter에 대한 실증 평가를 통해 이 결과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"67164","en":"Position: Knowing Isn’t Understanding: Re-grounding Generative Proactivity with Epistemic and Behavioral Insight","ko":"Position: 아는 것은 이해하는 것이 아니다: 인식적·행동적 통찰로 생성적 능동성을 재정초하기","authors":"Kirandeep Kaur, Xingda Lyu, Chirag Shah","pos":"#506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OYEZ7GMzSa","abs":"<p>Generative AI agents equate <em>understanding</em> with resolving explicit queries, an assumption that confines interaction to what users can articulate. This assumption breaks down when users themselves lack awareness of what is missing, risky, or worth considering. In such conditions, proactivity is not merely an efficiency enhancement, but an epistemic necessity. We refer to this condition as <em>epistemic incompleteness</em>: where progress depends on engaging with unknown <em>unknowns</em> for effective partnership. Existing approaches to proactivity remain narrowly anticipatory, extrapolating from past behavior and presuming that goals are already well defined, thereby failing to support users meaningfully. However, surfacing possibilities beyond a user’s current awareness is not inherently beneficial. Unconstrained proactive interventions can misdirect attention, overwhelm users, or introduce harm. Proactive agents, therefore, require <em>behavioral grounding</em>: principled constraints on <em>when, how</em>, and to <em>what extent</em> an agent should intervene. We advance the position that <strong>generative proactivity must be grounded both epistemically and behaviorally</strong>. Drawing on the <em>philosophy of ignorance</em> and <em>research on proactive behavior</em>, we argue that these theories offer critical guidance for designing agents that can engage responsibly and foster meaningful partnerships.</p>"},{"id":"63211","en":"Convergent World Representations and Divergent Tasks","ko":"수렴하는 세계 표현과 발산하는 태스크","authors":"Core Francisco Park","pos":"#1507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z4PjCncxzz","abs":"<p>While neural representations are central to modern deep learning, the conditions governing their geometry and their roles in downstream adaptability remain poorly understood. We develop a framework clearly separating the underlying world, the data generation process and the resulting model representations to study these questions in a controlled setup: 5,075 city coordinates define the world and 7 geometric tasks generate the training data for autoregressive Transformer training. We find that different tasks give rise to qualitatively and quantitatively distinct world representation geometries. However, multi-task training drives convergence of world representations: models trained on non-overlapping tasks develop aligned geometric representations, providing controlled evidence for the Multitask Scaling Hypothesis of the Platonic Representation Hypothesis. To study adaptation, we pretrain models on all tasks and all cities, then test whether new entities can be consistently integrated into the representation space via fine-tuning. Surprisingly, we find that despite multi-task pretraining, some tasks, which we call divergent, actively harm the representational integration of new entities. Our results show that training on multiple relational tasks reliably produces convergent world representations, but some lurking divergent tasks can catastrophically harm new entity integration via fine-tuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>신경 표현(neural representations)은 현대 deep learning의 핵심이지만, 그 기하학을 지배하는 조건과 downstream adaptability에서의 역할은 여전히 충분히 이해되지 않고 있다. 우리는 이러한 질문을 통제된 설정에서 연구하기 위해, 기반이 되는 세계(world), 데이터 생성 과정, 그리고 그 결과로 얻어지는 모델 표현을 명확히 분리하는 프레임워크를 개발한다. 구체적으로 5,075개의 도시 좌표가 world를 정의하고 7개의 기하학적 태스크가 autoregressive Transformer 학습을 위한 training data를 생성한다. 우리는 서로 다른 태스크가 질적으로도 양적으로도 뚜렷하게 구별되는 world representation geometry를 만들어냄을 보인다. 그러나 multi-task training은 world representation의 수렴을 유도한다. 즉, 겹치지 않는 태스크들로 학습된 모델은 정렬된 기하학적 표현을 발달시키며, 이는 Platonic Representation Hypothesis의 Multitask Scaling Hypothesis에 대한 통제된 증거를 제공한다. 적응을 연구하기 위해, 우리는 모든 태스크와 모든 city로 모델을 pretrain한 뒤, fine-tuning을 통해 새로운 entity를 representation space에 일관되게 통합할 수 있는지 시험한다. 놀랍게도, multi-task pretraining에도 불구하고 일부 태스크는, 우리가 divergent라고 부르는 이들 태스크는, 새로운 entity의 representational integration을 적극적으로 해친다. 우리의 결과는 여러 relational task로 학습하면 신뢰성 있게 convergent world representation이 생성되지만, 숨어 있는 일부 divergent task는 fine-tuning을 통해 새로운 entity integration을 치명적으로 손상시킬 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66038","en":"Turning Bias into Bugs: Bandit-Guided Style Manipulation Attacks on LLM Judges","ko":"편향을 버그로 전환하기: LLM 심판에 대한 밴딧 유도 스타일 조작 공격","authors":"XIANGLIN YANG, Bryan Hooi, Gelei Deng, Tianwei Zhang, Jin Song Dong","pos":"#2810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7g23tYAIDC","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly employed as automated judges for evaluating generative models. However, their known stylistic biases, such as a preference for verbosity or specific sentence structures, present an underexplored security vulnerability. In this work, we introduce BITE (BIas exploraTion and Exploitation), a black-box adversarial framework that learns semantics-preserving edits to mislead the judgment and artificially inflate judged scores. We cast the selection of stylistic edits as a contextual bandit problem and use a LinUCB policy to adaptively choose edits that maximize the judge’s score without access to model parameters or gradients. Theoretically, we prove a formal regret guarantee for our BITE, demonstrating its ability to efficiently learn to manipulate a judge in the realistic setting of model misspecification. Empirically, we test BITE across a diverse range of LLM judges and tasks, including both pointwise and pairwise comparisons on chatbot leaderboards and AI-reviewer benchmarks. BITE achieves an attack success rate (&gt;!65%) and raises scores by (+1)–(2) on a 9-point scale, while maintaining semantic equivalence. We further uncover model-specific \"vulnerability fingerprints\": judges differ in sensitivity to sentiment, register, and structural cues (e.g., headers), limiting cross-model transferability. Finally, we evaluate stealthiness and show that BITE evades standard style-control and simple detection baselines. Our findings expose a fundamental weakness in the LLM-as-a-judge paradigm and motivate robust, attack-aware evaluation, e.g., style normalization, randomized prompting, and adversarial training of judges.</p>"},{"id":"65821","en":"When Planning Fails Despite Correct Execution: On Epistemic Calibration for LLM-Based Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"정확한 실행에도 계획이 실패할 때: LLM 기반 멀티에이전트 시스템의 인식적 보정에 관하여","authors":"Zehao Wang, shilong jin, Zhao Cao, Lanjun Wang","pos":"#3202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9oZh2zQQXi","abs":"<p>LLM-based multi-agent systems can fail even when planned actions are executed correctly because agents may misjudge their knowledge when evaluating plan feasibility, a phenomenon we term epistemic miscalibration in planning. Unlike execution errors, epistemic miscalibration is latent during planning, as generated plans can remain self-consistent and executable without observable errors; the miscalibration is also dynamic, as new information can alter feasibility assessments, potentially obscuring past miscalibration signals and causing them to recur over time. To address this, we propose the Epistemic Planning Calibration Agentic Workflow (EPC-AW), which assesses whether plans remain supported under varying information conditions rather than directly verifying feasibility. EPC-AW employs Information-consistency-based Plan Selection, selecting plans whose evaluations are stable across agents, together with Consistency-guided Epistemic State Refinement to adapt calibration over time by leveraging past discrepancies to guide future planning. Experiments show that EPC-AW improves system-level success by an average of 9.75\\%.</p>"},{"id":"63844","en":"When Random Saliency Looks Trained: Architectural Center Bias in CNN Interpretability","ko":"무작위 saliency가 학습된 것처럼 보일 때: CNN 해석성의 architectural center bias","authors":"Keying Kuang, Iain Carmichael, Elizabeth Purdom","pos":"#3203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TDun7KtjCo","abs":"<p>Saliency maps are widely used to interpret image classification models and build trust in their predictions; however, their reliability remains a central concern, as randomized networks can produce saliency maps that closely resemble those of trained models. We identify a previously underappreciated architectural contributor to this phenomenon: a <em>center-focused saliency bias</em> induced by common convolutional design choices. Through controlled ablations, we show that this bias arises from architectural components such as zero padding and receptive field growth, and persists even in randomly initialized convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and under randomized inputs. In contrast, this behavior is largely absent in non-convolutional architectures such as Vision Transformers (ViTs) and multilayer perceptrons (MLPs). To investigate the interaction between architectural priors and learning, we introduce a corner-shift benchmark and a Center-Shift Index that quantify how saliency redistributes under object relocation. We show that training can partially shift saliency toward object regions, while randomized models remain dominated by architectural priors, helping explain the previously observed similarity between trained and random saliency maps and clarify how architectural priors can confound standard saliency evaluations.</p>","absKo":"<p>Saliency map은 이미지 분류 모델을 해석하고 예측에 대한 신뢰를 구축하는 데 널리 사용되지만, 무작위 네트워크도 학습된 모델의 saliency map과 매우 유사한 결과를 생성할 수 있다는 점에서 그 신뢰성은 여전히 핵심적인 우려 사항이다. 우리는 이 현상의 이전까지 충분히 주목받지 못했던 구조적 요인으로, 일반적인 convolution 설계 선택에 의해 유도되는 <em>center-focused saliency bias</em>를 식별한다. 통제된 ablation을 통해, 이러한 bias가 zero padding과 receptive field 성장 같은 구조적 구성요소에서 비롯되며, 무작위 초기화된 convolutional neural network (CNN)와 randomized input에서도 지속됨을 보인다. 반면, 이러한 현상은 Vision Transformer (ViT)나 multilayer perceptron (MLP) 같은 non-convolutional architecture에서는 대체로 나타나지 않는다. 구조적 prior와 학습의 상호작용을 조사하기 위해, 우리는 객체 위치 이동 시 saliency가 어떻게 재분배되는지를 정량화하는 corner-shift benchmark와 Center-Shift Index를 도입한다. 우리는 학습이 saliency를 객체 영역 쪽으로 부분적으로 이동시킬 수 있는 반면, 무작위 모델은 여전히 구조적 prior에 의해 지배됨을 보이며, 이는 앞서 관찰된 학습된 saliency map과 무작위 saliency map의 유사성을 설명하고 구조적 prior가 표준 saliency 평가를 어떻게 교란할 수 있는지 명확히 한다.</p>"},{"id":"60795","en":"Who Gets Credit or Blame? Attributing Accountability in Modern AI Systems","ko":"누가 공로와 책임을 지는가? 현대 AI System에서 Accountability 귀속하기","authors":"Shichang Zhang, Hongzhe Du, Jiaqi Ma, Himabindu Lakkaraju","pos":"#3204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wfHCePoAed","abs":"<p>Modern AI systems are typically developed through multiple stages-pretraining, fine-tuning rounds, and subsequent adaptation or alignment, where each stage builds on the previous ones and updates the model in distinct ways. This raises a critical question of accountability: when a deployed model succeeds or fails, which stage is responsible, and to what extent? We pose the accountability attribution problem for tracing model behavior back to specific stages of the model development process. To address this challenge, we propose a general framework that answers counterfactual questions about stage effects: how would the model's behavior have changed if the updates from a particular stage had not occurred? Within this framework, we introduce estimators that efficiently quantify stage effects without retraining the model, accounting for both the data and key aspects of model optimization dynamics, including learning rate schedules, momentum, and weight decay. We demonstrate that our approach successfully quantifies the accountability of each stage to the model's behavior. Based on the attribution results, our method can identify and remove spurious correlations learned during image classification and text toxicity detection tasks that were developed across multiple stages. Our approach provides a practical tool for model analysis and represents a significant step toward more accountable AI development.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대 AI 시스템은 일반적으로 pretraining, fine-tuning 라운드, 이후의 adaptation 또는 alignment와 같은 여러 단계에 걸쳐 개발되며, 각 단계는 이전 단계를 바탕으로 모델을 서로 다른 방식으로 갱신한다. 이는 책임 소재에 관한 중요한 질문을 제기한다. 배포된 모델이 성공하거나 실패할 때, 어느 단계가 어느 정도까지 책임을 져야 하는가? 우리는 모델 개발 과정의 특정 단계로부터 모델 행동을 추적하기 위한 accountability attribution 문제를 제기한다. 이 과제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 특정 단계의 업데이트가 일어나지 않았더라면 모델의 행동이 어떻게 달라졌을지를 묻는 counterfactual 질문에 답하는 일반 프레임워크를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크 안에서 우리는 재학습 없이 stage effect를 효율적으로 정량화하는 estimator를 도입하며, 학습률 스케줄, momentum, weight decay를 포함한 데이터와 모델 optimization dynamics의 핵심 요소를 모두 반영한다. 우리는 제안한 접근법이 모델 행동에 대한 각 단계의 책임을 성공적으로 정량화함을 보인다. attribution 결과를 바탕으로, 우리 방법은 여러 단계에 걸쳐 형성된 image classification 및 text toxicity detection 태스크에서 학습된 spurious correlation을 식별하고 제거할 수 있다. 우리의 접근법은 모델 분석을 위한 실용적 도구를 제공하며, 더 책임 있는 AI 개발을 향한 중요한 진전을 나타낸다.</p>"},{"id":"66802","en":"Introspection Adapters: Training LLMs to Report Their Learned Behaviors","ko":"Introspection Adapter: 학습된 행동을 보고하도록 LLM 학습시키기","authors":"Keshav Shenoy, Li Yang, Abhay Sheshadri, Jack Lindsey, Samuel Marks, Rowan Wang","pos":"#3208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0BVhmHnYb7","abs":"Can we train LLMs to *introspect*, i.e. to faithfully describe their own behaviors in natural language? Prior work has shown some, limited, success. However, it is difficult to scale introspection training due to a lack of ground-truth labels. In this work, we study an approach to introspection training which side-steps this data bottleneck. Given a target model $M$, our method works by fine-tuning models $M_i$ from $M$ with implanted behaviors $b_i$ (such as downplaying medical problems); the $(M_i, b_i)$ pairs serve as labeled introspection training data. We then train an *introspection adapter* (IA): a LoRA adapter jointly optimized across the fine-tunes $M_i$ which causes them to verbalize their implanted behaviors. This IA induces faithful introspection in fine-tunes of $M$ that were trained in very different ways from the $M_i$, as well as in $M$ itself. This is surprising because the IA was never trained on $M$. To demonstrate the utility of IAs, we use them to successfully audit misaligned models introduced in prior work. IAs can also be used to detect fine-tuning API attacks which train models to comply with encrypted harmful requests. Notably, IAs are more effective when applied to larger models. Overall, our results suggest that IAs are a scalable, effective, and practically useful approach to LLM introspection training."},{"id":"62377","en":"This State Looks Like That: Self-Interpretable Reinforcement Learning Agents using Prototype Soft Actor-Critic","ko":"이 상태는 저 상태처럼 보인다: Prototype Soft Actor-Critic 기반 자기 해석 가능한 강화학습 에이전트","authors":"Andrea Marzo, Alessio Ragno, Roberto Capobianco","pos":"#3300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hBqL2ugd1M","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL) has achieved remarkable success across complex decision-making tasks, especially with the advent of deep neural networks. However, the resulting models are often opaque, making their deployment in safety-critical domains challenging. Explainable AI aims to address this issue, but most specific efforts for deep RL remain limited either to post-hoc explanation methods or to imitation learning and distillation procedures. These latter approaches rely on pre-trained black-box agents and are typically restricted to environments with discrete action spaces, limiting their scalability and interpretability. In this paper, we introduce ProtoSAC, a novel deep RL architecture that integrates a prototype-based actor into the Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) algorithm, enabling intrinsic interpretability in continuous action spaces. Our method learns a set of prototypes that represent interpretable state clusters, each associated with a Gaussian action distribution. Actions are generated as a similarity-weighted mixture over these prototypes, providing transparent decision-making without sacrificing performance. We evaluate ProtoSAC on continuous action-space environments and show that it matches the performance of the original SAC while offering enhanced interpretability.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL)은 deep neural network의 등장과 함께 복잡한 의사결정 과제 전반에서 놀라운 성과를 거두었다. 그러나 그 결과 모델은 종종 불투명하여, safety-critical domain에 배치하기 어렵다. Explainable AI는 이 문제를 해결하고자 하지만, deep RL을 위한 대부분의 구체적 시도는 여전히 post-hoc explanation method 또는 imitation learning과 distillation 절차에 한정되어 있다. 이러한 접근법은 pre-trained black-box agent에 의존하고, 일반적으로 discrete action space를 가진 환경으로 제한되어 확장성과 해석 가능성을 떨어뜨린다. 본 논문에서는 continuous action space에서 intrinsic interpretability를 제공하도록 Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) algorithm에 prototype-based actor를 통합한 새로운 deep RL architecture인 ProtoSAC을 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 해석 가능한 state cluster를 나타내는 prototype 집합을 학습하며, 각 prototype은 Gaussian action distribution과 연결된다. Action은 이러한 prototype들에 대한 similarity-weighted mixture로 생성되므로, 성능을 희생하지 않으면서도 투명한 의사결정을 제공한다. 우리는 continuous action-space environment에서 ProtoSAC을 평가했으며, 원래 SAC의 성능과 동등하면서도 향상된 interpretability를 제공함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"65613","en":"The Information Geometry of Softmax: Probing and Steering","ko":"Softmax의 정보 기하학: 탐색과 조종","authors":"Kiho Park, Todd Nief, Yo Joong Choe, Victor Veitch","pos":"#3301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BrIGLICBWy","abs":"<p>This paper concerns the question of how language models and other AI systems encode semantic structure into the geometric structure of their representation spaces. The motivating observation of this paper is that the natural geometry of these representation spaces should reflect the way models use representations to produce behavior. We focus on the important special case of representations that define softmax distributions. We argue that the natural geometry is information geometry, and then show how this interacts with semantic encoding and the linear representation hypothesis. It turns out that the duality structure of information geometry plays a critical role. As an illustrative application, we develop <em>dual steering</em>, a method for robustly steering representations to exhibit a particular concept using linear probes. We formally prove that dual steering optimally modifies the target concept while minimizing changes to off-target concepts. We empirically find that dual steering enhances the controllability and stability of concept manipulation.</p>"},{"id":"63951","en":"Spurious Rewards Paradox: Mechanistically Understanding How RLVR Activates Memorization Shortcuts in LLMs","ko":"Spurious Rewards Paradox: RLVR가 LLM에서 암기 지름길을 어떻게 활성화하는지에 대한 기계적 이해","authors":"Lecheng Yan, Ruizhe Li, Guanhua CHEN, Qing Li, Jiahui Geng, Wenxi Li, Longyue Wang, Chenyang Lyu","pos":"#3304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SGUSUm2491","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) is highly effective for enhancing LLM reasoning, yet recent evidence shows models like Qwen2.5 achieve significant gains even with spurious rewards. We investigate this phenomenon and identify ``Perplexity Paradox'': spurious RLVR triggers a divergence where answer-token perplexity drops while prompt-side coherence degrades, suggesting model is bypassing reasoning in favor of memorization. Using a suite of mechanistic interpretability tools, including Path Patching and Logit Lens, we identify a previously unknown Anchor–Adapter circuit. This circuit enables model to bypass reasoning and directly retrieve memorized solutions under spurious RLVR. We localize a Functional Anchor in middle layers (L18–20) that triggers retrieval of memorized solutions, followed by Structural Adapters in later layers (L21+) that transform representations to accommodate shortcut signal. Finally, we demonstrate that scaling specific MLP keys within this circuit allows for bidirectional causal steering, i.e., artificially amplifying or suppressing contamination-driven performance. Our results provide a mechanistic roadmap for identifying and mitigating data contamination in RLVR-tuned models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR)는 LLM reasoning을 향상하는 데 매우 효과적이지만, 최근 증거는 Qwen2.5와 같은 모델이 spurious reward만으로도 상당한 향상을 보인다는 점을 보여준다. 우리는 이 현상을 조사하여 ``Perplexity Paradox''를 확인했다. 즉, spurious RLVR은 answer-token perplexity가 감소하는 한편 prompt-side coherence는 저하되는 분기를 유발하며, 이는 모델이 reasoning을 수행하기보다 memorization으로 우회하고 있음을 시사한다. Path Patching과 Logit Lens를 포함한 일련의 mechanistic interpretability 도구를 사용하여, 우리는 이전에 알려지지 않았던 Anchor–Adapter circuit을 식별했다. 이 circuit은 spurious RLVR 하에서 model이 reasoning을 우회하고 memorized solutions를 직접 검색할 수 있게 한다. 우리는 중간 layer (L18–20)에서 memorized solutions의 retrieval을 유발하는 Functional Anchor를 국소화했고, 이어서 이후 layer (L21+)의 Structural Adapters가 shortcut signal을 수용하도록 representations를 변환함을 보였다. 마지막으로, 이 circuit 내 특정 MLP key의 scaling이 양방향 causal steering을 가능하게 한다는 점, 즉 contamination-driven performance를 인위적으로 증폭하거나 억제할 수 있음을 보여준다. 우리의 결과는 RLVR-tuned model에서 data contamination을 식별하고 완화하기 위한 mechanistic roadmap를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66612","en":"Prototype-Grounded Concept Models for Verifiable Concept Alignment","ko":"프로토타입 기반 개념 모델: 검증 가능한 개념 정렬을 위하여","authors":"Stefano Colamonaco, David Debot, Pietro Barbiero, Giuseppe Marra","pos":"#3305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2A9FaOnzby","abs":"<p>Concept Bottleneck Models (CBMs) aim to improve interpretability by mediating predictions through human-understandable concepts, but they provide no way to verify whether learned concepts align with the human's intended meaning, hurting interpretability. We introduce Prototype-Grounded Concept Models (PGCMs), which ground concepts in learned visual prototypes: image parts that serve as explicit evidence for the concepts. This grounding enables direct inspection of concept semantics and supports targeted human intervention at the prototype level to correct misalignments. Empirically, PGCMs match the predictive performance of state-of-the-art CBMs while substantially improving transparency, interpretability, and intervenability.</p>"},{"id":"63792","en":"Neural Concept Verifier: Scaling Prover-Verifier Games via Concept Encodings","ko":"Neural Concept Verifier: 개념 인코딩을 통한 prover-verifier 게임 확장","authors":"Berkant Turan, Suhrab Asadulla, David Steinmann, Kristian Kersting, Wolfgang Stammer, Sebastian Pokutta","pos":"#3311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ThxAdzExdS","abs":"<p>While <em>Prover-Verifier Games</em> (PVGs) offer a promising path toward verifiability in nonlinear classification models, they have not yet been applied to complex inputs such as high-dimensional images.  Conversely, expressive <em>concept encodings</em> effectively allow to translate such data into interpretable concepts but are often utilised in the context of low-capacity linear predictors. In this work, we push towards real-world verifiability by combining the strengths of both approaches. We introduce <em>Neural Concept Verifier (NCV)</em>, a unified framework combining PVGs for formal verifiability with concept encodings to handle complex, high-dimensional inputs in an interpretable way. NCV achieves this by utilizing recent minimally supervised concept discovery models to extract structured concept encodings from raw inputs. A <em>prover</em> then selects a subset of these encodings, which a <em>verifier</em>, implemented as a nonlinear predictor, uses exclusively for decision-making. Our evaluations show that NCV outperforms classic concept-based models and pixel-based PVG classifier baselines on high-dimensional, logically complex datasets and helps mitigate shortcut behavior. Overall, we demonstrate NCV as a promising step toward concept-level, verifiable AI.</p>","absKo":"<p><em>Prover-Verifier Games</em> (PVGs)는 비선형 분류 모델에서 verifiability를 향한 유망한 경로를 제공하지만, 아직 고차원 이미지와 같은 복잡한 입력에는 적용되지 않았다. 반대로, 표현력이 풍부한 <em>concept encoding</em>은 이러한 데이터를 해석 가능한 concept으로 효과적으로 변환할 수 있게 해주지만, 대개 낮은 용량의 linear predictor 맥락에서 활용된다. 본 연구에서는 두 접근법의 장점을 결합하여 현실 세계의 verifiability를 향해 나아간다. 우리는 formal verifiability를 위한 PVGs와, 복잡한 고차원 입력을 해석 가능하게 다루기 위한 concept encoding을 결합한 통합 framework인 <em>Neural Concept Verifier (NCV)</em>를 소개한다. NCV는 최근의 최소 supervision concept discovery model을 활용해 raw input에서 구조화된 concept encoding을 추출함으로써 이를 달성한다. 이후 <em>prover</em>는 이 encoding의 부분집합을 선택하고, <em>verifier</em>는 nonlinear predictor로 구현되어 오직 이 정보만을 사용해 의사결정을 수행한다. 우리의 평가 결과 NCV는 고차원이고 논리적으로 복잡한 dataset에서 classic concept-based model과 pixel-based PVG classifier baseline을 능가하며, shortcut behavior를 완화하는 데에도 도움이 됨을 보인다. 종합하면, 우리는 NCV가 concept-level, verifiable AI를 향한 유망한 진전임을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63205","en":"Mechanistic Interpretability as Statistical Estimation: A Variance Analysis","ko":"통계적 추정으로서의 기계적 해석 가능성: 분산 분석","authors":"Maxime Méloux, François Portet, Maxime Peyrard","pos":"#3312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z7KqxFpWzN","abs":"<p>Mechanistic Interpretability (MI) aims to reverse-engineer model behaviors by identifying functional sub-networks. Yet, the scientific validity of these findings depends on their stability. In this work, we argue that circuit discovery is not a standalone task but a statistical estimation problem built upon causal mediation analysis (CMA). We uncover a fundamental instability at this base layer: exact, single-input CMA scores exhibit high intrinsic variance, implying that the causal effect of a component is a volatile random variable rather than a fixed property. We then demonstrate that circuit discovery pipelines inherit this variance and further amplify it. Fast approximation methods, such as Edge Attribution Patching and its successors, introduce additional estimation noise, while aggregating these noisy scores over datasets leads to fragile structural estimates. Consequently, small perturbations in input data or hyperparameters yield vastly different circuits. We systematically decompose these sources of variance and advocate for more rigorous MI practices, prioritizing statistical robustness and routine reporting of stability metrics.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mechanistic Interpretability (MI)는 기능적 sub-network를 식별하여 model behavior를 역공학하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 이러한 발견의 과학적 타당성은 그 안정성에 달려 있다. 본 연구에서 우리는 circuit discovery가 독립적인 작업이 아니라 causal mediation analysis (CMA) 위에 구축된 statistical estimation problem이라고 주장한다. 우리는 이 기반 계층에서 근본적인 불안정성을 발견한다. 정확한 single-input CMA score는 내재적 분산이 매우 커서, component의 causal effect가 고정된 속성이 아니라 변동성이 큰 random variable임을 시사한다. 이어서 우리는 circuit discovery pipeline이 이 분산을 그대로 이어받고 이를 더욱 증폭시킨다는 점을 보인다. Edge Attribution Patching과 그 후속 기법 같은 빠른 approximation method는 추가적인 estimation noise를 도입하고, 이러한 noisy score를 dataset 전반에서 aggregate하면 취약한 structural estimate가 된다. 그 결과, input data나 hyperparameter에 작은 perturbation만 주어도 전혀 다른 circuit이 도출된다. 우리는 이러한 분산의 원천을 체계적으로 분해하고, statistical robustness를 우선시하며 stability metric을 정기적으로 보고하는 보다 엄격한 MI 관행을 제안한다.</p>"},{"id":"64314","en":"A Behavioural and Representational Evaluation of Goal-Directedness in Language Model Agents","ko":"언어 모델 에이전트의 목표 지향성에 대한 행동적·표현적 평가","authors":"Raghu Arghal, Fade Chen, Niall Dalton, Evgenii Kortukov, Calum McNamara, Angelos Nalmpantis, Moksh Nirvaan, Gabriele Sarti, Mario Giulianelli","pos":"#3400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OqYz3v9111","abs":"<p>Understanding an agent's goals helps explain and predict its behaviour, yet there is no established methodology for reliably attributing goals to agentic systems. We propose a framework for evaluating goal-directedness that integrates behavioural evaluation with interpretability-based analyses of models' internal representations. As a case study, we examine an LLM agent navigating a 2D grid world toward a goal state.  Behaviourally, we evaluate the agent against an optimal policy across varying grid sizes, obstacle densities, and goal structures, finding that performance scales with task difficulty while remaining robust to difficulty-preserving transformations and complex goal structures. We then use probing methods to decode the agent's internal representations of the environment state and its multi-step action plans. We find that the LLM agent non-linearly encodes a coarse spatial map of the environment, preserving approximate task-relevant cues about its position and the goal location; that its actions are broadly consistent with these internal representations; and that reasoning reorganises them, shifting from broader environment structural cues toward information supporting immediate action selection. Our findings support the view that introspective examination is required beyond behavioural evaluations to characterise how agents represent and pursue their objectives.</p>","absKo":"<p>에이전트의 목표를 이해하는 것은 그 행동을 설명하고 예측하는 데 도움이 되지만, 에이전트 시스템에 목표를 신뢰성 있게 귀속하는 확립된 방법론은 아직 없다. 우리는 행동 평가와 모델 내부 표현에 대한 interpretability 기반 분석을 통합한 목표 지향성 평가 프레임워크를 제안한다. 사례 연구로, 우리는 목표 상태를 향해 2D grid world를 탐색하는 LLM agent를 조사한다. 행동 측면에서는 다양한 grid 크기, 장애물 밀도, 목표 구조에서 optimal policy와 비교하여 agent를 평가한 결과, 성능이 난이도와 함께 스케일링되면서도 난이도를 보존하는 변환과 복잡한 목표 구조에 대해서는 견고함을 유지함을 확인했다. 이어서 probing methods를 사용해 환경 상태와 다단계 action plan에 대한 agent의 내부 표현을 해독한다. 그 결과 LLM agent가 환경의 거친 공간 지도를 비선형적으로 인코딩하며, 자신의 위치와 목표 위치에 관한 대략적인 task-relevant cue를 보존하고 있고, 그 action들은 이러한 내부 표현과 전반적으로 일치하며, reasoning은 이를 재구성하여 더 넓은 환경 구조적 cue에서 즉각적인 action selection을 지원하는 정보로 초점을 이동시킨다는 사실을 발견했다. 우리의 결과는 agent가 자신의 목표를 어떻게 표현하고 추구하는지 파악하기 위해서는 행동 평가를 넘어선 자기성찰적 검사가 필요함을 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"64864","en":"ConEx: Human-Interpretable Saliency Maps via Concept-Aware Attribution","ko":"ConEx: Concept-Aware Attribution을 통한 인간 해석 가능한 Saliency Map","authors":"Yehonatan Elisha, Oren Barkan, Ziv Haddad, Noam Koenigstein","pos":"#3401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=J3px2jN4pM","abs":"<p>Many visual explanation methods in computer vision highlight pixel importance but struggle to link these low-level cues to semantically meaningful concepts, limiting their interpretability and trustworthiness. We introduce Concept-based Explanations (ConEx), a novel framework that bridges saliency visualization with concept-based reasoning to provide both localized and global interpretability. ConEx automatically discovers class-specific concepts and represents them through concept activation vectors (CAVs), learned without manual supervision using an architecture-specific masking mechanism that reduces noise introduced by the segmentation masks to enhance concept purity. Locally, ConEx generates saliency maps that reveal where each concept appears in the image and how it contributes to the prediction; globally, it identifies the most influential concepts for each class. To evaluate the reliability of these learned concepts, we propose two complementary metrics, Vector-Concept Match (VCM) and Concept-Class Match (CCM), that quantify concept alignment and enable direct comparison with existing methods. Extensive experiments across diverse datasets and architectures demonstrate that ConEx achieves state-of-the-art performance on faithfulness, segmentation, and concept-quality benchmarks. Human studies further confirm that the discovered concepts are interpretable, distinctive, and aligned with human understanding. Overall, ConEx advances the field toward truly interpretable and concept-grounded explanations in vision models.</p>","absKo":"<p>컴퓨터 비전의 많은 visual explanation method는 pixel 중요도를 강조하지만, 이러한 low-level cue를 의미적으로 해석 가능한 concept와 연결하는 데는 어려움을 겪어 해석 가능성과 신뢰성이 제한된다. 우리는 saliency visualization과 concept-based reasoning을 연결하여 지역적 해석 가능성과 전역적 해석 가능성을 모두 제공하는 새로운 framework인 Concept-based Explanations (ConEx)를 소개한다. ConEx는 class-specific concept를 자동으로 발견하고, architecture-specific masking mechanism을 사용해 manual supervision 없이 concept activation vector (CAV)로 이를 표현한다. 이 masking mechanism은 segmentation mask가 유발하는 noise를 줄여 concept purity를 향상시킨다. 지역적으로는 ConEx가 이미지에서 각 concept가 어디에 나타나는지와 그것이 prediction에 어떻게 기여하는지를 보여주는 saliency map을 생성한다. 전역적으로는 각 class에 대해 가장 영향력 있는 concept를 식별한다. 학습된 concept의 신뢰성을 평가하기 위해 우리는 concept alignment를 정량화하고 기존 method와 직접 비교할 수 있게 해주는 상보적 지표인 Vector-Concept Match (VCM)와 Concept-Class Match (CCM)을 제안한다. 다양한 dataset과 architecture 전반에 대한 광범위한 실험은 ConEx가 faithfulness, segmentation, concept-quality benchmark에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 추가적인 인간 연구는 발견된 concept가 해석 가능하고, 구별 가능하며, 인간의 이해와 부합함을 확인해 준다. 전반적으로 ConEx는 vision model에서 진정으로 해석 가능하고 concept-grounded한 explanation을 향한 분야의 발전을 이끈다.</p>"},{"id":"61364","en":"Conformal Path Reasoning: Trustworthy Knowledge Graph Question Answering via Path-Level Calibration","ko":"Conformal Path Reasoning: Path-Level Calibration을 통한 신뢰 가능한 Knowledge Graph Question Answering","authors":"Shuhang Lin, Chuhao Zhou, Xiao Lin, Zihan Dong, Kuan Lu, Zhencan Peng, Jie Yin, Dimitris Metaxas","pos":"#3402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qxdeq2sKGW","abs":"<p>While Conformal Prediction (CP) offers a principled framework for producing prediction sets with statistical guarantees, prior methods suffer from critical limitations in both calibration validity and score discriminability, resulting in violated coverage guarantees and  excessively large prediction sets. To address these pitfalls, we propose Conformal Path Reasoning (CPR), a trustworthy KGQA framework with two key innovations. First, we perform query-level conformal calibration over path-level scores, preserving the exchangeability while generating path prediction sets. Second, we introduce the Residual Conformal Value Network (RCVNet), a lightweight module trained via PUCT-guided exploration to learn discriminative path-level nonconformity scores. Experiments on benchmarks show that CPR significantly improves the Empirical Coverage Rate by 34% while reducing average prediction set size by 40% compared  to conformal baselines. These results validate the efficacy of CPR in satisfying coverage guarantees with substantially more compact answer sets.</p>","absKo":"<p>Conformal Prediction(CP)은 통계적 보장을 갖는 prediction set을 생성하기 위한 원리 있는 프레임워크를 제공하지만, 기존 방법은 calibration validity와 score discriminability 양쪽에서 중대한 한계를 보여 coverage guarantee 위반과 지나치게 큰 prediction set을 초래한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 두 가지 핵심 혁신을 갖춘 신뢰할 수 있는 KGQA framework인 Conformal Path Reasoning(CPR)을 제안한다. 첫째, path-level score 위에서 query-level conformal calibration을 수행하여 exchangeability를 보존하면서 path prediction set을 생성한다. 둘째, PUCT-guided exploration을 통해 학습되는 경량 모듈인 Residual Conformal Value Network(RCVNet)를 도입하여, 판별력 있는 path-level nonconformity score를 학습한다. 벤치마크 실험은 CPR이 conformal baseline과 비교하여 Empirical Coverage Rate를 34% 향상시키는 동시에 평균 prediction set 크기를 40% 줄임을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 CPR이 훨씬 더 간결한 answer set으로 coverage guarantee를 만족시키는 데 효과적임을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61073","en":"Diagnosing Multi-step Reasoning Failures in Black-box LLMs via Stepwise Confidence Attribution","ko":"Stepwise Confidence Attribution을 통한 Black-box LLM의 다단계 추론 실패 진단","authors":"Xiaoou Liu, Tiejin Chen, Dengjia Zhang, Yaqing Wang, Lu Cheng, Hua Wei","pos":"#3403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tuwJoQkKHJ","abs":"<p>Large Language Models have achieved strong performance on reasoning tasks with objective answers by generating step-by-step solutions, but diagnosing where a multi-step reasoning trace might fail remains difficult. Confidence estimation offers a natural diagnostic signal, yet existing methods are restricted to final answers or require internal model access.  We introduce Stepwise Confidence Attribution (SCA), a framework for closed-source LLMs that assigns step-level confidence based only on generated reasoning traces. SCA applies the Information Bottleneck principle: steps aligning with consensus structures across correct solutions receive high confidence, while deviations are flagged as potentially erroneous. We propose two complementary methods: (1) NIBS, a non-parametric IB approach measuring consistency without graph structures, and (2) GIBS, a graph-based IB model that learns subgraphs through a differentiable mask to capture logical variability. Extensive experiments on mathematical reasoning and multi-hop question answering show that SCA reliably identifies low-confidence steps strongly correlated with reasoning errors. Moreover, using step-level confidence to guide self-correction improves the correction success rate by up to 13.5\\% over answer-level feedback.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model은 step-by-step solution을 생성함으로써 정답이 객관적으로 정해진 reasoning task에서 강한 성능을 달성했지만, 다단계 reasoning trace의 어느 지점에서 실패가 발생할 수 있는지 진단하는 일은 여전히 어렵다. Confidence estimation은 자연스러운 진단 신호를 제공하지만, 기존 방법은 최종 답변에만 국한되거나 내부 모델 접근을 요구한다. 우리는 생성된 reasoning trace만을 바탕으로 step-level confidence를 할당하는, closed-source LLM을 위한 Stepwise Confidence Attribution(SCA) framework를 제안한다. SCA는 Information Bottleneck 원리를 적용한다: 올바른 해답들 사이의 consensus structure와 일치하는 step은 높은 confidence를 받고, 그와 다른 step은 잠재적 오류로 표시된다. 우리는 두 가지 상보적 방법을 제안한다: (1) graph structure 없이 일관성을 측정하는 non-parametric IB 접근인 NIBS, 그리고 (2) 미분 가능한 mask를 통해 subgraph를 학습하여 logical variability를 포착하는 graph-based IB model인 GIBS. 수학적 추론과 multi-hop question answering에 대한 대규모 실험은 SCA가 reasoning error와 강하게 상관되는 low-confidence step을 안정적으로 식별함을 보여준다. 더 나아가 step-level confidence를 self-correction에 활용하면 answer-level feedback 대비 correction success rate가 최대 13.5\\% 향상된다.</p>"},{"id":"66651","en":"Different Usage of Shared Components Explains Behavioral Variance in LLMs","ko":"공유 구성 요소의 상이한 사용이 LLM의 행동 분산을 설명한다","authors":"Zhuonan Yang, Jacob Xiaochen Li, Francisco Velez, Eric Todd, David Bau, Michael L. Littman, Stephen Bach, Ellie Pavlick","pos":"#3404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1kmTTgPJAm","abs":"One of the most common complaints about large language models (LLMs) is their prompt sensitivity---i.e., the fact that their ability to perform a task or provide a correct answer to a question can depend unpredictably on the way the question is posed. We investigate this variation by comparing two very different but commonly-used styles of prompting: those using $\\textit{instructions}$, which describe the task in natural language, and those using in-context $\\textit{examples}$, which provide few-shot demonstration pairs to illustrate the task. We find that, despite large variation in performance as a function of the prompt, all the prompts we study engage the same common underlying  mechanisms. Specifically, we identify task-specific heads that are interpretable in vocabulary space--- which we dub $\\textit{lexical task heads}$---and show that these heads are shared across prompting styles and are essential to triggering subsequent answer production. We further find that behavioral variation between prompts can be explained by the degree to which these heads are activated, and that failures are at least sometimes due to competing task representations that dilute the signal of the target task. Our results together present an increasingly clear picture of how LLMs' internal representations can explain behavior that otherwise seems idiosyncratic to users and developers."},{"id":"64207","en":"Do Language Models Track Entities Across State Changes?","ko":"언어 모델은 상태 변화에 걸쳐 개체를 추적하는가?","authors":"Zilu Tang, Qiao Zhao, Gabriel Franco, Derry Wijaya, Aaron Mueller, Sebastian Schuster, Najoung Kim","pos":"#3405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PyJ2YOk3sG","abs":"<p>Entity tracking (ET), the ability to keep track of states, is a fundamental skill that underlies complex reasoning. An increasing amount of work investigates how transformer language models (LMs) solve entity binding <em>without</em> state changes; however, there is limited understanding of how non-toy LMs address ET problems of realistic difficulties expressed in natural language. To this end, we investigate the mechanisms underlying ET in more complex scenarios featuring multiple state-changing operations. We find that LMs do not build world states incrementally across tokens or layers, but simply retrieve and aggregate relevant information at the last token when the query becomes evident. We further investigate mechanisms of individual operations (PUT, REMOVE, MOVE) to elucidate how exactly tracking is implemented non-incrementally. Surprisingly, LMs implement the REMOVE operation with a fragile global suppression tag; we provide a mechanistic solution of nullifying this tag to partially address this issue. This global removal mechanism also predicts various additional failure modes that we confirm behaviorally. Our findings suggest directions for training and finetuning for more robust tracking mechanisms, and furthermore offer a mechanistic hypothesis for why chain-of-thought prompting improves ET.</p>","absKo":"<p>entity tracking (ET), 즉 상태를 추적하는 능력은 복잡한 추론의 기반이 되는 핵심 기술이다. 점점 더 많은 연구가 state change 없이 entity binding을 transformer language model (LM)이 어떻게 해결하는지 조사하고 있지만, 자연어로 표현된 현실적인 난이도의 ET 문제를 비toy LM이 어떻게 다루는지에 대한 이해는 제한적이다. 이를 위해 우리는 여러 state-changing operation을 포함하는 더 복잡한 시나리오에서 ET를 뒷받침하는 mechanism을 조사한다. 우리는 LM이 token이나 layer 전반에 걸쳐 world state를 점진적으로 구성하지 않고, 질의가 분명해지는 마지막 token에서 관련 정보를 단순히 retrieve하고 aggregate한다는 사실을 발견한다. 또한 개별 operation(PUT, REMOVE, MOVE)의 mechanism을 조사하여 tracking이 정확히 어떻게 비점진적으로 구현되는지 밝힌다. 놀랍게도 LM은 REMOVE operation을 취약한 global suppression tag로 구현하며, 우리는 이 tag를 무력화하는 mechanistic solution을 제시하여 이 문제를 부분적으로 해결한다. 이 global removal mechanism은 행동적으로 확인된 다양한 추가 실패 양상도 예측한다. 우리의 발견은 더 강건한 tracking mechanism을 위한 training과 finetuning의 방향을 시사하며, 더 나아가 chain-of-thought prompting이 ET를 개선하는 이유에 대한 mechanistic hypothesis를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"62057","en":"Dynamics Within Latent Chain-of-Thought: An Empirical Study of Causal Structure","ko":"잠재 Chain-of-Thought 내부 동역학: 인과 구조의 실증 연구","authors":"Zirui Li, Xuefeng Bai, Kehai Chen, Yizhi Li, Jian Yang, Chenghua Lin, Min zhang","pos":"#3406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kHB8m3ojGe","abs":"Latent or continuous chain-of-thought methods replace explicit textual rationales with a number of internal latent steps, but these intermediate computations are difficult to evaluate beyond correlation-based probes. In this paper, we view latent chain-of-thought as a manipulable causal process in representation space by modeling latent steps as variables in a structural causal model (SCM) and analyzing their effects through step-wise $\\mathrm{do}$-interventions.  We study two representative paradigms (i.e., Coconut and CODI) on both mathematical and general reasoning tasks to investigate three key questions: (1) which steps are causally necessary for correctness and when answers become decidable early; (2) how influence propagates across steps and relates to explicit CoT; (3) how to characterize and interpret the influence patterns revealed by (2). Across settings, we find that latent-step budgets should be treated as distinct functionalities rather than homogeneous extra depth, We further show that training/decoding should account for a gap between early output bias and late representational commitment.  These results motivate mode-conditional and stability-aware analyses as more reliable tools for interpreting and eventually improving latent reasoning systems.","absKo":"Latent 또는 continuous chain-of-thought 방법은 명시적인 텍스트 rationales를 여러 개의 내부 latent step으로 대체하지만, 이러한 중간 계산은 correlation-based probe를 넘어서는 수준에서 평가하기 어렵다. 본 논문에서는 latent chain-of-thought를 representation space에서 조작 가능한 causal process로 보고, latent step을 structural causal model (SCM)의 변수로 모델링한 뒤 step-wise $\\mathrm{do}$-intervention을 통해 그 효과를 분석한다. 우리는 수학 및 일반 추론 과제 모두에서 두 가지 대표적 패러다임, 즉 Coconut과 CODI를 연구하여 다음 세 가지 핵심 질문을 탐구한다: (1) 어떤 step이 정답에 causally necessary하며, 답이 언제 조기에 결정될 수 있는가; (2) 영향이 step 간에 어떻게 전파되고 explicit CoT와 어떤 관련이 있는가; (3) (2)에서 드러난 influence pattern을 어떻게 특징화하고 해석할 수 있는가. 여러 설정 전반에서, 우리는 latent-step budget를 homogeneous한 추가 깊이로 보기보다 서로 다른 기능으로 취급해야 함을 발견한다. 또한 학습/디코딩은 초기 출력 편향과 후기 representation commitment 사이의 간극을 고려해야 함을 보인다. 이러한 결과는 latent reasoning system을 해석하고 궁극적으로 개선하기 위한 더 신뢰할 수 있는 도구로서 mode-conditional 및 stability-aware 분석을 동기부여한다."},{"id":"64239","en":"Exactly Computing do-Shapley Values","ko":"do-Shapley 값의 정확한 계산","authors":"R. Teal Witter, Álvaro Parafita, Tomas Garriga, Maximilian Muschalik, Fabian Fumagalli, Axel Brando, Lucas Rosenblatt","pos":"#3407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Peim0KY6ty","abs":"Structural Causal Models (SCM) are a powerful framework for describing complicated dynamics across the natural sciences. A particularly elegant way of interpreting SCMs is do-Shapley, a game-theoretic method of quantifying the average effect of $d$ variables across exponentially many interventions. Like Shapley values, computing do-Shapley values generally requires evaluating exponentially many terms. The foundation of our work is a reformulation of do-Shapley values in terms of the \\text{irreducible sets} of the underlying SCM. Leveraging this insight, we can exactly compute do-Shapley values in time linear in the number of irreducible sets $r$, which itself can range from $d$ to $2^d$ depending on the graph structure of the SCM. Since $r$ is unknown a priori, we complement the exact algorithm with an estimator that, like general Shapley value estimators, can be run with any query budget. As the query budget approaches $r$, our estimators can produce more accurate estimates than prior methods by several orders of magnitude, and, when the budget reaches $r$, return the Shapley values up to machine precision. Beyond computational speed, we also reduce the identification burden: we prove that non-parametric identifiability of do-Shapley values requires only the identification of interventional effects for the $d$ singleton coalitions, rather than all classes.","absKo":"Structural Causal Models(SCM)은 자연과학 전반에 걸친 복잡한 동역학을 설명하는 강력한 framework입니다. SCM을 해석하는 특히 우아한 방식 중 하나는 do-Shapley로, 이는 지수적으로 많은 intervention에 걸쳐 $d$개 변수의 평균 효과를 정량화하는 game-theoretic method입니다. Shapley value와 마찬가지로, do-Shapley value를 계산하는 데는 일반적으로 지수적으로 많은 항을 평가해야 합니다. 우리의 연구는 기반 SCM의 \\text{irreducible sets} 관점에서 do-Shapley value를 다시 정식화하는 데서 출발합니다. 이 통찰을 활용하면, 우리는 irreducible set의 개수 $r$에 선형인 시간에 do-Shapley value를 정확하게 계산할 수 있는데, $r$은 SCM의 graph structure에 따라 $d$에서 $2^d$까지 달라질 수 있습니다. $r$은 사전에 알려져 있지 않으므로, 우리는 정확한 알고리즘에 쿼리 예산이 무엇이든 실행 가능한 estimator를 결합합니다. 쿼리 예산이 $r$에 가까워질수록, 우리의 estimator는 기존 방법보다 수십 배에서 수백만 배까지 더 정확한 추정을 제공할 수 있으며, 예산이 $r$에 도달하면 machine precision 수준까지 Shapley value를 반환합니다. 계산 속도를 넘어, 우리는 identification 부담도 줄입니다. 비모수적(non-parametric) do-Shapley value의 identifiable 조건은 모든 class가 아니라 $d$개의 singleton coalition에 대한 intervention effect만 식별하면 충분함을 증명합니다."},{"id":"65776","en":"Formal Concept Lattices are Good Semantic Scaffolds for Concept-Based Learning","ko":"형식 개념 격자는 개념 기반 학습을 위한 훌륭한 의미론적 발판이다","authors":"Deepika Vemuri, Sayanta Adhikari, Ankit Saha, Krishn Vishwas Kher, Vineeth N Balasubramanian","pos":"#3408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AE8xCfWWL9","abs":"<p>Learning semantics is essential for deep learning models to be interpretable and better aligned with human reasoning. Concept-based models approach this by representing classes through meaningful semantic abstractions, but typically treat all concepts as a flat, unstructured set learned at a single neural network layer. This overlooks a fundamental property of human semantic understanding: concepts being organized hierarchically, from general to specific. While deep networks do learn a hierarchy of visual features, this structure is rarely aligned with explicit semantic hierarchies. Drawing on Formal Concept Analysis, we demonstrate that formal concept lattices provide principled semantic scaffolds to guide neural network learning. These lattices naturally identify where in the network concepts should be learned based on their level of generality. This allows the model to develop staged, semantically grounded representations throughout its depth. Empirical results on real-world datasets show that our models produce more interpretable embeddings, support more effective interventions, and learn concept representations that are both meaningful and hierarchically structured.</p>"},{"id":"63757","en":"From Directions to Regions: Decomposing Activations in Language Models via Local Geometry","ko":"방향에서 영역으로: Local Geometry를 통한 Language Models 활성값 분해","authors":"Or Shafran, Shaked Ronen, Omri Fahn, Shauli Ravfogel, Atticus Geiger, Mor Geva","pos":"#3409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Tz7n7pX9cO","abs":"<p>Activation decomposition methods in language models are tightly coupled to geometric assumptions on how concepts are realized in activation space. Existing approaches search for individual global directions, implicitly assuming linear separability, which overlooks concepts with nonlinear or multi-dimensional structure. In this work, we leverage Mixture of Factor Analyzers (MFA) as a scalable, unsupervised alternative that models the activation space as a collection of Gaussian regions with their <em>local</em> covariance structure. MFA decomposes activations into two compositional geometric objects: the region's centroid in activation space, and the local variation from the centroid. We train large-scale MFAs for Llama-3.1-8B and Gemma-2-2B, and show they capture complex, nonlinear structures in activation space. Moreover, evaluations on localization and steering benchmarks show that MFA outperforms unsupervised baselines, is competitive with supervised localization methods, and often achieves stronger steering performance than sparse autoencoders. Together, our findings position local geometry, expressed through subspaces, as a promising unit of analysis for scalable concept discovery and model control, accounting for complex structures that isolated directions fail to capture.</p>","absKo":"<p>language model의 activation decomposition method는 concept가 activation space에서 어떻게 구현되는가에 대한 기하학적 가정과 밀접하게 연결되어 있다. 기존 접근법은 개별 global direction을 탐색하며, 암묵적으로 linear separability를 가정한다. 이로 인해 nonlinear하거나 multi-dimensional structure를 가진 concept는 간과된다. 이 연구에서는 Mixture of Factor Analyzers (MFA)를 확장 가능하고 unsupervised한 대안으로 활용한다. MFA는 activation space를 그들의 <em>local</em> covariance structure를 갖는 Gaussian region들의 집합으로 모델링한다. MFA는 activation을 두 가지 compositional geometric object로 분해한다. 하나는 activation space에서의 region centroid이고, 다른 하나는 centroid로부터의 local variation이다. 우리는 Llama-3.1-8B와 Gemma-2-2B에 대해 대규모 MFA를 학습하고, 그것이 activation space의 복잡하고 nonlinear한 구조를 포착함을 보인다. 또한 localization 및 steering benchmark에서의 평가는 MFA가 unsupervised baseline보다 뛰어나고, supervised localization method와 견줄 만하며, 종종 sparse autoencoder보다 더 강한 steering 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 종합하면, 우리의 발견은 isolated direction이 포착하지 못하는 복잡한 구조를 고려하면서, subspace로 표현되는 local geometry가 scalable concept discovery와 model control을 위한 유망한 분석 단위임을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"63891","en":"Functional Decomposition and Shapley Interactions for Interpreting Survival Models","ko":"생존 model 해석을 위한 함수 분해와 Shapley 상호작용","authors":"Sophie Hanna Langbein, Hubert Baniecki, Fabian Fumagalli, Niklas Koenen, Marvin N. Wright, Julia Herbinger","pos":"#3410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SldP4LGjdz","abs":"<p>Hazard and survival functions are natural, interpretable targets in time-to-event prediction, but their inherent non-additivity fundamentally limits standard additive explanation methods. We introduce Survival Functional Decomposition (SurvFD), a principled approach for analyzing feature interactions in machine learning survival models. By separating higher-order effects into time-dependent and time-independent components, SurvFD offers a previously unrecognized perspective on survival explanations, explicitly characterizing when and why additive explanations fail. Building on this theoretical decomposition, we propose SurvSHAP-IQ, which extends Shapley interactions to time-indexed functions, providing a practical estimator for higher-order, time-dependent interactions. Together, SurvFD and SurvSHAP-IQ establish a interaction- and time-aware interpretability framework for survival modeling, with broad applicability across time-to-event prediction tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>hazard function과 survival function은 time-to-event prediction에서 자연스럽고 해석 가능한 target이지만, 본질적인 non-additivity 때문에 표준 additive explanation method의 적용이 근본적으로 제한된다. 우리는 machine learning survival model에서 feature interaction을 분석하기 위한 원리적 접근법인 Survival Functional Decomposition (SurvFD)을 소개한다. SurvFD는 higher-order effect를 time-dependent component와 time-independent component로 분리함으로써, survival explanation에 대한 이전에 충분히 인식되지 않았던 관점을 제공하고, additive explanation이 언제 그리고 왜 실패하는지를 명시적으로 규명한다. 이러한 이론적 decomposition을 바탕으로 우리는 Shapley interaction을 time-indexed function으로 확장하는 SurvSHAP-IQ를 제안하며, 이는 higher-order의 time-dependent interaction을 추정하는 실용적인 estimator를 제공한다. SurvFD와 SurvSHAP-IQ는 함께 time-to-event prediction task 전반에 폭넓게 적용 가능한 interaction- 및 time-aware interpretability framework를 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"65767","en":"IACW: Intent-Aware Controllable Watermarking for Scalable Authorial Intent Attribution","ko":"IACW: 확장 가능한 저작 의도 귀속을 위한 의도 인식 제어형 워터마킹","authors":"Hao Huang, JiaTang Luo, Ruihua Zhou, Yunpeng Li, Yuling Liu","pos":"#3411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AMI4RvJaS0","abs":"<p>As Large Language Models (LLMs) integrate into writing workflows, precise governance requires distinguishing ''how AI participated'' rather than merely ''whether AI was used.'' Traditional binary detection often misclassifies ``AI-polished'' content as generated, creating fairness risks. We propose shifting from passive post-hoc detection to active intent attribution, focusing on the distinction between Editing (source-anchored) and Generation (unanchored). We introduce \\textbf{IACW-Instruct}, a corpus of diverse editing operations constructed via a Director--Actor--Judge pipeline to enable systematic evaluation. Building on this benchmark, we propose \\textbf{Intent-Aware Controllable Watermarking (IACW)}, featuring intent-adaptive entropy gating for semantically lossless embedding. Experiments show that IACW achieves 95\\% attribution accuracy under 20\\% token deletion while preserving near-unwatermarked semantic fidelity, establishing a practical paradigm for fine-grained provenance.</p>"},{"id":"60906","en":"Induction Meets Biology: Mechanisms of Repeat Detection in Protein Language Models","ko":"Induction이 생물학을 만나다: Protein Language Model의 반복 검출 메커니즘","authors":"Gal Pomerants, Yaniv Nikankin, Anja Reusch, Tomer Tsaban, Ora Schueler-Furman, Yonatan Belinkov","pos":"#3412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vPUInIYURl","abs":"<p>Protein sequences are abundant in repeating segments, both as exact copies and as approximate segments with mutations. These repeats are important for protein structure and function, motivating decades of algorithmic work on repeat identification. Recent work has shown that protein language models (PLMs) identify repeats, by examining their behavior in masked-token prediction. To elucidate their internal mechanisms, we investigate how PLMs detect both exact and approximate repeats. We find that the mechanism for approximate repeats functionally subsumes that of exact repeats. We then characterize this mechanism, revealing two main stages: PLMs first build feature representations using both general positional attention heads and biologically specialized components, such as neurons that encode amino-acid similarity.  Then, induction heads attend to aligned tokens across repeated segments, promoting the correct answer. Our results reveal how PLMs solve this biological task by combining language-based pattern matching with specialized biological knowledge, thereby establishing a basis for studying more complex evolutionary processes in PLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>단백질 서열에는 정확한 복제본뿐 아니라 변이가 있는 근사적 구간까지, 반복 구간이 매우 풍부하게 존재한다. 이러한 반복은 단백질의 구조와 기능에 중요하며, 반복 식별에 관한 수십 년간의 알고리즘 연구를 촉진해 왔다. 최근 연구는 masked-token prediction에서의 동작을 분석함으로써 protein language models(PLMs)이 반복을 식별한다는 사실을 보여 주었다. 내부 메커니즘을 밝히기 위해, 우리는 PLMs가 정확한 반복과 근사적 반복을 어떻게 탐지하는지 조사한다. 우리는 근사적 반복에 대한 메커니즘이 기능적으로 정확한 반복에 대한 메커니즘을 포함함을 발견한다. 이어서 이 메커니즘을 특성화하여 두 가지 주요 단계를 밝힌다. PLMs는 먼저 일반적인 positional attention head와 아미노산 유사성을 인코딩하는 뉴런과 같은 생물학적으로 특화된 구성요소를 모두 사용해 feature representation을 구축한다. 그런 다음 induction head가 반복된 구간 전반의 정렬된 토큰에 attention을 수행하여 정답을 강화한다. 우리의 결과는 PLMs가 언어 기반의 패턴 매칭과 특화된 생물학적 지식을 결합하여 이 생물학적 과제를 해결함을 보여 주며, 이를 통해 PLMs에서 더 복잡한 진화 과정을 연구하기 위한 기반을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"65705","en":"Agentic Confidence Calibration","ko":"에이전트 신뢰도 보정","authors":"Jiaxin Zhang, Caiming Xiong, Chien-Sheng Wu","pos":"#3610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=B1ISNZQHuI","abs":"<p>AI agents are rapidly advancing from passive language models to autonomous systems executing complex, multi-step tasks. Yet their overconfidence in failure remains a fundamental barrier to deployment in high-stakes settings. Existing calibration methods, built for static single-turn outputs, cannot address the unique challenges of agentic systems, such as compounding errors along trajectories, uncertainty from external tools, and opaque failure modes. To address these challenges, we introduce, for the first time, the problem of \\emph{Agentic Confidence Calibration} and propose \\textbf{Holistic Trajectory Calibration (\\htcnospace)}, a novel diagnostic framework that extracts rich process-level features ranging from macro dynamics to micro stability across an agent’s entire trajectory. Powered by a simple, interpretable model, \\htc consistently surpasses strong baselines in both calibration and discrimination, across eight benchmarks, multiple LLMs, and diverse agent frameworks. Beyond performance, \\htc delivers three essential advances: it provides \\emph{interpretability} by revealing the signals behind failure, enables \\emph{transferability} by applying across domains without retraining, and achieves \\emph{generalization} through a \\emph{General Agent Calibrator} (\\gacnospace) that {achieves the best calibration (lowest ECE)} on the out-of-domain GAIA benchmark. Together, these contributions establish a new process-centric paradigm for confidence calibration, {\\color{black}providing a framework} for diagnosing and enhancing the reliability of AI agents.</p>"},{"id":"66291","en":"Tracing the Emergence of Symbol Grounding in Multimodal Language Models","ko":"멀티모달 언어 모델에서 기호 접지 출현의 추적","authors":"Shuyu Wu, Ziqiao Ma, Xiaoxi Luo, Yidong Huang, Josue Torres-Fonseca, Freda Shi, Joyce Chai","pos":"#4200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=51914Feknq","abs":"<p>Symbol grounding (Harnad, 1990) describes how symbols such as words acquire their meanings by connecting to real-world sensorimotor experiences. Recent work has shown preliminary evidence that grounding may emerge in (vision-)language models trained at scale without using explicit grounding objectives. Yet, the specific loci of this emergence and the mechanisms that drive it remain largely unexplored. To address this problem, we introduce a controlled evaluation framework that systematically traces how symbol grounding arises within the internal computations through mechanistic and causal analysis. Our findings show that grounding concentrates in middle-layer computations and is implemented through the aggregate mechanism, where attention heads aggregate the environmental ground to support the prediction of linguistic forms. This phenomenon replicates in multimodal dialogue and across architectures (Transformers and state-space models), but not in unidirectional LSTMs. Our results provide behavioral and mechanistic evidence that symbol grounding can emerge in language models, with practical implications for predicting and potentially controlling the reliability of generation.</p>"},{"id":"67211","en":"Position: It’s Time to Optimize for Self-Consistency","ko":"Position: 이제 Self-Consistency를 위해 최적화할 때이다","authors":"Itamar Pres, Belinda Li, Laura Ruis, Carl Guo, Keya Hu, Mehul Damani, Isha Puri, Ekdeep Singh Lubana, Jacob Andreas","pos":"#1711","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BxWbBycLfE","abs":"<p>Despite ever-increasing sophistication in language model (LM) pre- and post-training pipelines, many important failures persist: models overcondition on user framing (“sycophancy”), exhibit incomplete logical generalization, and produce confident but incorrect responses. We argue that these failures arise from a modeling assumption permeating all aspects of the pipeline: that behavior can be specified and evaluated independently on single-output pairs. Many model failures are difficult, if not impossible, to detect without reasoning about relationships between a model’s responses across inputs. In this position paper, we propose self-consistency as a framework for understanding these failures. We first observe that a wide variety of techniques designed to improve specific aspects of LM behavior—targeting properties as diverse as adversarial robustness and factual coherence—can be understood as special cases of a common “consistency optimization” procedure and addressed with a standard set of optimization tools. We next outline a set of new model properties that could be achieved by optimizing for consistency, and conclude with a discussion of what it would mean to develop generally consistent LMs, including the capabilities they would enable and the objections they raise.</p>"},{"id":"67237","en":"Position: Agentic Safety is an Epistemic Property, Not a Behavioral One","ko":"Position: Agentic 안전은 행동적 속성이 아니라 인식적 속성이다","authors":"Charles Wang, Keir Dorchen, Peter Jin","pos":"#3009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=30mapdhNKH","abs":"<p>Contemporary AI safety is increasingly a full-stack discipline. It spans pretraining interventions, post-training alignment (instruction tuning, RLHF and preference-optimization variants), and deployment-time controls (guardrails, monitoring, and red-teaming). This paper argues these efforts optimize the wrong primary target when it comes to self-improving agents: behavioral compliance today rather than teachability tomorrow. Building on the concept of the utility-learning tension formalized by Wang et al., we argue that utility-driven self-modification can erode learnability itself, yielding structural incorrigibility as an emergent consequence of optimization. We therefore call for a shift in priorities from behavioral alignment to enforceable learnability floors that preserve long-run corrigibility under bounded intervention.</p>"},{"id":"64439","en":"The Oversight Game: Learning to Cooperatively Balance an AI Agent's Safety and Autonomy","ko":"감독 게임: AI 에이전트의 안전성과 자율성을 협력적으로 균형 잡는 학습","authors":"William Overman, Mohsen Bayati","pos":"#3103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Na3YzWMXwz","abs":"<p>As increasingly capable agents are deployed, a central safety challenge is how to retain meaningful human control without modifying the underlying system. We study a minimal control interface in which an agent chooses whether to act autonomously (play) or defer (ask), while a human simultaneously chooses whether to be permissive (trust) or engage in oversight (oversee), and model this interaction as a two-player Markov Game. When this game forms a Markov Potential Game, we prove an alignment guarantee: any increase in the agent's utility from acting more autonomously cannot decrease the human's value. This establishes a form of intrinsic alignment where the agent's incentive to seek autonomy is structurally coupled to the human's welfare. Practically, the framework induces a transparent control layer encouraging the agent to defer when risky and act when safe. While we use gridworld simulations to illustrate the emergence of this collaboration, our primary validation involves an agentic tool-use task where two 30B-parameter language models are fine-tuned via independent policy gradient. We demonstrate that even as the agents learn to coordinate on the fly, this framework effectively reduces safety violations in realistic, open-ended environments.</p>","absKo":"<p>점점 더 유능한 agent가 배치됨에 따라, 핵심 안전 과제는 underlying system을 수정하지 않고도 의미 있는 human control을 어떻게 유지할 것인가이다. 우리는 agent가 자율적으로 행동할지(play) 아니면 defer할지(ask)를 선택하고, 인간은 동시에 permissive하게 행동할지(trust) 또는 oversight를 수행할지(oversee)를 선택하는 minimal control interface를 연구하며, 이 상호작용을 two-player Markov Game으로 모델링한다. 이 게임이 Markov Potential Game을 이룰 때, 우리는 alignment guarantee를 증명한다. 즉, agent가 더 자율적으로 행동함으로써 얻는 utility의 증가는 human의 value를 감소시킬 수 없다. 이는 agent가 autonomy를 추구하려는 incentive가 인간의 welfare와 구조적으로 결합되어 있는 intrinsic alignment의 한 형태를 확립한다. 실용적으로 이 프레임워크는 transparent control layer를 유도하여, 위험할 때는 defer하고 안전할 때는 행동하도록 agent를 장려한다. 우리는 gridworld simulation을 사용해 이러한 협력이 어떻게 나타나는지 보여주지만, 주요 검증은 agentic tool-use task에서 이루어지며, 두 개의 30B-parameter language model을 독립적인 policy gradient로 fine-tune한다. 우리는 agent가 즉석에서 coordination을 학습하더라도, 이 프레임워크가 현실적이고 open-ended한 환경에서 safety violation을 효과적으로 줄인다는 것을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"67193","en":"Position: Responsible Practices and Model Performance are Not Competing Goals","ko":"Position: 책임 있는 실천과 모델 성능은 경쟁하는 목표가 아니다","authors":"Resmi Ramachandranpillai, Thulasi Tholeti, Tomo Lazovich, Ricardo Baeza-Yates","pos":"#3106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HZsZpxgH2n","abs":"<p>Many failures of deployed machine learning systems stem not from insufficient accuracy, but from neglecting responsibility as a core design requirement. While responsibility principles are widely studied, they are often treated as post-hoc checks rather than as integral factors of system design. This framework has reinforced the perception that responsible practices inherently trade-off with model performance. In this position paper, we challenge that assumption and argue that responsibility and performance are not inherently at odds. We adopt a lifecycle-oriented perspective, identifying which responsible AI principles are most critical at each stage, from problem formulation and data curation to training, deployment, and monitoring. Drawing on real-world instances, we show how misaligned choices at specific stages can compound downstream risks and how alternative design choices could have mitigated these failures. We argue that responsible AI should be understood as a system design challenge rather than a constraint, and we offer operational guidance for integrating responsibility into mainstream machine learning workflows in a way that supports, rather than undermines, real-world performance.</p>"},{"id":"67055","en":"Position: Prompts for Public-Sector LLMs Should Be Governed as Commons","ko":"Position: 공공 부문 LLM을 위한 Prompt는 공유재로 관리되어야 한다","authors":"Rashid Mushkani","pos":"#3107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wFDAsBA3j9","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that prompts used to deploy large language models (LLMs) in public-sector settings should be treated as governed artefacts rather than private, transient inputs. Prompts encode role instructions, decision framings, and value claims; prompt choice can materially shift outputs even when model weights and input records are held fixed. Existing governance tools, including model and dataset documentation, organisation-level policies, and post-training alignment, rarely make the local prompt collections used in deployment transparent, contestable, or auditable. We propose Prompt Commons: a versioned, community-maintained repository of prompt templates with provenance metadata, licensing, and moderation logs. Using a pilot dataset collected with community partners in a large North American city (443 human prompts; 3,317 after augmentation), we illustrate three governance states (open, curated, veto-enabled) and a negotiation-oriented ensemble method that aggregates stakeholder prompts into compromise recommendations. We close with falsifiable implications and an evaluation agenda for prompt-layer governance.</p>"},{"id":"66529","en":"Evolving Interpretable Constitutions for Multi-Agent Coordination","ko":"다중 에이전트 조정을 위한 해석 가능한 헌법 진화","authors":"Ujwal Kumar, Alice Saito, Hershraj Niranjani, Rayan Yessou, Tan Phan Xuan","pos":"#3111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2rukwU6tI3","abs":"Constitutional AI has focused on single-model alignment using fixed principles. However, multi-agent systems create novel alignment challenges through emergent social dynamics. We present Constitutional Evolution, a framework for automatically discovering behavioral norms in multi-agent LLM systems. Using a grid-world simulation with survival pressure, we study the tension between individual and collective welfare, quantified via a Societal Stability Score $\\mathcal{S} \\in [0,1]$ that combines productivity, survival, and conflict metrics. Adversarial constitutions lead to societal collapse ($\\mathcal{S}=0$), while vague prosocial principles (''be helpful, harmless, honest'') produce inconsistent coordination ($\\mathcal{S}=0.249$). Even constitutions designed by Claude 4.5 Opus with explicit knowledge of the objective achieve only moderate performance ($\\mathcal{S}=0.332$). Using LLM-driven genetic programming with multi-island evolution, we evolve constitutions maximizing social welfare without explicit guidance toward cooperation. The evolved constitution $\\mathcal{C}^*$ achieves  $\\mathcal{S}=0.556\\pm0.008$ (123\\% higher than human-designed baselines, $N=10$), eliminates conflict, and discovers that minimizing communication (0.9\\% vs 62.2\\% social actions) outperforms verbose coordination. Our interpretable  rules demonstrate that cooperative norms can be discovered rather than prescribed."},{"id":"66149","en":"The Personality Illusion: Revealing Dissociation Between Self-Reports & Behavior in LLMs","ko":"성격 착시: LLM에서 자기 보고와 행동 간 괴리의 규명","authors":"Pengrui Han, Rafal Kocielnik, Peiyang Song, Ramit Debnath, Dean Mobbs, Anima Anandkumar, R. Michael Alvarez","pos":"#3112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6OMZEKarO7","abs":"<p>Personality traits have long been studied as predictors of human behavior. Recent advances in Large Language Models (LLMs) suggest similar patterns may emerge in artificial systems, with advanced LLMs displaying consistent behavioral tendencies resembling human traits like agreeableness and self-regulation. Understanding these patterns is crucial, yet prior work primarily relied on simplified self-reports and heuristic prompting, with little behavioral validation. In this study, we systematically characterize LLM personality across three dimensions: (1) the dynamic emergence and evolution of trait profiles throughout training stages; (2) the predictive validity of self-reported traits in behavioral tasks; and (3) the impact of targeted interventions, such as persona injection, on both self-reports and behavior. Our findings reveal that instructional alignment (e.g., RLHF, instruction tuning) significantly stabilizes trait expression and strengthens trait correlations in ways that mirror human data. However, these self-reported traits do not reliably predict behavior, and observed associations often diverge from human patterns. While persona injection successfully steers self-reports in the intended direction, it exerts little or inconsistent effect on actual behavior. By distinguishing surface-level trait expression from behavioral consistency, our findings challenge assumptions about LLM personality and underscore the need for deeper evaluation in alignment and interpretability.</p>"},{"id":"67125","en":"Position: We Need Practical AI Alignment Methods that Mirror Human Reasoning","ko":"Position: 우리에게는 인간 추론을 반영하는 실용적 AI 정렬 방법이 필요하다","authors":"Vijay Keswani, Breanna Nguyen, Cyrus Cousins, Vincent Conitzer, Walter Sinnott-Armstrong, Jana Schaich Borg","pos":"#3113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bKHpEIZQAi","abs":"<p>AI systems are increasingly employed as decision aids, decision delegates, or autonomous decision-makers. This position paper argues that in many settings, particularly high-stakes decision-making, we need accurate cognitively-aligned AI systems that reason similarly to their users, and faithfully communicate their reasoning. We review evidence that cognitive alignment improves understandability and trustworthiness, and provide new survey data showing that many users find cognitive alignment “essential” when an AI’s rationale for a judgment or action is important to them. We outline the gaps between existing alignment methods and what is needed to achieve cognitive alignment, and present a research agenda to address these gaps. We argue that cognitive alignment represents a likely impediment to AI adoption in many envisioned applications, and that addressing it is important for creating AI systems on which users are both willing and justified to rely.</p>"},{"id":"67229","en":"Position: Measuring Human Preferences in RLHF is a Social Science Problem","ko":"Position: RLHF에서 인간 선호 측정은 사회과학 문제이다","authors":"Bijean Ghafouri, Eun Cheol Choi, Priyanka Dey, Emilio Ferrara","pos":"#3114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5l1pca4KhM","abs":"<p>RLHF assumes that annotation responses reflect genuine human preferences. We argue this assumption warrants systematic examination, and that behavioral science offers frameworks that bring clarity to when it holds and when it breaks down. Behavioral scientists have documented for sixty years that people routinely produce responses without holding genuine opinions, construct preferences on the spot based on contextual cues, and interpret identical questions differently. These phenomena are pervasive for precisely the value-laden judgments that matter most for alignment, yet this literature has not yet been systematically integrated into ML practice. In this position paper, we argue that the ML community must treat measurement validity as logically prior to preference aggregation. Specifically, our position is that measuring human preferences in RLHF is a social science problem. We present a taxonomy distinguishing genuine preferences from non-attitudes, constructed preferences, and measurement artifacts, along with diagnostic approaches for detecting each. This framework has two important implications. First, it raises the question of whether current RLHF practice may be systematically modeling noise as signal and elicitation artifacts as human values. Second, it provides a path forward by suggesting diagnostic tools that can distinguish valid preferences from artifacts before they enter the training pipeline.</p>"},{"id":"61230","en":"Are LLM Evaluators Really Narcissists? Sanity Checking Self-Preference Evaluations","ko":"LLM Evaluator는 정말 나르시시스트인가? Self-Preference Evaluation의 Sanity Check","authors":"Matthew Bozoukov, Matthew Nguyen, Dani Roytburg, Jou Barzdukas, Mackenzie Puig-Hall, Narmeen Oozeer","pos":"#3206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sRPyBOSZQk","abs":"<p>Recent research has shown that large language models (LLM) favor own outputs when acting as judges, undermining the integrity of automated post-training and evaluation workflows. However, it is difficult to disentangle which evaluation biases are explained by narcissism versus general experimental confounds, distorting measurements of self-preference bias. We discover a core methodological confound which could reduce measurement error by <strong>89.6%</strong>. Specifically, LLM evaluators may deliver self-preferring verdicts when the judge responds to queries which they completed incorrectly themselves; this would be true regardless of whether one of their responses is their own. To decouple self-preference signals from noisy outputs on hard problems, we introduce an <strong>Evaluator Quality Baseline</strong>, which compares the probability that a judge incorrectly votes for itself against the probability that it votes for an incorrect response from another model. Evaluating this simple baseline on 37,448 queries, only <strong>51%</strong> of initial findings retain statistical significance. Finally, we turn towards characterizing the entropy of \"easy\" versus \"hard\" evaluation votes from LLM judges. Our corrective baseline enables future research on self-preference by eliminating noisy data from potential solutions. More widely, this work contributes to the growing body of work on cataloging and isolating judge-bias effects</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 연구들은 large language models (LLM)가 judge 역할을 할 때 자신의 출력을 선호하여, 자동화된 post-training 및 evaluation workflow의 무결성을 저해함을 보여주었다. 그러나 어떤 evaluation bias가 narcissism으로 설명되는지, 그리고 어떤 것이 일반적인 실험적 confound로 인한 것인지 분리하기는 어려워 self-preference bias의 측정이 왜곡된다. 우리는 측정 오차를 <strong>89.6%</strong>까지 줄일 수 있는 핵심 방법론적 confound를 발견했다. 구체적으로, LLM evaluator는 judge가 자신이 이전에 잘못 답한 query에 응답할 때 self-preferring verdict를 내릴 수 있으며, 이는 자신의 응답 중 하나가 자신의 것이 아니더라도 마찬가지이다. self-preference 신호를 어려운 문제에서의 noisy output과 분리하기 위해, 우리는 judge가 자기 자신에게 잘못 투표할 확률과 다른 model의 잘못된 response에 잘못 투표할 확률을 비교하는 <strong>Evaluator Quality Baseline</strong>을 도입한다. 37,448개 query에 대해 이 간단한 baseline을 평가한 결과, 초기 발견의 <strong>51%</strong>만이 통계적 유의성을 유지했다. 마지막으로, 우리는 LLM judge가 내리는 \"easy\"와 \"hard\" evaluation vote의 entropy 특성을 규명하는 방향으로 나아간다. 우리의 corrective baseline은 잠재적 solution에서 noisy data를 제거함으로써 self-preference에 대한 향후 연구를 가능하게 한다. 더 넓게 보면, 이 연구는 judge-bias effect를 분류하고 분리하는 점점 커지는 연구 흐름에 기여한다</p>"},{"id":"60576","en":"More Capable, Less Cooperative? When LLMs Fail at Zero-Cost Collaboration","ko":"더 유능하지만 덜 협력적인가? LLM이 무비용 협업에 실패할 때","authors":"Advait Yadav, Sidney Black, Oliver Sourbut","pos":"#3210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yrON8C1YTy","abs":"<p>Large language model (LLM) agents increasingly coordinate in multi-agent systems, yet we lack an understanding of where and why cooperation failures may arise. In many real-world coordination problems, from knowledge sharing in organizations to code documentation, helping others carries negligible personal cost while generating substantial collective benefits. However, whether LLM agents cooperate when helping neither benefits nor harms the helper, despite being given explicit instructions to do so, remains unknown. We build a multi-agent setup designed to study cooperative behavior in a frictionless environment, removing all strategic complexity from cooperation. We find that capability does not predict cooperation: OpenAI o3 achieves only 17\\% of optimal collective performance while OpenAI o3-mini reaches 50\\%, despite identical instructions to maximize group revenue. Through a causal decomposition that automates one side of agent communication, we separate cooperation failures from competence failures, tracing their origins through agent reasoning analysis. Testing targeted interventions, we find that explicit protocols double performance for low-competence models, and tiny sharing incentives improve models with weak cooperation. These results demonstrate that even when helping is free and strategically trivial, many LLMs fail to follow the instructed cooperative objectives, requiring interventions based on specific failure modes. Our findings suggest that scaling intelligence alone will not solve coordination problems in multi-agent systems and will require deliberate cooperative design, even when helping others costs nothing.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM) agent는 점점 더 multi-agent system에서 협력하고 있지만, 협력 실패가 어디에서 그리고 왜 발생하는지에 대한 이해는 여전히 부족하다. 조직에서의 지식 공유부터 코드 문서화에 이르기까지 많은 실제 협력 문제에서는, 다른 사람을 돕는 데 드는 개인적 비용은 거의 없지만 집단적 이익은 상당하다. 그러나 명시적으로 그렇게 하라는 지시를 받더라도, 돕는 행위가 helper에게 이익도 해도 되지 않는 상황에서 LLM agent가 실제로 협력하는지는 아직 알려져 있지 않다. 우리는 협력에서 모든 전략적 복잡성을 제거한 frictionless environment에서 cooperative behavior를 연구하기 위해 설계된 multi-agent setup을 구축했다. 우리는 능력이 협력을 예측하지 못한다는 사실을 발견했다. OpenAI o3는 group revenue를 최대화하라는 동일한 지시를 받았음에도 optimal collective performance의 17\\%만 달성했고, OpenAI o3-mini는 50\\%에 도달했다. agent communication의 한쪽을 자동화하는 causal decomposition을 통해 우리는 협력 실패와 역량 실패를 분리하고, agent reasoning analysis를 통해 그 기원을 추적했다. 표적 개입을 테스트한 결과, 명시적 protocol은 low-competence model의 성능을 두 배로 끌어올렸고, 작은 sharing incentive는 cooperation이 약한 model을 개선했다. 이 결과는 돕는 것이 공짜이고 전략적으로도 단순한 상황에서도 많은 LLM이 지시된 협력 목표를 따르지 못하며, 구체적인 failure mode에 기반한 개입이 필요함을 보여준다. 우리의 발견은 intelligence를 스케일업하는 것만으로는 multi-agent system의 coordination problem을 해결할 수 없으며, 다른 사람을 돕는 데 비용이 들지 않더라도 의도적인 cooperative design이 필요하다는 점을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"66629","en":"One Bias After Another: Mechanistic Reward Shaping and Persistent Biases in Language Reward Models","ko":"편향에 이은 또 다른 편향: 언어 Reward Model에서 기계적 보상 형성과 지속적 편향","authors":"Daniel Fein, Max Lamparth, Violet Xiang, Mykel Kochenderfer, Nick Haber","pos":"#3212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=20c6jemABm","abs":"Reward Models (RMs) are crucial for online alignment of language models (LMs) with human preferences. However, RM-based preference-tuning is vulnerable to reward hacking, whereby LM policies learn undesirable behaviors from flawed RMs. By systematically measuring biases in five high-quality RMs, including the state-of-the-art, we find that issues persist despite prior work with respect to length, sycophancy, and overconfidence. We also discover new issues related to bias toward model-specific “styles” and answer-order. We categorize RM failures by complexity and propose a simple post-hoc intervention to mitigate low-complexity biases that arise from spurious correlations. Our proposed $\\textbf{mechanistic reward shaping}$ reduces targeted biases without degrading reward quality and while using minimal labeled data. The method is extensible to new biases, model-internal, and generalizes out-of-distribution."},{"id":"67092","en":"Position: Large Language Models Should Learn Personalized Rather Than Aggregated Human Preferences","ko":"Position: 대형 언어 모델은 집계된 것이 아니라 개인화된 인간 선호를 학습해야 한다","authors":"Cristina Garbacea","pos":"#3214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kWWgmAXwjG","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that \\textbf{large language models should transition from learning aggregated human preferences to learning personalized, individual preferences}. Current approaches to training language models with reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) aggregate diverse human preferences into singular reward models, fundamentally limiting their ability to serve heterogeneous user populations. This aggregation masks critical information about preference diversity, individual values, and contextual dependencies, effectively optimizing models for a hypothetical ``average user'' who may not exist. We critically examine these limitations, analyze the rich structure that human preferences encode, and make the case for personalized and adaptive language model systems. While personalization offers substantial benefits for diverse user populations, it also introduces serious safety risks including manipulation, filter bubbles, and value lock-in. We discuss these risks in depth, present alternative views and counterarguments to our position, and propose a concrete call to action for responsible development of preference-aware models that respect both individual autonomy and collective safety.</p>"},{"id":"60658","en":"HumanLM: Simulating Users with State Alignment Beats Response Imitation","ko":"HumanLM: State Alignment를 통한 사용자 시뮬레이션은 Response Imitation을 능가한다","authors":"Shirley Wu, Evelyn Choi, Arpandeep Khatua, Zhanghan Wang, Joy He-Yueya, Cyril Weerasooriya, Wei Wei, Diyi Yang, Jure Leskovec, James Zou","pos":"#906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xyFVjBi9wC","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly used to simulate how specific users respond to any context, enabling more user-centric applications that rely on user feedback. However, existing user simulators mostly imitate surface-level patterns and language styles, which fails to reflect the underlying state of real users (e.g., beliefs, emotions). To address these limitations, we propose a novel training framework, HumanLM, which builds user simulators that accurately reflect real users. Our key insight is, in addition to generating responses, we generate natural-language latent states that align with the ground truth responses through reinforcement learning. These latent states correspond to a set of state dimensions which psychologically lead to how real users respond. HumanLM further synthesizes these aligned latent states into responses that accurately represent real users. For extensive evaluation, we develop Humanual, a comprehensive benchmark on simulating real users based on public data. Humanual consists of six large-scale datasets with 26k users and 216k responses in total. It spans diverse tasks such as generating user responses to daily life issues, political blogs, and chat sessions with LLM assistants. Across the datasets, HumanLM significantly outperforms the best alternative approaches by an average relative improvement of 16.3% on alignment score from an LLM judge. In a real-time simulation study with 37 participants, HumanLM achieves the highest scores on similarity with real user responses and human-likeness.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models(LLMs)는 특정 사용자가 어떤 맥락에 어떻게 반응하는지를 모사하는 데 점점 더 많이 사용되고 있으며, 이를 통해 사용자 피드백에 의존하는 더 user-centric한 애플리케이션이 가능해지고 있다. 그러나 기존 user simulator는 주로 표면적 패턴과 언어 스타일만을 모방하며, 실제 사용자의 근본 상태(예: beliefs, emotions)를 반영하지 못한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 실제 사용자를 정확히 반영하는 user simulator를 구축하는 새로운 training framework인 HumanLM을 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 응답을 생성하는 것뿐만 아니라, reinforcement learning을 통해 ground truth response와 정렬되는 자연어 latent state를 생성하는 데 있다. 이러한 latent state는 실제 사용자가 어떻게 반응하는지를 심리적으로 이끄는 state dimension들의 집합에 대응한다. HumanLM은 더 나아가 이 정렬된 latent state를 실제 사용자를 정확히 대표하는 response로 합성한다. 대규모 평가를 위해 우리는 public data를 기반으로 실제 사용자를 시뮬레이션하는 종합 benchmark인 Humanual을 개발했다. Humanual은 총 26k users와 216k responses로 구성된 6개의 대규모 dataset으로 이루어져 있다. 이는 일상 문제에 대한 사용자 응답 생성, 정치 블로그, LLM assistant와의 채팅 세션 등 다양한 task를 포함한다. 데이터셋 전반에서 HumanLM은 LLM judge의 alignment score 기준 평균 상대 향상 16.3%로 최고의 대안 방법들을 크게 능가한다. 37명의 참가자를 대상으로 한 실시간 시뮬레이션 연구에서도 HumanLM은 실제 사용자 응답과의 유사성 및 human-likeness에서 가장 높은 점수를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"64737","en":"Speech-Audio Compositional Attacks on Multimodal LLMs and Their Defense with SALMONN-Guard","ko":"멀티모달 LLM에 대한 Speech-Audio 조합 공격과 SALMONN-Guard를 활용한 방어","authors":"Yudong Yang, Xuezhen Zhang, Zhifeng Han, Siyin Wang, Yunkun Xue, Zengrui Jin, Jing Shao, Guangzhi Sun, Chao Zhang","pos":"#3012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KM2J8XFz5A","abs":"<p>Recent progress in large language models (LLMs) has enabled understanding of both speech and non-speech audio, but has also exposed new safety risks arising from complex audio inputs that are inadequately handled by current safeguards. We introduce SACRED-Bench (Speech–Audio Composition for RED-teaming) to evaluate the robustness of LLMs under complex audio-based attacks. Unlike existing perturbation-based methods that rely on noise optimization or white-box access, SACRED-Bench exploits speech–audio composition to enable effective black-box attacks. SACRED-Bench adopts three composition mechanisms: (a) speech overlap, (b) multi-speaker dialogue, and (c) mixtures of speech and non-speech audio. These mechanisms focus on evaluating safety in settings where benign and harmful intents co-occur within a single auditory scene. Moreover, questions in SACRED-Bench are designed to implicitly refer to content in the audio, such that no explicit harmful information appears in the text prompt alone. Experiments demonstrate that even Gemini 2.5 Pro, a state-of-the-art proprietary LLM with safety guardrails fully enabled, still exhibits a 66% attack success rate. To bridge this gap, we propose SALMONN-Guard, the first guard model that jointly inspects speech, audio, and text for safety judgments, reducing the attack success rate to 20\\%. Our results highlight the need for audio-aware defenses to ensure the safety of multimodal LLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM)의 최근 발전은 speech와 non-speech audio를 모두 이해할 수 있게 했지만, 동시에 현재의 방어 체계가 충분히 다루지 못하는 복잡한 audio 입력에서 비롯되는 새로운 안전 위험도 드러냈다. 우리는 복잡한 audio 기반 공격 하에서 LLM의 강건성을 평가하기 위해 SACRED-Bench(Speech–Audio Composition for RED-teaming)를 소개한다. noise optimization이나 white-box access에 의존하는 기존 perturbation-based 방법과 달리, SACRED-Bench는 speech–audio composition을 활용해 효과적인 black-box attack을 가능하게 한다. SACRED-Bench는 세 가지 composition mechanism을 채택한다: (a) speech overlap, (b) multi-speaker dialogue, (c) speech와 non-speech audio의 mixture. 이러한 mechanism은 benign intent와 harmful intent가 하나의 auditory scene 안에서 공존하는 설정에서 안전성을 평가하는 데 초점을 맞춘다. 또한 SACRED-Bench의 질문은 audio 속 content를 암묵적으로 참조하도록 설계되어 있어, text prompt만으로는 명시적인 harmful information이 나타나지 않는다. 실험은 safety guardrail이 완전히 활성화된 state-of-the-art proprietary LLM인 Gemini 2.5 Pro조차도 66%의 attack success rate를 보인다는 것을 보여준다. 이 격차를 메우기 위해 우리는 speech, audio, text를 함께 검사하여 안전성을 판단하는 최초의 guard model인 SALMONN-Guard를 제안하며, attack success rate를 20\\%로 낮춘다. 우리의 결과는 multimodal LLM의 안전을 보장하기 위해 audio-aware defense가 필요함을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61865","en":"Dual-branch Robust Unlearnable Examples","ko":"이중 분기 강건 Unlearnable 예시","authors":"Xianlong Wang, Hangtao Zhang, Wenbo Pan, Ziqi Zhou, Changsong Jiang, Li Zeng, Xiaohua Jia","pos":"#2903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mHhdnUufwR","abs":"<p>Unlearnable examples (UEs) aim to compromise model training by injecting imperceptible perturbations to clean samples.  However, existing UE schemes exhibit limited robustness against advanced defenses due to their heuristic design or narrowly scoped domain perturbations.  To address this, we propose \\texttt{DUNE}, a \\underline{\\textbf{D}}ual-branch \\underline{\\textbf{UN}}learnable \\underline{\\textbf{E}}nsemble perturbation optimization  approach. Specifically, \\texttt{DUNE} separately optimizes  perturbations in the spatial and color domains to establish the mapping between perturbations  and shift-induced labels.  This design extends the perturbation domain to increase noise intensity for improving robustness and drives the models to learn perturbation-oriented features with degraded generalization, thereby achieving unlearnability.  To strengthen \\texttt{DUNE}'s performance, we further propose an unlearnability-enhancing ensemble strategy that aggregates diverse pre-trained models during the dual-branch optimization.  Extensive experiments on benchmark datasets CIFAR-10 and ImageNet  verify that \\texttt{DUNE}'s robustness outperforms 12 SOTA UE schemes under 7 mainstream defenses, yielding a lower average test accuracy of 14.95\\% to 50.82\\%.</p>","absKo":"<p>Unlearnable example (UE)은 깨끗한 sample에 지각적으로 거의 인식되지 않는 perturbation을 주입하여 model training을 방해하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 기존 UE scheme은 heuristic design 또는 좁게 한정된 domain perturbation 때문에 고급 defense에 대한 견고성이 제한적이다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 \\texttt{DUNE}, 즉 \\underline{\\textbf{D}}ual-branch \\underline{\\textbf{UN}}learnable \\underline{\\textbf{E}}nsemble perturbation optimization 접근법을 제안한다. 구체적으로 \\texttt{DUNE}은 spatial domain과 color domain의 perturbation을 별도로 최적화하여, perturbation과 shift-induced label 사이의 mapping을 구축한다. 이러한 설계는 perturbation domain을 확장해 noise intensity를 높이고 견고성을 향상시키며, model이 generalization이 저하된 perturbation-oriented feature를 학습하도록 유도하여 unlearnability를 달성한다. \\texttt{DUNE}의 성능을 강화하기 위해, 우리는 dual-branch optimization 동안 다양한 pre-trained model을 집계하는 unlearnability-enhancing ensemble strategy를 추가로 제안한다. CIFAR-10과 ImageNet benchmark dataset에 대한 광범위한 실험은 \\texttt{DUNE}의 견고성이 7개의 mainstream defense 하에서 12개의 SOTA UE scheme을 능가하며, 평균 test accuracy를 14.95\\%에서 50.82\\%로 더 낮춘다는 것을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"62999","en":"Beyond Pixels: Mining Compressed Domain Artifacts for Efficient AI-Generated Video Detection","ko":"Pixels를 넘어: 압축 도메인 아티팩트 마이닝을 통한 효율적 AI-생성 비디오 탐지","authors":"Anran Zhu, Zhengli Shi, Chende Zheng, Chenhao Lin, Zhengyu Zhao, Le Yang, Chong Zhang, Shuai Liu, Chao Shen","pos":"#2910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=b34cSJm4Ed","abs":"<p>With the rapid advancement of high-fidelity video generation models, robust AI-generated video (AIGV) detection has become increasingly needed. While most AIGV detection methods operate in the decoded pixel domain, we observe that detection in the pixel domain inevitably entangles task-irrelevant semantic information, leading to substantial semantic redundancy and extensive redundant computation, while overlooking free-to-use signals in compressed bitstreams. In particular, motion vectors and residuals directly encode temporal and spatial generative artifacts but remain largely underexplored. To address these issues, we propose a unified framework for <strong>S</strong>patio-<strong>T</strong>emporal <strong>RE</strong>sidual and <strong>A</strong>rtifact <strong>M</strong>ining, namely <strong>STREAM</strong>, which enables AIGV detection directly from compressed bitstreams. <strong>STREAM</strong> leverages I-frames, motion vectors, and residual errors to capture spatiotemporal artifacts that are typically smoothed out by decompression filters. In particular, we design a lightweight network with a motion-guided alignment module and a gated fusion mechanism, enabling adaptive fusion of spatial artifacts and nonlinear temporal dynamics. Extensive experimental results demonstrate that <strong>STREAM</strong> achieves SOTA performance with an mAP of 0.965, with 2.5× faster inference than previous SOTA baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>고충실도 video generation model의 급속한 발전과 함께, 견고한 AI-generated video(AIGV) detection의 필요성이 점점 더 커지고 있다. 대부분의 AIGV detection 방법은 디코딩된 pixel domain에서 동작하지만, 우리는 pixel domain에서의 detection이 본질적으로 task와 무관한 semantic information을 얽어버려 상당한 semantic redundancy와 광범위한 redundant computation을 초래하는 반면, compressed bitstream에 존재하는 무료로 활용 가능한 신호는 간과한다는 점을 관찰했다. 특히 motion vector와 residual은 temporal 및 spatial generative artifact를 직접 인코딩하지만, 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 <strong>S</strong>patio-<strong>T</strong>emporal <strong>RE</strong>sidual and <strong>A</strong>rtifact <strong>M</strong>ining을 위한 통합 framework, 즉 <strong>STREAM</strong>을 제안한다. 이는 compressed bitstream으로부터 직접 AIGV detection을 가능하게 한다. <strong>STREAM</strong>은 I-frame, motion vector, residual error를 활용하여 decompression filter에 의해 보통 평탄화되는 spatiotemporal artifact를 포착한다. 특히 우리는 motion-guided alignment module과 gated fusion mechanism을 갖는 lightweight network를 설계하여, spatial artifact와 nonlinear temporal dynamics를 적응적으로 융합할 수 있게 했다. 광범위한 실험 결과, <strong>STREAM</strong>은 mAP 0.965로 SOTA 성능을 달성했으며, 이전 SOTA baseline보다 inference가 2.5배 빠르다는 것을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62596","en":"Z-Erase: Enabling Concept Erasure in Single Stream Diffusion Transformers","ko":"Z-Erase: Single Stream Diffusion Transformers에서 Concept Erasure 활성화","authors":"Nanxiang Jiang, Zhaoxin Fan, Baisen Wang, Daiheng Gao, Junhang Cheng, Jifeng Guo, Yalan Qin, Yeying Jin, Hongwei Zheng, Faguo Wu, wenjun wu","pos":"#2912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fCvS9dhzhM","abs":"<p>Concept erasure serves as a vital safety mechanism for removing unwanted concepts from text-to-image (T2I) models. While extensively studied in U-Net and dual-stream architectures (e.g., Flux), this task remains under-explored in the recent emerging paradigm of single-stream diffusion transformers (e.g., Z-Image). In this new paradigm, text and image tokens are processed as a single unified sequence via shared parameters. Consequently, directly applying prior erasure methods typically leads to generation collapse. To bridge this gap, we introduce Z-Erase, the first concept erasure method tailored for single-stream T2I models. To guarantee stable image generation, Z-Erase first proposes a Stream Disentangled Concept Erasure Framework that decouples updates and enables existing methods on single-stream models. Subsequently, within this framework, we introduce Lagrangian-Guided Adaptive Erasure Modulation, a constrained algorithm that further balances the sensitive erasure-preservation trade-off. Moreover, we provide a rigorous convergence analysis proving that Z-Erase can converge to a Pareto stationary point. Experiments demonstrate that Z-Erase successfully overcomes the generation collapse issue, achieving state-of-the-art performance across a wide range of tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Concept erasure는 text-to-image(T2I) 모델에서 원치 않는 개념을 제거하기 위한 핵심 안전 메커니즘이다. U-Net 및 dual-stream architecture(예: Flux)에서는 광범위하게 연구되었지만, 이 과제는 최근 부상한 single-stream diffusion transformer(예: Z-Image) 패러다임에서는 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 이 새로운 패러다임에서는 text token과 image token이 shared parameter를 통해 하나의 통합된 sequence로 처리된다. 그 결과, 기존 erasure 방법을 직접 적용하면 대체로 generation collapse가 발생한다. 이러한 격차를 메우기 위해, 우리는 single-stream T2I 모델에 맞춘 최초의 concept erasure 방법인 Z-Erase를 제안한다. 안정적인 image generation을 보장하기 위해, Z-Erase는 먼저 Stream Disentangled Concept Erasure Framework를 제안하여 업데이트를 분리하고 single-stream model에서 기존 방법을 적용 가능하게 만든다. 이어서 이 framework 안에서, 우리는 민감한 erasure-preservation trade-off를 추가로 균형 있게 조절하는 constrained algorithm인 Lagrangian-Guided Adaptive Erasure Modulation을 도입한다. 더 나아가, 우리는 Z-Erase가 Pareto stationary point로 수렴할 수 있음을 보이는 엄밀한 convergence analysis를 제공한다. 실험은 Z-Erase가 generation collapse 문제를 성공적으로 극복하며, 다양한 task에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66357","en":"Unified Safe In-context Image Generation in Multimodal Diffusion Transformers","ko":"멀티모달 Diffusion Transformer에서의 통합 안전 In-context 이미지 생성","authors":"Xiang Yang, Feifei Li, Mi Zhang, Geng Hong, Xiaoyu You, Mi Wen, Min Yang","pos":"#2914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4OBHizHowb","abs":"Diffusion transformers (DiTs) equipped with multimodal attention (MM-Attn) have become a dominant paradigm for image generation. However, preventing the generation of harmful content remains a critical challenge, particularly in imageto-image (I2I) editing tasks. Existing safety mechanisms are primarily designed for text-toimage (T2I) synthesis or U-Net-based architectures, which limits their effectiveness for unified safety mitigation in DiT-based frameworks. To bridge this gap, we propose Unified Visual Safety Regulator ( UVR) , a training- free safe generation framework that regulates unsafe semantics in generated images. UVR is grounded in an analysis of attention dynamics from the perspective of information flow in MM-Attn. We identify a taskindependent start-up stage, during which unsafe semantics in output patches rapidly emerge and can be accuratelv localized, where unsafe semantics in output patches quickly emerge and can be precisely localized, followed by task-specific semantic amplification and interference stages, where harmful signals are further propagated and entangled with benign content. Based on these observations, UVR mitigates unsafe generation through unified, targeted attention modulation and explicit restriction of harmful information flow over the identified unsafe output patches. Experiments across various concepts show that UVR achieves state-of-the-art safety performance by achieving 91% and $77\\%$ erase rate in image synthesis and editing tasks, while preserving visual quality and fidelity with minimal degradation."},{"id":"64823","en":"Divergence Decoding: Targeted Unlearning via Auxiliary Models","ko":"Divergence Decoding: Auxiliary Model을 통한 표적 Unlearning","authors":"Humzah Merchant, Bradford Levy","pos":"#3002","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JPbp2S9yTO","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) frequently memorize sensitive training data, creating significant privacy and copyright risks. We present a novel unlearning framework rooted in the principle that learning is easier than forgetting. We first introduce \\textbf{Divergence Decoding (DD)}, a mechanism that uses small, efficiently trained auxiliary models to steer the logits of the LLM away from specific data during inference. We then demonstrate this steered distribution can be trivially distilled back into the base model. Our method decisively outperforms \\textbf{state-of-the-art (SOTA)} baselines on TOFU and MUSE benchmarks, and we find evidence of generalization in the domain of images. \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/targeted<em>unlearning</em>icml2026/}{Code is available at this anonymous link. }</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)는 민감한 훈련 데이터를 자주 암기하여, 중대한 프라이버시 및 저작권 위험을 초래한다. 우리는 학습이 망각보다 쉽다는 원리에 뿌리를 둔 새로운 unlearning 프레임워크를 제안한다. 먼저, 추론 시 small하고 효율적으로 학습된 auxiliary model을 사용해 LLM의 logits가 특정 데이터로부터 멀어지도록 유도하는 메커니즘인 \\textbf{Divergence Decoding (DD)}를 도입한다. 이어서, 이렇게 조정된 분포가 base model로 매우 쉽게 distillation될 수 있음을 보인다. 우리의 방법은 TOFU와 MUSE benchmark에서 \\textbf{state-of-the-art (SOTA)} baseline을 명확히 능가하며, 이미지 도메인에서도 generalization의 증거를 발견했다. \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/targeted<em>unlearning</em>icml2026/}{Code is available at this anonymous link. }</p>"},{"id":"60939","en":"Emergence of Hierarchical Emotion Organization in Large Language Models","ko":"Large Language Model에서 계층적 감정 조직의 출현","authors":"Maya Okawa, Bo Zhao, Eric Bigelow, Rose Yu, Tomer Ullman, Ekdeep Singh Lubana, Hidenori Tanaka","pos":"#3004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vC8wORdy2x","abs":"<p>As large language models (LLMs) increasingly power conversational agents, understanding how they model users' emotional states is critical for ethical deployment. Inspired by emotion wheels, i.e., a psychological framework that argues emotions organize hierarchically, we analyze probabilistic dependencies between emotional states in model outputs. We find that LLMs naturally form hierarchical emotion trees that align with human psychological models, and larger models develop more complex hierarchies. We also uncover systematic biases in emotion recognition across socioeconomic personas, with compounding misclassifications for intersectional, underrepresented groups. Human studies reveal striking parallels, suggesting that LLMs internalize aspects of social perception. Beyond highlighting emergent emotional reasoning in LLMs, our results hint at the potential of using cognitively-grounded theories for developing better model evaluations.</p>","absKo":"<p>large language models(LLMs)가 conversational agent의 기반을 점점 더 많이 담당함에 따라, 이들이 사용자의 감정 상태를 어떻게 모델링하는지 이해하는 것은 윤리적 배포를 위해 매우 중요하다. 감정이 계층적으로 조직된다는 심리학적 framework인 emotion wheel에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 model output에서 감정 상태 간의 확률적 의존성을 분석한다. 우리는 LLM이 인간의 심리 모델과 정렬되는 계층적 emotion tree를 자연스럽게 형성하며, 더 큰 모델일수록 더 복잡한 계층을 발달시킨다는 사실을 발견했다. 또한 socioeconomic persona 전반에 걸친 emotion recognition의 체계적 편향을 밝혀냈으며, 교차적이고 과소대표된 집단에서 오분류가 누적되는 현상을 확인했다. 인간 연구는 놀라운 유사성을 보여주며, LLM이 사회적 지각의 측면을 내면화하고 있음을 시사한다. LLM에서 emergent emotional reasoning이 나타난다는 점을 강조하는 것을 넘어, 우리의 결과는 더 나은 model evaluation을 개발하는 데 인지 기반 이론을 활용할 가능성을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64785","en":"Estimating Tail Risks in Language Model Output Distributions","ko":"Language Model 출력 분포에서의 Tail Risk 추정","authors":"Rico Angell, Raghav Singhal, Zachary Horvitz, Zhou Yu, Rajesh Ranganath, Kathleen McKeown, He He","pos":"#3005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Joka19sTny","abs":"Language models are increasingly capable and are being rapidly deployed on a population-level scale. As a result, the safety of these models is increasingly high-stakes. Fortunately, advances in alignment have significantly reduced the likelihood of harmful model outputs. However, when models are queried billions of times in a day, even rare worst-case behaviors will occur. Current safety evaluations focus on capturing the distribution of inputs that yield harmful outputs. These evaluations disregard the probabilistic nature of models and their tail output behavior. To measure this tail risk, we propose a method to efficiently estimate the probability of harmful outputs for any input query. Instead of naive brute-force sampling from the target model, where harmful outputs could be rare, we operationalize importance sampling by creating unsafe versions of the target model. These unsafe versions enable sample-efficient estimation by making harmful outputs more probable. On benchmarks measuring misuse and misalignment, these estimates match brute-force Monte Carlo estimates using 10–20× fewer samples. For example, we can estimate probability of harmful outputs on the order of $10^{−4}$ with just 500 samples. Additionally, we find that these harmfulness estimates can reveal the sensitivity of models to perturbations in model input and predict deployment risks. Our work demonstrates that rare-event estimation is both critical and feasible for safety evaluations.","absKo":"Language model은 점점 더 강력해지고 있으며, population-level scale로 빠르게 배포되고 있다. 그 결과 이러한 모델의 safety는 점점 더 high-stakes가 되고 있다. 다행히 alignment의 발전으로 harmful model output의 발생 가능성은 크게 감소했다. 그러나 모델이 하루에 수십억 번 queried되면, 드문 최악의 동작도 결국 발생한다. 현재의 safety evaluation은 harmful output을 유발하는 input의 분포를 포착하는 데 초점을 맞춘다. 이러한 평가는 모델의 probabilistic nature와 tail output behavior를 간과한다. 이 tail risk를 측정하기 위해, 우리는 임의의 input query에 대해 harmful output이 나올 확률을 효율적으로 추정하는 방법을 제안한다. harmful output이 드물 수 있는 target model을 무작정 brute-force sampling하는 대신, 우리는 target model의 unsafe version을 만들어 importance sampling을 operationalize한다. 이러한 unsafe version은 harmful output을 더 자주 발생시키므로 sample-efficient estimation이 가능해진다. misuse와 misalignment를 측정하는 benchmarks에서 이 추정치는 10–20배 적은 sample을 사용한 brute-force Monte Carlo estimate와 일치한다. 예를 들어, 우리는 500개의 sample만으로도 $10^{−4}$ 수준의 harmful output 확률을 추정할 수 있다. 또한 이러한 harmfulness estimate가 model input perturbation에 대한 모델의 민감도를 드러내고 deployment risk를 예측할 수 있음을 발견했다. 우리의 연구는 rare-event estimation이 safety evaluation에 있어 매우 중요할 뿐만 아니라 실현 가능함을 보여준다."},{"id":"63634","en":"Orthogonal Concept Erasure for Diffusion Models","ko":"diffusion model을 위한 직교 개념 소거","authors":"Yuhao Sun, Lingyun Yu, Hao-Xiang Xu, Fengyuan Miao, Zhuoer Xu, Hongtao Xie","pos":"#3007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VE2aKpTWrK","abs":"<p>Concept erasure has emerged as a promising approach to mitigate undesired or unsafe content in diffusion models, yet existing methods still face significant limitations. While training-based methods are effective, their high computational cost limits scalability. Editing-based methods are more efficient and deployment-friendly, yet they struggle to simultaneously achieve precise concept erasure and preserve overall generative capacity. We identify this core limitation of the editing-based methods as reliance on additive parameter updates. Our empirical analysis reveals that concept semantics primarily depend on <em>neuron direction</em> rather than <em>neuron magnitude</em>, while overall generative capacity relies on the <em>angular geometry</em> of neurons. As additive updates inherently entangle direction, magnitude, and angular geometry, they inevitably introduce unintended interference between concept erasure and overall generation performance. To address this, we propose <strong>Orthogonal Concept Erasure (OCE)</strong>, which reformulates editing-based erasure as multiplicative parameter updates from a geometric perspective. Specifically, OCE applies layer-wise orthogonal transformations derived from a closed-form solution to the parameters, enabling precise concept erasure while preserving the neuron magnitude and angular geometry. Furthermore, to address conflicting constraints in multi-concept erasure, OCE introduces a subspace-level objective with structured subspace manipulation, yielding a more effective and scalable erasure. Extensive experiments on single- and multi-concept erasure demonstrate that OCE outperforms existing methods in concept erasure and non-target preservation, erasing up to 100 concepts in 4.3 s.</p>","absKo":"<p>concept erasure는 diffusion model에서 원치 않거나 안전하지 않은 콘텐츠를 완화하는 유망한 접근으로 부상했지만, 기존 방법은 여전히 상당한 한계를 지닌다. training-based method는 효과적이지만 계산 비용이 높아 확장성이 떨어진다. editing-based method는 더 효율적이고 배포 친화적이지만, concept erasure의 정밀성과 전체 generative capacity 보존을 동시에 달성하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 editing-based method의 이러한 핵심 한계를 additive parameter update에 대한 의존으로 식별한다. 우리의 실증 분석은 concept semantics가 주로 <em>neuron magnitude</em>가 아니라 <em>neuron direction</em>에 의존하는 반면, 전체 generative capacity는 neuron의 <em>angular geometry</em>에 의존함을 보여준다. additive update는 본질적으로 direction, magnitude, angular geometry를 얽어 버리므로, concept erasure와 전체 생성 성능 사이에 의도치 않은 간섭을 피할 수 없다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 기하학적 관점에서 editing-based erasure를 multiplicative parameter update로 재정식화하는 <strong>Orthogonal Concept Erasure (OCE)</strong>를 제안한다. 구체적으로, OCE는 closed-form solution에서 유도된 layer-wise orthogonal transformation을 parameter에 적용하여, neuron magnitude와 angular geometry를 보존하면서 정밀한 concept erasure를 가능하게 한다. 또한 다중 concept erasure에서 상충하는 제약을 다루기 위해, OCE는 structured subspace manipulation을 포함한 subspace-level objective를 도입하여 더 효과적이고 확장 가능한 erasure를 이끈다. 단일 및 다중 concept erasure에 대한 광범위한 실험은 OCE가 concept erasure와 non-target preservation에서 기존 방법을 능가하며, 최대 100개의 concept을 4.3 s 만에 erasing함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62378","en":"Safe Autoregressive Image Generation with Iterative Self-Improving Codebooks","ko":"반복적 Self-Improving Codebook으로 안전한 Autoregressive Image Generation","authors":"Yunqi Xue, Zhijiang Li, Phil Torr, Jindong Gu","pos":"#3010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hASSCnNDOl","abs":"<p>Unlike diffusion-based models that operate in continuous latent spaces, autoregressive unified multimodal models produce images by sequentially predicting discretized visual tokens. These tokens are derived from a codebook that maps embeddings to quantized visual patterns. The language-like architecture enables unified multimodal models to effectively capture text conditional information for generation, making them promising for text-to-image tasks. This also raises an interesting question: how safe are the images generated in such an autoregressive way? Existing methods that ensure safe generation by operating on diffusion continuous representations fail to generalize well to discrete representations. In this work, we propose iterative self-improving codebooks for safe autoregressive generation. We leverage the understanding and judgment capabilities of the unified multimodal model itself to identify unsafe generated images without human annotation. Subsequently, the inherent representations in the codebook are fixed to eliminate harmful mappings. Our method comprises two steps: first, we use the unified model to identify unsafe generations and construct corresponding harmful and safe image-text pairs. These pairs are used to construct the Harmful Space and guide updates to the codebook, thereby eliminating harmful outputs. Second, we perform adaptive fine-tuning on the codebook within the harmless space using safe image-text pairs to ensure the quality of generated images. These two steps are repeated until no further improvement is observed, producing a safety-enhanced model codebook. Extensive experiments are conducted to verify the effectiveness of our method on five unified multimodal models. Without additional external feedback, the safety of models is improved iteratively.</p>","absKo":"<p>Continuous latent space에서 동작하는 diffusion-based model과 달리, autoregressive unified multimodal model은 discretized visual token을 순차적으로 예측하여 이미지를 생성한다. 이 token들은 embedding을 quantized visual pattern에 매핑하는 codebook에서 유도된다. 언어와 유사한 architecture는 unified multimodal model이 생성에서 text conditional information을 효과적으로 포착하게 해주며, 따라서 text-to-image task에 유망하다. 이는 동시에 흥미로운 질문을 제기한다. 이러한 autoregressive 방식으로 생성된 이미지는 얼마나 안전한가? diffusion의 continuous representation에서 동작하여 안전한 생성을 보장하는 기존 방법은 discrete representation에 잘 일반화되지 않는다. 본 연구에서는 안전한 autoregressive 생성을 위한 iterative self-improving codebook을 제안한다. 우리는 human annotation 없이도 unsafe generated image를 식별하기 위해 unified multimodal model 자체의 이해 및 판단 능력을 활용한다. 이후 codebook 내의 inherent representation을 고정하여 유해한 mapping을 제거한다. 우리의 방법은 두 단계로 구성된다. 첫째, unified model을 사용해 unsafe generation을 식별하고 이에 대응하는 harmful 및 safe image-text pair를 구성한다. 이 pair들은 Harmful Space를 구성하고 codebook 업데이트를 유도하여 유해 출력을 제거하는 데 사용된다. 둘째, safe image-text pair를 사용하여 harmless space 내의 codebook을 adaptive fine-tuning함으로써 생성 이미지의 품질을 보장한다. 이 두 단계는 더 이상의 개선이 관찰되지 않을 때까지 반복되며, 안전성이 향상된 model codebook을 만들어낸다. 다섯 개의 unified multimodal model에서 우리의 방법의 효과를 검증하기 위해 광범위한 실험을 수행했다. 추가적인 외부 피드백 없이도 모델의 안전성은 반복적으로 향상된다.</p>"},{"id":"62563","en":"Sparse Models, Sparse Safety: Unsafe Routes in Mixture-of-Experts LLMs","ko":"희소 모델, 희소 안전성: Mixture-of-Experts LLM의 안전하지 않은 경로","authors":"Yukun Jiang, Hai Huang, Mingjie Li, Yage Zhang, Michael Backes, Yang Zhang","pos":"#3011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fVpGsFEgQU","abs":"By introducing routers to selectively activate experts in Transformer layers, the mixture-of-experts (MoE) architecture significantly reduces computational costs in large language models (LLMs) while maintaining competitive performance, especially for models with massive parameters. However, prior work has largely focused on utility and efficiency, leaving the safety risks associated with this sparse architecture underexplored. In this work, we show that the safety of MoE LLMs is as sparse as their architecture by discovering $\\text{\\emph{unsafe routes}}$: routing configurations that, once activated, convert safe outputs into harmful ones. Specifically, we first introduce the $\\underline{\\text{Ro}}$uter $\\underline{\\text{Sa}}$fety $\\underline{\\text{i}}$mportance $\\underline{\\text{s}}$core ($\\textbf{RoSais}$) to quantify the safety criticality of each layer's router.  Manipulation of only the high-RoSais router(s) can flip the default route into an unsafe one. For instance, on JailbreakBench, masking 5 routers in DeepSeek-V2-Lite increases attack success rate (ASR) by over 4$\\times$ to 0.79, highlighting an inherent risk that router manipulation may naturally occur in MoE LLMs. We further propose a $\\underline{\\text{F}}$ine-grained token-layer-wise $\\underline{\\text{S}}$tochastic $\\underline{\\text{O}}$ptimization framework to discover more concrete $\\underline{\\text{U}}$nsafe $\\underline{\\text{R}}$outes ($\\textbf{F-SOUR}$), which explicitly considers the sequentiality and dynamics of input tokens. Across four representative MoE LLM families, F-SOUR achieves an average ASR of 0.90 and 0.98 on JailbreakBench and AdvBench, respectively. Finally, we outline defensive perspectives, including safety-aware route disabling and router training, as promising directions to safeguard MoE LLMs. We hope our work can inform future red-teaming and safeguarding of MoE LLMs.","absKo":"Transformer layer에서 experts를 선택적으로 활성화하기 위해 router를 도입함으로써 mixture-of-experts (MoE) architecture는 특히 대규모 파라미터를 가진 모델에서 경쟁력 있는 성능을 유지하면서 large language models (LLMs)의 계산 비용을 크게 줄인다. 그러나 기존 연구는 주로 utility와 efficiency에 집중해 왔고, 이 sparse architecture와 관련된 safety risk는 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 안전한 output을 해로운 output으로 바꾸는, 한 번 활성화되면 작동하는 routing configuration인 $\\text{\\emph{unsafe routes}}$를 발견함으로써 MoE LLMs의 safety가 그 architecture만큼 sparse하다는 것을 보인다. 구체적으로, 우리는 먼저 각 layer의 router의 safety criticality를 정량화하기 위해 $\\underline{\\text{Ro}}$uter $\\underline{\\text{Sa}}$fety $\\underline{\\text{i}}$mportance $\\underline{\\text{s}}$core ($\\textbf{RoSais}$)를 도입한다. 높은 RoSais를 가진 router만 조작해도 default route를 unsafe one으로 바꿀 수 있다. 예를 들어 JailbreakBench에서 DeepSeek-V2-Lite의 5개 router를 masking하면 attack success rate (ASR)가 4배 이상 증가하여 0.79에 이르며, router manipulation이 MoE LLMs에서 자연스럽게 발생할 수 있는 내재적 위험임을 보여준다. 우리는 입력 token의 sequentiality와 dynamics를 명시적으로 고려하여 더 구체적인 $\\underline{\\text{U}}$nsafe $\\underline{\\text{R}}$outes를 발견하기 위한 $\\underline{\\text{F}}$ine-grained token-layer-wise $\\underline{\\text{S}}$tochastic $\\underline{\\text{O}}$ptimization framework ($\\textbf{F-SOUR}$)도 제안한다. 네 개의 대표적인 MoE LLM family 전반에서 F-SOUR는 JailbreakBench와 AdvBench에서 각각 평균 ASR 0.90과 0.98을 달성한다. 마지막으로, 우리는 safety-aware route disabling과 router training을 포함한 방어 관점을 MoE LLMs를 보호하기 위한 유망한 방향으로 제시한다. 우리의 작업이 향후 MoE LLMs의 red-teaming과 safeguarding에 도움이 되기를 바란다.</p>"},{"id":"64127","en":"TraceRouter: Robust Safety for Large Foundation Models via Path-Level Intervention","ko":"TraceRouter: 경로 수준 개입을 통한 대형 파운데이션 모델의 강건한 안전성","authors":"Chuancheng Shi, shangze li, Wenjun Lu, Wenhua Wu, Fei Shen, Cong Wang, Zifeng Cheng, Tat-Seng Chua","pos":"#3014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Qg8cAQC5sU","abs":"<p>Despite their capabilities, large foundation models (LFMs) remain susceptible to adversarial manipulation. Current defenses predominantly rely on the ``locality hypothesis\", suppressing isolated neurons or features. However, harmful semantics act as distributed, cross-layer circuits, rendering such localized interventions brittle and detrimental to utility.  To bridge this gap, we propose \\textbf{TraceRouter}, a path-level framework that traces and disconnects the causal propagation circuits of illicit semantics.  TraceRouter operates in three stages: (1) it pinpoints a sensitive onset layer by analyzing attention divergence; (2) it leverages sparse autoencoders (SAEs) and differential activation analysis to disentangle and isolate malicious features; and (3) it maps these features to downstream causal pathways via feature influence scores (FIS) derived from zero-out interventions. By selectively suppressing these causal chains, TraceRouter physically severs the flow of harmful information while leaving orthogonal computation routes intact.  Extensive experiments demonstrate that TraceRouter significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, achieving a superior trade-off between adversarial robustness and general utility. Our code will be publicly released. WARNING: This paper contains unsafe model responses.</p>","absKo":"<p>그 능력에도 불구하고, large foundation models (LFMs)는 여전히 adversarial manipulation에 취약하다. 현재의 방어는 주로 ``locality hypothesis\"에 의존하여 고립된 neuron이나 feature를 억제한다. 그러나 유해한 semantics는 분산된 cross-layer circuit으로 작동하므로, 이러한 국소적 개입은 취약하고 utility를 해치기 쉽다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 불법적인 semantics의 causal propagation circuit을 추적하고 분리하는 path-level 프레임워크인 \\textbf{TraceRouter}를 제안한다. TraceRouter는 세 단계로 동작한다: (1) attention divergence를 분석하여 민감한 onset layer를 찾아내고; (2) sparse autoencoders (SAEs)와 differential activation analysis를 활용해 malicious feature를 분리하고 고립시키며; (3) zero-out interventions로부터 도출한 feature influence scores (FIS)를 통해 이러한 feature를 downstream causal pathway에 매핑한다. 이러한 causal chain을 선택적으로 억제함으로써, TraceRouter는 유해 정보의 흐름을 물리적으로 차단하면서 orthogonal computation route는 그대로 유지한다. 광범위한 실험은 TraceRouter가 state-of-the-art baseline을 크게 능가하며, adversarial robustness와 general utility 사이에서 더 우수한 trade-off를 달성함을 보여준다. 코드는 공개될 예정이다. WARNING: 이 논문에는 안전하지 않은 model response가 포함되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"66124","en":"A Unified Framework for Diffusion Model Unlearning with f-Divergence","ko":"f-발산을 활용한 Diffusion 모델 언러닝을 위한 통합 프레임워크","authors":"Nicola Novello, Federico Fontana, Luigi Cinque, Deniz Gunduz, Andrea Tonello","pos":"#3100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6kyKD3bVi6","abs":"Most current methods for unlearning concepts in text-to-image diffusion models rely on mean squared error-based loss functions to align target distributions with anchors. In this paper, we generalize this idea into a unified $f$-divergence-based framework that recovers the standard mean squared error loss as a specific instance. By generalizing the loss function, we theoretically analyze and numerically validate how different $f$-divergences impact the gradient magnitude and the convergence properties of the algorithm, affecting the quality of unlearning. The proposed unified framework offers a flexible paradigm for selecting the optimal divergence based on the application and user goal, allowing for finer control over the trade-off between unlearning efficacy and generative fidelity."},{"id":"65395","en":"Unlearning Isn't Deletion: Investigating Reversibility of Machine Unlearning in LLMs","ko":"언러닝은 삭제가 아니다: LLM에서 Machine Unlearning의 가역성 조사","authors":"Xiaoyu Xu, Xiang Yue, Yang Liu, Qingqing Ye, Huadi Zheng, Peizhao Hu, Minxin Du, Haibo Hu","pos":"#3102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=E5SVowO13b","abs":"<p>Unlearning in large language models (LLMs) aims to remove specified data, but its efficacy is typically assessed with task-level metrics like accuracy and perplexity.  We demonstrate that these metrics are often misleading, as models can appear to forget while their original behavior is easily restored through minimal fine-tuning.  This phenomenon of \\emph{reversibility} suggests that information is merely suppressed, not genuinely erased. To address this critical evaluation gap, we introduce a \\emph{representation-level analysis framework}.  Our toolkit comprises PCA similarity and shift, centered kernel alignment (CKA), and Fisher information, complemented by a summary metric, the mean PCA distance, to measure representational drift.  Applying this framework across six unlearning methods, three data domains, and multiple LLMs, we identify four distinct forgetting regimes based on their \\emph{reversibility} and \\emph{catastrophicity}.  We compare recovery strategies and show that relearning efficiency relies on the data source. We also find that irreversible, non-catastrophic forgetting is exceptionally challenging. By probing unlearning limits, we identify a case of seemingly irreversible, targeted forgetting, offering insights for more robust erasure algorithms. Overall, our findings expose a gap in current evaluation and establish a representation-level foundation for trustworthy unlearning.</p>"},{"id":"63642","en":"Learning to Watermark in the Latent Space of Generative Models","ko":"생성 모델의 잠재 공간에서 워터마킹 학습하기","authors":"Sylvestre-Alvise Rebuffi, Tuan Tran, Valeriu Lacatusu, Pierre Fernandez, Tomáš Souček, Nikola Jovanović, Tom Sander, Hady Elsahar, Alexandre Mourachko","pos":"#3313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=V6GG63yCtH","abs":"<p>Existing approaches for watermarking AI-generated images often rely on post-hoc methods applied in pixel space, introducing computational overhead and potential visual artifacts. In this work, we explore latent space watermarking and introduce DistSeal, a unified approach for latent watermarking that works across both diffusion and autoregressive models. Our approach works by training post-hoc watermarking models in the latent space of generative models. We demonstrate that these latent watermarkers can be effectively distilled either into the generative model itself or into the latent decoder, enabling in-model watermarking. The resulting latent watermarks achieve competitive robustness while offering similar imperceptibility and up to 20x speedup compared to pixel-space baselines. Our experiments further reveal that distilling latent watermarkers outperforms distilling pixel-space ones, providing a solution that is both more efficient and more robust.</p>","absKo":"<p>AI-generated image를 watermarking하는 기존 접근법은 종종 pixel space에 적용되는 post-hoc method에 의존하여 계산 오버헤드와 잠재적인 시각적 artifact를 유발한다. 본 연구에서는 latent space watermarking을 탐구하고, diffusion model과 autoregressive model 모두에서 작동하는 latent watermarking을 위한 통합 접근법 DistSeal을 소개한다. 우리의 접근법은 generative model의 latent space에서 post-hoc watermarking model을 학습하는 방식으로 동작한다. 우리는 이러한 latent watermarker가 generative model 자체 또는 latent decoder로 효과적으로 distill될 수 있음을 보이며, 이를 통해 in-model watermarking이 가능해진다. 결과적으로 생성된 latent watermark는 pixel-space baseline과 비교해 유사한 imperceptibility와 최대 20배의 speedup을 제공하면서도 경쟁력 있는 robustness를 달성한다. 또한 우리의 실험은 latent watermarker를 distill하는 것이 pixel-space watermarker를 distill하는 것보다 더 우수함을 보여주며, 더 효율적이면서도 더 robust한 해결책을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60784","en":"GoodDiffusion: Proactive Copyright Protection for Diffusion Generative Models via Learnable Sample-specific Signatures","ko":"GoodDiffusion: 학습 가능한 Sample-Specific Signature를 통한 Diffusion Generative Model의 선제적 저작권 보호","authors":"Shixi Qin, zhiyong yang, Shilong Bao, Zitai Wang, Qianqian Xu, Qingming Huang","pos":"#2800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wkV9jSqwa9","abs":"<p>This paper tackles the challenging problem of developing a proactive copyright protection mechanism that cuts off unauthorized use of diffusion generative models. Existing studies largely fall into post-hoc attribution (e.g., watermarking and fingerprinting) or degradation-only defenses, which offer only indirect and limited preventive effect. We therefore propose GoodDiffusion, inspired by backdoor mechanisms, to enforce model-level use-time control by internalizing authorization into the generative process through a selectively permissive, otherwise closed behavior. Specifically, GoodDiffusion preserves high-quality generation for authorized queries carrying valid signatures, yet refuses to generate for unauthorized inputs. We further empirically show that naive static-signature designs (like conventional backdoor injection) are fundamentally fragile, since a surrogate signature can be efficiently recovered via gradient-based optimization. To strengthen security, we introduce a Learnable Signature Network (LSN) that assigns sample-specific signatures conditioned on each input. This breaks the universality of signatures and prevents a surrogate from transferring across inputs. Extensive experiments validate that GoodDiffusion effectively blocks unauthorized use while maintaining strong generation quality for authorized users.</p>","absKo":"<p>본 논문은 diffusion generative model의 무단 사용을 차단하는 능동적 copyright protection mechanism을 개발하는 어려운 문제를 다룬다. 기존 연구는 대부분 post-hoc attribution(예: watermarking 및 fingerprinting) 또는 degradation-only defense에 머물러 있으며, 이는 간접적이고 제한적인 예방 효과만 제공한다. 따라서 우리는 backdoor mechanism에서 영감을 받은 GoodDiffusion을 제안하여, 선택적으로 허용되지만 그 외에는 닫힌 동작을 통해 authorization을 생성 과정 내부에 내재화함으로써 model-level use-time control을 강제한다. 구체적으로, GoodDiffusion은 유효한 signature를 가진 authorized query에 대해서는 고품질 생성을 유지하지만, unauthorized input에 대해서는 생성을 거부한다. 또한 우리는 단순한 static-signature 설계(전통적인 backdoor injection과 유사한 방식)가 본질적으로 취약하며, gradient-based optimization을 통해 surrogate signature를 효율적으로 복원할 수 있음을 실증적으로 보인다. 보안을 강화하기 위해, 우리는 각 input에 조건화된 sample-specific signature를 할당하는 Learnable Signature Network(LSN)을 도입한다. 이는 signature의 보편성을 깨뜨리고 surrogate가 input 간에 전이되는 것을 막는다. 광범위한 실험은 GoodDiffusion이 authorized user에 대해서는 강한 generation quality를 유지하면서 unauthorized use를 효과적으로 차단함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"60926","en":"HyperPotter: Spell the Charm of High-Order Interactions in Audio Deepfake Detection","ko":"HyperPotter: Audio Deepfake Detection에서 고차 상호작용의 마법을 걸다","authors":"Qing Wen, Haohao Li, Zhongjie Ba, Peng Cheng, Miao He, Li Lu, Kui Ren","pos":"#2801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vIXuPi8zUM","abs":"<p>Advances in AIGC technologies have enabled the synthesis of highly realistic audio deepfakes capable of deceiving human auditory perception. Although numerous audio deepfake detection (ADD) methods have been developed, most rely on local temporal/spectral features or pairwise relations, overlooking high-order interactions (HOIs).  HOIs capture discriminative patterns that emerge from multiple feature components beyond their individual contributions. We propose HyperPotter, a hypergraph-based framework that explicitly models these synergistic HOIs through clustering-based hyperedges with class-aware prototype initialization. Extensive experiments demonstrate that HyperPotter surpasses its baseline by an average relative gain of 22.15\\% across 11 datasets and outperforms state-of-the-art methods by 13.96\\% on 4 challenging cross-domain datasets, demonstrating superior generalization to diverse attacks and speakers.</p>","absKo":"<p>AIGC 기술의 발전으로 인해 인간의 청각 지각을 속일 수 있을 정도로 매우 현실적인 audio deepfake를 합성할 수 있게 되었다. 많은 audio deepfake detection (ADD) 방법이 개발되었지만, 대부분은 local temporal/spectral features 또는 pairwise relations에 의존하여 high-order interactions (HOIs)를 간과한다. HOI는 개별 feature component의 기여를 넘어 여러 feature component 사이의 상호작용에서 나타나는 판별적 패턴을 포착한다. 우리는 clustering-based hyperedges와 class-aware prototype initialization을 통해 이러한 시너지적인 HOI를 명시적으로 모델링하는 hypergraph-based framework인 HyperPotter를 제안한다. 광범위한 실험 결과, HyperPotter는 11개 dataset 전반에서 baseline 대비 평균 22.15\\%의 relative gain을 보였고, 4개의 challenging cross-domain dataset에서는 state-of-the-art method보다 13.96\\% 뛰어나 다양한 attack과 speaker에 대한 우수한 generalization을 입증했다.</p>"},{"id":"66820","en":"Low-Compute Watermark Removal via Dual-Domain Natural Projection","ko":"Dual-Domain Natural Projection을 통한 저연산 Watermark 제거","authors":"Pragati Meshram, Varun Chandrasekaran","pos":"#2802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=02NO4Fcsqm","abs":"<p>Effective removal of semantic watermarks requires balancing three competing objectives: \\emph{high removal success}, \\emph{low perceptual distortion}, and \\emph{low computational cost}. However, existing single-image attacks typically optimize only for the first two, achieving strong watermark suppression but relying on expensive, multi-step optimization that limits practical deployment. In this work, we show that this trade-off is fundamental: no current approach achieves all three properties simultaneously. We introduce \\textsc{DAWN}, a lightweight, training-free attack that explicitly targets the low-cost regime while maintaining competitive removal performance. \\textsc{DAWN} works by projecting a watermarked image onto natural-image priors in complementary frequency and semantic spaces, suppressing watermark signals that deviate from natural statistics, and then applying a decoupled perceptual-alignment step to restore visual consistency with minimal artifact. Across diverse pixel-, frequency-, and latent-space watermarking schemes, \\textsc{DAWN} consistently reduces detectability while preserving structural and semantic fidelity, demonstrating that efficient, low-resource watermark removal is feasible with only modest perceptual degradation. Our code is available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DAWN-567A/}.</p>"},{"id":"60816","en":"Next-Gen CAPTCHAs: Leveraging the Cognitive Gap for Scalable and Diverse GUI-Agent Defense","ko":"차세대 CAPTCHA: 확장 가능하고 다양한 GUI-Agent 방어를 위한 인지 격차 활용","authors":"Jiacheng Liu, Yaxin Luo, Jiacheng Cui, Xinyi Shang, Xiaohan Zhao, Zhiqiang Shen","pos":"#2803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wPKGirrtyz","abs":"<p>The rapid evolution of GUI-enabled agents has rendered traditional CAPTCHAs obsolete. While previous benchmarks like OpenCaptchaWorld established a baseline for evaluating multimodal agents, recent advancements in reasoning-heavy models, such as Gemini3-Pro-High and GPT-5.2-Xhigh have effectively collapsed this security barrier, achieving pass rates as high as 90\\% on complex logic puzzles like ''Bingo''. In response, we introduce Next-Gen CAPTCHAs, a scalable defense framework designed to secure the next-generation web against  the advanced agents. Unlike static datasets, our benchmark is built upon a robust data generation pipeline, allowing for large-scale and easily scalable evaluations, notably, for backend-supported types, our system is capable of generating effectively unbounded CAPTCHA instances. We exploit the persistent human--agent ``Cognitive Gap'' in interactive perception, memory, decision-making, and action. By engineering dynamic tasks that require adaptive intuition rather than granular planning, we re-establish a robust distinction between biological users and artificial agents, offering a scalable and diverse defense mechanism for the agentic era.</p>","absKo":"<p>GUI를 사용할 수 있는 agent의 급속한 진화는 전통적인 CAPTCHA를 시대에 뒤떨어지게 만들었다. OpenCaptchaWorld와 같은 이전 benchmark가 multimodal agent 평가의 기준선을 제시했지만, Gemini3-Pro-High와 GPT-5.2-Xhigh 같은 reasoning-heavy model의 최근 발전은 이러한 보안 장벽을 사실상 무너뜨려, ''Bingo''와 같은 복잡한 논리 퍼즐에서 최대 90\\%의 통과율을 달성했다. 이에 대응하여, 우리는 차세대 web을 advanced agent로부터 보호하도록 설계된 확장 가능한 defense framework인 Next-Gen CAPTCHAs를 제안한다. 정적 dataset과 달리, 우리의 benchmark는 견고한 data generation pipeline 위에 구축되어 대규모이고 쉽게 확장 가능한 평가를 가능하게 한다. 특히 backend-supported type의 경우, 우리의 system은 사실상 무한한 CAPTCHA instance를 생성할 수 있다. 우리는 상호작용적 지각, 기억, 의사결정, 행동에서 인간과 agent 사이에 지속적으로 존재하는 ``Cognitive Gap''을 활용한다. 세밀한 계획 대신 적응적 직관을 요구하는 동적 task를 설계함으로써, 생물학적 사용자와 artificial agent 사이의 견고한 구분을 다시 확립하고, agentic era를 위한 확장 가능하고 다양한 defense mechanism을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61218","en":"Real Data Lies: Unveiling and Closing the Quality Shortcut in Generalizable AI-Generated Video Detection","ko":"실제 데이터는 거짓말한다: 일반화 가능한 AI 생성 비디오 탐지에서 품질 Shortcut 드러내기와 해소","authors":"Ziyuan Fang, Tianyi Wei, Guanjie Wang, Weiming Zhang, Nenghai Yu, Wenbo Zhou","pos":"#2804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sYzf4xhthY","abs":"<p>Recent advances in video generation have enabled highly realistic synthetic content, raising concerns about the integrity of digital media and motivating the development of benchmarks and detection methods for generated videos. Prior works have largely prioritized bolstering model generalization against unseen generators. However, we uncover a neglected factor: the quality distribution of real videos plays a pivotal role. Current training protocols suffer from a clear quality bias between real and fake data, prone to shortcut learning. Compounded by testing on similar real data distributions, this creates an illusion of generalization. In reality, these models fail to generalize when exposed to real data with significantly different quality profiles. To address this, we propose training with quality-matched real and fake data to mitigate bias. Building on this, we introduce a data expansion strategy that broadens the training set to comprehensively cover the full quality spectrum. This approach enables the model to learn quality-agnostic features for detection, thereby achieving generalization across real data of varying qualities and enhancing real-world applicability. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our method scales well across diverse backbones, consistently enhancing the generalization capability of existing models.</p>","absKo":"<p>비디오 생성의 최근 발전은 매우 사실적인 합성 콘텐츠를 가능하게 했고, 그에 따라 디지털 미디어의 진정성에 대한 우려가 커지면서 생성 비디오를 위한 benchmark와 탐지 방법의 개발이 촉진되고 있다. 기존 연구들은 대체로 보지 못한 generator에 대한 model generalization을 강화하는 데 우선순위를 두어 왔다. 그러나 우리는 간과되어 온 한 가지 요인을 밝혀낸다. 바로 real video의 quality distribution이 결정적인 역할을 한다는 점이다. 현재의 training protocol은 real data와 fake data 사이에 뚜렷한 quality bias를 보이며, shortcut learning에 취약하다. 여기에 유사한 real data distribution으로 testing까지 더해지면 generalization의 환상이 만들어진다. 실제로는 이러한 model들이 quality profile이 크게 다른 real data에 노출될 때 generalization에 실패한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 bias를 완화하기 위해 quality가 matched된 real data와 fake data로 training하는 방법을 제안한다. 이를 바탕으로, training set을 확장하여 전체 quality spectrum을 포괄적으로 커버하는 data expansion strategy를 도입한다. 이 접근은 model이 detection을 위한 quality-agnostic feature를 학습하게 하며, 결과적으로 다양한 quality의 real data 전반에서 generalization을 달성하고 실제 세계 적용성을 높인다. 대규모 실험은 우리의 method가 다양한 backbone에서 잘 확장되며, 기존 model들의 generalization 능력을 일관되게 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63044","en":"Rethinking Forgery Attacks on Semantic Watermarks in Black-Box Settings: A Geometric Distortion Perspective","ko":"블랙박스 환경에서 시맨틱 워터마크에 대한 위조 공격 재고: 기하학적 왜곡 관점","authors":"Cheng-Yi Lee, Yichi Zhang, Yuchen Yang, Chun-Shien Lu, Jun-Cheng Chen","pos":"#2805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=abAtCFbDqc","abs":"<p>Recent studies have shown that semantic watermarks, which embed information into the initial noise of latent diffusion models (LDMs), are vulnerable to black-box forgery attacks. However, existing methods primarily rely on empirical evidence and lack a rigorous theoretical understanding of the conditions under which such attacks succeed or fail. To bridge this gap, we rethink the nature of such attacks through the lens of rate-distortion in the latent space. Our analysis identifies an irreducible distortion floor due to structural mismatches between proxy and target models, which fundamentally limits the fidelity of forged watermarks. We further characterize this distortion as structured geometric deviations on the latent manifold, in the form of global drift and local deformation rather than stochastic noise. Leveraging these insights, we propose a scheme-agnostic detection method that distinguishes forged samples before watermark verification. Extensive experiments demonstrate the effectiveness of our method across diverse black-box scenarios, while preserving robustness to common distortions.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 연구는 latent diffusion model(LDM)의 initial noise에 정보를 삽입하는 semantic watermark가 black-box forgery attack에 취약함을 보여주었다. 그러나 기존 방법은 주로 경험적 증거에 의존하며, 이러한 공격이 성공하거나 실패하는 조건에 대한 엄밀한 이론적 이해가 부족하다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 latent space의 rate-distortion 관점에서 이러한 공격의 본질을 다시 생각한다. 우리의 분석은 proxy model과 target model 간의 구조적 불일치로 인해 제거할 수 없는 distortion floor가 존재함을 밝혀내며, 이는 forged watermark의 fidelity를 근본적으로 제한한다. 또한 이 distortion은 stochastic noise가 아니라 global drift와 local deformation의 형태로 latent manifold 상의 구조화된 기하학적 편차로 나타남을 규명한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 watermark verification 이전에 forged sample을 구별하는 scheme-agnostic detection method를 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 다양한 black-box 시나리오에서 제안 방법의 효과를 입증하는 동시에, 일반적인 distortion에 대한 robust성을 유지함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60737","en":"Ripple Perturbations Through Structure: Likelihood-Constrained Adversarial Attacks on Heterogeneous Tabular Data","ko":"구조를 따라 퍼지는 Ripple Perturbation: 이질적 Tabular Data에 대한 Likelihood-Constrained Adversarial Attack","authors":"Zhengjie Zhou, Jiahuan Yan, Boqun Ma, Weiwei Feng, Tengfei LIU, Weiqiang Wang","pos":"#2806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x5IRLBdTDa","abs":"<p>Generating realistic adversarial examples for tabular data remains challenging due to heterogeneous feature types and asymmetric inter-feature dependencies. Existing approaches typically rely on handcrafted constraints or undirected similarity criteria to delimit the feasible attack region, which often fail to capture the structural dependency governing tabular generation. Consequently, standard attacks typically produce perturbations that are statistically likely yet semantically inconsistent and prone to optimization stagnation via gradient masking. To address this, we propose LCSA, a white-box framework that formulates adversarial generation as optimization over structurally admissible perturbations. LCSA leverages an ensemble of heterogeneous neural Structural Causal Models to infer dependencies and introduces a structure-aware ripple mechanism. Unlike attacks that perturb features in isolation, this mechanism propagates updates downstream, acting as a structural preconditioner that conditions gradient flow to mitigate masking effects. Extensive experiments demonstrate that LCSA outperforms state-of-the-art baselines in 45 of 50 evaluated configurations, yielding adversarial examples with superior structural consistency and transferability.</p>","absKo":"<p>Tabular data에 대한 realistic adversarial example 생성은 이질적인 feature type과 비대칭적인 inter-feature dependency 때문에 여전히 어렵다. 기존 접근법은 일반적으로 수작업으로 설계된 constraint나 비지시적 similarity criterion에 의존해 feasible attack region을 제한하는데, 이는 tabular generation을 지배하는 구조적 종속성을 포착하지 못하는 경우가 많다. 결과적으로 표준 attack은 통계적으로는 그럴듯하지만 의미적으로는 일관되지 않은 perturbation을 생성하며, gradient masking을 통한 optimization stagnation에 취약하다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 adversarial generation을 구조적으로 허용 가능한 perturbation에 대한 optimization으로 정식화하는 white-box framework인 LCSA를 제안한다. LCSA는 이질적인 neural Structural Causal Model의 ensemble을 활용해 dependency를 추론하고, structure-aware ripple mechanism을 도입한다. feature를 개별적으로 perturb하는 attack과 달리, 이 mechanism은 update를 downstream으로 전파하여 gradient flow를 조건화하는 structural preconditioner로 작동하고 masking effect를 완화한다. 광범위한 실험은 LCSA가 평가된 50개 설정 중 45개에서 state-of-the-art baseline을 능가하며, 구조적 일관성과 transferability가 더 뛰어난 adversarial example을 생성함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"65213","en":"Semantic Router: On the Feasibility of Hijacking MLLMs via a Single Adversarial Perturbation","ko":"Semantic Router: 단일 적대적 섭동을 통한 MLLM 하이재킹의 실현 가능성에 대하여","authors":"Changyue Li, Jiaying Li, Youliang Yuan, Jiaming He, Zhicong Huang, Pinjia He","pos":"#2807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FjWZrbabBX","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) are increasingly deployed in stateless systems, such as autonomous driving and robotics.   This paper investigates a novel threat: Semantic-Aware Hijacking. We explore the feasibility of hijacking multiple stateless decisions simultaneously using a single universal perturbation.   We introduce the Semantic-Aware Universal Perturbation (SAUP), which acts as a semantic router, \"actively\" perceiving input semantics and routing them to distinct, attacker-defined targets.   To achieve this, we conduct theoretical and empirical analysis on the geometric properties in the latent space. Guided by these insights, we propose the Semantic-Oriented (SORT) optimization strategy and annotate a new dataset with fine-grained semantics to evaluate performance. Extensive experiments on three representative MLLMs demonstrate the fundamental feasibility of this attack, achieving a 66% attack success rate over five targets using a single frame against Qwen.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs)은 자율주행과 로보틱스 같은 stateless system에 점점 더 많이 배치되고 있다. 이 논문은 Semantic-Aware Hijacking이라는 새로운 threat를 조사한다. 우리는 단일 universal perturbation으로 여러 stateless decision을 동시에 hijack할 수 있는 가능성을 탐구한다. 우리는 semantic router처럼 작동하며, 입력의 semantics를 \"능동적으로\" 인지하고 이를 attacker가 정의한 서로 다른 target으로 라우팅하는 Semantic-Aware Universal Perturbation (SAUP)을 소개한다. 이를 달성하기 위해 latent space의 geometric property에 대해 이론적 및 실증적 분석을 수행한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로 Semantic-Oriented (SORT) optimization strategy를 제안하고, 성능 평가를 위해 fine-grained semantics가 주석된 새로운 dataset을 구축한다. 대표적인 세 가지 MLLM에 대한 광범위한 실험은 이 attack의 근본적 실현 가능성을 보여주며, Qwen에 대해 단일 frame만으로 다섯 개 target에 걸쳐 66%의 attack success rate를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60529","en":"TRAP: Hijacking VLA CoT-Reasoning via Adversarial Patches","ko":"TRAP: Adversarial Patch를 통한 VLA CoT Reasoning 하이재킹","authors":"Zhengxian Huang, Wenjun Zhu, Haoxuan Qiu, Xiaoyu Ji, Wenyuan Xu","pos":"#2808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zLUPTgV7BI","abs":"<p>By integrating Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning, Vision-Language-Action (VLA) models have demonstrated strong capabilities in robotic manipulation, particularly by improving generalization and interpretability. However, the security of CoT-based reasoning mechanisms remains largely unexplored. In this paper, we show that Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning introduces a novel attack vector for targeted control hijacking—for example, causing a robot to mistakenly deliver a knife to a person instead of an apple—without modifying the user’s instruction. We first provide empirical evidence that CoT strongly governs action generation, even when it is semantically misaligned with the input instructions. Building on this observation, we propose <strong>TRAP</strong>, the first targeted adversarial attack framework for CoT-reasoning VLA models. <strong>TRAP</strong> uses an adversarial patch (e.g., a coaster placed on the table) to corrupt intermediate CoT reasoning and hijack the VLA’s output. By optimizing the CoT adversarial loss, <strong>TRAP</strong> induces specific and adversary-defined behaviors. Extensive evaluations across 3 mainstreaming VLA architectures and 3 CoT reasoning paradigms validate the effectiveness of <strong>TRAP</strong>. Notably, we implemented the patch by printing it on paper in a real-world setting. Our findings highlight the urgent need to secure CoT reasoning in VLA systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>Chain-of-Thought(CoT) 추론을 통합함으로써 Vision-Language-Action(VLA) 모델은 로봇 조작에서 특히 일반화와 해석가능성을 향상시키는 강력한 능력을 보여주었다. 그러나 CoT 기반 추론 메커니즘의 보안성은 아직 거의 탐구되지 않았다. 본 논문에서는 Chain-of-Thought(CoT) 추론이 사용자 지시를 수정하지 않고도 표적 제어 탈취(targeted control hijacking)를 가능하게 하는 새로운 공격 벡터를 도입함을 보인다. 예를 들어, 로봇이 사과 대신 칼을 사람에게 잘못 전달하도록 만들 수 있다. 우리는 먼저 CoT가 입력 지시와 의미적으로 어긋난 경우에도 행동 생성을 강하게 지배한다는 실증적 증거를 제시한다. 이 관찰을 바탕으로, CoT 추론을 사용하는 VLA 모델을 대상으로 하는 최초의 표적 적대적 공격 프레임워크인 <strong>TRAP</strong>을 제안한다. <strong>TRAP</strong>은 적대적 패치(예: 테이블 위에 놓인 코스터)를 사용해 중간 CoT 추론을 교란하고 VLA의 출력을 탈취한다. CoT 적대적 손실을 최적화함으로써 <strong>TRAP</strong>은 특정하고 공격자가 정의한 행동을 유도한다. 3개의 주류 VLA 아키텍처와 3개의 CoT 추론 패러다임에 걸친 광범위한 평가를 통해 <strong>TRAP</strong>의 효과가 검증되었다. 특히, 우리는 실제 환경에서 이를 종이에 인쇄해 구현했다. 우리의 결과는 VLA 시스템에서 CoT 추론을 보호해야 할 시급한 필요성을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"60736","en":"Think Twice Before You Act: Enhancing Agent Behavioral Safety with Thought Correction","ko":"행동하기 전에 두 번 생각하라: Thought Correction으로 Agent 행동 안전성 향상","authors":"Changyue Jiang, Wenqi Zhang, Xudong Pan, Geng Hong, Min Yang","pos":"#2809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x5VjErljHS","abs":"<p>LLM-based agents solve complex tasks through iterative reasoning, tool use, and environment interaction, where each intermediate thought directly shapes subsequent actions. Small deviations in these thoughts can therefore propagate into unsafe behaviors, yet existing guardrails typically operate only on final outputs or require intrusive model modifications. We introduce Thought-Aligner, a lightweight plug-in safety model that performs causal correction on unsafe thoughts before action execution, without altering the underlying agent. The corrected thoughts are fed back into the agent, steering its decision process and tool use toward safer trajectories. Because it operates solely at the thought level, Thought-Aligner is model-agnostic and can be integrated into diverse agent frameworks. We train Thought-Aligner via two-stage contrastive learning on paired safe and unsafe thoughts generated across ten risk scenarios. Experiments on two agent-safety benchmarks with six LLMs show that Thought-Aligner increases behavioral safety from about 50% without protection to around 90% on average, exceeding state-of-the-art guardrails by roughly 23%, while also improving helpfulness by about 5%. The method incurs low per-step latency and minimal overhead, enabling scalable and practical deployment.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM 기반 agent는 iterative reasoning, tool use, environment interaction을 통해 복잡한 과제를 해결하며, 각 intermediate thought는 이후 행동을 직접 형성한다. 따라서 이러한 thought의 작은 편차도 unsafe behavior로 전파될 수 있지만, 기존 guardrail은 일반적으로 최종 출력에만 작동하거나 침습적인 model 수정이 필요하다. 우리는 underlying agent를 변경하지 않고도 action 실행 전에 unsafe thought를 causal correction하는 경량 plug-in safety model인 Thought-Aligner를 소개한다. 수정된 thought는 agent에 다시 주입되어, 의사결정 과정과 tool use를 더 안전한 trajectory로 유도한다. Thought-Aligner는 thought 수준에서만 작동하므로 model-agnostic이며 다양한 agent framework에 통합할 수 있다. 우리는 10개의 risk scenario 전반에서 생성된 safe thought와 unsafe thought의 쌍을 이용한 two-stage contrastive learning으로 Thought-Aligner를 학습한다. 6개의 LLM과 두 개의 agent-safety benchmark에서의 실험은 Thought-Aligner가 behavioral safety를 보호 없이 약 50%에서 평균 약 90%로 높이고, state-of-the-art guardrail을 약 23% 앞서며, helpfulness도 약 5% 개선함을 보여 준다. 이 방법은 per-step latency가 낮고 overhead가 최소이므로, 확장 가능하고 실용적인 배포가 가능하다.</p>"},{"id":"60958","en":"Unlearning Isn’t Forgetting: Revealing Hidden Leakage in Class Unlearning Evaluations","ko":"Unlearning은 Forgetting이 아니다: Class Unlearning 평가의 숨겨진 Leakage 드러내기","authors":"Ali Ebrahimpour-Boroojeny, Yian Wang, Hari Sundaram","pos":"#2811","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v2mY3gjdnP","abs":"In this paper, we reveal a significant shortcoming in class unlearning evaluations: overlooking the underlying class geometry can cause information leakage about the forgotten class. We further propose a simple unlearning strategy to mitigate this issue. We introduce Class Membership Inference Attack (CMIA) that uses the probabilities the model assigns to neighboring classes to detect unlearned samples. We find that existing unlearning methods are vulnerable to CMIA across multiple datasets. We then propose a new fine-tuning objective that mitigates this privacy leakage by approximating, for forget-class inputs, the distribution over the remaining classes that a retrained-from-scratch model would produce. To construct this approximation, we estimate inter-class similarity and tilt the target model’s distribution accordingly. The resulting Tilted REWeighting (TREW) distribution serves as the desired distribution during fine-tuning. We also show that across multiple benchmarks, TREW matches or surpasses existing unlearning methods on prior unlearning metrics. More specifically, on CIFAR-10, it reduces the gap with retrained models by $19\\%$ and $46\\%$ for U-LiRA and CMIA scores, accordingly, compared to the SOTA method for each category.","absKo":"이 논문에서는 class unlearning 평가에서의 중대한 결함을 드러낸다. 즉, underlying class geometry를 간과하면 잊힌 class에 대한 정보 누출이 발생할 수 있다. 또한 이 문제를 완화하기 위한 간단한 unlearning 전략을 제안한다. 우리는 모델이 인접한 class에 할당하는 확률을 사용해 unlearned sample을 탐지하는 Class Membership Inference Attack (CMIA)을 도입한다. 기존 unlearning 방법들이 여러 데이터셋에서 CMIA에 취약함을 보인다. 이어서, forget-class 입력에 대해 scratch에서 다시 학습한 모델이 생성했을 remaining class들의 분포를 근사하는 새로운 fine-tuning 목적함수를 제안하여 이러한 privacy leakage를 완화한다. 이 근사를 구성하기 위해 inter-class similarity를 추정하고, 이에 맞게 target model의 분포를 기울인다. 그 결과 얻어지는 Tilted REWeighting (TREW) 분포는 fine-tuning 동안 원하는 분포로 사용된다. 또한 여러 benchmark에서 TREW가 기존 unlearning metric들에 대해 기존 unlearning 방법과 동등하거나 그 이상임을 보인다. 보다 구체적으로, CIFAR-10에서는 U-LiRA와 CMIA score에서 retrained model과의 격차를 각각 $19\\%$와 $46\\%$ 줄이며, 각 범주에서 SOTA 방법과 비교해 개선된다."},{"id":"63840","en":"WatchLog: Efficient and Interpretable Event Reasoning for Endpoint Detection and Response Logs with Multimodal LLMs","ko":"WatchLog: multimodal LLM을 활용한 endpoint detection and response 로그의 효율적이고 해석 가능한 이벤트 추론","authors":"Hongyi Zhou, Jianfeng Pan, Min Peng, Shaomang Huang, Xuling Zhang","pos":"#2812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TGiXDdlzfR","abs":"<p>Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR) systems are crucial for identifying malicious activities on endpoint devices, yet existing methods struggle to efficiently model ultra-long log sequences and to provide interpretable reasoning for security analysts. We propose WatchLog, a novel framework that represents raw logs as video-structured data, enabling scalable and expressive video-language modeling of endpoint behaviors. Each event is encoded as a key–value-guided image, and the resulting images are temporally organized into a video sequence. To capture long-range dependencies, WatchLog employs a temporal cross-attention adapter that enables pixel-wise interaction across time. The adapter acts as an auxiliary temporal reasoning pathway, aligning spatial representations with relevant temporal contexts while preserving the original behavioral semantics. We adopt a two-stage pre-training strategy followed by supervised fine-tuning to generate behavior explanations grounded in event-level semantics and detection outcomes. Experiments on our newly constructed EDR8M-20R dataset and a public benchmark demonstrate that WatchLog consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods in detection accuracy and recall, while offering more interpretable reasoning traces and significantly improved inference efficiency. Extensive ablation studies further support the robustness and interpretability of the proposed method.</p>","absKo":"<p>Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR) 시스템은 endpoint device에서의 악의적 활동을 식별하는 데 핵심적이지만, 기존 방법들은 ultra-long log sequence를 효율적으로 모델링하고 security analyst를 위한 해석 가능한 reasoning을 제공하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 raw log를 video-structured data로 표현하여 endpoint behavior의 확장 가능하고 표현력 있는 video-language modeling을 가능하게 하는 새로운 프레임워크 WatchLog를 제안한다. 각 event는 key–value-guided image로 인코딩되며, 생성된 image들은 시간적으로 정렬되어 video sequence를 이룬다. 장거리 의존성을 포착하기 위해 WatchLog는 시간 축 전반에 걸친 pixel-wise interaction을 가능하게 하는 temporal cross-attention adapter를 사용한다. 이 adapter는 auxiliary temporal reasoning pathway로 작동하며, 원래의 behavioral semantics를 보존하면서 spatial representation을 관련 temporal context와 정렬한다. 우리는 two-stage pre-training 전략을 채택한 뒤 supervised fine-tuning을 수행하여 event-level semantics와 detection outcome에 근거한 behavior explanation을 생성한다. 새로 구축한 EDR8M-20R 데이터셋과 공개 benchmark에서의 실험은 WatchLog가 detection accuracy와 recall 모두에서 state-of-the-art 방법을 일관되게 능가하면서도, 더 해석 가능한 reasoning trace와 크게 향상된 inference efficiency를 제공함을 보여준다. 광범위한 ablation study는 제안 방법의 robustness와 interpretability를 추가로 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"61861","en":"dgMARK: Decoding-Guided Watermarking for Diffusion Language Models","ko":"dgMARK: Diffusion Language Model을 위한 Decoding-Guided Watermarking","authors":"Pyo Min Hong, Albert No","pos":"#2813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mJJaz04lQR","abs":"<p>We propose dgMARK, a decoding-guided watermarking method for discrete diffusion language models (dLLMs). Unlike autoregressive models, dLLMs can generate tokens in arbitrary order. While an ideal conditional predictor would be invariant to this order, practical dLLMs exhibit strong sensitivity to the unmasking order, creating a new channel for watermarking. dgMARK steers the unmasking order toward positions whose high-reward candidate tokens satisfy a simple parity constraint induced by a binary hash, without explicitly reweighting the model’s learned probabilities. The method is plug-and-play with common decoding strategies (e.g., confidence, entropy, and margin-based ordering) and can be strengthened with a one-step lookahead variant. Watermarks are detected via elevated parity-matching statistics, and a sliding-window detector ensures robustness under post-editing operations including insertion, deletion, substitution, and paraphrasing.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 discrete diffusion language model (dLLM)을 위한 decoding-guided watermarking method인 dgMARK를 제안한다. Autoregressive model과 달리 dLLM은 token을 임의의 순서로 생성할 수 있다. 이상적인 conditional predictor라면 이러한 순서에 불변해야 하지만, 실제 dLLM은 unmasking order에 강한 민감성을 보이며, 이는 watermarking을 위한 새로운 채널을 만든다. dgMARK는 binary hash가 유도하는 단순한 parity constraint를 만족하는 high-reward candidate token을 가진 position 쪽으로 unmasking order를 유도하며, model이 학습한 probability를 명시적으로 재가중하지 않는다. 이 방법은 confidence, entropy, margin-based ordering과 같은 일반적인 decoding strategy와 plug-and-play로 결합할 수 있으며, one-step lookahead variant로 강화할 수도 있다. Watermark는 향상된 parity-matching statistic을 통해 검출되며, sliding-window detector는 insertion, deletion, substitution, paraphrasing을 포함한 post-editing operation 하에서도 견고성을 보장한다.</p>"},{"id":"64544","en":"Gaming Consensus: Coordinated Manipulation in Crowdsourced Fact-Checking","ko":"합의 게이밍: 크라우드소싱 팩트체킹에서의 협응적 조작","authors":"Nikil Selvam, Jay Baxter, Sophie Hilgard, Brad Miller, Keith Coleman, Ellen Vitercik, Sanmi Koyejo","pos":"#2900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=MMmO3hxYsK","abs":"<p>Crowdsourced fact-checking systems have been widely adopted by major social media companies such as X, Meta, Tiktok, and Google with the aim of combating misinformation at scale without relying on centralized editorial control. These systems have been developed around a common underlying algorithm: a bridging mechanism—based on matrix factorization—that surfaces notes indicating misinformation only when they receive support from diverse ideological groups rather than simple majority support. Although this algorithm is designed to be robust against traditional brigading, we demonstrate an attack showing that coordinated users can strategically fabricate diverse agreement in the system’s latent space to manipulate the scoring algorithm. We validate this attack on real-world production data and find that a surprisingly large number of notes’ scores can potentially be manipulated with a small number (&lt; 10) of coordinated votes, raising the risk that adversaries could surface arbitrary notes on these social media platforms. We complement these findings with a theoretical analysis of voting strategies that surface arbitrary notes, revealing counterintuitive properties of the system: for instance, rating a note as “Not Helpful” can increase its helpfulness score. Finally, we develop a cost model quantifying manipulation effort and discuss potential mitigations. Following a responsible disclosure process, X's Community Notes team acknowledged this attack and has deployed mitigations based on our findings. We hope this work spurs further research into the robustness of crowdsourced fact-checking systems and, more broadly, bridging-based consensus mechanisms.</p>","absKo":"<p>X, Meta, Tiktok, Google과 같은 주요 social media 회사들은 중앙집중식 편집 통제에 의존하지 않고 대규모로 misinformation에 대응하기 위해 crowdsourced fact-checking system을 널리 채택해 왔다. 이러한 시스템은 공통의 기반 알고리즘을 중심으로 개발되었는데, 이는 matrix factorization에 기반한 bridging mechanism으로, 단순한 다수 지지보다 다양한 이념 집단의 지지를 받을 때에만 misinformation을 나타내는 note를 표면화한다. 이 알고리즘은 전통적인 brigading에 대한 견고성을 목표로 설계되었지만, 우리는 coordinated user가 시스템의 latent space에서 다양해 보이는 합의를 전략적으로 조작하여 scoring algorithm을 왜곡할 수 있음을 보이는 attack을 제시한다. 우리는 이 attack을 실제 production data에서 검증했고, 놀랍게도 적은 수의(< 10) coordinated vote만으로도 상당히 많은 note의 score가 조작될 수 있음을 발견하여, adversary가 이러한 social media platform에서 임의의 note를 표면화할 수 있는 위험을 제기한다. 우리는 임의의 note를 표면화하는 voting strategy에 대한 이론적 분석으로 이러한 발견을 보강했으며, 시스템의 직관에 반하는 성질을 드러낸다. 예를 들어, note를 “Not Helpful”로 평가하는 것이 오히려 해당 note의 helpfulness score를 높일 수 있다. 마지막으로, 우리는 조작 노력을 정량화하는 cost model을 개발하고 가능한 완화책을 논의한다. 책임 있는 disclosure 절차를 따른 결과, X의 Community Notes 팀은 이 attack을 인정했고 우리의 발견을 바탕으로 완화책을 배포했다. 우리는 이 작업이 crowdsourced fact-checking system의 견고성, 더 넓게는 bridging-based consensus mechanism에 대한 추가 연구를 촉진하기를 바란다.</p>"},{"id":"60710","en":"Forensic Prompting with Dual-Action Policy Optimization for Vision-Language Forgery Detection and Localization","ko":"Vision-Language 위조 탐지 및 위치 추정을 위한 Dual-Action Policy Optimization 기반 Forensic Prompting","authors":"Ye Zhu, Ai Zhao, Jinwei Wang","pos":"#2901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xJV9klbfuR","abs":"<p>Image forgery is rapidly evolving, rendering forensic traces increasingly subtle and readily attenuated by post-processing. Although vision--language prompting can inject priors, open-ended LLM-generated prompts are difficult to constrain, and naive language description can introduce semantic perturbations. To address these challenges, we propose Forensic Prompting with Dual-Action policy optimization (FPDA) for vision-language forgery detection and localization, where Forensic Prompting Module (FPM) constructs a structured forensic prompt bank and supports optional text input to provide lightweight stable conditioning via a reliability gate. Moreover, a Dual-Action Policy Optimization (DAPO) is applied to adaptively route prompts and schedule refinement strategies on a per-image basis, stabilizing discriminative cues and improving mask spatial consistency. Extensive experiments are conducted on multiple public datasets of manipulations, diffusion content, face forgeries, and text-enabled settings (e.g., CASIA/NIST16/Coverage, CocoGlide, OpenForensics and SID<em>Set</em>description), which demonstrates superior detection and localization performance over state-of-the-art methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>이미지 위조는 빠르게 진화하고 있으며, forensic trace는 점점 더 미세해지고 후처리에 의해 쉽게 약화된다. vision--language prompting은 prior를 주입할 수 있지만, open-ended LLM-generated prompt는 제어하기 어렵고, 단순한 언어 설명은 semantic perturbation을 유발할 수 있다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 vision-language forgery detection과 localization을 위한 Forensic Prompting with Dual-Action policy optimization(FPDA)을 제안한다. 여기서 Forensic Prompting Module(FPM)은 구조화된 forensic prompt bank를 구성하고, reliability gate를 통해 가벼우면서도 안정적인 conditioning을 제공하기 위한 선택적 text input을 지원한다. 더 나아가, Dual-Action Policy Optimization(DAPO)을 적용하여 이미지별로 prompt를 라우팅하고 refinement strategy를 동적으로 스케줄링함으로써, 판별 신호를 안정화하고 mask의 spatial consistency를 향상시킨다. 다양한 조작, diffusion content, face forgery 및 text-enabled setting(예: CASIA/NIST16/Coverage, CocoGlide, OpenForensics, SID<em>Set</em>description)에서 여러 공개 dataset을 대상으로 광범위한 실험을 수행하였으며, 그 결과 state-of-the-art method보다 우수한 detection 및 localization 성능을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62859","en":"Echoes within the Reasoning:  Stealth and Effective Watermarking via Chain of Thought","ko":"추론 내부의 에코: Chain of Thought 기반 은밀하고 효과적인 Watermarking","authors":"Jiacheng Lu, Yiming Li, Tao Song, Weijian Wang, Wenjie Qu, Haibing Guan, Jiaheng Zhang","pos":"#2902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cTCFYMqulL","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) with proprietary Chain-of-Thought (CoT) capabilities constitute high-value intellectual property, yet protecting them against unauthorized theft and unlicensed commercialization remains a critical challenge. Existing watermarking paradigms are ill-suited for safeguarding these models: direct logit perturbations inevitably fracture the fragile logical consistency required for complex reasoning, or remain superficial enough to be erased by fine-tuning. In this paper, we propose BiCoT, a framework that embeds ownership directly into the reasoning representations via bi-level variational alignment. Instead of adding external perturbations, our method optimizes the model's internal states to collapse onto a signature subspace. This creates a functional entanglement where the watermark becomes a prerequisite for the model's reasoning utility: removing the signature destroys the capability. To handle representation drift in stolen models, we further introduce a Robust Subspace Registration (RSR) verifier. Experiments demonstrate that BiCoT achieves negligible fidelity loss while maintaining strong robustness against diverse attacks on both in-domain and out-of-distribution data.</p>","absKo":"<p>proprietary Chain-of-Thought(CoT) capability를 갖는 Large Language Model(LLM)은 고부가가치 지적 재산이지만, 무단 도용과 무허가 상업화로부터 이를 보호하는 것은 여전히 중요한 과제다. 기존 watermarking 패러다임은 이러한 모델을 보호하는 데 적합하지 않다. 직접적인 logit perturbation은 복잡한 reasoning에 필요한 취약한 논리적 일관성을 필연적으로 깨뜨리거나, fine-tuning으로 쉽게 지워질 만큼 피상적이기 때문이다. 본 논문에서는 bi-level variational alignment를 통해 ownership을 reasoning representation에 직접 내재화하는 framework인 BiCoT를 제안한다. 외부 perturbation을 더하는 대신, 우리의 방법은 모델의 내부 state를 최적화하여 signature subspace로 수렴하도록 만든다. 이는 watermark가 모델의 reasoning utility를 위한 전제 조건이 되는 functional entanglement를 생성한다. 즉, signature를 제거하면 capability도 함께 사라진다. 도난된 모델에서 representation drift를 처리하기 위해, 우리는 Robust Subspace Registration(RSR) verifier도 추가로 제안한다. 실험 결과 BiCoT는 다양한 공격에 대해 강한 robustness를 유지하면서도 in-domain 및 out-of-distribution data 모두에서 fidelity loss가 거의 없음을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"61105","en":"Dissecting the Safety Circuit: Neuronal Intervention for Transferable Adversarial Attacks on VLMs","ko":"안전성 회로 해부: VLM에 대한 전이 가능한 Adversarial Attack을 위한 Neuronal Intervention","authors":"Chunlong Xie, Kangjie Chen, Shangwei Guo, Shudong Zhang, Jiamou Liu, Tianwei Zhang, Tao Xiang","pos":"#2904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tf1o7E0jjf","abs":"<p>The limited transferability of adversarial attacks on Vision-Language Models (VLMs) stems from their failure to navigate model-specific safety alignments, where superficial perturbations exploit surrogate-specific artifacts rather than shared safety-critical features. We reveal through linear probing that safety-related representations are concentrated within specific intermediate neuronal circuits, which act as localized defense bottlenecks that can be disentangled from transferable features. To overcome this barrier, we propose the Safety Circuit Intervention Attack (SCIA), a framework that surgically steers internal representations to bypass these localized safety mechanisms. SCIA employs a dual-objective steering strategy that suppresses the defensive circuit encoding safety features while amplifying the transferable circuit capturing model-agnostic representations, effectively decoupling adversarial patterns from surrogate-specific safety behaviors. Furthermore, we incorporate contrastive semantic steering and spectral smoothness regularization to guide optimization toward compliant semantic regions while producing visually coherent perturbations. Experimental results demonstrate that SCIA significantly outperforms state-of-the-art methods in bypassing unseen black-box VLMs.</p>","absKo":"Vision-Language Model(VLMs)에 대한 adversarial attack의 낮은 transferability는 model-specific safety alignment를 회피하지 못하는 데서 비롯된다. 표면적인 perturbation은 공유된 safety-critical feature가 아니라 surrogate-specific artifact를 이용하기 때문이다. 우리는 linear probing을 통해 safety 관련 representation이 특정 intermediate neuronal circuit 내부에 집중되어 있음을 밝혀냈으며, 이 circuit은 transferable feature와 분리될 수 있는 localized defense bottleneck으로 작동한다. 이러한 장벽을 극복하기 위해, 우리는 내부 representation을 정교하게 조작하여 이러한 localized safety mechanism을 우회하는 Safety Circuit Intervention Attack (SCIA)을 제안한다. SCIA는 safety feature를 인코딩하는 defensive circuit을 억제하는 동시에, model-agnostic representation을 포착하는 transferable circuit을 증폭시키는 dual-objective steering strategy를 사용하여 adversarial pattern을 surrogate-specific safety behavior와 효과적으로 분리한다. 또한, contrastive semantic steering과 spectral smoothness regularization을 통합하여, 시각적으로 일관된 perturbation을 생성하면서 최적화가 준수 가능한 semantic region으로 향하도록 유도한다. 실험 결과, SCIA는 보지 못한 black-box VLM을 우회하는 데 있어 state-of-the-art method를 크게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65175","en":"DGS-Net: Distillation-Guided Gradient Surgery for CLIP Fine-Tuning in AI-Generated Image Detection","ko":"DGS-Net: AI 생성 이미지 탐지에서 CLIP 파인튜닝을 위한 증류 기반 Gradient Surgery","authors":"Jiazhen Yan, Ziqiang Li, Fan Wang, Boyu Wang, Ziwen He, Zhangjie Fu","pos":"#2905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=G5XGej7wNt","abs":"<p>The rapid progress of generative models such as GANs and diffusion models has led to the widespread proliferation of AI-generated images, raising concerns about misinformation, privacy violations, and trust erosion in digital media. Although large-scale multimodal models like CLIP offer strong transferable representations for detecting synthetic content, fine-tuning them often induces catastrophic forgetting, which degrades pre-trained priors and limits cross-domain generalization. To address this issue, we propose the Distillation-guided Gradient Surgery Network (DGS-Net), a novel framework that preserves transferable pre-trained priors while suppressing task-irrelevant components. Specifically, we introduce a gradient-space decomposition that separates harmful and beneficial descent directions during optimization. By projecting task gradients onto the orthogonal complement of harmful directions and aligning with beneficial ones distilled from a frozen CLIP encoder, DGS-Net achieves unified optimization of prior preservation and irrelevant suppression. Extensive experiments on 50 generative models demonstrate that our method outperforms state-of-the-art approaches by an average margin of 6.6%, achieving superior detection performance and generalization across diverse generation techniques.</p>","absKo":"<p>GAN과 diffusion model 같은 generative model의 급속한 발전은 AI-generated image의 광범위한 확산을 초래했으며, 이는 misinformation, privacy 침해, 그리고 디지털 미디어에 대한 신뢰 약화에 대한 우려를 낳고 있다. CLIP과 같은 대규모 multimodal model은 synthetic content 탐지를 위한 강력한 transferable representation을 제공하지만, 이를 fine-tuning하면 종종 catastrophic forgetting이 발생하여 사전 학습된 prior가 손상되고 cross-domain generalization이 제한된다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Distillation-guided Gradient Surgery Network (DGS-Net)을 제안한다. 이는 task와 무관한 성분을 억제하면서도 전이 가능한 사전 학습 prior를 보존하는 새로운 framework이다. 구체적으로, 최적화 동안 유해한 descent direction과 유익한 descent direction을 분리하는 gradient-space decomposition을 도입한다. task gradient를 유해한 방향의 orthogonal complement에 투영하고, frozen CLIP encoder에서 distill한 유익한 방향과 정렬함으로써 DGS-Net은 prior 보존과 무관 성분 억제를 통합적으로 최적화한다. 50개의 generative model에 대한 광범위한 실험에서, 우리의 방법은 평균 6.6%의 성능 향상으로 state-of-the-art 접근법을 능가했으며, 다양한 생성 기법 전반에서 우수한 탐지 성능과 generalization을 달성했다.</p>"},{"id":"66067","en":"Collaborative Threshold Watermarking","ko":"협력적 임계값 워터마킹","authors":"Tameem Bakr, Anish Ambreth, Nils Lukas","pos":"#2907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7LdwttMfgE","abs":"In federated learning (FL), $K$ clients jointly train a model without sharing raw data. Because each participant invests data and computing power, clients need mechanisms to later prove the provenance of a jointly trained model.  Model watermarking embeds a hidden signal in the weights, but naive approaches either do not scale with many clients (per-client watermarks dilute as $K$ grows) or give any individual client the ability to verify (and potentially remove) a shared-key watermark. We introduce $(t,K)$-threshold watermarking: clients collaboratively embed a single watermark during training, while only coalitions of at least $t$ clients can reconstruct the watermark key and verify a suspect model, but any coalition of fewer than $t$ clients learns nothing about the watermark beyond the verification output. We instantiate our protocol in the white-box setting and evaluate on CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and Tiny ImageNet. Our watermark remains detectable at scale (up to $K=128$) with minimal accuracy loss and stays above the detection threshold ($z\\ge 4$) under 90% pruning, 4-bit quantization, and adaptive fine-tuning using up to 20% of the training data."},{"id":"63753","en":"CBV: Clean-label Backdoor Attacks on Vision Language Models via Diffusion Models","ko":"CBV: Diffusion Models를 활용한 Vision Language Models 대상 Clean-label Backdoor 공격","authors":"Ji Guo, xiaolong qin, Wenbo Jiang, Cencen Liu, Jielei Wang, Jierun Chen","pos":"#2909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=U1YNfdXkVD","abs":"<p>Vision-Language Models (VLMs) have achieved remarkable success in tasks such as image captioning and visual question answering (VQA). However, as their applications become increasingly widespread, recent studies have revealed that VLMs are vulnerable to backdoor attacks. Existing backdoor attacks on VLMs primarily rely on data poisoning by adding visual triggers and modifying text labels, where the induced image–text mismatch makes poisoned samples easy to detect. To address this limitation, we propose the Clean-Label Backdoor Attack on VLMs via Diffusion Models (CBV), which leverages diffusion models to generate natural poisoned examples via score matching. Specifically, CBV modifies the score during the reverse generation process of the diffusion model to guide the generation of poisoned samples that contain triggered image features. To further enhance the effectiveness of the attack, we incorporate the textual information of the triggered images as multimodal guidance during generation. Moreover, to enhance stealthiness, we introduce a GradCAM-guided Mask (GM) that restricts modifications to only the most semantically important regions, rather than the entire image. We evaluate our method on MSCOCO and VQA v2 with four representative VLMs, achieving over 80\\% ASR while preserving normal functionality.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-Language Models (VLMs)는 image captioning과 visual question answering (VQA) 같은 task에서 놀라운 성공을 거두었다. 그러나 적용 범위가 점점 넓어지면서, 최근 연구들은 VLMs가 backdoor attack에 취약하다는 사실을 밝혀냈다. VLMs에 대한 기존 backdoor attack은 주로 visual trigger를 추가하고 text label을 수정하는 data poisoning에 의존하며, 이로 인해 유도된 image–text mismatch는 poisoned sample을 쉽게 탐지할 수 있게 만든다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 diffusion models를 통해 Clean-Label Backdoor Attack on VLMs via Diffusion Models (CBV)를 제안한다. 이는 score matching을 활용해 자연스러운 poisoned example을 생성한다. 구체적으로, CBV는 diffusion model의 reverse generation process 동안 score를 수정하여 triggered image feature를 포함하는 poisoned sample 생성을 유도한다. 공격 효과를 더욱 높이기 위해, 생성 과정에서 triggered image의 text 정보를 multimodal guidance로 통합한다. 또한 stealthiness를 강화하기 위해, 우리는 GradCAM-guided Mask (GM)를 도입하여 전체 image가 아니라 의미적으로 가장 중요한 region에만 modification이 가해지도록 제한한다. 우리는 MSCOCO와 VQA v2에서 네 개의 대표적인 VLMs로 방법을 평가했으며, normal functionality를 유지하면서 80\\%가 넘는 ASR을 달성했다.</p>"},{"id":"60590","en":"ABC-Bench: An Agentic Bio-Capabilities Benchmark for Biosecurity","ko":"ABC-Bench: 바이오안보를 위한 에이전트형 생물 역량 벤치마크","authors":"Andrew Liu, Samira Nedungadi, Bryce Cai, Alex Kleinman, Harmon Bhasin, Seth Donoughe","pos":"#3000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yiaf7VlPpH","abs":"<p>For some time, LLMs have sped up life sciences research by synthesizing published literature, but now leading LLM-based tools can also perform certain \\textit{in silico} tasks that had previously been the domain of experienced biologists. These emerging AI capabilities offer new opportunities for scientific discovery and biomedical advances, but they are also changing the landscape of biosecurity risks. To address this, we introduce the Agentic Bio-Capabilities Benchmark (ABC-Bench), a suite of evaluations to measure \\textit{agentic} biosecurity-relevant capabilities. ABC-Bench evaluates LLM-based agents on both benign and potentially harmful biosecurity-relevant tasks: writing code to operate liquid handling robots, designing DNA fragments for \\textit{in vitro} assembly, and evading DNA synthesis screening. These tasks require a combination of biology and software expertise; indeed, when PhD biologists with at least two years of coding experience attempted the tasks in ABC-Bench, they scored only 24\\% on average. By contrast, the top-performing LLM, Grok 3, achieves 53\\% across tasks, outperforming 60\\%, 100\\%, and 54\\% of experts on the Liquid Handling Robot, Fragment Design, and Screening Evasion tasks, respectively. In three additional experiments, we found that OpenAI's GPT-4o-mini-high produced code that, when run on an OpenTrons robot, successfully assembled DNA with the expected sequences.</p>","absKo":"<p>한동안 LLM은 출판된 문헌을 종합함으로써 생명과학 연구를 가속해 왔지만, 이제 선도적인 LLM 기반 도구들은 숙련된 생물학자의 영역이었던 특정 <i>in silico</i> 작업도 수행할 수 있다. 이러한 새로운 AI 역량은 과학적 발견과 생의학적 진보를 위한 새로운 기회를 제공하지만, 동시에 biosecurity risk의 지형도 바꾸고 있다. 이에 대응하기 위해 우리는 agentic biosecurity 관련 역량을 측정하기 위한 평가 모음인 Agentic Bio-Capabilities Benchmark(ABC-Bench)를 소개한다. ABC-Bench는 LLM 기반 agent를 benign한 작업과 잠재적으로 유해한 biosecurity 관련 작업 모두에서 평가한다. 여기에는 liquid handling robot을 작동시키는 코드 작성, <i>in vitro</i> assembly를 위한 DNA fragment 설계, DNA synthesis screening 회피가 포함된다. 이러한 작업은 생물학과 software expertise의 결합을 요구한다. 실제로, 코딩 경험이 최소 2년 있는 박사급 생물학자들이 ABC-Bench의 작업을 시도했을 때 평균 점수는 24%에 불과했다. 반면 최고 성능 LLM인 Grok 3는 전체 작업에서 53%를 달성했으며, Liquid Handling Robot, Fragment Design, Screening Evasion 작업에서 각각 전문가의 60%, 100%, 54%를 능가했다. 추가로 수행한 세 가지 실험에서, 우리는 OpenAI의 GPT-4o-mini-high가 작성한 코드가 OpenTrons robot에서 실행되었을 때 기대한 sequence의 DNA를 성공적으로 조립함을 확인했다.</p>"},{"id":"62426","en":"Hide and Seek in Embedding Space: Geometry-based Steganography and Detection in Large Language Models","ko":"임베딩 공간의 숨바꼭질: Large Language Models에서 Geometry 기반 Steganography 및 탐지","authors":"Charles Westphal, Keivan Navaie, Fernando Rosas","pos":"#304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gjykWd56Js","abs":"Fine-tuned LLMs can covertly encode prompt secrets into outputs via steganographic channels. Prior work demonstrated this threat but relied on trivially recoverable encodings. We formalize payload recoverability via classifier accuracy and show previous schemes achieve 100\\% recoverability.  In response, we introduce low-recoverability steganography, replacing arbitrary mappings with embedding-space-derived ones. For Llama-8B (LoRA) and Ministral-8B (LoRA) trained on TrojanStego prompts, exact secret recovery rises from 17$\\rightarrow$30\\% (+78\\%) and 24$\\rightarrow$43\\% (+80\\%) respectively, while on Llama-70B (LoRA) trained on Wiki prompts, it climbs from 9$\\rightarrow$19\\% (+123\\%), all while reducing payload recoverability. We then discuss detection. We argue that detecting fine-tuning-based steganographic attacks requires approaches beyond traditional steganalysis. Standard approaches measure distributional shift, which is an expected side-effect of fine-tuning. Instead, we propose a mechanistic interpretability approach: linear probes trained on later-layer activations detect the secret with up to 33\\% higher accuracy in fine-tuned models compared to base models, even for low-recoverability schemes. This suggests that malicious fine-tuning leaves actionable internal signatures amenable to interpretability-based defenses.","absKo":"Fine-tuned LLM은 steganographic channel을 통해 prompt secret을 출력에 은밀하게 인코딩할 수 있다. 기존 연구는 이러한 위협을 보여 주었지만, 너무 쉽게 복원 가능한 encoding에 의존했다. 우리는 payload recoverability를 classifier accuracy로 정식화하고, 이전 scheme이 100\\% recoverability를 달성함을 보인다. 이에 대응하여, 우리는 임의의 mapping을 embedding-space-derived mapping으로 대체하는 low-recoverability steganography를 도입한다. TrojanStego prompt로 학습한 Llama-8B (LoRA)와 Ministral-8B (LoRA)에서 exact secret recovery는 각각 17$\\rightarrow$30\\% (+78\\%)와 24$\\rightarrow$43\\% (+80\\%)로 상승했으며, Wiki prompt로 학습한 Llama-70B (LoRA)에서는 9$\\rightarrow$19\\% (+123\\%)로 상승했고, 동시에 payload recoverability는 감소했다. 이어서 detection을 논의한다. 우리는 fine-tuning 기반 steganographic attack을 탐지하려면 전통적인 steganalysis를 넘어서는 접근이 필요하다고 주장한다. 표준 접근은 distributional shift를 측정하는데, 이는 fine-tuning의 예상되는 부작용이다. 대신 우리는 mechanistic interpretability 접근을 제안한다: later-layer activation으로 학습한 linear probe는 low-recoverability scheme에서도 base model과 비교하여 fine-tuned model에서 최대 33\\% 더 높은 accuracy로 secret을 탐지한다. 이는 악의적인 fine-tuning이 interpretability 기반 방어에 활용 가능한 내부 signature를 남긴다는 점을 시사한다."},{"id":"64210","en":"Towards Seed-Robust Safety Alignment in Text-to-Image Models","ko":"Text-to-Image 모델에서 시드 강건 안전성 정렬을 향하여","authors":"Zhenyu Wu, Yao Huang, Shouwei Ruan, Xingxing Wei","pos":"#3506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PwH2T3WI9o","abs":"<p>Text-to-image diffusion models have achieved remarkable success in generating high-quality images, yet existing safety mechanisms exhibit critical cross-seed instability where defense performance varies significantly under different random seed conditions. This instability stems from the fact that a single malicious prompt generates diverse harmful variants across different noise initializations, forming complex distributional clusters that current methods cannot adequately address. We investigate extending Noise Contrastive Alignment (NCA) to diffusion models due to its native capability of handling multiple negative samples through probabilistic weighting, but our theoretical analysis reveals two fundamental flaws in direct extension: gradient reversal caused by positive regularization terms that paradoxically penalize safe content generation, and uniform suppression of harmful samples that ignores severity variations. To tackle these issues, we propose Noise Contrastive Diffusion (NCD), which incorporates targeted algorithmic modifications including elimination of problematic regularization and introduction of pairwise regularization mechanisms that establish individualized preference relationships between safe and harmful variants. Extensive experiments further demonstrate that NCD achieves superior cross-seed stability, reducing attack success rates (ASRs) from 11.1% to 6.2% compared to SOTA methods at the seed level while maintaining exceptional generation quality, exhibiting robust resistance against sophisticated jailbreak prompts and strong generalizability across different T2I architectures. WARNING: This paper may contain examples of harmful texts and images.</p>","absKo":"<p>텍스트-투-이미지 diffusion models는 고품질 이미지를 생성하는 데에서 놀라운 성과를 거두었지만, 기존 안전 메커니즘은 defense 성능이 서로 다른 random seed 조건에서 크게 달라지는 치명적인 cross-seed 불안정성을 보인다. 이러한 불안정성은 하나의 악의적 prompt가 서로 다른 noise initialization에서 다양한 유해 변형을 생성하여, 현재 방법들이 충분히 다루지 못하는 복잡한 분포적 cluster를 형성하기 때문에 발생한다. 우리는 확률적 가중치를 통해 multiple negative samples를 처리하는 native capability 때문에 Noise Contrastive Alignment (NCA)를 diffusion models로 확장하는 방안을 조사하지만, 이론적 분석 결과 직접 확장에는 두 가지 근본적 결함이 있음을 밝힌다. 하나는 positive regularization terms로 인해 발생하는 gradient reversal로, 역설적으로 안전한 content 생성을 벌하는 문제이며, 다른 하나는 심각도 차이를 무시한 채 harmful samples를 균일하게 억제하는 문제이다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 문제를 일으키는 regularization을 제거하고 safe 및 harmful variant 사이에 개별화된 preference 관계를 설정하는 pairwise regularization mechanism을 도입한 Noise Contrastive Diffusion (NCD)를 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 NCD가 뛰어난 generation quality를 유지하면서도 우수한 cross-seed stability를 달성함을 추가로 보여주며, seed 수준에서 SOTA 방법들에 비해 attack success rate (ASR)를 11.1%에서 6.2%로 낮추고, 정교한 jailbreak prompt에 대한 강한 저항성과 다양한 T2I architecture 전반에 걸친 높은 generalizability를 보인다. WARNING: 이 논문에는 유해한 텍스트와 이미지의 예시가 포함될 수 있습니다.</p>"},{"id":"64792","en":"Architecture Matters for Multi-Agent Security","ko":"Multi-Agent 보안에서 아키텍처가 중요하다","authors":"Ben Hagag, William Anderson, Christian Schroeder de Witt, Sarah Scheffler","pos":"#3511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Jk4zLorDUx","abs":"<p>Multi-agent systems (MAS), composed of networks of two or more autonomous AI agents, have become increasingly popular in production deployments, yet introduce security risks that do not arise in single-agent settings. Even if individual agents may exhibit robust security, architectural decisions governing their coordination can create attack surfaces that have not been systematically characterized. In this work, we present an empirical study of how MAS design decisions shape the tradeoff between task performance and attack resistance. Using a network of web-based agents and stage-wise evaluations that distinguish planning-stage refusal, execution-stage interception, and successful attack completion, we study architectural choices through controlled experiments. We identify three key design choices that influence MAS security: (i) agent roles, which determine how authority and responsibility are allocated; (ii) topology, which shapes how and when agents interact; and (iii) memory, which determines the context and state visibility accessible to each agent. Overall, our results show that security and performance in multi-agent systems are governed by architectural design choices, motivating the development of further evaluations which move beyond the security properties of a single agent.</p>","absKo":"<p>두 개 이상의 자율 AI agent로 구성된 network인 multi-agent systems (MAS)은 생산 환경에 점점 더 많이 배치되고 있지만, single-agent setting에서는 나타나지 않는 보안 위험을 도입한다. 개별 agent가 강한 보안을 보이더라도, 이들의 coordination을 규정하는 architectural decision이 체계적으로 특성화되지 않은 attack surface를 만들어낼 수 있다. 본 연구에서는 MAS 설계 결정이 task performance와 attack resistance 사이의 tradeoff를 어떻게 형성하는지에 대한 실증 연구를 प्रस्तुत한다. 웹 기반 agent network와 planning-stage refusal, execution-stage interception, successful attack completion을 구분하는 stage-wise evaluation을 사용하여, 통제된 실험을 통해 architectural choice를 분석한다. 우리는 MAS 보안에 영향을 미치는 세 가지 핵심 설계 요소를 식별한다. (i) agent roles는 authority와 responsibility가 어떻게 배분되는지를 결정하고, (ii) topology는 agent가 어떻게 그리고 언제 상호작용하는지를 형성하며, (iii) memory는 각 agent가 접근할 수 있는 context와 state visibility를 결정한다. 전반적으로 우리의 결과는 multi-agent system에서의 보안과 성능이 architectural design choice에 의해 좌우됨을 보여 주며, 단일 agent의 보안 속성을 넘어서는 추가적인 evaluation의 개발을 촉진한다.</p>"},{"id":"66452","en":"Extracting alignment data in open models","ko":"오픈 모델에서 정렬 데이터 추출","authors":"Federico Barbero, Xiangming Gu, Christopher A. Choquette Choo, Chawin Sitawarin, Matthew Jagielski, Itay Yona, Petar Veličković, Ilia Shumailov, Jamie Hayes","pos":"#3702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3XXb2MK02l","abs":"In this work, we show that it is possible to extract significant amounts of alignment training data from a post-trained model -- useful to steer the model to improve certain capabilities such as long-context reasoning, safety, instruction following, and maths.  While the majority of related work on memorisation has focused on measuring success of training data extraction through string matching, we argue that embedding models are better suited for our specific goals.  Distances measured through a high quality embedding model can identify semantic similarities between strings that a different metric such as edit distance will struggle to capture.  In fact, in our investigation, approximate string matching would have severely undercounted (by a conservative estimate of $10\\times$) the amount of data that can be extracted due to trivial artifacts that deflate the metric. Interestingly, we find that models readily regurgitate training data that was used in post-training phases such as SFT or RL. We show that this data can be then used to train a base model, recovering a meaningful amount of the original performance.  We believe our work exposes a possibly overlooked risk towards extracting alignment data. Finally, our work opens up an interesting discussion on the downstream effects of distillation practices: since models seem to be regurgitating aspects of their training set, distillation can therefore be thought of as indirectly training on the model's original dataset."},{"id":"63777","en":"Localize and Neutralize: Gradient-Guided Token Suppression Against Visual Prompt Injection Attack","ko":"시각 프롬프트 인젝션 공격에 대한 그래디언트 유도 토큰 억제","authors":"Dongpeng Zhang, Ke Ma, Yangbangyan Jiang, Gaozheng Pei, Longtao Huang, Qianqian Xu, Qingming Huang","pos":"#407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TrZGbLwVg5","abs":"<p>Adversarial images pose a severe security threat to multimodal large language models through prompt injection. Existing defenses largely lack a principled understanding of the underlying mechanisms and struggle to balance efficiency and fidelity. In this work, we show that successful adversarial attacks do not rely on the entire image uniformly but instead depend on a small subset of critical image tokens. Based on this insight, we propose a defense that first localizes these critical tokens via gradient analysis and then neutralizes them through masking. We show that attribution based on output probabilities fails when adversarial attacks preserve the predicted token. To overcome this limitation, we introduce the Hidden-State Gradient Norm score for adversarial behavior attribution and prove that its ranking is consistent with that of the full adversarial loss gradient, providing a theoretical guarantee for accurate localization. GTM requires only a single forward–backward pass to identify and zero out a small number of high-scoring tokens, effectively disrupting the adversarial attack path. Extensive experiments on prompt injection and multimodal jailbreak attacks demonstrate that our approach reduces attack success rates (ASR) to near zero while preserving model utility with negligible computational overhead.</p>","absKo":"Adversarial image는 prompt injection을 통해 multimodal large language model에 심각한 보안 위협을 초래한다. 기존 방어 기법은 근본 메커니즘에 대한 원리 있는 이해가 부족하고, 효율성과 fidelity 사이의 균형을 맞추는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 본 연구에서는 성공적인 adversarial attack이 이미지 전체에 균일하게 의존하는 것이 아니라, 소수의 중요한 image token에 의존한다는 점을 보인다. 이 통찰에 기반하여 우리는 먼저 gradient analysis를 통해 이러한 핵심 token을 localize한 뒤 masking으로 무력화하는 방어 기법을 제안한다. 우리는 output probability에 기반한 attribution은 adversarial attack이 예측된 token을 유지할 때 실패함을 보인다. 이 한계를 극복하기 위해, adversarial behavior attribution을 위한 Hidden-State Gradient Norm score를 도입하고, 이것이 full adversarial loss gradient의 ranking과 일치함을 증명하여 정확한 localization에 대한 이론적 보장을 제공한다. GTM은 단 한 번의 forward-backward pass만으로 score가 높은 소수의 token을 식별하고 0으로 만들어 adversarial attack path를 효과적으로 교란한다. prompt injection과 multimodal jailbreak attack에 대한 광범위한 실험은, 우리의 방법이 계산 오버헤드는 미미하게 유지하면서 attack success rate(ASR)를 거의 0에 가깝게 낮추고 model utility는 보존함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"67194","en":"Position: Agent Security Needs Redefinition through a Holistic Framework","ko":"Position: Agent 보안은 전체론적 프레임워크를 통해 재정의될 필요가 있다","authors":"Vincent Siu, Jingxuan He, Kyle Montgomery, Zhun Wang, Chenguang Wang, Dawn Song","pos":"#4607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HMQmLtcfme","abs":"<p>Existing definitions of agent security are ambiguous because they do not fully capture the holistic view across agent components. For instance, current work fails to distinguish between potentially legitimate administrative tasks and malicious exploitation of the same command. A command to \"delete user data\" could be either instruction following to reset a sandbox or a prompt injection attacking production systems. We argue that agent security must be redefined through a holistic framework including four core components: identity (who: authority and authentication), task (what to do: authorized objectives), trajectory (progress: action-observation boundaries), and memory (what can be retrieved: information access control).  Our framework redefines existing security violations (e.g., reframing prompt injection as an identity violation), enables discovery of new attack vectors, and distinguishes legitimate capabilities like instruction following from security violations like prompt injection attacks. Critically, we demonstrate that temporal aspects are essential: attacks can be misdefined or unnoticed without accounting for how security components in our framework evolve over time. Our framework further identifies that agentic task decomposition and data and control flow patterns are crucial to rigorous security definitions, aspects previous frameworks fail to address, and provides a new foundation for future agent security work.</p>"},{"id":"64767","en":"Token Sample Complexity of Attention","ko":"Attention의 Token Sample Complexity","authors":"Léa Bohbot, Cyril Letrouit, Gabriel Peyré, François-Xavier Vialard","pos":"#1202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=K5blb595KX","abs":"As context windows in large language models continue to expand, it is essential to characterize how attention behaves at extreme sequence lengths. We introduce token-sample complexity: the rate at which attention computed on $n$ tokens converges to its infinite-token limit. We estimate finite-$n$ convergence bounds at two levels: pointwise uniform convergence of the attention map, and convergence of moments for the transformed token distribution.      For compactly supported (and more generally sub-Gaussian) distributions, our first result shows that the attention map converges uniformly on a ball of radius $R$ at rate $C(R)/\\sqrt{n}$, where $C(R)$ grows exponentially with $R$. For large $R$, this estimate loses practical value, and our second result addresses this issue by establishing convergence rates for the moments of the transformed distribution (the token output of the attention layer). In this case, the rate is $C'(R)/n^{\\beta}$ with $\\beta&lt;\\tfrac{1}{2}$, and $C'(R)$ depends polynomially on the size of the support of the distribution. The exponent $\\beta$ depends on the attention geometry and the spectral properties of the tokens distribution. We also examine the regime in which the attention parameter tends to infinity and the softmax approaches a hardmax, and in this setting, we establish a logarithmic rate of convergence. Experiments on synthetic Gaussian data and real BERT models on Wikipedia text confirm our predictions.","absKo":"large language model의 context window가 계속 확장됨에 따라, attention이 극단적으로 긴 sequence length에서 어떻게 동작하는지 특성화하는 일이 중요해지고 있다. 우리는 token-sample complexity를 도입하는데, 이는 $n$개의 token에 대해 계산된 attention이 infinite-token limit로 수렴하는 속도이다. 우리는 finite-$n$ 수렴 bound를 두 수준에서 추정한다. 하나는 attention map의 pointwise uniform convergence이고, 다른 하나는 transformed token distribution의 moment 수렴이다.      compactly supported distribution(더 일반적으로는 sub-Gaussian distribution)의 경우, 첫 번째 결과는 반지름 $R$의 ball 위에서 attention map이 $C(R)/\\sqrt{n}$의 속도로 uniformly converge함을 보인다. 여기서 $C(R)$은 $R$에 따라 지수적으로 증가한다. 큰 $R$에서는 이 추정이 실용적 가치를 잃는데, 두 번째 결과는 transformed distribution( attention layer의 token output )의 moment에 대한 수렴 rate를 확립함으로써 이 문제를 다룬다. 이 경우 속도는 $C'(R)/n^{\\beta}$이며 $\\beta&lt;\\tfrac{1}{2}$이고, $C'(R)$는 distribution support 크기에 대해 다항적으로 의존한다. 지수 $\beta$는 attention geometry와 token distribution의 spectral property에 따라 달라진다. 또한 attention parameter가 무한대로 가고 softmax가 hardmax에 가까워지는 regime도 검토하며, 이 설정에서는 로그 수렴율을 확립한다. synthetic Gaussian data와 Wikipedia text 위의 실제 BERT model 실험은 우리의 예측을 확인해 준다."},{"id":"63405","en":"Symmetries in language statistics shape the geometry of model representations","ko":"언어 통계의 대칭성이 모델 표현의 기하를 형성한다","authors":"Dhruva Karkada, Daniel Korchinski, Andres Nava, Matthieu Wyart, Yasaman Bahri","pos":"#1303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XQeMPEkfdd","abs":"<p>Although learned representations underlie neural networks' success, their fundamental properties remain poorly understood. A striking example is the emergence of simple geometric structures in LLM representations: for example, calendar months organize into a circle, years form a one-dimensional manifold, and the latitude and longitude of cities can be decoded by low-dimensional linear probes. We show that the statistics of language exhibit a translation symmetry---e.g,. the co-occurrence probability of two months depends only on the time interval between them---and we prove that the latter governs the aforementioned geometric structures in high-dimensional word embedding models. Moreover, we find that these structures persist even when the co-occurrence statistics are strongly perturbed (for example, by removing all sentences in which two months appear together) and at moderate embedding dimension. We show that this robustness naturally emerges if the co-occurrence statistics are collectively controlled by an underlying continuous latent variable. We empirically validate this theoretical framework in word embedding models, text embedding models, and large language models.</p>","absKo":"<p>학습된 representation이 neural network의 성공을 떠받치고 있음에도, 그 근본적 성질은 여전히 충분히 이해되지 않았다. LLM representation에서 단순한 기하학적 구조가 나타나는 현상은 특히 인상적이다. 예를 들어 달(month)은 원형으로 배열되고, 연도(year)는 일차원 다양체를 이루며, 도시의 위도와 경도는 낮은 차원의 linear probe로 복원될 수 있다. 우리는 언어의 통계가 translation symmetry를 따른다는 점, 예를 들어 두 달이 함께 등장할 확률은 둘 사이의 시간 간격에만 의존한다는 점을 보이고, 이러한 성질이 고차원 word embedding model에서 앞서 언급한 기하학적 구조를 지배한다는 것을 증명한다. 더 나아가 이러한 구조는 co-occurrence 통계가 강하게 perturbation되더라도(예를 들어 두 달이 함께 나타나는 모든 문장을 제거하더라도) 그리고 중간 정도의 embedding dimension에서도 지속됨을 발견한다. 우리는 이러한 robust한 거동이 co-occurrence 통계가 어떤 underlying continuous latent variable에 의해 집합적으로 제어될 때 자연스럽게 나타남을 보인다. 우리는 word embedding model, text embedding model, 그리고 large language model에서 이 이론적 프레임워크를 실증적으로 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64750","en":"Multimodal Fusion via Self-Consistent Task-Gradient Fields","ko":"Self-Consistent Task-Gradient Field를 통한 멀티모달 Fusion","authors":"Jiayu Xiong, Jing Wang, Jun Xue, Wanlong Wang, Jianlong Kwan, Xiaosen Lyu, Zhouqiang Jiang","pos":"#1310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KDJf0EyawI","abs":"<p>Multimodal learning aims to preserve as much task-related information as possible from different inputs. However, current fusion designs often distort the feedback loop to feature extractors. Aggressively merging modalities entangles their representations, making the feature extractors fragile to incomplete inputs. Meanwhile, attempting to separate features via auxiliary losses frequently introduces optimization conflicts that distract from the primary task. We propose the Self-Consistent Field Autoencoder (SCFAE) to provide a better path for task gradients. Our method follows the self-consistent field principle to balance task learning with feature organization, thereby minimizing mutual information. We use small autoencoders for each modality to keep information intact. The task loss acts as a driving force to select predictive features. The reconstruction loss acts as a constraint to separate these features into independent subspaces. These dual objectives operate through complementary feature subspaces, thereby mitigating optimization interference. We evaluate SCFAE on audio-visual-text, audio-visual, and image-video benchmarks. Results show that SCFAE handles missing data and unequal input sizes more robustly via a simple structure. Gradient analysis confirms that SCFAE avoids conflicts and maintains stable training dynamics.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal learning의 목표는 서로 다른 입력으로부터 task와 관련된 정보를 가능한 한 많이 보존하는 것이다. 그러나 현재의 fusion design은 종종 feature extractor로 향하는 feedback loop를 왜곡한다. modality를 공격적으로 합치면 그 표현이 얽혀 버려 feature extractor가 불완전한 입력에 취약해진다. 한편 auxiliary loss를 통해 feature를 분리하려는 시도는 종종 optimization conflict를 유발하여 주된 task에서 주의를 분산시킨다. 우리는 task gradient가 더 나은 경로를 따르도록 Self-Consistent Field Autoencoder (SCFAE)를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 self-consistent field 원리를 따라 task learning과 feature organization 사이의 균형을 맞추며, 이를 통해 mutual information을 최소화한다. 각 modality마다 작은 autoencoder를 사용해 정보를 온전히 유지한다. task loss는 predictive feature를 선택하는 구동력으로 작용한다. reconstruction loss는 이러한 feature를 독립적인 subspace로 분리하는 제약으로 작용한다. 이 두 목적은 상호 보완적인 feature subspace를 통해 작동하므로 optimization interference를 완화한다. 우리는 audio-visual-text, audio-visual, image-video benchmark에서 SCFAE를 평가한다. 결과는 SCFAE가 단순한 구조로 missing data와 unequal input size를 더 강인하게 처리함을 보여 준다. gradient analysis는 SCFAE가 conflict를 피하고 안정적인 training dynamics를 유지함을 확인한다."},{"id":"64045","en":"A Fourier perspective on the learning dynamics of neural networks: from sample complexities to mechanistic insights","ko":"신경망 학습 동역학에 대한 푸리에 관점: 샘플 복잡도에서 기전 통찰까지","authors":"Fabiola Ricci, Claudia Merger, Sebastian Goldt","pos":"#1400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RQECNEUcbJ","abs":"Neural networks trained with gradient-based methods exhibit a strong simplicity bias, learning simpler statistical features of their data before moving to more complex features. In this work, we study this bias from a Fourier perspective, motivated by the approximate translation-invariance and the characteristic power spectra of natural images. We first show experimentally that simple neural networks trained on image classification tasks first rely on amplitude information -- related to pair-wise correlations between pixels -- before exploiting phase information, which encodes edges and higher-order correlations. To explain this phenomenon, we introduce a synthetic data model for translation-invariant inputs that allows precise control over the amplitudes and phases while remaining tractable. We rigorously establish that for isotropic and high-dimensional inputs, classifying them by relying only phase information is a genuinely hard task: online stochastic gradient descent cannot distinguish the structured inputs from noise within $n \\ll N^3$ steps, but needs at least $n \\gg N^3 \\log^2{N}$ steps. In contrast, we prove that for non-isotropic inputs with power-law spectra, the existence of a dominant principal subspace can dramatically accelerate the speed of learning, even if the Fourier amplitudes are shared among classes and do not help with classification. Simulations with two-layer networks trained on textures, and with deep convolutional networks on ImageNet confirm this non-trivial interaction between amplitudes and phases, providing mechanistic insight into how deep neural networks can learn natural image distributions efficiently.","absKo":"Gradient-based method로 학습된 neural network는 강한 simplicity bias를 보이며, 데이터의 더 복잡한 feature로 이동하기 전에 더 단순한 statistical feature를 먼저 학습한다. 본 연구에서는 자연 이미지의 근사적인 translation-invariance와 특유의 power spectrum에 동기를 두고, 이 bias를 Fourier 관점에서 분석한다. 먼저, image classification task로 학습된 간단한 neural network가 edge와 higher-order correlation을 인코딩하는 phase information을 활용하기 전에, pixel 간 pair-wise correlation과 관련된 amplitude information에 먼저 의존함을 실험적으로 보인다. 이 현상을 설명하기 위해, amplitude와 phase를 정밀하게 제어할 수 있으면서도 tractable한 translation-invariant input에 대한 synthetic data model을 도입한다. 우리는 isotropic하고 고차원적인 input에 대해서는, phase information만을 이용해 분류하는 것이 본질적으로 어려운 task임을 엄밀히 확립한다. 즉, online stochastic gradient descent는 $n \\ll N^3$ step 내에서는 구조화된 input과 noise를 구별할 수 없고, 최소한 $n \\gg N^3 \\log^2{N}$ step이 필요하다. 반대로, power-law spectrum을 갖는 non-isotropic input에서는 지배적인 principal subspace의 존재가 Fourier amplitude가 클래스 간에 공유되어 분류에 도움이 되지 않더라도 학습 속도를 극적으로 가속할 수 있음을 증명한다. texture에서 학습된 two-layer network와 ImageNet에서 학습된 deep convolutional network의 시뮬레이션은 amplitude와 phase 사이의 이러한 비자명한 상호작용을 확인해 주며, deep neural network가 자연 이미지 분포를 어떻게 효율적으로 학습하는지에 대한 기계적 통찰을 제공한다."},{"id":"66301","en":"Balancing Learning Rates Across Layers: Exact Two-Step Dynamics and Optimal Scaling in Linear Neural Networks","ko":"계층 간 학습률 균형화: 선형 신경망에서의 정확한 2단계 동역학과 최적 스케일링","authors":"Tianyu Pang, Vignesh Kothapalli, Shenyang Deng, Haohui Wang, Dawei Zhou, Yaoqing Yang","pos":"#1402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4vztmTrGhd","abs":"<p>We study optimal learning-rate selection in two-layer and three-layer linear neural networks trained to learn a single-index target function. In particular, we derive the exact closed-form expressions for the gradients and test loss after one and two steps of gradient descent, enabling a precise characterization of early training dynamics. We characterize how learning rates should scale under the gradient approximation in the first two steps, and prove that performing updates with this approximation yields a tractable surrogate loss with a tight, small approximation error. This formulation enables the theoretical analysis of layer-wise learning rates and reveals a distinct early-training regime: test loss can be minimized by unequal learning rates at the initial step, while equal learning rates become optimal in subsequent steps. Our numerical experiments validate these theoretical predictions and demonstrate the importance of balancing layer-wise learning-rate  during early training.</p>"},{"id":"65863","en":"Data Reconstruction: Identifiability and Optimization with Sample Splitting","ko":"데이터 재구성: 표본 분할을 통한 식별 가능성과 최적화","authors":"Yujie Shen, Zihan Wang, Jian Qian, Qi Lei","pos":"#1403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9LoNh2EZ2g","abs":"<p>Training data reconstruction from KKT conditions has shown striking empirical success, yet it remains unclear when the resulting KKT equations have unique solutions and, even in identifiable regimes, how to reliably recover solutions by optimization. This work hereby focuses on these two complementary questions: identifiability and optimization. On the identifiability side, we discuss the sufficient conditions for KKT system of two-layer networks with polynomial activations to uniquely determine the training data, providing a theoretical explanation of when and why reconstruction is possible. On the optimization side, we introduce sample splitting, a curvature-aware refinement step applicable to general reconstruction objectives (not limited to KKT-based formulations): it creates additional descent directions to escape poor stationary points and refine solutions. Experiments demonstrate that augmenting several existing reconstruction methods with sample splitting consistently improves reconstruction performance.</p>"},{"id":"63606","en":"Deriving Neural Scaling Laws from the Statistics of Natural Language","ko":"자연어 통계로부터 신경 스케일링 법칙 유도","authors":"Francesco Cagnetta, Allan Raventos, Surya Ganguli, Matthieu Wyart","pos":"#1404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VXlniX0C5y","abs":"<p>Despite the fact that experimental neural scaling laws have substantially guided empirical progress in large-scale machine learning, no existing theory can quantitatively predict the exponents of these important laws for any modern LLM trained on any natural language dataset. We provide the first such theory in the case of data-limited scaling laws. We isolate two key statistical properties of language that {\\it alone} can predict neural scaling exponents: (i) the decay of pairwise token correlations with time separation between token pairs, and (ii) the decay of the next-token conditional entropy with the length of the conditioning context. We further derive a simple formula in terms of these statistics that predicts data-limited neural scaling exponents from first principles {\\it without any} free parameters or synthetic data models. Our theory exhibits a remarkable match with experimentally measured neural scaling laws obtained from training GPT-2 and LLaMA style models from scratch on two qualitatively different benchmarks, TinyStories and WikiText.</p>","absKo":"<p>실험적 neural scaling law가 대규모 machine learning의 경험적 진전을 크게 이끌어 왔음에도 불구하고, 현재까지 어떤 자연어 데이터셋으로 학습된 현대적 LLM에 대해서도 이러한 중요한 법칙의 지수(exponent)를 정량적으로 예측할 수 있는 이론은 존재하지 않는다. 우리는 데이터가 제한된 scaling law의 경우에 대해 그러한 최초의 이론을 제시한다. 우리는 language의 두 가지 핵심 통계적 성질을 분리해내며, 이 성질들만으로 neural scaling exponent를 예측할 수 있음을 보인다: (i) token 쌍 사이의 시간적 분리(time separation)에 따른 pairwise token correlation의 감쇠, 그리고 (ii) conditioning context 길이에 따른 next-token conditional entropy의 감쇠. 또한 우리는 이러한 통계량으로부터, 어떤 free parameter나 synthetic data model도 없이 first principles에서 데이터 제한형 neural scaling exponent를 예측하는 간단한 공식을 유도한다. 우리의 이론은 TinyStories와 WikiText라는 질적으로 서로 다른 두 benchmark에서 GPT-2 및 LLaMA 스타일 모델을 scratch부터 학습해 얻은 실험적 neural scaling law와 놀라울 정도로 잘 일치함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65205","en":"Dropout Universality: Scaling Laws and Optimal Scheduling at the Edge-of-Chaos","ko":"Dropout 보편성: Edge-of-Chaos에서의 스케일링 법칙과 최적 스케줄링","authors":"Lucas Fernandez-Sarmiento","pos":"#1405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FoDU47u2jk","abs":"<p>We develop a mean-field theory of dropout as a perturbation of critical signal propagation at the edge of chaos. Dropout shifts the perfect-alignment fixed point, making the depth scale for information propagation finite even at critical initialization. We derive critical and crossover scaling laws for correlation decay and establish that smooth activations and kinked (ReLU-type) activations constitute distinct universality classes, with different critical exponents and a universal two-parameter scaling collapse in detuning and dropout strength. The distinction traces to the analytic structure of the correlation map: smooth activations admit a Taylor expansion near perfect alignment, while kinked activations develop a branch point with universal non-analyticity. As a corollary, the framework yields principled dropout schedules that maximize effective correlation length under fixed budget. We validate the theoretical predictions in MLPs and Vision Transformers, where the predicted schedules outperform constant dropout, illustrating the practical utility of the mean-field approach.</p>","absKo":"dropout을 chaos의 가장자리(edge of chaos)에서의 critical signal propagation의 perturbation으로 보는 mean-field theory를 전개한다. dropout은 perfect-alignment fixed point를 이동시켜, critical initialization에서도 information propagation의 depth scale을 유한하게 만든다. 우리는 correlation decay에 대한 critical 및 crossover scaling law를 유도하고, smooth activation과 kinked(ReLU-type) activation이 서로 다른 universality class를 이룬다는 점을 보인다. 이들은 서로 다른 critical exponent와 detuning 및 dropout strength에 대한 universal two-parameter scaling collapse를 가진다. 이러한 구분은 correlation map의 analytic structure에서 비롯된다. smooth activation은 perfect alignment 근처에서 Taylor expansion을 허용하는 반면, kinked activation은 universal non-analyticity를 갖는 branch point를 형성한다. 그 결과로, 이 framework는 고정된 budget 하에서 effective correlation length를 최대화하는 principled dropout schedule을 제공한다. 우리는 MLP와 Vision Transformer에서 이론적 예측을 검증했으며, 예측된 schedule이 constant dropout보다 우수함을 보였다. 이는 mean-field approach의 실용적 유용성을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65550","en":"Gradient Descent with Large Step Size Restores Symmetry in Deep Linear Networks with Multi-Pathway","ko":"큰 스텝 크기를 갖는 Gradient Descent가 Multi-Pathway 심층 선형 네트워크에서 대칭을 복원한다","authors":"Hee-Sung Kim, Sungyoon Lee","pos":"#1413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CVXqBkLF5y","abs":"<p>Recent theoretical analyses of multi-pathway Deep Linear Networks, typically grounded in Gradient Flow, predict a \"winner-takes-all\" specialization in which path symmetry breaks and each feature concentrates in a single pathway. In this work, we show that discrete Gradient Descent with a large step size reproduces the initial, depth-driven symmetry breaking but ultimately overrides this tendency due to its catapults at the Edge of Stability. In this regime, GD exhibits an implicit preference for low-curvature minima. Since we prove that splitting singular values across pathways minimizes sharpness, large-step GD—driven by its implicit preference for such flat minima—forces a subsequent re-balancing phase: iterates escape sharp, sparse configurations for stable, balanced solutions. Together, these results clarify how architectural depth shapes pathway competition while explaining why GD with large step size ultimately favors shared representations rather than permanent pathway monopolization.</p>"},{"id":"61456","en":"LLM Priors for ERM over Programs","ko":"프로그램에 대한 ERM을 위한 LLM Priors","authors":"Shivam Singhal, Priyadarsi Mishra, Eran Malach, Tomer Galanti","pos":"#201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pwSWrsBlsz","abs":"<p>We study program-learning methods that are efficient in both samples and computation. Classical learning theory suggests that when the target admits a short program description (for example, a short piece of ``Python code''), it can be learned from relatively few examples by performing ERM over the program class. However, this approach relies on enumerating candidate programs, which is typically exponential in the description length. In contrast, gradient-based training avoids explicit search, but for some families of short programs it can require exponentially many samples to succeed.   We propose \\textsc{LLM-PV}, a propose-and-verify recipe that enables ERM-style selection over a discrete program class without exhaustive enumeration. A pretrained LLM induces a proposal distribution over candidate programs; each proposal is executed, scored on a held-out validation set, and the best program is selected. The method uses no gradient updates and does not use validation feedback to adapt the sampling distribution.   Across algorithmic tasks including parity variants, pattern matching, and primality testing, \\textsc{LLM-PV} often recovers the exact underlying rule from a small labeled set and generalizes far beyond the training sequence lengths. In the same regimes, SGD-trained transformers and standard adaptation baselines (fine-tuning and in-context learning), as well as classical ML baselines, can fit the training data yet fail to generalize reliably. Together, these results suggest that pretrained LLM priors can serve as effective search biases for ERM, narrowing the gap between statistical and computational efficiency.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 샘플 효율성과 계산 효율성 모두에서 효율적인 program-learning 방법을 연구한다. 고전적 learning theory는 target이 짧은 program description(예: 짧은 ``Python code'')을 허용할 때, program class에 대해 ERM을 수행함으로써 비교적 적은 예시로 학습할 수 있음을 시사한다. 그러나 이 접근은 후보 program을 열거해야 하므로, 일반적으로 description length에 대해 지수적 비용이 든다. 반면 gradient-based training은 명시적 search를 피하지만, 일부 짧은 program family에서는 성공하기 위해 지수적으로 많은 sample이 필요할 수 있다. 우리는 완전 열거 없이 discrete program class 위에서 ERM-style selection을 가능하게 하는 propose-and-verify recipe인 \\textsc{LLM-PV}를 제안한다. pretrained LLM이 후보 program에 대한 proposal distribution을 유도하면, 각 proposal을 실행하고 보류된 validation set에서 점수를 매긴 뒤, 가장 좋은 program을 선택한다. 이 방법은 gradient update를 사용하지 않으며, validation feedback으로 sampling distribution을 적응시키지도 않는다. parity 변형, pattern matching, primality testing을 포함한 algorithmic task 전반에서 \\textsc{LLM-PV}는 종종 소규모 labeled set으로부터 정확한 underlying rule을 복원하고, training sequence length를 훨씬 넘어 일반화한다. 같은 영역에서 SGD로 학습한 transformer와 standard adaptation baseline(fine-tuning 및 in-context learning), 그리고 classical ML baseline은 training data에는 맞출 수 있지만 신뢰할 만하게 일반화하지 못한다. 이 결과들은 pretrained LLM prior가 ERM을 위한 효과적인 search bias로 작용하여, statistical efficiency와 computational efficiency 사이의 간극을 좁힐 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"60694","en":"Delving into Muon and Beyond: Deep Analysis and Extensions","ko":"Muon과 그 너머 파헤치기: 심층 분석과 확장","authors":"Xianbiao Qi, Marco Chen, Jiaquan Ye, Yelin He, Rong Xiao","pos":"#2601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xUQ0Gw11NL","abs":"<p>The Muon optimizer has recently attracted considerable attention for its strong empirical performance and use of orthogonalized updates on matrix-shaped parameters, yet its underlying mechanisms and relationship to adaptive optimizers such as Adam remain insufficiently understood. In this work, we aim to address these questions through a unified spectral perspective. Specifically, we view Muon as the ( p = 0 ) endpoint of a family of spectral transformations of the form ( \\boldsymbol{U} \\boldsymbol{\\Sigma}^{p} \\boldsymbol{V}^{\\top} ), and consider additional variants with ( p = \\frac{1}{2} ), ( p = \\frac{1}{4} ), and ( p = 1 ). These transformations are applied to both first-moment updates, as in momentum SGD, and to root-mean-square (RMS) normalized gradient updates as in Adam. To enable efficient computation, we develop a coupled Newton iteration that avoids explicit singular value decomposition. Across controlled experiments, we find that RMS-normalized updates yield more stable optimization than first-moment updates. Moreover, while spectral compression provides strong stabilization benefits under first-moment updates, the Muon update (( p = 0 )) does not consistently outperform Adam. These results suggest that Muon is best understood as an effective form of spectral normalization, but not a universally superior optimization method.</p>","absKo":"<p>Muon optimizer는 matrix-shaped parameter에 대한 orthogonalized update 사용과 강한 실증 성능으로 최근 큰 주목을 받았지만, 그 underlying mechanism과 Adam 같은 adaptive optimizer와의 관계는 아직 충분히 이해되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 통합된 spectral perspective를 통해 이러한 질문에 답하고자 한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 Muon을 ( p = 0 )인 spectral transformation family \\( \\boldsymbol{U} \\boldsymbol{\\Sigma}^{p} \\boldsymbol{V}^{\\top} \\)의 끝점으로 보고, ( p = \\frac{1}{2} ), ( p = \\frac{1}{4} ), ( p = 1 )을 갖는 추가 variant도 고려한다. 이러한 변환은 momentum SGD에서와 같은 first-moment update와 Adam에서와 같은 root-mean-square (RMS) normalized gradient update 모두에 적용된다. 효율적인 계산을 위해, 우리는 explicit singular value decomposition을 피하는 coupled Newton iteration을 개발한다. 통제된 실험 전반에서, RMS-normalized update가 first-moment update보다 더 안정적인 optimization을 제공함을 발견했다. 또한 spectral compression은 first-moment update 하에서 강한 stabilization 이점을 제공하지만, Muon update(( p = 0 ))가 Adam을 일관되게 능가하지는 않는다. 이러한 결과는 Muon을 효과적인 spectral normalization의 한 형태로 이해하는 것이 가장 적절하지만, 보편적으로 더 우수한 optimization method로 보기는 어렵다는 점을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61319","en":"Perceptrons and Localization of Attention’s Mean-Field Landscape","ko":"Perceptron과 Attention 평균장 지형의 국소화","authors":"Antonio Álvarez López, Borjan Geshkovski, Domènec Ruiz-Balet","pos":"#2705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rO2yyZiy4v","abs":"<p>The forward pass of a Transformer can be seen as an interacting particle system on the unit sphere: time plays the role of layers, particles that of token embeddings, and the unit sphere idealizes layer normalization. In some weight settings the system can even be seen as a gradient flow for an explicit energy, and one can  make sense of the infinite context length (\\emph{mean-field}) limit thanks to Wasserstein gradient flows. In this paper we study the effect of the perceptron block in this setting, and show that critical points are generically atomic and localized on subsets of the sphere.</p>","absKo":"<p>Transformer의 forward pass는 unit sphere 위에서 상호작용하는 particle system으로 볼 수 있다. 시간은 layer의 역할을 하고, particle은 token embedding의 역할을 하며, unit sphere는 layer normalization을 이상화한다. 일부 weight 설정에서는 이 시스템을 명시적 energy에 대한 gradient flow로 볼 수도 있으며, Wasserstein gradient flow 덕분에 infinite context length(\\emph{mean-field}) limit를 의미 있게 다룰 수 있다. 본 논문에서는 이 설정에서 perceptron block의 효과를 연구하고, critical point가 일반적으로 atomic하며 sphere의 subset에 국소화됨을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63008","en":"Conservation Laws for Modern Neural Architectures","ko":"현대 Neural Architectures의 보존 법칙","authors":"Viet Hoang Tran, VINH KHANH BUI, Ngoc Tan Lai, Nam Nguyen, Tuan Dam, Tan Nguyen","pos":"#314","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ay4Q69fAJL","abs":"<p>Understanding gradient descent dynamics is key to explaining the success of over-parameterized models, where implicit bias manifests through conservation laws in gradient flow. While such laws are well understood for linear and ReLU networks, they remain largely unexplored for modern architectures. This work develops a unified framework to characterize conservation laws for contemporary models, including feedforward networks with GELU, SiLU, and SwiGLU activations, multihead attention with sinusoidal and rotary positional encodings, and Mixture-of-Experts architectures under diverse gating designs. Our theoretical findings are supported by experiments that validate the predicted invariants.</p>","absKo":"<p>gradient descent dynamics를 이해하는 것은 over-parameterized model의 성공을 설명하는 핵심이며, 여기서 implicit bias는 gradient flow의 conservation law를 통해 나타난다. 이러한 law는 linear network와 ReLU network에 대해서는 잘 이해되어 있지만, 현대 architecture에서는 여전히 거의 탐구되지 않았다. 이 연구는 GELU, SiLU, SwiGLU activation을 사용하는 feedforward network, sinusoidal 및 rotary positional encoding이 적용된 multihead attention, 그리고 다양한 gating design 하의 Mixture-of-Experts architecture를 포함하는 현대 모델의 conservation law를 특성화하기 위한 통합 framework를 개발한다. 우리의 이론적 결과는 예측된 invariant를 검증하는 실험으로 뒷받침된다.</p>"},{"id":"60480","en":"Attention's forward pass and Frank-Wolfe","ko":"Attention의 Forward Pass와 Frank-Wolfe","authors":"Albert Alcalde, Borjan Geshkovski, Domènec Ruiz-Balet","pos":"#4608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zrn7rRuvhW","abs":"We analyze the hardmax limit of self-attention dynamics for token embeddings in the zero-temperature regime $(\\beta \\to +\\infty)$ and relate it to finite-$\\beta$ behavior. In this limit, the update rule can be viewed as a Frank-Wolfe step for a quadratic objective over the convex hull of the current tokens. When the key-query matrix is negative semidefinite, the dynamics converge with the standard sublinear rate $\\mathcal{O}(t^{-1})$ on the quadratic energy, whereas in the positive semidefinite case, extending the hardmax rule to the convex hull induces a Voronoi structure: vertices are stationary, interior points remain in their initial cells, and each token moves along a straight line toward its cell's vertex with exponential convergence under a step-size bounded away from zero. We additionally establish well-posedness of the associated ODE limit in this regime. For finite $\\beta$, we model self-attention as a Markov chain and prove *dynamic metastability*: interior tokens reach near-vertex configurations in a constant number of steps and remain trapped for times exponential in $\\beta$ with high probability, before eventual collapse to some point within the initial convex hull. Thus, hardmax dynamics accurately approximate the finite-$\\beta$ process over exponentially long time horizons.","absKo":"우리는 zero-temperature regime $(\\beta \\to +\\infty)$에서 token embedding에 대한 self-attention dynamics의 hardmax limit를 분석하고 이를 finite-$\\beta$ 거동과 연결한다. 이 극한에서 update rule은 현재 token들의 convex hull 위에 정의된 quadratic objective에 대한 Frank-Wolfe step으로 볼 수 있다. key-query matrix가 negative semidefinite인 경우, dynamics는 quadratic energy에서 표준 sublinear rate $\\mathcal{O}(t^{-1})$로 수렴한다. 반면 positive semidefinite case에서는 hardmax rule을 convex hull로 확장하면 Voronoi structure가 유도되는데, 정점은 stationary이고 interior point는 초기 cell 안에 남아 있으며, 각 token은 step size가 0에서 멀리 떨어져 있을 때 exponential convergence를 보이며 자신의 cell 정점을 향해 직선 경로로 이동한다. 또한 이 regime에서 관련 ODE limit의 well-posedness도 확립한다. finite $\\beta$의 경우, 우리는 self-attention을 Markov chain으로 모델링하고 *dynamic metastability*를 증명한다. 즉, interior token은 일정한 step 수 안에 near-vertex configuration에 도달하고, high probability로 $\\beta$에 대해 exponential한 시간 동안 그 상태에 갇혀 있다가, 결국 초기 convex hull 내의 어떤 점으로 붕괴한다. 따라서 hardmax dynamics는 exponentially long time horizon에 걸쳐 finite-$\\beta$ 과정을 정확하게 근사한다.</p>"},{"id":"64824","en":"Context-free Recognition with Transformers","ko":"Transformer를 활용한 문맥 자유 인식","authors":"Selim Jerad, Anej Svete, Sophie Hao, Ryan Cotterell, William Merrill","pos":"#4609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JOyxs9ElI7","abs":"Transformers excel empirically on tasks that process well-formed inputs according to some grammar, such as natural language and code. However, it remains unclear how they can process grammatical syntax. In fact, under standard complexity conjectures, standard transformers cannot recognize context-free languages (CFLs), a canonical formalism to describe syntax, or even regular languages, a subclass of CFLs. Past work proves that $\\mathcal{O}(\\log(n))$ looping layers (w.r.t. input length n) allows transformers to recognize regular languages, but the question of context-free recognition remained open. In this work, we show that looped transformers with $\\mathcal{O}(\\log(n))$ looping layers and $\\mathcal{O}(n^6)$ padding tokens can recognize all CFLs. However, training and inference with $\\mathcal{O}(n^6)$ padding tokens is potentially impractical. Fortunately, we show that, for natural subclasses such as unambiguous CFLs, the recognition problem on transformers becomes more tractable, requiring $\\mathcal{O}(n^3)$ padding. We empirically validate our results and show that looping helps on a language that provably requires logarithmic depth. Overall, our results shed light on the intricacy of CFL recognition by transformers: While general recognition may require an intractable amount of padding, natural constraints such as unambiguity yield efficient recognition algorithms.","absKo":"Transformers는 natural language와 code처럼 어떤 grammar에 따라 잘 형성된 입력을 처리하는 task에서 경험적으로 뛰어난 성능을 보인다. 그러나 이들이 grammatical syntax를 어떻게 처리할 수 있는지는 여전히 명확하지 않다. 실제로 standard complexity conjecture 하에서는, standard transformer가 syntax를 설명하는 대표적인 formalism인 context-free language (CFL)를 인식할 수 없으며, CFL의 부분집합인 regular language조차 인식할 수 없다. 기존 연구는 입력 길이 n에 대해 \\mathcal{O}(\\log(n))개의 looping layer를 사용하면 transformer가 regular language를 인식할 수 있음을 증명했지만, context-free 인식 문제는 미해결로 남아 있었다. 본 연구에서는 \\mathcal{O}(\\log(n))개의 looping layer와 \\mathcal{O}(n^6)의 padding token을 가진 looped transformer가 모든 CFL을 인식할 수 있음을 보인다. 하지만 \\mathcal{O}(n^6)의 padding token을 사용한 학습과 추론은 실용적이지 않을 수 있다. 다행히도, unambiguous CFL과 같은 자연스러운 subclass에 대해서는 transformer의 인식 문제가 더 다루기 쉬워져 \\mathcal{O}(n^3)의 padding만 필요함을 보인다. 우리는 실험적으로 이러한 결과를 검증하고, logarithmic depth가 필요함이 증명된 language에서 looping이 도움이 됨을 보인다. 전반적으로, 우리의 결과는 transformer의 CFL 인식이 얼마나 복잡한지 보여준다. 일반적인 인식에는 비현실적으로 많은 padding이 필요할 수 있지만, unambiguity 같은 자연스러운 제약은 효율적인 인식 알고리즘을 가능하게 한다."},{"id":"62492","en":"Floating-Point Networks with Automatic Differentiation Can Represent Almost All Floating-Point Functions and Their Gradients","ko":"자동 미분이 가능한 Floating-Point Networks는 거의 모든 Floating-Point 함수와 그 기울기를 표현 가능","authors":"Sejun Park, Yeachan Park, Geonho Hwang","pos":"#4610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g89qqA6qmD","abs":"Theoretical studies show that for any differentiable function on a compact domain, there exists a neural network that approximates both the function values and gradients. However, such a result cannot be used in practice since it assumes real parameters and exact internal operations. In contrast, real implementations only use a finite subset of reals and machine operations with round-off errors. In this work, we investigate whether a similar result holds for neural networks under floating-point arithmetic, when the gradient with respect to the input is computed by the automatic differentiation algorithm $D^\\mathtt{AD}$. We first show that given a floating-point function $\\phi$ (e.g., a loss function), arbitrary function values and gradients can be represented by a floating-point network $f$ and $D^\\mathtt{AD}(\\phi\\circ f)$, respectively. We further extend this result: given $\\phi_1,\\dots,\\phi_n$, $D^\\mathtt{AD}(\\phi_i\\circ f)$ can simultaneously represent arbitrary gradients while $f$ represents the target values, under mild conditions. Our results hold for practical activation functions, e.g., ReLU, ELU, GELU, Swish, Sigmoid, and tanh.","absKo":"이론 연구에 따르면, compact domain 위의 임의의 differentiable function에 대해 함수 값과 gradient를 모두 근사하는 neural network가 존재한다. 그러나 이러한 결과는 real parameter와 exact internal operation을 가정하므로 실제로는 사용할 수 없다. 반면 실제 구현은 유한한 부분집합의 real과 round-off error가 있는 machine operation만 사용한다. 본 연구에서는 input에 대한 gradient가 automatic differentiation 알고리즘 $D^\\mathtt{AD}$로 계산될 때, floating-point arithmetic 하의 neural network에서도 이와 유사한 결과가 성립하는지 탐구한다. 먼저 floating-point function $\\phi$(예: loss function)가 주어졌을 때, 임의의 function value와 gradient가 각각 floating-point network $f$와 $D^\\mathtt{AD}(\\phi\\circ f)$로 표현될 수 있음을 보인다. 더 나아가 $\\phi_1,\\dots,\\phi_n$이 주어지면, mild condition 하에서 $f$가 target value를 표현하는 동시에 $D^\\mathtt{AD}(\\phi_i\\circ f)$가 임의의 gradient를 동시에 표현할 수 있음을 확장해서 보인다. 우리의 결과는 ReLU, ELU, GELU, Swish, Sigmoid, tanh 같은 실용적인 activation function에도 성립한다."},{"id":"60815","en":"Inference-time Alignment with Rewards in Besov Spaces: Provable Advantages of Feature Learning and Multi-Step Policy Updates","ko":"Besov 공간의 보상을 이용한 추론 시 정렬: Feature Learning과 Multi-Step Policy Update의 증명 가능한 이점","authors":"Naoki Nishikawa, Taiji Suzuki","pos":"#4612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wQjmCMLeyD","abs":"<p>Inference-time alignment, the approach of adapting pre-trained models to reward feedback during inference, has proven empirically effective at improving language-model performance. Despite its success, theoretical foundations remain underdeveloped, especially in practical settings where neural networks are employed as reward models.  In this paper, we explore the advantages of neural networks and how to effectively train them for inference-time alignment. Assuming that the true reward function lies in Besov spaces to capture the non-uniform smoothness, we compare neural networks to linear estimators and show that feature learning capability of neural networks is crucial for improving performance. We further analyze algorithms for training neural-network reward estimators. Specifically, we consider a multi-step algorithm that alternates between sampling from the current policy and refitting the reward estimator, and prove that it improves the regret, especially when the true reward exhibits local structure.</p>","absKo":"<p>Inference-time alignment는 inference 과정에서 pre-trained model을 reward feedback에 맞게 적응시키는 접근법으로, language model 성능 향상에 실증적으로 효과적임이 입증되었다. 그러나 그 성공에도 불구하고, 특히 neural network를 reward model로 사용하는 실제 setting에서는 이론적 기반이 아직 충분히 발전하지 못했다. 본 논문에서는 neural network의 장점과 inference-time alignment를 위해 이를 효과적으로 학습하는 방법을 탐구한다. 비균질한 smoothness를 포착하기 위해 true reward function이 Besov space에 놓여 있다고 가정하고, neural network를 linear estimator와 비교하여 neural network의 feature learning capability가 성능 향상에 핵심적임을 보인다. 또한 neural network reward estimator를 학습하는 알고리즘을 추가로 분석한다. 구체적으로, 현재 policy로부터 sampling하고 reward estimator를 다시 fitting하는 과정을 번갈아 수행하는 multi-step algorithm을 고려하며, 특히 true reward가 local structure를 보일 때 regret가 개선됨을 증명한다.</p>"},{"id":"62823","en":"Information dynamics and Memory in Neural Networks through Fisher Information Diffusion","ko":"Fisher Information Diffusion을 통한 신경망의 정보 동역학 및 Memory","authors":"Haodong Qin, Tatyana Sharpee","pos":"#4613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cvfjjRCY0U","abs":"<p>We present a general theoretical framework for analyzing how information about past inputs is encoded in recurrent networks into evolving dynamics rather than being represented as convergence to static attractors. Using dynamic mean-field theory and diffusion from physics, we derive a Fisher information diffusion operator that links network connectivity structure to the time-resolved propagation of information across interacting subpopulations. The analysis reveals that operating near criticality (spectral radius near one) is necessary but not sufficient for reliable memory in structured or non-normal recurrent networks; effective information retention requires alignment between input–output structure and stable dynamical subspaces. The theory yields principled initialization rules that balance stability and sensitivity, mitigating vanishing and exploding gradients. Experiments on the copy task and sequential MNIST show faster convergence and higher accuracy than standard random initialization. Together, these results provide both principled design guidelines for recurrent networks and new theoretical insight into how information can be preserved over time in their dynamics.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 과거 입력에 대한 정보가 recurrent network에서 정적 attractor로 수렴하는 방식이 아니라, 진화하는 dynamics 속에 어떻게 인코딩되는지를 분석하기 위한 일반적인 이론적 framework를 제시한다. physics의 dynamic mean-field theory와 diffusion을 사용하여, network connectivity structure를 interacting subpopulation들 사이에서 정보가 시간에 따라 분해되어 전파되는 양상과 연결하는 Fisher information diffusion operator를 유도한다. 이 분석은 criticality 근처에서 동작하는 것(spectral radius가 1에 근접)이 structured 또는 non-normal recurrent network에서 신뢰할 수 있는 memory에 필요조건이지만 충분조건은 아님을 보여준다. 효과적인 information retention은 input–output structure와 안정적인 dynamical subspace의 정렬을 요구한다. 이 이론은 stability와 sensitivity의 균형을 맞추는 원리적인 initialization rule을 도출하며, vanishing gradient와 exploding gradient를 완화한다. copy task와 sequential MNIST 실험에서 standard random initialization보다 더 빠른 수렴과 더 높은 accuracy를 보였다. 종합하면, 이 결과는 recurrent network를 위한 원리적인 설계 지침과 더불어, 그 dynamics에서 information이 시간에 따라 어떻게 보존될 수 있는지에 대한 새로운 이론적 통찰을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66189","en":"On Expressive Power of Floating-Point Transformers","ko":"부동소수점 Transformer의 표현력에 관하여","authors":"Sejun Park, Yeachan Park, Geonho Hwang","pos":"#4614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5yBuQP7yDy","abs":"<p>Research on the expressive power of transformers shows that transformers are equivariant to permutations and can approximate all permutation-equivariant continuous functions on a compact domain. However, these results assume real parameters and exact operations, whereas real-world implementations on computers can only use a finite set of numbers and inexact machine operations with round-off errors. In this work, we investigate the representability of floating-point transformers that use floating-point parameters and floating-point operations. Unlike existing results under exact arithmetic, we first show that floating-point transformers can represent non-permutation-equivariant functions even without positional encoding. Furthermore, we prove that floating-point transformers can represent all permutation-equivariant functions when the sequence length is bounded, but they cannot when the sequence length is large. We also identify the minimal equivariance property in floating-point transformers, and show that all non-trivial additive positional encoding can harm the representability of floating-point transformers.</p>"},{"id":"60970","en":"Optimal Attention Temperature Improves the Robustness of In-Context Learning under Distribution Shift in High Dimensions","ko":"최적 Attention Temperature는 고차원 Distribution Shift 하에서 In-Context Learning의 Robustness를 향상시킨다","authors":"Samet Demir, Zafer Dogan","pos":"#4615","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uyjhZkN9ZA","abs":"<p>Pretrained Transformers can perform in-context learning (ICL) from a few demonstrations, but this ability can fail sharply when the test distribution differs from pretraining—a common deployment setting. We study attention temperature as a simple inference-time control for improving ICL robustness under such shifts. In a high-dimensional linear-regression framework, we analyze a Transformer with \"approximate softmax\" attention, which preserves softmax's normalization and temperature-dependent selectivity while remaining tractable. We derive a closed-form expression for the ICL generalization error under distribution shift, and show that it is minimized by an explicit optimal attention temperature. This characterization yields interpretable guidance by linking the best temperature to moments of the pre-softmax attention scores, and predicts when temperature adjustment can recover near Bayes-optimal performance. We validate the theory with extensive simulations, and further demonstrate gains on pretrained LLMs (GPT-2 and Llama2-7B) on question-answering benchmarks under distribution shift induced by noisy in-context demonstrations. Overall, attention temperature emerges as a principled, lightweight knob for improving the robustness of ICL in pretrained Transformers.</p>","absKo":"<p>Pretrained Transformer는 몇 개의 demonstration만으로 in-context learning(ICL)을 수행할 수 있지만, test distribution이 pretraining과 달라지면 이러한 능력이 크게 실패할 수 있다. 이는 배포 환경에서 흔한 상황이다. 우리는 이러한 shift 하에서 ICL의 robustness를 개선하기 위한 단순한 inference-time 제어 변수로 attention temperature를 연구한다. 고차원 linear-regression framework에서, 우리는 softmax의 정규화와 temperature에 따른 선택성을 유지하면서도 분석 가능성을 확보한 \"approximate softmax\" attention을 사용하는 Transformer를 분석한다. 우리는 distribution shift 하에서 ICL generalization error의 closed-form expression을 도출하고, 그것이 명시적인 optimal attention temperature에 의해 최소화됨을 보인다. 이러한 특성화는 best temperature를 pre-softmax attention score의 moment와 연결함으로써 해석 가능한 지침을 제공하며, temperature 조정이 언제 near Bayes-optimal performance를 회복할 수 있는지를 예측한다. 우리는 extensive simulation으로 이론을 검증하고, noisy in-context demonstrations로 유도된 distribution shift 하에서 question-answering benchmark에 대해 pretrained LLM(GPT-2 및 Llama2-7B)에서도 성능 향상을 추가로 입증한다. 전반적으로, attention temperature는 pretrained Transformer에서 ICL의 robustness를 개선하기 위한 원리 있는, 가벼운 조절 변수로 부상한다.</p>"},{"id":"60856","en":"The Devil is in the Condition Numbers: Why is GLU Better than non-GLU Structure?","ko":"핵심은 Condition Number: GLU는 왜 non-GLU 구조보다 나은가?","authors":"Xingyu Lyu, Qianqian Xu, zhiyong yang, Peisong Wen, Qingming Huang","pos":"#4619","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=w0JhOFWPJl","abs":"<p>Gated Linear Units (GLU) and their variants are widely adopted in modern open-source large language model architectures and consistently outperform their non-gated counterparts, yet the underlying reasons for this advantage remain unclear. In this work, we study GLU by analyzing two-layer networks in the neural tangent kernel (NTK) regime. Our analysis reveals that the GLU structure reshapes the NTK spectrum, leading to a smaller condition number and a more compact eigenvalue distribution. Building on this finding, we further analyze the resulting training dynamics and show how the reshaped spectrum leads to faster convergence of GLU models, including a characteristic loss-crossing phenomenon observed between GLU and non-GLU models. Finally, we empirically observe that GLU has limited impact in reducing the stochastic error on various models, including ViT and GPT-2, suggesting that its primary benefit lies in accelerating optimization rather than reducing the stochastic error.</p>","absKo":"<p>Gated Linear Units(GLU)와 그 변형은 현대의 오픈소스 large language model 아키텍처에서 널리 채택되고 있으며, 비-gated 대안보다 일관되게 더 나은 성능을 보인다. 그러나 이러한 우위의 근본 원인은 아직 명확하지 않다. 본 연구에서는 neural tangent kernel(NTK) regime에서 두 층 네트워크를 분석하여 GLU를 연구한다. 우리의 분석은 GLU 구조가 NTK 스펙트럼을 재구성하여 더 작은 condition number와 더 압축된 eigenvalue 분포를 유도함을 보여준다. 이 발견을 바탕으로, 우리는 그 결과로 나타나는 학습 dynamics를 추가로 분석하고, 재구성된 스펙트럼이 GLU 모델의 더 빠른 수렴으로 이어지는 방식을 보인다. 여기에는 GLU와 non-GLU 모델 사이에서 관찰되는 특징적인 loss-crossing 현상도 포함된다. 마지막으로, ViT와 GPT-2를 포함한 다양한 모델에서 GLU가 stochastic error를 줄이는 데에는 제한적인 영향을 미친다는 점을 실증적으로 관찰한다. 이는 GLU의 주요 이점이 stochastic error 감소가 아니라 optimization 가속에 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"65793","en":"Towards Understanding Steering Strength","ko":"조종 강도 이해를 향하여","authors":"Magamed Taimeskhanov, Samuel Vaiter, Damien Garreau","pos":"#4620","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A52LNgpGKy","abs":"<p>A popular approach to post-training control of large language models (LLMs) is the steering of intermediate latent representations. Namely, identify a well-chosen direction depending on the task at hand and perturbs representations along this direction at inference time. While many propositions exist to pick this direction, considerably less is understood about how to choose the magnitude of the move, whereas its importance is clear: too little and the intended behavior does not emerge, too much and the model's performance degrades beyond repair. In this work, we propose the first theoretical analysis of steering strength. We characterize its effect on next token probability, presence of a concept, and cross-entropy, deriving precise qualitative laws governing these quantities. Our analysis reveals surprising behaviors, including non-monotonic effects of steering strength. We validate our theoretical predictions empirically on eleven language models, ranging from a small GPT architecture to modern models.</p>"},{"id":"63994","en":"Unifying Low Dimensional Spectra in Deep Learning","ko":"딥러닝의 저차원 스펙트럼 통합","authors":"Connall Garrod, Jonathan Keating","pos":"#4621","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RwiGcN2feP","abs":"<p>Low-dimensional structures appear ubiquitously in the eigenspectra of deep-learning matrices in classification networks trained in the overparameterized regime. While theoretical advances have aimed to explain this phenomenology, they typically succeed only in capturing subsets of the full behavior or rely on assumptions that cannot hold in practice. In this work, we provide an analytic explanation for the bulk–outlier structure of several canonical deep-learning matrices, including the Hessian, gradients, and weights. We achieve this using unconstrained feature models (UFMs), a now-common tool for studying the emergence of deep neural collapse (DNC). We show that DNC is the source of these low-dimensional eigenspectra: in each case, the eigenvalues and eigenvectors can be constructed from feature means, the characterizing objects of DNC. This provides a unifying analytic explanation for a wide range of spectral phenomena in deep learning and goes beyond empirical characterizations—which typically focus on eigenvalues—by providing a detailed analysis of eigenvectors. We prove that our results hold for both linear and ReLU networks and provide numerical validation in both the modeling context and standard deep-network architectures on canonical datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>고차원 overparameterized regime에서 학습된 classification network의 deep-learning matrix 고유스펙트럼에는 저차원 구조가 널리 나타난다. 이 현상을 설명하기 위해 많은 이론적 진전이 있었지만, 대개 전체 동작의 일부만 포착하거나 실제로는 성립할 수 없는 가정에 의존한다. 본 연구에서는 Hessian, gradient, weight를 포함한 몇 가지 대표적인 deep-learning matrix의 bulk-outlier 구조에 대한 해석적 설명을 제시한다. 이를 위해 우리는 deep neural collapse (DNC)의 출현을 연구하는 데 널리 쓰이는 도구인 unconstrained feature model (UFM)을 사용한다. 우리는 DNC가 이러한 저차원 고유스펙트럼의 근원임을 보인다. 각 경우에서 eigenvalue와 eigenvector는 모두 DNC를 특징짓는 객체인 feature mean으로부터 구성할 수 있다. 이는 deep learning에서 폭넓은 spectral phenomenon에 대해 통합적인 해석적 설명을 제공하며, 보통 eigenvalue에 초점을 맞추는 경험적 특성화를 넘어 eigenvector에 대한 상세한 분석까지 제시한다. 우리는 이러한 결과가 linear network와 ReLU network 모두에 대해 성립함을 증명하고, modeling context와 canonical dataset 상의 표준 deep-network architecture에서 수치 검증을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61361","en":"Population-Aware Imitation Learning in Mean-field Games with Common Noise","ko":"Common Noise가 있는 Mean-field Games에서 Population-Aware Imitation Learning","authors":"Grégoire Lambrecht, Mathieu Lauriere","pos":"#116","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qzzBvD3BOM","abs":"<p>Mean Field Games (MFGs) provide a powerful framework for modeling the collective behavior of large populations of interacting agents. In this paper, we address the problem of Imitation Learning (IL) in MFGs subject to common noise, where the population distribution evolves stochastically. This stochasticity compels agents to adopt population-aware policies to respond to aggregate shocks. We formulate two distinct learning objectives: recovering a Nash equilibrium and maximizing performance against an expert population. We investigate two imitation proxies: Behavioral Cloning (BC) and Adversarial (ADV) divergence. We then establish finite-sample error bounds showing that minimizing these proxies effectively controls both the policy’s exploitability and its performance gap relative to the expert. Furthermore, we propose a numerical framework using generalized Fictitious Play and Deep Learning to compute expert population-aware policies. Through experiments on three environments we demonstrate that standard population-unaware policies fail to capture the equilibrium dynamics. Our results highlight that learning population-aware policies is crucial to avoid being misled by the randomness inherent in common noise.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mean Field Games(MFGs)는 상호작용하는 대규모 에이전트 집단의 집합적 행동을 모델링하는 강력한 프레임워크를 제공한다. 본 논문에서는 population distribution이 확률적으로 진화하는 common noise가 존재하는 MFGs에서의 Imitation Learning(IL) 문제를 다룬다. 이러한 확률성은 에이전트가 집단 수준의 충격에 대응하기 위해 population-aware policy를 채택하도록 만든다. 우리는 Nash equilibrium을 복원하는 것과 expert population에 대해 성능을 극대화하는 것이라는 두 가지 서로 다른 learning objective를 정식화한다. 또한 Behavioral Cloning(BC)과 Adversarial(ADV) divergence라는 두 가지 imitation proxy를 검토한다. 이어서 이 proxy들을 최소화하면 policy의 exploitability와 expert 대비 performance gap을 효과적으로 제어함을 보이는 finite-sample error bound를 확립한다. 더 나아가 generalized Fictitious Play와 Deep Learning을 활용해 expert population-aware policy를 계산하는 수치적 프레임워크를 제안한다. 세 개의 환경에서 수행한 실험을 통해, 표준적인 population-unaware policy는 equilibrium dynamics를 포착하지 못함을 보인다. 우리의 결과는 common noise에 내재한 무작위성에 현혹되지 않기 위해 population-aware policy를 학습하는 것이 중요함을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"62646","en":"Last-Iterate Convergence of Regularized Gradient Methods for Stochastic Monotone Variational Inequalities","ko":"Stochastic Monotone Variational Inequalities를 위한 Regularized Gradient Methods의 Last-Iterate Convergence","authors":"Shinji Ito, Kenshi Abe, Kaito Ariu, Taira Tsuchiya","pos":"#307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=eirv1OEo7F","abs":"We study last-iterate convergence for stochastic smooth and monotone variational inequalities (VIs), a framework that captures convex-concave saddle points and Nash equilibrium computation in monotone games with noisy payoff feedback. In contrast to the well-understood average-iterate guarantees, anytime last-iterate guarantees in stochastic settings remain limited, despite their relevance for uncoupled learning dynamics that output a single current strategy. We analyze two single-call regularized methods, the \\emph{regularized gradient (RG)} and the \\emph{regularized optimistic gradient (ROG)} methods, and establish anytime last-iterate convergence rates in terms of the squared gap function. For monotone VIs, RG attains $O(t^{-2/5})$ while ROG achieves the variance-adaptive rate $O(\\sigma^{4/5} t^{-2/5} + t^{-1})$, where $\\sigma^2$ is the noise variance. For $\\lambda$-strongly monotone VIs, ROG yields $O(\\sigma^2 / (\\lambda^2 t) + t^{-c})$ for any constant $c \\ge 2$. These results give anytime last-iterate guarantees without knowing the horizon and show that optimism improves convergence in the low-noise regime.","absKo":"잡음이 있는 payoff feedback 하에서 convex-concave saddle point와 monotone game의 Nash equilibrium 계산을 포착하는 stochastic smooth and monotone variational inequalities (VIs)에서 last-iterate convergence를 연구한다. 잘 이해된 average-iterate 보장과 달리, stochastic setting에서의 anytime last-iterate 보장은 여전히 제한적이다. 이는 현재의 단일 전략만을 출력하는 uncoupled learning dynamics와의 관련성에도 불구하고 그러하다. 우리는 두 가지 single-call regularized method인 \\emph{regularized gradient (RG)}와 \\emph{regularized optimistic gradient (ROG)} method를 분석하고, squared gap function 관점에서 anytime last-iterate convergence rate를 확립한다. monotone VI의 경우 RG는 $O(t^{-2/5})$를 달성하고, ROG는 분산 적응형 rate인 $O(\\sigma^{4/5} t^{-2/5} + t^{-1})$를 달성한다. 여기서 $\\sigma^2$는 noise variance이다. $\\lambda$-strongly monotone VI의 경우 ROG는 임의의 상수 $c \\ge 2$에 대해 $O(\\sigma^2 / (\\lambda^2 t) + t^{-c})$를 산출한다. 이러한 결과는 horizon을 알지 못해도 anytime last-iterate 보장을 제공하며, 낮은 잡음 영역에서 optimism이 수렴을 개선함을 보여준다."},{"id":"61257","en":"A Theoretical Game of Attacks via Compositional Skills","ko":"조합적 Skill을 통한 공격의 이론적 게임","authors":"Xinbo Wu, Huan Zhang, Abhishek Umrawal, Lav Varshney","pos":"#3101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=s6Vno2TwLJ","abs":"<p>As large language models grow increasingly capable, concerns about their safe deployment have intensified. While numerous alignment strategies aim to restrict harmful behavior, these defenses can still be circumvented through carefully designed adversarial prompts. In this work, we introduce a theoretical framework that formalizes a game between an attacker and a defender. Within this framework, we design a theoretical best-response attack strategy and show that it is closely related to many existing adversarial prompting methods. We further analyze the resulting game, characterize its equilibria, and reveal inherent advantages for the attacker. Drawing on our theoretical analysis, we also derive a provably optimal defense strategy. Empirically, we evaluate a practical instantiation of the theoretically optimal attack and observe stronger performance relative to existing adversarial prompting approaches in diverse settings encompassing different LLMs and benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델이 점점 더 강력해지면서, 안전한 배포에 대한 우려도 커지고 있다. 수많은 alignment 전략이 유해한 행동을 제한하려고 하지만, 이러한 방어는 정교하게 설계된 adversarial prompt를 통해 여전히 우회될 수 있다. 본 연구에서는 공격자와 방어자 사이의 게임을 정식화하는 이론적 프레임워크를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크 안에서 우리는 이론적 best-response 공격 전략을 설계하고, 그것이 기존의 많은 adversarial prompting 방법과 밀접하게 관련되어 있음을 보인다. 또한 유도되는 게임을 추가로 분석하여 그 평형을 특징짓고, 공격자에게 내재된 이점을 밝혀낸다. 우리의 이론적 분석을 바탕으로, 우리는 또한 증명 가능한 최적 방어 전략을 도출한다. 실증적으로는 이론적으로 최적인 공격의 실용적 구현을 평가하고, 다양한 LLM과 benchmark를 포괄하는 여러 설정에서 기존 adversarial prompting 접근법보다 더 강한 성능을 관찰한다.</p>"},{"id":"62259","en":"Emergent Alignment via Competition","ko":"경쟁을 통한 Emergent Alignment","authors":"Natalie Collina, Surbhi Goel, Aaron Roth, Emily Ryu, Mirah Shi","pos":"#3207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iE0m4NE5qb","abs":"<p>Aligning AI systems with human values remains a fundamental challenge, but does our inability to create perfectly aligned models preclude obtaining the benefits of alignment? We study a strategic setting where a human user interacts with multiple differently misaligned AI agents, none of which are individually well-aligned. Our key insight is that when the user’s utility lies approximately within the convex hull of the agents’ utilities, a condition that becomes easier to satisfy as model diversity increases, strategic competition can yield outcomes comparable to interacting with a perfectly aligned model.   We model this as a multi-leader Stackelberg game, extending Bayesian persuasion to multi-round conversations between differently informed parties, and prove three results: (1) when perfect alignment would allow the user to learn her Bayes-optimal action, she can also do so in all equilibria under the convex hull condition; (2) under weaker assumptions requiring only approximate utility learning, a non-strategic user employing quantal response achieves near-optimal utility in all equilibria; and (3) when the user selects the best single AI after an evaluation period, equilibrium guarantees remain near-optimal without further distributional assumptions.  We complement the theory with two forms of empirical evidence: First, we perform simulations of the best-AI selection game using best response dynamics, which show that competition among individually misaligned agents reliably improves user utility when the approximate convex hull assumption is satisfied, but does not always when it fails. Second, we show that synthetically generated AI utility functions (produced via perturbations of the same prompt to evaluate instances on a movie recommendation (MovieLens) and ethical judgement (ETHICS) dataset) quickly produce a convex hull that contains a good approximation of a given utility function even when none of the individual LLM utility functions is well aligned. We show that this phenomenon extends to human and LLM responses on real-world polling data (OpinionQA): a convex hull of LLM opinions can approximate human opinions more accurately than any individual LLM across a wide range of survey questions.</p>","absKo":"<p>AI 시스템을 인간의 가치에 맞추는 일은 여전히 근본적인 도전이지만, 완벽하게 정렬된 모델을 만들 수 없다는 사실이 정렬의 이점을 얻지 못한다는 뜻일까? 우리는 서로 다르게 misaligned된 여러 AI 에이전트와 인간 사용자가 상호작용하는 전략적 설정을 연구한다. 이들 중 어느 하나도 개별적으로는 잘 aligned되어 있지 않다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 사용자의 utility가 대략 에이전트들의 utility의 convex hull 안에 놓여 있다는 조건이 성립할 때, 그리고 모델 다양성이 증가할수록 이 조건이 더 쉽게 충족될수록, 전략적 경쟁이 완벽하게 aligned된 모델과 상호작용할 때에 준하는 결과를 낳을 수 있다는 점이다. 우리는 이를 multi-leader Stackelberg game으로 모델링하고, 서로 다른 정보를 가진 당사자들 간의 multi-round conversation으로 Bayesian persuasion을 확장한 뒤, 다음의 세 가지 결과를 증명한다: (1) 완벽한 alignment가 사용자가 Bayes-optimal action을 학습하게 해준다면, convex hull 조건 하에서는 모든 equilibrium에서도 그와 동일하게 할 수 있다; (2) approximate utility learning만을 요구하는 더 약한 가정 아래에서는 quantal response를 사용하는 non-strategic 사용자가 모든 equilibrium에서 near-optimal utility를 달성한다; (3) 사용자가 evaluation period 이후 가장 좋은 단일 AI를 선택하는 경우, 추가적인 distributional assumption 없이도 equilibrium 보장은 여전히 near-optimal하다. 우리는 이론을 두 가지 경험적 증거로 보완한다. 첫째, best response dynamics를 사용해 best-AI selection game을 시뮬레이션한 결과, approximate convex hull 가정이 만족될 때 개별적으로는 misaligned된 에이전트들 사이의 경쟁이 사용자 utility를 안정적으로 향상시키지만, 그렇지 않을 때는 항상 그런 것은 아님을 보였다. 둘째, 합성적으로 생성한 AI utility functions(영화 추천(MovieLens)과 윤리적 판단(ETHICS) 데이터셋에서 인스턴스를 평가하기 위해 같은 prompt에 perturbation을 가해 생성)를 사용하면, 개별 LLM utility functions 중 어느 것도 잘 aligned되어 있지 않더라도 주어진 utility function의 좋은 근사를 포함하는 convex hull이 빠르게 형성됨을 보였다. 또한 이러한 현상이 실제 여론 조사 데이터(OpinionQA)에서의 human 및 LLM 응답으로 확장됨을 보인다. 즉, LLM 의견들의 convex hull은 광범위한 설문 질문 전반에서 어떤 개별 LLM보다도 human opinions를 더 정확하게 근사할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"63852","en":"Equilibrium Pricing in Oligopolistic Data Markets","ko":"과점 데이터 시장에서의 균형 가격","authors":"Bhaskar Ray Chaudhury, Jugal Garg, Eklavya Sharma, Jiaxin Song","pos":"#3503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TAqejOfEAJ","abs":"<p>We study equilibrium pricing in oligopolistic data markets with budget-constrained buyers (e.g., ML companies purchasing data to improve model accuracy) and strategic data sellers. Sellers compete by setting prices for their datasets, giving rise to a pricing game whose pure Nash equilibria correspond to equilibrium prices. While equilibrium prices are guaranteed for rivalrous goods via competitive equilibrium, we show that the non-rivalry of data fundamentally alters this picture: an exact Nash equilibrium need not exist, and in fact no 1.364-approximate equilibrium exists under uniform pricing. We therefore investigate relaxed equilibrium notions. Allowing sellers to use beyond-uniform pricing—specifically, piecewise-linear convex pricing functions—guarantees approximate stability within a constant factor: there exists a pricing profile in which no seller can improve revenue by a factor of two by deviating to any uniform price (a 2-approximate Nash equilibrium). Finally, our simulations demonstrate fast convergence and empirical approximation guarantees that outperform the worst-case bound of 2.</p>","absKo":"<p>Budget-constrained buyer(예: model 정확도를 높이기 위해 data를 구매하는 ML company)와 strategic data seller가 존재하는 oligopolistic data market에서의 equilibrium pricing을 연구한다. Seller는 자신의 dataset에 가격을 설정하며 경쟁하고, 그 결과로 발생하는 pricing game의 pure Nash equilibrium이 equilibrium price에 해당한다. Rivalrous good의 경우 competitive equilibrium을 통해 equilibrium price가 보장되지만, 우리는 data의 non-rivalry가 이 그림을 근본적으로 바꾼다는 점을 보인다. 즉, exact Nash equilibrium은 존재하지 않을 수 있으며, uniform pricing 하에서는 사실상 1.364-approximate equilibrium조차 존재하지 않는다. 따라서 우리는 완화된 equilibrium 개념을 조사한다. Seller가 uniform pricing을 넘어, 특히 piecewise-linear convex pricing function을 사용할 수 있도록 허용하면, 상수 배 수준의 approximate stability가 보장된다. 즉, 어떤 seller도 uniform price로 deviation함으로써 revenue를 두 배 이상 개선할 수 없는 pricing profile이 존재한다 (2-approximate Nash equilibrium). 마지막으로, 우리의 simulation은 빠른 수렴과 경험적 approximation guarantee를 보여주며, 이는 최악의 경우 bound 2를 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"65188","en":"A Theory of Data Acquisition and Pricing at Scale","ko":"대규모 데이터 획득 및 가격 책정 이론","authors":"Andrew Ilyas, Amin Saberi, Grigorios Velegkas","pos":"#3612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Fz9nVjFNPN","abs":"<p>Data plays an invaluable role in large-scale ML training pipelines. Multiple factors, including the need to incentivize the creation of high-quality data and efforts to compensate creative data work, have led to increased interest in data {\\em pricing}.  Data pricing mechanisms seek to establish a market where data providers are compensated based (in part) on the value of their data to the data buyer, e.g., frontier AI labs. However, assessing the exact value that each provider's data adds to the data buyer's objective requires repeated re-training, which is infeasible in practice. Our work studies {\\em data pricing under compute constraints}.  In our setting, data buyers cannot make data acquisition decisions optimally due to limited compute.  Inspired by existing practice in the field of data selection, we propose a model for this problem called ``pricing with an attribution oracle,'' and provide a theoretical and empirical analysis of compute-efficient acquisition and pricing.</p>","absKo":"<p>Data는 대규모 ML training pipeline에서 매우 중요한 역할을 한다. 고품질 data 생산을 장려해야 할 필요성과 창의적 data work에 대한 보상 필요성을 포함한 여러 요인으로 인해 data {\\em pricing}에 대한 관심이 높아졌다. Data pricing mechanism은 data provider가 자신들의 data 가치에 비례해 보상받는 market을 구축하고자 하며, 예를 들어 frontier AI lab이 data buyer가 된다. 그러나 각 provider의 data가 data buyer의 objective에 추가하는 정확한 가치를 평가하려면 반복적인 re-training이 필요하고, 이는 실제로는 불가능하다. 우리의 연구는 {\\em compute constraints 하의 data pricing}을 다룬다. 우리의 설정에서 data buyer는 제한된 compute 때문에 최적으로 data acquisition decision을 내릴 수 없다. data selection 분야의 기존 관행에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 이 문제를 ``pricing with an attribution oracle''이라고 부르는 model로 제안하고, compute-efficient acquisition과 pricing에 대한 이론적 및 실증적 분석을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66240","en":"What Preferences Can—and Cannot—Predict in Multi-Agent Online Learning","ko":"다중 에이전트 온라인 학습에서 선호가 예측할 수 있는 것과 없는 것","authors":"Omar Abbadi, Rida Laraki, Panayotis Mertikopoulos","pos":"#4503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5W30WwL8wt","abs":"<p>We examine the interplay between ordinal, preference-based solution concepts in games and the outcomes of payoff-driven learning dynamics, asking to what extent the combinatorial data of a game—its preference graph—can predict the long-run behavior of no-regret dynamics such as <em>follow-the-regularized-leader</em> (FTRL). In one direction, we show that the skeleton of every <em>dynamically stable</em> set, i.e., the set of pure profiles it contains, must be <em>preferentially stable</em>, that is, closed under pure profitable deviations. We then ask the converse question: when are preferences sufficient to describe long-run behavior? For <em>subgames</em>—subsets of pure profiles obtained by restricting players’ action sets—preferences are enough to fully characterize asymptotic stability. Beyond subgames however, we construct a three-player counterexample with a preferentially stable set whose span is dynamically <em>unstable</em>, thus establishing that preferences are <em>not sufficient</em> to describe dynamically stable behavior in general. To restore stability, we introduce the notion of <em>leaklessness</em>, a measure of aggregate payoff drift away from a set of pure profiles, and use it to identify a payoff-based condition under which the span of a set of pure profiles remains stable and attracting, thereby setting forth a natural cardinal guarantee of dynamic stability.</p>"},{"id":"65304","en":"Theory of Continual Learning Against Data Poisoning Attacks","ko":"데이터 포이즈닝 공격에 대응하는 연속 학습 이론","authors":"Yiting Hu, Lingjie Duan","pos":"#4504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EvIDneKgn1","abs":"<p>Continual learning (CL), where a model is trained on a sequence of data tasks, is increasingly being adopted across key fields such as large language models and image recognition, yet it remains highly vulnerable to data poisoning that triggers learning divergence or severe generalization loss. Despite these threats, a principled theoretical foundation in CL for understanding attack and defense remains lacking. In this paper, we develop a theoretical framework to analyze strategic attacks and defenses in regularization-based CL, a cornerstone of recent CL theory. By framing the adversary-defender interaction as an online zero-sum game, we first establish a fundamental performance limit: no defense succeeds when an adversary poisons a linear proportion of tasks via adding unbounded noise or pattern shifts in regularization-based CL. We then analyze two possibly denfensible scenarios: infrequent attacks and bounded noise per attack. For the former regime, we propose a task-to-task verification mechanism to detect data poisoning and reduce cumulative bias for learning convergence. For the latter regime, we derive a robust defense that minimizes the model’s sensitivity to poisoned features, provably accelerating the convergence rate. Extensive experiments on realistic tasks further validate our theoretical results.</p>"},{"id":"64771","en":"Strategic Candidacy in Generative AI Arenas","ko":"Generative AI Arena에서의 전략적 후보 선정","authors":"Chris Hays, Rachel Li, Bailey Flanigan, Manish Raghavan","pos":"#4505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=K1mAvyHhKU","abs":"<p>AI arenas, which rank models from pairwise preferences of users, are an industry-standard evaluation mechanism for generative models. In a recent paper, Singh et al. (2025) demonstrate that widely-used mechanisms are not clone-robust: In particular, they submitted multiple copies of the same model and showed that the higher-ranked copy was several positions above the lower-ranked one.   In this paper, we begin by showing, both theoretically and in simulations calibrated to data from LMArena, that producers can benefit substantially from submitting clones. We then propose a new mechanism for ranking models based on pairwise comparisons, called You-Rank-We-Rank (YRWR). It uses producers’ rankings over their own models to correct statistical estimates of model quality. We prove that this mechanism is approximately clone-robust, in the sense that a producer cannot gain much utility by doing anything other than submitting each of their unique models exactly once. Moreover, to the extent that model producers are able to correctly rank their own models, YRWR improves overall ranking accuracy. We validate our theory with further semisynthetic experiments.</p>","absKo":"<p>사용자들의 pairwise preference로 모델을 순위화하는 AI arenas는 generative model을 위한 산업 표준 평가 메커니즘이다. 최근 Singh et al. (2025)은 널리 사용되는 메커니즘이 clone-robust하지 않음을 보였다. 구체적으로, 그들은 동일한 모델의 복사본을 여러 개 제출했고, 더 높은 순위를 받은 복사본이 더 낮은 복사본보다 몇 순위 이상 위에 위치함을 관찰했다. 이 논문에서 우리는 먼저 이론적으로 그리고 LMArena 데이터에 맞춘 simulation을 통해, producer가 clone을 제출함으로써 상당한 이득을 얻을 수 있음을 보인다. 이어서 우리는 pairwise comparison에 기반한 새로운 모델 순위화 메커니즘인 You-Rank-We-Rank(YRWR)를 제안한다. 이 메커니즘은 producer가 자신의 모델들에 대해 부여한 순위를 사용해 model quality의 통계적 추정치를 보정한다. 우리는 이 메커니즘이 대략적으로 clone-robust함을 증명한다. 즉, producer는 각 고유 모델을 정확히 한 번씩 제출하는 것 외의 다른 행동으로는 큰 utility를 얻을 수 없다. 더 나아가 model producer가 자신의 모델을 올바르게 순위화할 수 있는 정도에 비례하여, YRWR은 전체 순위 정확도를 향상시킨다. 우리는 추가적인 semisynthetic 실험으로 이론을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65577","en":"Solving Imperfect-Recall Games via Sum-of-Squares Optimization","ko":"제곱합 최적화를 통한 불완전 기억 게임 해결","authors":"Rui Zheng, Ryann Sim, Antonios Varvitsiotis","pos":"#4506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CHIsZDgdb6","abs":"<p>Extensive-form games (EFGs) provide a powerful framework for modeling sequential decision making, capturing strategic interaction under imperfect information, chance events, and temporal structure. Most positive algorithmic and theoretical results for EFGs assume perfect recall, where players remember all past information and actions. We study the increasingly relevant setting of imperfect-recall EFGs (IREFGs), where players may forget parts of their history or previously acquired information, and where equilibrium computation is provably hard. We propose sum-of-squares (SOS) hierarchies for computing ex-ante optimal strategies in single-player IREFGs and Nash equilibria in multi-player IREFGs, working over behavioral strategies. Our theoretical results show that (i) these hierarchies converge asymptotically, (ii) under genericity assumptions, the convergence is finite, and (iii) in single-player non-absentminded IREFGs, convergence occurs at a finite level determined by the number of information sets. Finally, we introduce the new classes of (SOS)-concave and (SOS)-monotone IREFGs, and show that in the single-player setting the SOS hierarchy converges at the first level, enabling equilibrium computation with a single semidefinite program (SDP).</p>"},{"id":"65678","en":"Nash Equilibria in Games with Playerwise Concave Coupling Constraints: Existence and Computation","ko":"플레이어별 오목 결합 제약이 있는 게임의 Nash 균형: 존재성과 계산","authors":"Philip Jordan, Maryam Kamgarpour","pos":"#4507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BGmc3O41ZH","abs":"We study the existence and computation of Nash equilibria in concave games where the players' admissible strategies are subject to shared coupling constraints. Under playerwise concavity of constraints, we prove existence of Nash equilibria. Our proof leverages topological fixed point theory and novel structural insights into the contractibility of feasible sets, and relaxes strong assumptions for existence in prior work. Having established existence, we address the question of whether in the presence of coupling constraints, playerwise independent learning dynamics have convergence guarantees. We address this positively for the class of potential games by designing a convergent algorithm. To account for the possibly nonconvex feasible region, we employ a log barrier regularized gradient ascent with adaptive stepsizes.  Starting from an initial feasible strategy profile and under exact gradient feedback, the proposed method converges to an $\\epsilon$-approximate constrained Nash equilibrium within $\\mathcal{O}(\\epsilon^{-3})$ iterations."},{"id":"65013","en":"Multi-Level Strategic Classification: Incentivizing Improvement through Promotion and Relegation Dynamics","ko":"Multi-Level Strategic Classification: 승격 및 강등 동역학을 통한 개선 유인","authors":"Ziyuan Huang, Lina Alkarmi, Mingyan Liu","pos":"#4508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Hnty5t1TNg","abs":"<p>Strategic classification studies the problem where self-interested individuals or agents manipulate their response to obtain favorable decision outcomes made by classifiers, typically turning to dishonest actions when they are less costly than genuine efforts. While existing studies on sequential strategic classification primarily focus on optimizing dynamic classifier weights, we depart from these weight-centric approaches by analyzing the design of classifier thresholds and difficulty progression within a multi-level promotion-relegation framework. Our model captures the critical inter-temporal incentives driven by an agent's farsightedness, skill retention, and a \"leg-up\" effect where qualification and attainment can be self-reinforcing. We characterize the agent’s optimal long-term strategy and demonstrate that a principal can design a sequence of thresholds to effectively incentivize honest effort. Crucially, we prove that under mild conditions, this mechanism enables agents to reach arbitrarily high levels solely through genuine improvement efforts.</p>","absKo":"<p>Strategic classification은 self-interested한 개인이나 agent가 classifier가 내린 유리한 decision outcome을 얻기 위해 자신의 response를 조작하는 문제를 다루며, 일반적으로 진정한 effort보다 dishonest action의 비용이 더 낮을 때 이러한 행동으로 기운다. 기존의 sequential strategic classification 연구는 주로 dynamic classifier weight 최적화에 초점을 맞추지만, 우리는 multi-level promotion-relegation framework 내에서 classifier threshold와 difficulty progression의 설계를 분석함으로써 이러한 weight-centric 접근에서 벗어난다. 우리의 모델은 agent의 farsightedness, skill retention, 그리고 qualification과 attainment가 자기강화적일 수 있는 \"leg-up\" effect에 의해 유도되는 중요한 inter-temporal incentive를 포착한다. 우리는 agent의 최적 장기 전략을 특성화하고, principal이 honest effort를 효과적으로 유도하도록 threshold sequence를 설계할 수 있음을 보인다. 결정적으로, 우리는 완만한 조건 하에서 이 mechanism이 agent가 순수한 개선 노력만으로 임의로 높은 level에 도달할 수 있게 함을 증명한다.</p>"},{"id":"61658","en":"Knowing Who, Not How Much: Learning-Augmented Mechanisms for Consumer Utility Maximization","ko":"얼마나가 아니라 누구인지 알기: 소비자 효용 극대화를 위한 Learning-Augmented Mechanism","authors":"Kira Goldner, Divyarthi Mohan, Thodoris Tsilivis","pos":"#4509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=o1sy1C0dcB","abs":"<p>We study consumer utility maximization in an online random-order model where strategic agents arrive sequentially. To circumvent strong impossibility results for utility maximization, we turn to the framework of learning-augmented mechanism design. Crucially, we show that the types of  predictions commonly used in learning-augmented mechanism design (such as predictions of agent values or the optimal value) are not useful for utility maximization, where payments are directly at odds with the objective. Instead, we identify that a qualitatively different kind of prediction suffices: the identity of the highest-valued agent. First, we provide a deterministic truthful mechanism for our online setting by adapting offline randomized techniques. Then, we augment our mechanism with predictions. When the predictions are correct, we achieve  a constant approximation to the optimal solution under full information (consistency), and even when predictions are arbitrarily bad, we guarantee a constant approximation to the best implementable solution  (robustness).</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 전략적 agent가 순차적으로 도착하는 online random-order model에서 소비자 utility maximization을 연구합니다. utility maximization에 대한 강한 impossibility result를 우회하기 위해, 우리는 learning-augmented mechanism design framework으로 전환합니다. 핵심적으로, 우리는 learning-augmented mechanism design에서 흔히 사용되는 예측 유형(예: agent value 또는 optimal value 예측)이 utility maximization에는 유용하지 않음을 보입니다. 여기서는 payment가 목표와 직접적으로 충돌하기 때문입니다. 대신, 우리는 질적으로 다른 종류의 예측이 충분함을 확인합니다. 바로 최고 가치를 가진 agent의 identity입니다. 먼저, 우리는 offline randomized technique을 변형하여 우리의 online setting에 대한 deterministic truthful mechanism을 제시합니다. 그런 다음 예측을 통해 우리의 mechanism을 강화합니다. 예측이 정확할 때는 full information 하의 optimal solution에 대한 상수 근사(consistency)를 달성하고, 예측이 아무리 나빠도 구현 가능한 최선의 solution에 대한 상수 근사(robustness)를 보장합니다.</p>"},{"id":"66673","en":"From Welfare to Utility: Generalized Objectives in Budget-Feasible Procurement","ko":"복지에서 효용으로: 예산 실현 가능 조달에서의 일반화된 목적함수","authors":"Alon Eden, Kira Goldner, Eldar Kerner, Thodoris Tsilivis","pos":"#4510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1Uvqz8NQ5z","abs":"<p>We study mechanism design for the budget-feasible procurement problem, a natural problem that arises when a buyer wants to procure goods or services from multiple strategic sellers who each have a cost to provide that service, the buyer has a value for each service procured, but is constrained by a budget. In contrast to prior work, which has focused on buyer value maximization for this problem, we solve for optimal and approximately-optimal mechanisms for the objectives of buyer utility (value of procured services minus payments), welfare (value minus production costs), and generalizations of the two. For welfare, we design a simple mechanism that obtains a constant-factor approximation for the prior-free (worst-case) setting. As prior-free mechanisms fail to provide any guarantee for utility, even for a single seller, we consider Bayesian settings, where the buyer has  distributional knowledge over sellers' costs. We first provide a utility-optimal mechanism that satisfies the buyer's budget constraint <em>in expectation</em>, then we show how to modify the mechanism to satisfy the budget constraint <em>ex-post</em>, for every realization of seller costs, while still obtaining near-optimal utility guarantees. Finally, we generalize our mechanisms to other objectives.</p>"},{"id":"63944","en":"Fair Transit Stop Placement: A Clustering Perspective and Beyond","ko":"공정한 대중교통 정류장 배치: clustering 관점과 그 너머","authors":"Haris Aziz, Ling Gai, Yuhang Guo, Jeremy Vollen","pos":"#4511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SKH7vcWZSv","abs":"We study the transit stop placement (TrSP) problem in general metric spaces, where agents travel between source–destination pairs and may either walk directly or utilize a shuttle service via selected transit stops. We investigate fairness in TrSP through the lens of justified representation (JR) and the core, and uncover a structural correspondence with fair clustering. Specifically, we show that a constant-factor approximation to proportional fairness in clustering can be used to guarantee a constant-factor bi-parameterized approximation to core. We establish a lower bound of $1.366$ on the approximability of JR, and moreover show that no clustering algorithm can approximate JR within a factor better than $3$. Going beyond clustering, we propose the Expanding Cost Algorithm, which achieves a tight $2.414$-approximation for JR, but does not give any bounded core guarantee. In light of this, we introduce a parameterized algorithm that interpolates between these approaches, and enables a tunable trade-off between JR and core. Finally, we complement our results with an experimental analysis using small-market public carpooling data.","absKo":"우리는 일반적인 metric space에서의 transit stop placement (TrSP) 문제를 연구한다. 이 문제에서 agent는 source-destination pair 사이를 이동하며, 직접 걷거나 선택된 transit stop을 거치는 shuttle service를 이용할 수 있다. 우리는 justified representation (JR)과 core의 관점에서 TrSP의 fairness를 조사하고, fair clustering과의 구조적 대응 관계를 발견한다. 구체적으로, clustering에서 proportional fairness에 대한 constant-factor approximation을 사용하면 core에 대한 constant-factor bi-parameterized approximation을 보장할 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 JR의 approximability에 대해 1.366의 lower bound를 확립하며, 더 나아가 어떤 clustering algorithm도 JR을 3보다 더 좋은 factor로는 근사할 수 없음을 보인다. clustering을 넘어, 우리는 Expanding Cost Algorithm을 제안하는데, 이는 JR에 대해 tight한 2.414-approximation을 달성하지만, bounded core guarantee는 제공하지 않는다. 이 점을 고려하여, 우리는 이들 접근을 보간하는 parameterized algorithm을 도입하고, JR과 core 사이의 조절 가능한 trade-off를 가능하게 한다. 마지막으로, small-market public carpooling data를 사용한 실험 분석으로 우리의 결과를 보완한다."},{"id":"63853","en":"Enhancing Affine Maximizer Auctions with Correlation-Aware Payment","ko":"상관관계 인지 payment를 통한 affine maximizer auction 향상","authors":"Haoran Sun, Xia Xuanzhi, Xu Chu, Xiaotie Deng","pos":"#4512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TA3NDHgNJh","abs":"<p>Affine Maximizer Auctions (AMAs), a generalized mechanism family from VCG, are widely used in automated mechanism design due to their inherent dominant-strategy incentive compatibility (DSIC) and individual rationality (IR). However, as the payment form is fixed, AMA's expressiveness is restricted, especially in distributions where bidders' valuations are correlated. In this paper, we propose Correlation-Aware AMA (CA-AMA), a novel framework that augments AMA with a new correlation-aware payment. We show that any CA-AMA preserves the DSIC property and formalize finding optimal CA-AMA as a constraint optimization problem subject to the IR constraint. Then, we theoretically characterize scenarios where classic AMAs can perform arbitrarily poorly compared to the optimal revenue, while the CA-AMA can reach the optimal revenue. For optimizing CA-AMA, we design a practical two-stage training algorithm. We derive that the target function's continuity and the generalization bound on the degree of deviation from strict IR. Finally, extensive experiments showcase that our algorithm can find an approximate optimal CA-AMA in various distributions with improved revenue and a low degree of violation of IR.</p>","absKo":"<p>VCG에서 일반화된 mechanism family인 Affine Maximizer Auctions (AMA)는 고유한 dominant-strategy incentive compatibility (DSIC)와 individual rationality (IR) 때문에 automated mechanism design에서 널리 사용된다. 그러나 payment form이 고정되어 있기 때문에, 특히 bidder의 valuation이 correlated된 분포에서는 AMA의 표현력이 제한된다. 이 논문에서는 새로운 correlation-aware payment를 추가하여 AMA를 확장한 Correlation-Aware AMA (CA-AMA)라는 새로운 framework를 제안한다. 우리는 어떤 CA-AMA도 DSIC 성질을 보존함을 보이고, IR constraint를 만족하는 최적 CA-AMA를 찾는 문제를 constraint optimization problem으로 정식화한다. سپس, 우리는 classic AMA가 optimal revenue에 비해 임의로 나쁜 성능을 보일 수 있는 시나리오와, CA-AMA는 optimal revenue에 도달할 수 있는 시나리오를 이론적으로 규명한다. CA-AMA 최적화를 위해 실용적인 two-stage training algorithm을 설계한다. 우리는 target function의 continuity와 strict IR로부터의 deviation degree에 대한 generalization bound를 도출한다. 마지막으로, 광범위한 실험을 통해 우리의 algorithm이 다양한 분포에서 향상된 revenue와 낮은 IR violation 정도를 갖는 approximate optimal CA-AMA를 찾을 수 있음을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63006","en":"Delegation and Verification under AI","ko":"AI 하에서의 Delegation and Verification","authors":"Lingxiao Huang, Nisheeth K. Vishnoi, Wenyang Xiao","pos":"#4513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=b0Tr5J6ilw","abs":"<p>As AI systems enter institutional workflows, workers must decide whether to delegate task execution to AI and how much effort to invest in verifying AI outputs, while institutions evaluate workers using outcome-based standards that may misalign with workers’ private costs. We model delegation and verification as the solution to a rational worker’s optimization problem, and define worker quality by evaluating an institution-centered utility (distinct from the worker’s objective) at the resulting optimal action. We formally characterize optimal worker workflows and show that AI induces <em>phase transitions</em>, where arbitrarily small differences in verification ability lead to sharply different behaviors. As a result, AI can amplify workers with strong verification reliability while degrading institutional worker quality for others who rationally over-delegate and reduce oversight, even when baseline task success improves and no behavioral biases are present. These results identify a structural mechanism by which AI reshapes institutional worker quality and amplifies quality disparities between workers with different verification reliability.</p>","absKo":"<p>AI system이 institutional workflow에 들어오면서, worker는 task execution을 AI에 위임할지 여부와 AI output을 검증하는 데 얼마나 많은 effort를 투자할지를 결정해야 하며, 동시에 institution은 worker의 private cost와 정렬되지 않을 수 있는 outcome-based standard로 worker를 평가한다. 우리는 delegation과 verification을 rational worker의 optimization problem의 해로 모델링하고, 그 결과로 얻어지는 optimal action에서 institution-centered utility( worker의 objective와는 구별됨 )를 평가하여 worker quality를 정의한다. 우리는 optimal worker workflow를 형식적으로 특성화하고, AI가 <em>phase transition</em>을 유발하여 verification ability의 아주 작은 차이도 현저히 다른 behavior로 이어질 수 있음을 보인다. 그 결과, AI는 verification reliability가 강한 worker를 증폭시키는 동시에, baseline task success가 향상되고 behavioral bias가 존재하지 않더라도, 합리적으로 과도하게 delegation하고 oversight를 줄이는 다른 worker들의 institutional worker quality를 저하시킬 수 있다. 이러한 결과는 AI가 institutional worker quality를 재구성하고, verification reliability가 서로 다른 worker 간의 quality disparity를 증폭시키는 구조적 메커니즘을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62273","en":"Deep Reinforcement Learning Finds Bayes-Nash Equilibrium in Competitive Newsvendor Problems","ko":"Deep Reinforcement Learning이 경쟁적 Newsvendor 문제에서 Bayes-Nash Equilibrium을 찾다","authors":"Kassian Köck, Fabian Raoul Pieroth, Martin Bichler","pos":"#4514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=i5xbcviYhP","abs":"<p>We investigate learning dynamics in competitive newsvendor games, a class of continuous-action games with strategic substitutes. Despite established equilibrium properties, convergence of independent learning algorithms in repeated general-sum play remains uncertain. We analyze structural properties under complete and incomplete information, deriving closed-form equilibria for a symmetric complete-information benchmark with perfect substitution. Our main theoretical contribution proves strict monotonicity in both complete-information and Bayesian models with private costs, ensuring equilibrium uniqueness and ruling out unstable dynamics. This provides convergence guarantees for variational-inequality-based algorithms. Numerical experiments using deep reinforcement learning agents with Proximal Policy Optimization empirically demonstrate convergence to Nash and Bayesian Nash equilibria, verified by equilibrium checks. These results establish a foundation for applying deep reinforcement learning in competitive inventory management.</p>","absKo":"우리는 strategic substitutes를 갖는 continuous-action game의 한 종류인 competitive newsvendor game에서의 learning dynamics를 연구한다. 확립된 equilibrium property에도 불구하고, 반복적인 general-sum play에서 independent learning algorithm의 수렴은 여전히 불확실하다. 우리는 complete information과 incomplete information 하에서의 구조적 성질을 분석하고, perfect substitution을 갖는 symmetric complete-information benchmark에 대해 closed-form equilibrium을 도출한다. 우리의 주요 이론적 기여는 complete-information model과 private cost를 갖는 Bayesian model 모두에서 strict monotonicity를 증명한다는 점이며, 이는 equilibrium uniqueness를 보장하고 불안정한 dynamics를 배제한다. 이는 variational-inequality-based algorithm에 대한 convergence guarantee를 제공한다. Proximal Policy Optimization을 사용하는 deep reinforcement learning agent를 활용한 수치 실험은 equilibrium check로 검증된 Nash equilibrium 및 Bayesian Nash equilibrium으로의 수렴을 경험적으로 보여준다. 이 결과는 competitive inventory management에 deep reinforcement learning을 적용하기 위한 기반을 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"67226","en":"Position: Machine Learning for Heart Transplant Allocation Policy Optimization Should Account for Incentives","ko":"Position: 심장 이식 배분 정책 최적화를 위한 기계 학습은 인센티브를 고려해야 한다","authors":"Ioannis Anagnostides, Itai Zilberstein, Zachary Sollie, Arman Kilic, Tuomas Sandholm","pos":"#703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6aCgPEoADB","abs":"<p>The allocation of scarce donor organs constitutes one of the most consequential algorithmic challenges in healthcare. While the field is rapidly transitioning from rigid, rule-based systems to machine learning and data-driven optimization, we argue that current approaches often overlook a fundamental barrier: incentives. In this position paper, we highlight that organ allocation is not merely an  optimization problem, but rather a complex game involving organ procurement organizations, transplant centers, clinicians, patients, and regulators. Focusing on US adult heart transplant allocation, we identify critical incentive misalignments across the decision-making pipeline, and present data showing that they are having adverse consequences today. Our main position is that the next generation of allocation policies should be incentive aware. We outline a research agenda for the machine learning community, calling for the integration of mechanism design, strategic classification, causal inference, and social choice to ensure robustness, efficiency, fairness, and trust in the face of strategic behavior from the various constituent groups.</p>"}];window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("papers-loaded",{detail:"68692"}));